B040C001V001	40	1	1	THE RECORD of the generation of Jeshu the Meshicha, the son of David, son of Abraham.
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham begat Ishok, Ishok begat Jakub, Jakub begat Jehuda and his brethren,
B040C001V003	40	1	3	Jehuda begat Pharets and Zoroch from Thomar. Pharets begat Hetsron, Hetsron begat Arom,
B040C001V004	40	1	4	Arom begat Aminodob, Aminodob begat Nachshun, Nachshun begat Salmun,
B040C001V005	40	1	5	Salmun begat Booz from Rochab, Booz begat Ubid from Ruth, Ubid begat Ishai,
B040C001V006	40	1	6	Ishai begat David the king; David begat Shelemun from the wife of Uria;
B040C001V007	40	1	7	Shelemun begat Rehebaam, Rehebaam begat Abia, Abia begat Asa,
B040C001V008	40	1	8	Asa begat Johushaphat, Johushaphat begat Jurom, Jurom begat Uzia,
B040C001V009	40	1	9	Uzia begat Juthom, Juthom begat Ahaz, Ahaz begat Hezakia,
B040C001V010	40	1	10	Hezakia begat Menasha, Menasha begat Amun, Amun begat Jushia,
B040C001V011	40	1	11	Jushia begat Jukania and his brethren at the exile of Bobel.
B040C001V012	40	1	12	And after the exile of Bobel Jukania begat Shalathiel, Shalathiel begat Zurbobel,
B040C001V013	40	1	13	Zurbobel begat Abiud, Abiud begat Aliakim, Aliakim begat Ozur,
B040C001V014	40	1	14	Ozur begat Zoduk, Zoduk begat Akin, Akin begat Aliud,
B040C001V015	40	1	15	Aliud begat Aliozar, Aliozar begat Mathan, Mathan begat Jakub,
B040C001V016	40	1	16	Jakub begat Jauseph, husband of Mariam, of whom was born JESHU who is called the Meshicha.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	Thus all the generations from Abraham to David (were) fourteen generations; and from David to the exile of Bobel, fourteen generations; and from the exile of Bobel to the Meshicha, fourteen generations.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	NOW the nativity of Jeshu the Meshicha was thus: While Mariam his mother was betrothed to Jauseph, before they could be consociated, she was found to be with child from the Spirit of Holiness.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	But Jauseph her husband was just, and, not willing to defame her, meditated privately to release her.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	But while (on) these (things) he reflected, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream, and said to him, Jauseph, son of David, fear not to take Mariam thy wife; for that which is conceived in her is from the Spirit of Holiness.
B040C001V021	40	1	21	She shall give birth to a son, and thou shalt call his name JESHU; for he shall save his people from their sins.
B040C001V022	40	1	22	Now all this was done, that what was spoken from the Lord by the prophet might be fulfilled:
B040C001V023	40	1	23	Behold, a virgin shall be with child, and shall bring forth the son, and they shall call his name Amanuel; which is interpreted, With us (is) our Aloha.
B040C001V024	40	1	24	Then Jauseph, when he had arisen from his sleep, did as the angel of the Lord commanded him, and took unto him his wife;
B040C001V025	40	1	25	and knew her not until she had given birth to her son, the firstborn; and she called his name Jeshu.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	NOW when Jeshu was born in Beth-lechem of Jehuda, in the days of Herodes the king, there came Magians from the East to Urishlem:
B040C002V002	40	2	2	and they said, Where is the king of the Jews who is born? for we have seen his star in the east, and have come to worship him.
B040C002V003	40	2	3	But Herodes the king heard, and was troubled, and all Urishlem with him.
B040C002V004	40	2	4	And he assembled all the chief priests and scribes of the people, and anxiously inquired of them where the Meshicha should be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	But they said, In Beth-lechem of Jehuda; for so it is written in the prophet:
B040C002V006	40	2	6	Also thou, Beth-lechem of Jehuda, wast not the least among the kings of Jehuda; for from thee shall come forth the king who shall be as a shepherd to my people Isroel.
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herodes privately called the Magians, and learned from them at what time the star appeared to them:
B040C002V008	40	2	8	and he sent them to Beth-lechem, and said to them, Go and inquire diligently concerning the child; and when you have found him, come, show me, and I also will go and will worship him.
B040C002V009	40	2	9	But they, when they had heard the king, went forth; and, lo, the star, which they had seen in the east, proceeded before them, until it came and stood over against where the child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	Now when they saw the star, they rejoiced with very great joy.
B040C002V011	40	2	11	And they entered the house, and beheld the child with Mariam his mother; and they fell down, and worshipped him. And they opened their treasures, and offered unto him oblations; gold, and myrrh, and frankincense.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	And it was shown to them in a dream, that they should not return unto Herodes; so, by another way, they went unto their place.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	AND when they were gone, the angel of the Lord appeared in a dream unto Jauseph, and said to him, Arise, take the child and his mother, and flee into Metsreen, and there be until I tell thee; for it will be that Herodes will seek the child, that he may destroy him.
B040C002V014	40	2	14	Then Jauseph arose, took up the child and his mother, and fled by night into Metsreen,
B040C002V015	40	2	15	and was there until the death of Herodes. That it might be fulfilled which was spoken from the Lord by the prophet, saying, Out of Metsreen have I called my son.
B040C002V016	40	2	16	Then Herodes, when he saw that he had been deluded by the Magians, was greatly wroth, and sent (and) killed all the children of Beth-lechem, and all its limits, from two years and under, according to the time which he had inquired from the Magians.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then was fulfilled what was spoken by Eramio the prophet, who said,
B040C002V018	40	2	18	A cry was heard in Rometha; weeping and great lamentation; Rochel weeping for her children, and not willing to be comforted, because they are not.
B040C002V019	40	2	19	BUT when Herodes, the king, was dead, the angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Jauseph in Metsreen,
B040C002V020	40	2	20	and said to him, Arise, take the child and his mother, and go into the land of Isroel; for they are dead who sought the life of the child.
B040C002V021	40	2	21	And Jauseph arose, (and) took the child and his mother, and came into the land of Isroel.
B040C002V022	40	2	22	But when he heard that Arkelaos was the king in Jehud, instead of Herodes his father, he was afraid to go thither: and it was shown to him in a dream, that he should go into the region of Galila.
B040C002V023	40	2	23	And he came and dwelt in a city which is called Natsrath. So would be fulfilled that which was spoken by the prophet, that a Nazarene he should be called.
B040C003V001	40	3	1	NOW in those days came Juchanon the Baptizer preaching in the desert of Jehud,
B040C003V002	40	3	2	and saying, Repent! the kingdom of heaven hath drawn nigh.
B040C003V003	40	3	3	For this is he of whom it was spoken by Eshaia the prophet: The voice which crieth in the desert, Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths plain.
B040C003V004	40	3	4	But this Juchanon, his clothing was of the hair of camels, with a loins-belt of leather upon his loins; and his food was locusts and wilderness-honey.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	Then went forth to him Urishlem, and all Jehud, and the whole country about Jurdan;
B040C003V006	40	3	6	and were baptized of him in Jurdan, the river, while they were confessing their sins.
B040C003V007	40	3	7	But when he saw many of the Pharishee and Zodukoyee coming to be baptized, he said to them, Generation of vipers, who hath showed you to escape from the wrath that cometh?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Work, therefore, fruits which are suitable to repentance.
B040C003V009	40	3	9	Neither ruminate and say within yourselves, that Abraham is father to us; for I say to you that Aloha is able from these stones to raise up sons unto Abraham.
B040C003V010	40	3	10	But, behold, the axe lieth at the root of the trees; every tree, therefore, which maketh not good fruit is cut down and falleth into the fire.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	I, indeed, baptize you with water unto repentance; but He who cometh after me is mightier than I; he, whose sandals I am not worthy to bear,-he baptizeth you with the Spirit of Holiness and with fire.
B040C003V012	40	3	12	He (it is) whose fan is in his hand, and, purifying his floors, the wheat he gathereth into his garner, but the chaff he burneth with the fire that is not quenched.
B040C003V013	40	3	13	Then came Jeshu from Galila unto Jurdan to Juchanan to be baptized of him.
B040C003V014	40	3	14	But Juchanon prohibited him, and said, I need from thee to be baptized, and hast thou come unto me?
B040C003V015	40	3	15	But Jeshu answered and said unto him, Permit now; for thus it becometh us to accomplish all righteousness. And then he permitted him.
B040C003V016	40	3	16	But when Jeshu was baptized, he immediately ascended from the waters; and the heaven was opened unto him; and he saw the Spirit of Aloha, who descended, like the dove, and came upon him.
B040C003V017	40	3	17	And, lo, the voice from heaven, which said, This (is) my Son, the Beloved, in whom I have delighted.
B040C004V001	40	4	1	THEN Jeshu was led by the Spirit of Holiness into the desert, that he should be tempted by the Accuser.
B040C004V002	40	4	2	And he fasted forty days and forty nights; but afterward he hungered.
B040C004V003	40	4	3	And he who tempteth approached and said, If the Son thou art of Aloha, say that these stones shall become bread.
B040C004V004	40	4	4	But he answered and said, It is written that not by bread alone liveth the Son of man, but by every word which proceedeth from the mouth of Aloha.
B040C004V005	40	4	5	Then the Accuser taketh him to the holy city, and caused him to stand on the pinnacle of the temple;
B040C004V006	40	4	6	and said to him, If the Son thou art of Aloha, throw thyself down; for it is written that his angels he shall command concerning thee, and upon their hands they shall bear thee, that thou strike not against a stone thy foot.
B040C004V007	40	4	7	Jeshu said to him, Again it is written, Thou shalt not tempt the Lord thy Aloha.
B040C004V008	40	4	8	Again the Accuser took him to a mountain which is exceeding high, and showed him all the kingdoms of the world and their glory;
B040C004V009	40	4	9	and said to him, These all to thee will I give, if thou wilt fall and worship me,
B040C004V010	40	4	10	Then said Jeshu to him, Away with thee, Satana! for it is written that the Lord thy Aloha thou shalt worship, and him only thou shalt serve.
B040C004V011	40	4	11	Then the Accuser left him, and, behold, the angels drew nigh and ministered unto him.
B040C004V012	40	4	12	BUT when Jeshu heard that Juchanan was perfected, he removed into Galila.
B040C004V013	40	4	13	And he left Natsrath, and came and dwelt in Kaphar-Nachum by the sea-side on the borders of Zabolon and of Naptholi.
B040C004V014	40	4	14	That the thing might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet Eshaia, who said,
B040C004V015	40	4	15	The land of Zabolon, the land of Naptholi, the way of the sea beyond Jurdan, Galila of the peoples.
B040C004V016	40	4	16	The people who sat in darkness the great light hath seen; and they who have sat in the region and shadow of death, the light has arisen upon them.
B040C004V017	40	4	17	From that time began Jeshu to preach, and to say, Repent! for the kingdom of heaven hath drawn nigh.
B040C004V018	40	4	18	And while he walked by the sea of Galila, he saw two brethren, Shemun who was called Kipha, and Andreas his brother, who were casting their nets into the sea, for they were fishers.
B040C004V019	40	4	19	And Jeshu said to them, Come after me, and I will make you to become fishers of men.
B040C004V020	40	4	20	And they immediately forsook their nets and went after him.
B040C004V021	40	4	21	And when he had passed thence, he saw two other brethren, Jakub-bar-Zabdai and Juchanan his brother, in a vessel with Zabdai their father, repairing their nets: and Jeshu called them;
B040C004V022	40	4	22	and they forthwith left the vessel and their father, and went after him.
B040C004V023	40	4	23	And Jeshu perambulated all Galila, and taught in their synagogues, and preached the announcement of the kingdom, and healed all disease and affliction in the people.
B040C004V024	40	4	24	And his fame was heard in all Suria; and they brought to him all those who were grievously affected with various diseases, and those who were pressed down by strong pains, and demoniacs, and lunatics, and the paralysed; and he healed them.
B040C004V025	40	4	25	And there went after him great gatherings from Galila, and from the ten cities, and from Urishlem, and from Jehud, and from beyond Jurdan.
B040C005V001	40	5	1	BUT when Jeshu saw the multitudes, he ascended a mountain; and when he had sat down, his disciples drew near to him;
B040C005V002	40	5	2	and he opened his mouth and taught them, saying:
B040C005V003	40	5	3	BLESSED (are) the poor in spirit, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V004	40	5	4	Blessed the mourners, for they shall be comforted.
B040C005V005	40	5	5	Blessed the meek, for they shall inherit the earth.
B040C005V006	40	5	6	Blessed they who hunger and thirst unto righteousness, for they shall be satisfied.
B040C005V007	40	5	7	Blessed the merciful, for upon them shall be mercy.
B040C005V008	40	5	8	Blessed they who are pure in their hearts, for they shall see Aloha.
B040C005V009	40	5	9	Blessed the makers of peace, for the children of Aloha shall they be called.
B040C005V010	40	5	10	Blessed they who are persecuted because of righteousness, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V011	40	5	11	Blessed are you when they treat you with reviling, and persecute you, and say concerning you every evil word, for my sake, in falsity.
B040C005V012	40	5	12	Then be glad and exult, for your reward is great in heaven; for so persecuted they the prophets who were before you.
B040C005V013	40	5	13	You are the salt of the earth: but if it happen that salt become tasteless, with what shall it be seasoned? It goeth for nothing but to be thrown without and trodden down by men.
B040C005V014	40	5	14	You are the light of the world: It is not possible that a city which is built upon a hill can be hidden.
B040C005V015	40	5	15	Nor do they kindle a lamp and place it beneath a measure, but on a candlestick, and it enlighteneth all who are in the house.
B040C005V016	40	5	16	So let your light shine before the sons of men, that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father who is in heaven.
B040C005V017	40	5	17	Think not that I came to loose the law or the prophets: not that I might loose, but that I might fulfill.
B040C005V018	40	5	18	For, Amen I say unto you, that until heaven and earth shall pass away, one yod, or one point, shall not pass from the law, till all be done.
B040C005V019	40	5	19	Every one, therefore, who shall set loose one from these least commandments, and shall so teach the children of men, the least shall he be called in the kingdom of heaven: but every one who shall do and teach, this shall be called great in the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V020	40	5	20	For I say to you, that unless your righteousness shall abound more than that of the scribes and the Pharishee, you shall not enter into the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V021	40	5	21	YOU have heard that it was said unto them who were before, Thou shalt not kill; and whosoever shall kill is obnoxious to the judgment.
B040C005V022	40	5	22	But I say unto you, that he who is angry against his brother rashly, is obnoxious to the judgment; and he who shall say to his brother, Thou empty one! is liable to the council; and every one who shall say, Thou fool! is liable to the gihano of fire.
B040C005V023	40	5	23	If it occur, therefore, that thou bring thy oblation to the altar, and there rememberest that thy brother retaineth some enmity against thee;
B040C005V024	40	5	24	leave there thy oblation at the altar, and go, first be reconciled with thy brother, and then come and offer thy oblation.
B040C005V025	40	5	25	Be at one with thine adversary quickly, while thou art with him in the way; lest thy adversary deliver thee to the judge, and the judge deliver thee to the exactor, and thou fall into the house of the bound.
B040C005V026	40	5	26	And, Amen I say unto thee, that thou shalt not come forth from thence till thou hast rendered the last shamuna.
B040C005V027	40	5	27	You have heard that it hath been said, Thou shalt not commit adultery.
B040C005V028	40	5	28	But I say to you, that every one who beholdeth a woman so as that he shall desire her, already committeth adultery in his heart.
B040C005V029	40	5	29	But if thy right eye cause thee to offend, root it out and cast it from thee: it is better to thee that one of thy members should perish, than that thy whole body should fall into gihano.
B040C005V030	40	5	30	And if thy right hand cause thee to offend, cut it off and cast it from thee; for it is better to thee that one from thy members should perish, rather than thy whole body should fall into gihano.
B040C005V031	40	5	31	It hath been said, that he who looseth his wife should give her a writing of divorcement.
B040C005V032	40	5	32	But I say unto you, that whosoever looseth his wife, except on account of fornication, maketh her to commit adultery; and whosoever taketh her who is sent away, committeth adultery.
B040C005V033	40	5	33	Again, you have heard it was said to those beforetime, Thou shalt not lie in thine oaths, but shalt fulfil thine oaths unto the Lord.
B040C005V034	40	5	34	But I say unto you, Swear not at all: not by heaven, for it is the throne of Aloha;
B040C005V035	40	5	35	nor by earth, for it is the foot-stool beneath his feet; neither by Urishlem, for it is the city of the great king.
B040C005V036	40	5	36	Neither shalt thou swear by thy head, for thou canst not make a single hair in it either black or white.
B040C005V037	40	5	37	But let your discourse be, Yea, yea; Nay, nay; for whatsoever is more than these is from the evil.
B040C005V038	40	5	38	You have heard that it hath been said, An eye for an eye, and a tooth for a tooth.
B040C005V039	40	5	39	But I say unto you, that you shall not rise up against evil: but if any one strike thee on the right cheek, turn to him the other also.
B040C005V040	40	5	40	And if any one will contend with thee to take away thy tunic, leave him thy mantle also;
B040C005V041	40	5	41	and if a man compel thee one mile, go with him twain.
B040C005V042	40	5	42	Give to him who asketh from thee, and him who would borrow from thee refuse not.
B040C005V043	40	5	43	You have heard that it hath been said, Thou shalt love thy neighbour, and hate thine enemy.
B040C005V044	40	5	44	But I say unto you, Love your enemies; bless them who execrate you; do that which is good to him who hateth you; and pray for them who lead you with a chain, and persecute you.
B040C005V045	40	5	45	That you may be the children of your Father who is in heaven, who causeth his sun to arise on the good and on the evil, and who sendeth showers on the just and on the unjust.
B040C005V046	40	5	46	For if you love those (only) who love you, what reward have you? do not even the tribute-gatherers this?
B040C005V047	40	5	47	And if you wish peace to your brethren only, what more do you than they? do not also the tribute-gatherers this?
B040C005V048	40	5	48	Be ye therefore perfect, as your Father who is in heaven is perfect!
B040C006V001	40	6	1	SEE that in your almsgiving you do it not before men, so as that you may be observed by them; otherwise no reward is for you with your Father who is in heaven.
B040C006V002	40	6	2	When, therefore, thou art doing alms, sound not a trumpet before thee, as do the assumers of faces in the assemblies and streets, so that they may be praised from men; and, Amen I say to you, they receive their reward.
B040C006V003	40	6	3	But thou, when thou art doing thy alms, let not thy left hand know what thy right hand doeth,
B040C006V004	40	6	4	that thine alms may be in secret; and thy Father, who seeth in secret, shall recompense thee in openness.
B040C006V005	40	6	5	And when thou prayest, be not as the face-takers, who love to stand in the assemblies and at the corners of the streets to pray, that they may be seen of men; and truly I say to you that they receive their reward.
B040C006V006	40	6	6	But thou, when thou prayest, enter into thy secret chamber, and shut thy door, and pray to thy Father who is in secret; and thy Father, who seeth in secret, shall reward thee in openness.
B040C006V007	40	6	7	And when thou art praying, be not wordy, like the profane; for they think that in much speaking they are heard.
B040C006V008	40	6	8	Be you not like them, for your Father knoweth what is needful for you before that you ask him.
B040C006V009	40	6	9	Thus pray: Our Father who art in the heavens! be sanctified thy Name.
B040C006V010	40	6	10	Come thy kingdom. Be done thy will, as in heaven, also in earth.
B040C006V011	40	6	11	Give to us the bread of our need to-day;
B040C006V012	40	6	12	and forgive us our debts, as also we forgive our debtors;
B040C006V013	40	6	13	and lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil. For thine is the kingdom and the power and the glory to the age of ages.
B040C006V014	40	6	14	For if you forgive men their trespasses, your Father who is in heaven will forgive you also.
B040C006V015	40	6	15	But if you will not forgive men, your Father also forgiveth not your trespasses unto you.
B040C006V016	40	6	16	WHEN, too, you fast, be not morosely sad as the assumers of faces, for they defile their countenances so as that they may appear unto men to fast: and, Amen I say unto you, they receive their reward.
B040C006V017	40	6	17	But thou, when thou art fasting, wash thy face and anoint thine head,
B040C006V018	40	6	18	that it may not appear to men that thou art fasting, but to thy Father who is in secret; and thy Father who seeth in secret, he shall reward thee.
B040C006V019	40	6	19	Lay not up for yourselves treasures in the earth, a place where moth and rust corrupt, and where thieves dig through and steal:
B040C006V020	40	6	20	but lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where no moth and no rust corrupt, and where thieves do not dig through and steal.
B040C006V021	40	6	21	For where your treasure is, there also your hearts are.
B040C006V022	40	6	22	The lamp of the body is the eye: if thine eye therefore be perfect, thy whole body will be illuminated;
B040C006V023	40	6	23	but if thine eye be evil, thy whole body will be dark. If therefore the light that is in thee be darkness, what will thy darkness be?
B040C006V024	40	6	24	No man can serve two lords; for the one he will hate, and the other he will love, or the one he will honour, and the other he will neglect: you cannot serve Aloha and riches.
B040C006V025	40	6	25	WHEREFORE I say unto you, Let not your souls be anxious what you shall eat and what you shall drink, and for your bodies what you shall wear. Is not the life more excellent than food, and the body than raiment?
B040C006V026	40	6	26	Behold the fowls of the heaven; they sow not, neither do they reap, nor collect into granaries; yet your Father who is in heaven nourisheth them: are you not far more considerable than they?
B040C006V027	40	6	27	But who among you by being anxious can add to his stature one cubit?
B040C006V028	40	6	28	and concerning raiment why are you anxious? Look upon the lilies of the wilderness how they increase; they toil not, neither do they spin.
B040C006V029	40	6	29	Yet I say to you, Not even Shelemun in all his glory was covered like one from among these.
B040C006V030	40	6	30	But if the herb of the field, which to-day exists, and tomorrow falleth into the oven, Aloha thus clotheth, how much more you, little of faith?
B040C006V031	40	6	31	Be not anxious, therefore, nor say, What shall we eat, or, What shall we drink, or, How shall we be covered?
B040C006V032	40	6	32	For after all these things do the people of the world inquire: but your Father who is in heaven knoweth that also by you are required these all.
B040C006V033	40	6	33	But seek first the kingdom of Aloha and his righteousness, and all these shall be added unto you.
B040C006V034	40	6	34	Be not therefore anxious for to-morrow; the morrow shall care for its own: the evil of to-day is enough for it.
B040C007V001	40	7	1	JUDGE not, that you be not judged.
B040C007V002	40	7	2	For with the judgment that you judge, you shall be judged; and with the measure that you mete, it shall be measured to you.
B040C007V003	40	7	3	But why dost thou look at the rod that is in thy brother's eye, while the rafter that is in thine own eye thou dost not consider?
B040C007V004	40	7	4	Or how sayest thou to thy brother, Permit that I draw forth the rod from thine eye, and, behold, there is a rafter in thine own eye?
B040C007V005	40	7	5	Hypocrite! draw forth first the rafter from thine own eye, and then thou wilt see to draw forth the rod from thy brother's eye.
B040C007V006	40	7	6	Give not the holy unto dogs, and throw not your precious stones before swine, lest they trample them under their feet, and turn again and rend you.
B040C007V007	40	7	7	Ask, and it shall be given to you; seek, and you shall find; knock, and it shall be opened unto you.
B040C007V008	40	7	8	For every one who asketh receiveth, and he who seeketh findeth; and to him who knocketh it is opened.
B040C007V009	40	7	9	Or what man from among you, who if his son shall ask bread, will reach forth a stone to him?
B040C007V010	40	7	10	if a fish he shall ask of him, a serpent will he reach forth to him?
B040C007V011	40	7	11	If, therefore, you who are evil know to give good gifts unto your children, how much more shall your Father who is in heaven give good things to those who ask him?
B040C007V012	40	7	12	All therefore that you will that men shall do unto you, so also do you unto them: for this is the law and the prophets.
B040C007V013	40	7	13	ENTER in at the narrow gate: for wide is the gate, and spacious the way, that conducteth to destruction; and they are many who go therein.
B040C007V014	40	7	14	How small is the gate, and narrow the way, that leadeth unto salvation; and they are few who find it!
B040C007V015	40	7	15	Beware of false prophets, who come to you in the clothing of sheep, but within are ravening wolves.
B040C007V016	40	7	16	By their fruits you shall know them. Do they gather from thorns grapes, or from briers figs?
B040C007V017	40	7	17	So every good tree maketh good fruits; but an evil tree maketh evil fruits.
B040C007V018	40	7	18	A good tree cannot make evil fruits, nor an evil tree make good fruits.
B040C007V019	40	7	19	Every tree that maketh not good fruits is cut down, and falleth into the fire.
B040C007V020	40	7	20	Wherefore by their fruits you shall know them.
B040C007V021	40	7	21	Not every one that saith to me, My Lord, my Lord, entereth into the kingdom of heaven; but he who doeth the will of my Father who is in heaven.
B040C007V022	40	7	22	Multitudes will say to me in that day My Lord, my Lord, in thy name have we not prophesied, and in thy name ejected devils, and in thy name performed many mighty works?
B040C007V023	40	7	23	And then will I confess to them, I never knew you; go far from me, ye workers of iniquity.
B040C007V024	40	7	24	Every one therefore who heareth these my words, and doeth them, shall be likened to a wise man, who built his house upon a rock.
B040C007V025	40	7	25	And the rain descended, and the torrents came, and the winds blew, and rushed against that house, but it fell not, for its foundations were placed upon the rock.
B040C007V026	40	7	26	And every one who heareth these my words, and doeth them not, shall be likened to a man who built his house upon sand.
B040C007V027	40	7	27	And the rain descended, and the torrents came, and the winds blew, and rushed against that house, and it fell, and the ruin of it was great.
B040C007V028	40	7	28	And when Jeshu had finished these words, the multitudes wondered at his doctrine.
B040C007V029	40	7	29	For he taught them as one having power, and not as their scribes and the Pharishee.
B040C008V001	40	8	1	WHEN he had descended from the mountain, great multitudes clave to him.
B040C008V002	40	8	2	And, behold, a certain leper came (and) worshipped him, and said, My Lord, if thou art willing, thou canst cleanse me.
B040C008V003	40	8	3	And Jeshu extended his hand, and touched him, and said, I am willing: be clean; and in that very hour his leprosy was cleansed.
B040C008V004	40	8	4	And Jeshu said to him, See that thou tell no man, but go, show thyself to the priests, and offer the oblation that Musha required for their testimony.
B040C008V005	40	8	5	Then when Jeshu had entered into Kapharnachum, a certain centurion approached him, and besought of him,
B040C008V006	40	8	6	saying, My Lord, my child is lying in the house, paralysed and grievously tormented.
B040C008V007	40	8	7	Jeshu saith to him, I will come and heal him.
B040C008V008	40	8	8	The centurion answered and saith, My Lord, I am not worthy that thou shouldst come beneath my roof; only speak in a word, and my child shall be healed.
B040C008V009	40	8	9	For I also am a man under authority, and under my hand there are soldiers. I say to this one, Go, and he goeth; and to the other, Come, and he cometh; and to my servant, Do this, and he doeth.
B040C008V010	40	8	10	When Jeshu heard this, he was moved with admiration, and said to those with him, Truly I say to you, that in Isroel I have not found faith like this.
B040C008V011	40	8	11	But I tell you, That many shall come from the east, and from the west, and shall recline with Abraham, and Is'hok, and Jakub, in the kingdom of the heavens;
B040C008V012	40	8	12	but the children of the kingdom shall go forth into outer darknesses; there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C008V013	40	8	13	And Jeshu said unto the centurion, Go; as thou hast believed, it shall be to thee. And his child was healed in that very hour.
B040C008V014	40	8	14	AND Jeshu came to the house of Shemun, and saw his mother-in-law lying, a fever having seized her.
B040C008V015	40	8	15	And he touched her with his hand, and the fever left her; and she arose and ministered to them.
B040C008V016	40	8	16	And when it was evening, they brought before him many demoniacs, and he cast out their devils by a word; and all those who were heavily afflicted he healed.
B040C008V017	40	8	17	So was fulfilled what had been spoken by the prophet Eshaia, who said, That he should take our griefs, and bear our infirmities.
B040C008V018	40	8	18	Now when Jeshu saw the great multitudes which encompassed him, he commanded that they should go to the opposite shore.
B040C008V019	40	8	19	And a certain scribe approached him, and said, Rabi, I will come after thee to the place whither thou goest.
B040C008V020	40	8	20	Jeshu saith to him, The foxes have their dens, and the fowls of heaven a bower, but the Son of man hath not where to lay his head.
B040C008V021	40	8	21	And another from his disciples said to him, My Lord, permit me first to go and bury my father.
B040C008V022	40	8	22	But Jeshu said to him Come after me, and leave the dead ones burying their dead.
B040C008V023	40	8	23	AND when Jeshu had ascended into the ship, his disciples ascended with him.
B040C008V024	40	8	24	And, behold, a great commotion was made on the sea, insomuch that the vessel was covered by the waves; but Jeshu himself was asleep.
B040C008V025	40	8	25	And the disciples approached him, that they might awake him, saying to him, Our Lord, deliver us, we are perishing!
B040C008V026	40	8	26	And Jeshu said to them, Why are you fearful, you little in faith? Then he arose, and forbade the wind and the sea, and there was a great calm.
B040C008V027	40	8	27	But the men were struck with wonder, saying, What (being) is this, to whom the winds and the sea are obedient?
B040C008V028	40	8	28	And when Jeshu came to the other side, to the region of the Godroyee, there met him two demoniacs, who came forth from the place of sepulchres, exceedingly malignant, insomuch that no man could pass by that way.
B040C008V029	40	8	29	And they shouted, saying, What to us, and to thee, Jeshu, son of Aloha? Hast thou come hither before the time, to torment us?
B040C008V030	40	8	30	Now there was at a distance from them a herd of many swine feeding.
B040C008V031	40	8	31	Those demons, therefore, supplicated from him, saying, If thou cast us out, suffer us to go into the herd of swine.
B040C008V032	40	8	32	Jeshu saith to them, Go: and immediately they went forth, and entered into the swine; and the whole herd rushed directly over the rock, and, plunging into the sea, perished in the waters.
B040C008V033	40	8	33	And they who tended them, fled, and went into the city, and showed every thing that was done, and what concerned these demoniacs.
B040C008V034	40	8	34	the whole city came forth to meet Jeshu himself; and when they beheld him, they besought from him that he would remove from their coasts.
B040C009V001	40	9	1	And he ascended (into) the ship, and went over, and came to his city.
B040C009V002	40	9	2	And they brought to him a paralytic lying on a bed; and Jeshu saw their faith, and said to the paralytic, Be comforted, my son, thy sins are forgiven thee.
B040C009V003	40	9	3	But men from among the scribes said within themselves, This blasphemeth.
B040C009V004	40	9	4	But Jeshu knew their reasonings, and said to them, Why reason ye evil in your hearts?
B040C009V005	40	9	5	For which is easier, to say, Forgiven are thy sins, or to say, Arise, walk?
B040C009V006	40	9	6	But that ye may know that authority hath the Son of man in the earth to remit sins, he saith to him-the paralytic,-Arise, lift up thy bed, and go to thy house:
B040C009V007	40	9	7	and he arose (and) went to his house.
B040C009V008	40	9	8	When the assembly saw this, they feared, and glorified Aloha who had given such power as this unto men.
B040C009V009	40	9	9	AND when Jeshu had passed thence, he saw a man who was sitting at the place of the tribute-takers, whose name was Mathai; and he said to him, Come after me; and he arose and went after him.
B040C009V010	40	9	10	And while he reclined in the house, there came to him many tribute-gatherers and sinners, and reclined with Jeshu and with his disciples.
B040C009V011	40	9	11	And when the Pharishee saw (it), they say to his disciples, Why doth your master eat with tribute-takers and sinners?
B040C009V012	40	9	12	But Jeshu, when he heard (it), said to them, The healthful have no need for the physician, but they who are diseased.
B040C009V013	40	9	13	Go, learn what that is:-" I require mercy, and not sacrifice; " for I am not come to call the righteous, but the sinners.
B040C009V014	40	9	14	Then drew nigh to him the disciples of Juchanon, and said, Why do we and the Pharishee fast much, and thy disciples fast not?
B040C009V015	40	9	15	Jeshu said to them, Neither can the sons of the marriage-chamber fast while the bridegroom is with them: but the days are coming when the bridegroom shall be taken up from them, and then shall they fast.
B040C009V016	40	9	16	No man inserteth a piece of new cloth upon an old garment, lest he should take away its fulness from that garment, and the rent be greater.
B040C009V017	40	9	17	Neither do they pour new wine into old bottles, that the bottles may not be broken, and the wine be spilled, and the bottles perish. But they pour new wine into new bottles, and both are preserved.
B040C009V018	40	9	18	WHILE he spake these words with them, a certain chief came, drew near, worshipped him, and said, My daughter is now dead; but come, lay thy hand upon her, and she shall live!
B040C009V019	40	9	19	And Jeshu arose, with his disciples, and went after him.
B040C009V020	40	9	20	And, behold, a woman whose blood had flowed twelve years, came behind him, and touched the edge of his vestment.
B040C009V021	40	9	21	For she was saying within herself, If I touch but his garment, I shall be healed.
B040C009V022	40	9	22	But Jeshu turned and seeth her, and said to her, Be comforted, my daughter, thy faith hath saved thee. And the woman was healed from that very hour.
B040C009V023	40	9	23	And Jeshu came to the ruler's house, and saw the minstrels and the crowds which were making a tumult.
B040C009V024	40	9	24	And he said to them, Retire; for the damsel is not dead, but asleep. And they laughed at him.
B040C009V025	40	9	25	And when he had put forth the crowds, he entered, and took her by the hand; and the damsel arose.
B040C009V026	40	9	26	And the rumour of this went forth through all that land.
B040C009V027	40	9	27	AND when Jeshu had passed thence, two blind men clave to him, and besought him, and said, Have compassion on us, Son of David!
B040C009V028	40	9	28	And when he had come into the house, these blind men were brought to him. Jeshu saith to them, Believe you that I am able to do this? They say to him, Yes, our Lord!
B040C009V029	40	9	29	Then he touched their eyes, and said, As you believe be it to you.
B040C009V030	40	9	30	And immediately their eyes were opened. And Jeshu forbad them and said, Beware lest any man know.
B040C009V031	40	9	31	But they went forth and spread the report of it through all that land.
B040C009V032	40	9	32	And when Jeshu went forth, they brought to him a dumb person in whom was a demon.
B040C009V033	40	9	33	And when the demon had gone out, the dumb spake; and the multitudes were astonished, and said, Never was it thus seen in Isroel.
B040C009V034	40	9	34	But the Pharishee said, By the chief of the devils he casteth out devils.
B040C009V035	40	9	35	And Jeshu itinerated in all their cities and villages, and taught in their assemblies, and preached the gospel of the kingdom, and healed all diseases and all pains.
B040C009V036	40	9	36	BUT when Jeshu saw the multitudes, he had compassion upon them, because they fainted and were dispersed as sheep that had no shepherd;
B040C009V037	40	9	37	and said to his disciples, The harvest is great, and the labourers few.
B040C009V038	40	9	38	Ask, therefore, from the Lord of the harvest, that he would thrust forth labourers into his harvest.
B040C010V001	40	10	1	And he called his twelve disciples, and gave them power over unclean spirits to cast them out, and to cure every disease and infirmity.
B040C010V002	40	10	2	Now, of the twelve apostles the names are these: the first of them, Shemun who is called Kipha, and Andreas his brother, and Jakubbar-Zabdai, and Juchanon his brother,
B040C010V003	40	10	3	and Philipos, and Bar-Tholmai, and Thoma, and Mathai the tribute-gatherer, and Jakubbar-Chalphai, and Labi who was surnamed Thadai,
B040C010V004	40	10	4	and Shemun the zealous, and Jihuda S'carjuta, he who betrayed him.
B040C010V005	40	10	5	These twelve Jeshu sent, and commanded them and said, In the way of the heathens go not, and into the city of the Shomroyee do not enter;
B040C010V006	40	10	6	but go rather unto the sheep which have perished from the house of Isroel.
B040C010V007	40	10	7	And as you go, proclaim and say that the kingdom of heaven hath drawn near.
B040C010V008	40	10	8	The diseased heal, the lepers cleanse, the dead raise, and the demons cast forth. Freely you have received, freely give.
B040C010V009	40	10	9	Provide neither gold, nor silver, nor brass in your purses,
B040C010V010	40	10	10	nor a wallet for the road; neither two tunics, nor sandals, nor staff: for worthy is the workman of his meat.
B040C010V011	40	10	11	And into whatsoever city or town you enter, inquire who is worthy in it, and there be till you depart.
B040C010V012	40	10	12	And when you enter into the house, invoke peace for the house;
B040C010V013	40	10	13	and if the house be worthy, your peace shall come upon it; but if it be not worthy, your peace upon yourselves shall revert.
B040C010V014	40	10	14	But whosoever doth not receive you or hear your words, when you depart from that house, or that town, set free the dust from your feet.
B040C010V015	40	10	15	And, Amen, I say unto you, that for the land of Sadum and of Amura it will be more tolerable, in the day of the judgment, than for that city.
B040C010V016	40	10	16	LO, I send you forth as sheep among wolves: be you, therefore, wise as serpents and guileless as doves.
B040C010V017	40	10	17	But beware of the sons of men; for, delivering you to the house of judgments, in their synagogues they will scourge you,
B040C010V018	40	10	18	and before governors and kings bring you, on my account, for the testimony concerning them and the gentiles.
B040C010V019	40	10	19	But when they deliver you up, be not solicitous how or what you shall speak; for it is given you in that hour what you shall speak.
B040C010V020	40	10	20	For it is not you speaking, but the Spirit of your Father speaking in you.
B040C010V021	40	10	21	But the brother shall deliver his brother unto death, and the father his son; and the sons shall rise up against their fathers, and shall slay them.
B040C010V022	40	10	22	And you shall be abhorred by all men on account of my name: but he who shall persevere until the end, he shall be saved.
B040C010V023	40	10	23	When they persecute you in this city, escape to the other; for, Amen I say unto you, that you shall not have completed all the cities of the house of Isroel, till the Son of man shall come.
B040C010V024	40	10	24	The disciple is not greater than his master, nor the servant than his lord.
B040C010V025	40	10	25	It sufficeth the disciple that he be as his master, and the servant as his lord. If the master of the house they have called Beelzebub, how much more his house-sons!
B040C010V026	40	10	26	You shall not fear, therefore, from them; for there is nothing covered which shall not be revealed, nor secret which shall not be known.
B040C010V027	40	10	27	Whatsoever I say to you in darkness, declare you in the light; and whatsoever you have heard in your ears, proclaim upon the roofs.
B040C010V028	40	10	28	And fear not them who kill the body, but the soul cannot kill; but fear rather One who the soul and the body can destroy in gihano.
B040C010V029	40	10	29	Are not two sparrows sold for an asor? yet one of them, without your Father, doth not fall upon the earth.
B040C010V030	40	10	30	But of you, also, the hairs of your head are all numbered.
B040C010V031	40	10	31	Fear not, therefore; than many sparrows more precious are you.
B040C010V032	40	10	32	Every man, therefore, who shall confess me before the sons of men, I myself will confess him also before my Father who is in heaven.
B040C010V033	40	10	33	But whosoever shall deny me before the sons of men, I also will deny him, I, before my Father who is in heaven.
B040C010V034	40	10	34	EXPECT not that I have come to send forth peace on the earth; I have not come to send forth peace, but the sword.
B040C010V035	40	10	35	For I have come to cause a man to separate from his father, and a daughter from her mother, and a daughter-in-law from her mother-in-law;
B040C010V036	40	10	36	and the adversaries of a man (to be) his own house-sons.
B040C010V037	40	10	37	Whosoever loveth father or mother more than me is not worthy (of) me; and whosoever loveth son or daughter more than me is not worthy (of) me.
B040C010V038	40	10	38	And every one who taketh not his cross and cometh after me, is not worthy of me.
B040C010V039	40	10	39	Whosoever will find his life shall lose it, and whosoever shall lose his life for my sake shall find it.
B040C010V040	40	10	40	Whosoever receiveth you, receiveth me; and whosoever receiveth me, Him who sent me he receiveth.
B040C010V041	40	10	41	Whosoever entertaineth a prophet in the name of a prophet, the reward of a prophet receiveth. Whosoever entertaineth a just man in the name of a just man, the reward of the just man he receiveth.
B040C010V042	40	10	42	And whosoever only giveth one of these little ones a cup of cold (waters) to drink in the name of a disciple, Amen, I say unto you, he shall not lose his reward.
B040C011V001	40	11	1	AND it was that when Jeshu had finished instructing his twelve disciples, he removed from thence to teach and preach in their cities.
B040C011V002	40	11	2	But Juchanon, when he heard in the house of the bound the works of the Meshicha, sent by his disciples,
B040C011V003	40	11	3	and said to him, Art thou He that cometh, or another are we to expect?
B040C011V004	40	11	4	Jeshu answered and said to them, Go, recount to Juchanon these things which you hear and see;
B040C011V005	40	11	5	(that) the blind see, the lame are walking, the lepers are made clean, the deaf hear, the dead arise, and the poor are evangelized;
B040C011V006	40	11	6	and blessed is he who shall not be offended with me.
B040C011V007	40	11	7	But when they were gone, Jeshu began to speak to the assembly concerning Juchanon: What went you forth into the waste to see? a reed that by the wind was shaken?
B040C011V008	40	11	8	And if not, what went you forth to see? a man clothed in soft vestments? Behold, they who are softly clothed are in the house of kings.
B040C011V009	40	11	9	And if not, what went you forth to see? a prophet? I tell you, Yes; and more than a prophet.
B040C011V010	40	11	10	For this is he concerning whom it is written, Behold, I send my angel before thy face, to prepare the way before thee.
B040C011V011	40	11	11	Amen I say to you, there hath not arisen among them born of women who greater than Juchanon the Baptizer: yet, the least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he.
B040C011V012	40	11	12	But from the days of Juchanon the Baptizer until now, the kingdom of the heavens by violence is taken, and the violent ones seize it.
B040C011V013	40	11	13	For all the prophets and the law prophesied until Juchanon;
B040C011V014	40	11	14	and if you are willing, receive, that he is Elia who was to come.
B040C011V015	40	11	15	Whoever hath ears to hear, he shall hear.
B040C011V016	40	11	16	BUT to what shall I compare this generation? It is like children who sit in the public place, and cry to their companions,
B040C011V017	40	11	17	and say, We have sung to you, and you have not danced; we have wailed unto you, and you have not mourned.
B040C011V018	40	11	18	For Juchanon came neither eating nor drinking, and they say, He hath a devil.
B040C011V019	40	11	19	The Son of man came eating and drinking, and they say, See a man a devourer, a wine-drinker, a friend of tribute-takers and of sinners. But justified is wisdom by her servants.
B040C011V020	40	11	20	Then began Jeshu to reproach those cities in which were done many of his miracles, and which did not repent,
B040C011V021	40	11	21	saying, Woe to thee, Korazin! woe to thee, Bethtsaida! for if in Tsur and in Tsaidon those miracles had been done which have been performed in you, they would a while ago in sackcloth and ashes have repented.
B040C011V022	40	11	22	But I say to you, that for Tsur and Tsaidon it shall be more tolerable in the day of judgment than for you.
B040C011V023	40	11	23	And thou, Kaphernachum, who unto heaven art exalted, unto Shiul shalt be brought down; for if in Sadum had been done those miracles which have been done in thee, it would have stood until this day.
B040C011V024	40	11	24	But I tell you that for the land of Sadum it shall be more tolerable in the day of judgment than for thee.
B040C011V025	40	11	25	IN that time Jeshu answered and said, I praise thee, my Father, the Lord of the heavens and of the earth, that thou hast concealed these (things) from the wise and prudent, but hast revealed them unto little children.
B040C011V026	40	11	26	Yes, my Father, for thus was it pleasing before thee!
B040C011V027	40	11	27	All things are delivered to me from my Father; and no man knoweth the Son but the Father; also the Father no man knoweth, except the Son, and he (to) whom the Son pleaseth to reveal (him).
B040C011V028	40	11	28	Come unto me, all you (who) are wearied and bearing burdens, and I will give you rest.
B040C011V029	40	11	29	Bear my yoke upon you, and learn of me; for I am peaceful and lowly in my heart, and you shall find repose for your souls.
B040C011V030	40	11	30	For my yoke is kindly, and my burden is light.
B040C012V001	40	12	1	At that time Jeshu was walking on the sabbath among the grain; and his disciples hungered, and began to pluck the ears and to eat.
B040C012V002	40	12	2	But when the Pharishee saw them, they say to him, Look, thy disciples do something which is not lawful to be done on the sabbath.
B040C012V003	40	12	3	But he said to them, Have you not read what David did when he hungered, and they who were with him?
B040C012V004	40	12	4	how he went to the house of Aloha, and the bread of the table of the Lord did he eat,-that which was not lawful for him to eat, nor for them who were with him, but for the priests only?
B040C012V005	40	12	5	Or have you not read in the law that the priests in the temple profane the sabbath in it, and are without blame?
B040C012V006	40	12	6	But I say to you, that (one) greater than the temple is here.
B040C012V007	40	12	7	Moreover, if you knew what that (meaneth), " I desire mercy and not a sacrifice," you would not have condemned them who are not faulty.
B040C012V008	40	12	8	For the Lord of the sabbath is the Son of man.
B040C012V009	40	12	9	AND Jeshu passed thence, and came into their synagogue.
B040C012V010	40	12	10	And a certain man was there whose hand was withered. And they questioned him, saying, Is it lawful on the sabbath to heal? that they might accuse him.
B040C012V011	40	12	11	But he said to them, What man is there among you that hath one sheep, (who), if it fall into a pit on the sabbath-day, doth not take and lift it up?
B040C012V012	40	12	12	How much more precious is a child of man than a sheep! Wherefore it is lawful on the sabbath-day to do that which is good.
B040C012V013	40	12	13	Then saith he to the man, Stretch forth thine hand! and he stretched forth his hand, and it was restored like the other its fellow.
B040C012V014	40	12	14	And the Pharishee went forth and took counsel against him, how they might destroy him.
B040C012V015	40	12	15	But Jeshu knew, and passed from thence; and great crowds went after him, and he healed them all.
B040C012V016	40	12	16	And he forbad that they should make him known.
B040C012V017	40	12	17	That what was spoken by the prophet Eshaia might be fulfilled, who said,
B040C012V018	40	12	18	Behold my servant, in whom is my pleasure: My beloved, in whom my soul delighteth. My Spirit will I put upon him, And judgment to the peoples shall he preach.
B040C012V019	40	12	19	He shall not contend nor cry, And no man shall hear his voice in the street.
B040C012V020	40	12	20	A bruised reed he will not break, And a flickering lamp he will not extinguish, Until he bring forth judgment unto victory.
B040C012V021	40	12	21	And in his name shall the gentiles hope.
B040C012V022	40	12	22	THEN they brought to him a certain demoniac who was dumb and blind; and he healed him, so that the dumb and blind could speak and see.
B040C012V023	40	12	23	And all the multitude were amazed, and said, Is not this the Son of David?
B040C012V024	40	12	24	But the Pharishee, when they heard, said, This (man) doth not cast forth demons unless by Beelzebub, the prince of the devils.
B040C012V025	40	12	25	But Jeshu knew their reasonings, and said to them, Every kingdom that is divided against itself is destroyed; and every city which is divided against itself shall not stand.
B040C012V026	40	12	26	And if Satan cast out Satan, he is divided against himself; how then standeth his kingdom?
B040C012V027	40	12	27	And if I by Beelzebub cast forth demons, your sons, by whom do they cast them forth? On this account they shall be your judges.
B040C012V028	40	12	28	But if I by the Spirit of Aloha cast forth demons, the kingdom of Aloha hath come nigh upon you.
B040C012V029	40	12	29	Or, how can one enter the strong one's house, and spoil his goods, unless he first bind the strong one? and then can he spoil his house.
B040C012V030	40	12	30	He who is not with me is against me; and he who gathereth not with me, in scattering scattereth.
B040C012V031	40	12	31	Wherefore, this I say to you: That all sins and blasphemies shall be forgiven unto the sons of men; but the blasphemy which is against the Spirit shall not be forgiven to the sons of men.
B040C012V032	40	12	32	And every one who shall speak a word against the Son of man, it shall be forgiven him; but every one who against the Spirit of Holiness shall speak, it shall not be forgiven to him, neither in this world nor in the world to come.
B040C012V033	40	12	33	Or make the tree good, and the fruits (will be) good; or make the tree evil, and the fruits (will be) evil: for by the fruits the tree is known.
B040C012V034	40	12	34	Brood of vipers! how can you speak good who are evil? For from the abundancies of the heart the mouth speaketh.
B040C012V035	40	12	35	A good man from the good treasuries bringeth forth good things, and an evil man out of the evil treasuries bringeth forth evil (things).
B040C012V036	40	12	36	But I tell you, that for every useless word which the sons of men shall speak, they must give the answer for it in the day of judgment.
B040C012V037	40	12	37	For by thy words thou shalt be justified, and by thy words thou shalt be condemned.
B040C012V038	40	12	38	THEN answered certain from the scribes and Pharishee, and said to him, Teacher, we would wish to see a sign from thee.
B040C012V039	40	12	39	But he answered them and said, A generation depraved and adulterous requireth a sign; but a sign shall not be given to it, but the sign of Jaunon the prophet;
B040C012V040	40	12	40	for as Jaunon was in the belly of the fish three days and three nights, so the Son of man shall be in the heart of the earth three days and three nights.
B040C012V041	40	12	41	The men of Ninevoë. shall rise up in the judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it; for they repented at the preaching of Jaunon; and, behold, a greater than Jaunon (is) here.
B040C012V042	40	12	42	The queen of the south shall arise in the judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it; for she came from the confines of the earth that she might hear the wisdom of Shelemun; but one more excellent than Shelemun is here.
B040C012V043	40	12	43	When the unclean spirit shall have gone forth from a child of man, he wandereth through places that have no waters in them, and seeketh repose, but findeth (it) not.
B040C012V044	40	12	44	Then he saith, I will return unto the house from whence I came forth; and coming, he findeth it untenanted, cleansed, and decorated.
B040C012V045	40	12	45	Then he goeth and taketh with him seven other spirits, than himself more wicked, and they enter and dwell in him. And the end of that man is worse than his beginning. So shall it be with this wicked race!
B040C012V046	40	12	46	While he spake to the assembly, his mother and his brethren came, standing without, and seeking to speak with him.
B040C012V047	40	12	47	And a man said to him, Thy mother and thy brethren are standing without, and are requesting to speak with thee.
B040C012V048	40	12	48	But he answered and said to him who spake to him, Who is my mother, and who are my brethren?
B040C012V049	40	12	49	And he stretched forth his hand towards his disciples, and said, Behold my mother, and behold my brethren!
B040C012V050	40	12	50	For every one who doeth the will of my Father who is in heaven, he is my brother, and my sister, and my mother.
B040C013V001	40	13	1	IN that day Jeshu went forth from the house and sat by the sea-side;
B040C013V002	40	13	2	and great multitudes gathered near him, so that he went up and sat in a vessel; and all the multitude were standing on the shore of the sea.
B040C013V003	40	13	3	And he discoursed largely to them in parables, and said: Behold, there went forth a sower to sow;
B040C013V004	40	13	4	and as he sowed, some fell by the road-side, and the fowl came and devoured it.
B040C013V005	40	13	5	Another (portion) fell upon the rock, where there was not much soil; and immediately it sprung up, because there was no depth of earth.
B040C013V006	40	13	6	But when the sun was risen, it burned, and, because it had no root, it withered away.
B040C013V007	40	13	7	And another fell among the thorns, and the thorns sprang up and choked it.
B040C013V008	40	13	8	And another fell into good earth, and gave fruits, this a hundred, another sixty, and another thirty.
B040C013V009	40	13	9	He who hath ears to hear, let him hear.
B040C013V010	40	13	10	And his disciples approached, saying to him, Why dost thou speak to them in parables?
B040C013V011	40	13	11	He replied and said to them, Because unto you it is given to know the mystery of the kingdom of heaven, but unto them it is not given.
B040C013V012	40	13	12	For unto him who hath, it shall be given, and it shall be increased to him: but to him who hath not, that also which he hath shall be taken from him.
B040C013V013	40	13	13	On this account I speak to them in parables. Hence they see, and (yet) see not; and they hear, and (yet) hear not, neither understand;
B040C013V014	40	13	14	and accomplished in them is the prophecy of Eshaia, who said, that hearing they should hear, but not understand, and seeing they should see, but not know.
B040C013V015	40	13	15	For the heart of this people is become gross, and with their ears they have heard heavily, and their eyes they have shut, that they may not see with their eyes, nor hear with their ears, nor understand with their hearts, and be converted, and I heal them.
B040C013V016	40	13	16	But blessed are your eyes which see, and your ears which hear:
B040C013V017	40	13	17	for, Amen I say unto you, that many prophets and just ones have desired to behold what you see, and have not beheld, and to hear what you hear, and have not heard.
B040C013V018	40	13	18	You, then, attend to the comparison of the seed:
B040C013V019	40	13	19	(When) any one who heareth the doctrine of the kingdom doth not understand it, there cometh the evil (one), and snatcheth away the doctrine that was sown in his heart: this is what by the road-side was sown.
B040C013V020	40	13	20	But that which was sown upon the rock is he who heareth the word, and at once with joy apprehendeth it.
B040C013V021	40	13	21	Yet hath he no root in him, but is (only) for a time; and when affliction or persecution occurs on account of the doctrine, he is quickly offended.
B040C013V022	40	13	22	That sown the place of thorns, is he who heareth the word, but the anxious thought of this world and the illusions of riches stifle the word in him, and he is without fruits.
B040C013V023	40	13	23	But that which upon good ground was sown is he who heareth my doctrine, and understandeth (it), and giveth fruits, and produceth, whether a hundred, or sixty, or thirty fold.
B040C013V024	40	13	24	ANOTHER comparison he allegorized unto them, and said: The kingdom of heaven is like unto a man who sowed good seed in his field.
B040C013V025	40	13	25	And while men slept, came his adversary, and sowed zizania among the wheat, and went.
B040C013V026	40	13	26	And when the plant sprang up and produced fruit, then appeared the zizania.
B040C013V027	40	13	27	And the labourers of the house-lord drew near and said to him, Our lord, didst thou not sow good seed in thy field? From whence then is the zizania in it?
B040C013V028	40	13	28	But he said to them, A foeman hath done this. The labourers say to him, Art thou willing that we go and gather them?
B040C013V029	40	13	29	But he said to them, (No,) lest, when ye gather the zizania, you root out with them the wheat also.
B040C013V030	40	13	30	Leave (them), that both may grow together till the harvest; and in the season of harvest I will say to the reapers, Gather first the zizania, and bind them (together in) bundles, that they may burn; but the wheat collect into my barns.
B040C013V031	40	13	31	Another comparison allegorized he to them, and said: The kingdom of heaven is like a grain of mustard, which a man took and sowed in his field.
B040C013V032	40	13	32	This is less than all other seeds; but when it has grown, it is greater than all herbs, and becometh a tree, so that the fowl of the heavens come (and) build in its branches.
B040C013V033	40	13	33	Another parable he spake to them: The kingdom of heaven resembles that leaven which a woman took and hid in three satas of meal, until the whole was leavened.
B040C013V034	40	13	34	All these spake Jeshu in parables to the multitude; and without a parable he did not speak with them.
B040C013V035	40	13	35	That there should be fulfilled what was spoken by the prophet, who said, I will open my mouth in comparisons, and pour forth things hidden from before the foundation of the world.
B040C013V036	40	13	36	Then Jeshu dismissed the multitudes, and came into the house; and his disciples drew near him, and said to him, Expound to us the comparison of the zizania of the field.
B040C013V037	40	13	37	He answered and said to them, He who sowed the good seed is the Son of man.
B040C013V038	40	13	38	The field is the world. Now, the good seed are the sons of the kingdom, but the zizania are the sons of the evil one.
B040C013V039	40	13	39	The adversary who sowed them is Satana; the harvest is the consummation of the world; the reapers are the angels.
B040C013V040	40	13	40	As, therefore, the zizania are gathered and burned in the fire, so shall it be in the completion of this world.
B040C013V041	40	13	41	The Son of man shall send forth his angels, and they shall collect from his kingdom all those who cause offence, and all (who) work iniquity,
B040C013V042	40	13	42	and shall throw them into a furnace of fire; there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C013V043	40	13	43	Then the just shall shine forth as the sun in the kingdom of their Father. He who hath ears to hear, let him hear.
B040C013V044	40	13	44	Again, the kingdom of heaven is like a treasure which was hidden in a field, (and) which a man found and concealed, and from joy went and sold all that he had, and bought that field.
B040C013V045	40	13	45	Again, the kingdom of heaven is like unto a man a merchant, who sought goodly pearls;
B040C013V046	40	13	46	but who, when he had found one pearl of exceeding price, went, sold all that he had, and bought it.
B040C013V047	40	13	47	Again, the kingdom of heaven is like unto a net, which was thrown into the sea, and from every kind collected.
B040C013V048	40	13	48	And when it was full, they drew to the shore, and sat down, and selected; and the good they threw into vessels, and the bad they cast without.
B040C013V049	40	13	49	Thus shall it be at the consummation of the world. The angels shall go forth, and separate the evil from among the just,
B040C013V050	40	13	50	and cast them into the furnace of fire; there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth!
B040C013V051	40	13	51	Jeshu said to them, Have you understood all these? They say to him, Yes, our Lord.
B040C013V052	40	13	52	He saith to them, On this account every scribe who is learned in the kingdom of heaven, is like to a man a house-lord, who bringeth forth from his treasuries the new and the old.
B040C013V053	40	13	53	AND when Jeshu had finished these parables, he passed from thence,
B040C013V054	40	13	54	and came to his city, and taught them in their synagogues, so that they were astounded and said, Whence hath he (Whence to him) this wisdom and these powers?
B040C013V055	40	13	55	Is not this the son of the carpenter? Is not his mother called Mariam, and his brothers, Jakub, and Josi, and Shemun, and Jehuda?
B040C013V056	40	13	56	and his sisters, all, are they not with us? Whence to this one all these?
B040C013V057	40	13	57	And they were offended with him. But Jeshu said to them, No prophet is contemned except in his own city, and in his own house.
B040C013V058	40	13	58	And he did not many miracles there on account of their unbelief.
B040C014V001	40	14	1	In that time Herodes Tetrarka heard the rumour concerning Jeshu;
B040C014V002	40	14	2	and he said to his servants, This is Juchanon the Baptizer: he hath risen from the house of the dead, therefore powerful works are wrought by him.
B040C014V003	40	14	3	For he, Herodes, had seized Juchanon, and bound him, and cast him (into) the house of the chained, because of Herodia the wife of Philip his brother.
B040C014V004	40	14	4	for Juchanon had said to him, It is not lawful that she should be to thee a wife.
B040C014V005	40	14	5	And he would have killed him, but he feared the people, because as a prophet they held him.
B040C014V006	40	14	6	But at the birth-day of Herodes, the daughter of Herodia danced before those who reclined, and she pleased Herodes;
B040C014V007	40	14	7	wherefore with an oath he sware to her to give her whatever she should demand.
B040C014V008	40	14	8	Then she, because instructed by her mother, said, Give me here in a dish the head of Juchanon the Baptizer.
B040C014V009	40	14	9	And the king sickened, yet, on account of the oath and the guests, he commanded that it should be given to her.
B040C014V010	40	14	10	And he sent cut off the head of Juchanon in the house of the chained.
B040C014V011	40	14	11	And his head was brought in a dish, and given to the girl, and she carried it herself to her mother.
B040C014V012	40	14	12	And his disciples came near, took up his corpse, buried (it), and came and showed Jeshu.
B040C014V013	40	14	13	Then Jeshu, when he heard, removed from thence by ship to a desert place by himself; and when the multitude heard it, they came after him on dry land from the cities.
B040C014V014	40	14	14	And Jeshu came forth, and saw great multitudes, and felt compassion for them, and healed their diseases.
B040C014V015	40	14	15	BUT when it was eventide, his disciples approached him, and said to him, The place is desert, and the time passed over; send away these multitudes of men, that they may go to the villages, and buy for themselves food.
B040C014V016	40	14	16	But he said to them, It is not needful that they should go; give you them to eat.
B040C014V017	40	14	17	They said to him, We have nothing here but five cakes and two fishes.
B040C014V018	40	14	18	Jeshu said to them, Bring them hither to me.
B040C014V019	40	14	19	And he directed the multitudes to recline upon the ground; and he took the five loaves and two fishes, and looked up to heaven, and blessed, and brake, and gave to his disciples, and the disciples themselves placed (it) before the multitudes.
B040C014V020	40	14	20	And all did eat, and were satisfied; and they took up, of the abundance of the fragments, twelve baskets when full.
B040C014V021	40	14	21	Now those men who had eaten were five thousand, besides women and children.
B040C014V022	40	14	22	And immediately he constrained his disciples to ascend into the bark, and proceed before him to the other shore, while he was dismissing the crowds.
B040C014V023	40	14	23	And when he had sent the multitudes away, he went up to a mountain by himself, to pray. AND when it was dark, he alone was there.
B040C014V024	40	14	24	But the vessel was distant from the land many stadia, being greatly beaten with the waves, for the wind was against them.
B040C014V025	40	14	25	But in the fourth watch of the night, Jeshu came to them, walking upon the waters.
B040C014V026	40	14	26	And the disciples beheld him walking on the waters, and they were troubled, saying, That it was a spectre; and from fear they cried out.
B040C014V027	40	14	27	But Jeshu at once spoke to them, and said, Take courage, I am, fear not!
B040C014V028	40	14	28	And Kipha answered, and said to him, My Lord, if it be thou, command me to come to thee upon the waters.
B040C014V029	40	14	29	Jeshu said to him, Come. And Kipha descended from the ship, and walked on the waters to go to Jeshu.
B040C014V030	40	14	30	But when he saw the furious wind, he feared, and began to sink; and he lifted up his voice, and said, My Lord, deliver me!
B040C014V031	40	14	31	And immediately our Lord reached forth his hand, and seized him, and said to him, Little of faith, why art thou divided (in mind)?
B040C014V032	40	14	32	And when they had ascended into the ship, the wind was tranquil.
B040C014V033	40	14	33	And they who were in the ship, came and adored him, and said, Truly the Son thou art of Aloha.
B040C014V034	40	14	34	And they rowed, and came to the land of Genésar;
B040C014V035	40	14	35	and the men of that country recognized him, and sent to all the villages that were about them, and they brought to him all those who were grievously afflicted,
B040C014V036	40	14	36	and besought from him that they might touch only the border of his mantle; and those who touched were healed.
B040C015V001	40	15	1	THEN came to Jeshu Pharishee and Sophree, who were from Urishlem, saying,
B040C015V002	40	15	2	Why do thy disciples transgress the tradition of the elders, and wash not their hands when they eat bread?
B040C015V003	40	15	3	Jeshu answered, and said to them, Why also do ye transgress the commandment of Aloha for the sake of your tradition?
B040C015V004	40	15	4	For Aloha hath said, Honour thy father and thy mother; and whoso curseth his father or his mother, to die he shall die:
B040C015V005	40	15	5	but ye say, Every one who shall say to a father, or to a mother, (It is) my oblation whatever thou wouldst be profited by me,
B040C015V006	40	15	6	and shall not honour his father or his mother (shall be guiltless). Thus you have abolished the word of Aloha for the sake of your tradition.
B040C015V007	40	15	7	Ye hypocrites! rightly prophesied concerning you Eshaia the prophet, and said,
B040C015V008	40	15	8	This people with the lips honour me, but their heart (is) very far from me.
B040C015V009	40	15	9	But in vain they reverence me, while they teach the doctrines of the commandments of men.
B040C015V010	40	15	10	And he called to the multitudes, and said to them, Hear, and understand:
B040C015V011	40	15	11	It is not that which, entering the mouth, contaminates a man; but that which shall come from the mouth, that contaminates a man.
B040C015V012	40	15	12	Then drew near his disciples, saying to him, Knowest thou that the Pharishee who heard this word were offended?
B040C015V013	40	15	13	But he answered, and said to them, Every plantation which my Father who is in heaven hath not planted shall be rooted up.
B040C015V014	40	15	14	Leave them: they are blind leaders of the blind; but if a blind man shall lead a blind man, both shall fall into the ditch.
B040C015V015	40	15	15	And Shemun Kipha answered and said, My Lord, expound to us this parable.
B040C015V016	40	15	16	But he said to them, Do you also not yet understand?
B040C015V017	40	15	17	Know you not that whatsoever entereth the mouth, goeth into the belly, and from thence in purification it is cast without?
B040C015V018	40	15	18	But whatsoever from the mouth shall come forth, from the heart cometh forth, and this contaminates a child of man.
B040C015V019	40	15	19	For from the heart proceed evil thoughts, adultery, murder, fornication, robbery, false witness, blasphemy.
B040C015V020	40	15	20	These are they which defile a man; but if any one eat when his hands are not washed, he is not defiled.
B040C015V021	40	15	21	AND Jeshu went forth from thence, and came to the borders of Tsur and Tsaidon.
B040C015V022	40	15	22	And, beheld, a Canaanite woman from those coasts came forth crying, and saying, Have mercy upon me, my Lord, son of David! my daughter is grievously possessed with the demon!
B040C015V023	40	15	23	But he did not return her an answer. And the disciples approached and requested from him, saying, Dismiss her, for she crieth after us.
B040C015V024	40	15	24	But he answered and said to them, I am not sent but to the sheep which have wandered from the house of Israel.
B040C015V025	40	15	25	Then she came, worshipped him, and said, My Lord, help me!
B040C015V026	40	15	26	Jeshu said to her, It is not proper to take the children's bread and throw it to the dogs.
B040C015V027	40	15	27	But she said, Even so, my Lord; yet the dogs eat from the crumbs that fall from the tables of their masters, and live.
B040C015V028	40	15	28	Then said Jeshu to her, O woman, great is thy faith! be it to thee as thou wilt! And healed was her daughter from that hour.
B040C015V029	40	15	29	And Jeshu passed from thence, and came near the sea of Galila; and he ascended the mountain and sat there.
B040C015V030	40	15	30	And there drew near to him great gatherings (of people), and with them there were the lame, and the blind, and the dumb, and the mutilated, and many others; and they cast them at the feet of Jeshu, and he healed them.
B040C015V031	40	15	31	So that those multitudes were astounded as they beheld the dumb speaking, and the mutilated made whole, and the lame walking, and the blind seeing; and they glorified the Aloha of Isroel.
B040C015V032	40	15	32	BUT Jeshu himself called his disciples, and said to them, I have pity for this multitude, who, behold, for three days have continued with me, but there is nothing for them to eat; and to send them away fasting, I am unwilling, lest they should faint in the way.
B040C015V033	40	15	33	The disciples say to him, Whence can we have bread in the wilderness, that we may satisfy this whole multitude?
B040C015V034	40	15	34	Jeshu saith to them, How many loaves have you? They say to him, Seven, and a few small fishes.
B040C015V035	40	15	35	And he directed that the multitudes should recline upon the ground.
B040C015V036	40	15	36	And he took those seven loaves and the fishes, and offered praise, and brake, and gave to his disciples, and the disciples gave to the multitudes;
B040C015V037	40	15	37	and they all did eat and were satisfied: and they took up of the abundance of fragments seven baskets full.
B040C015V038	40	15	38	And they who had eaten, were four thousand men, besides women and children.
B040C015V039	40	15	39	And when he had dismissed the multitudes, he ascended into a ship, and came to the coasts of Magodu.
B040C016V001	40	16	1	And there came Pharishee and Zadukoyee, tempting him, and demanding that he would show them a sign from heaven.
B040C016V002	40	16	2	3But he answered and said to them, When it is evening, you say, It will be serene weather, for the heaven hath reddened.
B040C016V003	40	16	3	And in the early morning you say, To-day will be tempestuous, for the heaven hath reddened gloomily. Hypocrites! the aspect of the heaven you are skilful to discriminate, (but) the signs of this time you know not how to distinguish.
B040C016V004	40	16	4	A depraved and adulterous race requireth a sign, but a sign shall not be given to it, save the sign of Jaunon the prophet; and he left them, and went away.
B040C016V005	40	16	5	And when his disciples had come to the opposite, they had forgotten to take bread with them.
B040C016V006	40	16	6	But he said to them, Take heed and beware of the leaven of the Pharishee and Zadukoyee.
B040C016V007	40	16	7	But they thought within themselves, saying, (It is) because bread we have not taken.
B040C016V008	40	16	8	But Jeshu knew, and said to them, Why reason you within yourselves, little in faith, because bread you have not brought?
B040C016V009	40	16	9	Have you not yet understood? Do you not remember those five loaves for the five thousand, and how many panniers you took up?
B040C016V010	40	16	10	Or those seven loaves and the four thousand, and how many baskets you took up?
B040C016V011	40	16	11	Why do you not understand that it was not concerning bread I spoke to you, but that you should beware of the leaven of the Pharishee and of the Zadukoyee?
B040C016V012	40	16	12	Then they understood that he did not say that they should beware of the leaven of bread, but of the doctrine of the Pharishee and of the Zadukoyee.
B040C016V013	40	16	13	NOW when Jeshu had come to the place of Cesarea of Philipos, he questioned his disciples, saying, What do men say concerning me who am the Son of man?
B040C016V014	40	16	14	They said to him, Some say that thou art Juchanon the Baptizer, but others Elia, and others Eramia, or one from the prophets.
B040C016V015	40	16	15	He saith to them, But you, whom say you that I am?
B040C016V016	40	16	16	Shemun Kipha answered and said, Thou art the Meshicha, Son of Aloha the Living.
B040C016V017	40	16	17	Jeshu responded and said to him, Blessed art thou, Shemun-bar-Jona; because flesh and blood have not revealed (this) to thee, but my Father who is in heaven.
B040C016V018	40	16	18	Also I say unto thee, that thou art Kipha, and upon this rock will I build my church, and the gates of Sheul shall not prevail against her.
B040C016V019	40	16	19	To thee will I give the keys of the kingdom of heaven; and whatsoever thou shalt bind on earth, shall be bound in heaven; and whatsoever thou shalt loose on earth, shall be loosed in heaven.
B040C016V020	40	16	20	Then he commanded his disciples that no man they should tell that he was the Meshicha.
B040C016V021	40	16	21	AND from that time began Jeshu to show to his disciples that it was to be that he should go to Urishlem, and suffer much from the elders and the chief priests and scribes, and be slain, and the third day arise again.
B040C016V022	40	16	22	Then Kipha took him (apart?) and began to expostulate with him, and said, Far be it from thee, my Lord, that this should be to thee!
B040C016V023	40	16	23	But he turned and said to Kipha, Get thee behind me, Satana! thou art a stumbling-block to me, because thou thinkest not from Aloha, but from the sons of men!
B040C016V024	40	16	24	Then said Jeshu to his disciples. Whosoever willeth to come after me, let him deny himself, and let him take up his cross and follow me.
B040C016V025	40	16	25	For whosoever willeth to save his life, shall lose it; and whosoever will lose his life for my sake, shall find it.
B040C016V026	40	16	26	For what shall a man be profited, if the whole world he shall acquire, and his soul shall perish? or what equivalent shall a man give for his soul?
B040C016V027	40	16	27	For it is to be, that the Son of man shall come in the glory of his Father with his holy angels, and then shall he render unto every man according to his works.
B040C016V028	40	16	28	AMEN, I say unto you, There are men standing here who shall not taste death, until they shall have seen the Son of man coming in his kingdom.
B040C017V001	40	17	1	And after six days, Jeshu took Kipha, and Jakub, and Juchanon his brother, and led them to a high mountain by themselves.
B040C017V002	40	17	2	And Jeshu was changed before them; and his countenance shone like the sun, and his vestments were resplendent as the light.
B040C017V003	40	17	3	And there were seen with them Musha and Elia talking with him.
B040C017V004	40	17	4	Then answered Kipha, and said to Jeshu, My Lord, it is good for us to be here; and if thou art willing, we will make here three tabernacles; one for thee, and one for Musha, and one for Elia.
B040C017V005	40	17	5	But while he spake, behold, a bright cloud overspread them, and the voice was from the cloud, saying, This is my Son, the Beloved, in whom I have delighted: to him attend.
B040C017V006	40	17	6	And when the disciples heard, they fell upon their faces and feared greatly.
B040C017V007	40	17	7	And Jeshu approached them and touched them, and said, Arise, fear not.
B040C017V008	40	17	8	And they lifted up their eyes and saw no man, except Jeshu by himself.
B040C017V009	40	17	9	And while they were descending from the mountain, Jeshu charged them, and said to them, Before no man declare this vision, until the Son of man be risen from the dead.
B040C017V010	40	17	10	And the disciples asked and said to him, Why therefore say the scribes that Elia must come first?
B040C017V011	40	17	11	Jeshu answered and said to them, Elia cometh first that he may fulfil every thing;
B040C017V012	40	17	12	but I say to you, that, behold, Elia hath come, but they knew him not, and have done to him as they would. So also is the Son of man to suffer from them.
B040C017V013	40	17	13	Then understood the disciples that concerning Juchanon the Baptizer he spake to them.
B040C017V014	40	17	14	AND when they came to the multitude, a man approached him and kneeled upon his knees, and said to him,
B040C017V015	40	17	15	My Lord, have mercy on me! my son is lunatic and grievously afflicted; for often he falleth into the fire and often into the water.
B040C017V016	40	17	16	And I brought him to thy disciples, but they could not heal him.
B040C017V017	40	17	17	Jeshu answered and said, O unbelieving and perverse generation! how long shall I be with you, how long shall I bear with you? Bring him hither to me.
B040C017V018	40	17	18	And Jeshu rebuked him, and the demon went forth from him, and the youth was healed from that hour.
B040C017V019	40	17	19	Then came the disciples to Jeshu by himself, and said to him, Why were we not able to heal him?
B040C017V020	40	17	20	Jeshu saith to them, Because of your unbelief; for assuredly I tell you, if there were in you faith as a grain of mustard, you should say to this mountain, Pass hence, and it would pass away; and nothing should overcome you.
B040C017V021	40	17	21	But this kind goeth not forth but by fasting and by prayer.
B040C017V022	40	17	22	WHEN they had returned into Galila, Jeshu said to them, It is coming that the Son of man shall be delivered into the hands of men,
B040C017V023	40	17	23	and they shall kill him; and in the third day he shall arise. And it grieved them exceedingly.
B040C017V024	40	17	24	And when they came to Kapher-nachum, they who took the two zuzis, the head-silver, approached Kipha and said to him, Your master, doth he not give his two zuzeen?
B040C017V025	40	17	25	He saith to them, Yes. And when Kipha entered the house, Jeshu anticipated him, and said to him, How doth it appear to thee, Shemun? the kings of the earth, from whom do they take custom and headsilver, from their children, or from aliens?
B040C017V026	40	17	26	Shemun saith to him, From aliens: Jeshu saith to him, Then the children are free.
B040C017V027	40	17	27	But that we may not offend them, go to the sea, and cast the hook; and the fish that first cometh up, open his mouth; and thou shalt find a stater, that take and present for me and thee.
B040C018V001	40	18	1	IN that hour the disciples came near to Jeshu, saying, Who is greatest in the kingdom of heaven?
B040C018V002	40	18	2	And Jeshu called a child, and made him stand in the midst of them,
B040C018V003	40	18	3	and said, Amen I say to you, unless you be converted and become as children, you shall not enter the kingdom of heaven.
B040C018V004	40	18	4	Whosoever therefore humbleth himself as this child, he shall be greatest in the kingdom of heaven.
B040C018V005	40	18	5	And whosoever shall receive as like this child in my name, he receiveth me.
B040C018V006	40	18	6	And every one that shall offend one of these little ones who believe in me, to him it had been better that the mill-stone of an ass were hung to his neck, and himself plunged into the depths of the sea.
B040C018V007	40	18	7	Woe to the world from causes of offence! for it is unavoidable that causes of offence will come;
B040C018V008	40	18	8	but woe to the man by whom the causes of offence shall come! If, then, thine hand or thy foot shall be a cause of offence to thee, cut it off, and cast it from thee; for it is good for thee that thou enter into life lame or mutilated; and not that, having two hands or two feet, thou fall into the fire of eternity.
B040C018V009	40	18	9	And if thine eye be a cause of offence to thee, dig it out, and cast it from thee; good (it is) for thee that with one eye thou enter into life; and not that, having two eyes, thou fall into the gihâna of fire.
B040C018V010	40	18	10	See that you contemn not one of these little ones: for I say unto you that their angels in all time are beholding the face of my Father who is in heaven.
B040C018V011	40	18	11	For the Son of man is come to save that which had perished.
B040C018V012	40	18	12	How doth it appear to you? if a man have an hundred sheep, and one of them shall wander from them, doth he not leave the ninety and nine on the mountain, and, going, seek that which had wandered?
B040C018V013	40	18	13	And if he shall find it, assuredly I tell you that he rejoiceth in it more than (in) the ninety and nine which wandered not.
B040C018V014	40	18	14	So it is not good before your Father who is in heaven, that one of these little ones should perish.
B040C018V015	40	18	15	NOW if thy brother offend against thee, go, and argue (the matter) between thyself and him alone; and if he hear thee, thou hast gained thy brother.
B040C018V016	40	18	16	But if he hear thee not, take with thee one or two, that upon the mouth of two or three witnesses may be established every word.
B040C018V017	40	18	17	And if, also, he will not hear them, tell the church; but if he will neither hear the church, let him be to thee as a publican and as a heathen.
B040C018V018	40	18	18	And, Amen I say unto you, that whatsoever you shall bind on earth shall be bound in heaven; and whatsoever you shall loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven.
B040C018V019	40	18	19	Again I say to you, that if two of you shall consent on earth concerning every thing that they shall ask, it shall be done for them by my Father who is in heaven.
B040C018V020	40	18	20	For where two or three are assembled in my name, there am I in the midst of them.
B040C018V021	40	18	21	Then Kipha came near to him, and said to him, My Lord, how many times, if my brother offend me, shall I forgive him; until seven times?
B040C018V022	40	18	22	Jeshu said to him, I say not to thee, Until seven, but, Until seventy times seven and seven.
B040C018V023	40	18	23	THEREFORE is the kingdom of the heavens likened to a royal person who would take the account from his servants.
B040C018V024	40	18	24	And when he began to receive, they brought to him one who owed a myriad talents.
B040C018V025	40	18	25	And when he had nothing to pay, his lord commanded that they should sell (both) himself, his wife, and his children, and all that he had, and to pay.
B040C018V026	40	18	26	And that servant fell and worshipped him, saying, My lord, be patient of spirit toward me, and all things I (will) pay thee.
B040C018V027	40	18	27	And the lord of that servant had mercy, and absolved him, and forgave him his debt.
B040C018V028	40	18	28	Then went forth that servant, and found one of his fellows who owed him a hundred pence; and he seized him, strangling, and saying to him, Give me what thou owest to me.
B040C018V029	40	18	29	His fellow-servant fell at his feet, beseeching him, and saying, Be patient of spirit towards me, and I (will) pay thee.
B040C018V030	40	18	30	But he would not, but went and threw him into the house of the chained until he should have rendered him what he owed him.
B040C018V031	40	18	31	When their fellow-servants saw what was done, they were greatly grieved, and went and declared to their lord all that was done.
B040C018V032	40	18	32	Then his lord summoned him and said to him, Evil servant! all that debt did I forgive thee, because thou didst entreat me.
B040C018V033	40	18	33	Oughtest thou not to have been as gracious to thy fellow-servant as I was gracious unto thee?
B040C018V034	40	18	34	And his lord was indignant, and delivered him to the tormentors, until he should have paid all whatsoever he owed to him.
B040C018V035	40	18	35	Thus will your heavenly Father deal with you unless you forgive each his brother from your heart his trespasses.
B040C019V001	40	19	1	AND it was that when Jeshu had finished these words, he removed from Galila and came into the confines of Jehud beyond Jurdan.
B040C019V002	40	19	2	And great multitudes came after him, and he healed them there.
B040C019V003	40	19	3	And the Pharishee approached him, and, tempting him, propounded to him whether it was lawful for a man to send away his wife for every cause.
B040C019V004	40	19	4	But he answered and said to them, Have you not read that He who created from the beginning, male and female hath made them?
B040C019V005	40	19	5	And he said, On this account a man shall leave his father and his mother, and shall cleave to his wife, and they two shall be one flesh.
B040C019V006	40	19	6	Wherefore they were not two, but one body. That, therefore, which Aloha hath conjoined, man shall not separate.
B040C019V007	40	19	7	They said to him, Why then did Musha direct that he should give a writing of dismissal and send her away?
B040C019V008	40	19	8	He said to them, Musha, on account of the hardness of your heart, permitted you to send away your wives; but from the beginning it was not so.
B040C019V009	40	19	9	And I say to you that whosoever shall forsake his wife who is not adulterous, and take another, committeth adultery; and whosoever taketh the deserted one, committeth adultery.
B040C019V010	40	19	10	His disciples say to him, If thus be the case between the man and the woman, it is not expedient to take a wife.
B040C019V011	40	19	11	But he said to them, Not every man is sufficient for this doctrine, but he to whom it is given.
B040C019V012	40	19	12	For there are some eunuchs who from their mother's womb are born so; and there are some eunuchs who by men are made eunuchs; and there are eunuchs who have made themselves eunuchs on account of the kingdom of heaven. Whosoever is capable of receiving (this), let him receive (it).
B040C019V013	40	19	13	Then they brought to him children, that he should put his hand upon them and pray. And his disciples forbad them.
B040C019V014	40	19	14	But Jeshu himself said, Suffer children to come unto me, and forbid them not; for of those who are as these, is the kingdom of heaven.
B040C019V015	40	19	15	And he put his hand upon them, and went thence.
B040C019V016	40	19	16	AND one came and approached and said to him, Good teacher, what of good shall I do, that I may have the life of eternity?
B040C019V017	40	19	17	But he said to him, Why dost thou call me good? none is good but one, Aloha. But if thou wilt enter into life, keep the commandments.
B040C019V018	40	19	18	He said to him, Which? Jeshu answered him, Thou shalt not kill, neither commit adultery, nor steal, neither shalt thou witness false testimony;
B040C019V019	40	19	19	and honour thy father and thy mother, and love thy neighbour as thyself.
B040C019V020	40	19	20	The young man saith to him, These all have I kept from my childhood: how am I deficient?
B040C019V021	40	19	21	Jeshu saith to him, If thou wilt become perfect, go, sell thy possession and give to the poor, and there shall be for thee a treasure in heaven: and come after me.
B040C019V022	40	19	22	But he, the young man, heard this word, and went away with sadness, for he had great property.
B040C019V023	40	19	23	But Jeshu said to his disciples, Amen I say unto you, that it is difficult for the rich to enter the kingdom of heaven.
B040C019V024	40	19	24	Again I say to you, that it is easier for a camel to enter through the aperture of a needle, than the rich to enter into the kingdom of Aloha.
B040C019V025	40	19	25	But the disciples when they heard were greatly hurt, saying, Who then can be saved?
B040C019V026	40	19	26	Jeshu, beholding them, said, With the sons of men it is not possible; but with Aloha every thing is possible.
B040C019V027	40	19	27	THEN answered Kipha and said to him, Behold, we have abandoned every thing, and have come after thee: what then shall there be for us?
B040C019V028	40	19	28	Jeshu saith to them, Amen I say to you, that you who have come after me, in the new world, when the Son of man shall sit upon the throne of his glory, you also shall sit upon twelve seats, and shall judge the twelve tribes of Isroel.
B040C019V029	40	19	29	And every man who hath relinquished houses, or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or lands, on account of my name, shall receive a hundred-fold, and shall inherit the life of eternity,
B040C019V030	40	19	30	Many however are first who shall be last, and the last first.
B040C020V001	40	20	1	FOR the kingdom of heaven is like a man, a house-lord, who went forth in the early morn to hire labourers for his vinery.
B040C020V002	40	20	2	And he bargained with the labourers for a denarius a day, and sent them into his vinery.
B040C020V003	40	20	3	And he went forth in three hours, and saw others who were standing in the public place and unemployed.
B040C020V004	40	20	4	And he said to them, Go also you in the vinery, and what is suitable I will give you. Then went they.
B040C020V005	40	20	5	And he went forth again in six and nine hours, and did the same.
B040C020V006	40	20	6	And about eleven hours he went out, and found others who were standing and unemployed; and he said to them, Why are you standing all the day unemployed?
B040C020V007	40	20	7	They say to him, Because no man hath hired us. He saith to them, Go also you into the vinery, and whatever is suitable you shall receive.
B040C020V008	40	20	8	But when it was evening, the lord of the vinery said to the chief of his household, Call the workmen and give to them their wages; and begin from the last unto the first.
B040C020V009	40	20	9	And they came who (had wrought) from eleven hours; and they received each a denarius.
B040C020V010	40	20	10	But when the first came, they expected to take more; but they also received each a denarius.
B040C020V011	40	20	11	And when they had received, they murmured against the house-lord,
B040C020V012	40	20	12	and said, These last have wrought one hour, and thou hast made them equal with us, who have borne the burden of the day and its heat.
B040C020V013	40	20	13	But he answered and said to one of them, My friend, I am not unjust towards thee: didst thou not bargain with me for a denarius?
B040C020V014	40	20	14	Take what is thine and go: I will unto these last to give as unto thee.
B040C020V015	40	20	15	Is it not lawful for me that whatsoever l am willing, I may do with mine own? Is thine eye evil because I am good?
B040C020V016	40	20	16	Thus the last shall be first, and the first last; for many are the called, but few the chosen.
B040C020V017	40	20	17	NOW Jeshu was about to go up to Urishlem, and he took his twelve disciples by themselves in the way, and said to them,
B040C020V018	40	20	18	Behold, we go up to Urishlem, and the Son of man is betrayed to the chief priests and to the scribes, and they shall condemn him to the death;
B040C020V019	40	20	19	and they shall consign him to the Gentiles, and they shall mock him, and scourge him, and shall crucify him, and on the third day he shall arise.
B040C020V020	40	20	20	Then came to him the mother of the sons of Zabdai, she and her sons, and worshipped him, and supplicated a certain thing of him.
B040C020V021	40	20	21	But he said to her, What wilt thou? She said to him, Declare that these my two sons shall sit, one at thy right hand, and one at thy left, in thy kingdom.
B040C020V022	40	20	22	Jeshu answered and said, You know not what you ask: are you able to drink the cup of which I am about to drink, or with the baptism with which I am baptized will you be baptized? They say unto him, We are able!
B040C020V023	40	20	23	He saith to them, My cup you shall drink, and with the baptism with which I am baptized you shall be baptized: but that you may sit at my right hand, and at my left, is not mine to give, unless to them for whom it is prepared by my Father.
B040C020V024	40	20	24	And when the ten heard it, they were indignant against those two brothers.
B040C020V025	40	20	25	And Jeshu called them, and said to them, You know that the princes of the Gentiles are their lords, and their great ones exercise power over them;
B040C020V026	40	20	26	but it shall not be so among you; but whoever among you willeth to be great, let him be minister to you.
B040C020V027	40	20	27	And whoever among you willeth to be first, let him be to you the servant.
B040C020V028	40	20	28	So, the Son of man came not to be served, but to serve, and to give his life the redemption for many.
B040C020V029	40	20	29	AND when Jeshu went forth from Jirichu, a great multitude cometh after him.
B040C020V030	40	20	30	And, behold, two blind men were sitting by the side of the way; and when they heard that Jeshu was passing, they gave voice, saying, Be merciful upon us, my Lord, Son of David!
B040C020V031	40	20	31	But the crowds rebuked them that they should be silent; but they lifted up their voice the more, saying, Our Lord, be merciful upon us, O Son of David!
B040C020V032	40	20	32	And Jeshu stood and called them, and said, What will you that I should do for you?
B040C020V033	40	20	33	They say to him, Our Lord, that our eyes may be opened.
B040C020V034	40	20	34	And he had compassion on them, and touched their eyes, and immediately their eyes were opened, and they went after him.
B040C021V001	40	21	1	AND when he drew nigh to Urishlem, and had come to Beth-phage, at the mount of Olives, Jeshu sent two of his disciples,
B040C021V002	40	21	2	and said to them, Go to this village which is over against you, and you shall at once find an ass tied, and her colt with her; loose and bring (them) to me.
B040C021V003	40	21	3	And if any one say ought to you, say to him that it is requested for our Lord, and immediately he will send them hither.
B040C021V004	40	21	4	But all this was done that there should be fulfilled what was spoken by the prophet, who said,
B040C021V005	40	21	5	Tell you the daughter of Tsheum, Behold, thy king cometh to thee, lowly, and riding on an ass, and on a colt the foal of an ass.
B040C021V006	40	21	6	Then the disciples went, and did as Jeshu had commanded them;
B040C021V007	40	21	7	and brought the ass and the colt, and laid upon the colt their clothes, and Jeshu rode upon him.
B040C021V008	40	21	8	And many of the crowds spread their vestments in the way; and others cut down branches from the trees, and strewed them in the way.
B040C021V009	40	21	9	But the throngs who went before him, and came after him, cried out and said, Ushana to the son of David! blessed be He who cometh in the name of the Lord! Ushana in the heights!
B040C021V010	40	21	10	And when he had entered Urishlem, the whole city was commoved, and said, Who is this?
B040C021V011	40	21	11	But the multitude answered, This is Jeshu, the prophet who is from Natsrath of Galila.
B040C021V012	40	21	12	And Jeshu went into the temple of Aloha, and cast out all those who sold and bought in the temple, and overthrew the tables of the money-changers, and the seats of those who sold doves;
B040C021V013	40	21	13	and said to them, It is written, that my house shall the house of prayer be called, but ye have made it a den of thieves.
B040C021V014	40	21	14	And there came to him in the temple the blind and the lame, and he healed them.
B040C021V015	40	21	15	But when the chief priests and Pharishee saw the wondrous things which he did, and the children who were crying in the temple, and saying, Ushana to the son of David, they were displeased with them,
B040C021V016	40	21	16	saying to him, Hearest thou what these say? Jeshu saith to them, Yes: have ye not read, that from the mouth of children and of babes thou hast prepared praise?
B040C021V017	40	21	17	AND he abandoned them, and went forth without the city to Bethania, and lodged there.
B040C021V018	40	21	18	But in the early morn, as he returned to the city, he hungered:
B040C021V019	40	21	19	and he saw a certain fig-tree in the way, and came to it, but found nothing thereon but leaves only; and he said, Let there be no fruit upon thee again for ever. And immediately that fig-tree withered.
B040C021V020	40	21	20	And the disciples saw, and were astonished, saying, How in a moment is the fig-tree withered!
B040C021V021	40	21	21	Jeshu answered and said to them, Amen I say to you, that if faith were in you, and you did not hesitate, you should not only do (as) to this fig-tree, but also were you to say to this mountain, Be thou lifted up and fall into the sea, it should be done.
B040C021V022	40	21	22	And whatsoever you shall ask in prayer and shall believe, you shall obtain.
B040C021V023	40	21	23	And when Jeshu came to the temple, the chief priests and elders of the people approached him, while he taught, saying to him, By what authority doest thou these things, and who gave thee this authority?
B040C021V024	40	21	24	Jeshu answered and said to them, I will also ask you one word; and if you will tell me, I will also tell you by what authority I do these (things).
B040C021V025	40	21	25	The baptism of Juchanon, whence is it, from heaven or from men? But they thought within themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven, he saith to us, Why did ye not believe him?
B040C021V026	40	21	26	And if we shall say, From men, we fear from the crowd; for all have regarded Juchanon as a prophet.
B040C021V027	40	21	27	And they answered, saying to him, We know not: Jeshu saith to them, Also I tell not you by what authority I do these (things).
B040C021V028	40	21	28	BUT how doth appear to you? a certain man had two sons; and he came to the elder, and said to him, My son, go to-day work in the vinery.
B040C021V029	40	21	29	But he answered and said, I am not willing: yet afterwards he relented, and went.
B040C021V030	40	21	30	He came to the other, and said likewise. He answered and said, I (will), my lord; yet went not.
B040C021V031	40	21	31	Which of these two did the will of his father? They say to him, The elder. Jeshu saith to them, Amen I tell you, the tribute-takers and harlots go before you into the kingdom of Aloha.
B040C021V032	40	21	32	For Juchanon came to you in the way of righteousness; and you believed him not. But the tribute-takers and harlots believed him: but you neither when you saw (him, nor) afterwards, repented, that you might believe him.
B040C021V033	40	21	33	Hear another comparison: A certain man was a house-lord; and he planted a vinery, and surrounded it with an hedge, and dug a wine-press in it, and built in it a tower, and had it taken by labourers, and journeyed.
B040C021V034	40	21	34	And when the time of fruits drew near, he sent his servants to the husbandmen, that they might send him of the fruits of his vinery.
B040C021V035	40	21	35	And the husband-men took his servants, and beat some, and stoned some, and killed others.
B040C021V036	40	21	36	And again he sent other servants more than the first, and they acted towards them likewise:
B040C021V037	40	21	37	last, he sent to them his son, saying, Now will they be ashamed from my son.
B040C021V038	40	21	38	But the husbandmen, when they saw the son, said among themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and take the inheritance.
B040C021V039	40	21	39	And they seized and cast him without the vinery, and killed him.
B040C021V040	40	21	40	When the lord of the vinery, therefore, cometh, what will he do to these husbandmen?
B040C021V041	40	21	41	They say to him, Most miserably will he destroy them, and the vinery will he cause to be held by other labourers, (even) such as will give him the fruits in their seasons.
B040C021V042	40	21	42	Jeshu saith to them, Have you not read in the scripture, that the stone which the builders rejected, this is become the head of the corner? By the Lord was this done, and it is wondrous in our eyes.
B040C021V043	40	21	43	On this account I tell you, that the kingdom of Aloha is taken from you, and shall be given to a people who will yield fruits.
B040C021V044	40	21	44	And whosoever shall fall upon this stone shall be broken; but every one upon whom it shall fall, it will scatter (him).
B040C021V045	40	21	45	And when the chief priests and Pharishee heard his comparisons, they knew that concerning themselves he had spoken.
B040C021V046	40	21	46	And they sought to apprehend him, but feared the people, because as a prophet they regarded him.
B040C022V001	40	22	1	AND Jeshu answered again by comparisons, and said,
B040C022V002	40	22	2	The kingdom of heaven resembles a royal person who made a feast to his son;
B040C022V003	40	22	3	and he sent his servants to call the invited ones to the feast, but they were not willing to come.
B040C022V004	40	22	4	And again he sent other servants, and said, Tell the invited ones, Behold, my dinner is prepared, my oxen and my fatlings are killed, and all things are ready; come to the feast.
B040C022V005	40	22	5	But they despised (it), and went, one to his domain, and another to his business.
B040C022V006	40	22	6	But the rest took his servants and shamefully treated and killed (them).
B040C022V007	40	22	7	But when the king heard, he was wroth; and sent his forces and destroyed those murderers, and burned their city.
B040C022V008	40	22	8	Then said he to his servants, The feast is prepared, and those who were invited were not worthy.
B040C022V009	40	22	9	Go therefore into the outlets of the highways, and every one whom you find call to the feast.
B040C022V010	40	22	10	And those servants went forth into the highways, and assembled all whom they found, the bad and the good; and the place of feasting was filled with guests,
B040C022V011	40	22	11	And the king entered to see the guests, and he saw there a man who was not dressed in the garments of a festival.
B040C022V012	40	22	12	And he said to him, My friend, how didst thou enter here, when thou hast not the vestments of the feast? But he was silent.
B040C022V013	40	22	13	Then said the king unto the servitors, Bind his hands and his feet, and cast him forth into the darknesses without: there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C022V014	40	22	14	For many are the called, but few the chosen.
B040C022V015	40	22	15	THEN went the Pharishee and took counsel how they might ensnare him in discourse.
B040C022V016	40	22	16	And they sent to him their disciples with (certain) of the household of Herodes, saying to him, Doctor, we know that thou art resolutely true, and (that) the way of Aloha in truth thou teachest; neither carriest thou fear for man, for thou acceptest not the person of men.
B040C022V017	40	22	17	Tell us then, how doth it appear to thee? is it lawful to give head-money unto Cesar or not?
B040C022V018	40	22	18	But Jeshu knew their malice, and said, Why do you tempt me, you hypocrites?
B040C022V019	40	22	19	Show me the denarius of the head-silver. And they presented to him a denarius.
B040C022V020	40	22	20	And Jeshu said to them, Whose are this image and inscription?
B040C022V021	40	22	21	They say, Cesar's. He saith to them, Give then (the things) of Cesar unto Cesar, and (the things) of Aloha unto Aloha.
B040C022V022	40	22	22	And when they heard, they wondered, and left him, and went.
B040C022V023	40	22	23	IN that (same) day came the Zadukoyee, affirming to him, (that) there is no life for the dead. And they questioned him,
B040C022V024	40	22	24	saying to him, Doctor, Musha has said to us that if a man die having no children, his brother shall take his wife and raise up seed unto his brother.
B040C022V025	40	22	25	But there were with us seven brethren: the eldest (of whom) took a wife, and died. And because he had no children, he left his wife unto his brother.
B040C022V026	40	22	26	So also did he who was second, and he who was the third, and unto the seventh of them.
B040C022V027	40	22	27	But the last of all the woman also is dead.
B040C022V028	40	22	28	In the resurrection, therefore, of whom from these seven shall she be the wife? for all had taken her.
B040C022V029	40	22	29	Jeshu answered and said to them, You do err, because you understand not the scriptures nor the power of Aloha.
B040C022V030	40	22	30	For in the resurrection of the dead, they take not wives, neither are wives to husbands; but as the angels of Aloha in heaven are they.
B040C022V031	40	22	31	But concerning the resurrection of the dead, have you not read that which has been spoken to you by Aloha, who said,
B040C022V032	40	22	32	I am the God of Abraham, the God of Is'hok, the God of Jakub? But Aloha is not of those who are dead, but of those who are alive.
B040C022V033	40	22	33	And when the multitudes heard, they were wonder-struck at his doctrine.
B040C022V034	40	22	34	BUT when the Pharishee heard that he had silenced the Zadukoyee, they gathered together.
B040C022V035	40	22	35	And one from them, who was skilful in the law, questioned him, tempting him,
B040C022V036	40	22	36	Doctor, which commandment is greatest in the law?
B040C022V037	40	22	37	Jeshu said to him, Thou shalt love the Lord thy Aloha with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy strength, and with all thy mind.
B040C022V038	40	22	38	This is the commandment, the great and the first.
B040C022V039	40	22	39	And the second is like unto it, That thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.
B040C022V040	40	22	40	On these two commandments hang the law and the prophets.
B040C022V041	40	22	41	while the Pharishee were gathered together, Jeshu questioned them,
B040C022V042	40	22	42	and said, What say you concerning the Meshicha,-whose son? They say to him, Son of David.
B040C022V043	40	22	43	Saith he to them, And how doth David in spirit call him THE LORD? For he said,
B040C022V044	40	22	44	that the Lord said unto my Lord, Sit thou at my right hand until I put thine adversaries beneath thy feet.
B040C022V045	40	22	45	If, then, David calleth him the Lord, how is he his son?
B040C022V046	40	22	46	And no man could give to him the answer; nor did any man dare again from that day to question him.
B040C023V001	40	23	1	Then Jeshu discoursed with the multitudes and with his disciples,
B040C023V002	40	23	2	and said to them, Upon the chair of Musha sit the scribes and the Pharishee.
B040C023V003	40	23	3	Every thing, therefore, which they tell you to observe, observe and do; but after their practices do not act; for they say, and do not.
B040C023V004	40	23	4	And they bind heavy burdens, and lay them on the shoulders of men, but they with their fingers are not willing to touch them.
B040C023V005	40	23	5	And all their works they do that they may be seen of men; for they widen their tephillin, and lengthen the fringes of their waving vestments,
B040C023V006	40	23	6	and love the chief reclining-places at evening feasts, and the highest seats in synagogues,
B040C023V007	40	23	7	and the shaloma in public places, and to be called of men Râbi.
B040C023V008	40	23	8	But be you not called Râbi: for One is your Master; but all ye are brethren.
B040C023V009	40	23	9	And call no man Abâ to you upon earth: for One is your Father, who is in heaven.
B040C023V010	40	23	10	Neither be ye called Medabronee: for One is your Guide,-the Meshicha.
B040C023V011	40	23	11	But he who is great among you, let him be your servitor.
B040C023V012	40	23	12	For whosoever will exalt himself shall be humbled; and whosoever will abase himself shall be exalted.
B040C023V013	40	23	13	Woe to you, scribes and Pharishee, hypocrites! because you hold the kingdom of heaven closed before the children of men; for you will not enter in yourselves, and them who are entering you will not permit to enter.
B040C023V014	40	23	14	WOE to you, scribes and Pharishee, hypocrites! because you devour the houses of widows, with the pretext of prolonging your prayers; on account of which you shall receive the greater judgment.
B040C023V015	40	23	15	Woe to you, scribes and Pharishee, hypocrites! because you go over sea and dry (land) to make one proselyte; and when you have done it, you make him doubly more a son of gihana than yourselves.
B040C023V016	40	23	16	Woe to you, ye blind guides, who say, That who sweareth by the temple, it is nothing; but if he swear by the gold which is in the temple, he is liable!
B040C023V017	40	23	17	You senseless and blind! for which is greater, the gold, or the temple that sanctifieth the gold?
B040C023V018	40	23	18	And (that) whoever sweareth by the altar, it is nothing; but he swear by the oblation which is upon it, he is liable.
B040C023V019	40	23	19	You foolish and sightless! for which is greater, the oblation, or the altar that sanctifieth the oblation?
B040C023V020	40	23	20	He therefore who sweareth by the altar, sweareth by it, and by all things that are upon it.
B040C023V021	40	23	21	And he who sweareth by the temple, sweareth by it, and by whatever abideth in it.
B040C023V022	40	23	22	And whosoever sweareth by heaven, sweareth by the throne of Aloha, and by Him who sitteth thereon.
B040C023V023	40	23	23	Woe to you, scribes, Pharishee, hypocrites! because you tithe mint, dill, and cummin, and omit the more grave of the law,-justice, benignity, and faithfulness. For these you should have done, and those not omitted.
B040C023V024	40	23	24	You blind guides, who strain out gnats and swallow camels.
B040C023V025	40	23	25	Woe to you, scribes and Pharishee, hypocrites! who cleanse the outside of the cup and dish (which) within are full of rapine and injustice.
B040C023V026	40	23	26	Sightless Pharishee! cleanse first the inside of the cup and the dish, that their outside also may be clean.
B040C023V027	40	23	27	Woe to you, scribes and Pharishee, hypocrites! for you are like whited sepulchres, which without appear beautiful, but within are full of the bones of the dead and all impurity.
B040C023V028	40	23	28	So you also from without appear to the sons of men as righteous, but within you are full of unrighteousness and hypocrisy.
B040C023V029	40	23	29	WOE to you, scribes and Pharishee, hypocrites! because you rebuild the tombs of the prophets and beautify the sepulchres of the just; and say,
B040C023V030	40	23	30	If we had been in the days of our fathers, we would not have been with them partakers in the blood of the prophets:
B040C023V031	40	23	31	thus bearing witness against yourselves, that you are the sons of them who killed the prophets.
B040C023V032	40	23	32	And you also,-complete the measure of your fathers.
B040C023V033	40	23	33	Serpents, birth of vipers! how will you escape from the judgment of gihana?
B040C023V034	40	23	34	On this account, behold, I send to you prophets, and wise men, and scribes; (some) of these you shall kill and crucify; and (some) of these you shall scourge in your synagogues, and persecute them from city to city.
B040C023V035	40	23	35	So that there shall come upon you all the blood of the just which hath been shed upon the earth; from the blood of Habil the righteous, unto the blood of Zakaria-bar-Barakia, whom you slew between the temple and the altar.
B040C023V036	40	23	36	Amen I say unto you, that all these shall come upon this generation.
B040C023V037	40	23	37	Urishlem, Urishlem! who killest the prophets, and stonest them who are sent unto her, what times would I have gathered thy children, as gathereth the hen her young ones beneath her wings, and you would not!
B040C023V038	40	23	38	Lo, your house is left unto you desolate.
B040C023V039	40	23	39	For I say unto you, That you shall not see me from henceforth, until you shall say, Blessed is he who cometh in the name of the Lord.
B040C024V001	40	24	1	AND Jeshu went forth from the temple to depart: and his disciples approached him, showing him the building of the temple.
B040C024V002	40	24	2	But he said to them, See you not all these? Amen I say to you, There shall not be left here a stone upon a stone which shall not be destroyed.
B040C024V003	40	24	3	And while Jeshu sat upon the mount of Olives, his disciples drew near and said between themselves and him, Tell us when these things shall be; and what is the sign of thy coming and of the consummation of the world.
B040C024V004	40	24	4	Jeshu answered and said to them, Beware that no man cause you to err;
B040C024V005	40	24	5	for many will come in my name and will say, I am the Meshicha; and many will be deceived.
B040C024V006	40	24	6	But it will be for you to hear wars and the noise of battles; (yet) see that you be not perturbed; for all these will take place, but not yet is the end.
B040C024V007	40	24	7	For people will rise against people, and kingdom against kingdom; and there shall be famines, and plagues, and earthquakes in various places.
B040C024V008	40	24	8	But these are all the beginning of sorrows.
B040C024V009	40	24	9	Then shall they deliver you to affliction, and shall kill you; and you shall be hated of all peoples on account of my name.
B040C024V010	40	24	10	Then shall many be offended, and shall hate one another, and betray one another.
B040C024V011	40	24	11	And many lying prophets shall stand up, and shall delude the multitudes.
B040C024V012	40	24	12	And because of the abounding of iniquity, the love of many will languish.
B040C024V013	40	24	13	But he who shall persevere unto the end,-he shall live.
B040C024V014	40	24	14	And this annunciation of the kingdom shall be proclaimed in the whole world as a testimony for all nations; and then will come the end.
B040C024V015	40	24	15	But when you see the unclean sign of desolation which was spoken of by Daniel the prophet, that it standeth in the holy place;-he who readeth let him understand!-
B040C024V016	40	24	16	then let those who are in Jehud escape to the mountain.
B040C024V017	40	24	17	And let not him who is on the roof descend to take what his house;
B040C024V018	40	24	18	nor he who is in the field turn back to take his vestment.
B040C024V019	40	24	19	But woe to those who are with child, and to those who give suck in those days!
B040C024V020	40	24	20	But pray that your flight may not be in the winter, nor on the shabath.
B040C024V021	40	24	21	For then shall be the great affliction, such as hath not been from the beginning of the world until now, neither shall be (again).
B040C024V022	40	24	22	And unless those days be cut short, none could live of all flesh: but on account of the chosen those days shall be cut short.
B040C024V023	40	24	23	Then if any one shall say to you, Lo, here is the Meshicha, or there; believe them not.
B040C024V024	40	24	24	For there shall arise false Meshichas and prophets of untruth; and they shall give forth magnificent signs, so as to seduce, if possible, the chosen also.
B040C024V025	40	24	25	(observe! I have told you before,)
B040C024V026	40	24	26	If therefore they shall say to you, Behold, he is in the desert; go not forth: or, Behold, he is in the inner chamber; believe not.
B040C024V027	40	24	27	As the lightning cometh forth from the east, and is seen unto the west, so shall be the advent of the Son of man.
B040C024V028	40	24	28	But where the body shall be, there will be assembled the eagles.
B040C024V029	40	24	29	But immediately after the affliction of those days, the sun will become dark, and the moon show not her light, and the stars shall fall from heaven, and the powers of heaven be commoved.
B040C024V030	40	24	30	And then shall be seen the standard of the Son of man in heaven, and then all the generations of the earth shall wail, and they shall see the Son of man coming upon the clouds of heaven, with great power and glory.
B040C024V031	40	24	31	And he shall send his angels with the great trumpet, and they shall gather the chosen who are his from the four winds and from the ends of heaven.
B040C024V032	40	24	32	But from the fig-tree learn a parable: As soon as her branches are soft, and they put forth her leaves, you know that summer draweth nigh.
B040C024V033	40	24	33	So also, when all these are seen, you know that it cometh to the door.
B040C024V034	40	24	34	Amen I say to you, that this race shall not have passed away until all these shall take place.
B040C024V035	40	24	35	Heaven and earth shall pass away; but my words shall not pass away.
B040C024V036	40	24	36	BUT concerning that day and concerning that hour, no man knoweth; neither the angels of heaven, but the Father only.
B040C024V037	40	24	37	But as the days of Nûch, so shall be the coming of the Son of man.
B040C024V038	40	24	38	For as before the deluge they were eating and drinking, taking wives and giving to husbands, until the day that Nûch went into the ark;
B040C024V039	40	24	39	and knew not till the deluge came, and carried them all away; so shalt be the advent of the Son of man.
B040C024V040	40	24	40	Then two shall be in the field; one shall be taken, and one be left.
B040C024V041	40	24	41	Two shall be grinding in the mill; one is taken, and one is left.
B040C024V042	40	24	42	Be wakeful therefore, because ye know not in what hour cometh your Lord.
B040C024V043	40	24	43	But this know; that if the master of the house knew in what watch the thief would come, he would have been watching, and not have suffered his house to be broken through.
B040C024V044	40	24	44	Wherefore be ye also prepared, because in the hour that ye expect not shall come the Son of man.
B040C024V045	40	24	45	WHO is the servant faithful and wise whom his lord shall appoint over the children of his house, to give every one his meat in his time?
B040C024V046	40	24	46	Blessed is that servant, who, when cometh his lord, shall be found doing so.
B040C024V047	40	24	47	Amen I say to you, that he will establish him over all that he hath.
B040C024V048	40	24	48	But if that evil servant shall say in his heart, My lord withholdeth to come;
B040C024V049	40	24	49	and shall begin to beat his fellow-servants, and shall be eating and drinking with drunkards;
B040C024V050	40	24	50	the lord of that servant shall come in a day that he computeth not, and in an hour which he doth not know,
B040C024V051	40	24	51	and shall sunder him, and set his lot with the hypocrites. There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C025V001	40	25	1	THEN shall be likened the kingdom of heaven unto ten virgins, who took their lamps, and went forth to meet the bridegroom and the bride.
B040C025V002	40	25	2	But five of them were wise, and five foolish.
B040C025V003	40	25	3	And those foolish (ones) took their lamps, but did not take with them the oil:
B040C025V004	40	25	4	but those were wise who took oil in vessels with their lamps.
B040C025V005	40	25	5	But while the bridegroom withheld, they all dozed and slept.
B040C025V006	40	25	6	And in the dividing of the night there was the cry, Behold, the bridegroom cometh; go forth to his meeting.
B040C025V007	40	25	7	Then all the virgins arose, and prepared their lamps.
B040C025V008	40	25	8	But those foolish ones said to the wise, Give to us from your oil; for, behold, our lamps are gone out.
B040C025V009	40	25	9	But the wise ones answered them, saying, Lest it should not suffice for us and for you; but go to those who sell, and buy for you.
B040C025V010	40	25	10	And while they were gone to buy, the bridegroom came, and those who were prepared entered with him into the house of festivity, and the gate was shut.
B040C025V011	40	25	11	At last came also those other virgins, saying, Our Lord, our Lord, open to us!
B040C025V012	40	25	12	But he answered and said to them, Assuredly I tell you, I know you not.
B040C025V013	40	25	13	Be wakeful therefore, for you know not that day nor the hour.
B040C025V014	40	25	14	FOR as a man who journeyed called his servants, and delivered to them his property:
B040C025V015	40	25	15	To one he gave five talents, and to another two, and to another one, each man according to his faculty; and forthwith went away.
B040C025V016	40	25	16	But he who had received five talents went and traded with them, and gained five others.
B040C025V017	40	25	17	Likewise he who (had received) two by trading gained two others.
B040C025V018	40	25	18	But he who had received one went, dug in the earth, and hid the money of his lord.
B040C025V019	40	25	19	After a long time the lord of those servants came, and received from them the account.
B040C025V020	40	25	20	Then he drew near who had received the five talents, and brought five others, and said, My lord, five talents thou gavest me: behold, five others I have gained by them.
B040C025V021	40	25	21	His lord said to him, It is well, good and faithful servant; over a little thou hast been faithful, over much I will establish thee: enter into the joy of thy lord.
B040C025V022	40	25	22	And he of the two talents approached, and said, My lord, two talents thou gavest me: behold, two others I have gained by them.
B040C025V023	40	25	23	His lord saith to him, It is well, servant good and faithful; over a little thou hast been faithful, over much will I establish thee: enter into the joy of thy lord.
B040C025V024	40	25	24	But he also drew near who had received the one talent, and said, My lord, I knew thee, that thou wast a hard man, reaping where thou hadst not sowed, and gathering together from whence thou hadst not dispersed.
B040C025V025	40	25	25	And I feared, and went and hid thy talent in the earth: behold, thou hast thine own.
B040C025V026	40	25	26	His lord answered, Thou evil and slothful servant, thou didst know me that I reap where I have not sowed, and collect from whence I have not dispersed.
B040C025V027	40	25	27	Did it not behove thee to cast my money upon the table, that when I came I might require mine own with its increase?
B040C025V028	40	25	28	Take therefore from him the talent, and give it unto him who hath ten talents.
B040C025V029	40	25	29	For unto him who hath shall be given, and it shall be added to him; but he who hath not, that also which he hath shall be taken from him.
B040C025V030	40	25	30	And the indolent servant cast forth into the darknesses without; there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C025V031	40	25	31	WHEN the Son of man cometh in his glory, and all his holy angels with him, then shall he sit upon the throne of his glory.
B040C025V032	40	25	32	And before him shall be gathered all nations: and he shall separate them one from another, as the shepherd separateth the sheep from the goats.
B040C025V033	40	25	33	And he shall cause the sheep to stand upon his right hand, and the goats on his left.
B040C025V034	40	25	34	Then shall the King say to them on his right hand, Come, blessed of my Father, inherit the kingdom which was to be for you from the foundation of the world.
B040C025V035	40	25	35	For I was hungry, and you gave me to eat; I thirsted, and you made me to drink; I was a stranger, and you received me;
B040C025V036	40	25	36	I was naked, and you covered me; I was sick, and you cared for me; and I was in prison, and you came to me.
B040C025V037	40	25	37	Then shall say unto him those righteous, Our Lord! when did we see that thou wast hungry, and fed thee, or that thou didst thirst, and we gave thee drink?
B040C025V038	40	25	38	and when did we see thee a stranger, and received thee, or naked, and covered thee?
B040C025V039	40	25	39	and when did we see thee sick, or in prison, and came to thee?
B040C025V040	40	25	40	And the King shall answer and say to them, Amen I say to you, Inasmuch as you did it unto one of these my least brethren, unto me you did it.
B040C025V041	40	25	41	Then shall he say also unto them on his left hand, Go from me, accursed, into the fire of eternity, which was prepared for the accuser and for his angels.
B040C025V042	40	25	42	For I was hungry and you gave me not to eat; and I thirsted, but you made me not to drink;
B040C025V043	40	25	43	and I was a stranger, and you received me not; and naked, and you clothed me not; and I was sick, and in prison, and you visited me not.
B040C025V044	40	25	44	Then shall they also answer and say, Our Lord! when saw we thee hungry, or thirsty, or a stranger, or naked, or sick, or in prison, and did not minister unto thee?
B040C025V045	40	25	45	Then shall he answer and say to them, Amen I say unto you, that inasmuch as you did it not unto one of these little ones, you did it not to me.
B040C025V046	40	25	46	And these shall go away into the torment which is eternal, and the just into the life which is eternal.
B040C026V001	40	26	1	AND when Jeshu had finished all these discourses, he said to his disciples,
B040C026V002	40	26	2	You know not that after two days is the Petzcha, and the Son of man is delivered up to be crucified.
B040C026V003	40	26	3	Then assembled the chief priests, and the scribes, and the elders of the people, in the hall of the chief of the priests, who was called Kaiapha.
B040C026V004	40	26	4	And they held counsel concerning Jeshu, how that by artifice they might apprehend and kill him.
B040C026V005	40	26	5	And they said, Let it not be on the festival, lest there be a tumult among the people.
B040C026V006	40	26	6	And when Jeshu was at Bethania, in the house of Shemun the leper,
B040C026V007	40	26	7	there drew near to him a woman who carried a vase of aromatic balsam, great of price, and she poured it upon the head of Jeshu as he reclined.
B040C026V008	40	26	8	But his disciples saw and were displeased, and said, For what is this destruction?
B040C026V009	40	26	9	For this could have been sold for much, and given to the poor.
B040C026V010	40	26	10	But Jeshu knew, and said to them, Why grieve you the woman? a good work hath she wrought upon me.
B040C026V011	40	26	11	For in all time the poor you have with you, but me you have not in all time with you.
B040C026V012	40	26	12	For this (woman) who hath poured this balsam upon my body, as unto my funeral hath done .
B040C026V013	40	26	13	And Amen I say unto you, Wheresoever this my Gospel shall be proclaimed, in all the world, this also which she hath done shall be told for her memorial.
B040C026V014	40	26	14	Then went one from the twelve, named Jihuda S'carjuta, unto the chief priests,
B040C026V015	40	26	15	and said to then, What are you willing to give me, and I will deliver him to you? But they settled to him thirty of silver.
B040C026V016	40	26	16	And from that time he sought to him opportunity to betray him.
B040C026V017	40	26	17	BUT in the first day of the (Phatiree) unleavened-bread days, the disciples came to Jeshu, and said to him, Where wilt thou that we prepare for thee to eat the passover?
B040C026V018	40	26	18	But he said to them, Go into the city to a certain man, and say to him, Our master saith, My time hath come! with thee will I perform the passover with my disciples.
B040C026V019	40	26	19	And the disciples did as Jeshu had commanded, and prepared the passover.
B040C026V020	40	26	20	And when it was evening, he reclined with his twelve disciples.
B040C026V021	40	26	21	And while they were eating, he said, Amen I say unto you, that one from you betrayeth me.
B040C026V022	40	26	22	And they were very sad, and began to say to him, one by one of them, My Lord, is it I?
B040C026V023	40	26	23	But he answered and said, One who dippeth his hand with me in the dish, he shall betray me.
B040C026V024	40	26	24	And the Son of man goeth as it is written concerning him; but woe to him, to that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed! Better had it been for that man if he had not been born.
B040C026V025	40	26	25	Then Jihuda the traitor answered and said, Am not I (he), Rabi? Jeshu replieth to him, Thou hast said!
B040C026V026	40	26	26	But while they were eating, Jeshu took the bread, and blessed, and brake, and gave to his disciples, and said, Take, eat, this (is) my body.
B040C026V027	40	26	27	And he took the cup, and offered thanks, and gave to them, and said, Take, drink of this all of you:
B040C026V028	40	26	28	this (is) my blood of the new covenant, which for multitudes is shed for the remission of sins.
B040C026V029	40	26	29	But I say to you, that I will not drink from henceforth of this product of the vines, until the day in which I shall drink it with you new in the kingdom of Aloha.
B040C026V030	40	26	30	And they sang praises, and went forth unto the mount of Olives.
B040C026V031	40	26	31	THEN said Jeshu unto them, You all shall be offended in me this night; for it is written, I will strike the shepherd, and scattered shall be the sheep of his flock.
B040C026V032	40	26	32	But after that I am risen I am before you in Galila.
B040C026V033	40	26	33	Kipha answered and said to him, Though every man should be offended in thee, I never will be offended in thee.
B040C026V034	40	26	34	Jeshu saith to him, Amen I say to thee, that in this night, before the cock shall crow, three times thou wilt deny me.
B040C026V035	40	26	35	Kipha saith to him, If I am to die with thee, I will not deny thee. The same also all the disciples said.
B040C026V036	40	26	36	Then cometh Jeshu with them unto the place which is called Gedsiman; and he said to his disciples, Sit here while I go and pray.
B040C026V037	40	26	37	And he took Kipha and the two sons of Zabdai; and he began to be sorrowful, and to be vehemently agonized.
B040C026V038	40	26	38	And he said to them, My soul is afflicted unto death; wait for me here, and watch with me.
B040C026V039	40	26	39	And he removed a little, and fell upon his face, praying, and saying, My Father, if it be possible, let this cup pass from me; yet not as I will, but as thou.
B040C026V040	40	26	40	Then he came to his disciples, and found them sleeping; and he said to Kipha, How, could you not for one hour watch with me?
B040C026V041	40	26	41	Be watchful and pray, that you enter not into temptation. The spirit is ready, but the body is infirm.
B040C026V042	40	26	42	Again he went the second time, and prayed, and said, My Father, if it be not possible for this cup to pass, unless I drink it, be done thy will!
B040C026V043	40	26	43	And he came again, and found them asleep; for their eyes had become heavy.
B040C026V044	40	26	44	And he left them, and went again, and prayed the third time, and said the same word.
B040C026V045	40	26	45	Then he came to the disciples, and said to them, Sleep on now, and be at rest; lo, the hour cometh, and the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.
B040C026V046	40	26	46	Arise, let us go: behold, he cometh who betrayeth me.
B040C026V047	40	26	47	And while he was speaking, behold, Jihuda the traitor, one from the twelve, came, and a great multitude with him, with swords and clubs, from the chief priests and elders of the people.
B040C026V048	40	26	48	And Jihuda the traitor had given to them a sign, and said, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that is he: take him.
B040C026V049	40	26	49	And immediately he approached Jeshu, and said, Peace, my master! and kissed him.
B040C026V050	40	26	50	But he, Jeshu, said to him, (Is it) for that thou hast come, my companion? Then they came on, and laid their hands upon Jeshu, and took him.
B040C026V051	40	26	51	And, behold, one from those who were with Jeshu stretched forth his hand, and unsheathed a sword, and struck a servant of the high priest, and took off his ear.
B040C026V052	40	26	52	Then said Jeshu to him, Return thy sword to his place; for every one of them who take swords, by swords shall die.
B040C026V053	40	26	53	Or thinkest thou that I cannot request from my Father, and he shall appoint to me now more than twelve legions of angels?
B040C026V054	40	26	54	(But) how, then, would the scripture be accomplished, that thus it ought to be?
B040C026V055	40	26	55	In that hour Jeshu said to the multitudes, As against a robber are you come out, with swords, and with clubs, to seize me? Every day with you in the temple I sat and taught, and you did not apprehend me.
B040C026V056	40	26	56	But this was done that what is written in the prophets might be fulfilled. Then the disciples all deserted him, and fled.
B040C026V057	40	26	57	And they who apprehended Jeshu led him unto Kaiapha, chief of the priests, where the jurists and elders were assembled.
B040C026V058	40	26	58	But Shemun Kipha went after him from afar unto the court of the chief of the priests, and entered and sat within with the attendants, that he might see the end.
B040C026V059	40	26	59	But the chief priests, and the elders, and the whole assembly, sought against Jeshu witnesses, that they might put him to death;
B040C026V060	40	26	60	but they found not (any). And many witnesses of falsehood came. But, last, two came near,
B040C026V061	40	26	61	declaring, This said, I can destroy the temple of Aloha, and in three days rebuild it.
B040C026V062	40	26	62	And the chief of the priests arose, and said to him, Dost thou return no word? What are these witnessing against thee?
B040C026V063	40	26	63	But Jeshu was silent. And the chief of the priests answered and said to him, I swear thee, by Aloha the Living, that thou declare to us whether thou be the Meshicha, the Son of Aloha?
B040C026V064	40	26	64	Jeshu saith to him, Thou hast said: but I say to you, That hereafter ye shall see him, the Son of man, sitting at the right hand of Power, and coming on the clouds of heaven.
B040C026V065	40	26	65	Then the chief of the priests tore his robes, and said, Behold, he hath blasphemed! what further need have we of witnesses? Behold, now we have heard his blasphemy.
B040C026V066	40	26	66	What will you? They answered saying, He deserves death.
B040C026V067	40	26	67	Then did they spit in his face, and smote him; and others struck him,
B040C026V068	40	26	68	saying, Prophesy to us, Meshicha! Who is he that smiteth thee?
B040C026V069	40	26	69	But Kipha was sitting without, in the hall, and a certain female domestic approached him, saying to him, Thou also wast with Jeshu Natsroia.
B040C026V070	40	26	70	But he denied before all, and said, I know not what thou sayest.
B040C026V071	40	26	71	And when he had gone out into the vestibule, another saw him, and said to them, This also was there with Jeshu Natsroia.
B040C026V072	40	26	72	And again he denied with oaths, I know not the man.
B040C026V073	40	26	73	But, after a little while, they who were standing drew near, and said to Kipha, Assuredly thou art of them; for thy speech also makes thee known.
B040C026V074	40	26	74	Then began he to imprecate and to swear, I know not the man! And in that hour the cock crowed.
B040C026V075	40	26	75	And Kipha remembered the word of Jeshu, who had said to him, That before the cock shall crow, three times wilt thou have denied me. And he went without, and wept bitterly.
B040C027V001	40	27	1	BUT when it was morning, the chief priests and elders of the people took counsel against Jeshu, how they should put him to death.
B040C027V002	40	27	2	And they bound him, and led him away, and delivered him to Pilatos the governor.
B040C027V003	40	27	3	Then Jihuda the traitor, when he saw that Jeshu was condemned, repented him, and went hastily, and returned those thirty of silver unto the chief priests and elders,
B040C027V004	40	27	4	and said, I have sinned, for I have betrayed the innocent blood. But they said to him, To us? what to us? Thou knowest,-thou!
B040C027V005	40	27	5	And he cast down the silver in the temple, and passed away, and went and strangled himself.
B040C027V006	40	27	6	But the chief priests took up the silver, and said, It is not lawful that we throw it into the place of offering, because it is the price of blood.
B040C027V007	40	27	7	And they took counsel, and bought with it the field of the potter, for the burial-place of strangers.
B040C027V008	40	27	8	Wherefore that field has been called, The field of blood, until this day.
B040C027V009	40	27	9	Then was fulfilled what had been spoken by the prophet, who said, And I took the thirty (pieces) of silver, the price of him who was precious, whom the sons of Isroel bargained for;
B040C027V010	40	27	10	and gave them for the field of the potter, as the Lord commanded me.
B040C027V011	40	27	11	But Jeshu himself stood before the governor. And the governor questioned him, and said to him, Thou art the king of the Jihudoyee? Jeshu said to him, Thou hast said.
B040C027V012	40	27	12	And while the chief priests and elders were accusing him, he returned not a word.
B040C027V013	40	27	13	Then said Pilatos unto him, Hearest thou not what they witness against thee?
B040C027V014	40	27	14	But he gave him no answer, no, not in one word; and upon this (Pilate) marvelled greatly.
B040C027V015	40	27	15	Now at every festival the governor was accustomed to release one of the bound unto the people, whomsoever they would.
B040C027V016	40	27	16	But there was (then) bound a notorious prisoner who was called Bar-aba.
B040C027V017	40	27	17	And when they were assembled, Pilatos said to them, Whom will you that I release unto you, Bar-aba, or Jeshu who is called the Meshicha?
B040C027V018	40	27	18	For Pilatos knew that from malice they had delivered him.
B040C027V019	40	27	19	But while the governor sat upon his tribunal, his wife sent to him saying, Let there be nothing between thee and that Just One; for much have I suffered in a dream to-day on his account.
B040C027V020	40	27	20	But the chief priests and elders persuaded the multitude that he should release to them Bar-aba, that they might destroy Jeshu.
B040C027V021	40	27	21	And the governor answered and said to them, Whom will you that I shall release to you of these two? Then they said, Bar-aba.
B040C027V022	40	27	22	Pilatos saith to them, And to Jeshu who is called the Meshicha, what shall I do with him? They all said, Let him be crucified.
B040C027V023	40	27	23	Pilatos saith to them, Why, what evil hath he done? But they clamoured the more, and said, Let him be crucified!
B040C027V024	40	27	24	Then Pilatos, when he saw that nothing availed, but that the tumult became greater, took waters (and) washed his hands before the assembly, and said, I am expiated from the blood of this Just One. You shall know.
B040C027V025	40	27	25	And all the people answered and said, His blood upon us, and upon our children!
B040C027V026	40	27	26	THEN he released to them Bar-aba; and scourged Jeshu with thongs, and delivered him to be crucified.
B040C027V027	40	27	27	Then the soldiers of the governor took Jeshu to the Praetorium, and the whole cohort gathered against him.
B040C027V028	40	27	28	And they stripped him, and invested him with a cloak of crimson.
B040C027V029	40	27	29	And they interwove a crown of thorns, and set it upon his head, and a cane in his right hand: and they kneeled upon their knees before him, and mocked him, saying, Hail, king of the Jihudoyee!
B040C027V030	40	27	30	And they did spit in his face, and took the cane, and struck him upon his head.
B040C027V031	40	27	31	And when they had derided him, they stripped him of the cloak, and clothed him with his own garments, and led him away to be crucified.
B040C027V032	40	27	32	And when they had gone forth, they found a Kurinean man whose name was Shemun: this (man) they compel to carry his cross.
B040C027V033	40	27	33	And they came to a place which is called Gogultho, which is expounded, The skull.
B040C027V034	40	27	34	And they gave him to drink vinegar mingled with gall: and he tasted, but was not willing to drink.
B040C027V035	40	27	35	And when they had crucified him, they divided his garments by lot: that what was spoken by the prophet might be fulfilled, They parted my garments among them, and upon my vesture did they cast lots.
B040C027V036	40	27	36	And they sat down and watched him there.
B040C027V037	40	27	37	And they placed over his head the occasion of his death, in the writing, This (is) Jeshu, the King of the Jihudoyee.
B040C027V038	40	27	38	AND they crucified with him two thieves, one on his right hand, and one on his left.
B040C027V039	40	27	39	But they who passed by railed against him, moving their heads,
B040C027V040	40	27	40	and saying, Destroyer of the temple, and builder of it in three days! deliver thyself, if thou art the Son of Aloha, and come down from the cross.
B040C027V041	40	27	41	Likewise also the chief priests mocking him, with the scribes and elders and Pharishee, saying,
B040C027V042	40	27	42	He saved others; himself he cannot save. If he be the King of Isroel, let him now descend from the cross, that we may see and believe in him.
B040C027V043	40	27	43	He trusted upon Aloha; let him liberate him now, if he delighteth in him; for he said, I am the Son of Aloha.
B040C027V044	40	27	44	Likewise also the robbers who were crucified with him reviled him.
B040C027V045	40	27	45	BUT from the sixth hour there was darkness upon all the land until the ninth hour.
B040C027V046	40	27	46	And about the ninth hour Jeshu cried with a high voice, Aloha! Aloha! why hast thou forsaken me?
B040C027V047	40	27	47	But certain of them who stood there, when they heard, said, This hath cried unto Ilio.
B040C027V048	40	27	48	And forthwith ran one from them, and took a sponge, and filled it with vinegar, and set it upon a cane, and gave him to drink.
B040C027V049	40	27	49	But the rest said, Let alone, we will see whether Ilio (will) come to deliver him.
B040C027V050	40	27	50	But he, Jeshu, again cried with a high voice, and dismissed his spirit.
B040C027V051	40	27	51	And at once the veil of the temple was rent in twain from above to beneath; and the earth was shaken, and the rocks were riven.
B040C027V052	40	27	52	And the house of the buried was opened; and the bodies of many of the saints who had been asleep arose,
B040C027V053	40	27	53	and came forth, and after his resurrection went into the holy city, and were seen by many.
B040C027V054	40	27	54	But the centurion and those with him, who guarded Jeshu, when they saw the commotion and those (portents) which took place, feared greatly, and said, Assuredly this was the Son of Aloha.
B040C027V055	40	27	55	(And) many women were there, beholding from afar; those who had come after Jeshu from Galila, and had ministered unto him.
B040C027V056	40	27	56	One of them was Mariam Magdolitha, and Mariam the mother of Jakub and of Josi, and the mother of the sons of Zabdai.
B040C027V057	40	27	57	BUT when it was evening, there came a rich man from Rometha, whose name was Jauseph, who himself also was a disciple of Jeshu.
B040C027V058	40	27	58	This went unto Pilatos, and begged the body of Jeshu. And Pilatos commanded that the body should be given to him.
B040C027V059	40	27	59	And Jauseph took the body, and wound it round in a cloth of pure linen,
B040C027V060	40	27	60	and laid it in a new house of burial of his own, which was hewn out in the rock. And they rolled a great stone, and heaved it against the door of the sepulchre, and went.
B040C027V061	40	27	61	Now there were there Mariam Magdolitha and the other Mariam, who were sitting over against the sepulchre.
B040C027V062	40	27	62	BUT the day which was next after the preparation, the chief priests and Pharishee came together unto Pilatos,
B040C027V063	40	27	63	saying to him, Our lord, we remember that that impostor said while alive, That after three days I will arise.
B040C027V064	40	27	64	Command therefore that they watch the sepulchre till (after) the third of the days; lest his disciples come, and steal him away by night, and tell the people that from the house of the dead he has risen, and the last delusion be worse than the first.
B040C027V065	40	27	65	Pilatos saith to them, Ye have guards; go, watch diligently, as ye know how.
B040C027V066	40	27	66	So they went, and set a watch (about) the sepulchre, and sealed the stone along with the guards.
B040C028V001	40	28	1	FROM the evening (end) of the sabbath, when the first (day) in the week was lightening, Mariam Magdolitha and the other Mariam came to see the sepulchre.
B040C028V002	40	28	2	And, behold, there was a great earthquake; for the angel of the Lord descended from heaven and drew near, rolled the stone from the door, and sat upon it.
B040C028V003	40	28	3	His aspect was like lightning, and his raiment was white as the snow.
B040C028V004	40	28	4	And with fear of him they who were watching were shaken, and became as the dead.
B040C028V005	40	28	5	But the angel answered and said to the women, Fear not ye; for I know that for Jeshu who was crucified you are seeking.
B040C028V006	40	28	6	He is not here: for he is risen, even as he said. Come, see the place in which our Lord was laid:
B040C028V007	40	28	7	and go with speed, and tell his disciples that he is risen from the house of the dead; and, behold, he goeth before you into Galila. There shall you see him. Lo, I have told you.
B040C028V008	40	28	8	And they went quickly from the sepulchre, with fear and with great joy, and ran that they might tell his disciples.
B040C028V009	40	28	9	And, behold, Jeshu met them, and said to them, Peace to you! And they approached, held him by the feet, and adored him.
B040C028V010	40	28	10	Then said Jeshu to them, Fear not; but go tell my brethren, that I will go into Galila, and there they shall see me.
B040C028V011	40	28	11	But while they went, there came certain from those guards into the city, and told the chief priests every thing that had been done.
B040C028V012	40	28	12	And they assembled with the elders, and took counsel; and they gave money not a little to the guards,
B040C028V013	40	28	13	telling them, Say you that his disciples came (and) stole him away in the night, while we slept.
B040C028V014	40	28	14	And if this be heard before the governor, we will persuade him, and make you without care.
B040C028V015	40	28	15	But they, when they had received the money, did as they had instructed them; and that saying went forth among the Jihudoyee until to-day.
B040C028V016	40	28	16	But the eleven disciples went into Galila, unto the mountain where Jeshu had appointed them.
B040C028V017	40	28	17	And when they saw him, they worshipped him; but from them some had doubted.
B040C028V018	40	28	18	And Jeshu drew near, and discoursed with them, and said to them, There is given unto me all power in heaven and in earth.
B040C028V019	40	28	19	As the Father sent me, so also I send you. Go therefore, disciple all nations, and baptize them in the name (of) the Father, and (of) the Son, and (of) the Spirit of Holiness.
B040C028V020	40	28	20	And teach them to observe all things whatsoever I have commanded you. And, behold, I am with you all the days, until the consummation of the world. Amen.
B041C001V001	41	1	1	THE beginning of the Gospel of Jeshu Meshicha, the Son of Aloha.
B041C001V002	41	1	2	As it is written in Eshaia the prophet: Behold, I send my angel before thy face, Who shall make straight thy way.
B041C001V003	41	1	3	The voice which crieth in the desert, Prepare the way of the Lord, Make level his paths.
B041C001V004	41	1	4	Juchanon was in the desert, baptizing, and proclaiming the baptism of repentance for the remission of sins.
B041C001V005	41	1	5	And all the region of Jehud and all the sons of Urishlem went out to him; and he baptized them in Jurdan the river, while they were confessing their sins.
B041C001V006	41	1	6	But Juchanon himself was clothed with a garment of the hair of camels, and engirded with a belt of leather upon his loins; and his food was locusts and wilderness honey.
B041C001V007	41	1	7	And he proclaimed and said, Behold, (One) cometh after me, who is mightier than I; he, the latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to bow myself to unloose.
B041C001V008	41	1	8	I have baptized you with waters; but he shall baptize you with the Spirit of Holiness.
B041C001V009	41	1	9	And it was in those days that Jeshu came from Natsrath of Galila, and was baptized in Jurdan by Juchanon.
B041C001V010	41	1	10	And as soon as he had ascended from the waters, he saw the heavens part asunder, and the Spirit, as a dove, descend upon him.
B041C001V011	41	1	11	And the voice was from the heavens, Thou art my Son, the Beloved: in thee I have delighted.
B041C001V012	41	1	12	And immediately the Spirit led him forth into the desert.
B041C001V013	41	1	13	And he was there in the desert forty days, being tempted by Satana: and he was with the wild beasts; and the angels ministered to him.
B041C001V014	41	1	14	BUT after Juchanon was delivered up, Jeshu came to Galila, and proclaimed the annunciation of the kingdom of Aloha.
B041C001V015	41	1	15	And he said, The time is complete; the kingdom of Aloha cometh: repent, and believe the gospel.
B041C001V016	41	1	16	And while he walked about the sea of Galila, he saw Shemun and Andreas his brother, who were casting nets into the sea: for they were fishers.
B041C001V017	41	1	17	And Jeshu said to them, Come after me, and I will make you fishers of the sons of men.
B041C001V018	41	1	18	And at once they forsook their nets, and went after him.
B041C001V019	41	1	19	And when he had passed on a little, he saw Jakub bar Zabdai and Juchanon his brother; and they also were in a vessel, preparing their nets.
B041C001V020	41	1	20	And he called them; and forthwith they left Zabdai their father with the hirelings, and went after him.
B041C001V021	41	1	21	And when they were come to Kapher-nachum, he forthwith taught on the sabbaths in their assemblies.
B041C001V022	41	1	22	And they wondered at his doctrine; for he taught them as having power, and not as their Sophree.
B041C001V023	41	1	23	And there was in their assembly a man who had an unclean spirit: and he cried
B041C001V024	41	1	24	and said, What to us and to thee, Jeshu Natsroya? Art thou come to destroy us? I know thee who thou art, the Holy One of Aloha.
B041C001V025	41	1	25	And Jeshu restrained him, and said, Close thy mouth, and come forth from him.
B041C001V026	41	1	26	And the impure spirit threw him down, and cried with a high voice, and went forth from him.
B041C001V027	41	1	27	And all wondered, and questioned one with another, Who is this? and what is this new doctrine? because with authority he commandeth the impure spirits, and they obey him.
B041C001V028	41	1	28	And his fame soon went out through all the region of Galila.
B041C001V029	41	1	29	And he proceeded from the assembly, and came to the house of Shemun and Andreas with Jacub and Juchanon.
B041C001V030	41	1	30	And the mother-in-law of Shemun was lying in a fever; and they told him concerning her.
B041C001V031	41	1	31	And he approached, took her by her hand; and she arose, and at once the fever left her, and she served them.
B041C001V032	41	1	32	Then in the evening at sun-setting they brought to him all those who were grievously affected and demoniacs.
B041C001V033	41	1	33	And the whole city was assembled at the gate:
B041C001V034	41	1	34	and he healed multitudes who were grievously affected with various diseases, and cast out many demons, and would not permit the demons to speak; for they knew him.
B041C001V035	41	1	35	AND in the morning he arose long before (day), and went into a solitude, and there prayed.
B041C001V036	41	1	36	And Shemun and (they) who (were) with him sought for him;
B041C001V037	41	1	37	and when they had found him, they said to him, All men are seeking thee.
B041C001V038	41	1	38	He said to them, Proceed you to the neighbouring towns and cities; for there also I will preach, because for this am I come.
B041C001V039	41	1	39	And he preached in all their assemblies in all Galila, and cast out devils.
B041C001V040	41	1	40	And a leper came to him, and fell at his feet, and besought him, and said to him, If thou wilt, thou canst cleanse me.
B041C001V041	41	1	41	And Jeshu had compassion on him, and stretched forth his hand, touched him, and said, I will, be clean.
B041C001V042	41	1	42	And in that very hour his leprosy went from him, and he was cleansed.
B041C001V043	41	1	43	And he restrained him, and led him forth,
B041C001V044	41	1	44	and said to him, See lest thou tell any one; but go, show thyself to the priests, and offer the oblation for thy purification as Musha commanded for their testimony.
B041C001V045	41	1	45	But he, when he was gone forth, began to announce it much, and so divulged the matter as that Jeshu could not go openly in the city, but was without in a solitary part: and they came to him from every place.
B041C002V001	41	2	1	AND Jeshu entered again into Kapher-nachum for some days. And when they had heard that he was in the house,
B041C002V002	41	2	2	many were gathered together, so that it could not contain them, nor yet (the space) before the gate; and he spake with them the word.
B041C002V003	41	2	3	And they came to him, and brought him a paralytic borne between four.
B041C002V004	41	2	4	And when they could not approach him for the crowd, they ascended to the roof, and took the covering from the place where Jeshu was, and let down the couch on which the paralytic lay.
B041C002V005	41	2	5	When Jeshu saw their faith, he said to the paralytic himself, My son, forgiven to thee are thy sins.
B041C002V006	41	2	6	But some of the Sophree and Pharishee were there, who sat and reasoned in their heart,
B041C002V007	41	2	7	Who is this uttering blasphemy? Who can forgive sins but One, Aloha?
B041C002V008	41	2	8	But Jeshu knew in his spirit that they so reasoned within themselves, and said to them, Why reason you these things in your heart?
B041C002V009	41	2	9	Which is easier, to say to the paralytic, Forgiven are thy sins, or to say, Arise, lift up thy couch, and walk?
B041C002V010	41	2	10	But, that you may know that the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins, he said to the paralytic,
B041C002V011	41	2	11	To thee I say, Arise, take up thy couch, and go to thy house.
B041C002V012	41	2	12	And he arose at once, and took up his couch, and went forth before them all; so that all wondered, and glorified Aloha, saying, Never saw we thus.
B041C002V013	41	2	13	AND he went forth again to the sea; and the whole multitude came to him, and he taught them.
B041C002V014	41	2	14	And when he had passed, he saw Levi bar Chalphai sitting among the publicans: and he said to him, Come after me; and arising, he went after him.
B041C002V015	41	2	15	And while he reclined in the house, many publicans and sinners reclined with Jeshu and with his disciples; for they were many, and they followed him.
B041C002V016	41	2	16	And the Sophree and Pharishee, when they saw him eat with publicans and with sinners, said to his disciples, Why with publicans and with sinners doth he eat and drink?
B041C002V017	41	2	17	But when Jeshu heard, he said to them, The healthy have no need of the physician, but they who are sorely affected: I have not come to call the righteous but the sinners.
B041C002V018	41	2	18	Now the disciples of Juchanon and of the Pharishee fasted. And they came and said to him, (While) the disciples of Juchanon and of the Pharishee fast, why do not thy disciples fast?
B041C002V019	41	2	19	Jeshu said to them, Can the sons of the marriage-chamber fast, while the bridegroom is with them? No;
B041C002V020	41	2	20	but the days shall come when the bridegroom shall be taken up from them: then shall they fast in those days.
B041C002V021	41	2	21	No man inserteth a new piece, and seweth it upon an old vestment; lest that new should take away its fulness from the old, and make the rent the greater.
B041C002V022	41	2	22	And no man putteth new wine into old bottles; lest the wine rend the bottles, and the bottles perish, and the wine be spilled: but they put new vine into new bottles.
B041C002V023	41	2	23	AND it was that, as Jeshu went among the grain, his disciples walked and plucked the ears.
B041C002V024	41	2	24	And the Pharishee said to him, See how on the shabath they do what is not lawful.
B041C002V025	41	2	25	Jeshu saith to them, Have you never read what David did, when he needed and was hungry, he, and they (who were) with him?
B041C002V026	41	2	26	how he entered the house of Aloha, when Abiathar was high priest, and did eat the bread of the table of the Lord, that which it is not lawful except for the priests to eat, and gave also to those who were with him?
B041C002V027	41	2	27	And he said to them, that the shabath on account of the Son of man was made, and not the Son of man on account of the shabath.
B041C002V028	41	2	28	The Son of man, therefore, is the Lord also of the shabath.
B041C003V001	41	3	1	And Jeshu again entered the congregation: and a certain man was there whose hand was withered;
B041C003V002	41	3	2	and they watched him whether he would cure him on the shabath, that they might accuse him.
B041C003V003	41	3	3	And he said to him, the man with the withered hand, Stand up in the midst.
B041C003V004	41	3	4	He said also to them, Is it lawful on the shabath to do good, or (that) which (is) evil? to save life, or to destroy it? But they were silent.
B041C003V005	41	3	5	And he beheld them with indignation, while it grieved him on account of the hardness of their hearts. And he said to the man, Stretch out thy hand. And he stretched (it); and his hand straightened.
B041C003V006	41	3	6	And the Pharishee went out immediately, and took counsel against him, how they might destroy him.
B041C003V007	41	3	7	And Jeshu with his disciples went towards the sea: and many people joined him from Galila, and from Jehud,
B041C003V008	41	3	8	and from Urishlem, and from Edum, and from beyond Jurdan, and from Tsur, and from Tsaidon; great multitudes, who, having heard all that he had done, came to him.
B041C003V009	41	3	9	And he spoke to his disciples to bring a vessel for him, that the crowds might not oppress him;
B041C003V010	41	3	10	for he had healed multitudes, until they were falling upon him to touch him.
B041C003V011	41	3	11	And they who were troubled with impure spirits, when they saw him, fell down, and cried, saying, Thou art the Son of Aloha.
B041C003V012	41	3	12	And he strongly prohibited them to make him known.
B041C003V013	41	3	13	AND he ascended a mountain, and called those whom he willed; and they came to him.
B041C003V014	41	3	14	And he chose twelve to be with him, and to send them to preach,
B041C003V015	41	3	15	and to have authority to heal diseases and to cast out devils.
B041C003V016	41	3	16	And he named to Shemun the name of Kipha;
B041C003V017	41	3	17	and upon Jacub bar Zabdai, and Juchanon the brother of Jacub, he set the name of B'nai-regesh, which is, (B'nai-râmo,) Sons of thunder.
B041C003V018	41	3	18	And Andreas, and Philipos, and Bar-Thulmai, and Mathai, and Thoma, and Jacub bar Chalphai, and Thadai, and Shemun the Zealous,
B041C003V019	41	3	19	and Jihuda S'carjuta,-he who betrayed him.
B041C003V020	41	3	20	And they came to the house: and the assemblies gathered again, so that they could not eat bread.
B041C003V021	41	3	21	And his relatives heard, and came forth to take him; for they said, He hath gone out of himself.
B041C003V022	41	3	22	And the Sophree, they who had come down from Urishlem, said, Belzebub is in him, and by the prince of devils he casteth out devils.
B041C003V023	41	3	23	And Jeshu called them, and by similitudes said to them, How can Satan cast out Satan?
B041C003V024	41	3	24	For if a kingdom against itself be divided, that kingdom cannot stand;
B041C003V025	41	3	25	and if a house against itself be divided, that house cannot stand;
B041C003V026	41	3	26	and if Satan rise against Satan, and be divided, he cannot stand, but his end is.
B041C003V027	41	3	27	No one can enter into the house of the strong, and spoil his goods, unless first the strong one he bind; and then his house he may destroy.
B041C003V028	41	3	28	Amen I say to you, That all sin and blasphemy which the sons of men blaspheme may be remitted them;
B041C003V029	41	3	29	but whosoever shall blaspheme against the Spirit of Holiness hath no remission for ever, but is condemned to the judgment that is eternal.
B041C003V030	41	3	30	Because they had said that an unclean spirit was in him.
B041C003V031	41	3	31	AND there came his mother and his brethren, standing without; and they sent to call him to them.
B041C003V032	41	3	32	But the congregation sat about him. And they say to him, Behold, thy mother and thy brethren without inquire for thee.
B041C003V033	41	3	33	And he answered, and said to them, Who is my mother, and who are my brethren?
B041C003V034	41	3	34	And looking upon those who sat with him, he said, Behold my mother, and behold my brethren:
B041C003V035	41	3	35	for whosoever shall do the will of Aloha, he is my brother, and my sister, and my mother.
B041C004V001	41	4	1	And he began again to teach by the sea-side: and great assemblies were gathered to him; so that, ascending, he sat in a bark on the sea, and the whole multitude stood on the land, by the edge of the water.
B041C004V002	41	4	2	And he instructed them by many parables, and said in his teaching,
B041C004V003	41	4	3	Listen: Behold, a sower went forth to sow;
B041C004V004	41	4	4	and as he sowed, some fell by the way-side, and the fowl came and devoured it.
B041C004V005	41	4	5	And other fell upon the rock, so that it had not much earth; and it soon came up, because it had not depth of earth:
B041C004V006	41	4	6	but when the sun arose, it became hot; and inasmuch as it had no root, it dried up.
B041C004V007	41	4	7	And other fell in a place of thorns; and the thorns sprang up, and choked it, and it gave no fruits.
B041C004V008	41	4	8	But other fell upon good ground; and it came up, and grew, and gave fruits, some thirty, some sixty, and some a hundred.
B041C004V009	41	4	9	And he said, Whoever hath ears to hear, let him hear.
B041C004V010	41	4	10	And when he was alone, they who were with him along with his twelve inquired of him that parable.
B041C004V011	41	4	11	And Jeshu said to them, To you it is given to know the mystery of the kingdom of Aloha; but to those without every thing is in parables:
B041C004V012	41	4	12	that while seeing they may see, and not see; and while hearing they may hear, and not understand; lest they should be converted, and their sins be forgiven them.
B041C004V013	41	4	13	And he said to them, Do you not know this parable? how will you know all parables?
B041C004V014	41	4	14	The sower who sowed, the word sowed.
B041C004V015	41	4	15	These which were by the way-side, these are they in whom the word is sown; and when they have heard, immediately cometh Satana, and taketh up the word which was sowed in their heart.
B041C004V016	41	4	16	And these who upon the rock are sowed, these are they who, when they have heard the word, at once with joy receive it:
B041C004V017	41	4	17	but they have no root in themselves, but are (only) for a time; and when there is affliction or persecution on account of the word, they are soon offended.
B041C004V018	41	4	18	And these who in the place of thorns are sown, these are they who hear the word;
B041C004V019	41	4	19	and the care of this world, and the deceptiveness of wealth, and the remainder of other lusts, entering, choke the word, and it is without fruits.
B041C004V020	41	4	20	And these who in good ground are sowed, these are they who hear the word, and receive, and give fruits, thirty, and sixty, and a hundred.
B041C004V021	41	4	21	And he said to them, A lamp never cometh to be put under a measure, or under a bed: is it not set upon a candlestick?
B041C004V022	41	4	22	For nothing is hid which shall not be revealed; nor is there any thing in secret which is not to be manifested.
B041C004V023	41	4	23	If any man hath ears to hear, let him hear.
B041C004V024	41	4	24	AND he said to them, Consider what you hear. With that measure which you mete, you shall have measured to you; and there shall be, added to you those which you hear.
B041C004V025	41	4	25	For whosoever hath, unto him shall be given; and whosoever hath not, that also which he hath shall be taken from him.
B041C004V026	41	4	26	And he said, So is the kingdom of God, as a man who shall cast seed into the earth;
B041C004V027	41	4	27	and shall sleep, and rise up by night and day, and the seed shall increase, and become long, while he knoweth not,
B041C004V028	41	4	28	For the earth yieldeth him fruit; and first is there the plant, and after it the ear, but lastly the completed corn in the ear.
B041C004V029	41	4	29	But when the fruit is mature, immediately cometh the sickle, because the harvest is come.
B041C004V030	41	4	30	And he said, To what may we compare the kingdom of Aloha? and with what comparison shall we compare it?
B041C004V031	41	4	31	It is like a grain of mustard, which, when sown in the earth, is smaller than all seeds which are in the earth:
B041C004V032	41	4	32	and when it is sown, it springeth up, and becometh greater than all herbs, and maketh great branches; so that in its shadow the fowl can dwell.
B041C004V033	41	4	33	In parables such as these spake Jeshu with them, in parables such as they could hear.
B041C004V034	41	4	34	And without parable did he not speak with them: but to his disciples, between him and them, he explained all.
B041C004V035	41	4	35	AND he said to them that day, in the evening, Let us pass to the opposite shore.
B041C004V036	41	4	36	And they sent away the assembles, and took him into the vessel; and other vessels were with him.
B041C004V037	41	4	37	And there was a great commotion and wind, and the waves fell upon the vessel, which was nigh being filled.
B041C004V038	41	4	38	But Jeshu upon a pillow slept in the after-part of the vessel, and they came and raised him, saying to him, Raban, hast thou no care that we are perishing?
B041C004V039	41	4	39	And he arose, and restrained the wind, and said to the sea, Peace, be silent. And the wind ceased, and there was a great stillness.
B041C004V040	41	4	40	And he said to them, Why feared ye? how is it ye have no faith?
B041C004V041	41	4	41	And they feared with great fear, and said among themselves, Who is this, to whom the winds and the sea are obedient?
B041C005V001	41	5	1	AND they came to the other side of the sea, to the region of the Gadroyee.
B041C005V002	41	5	2	And when he had come from the vessel, there met him from the place of tombs a man who had an unclean spirit,
B041C005V003	41	5	3	and he dwelt in the place of tombs; and with chains no man could bind him:
B041C005V004	41	5	4	for, so often as with shackles and chains he had been bound, the chains he had broken, and the shackles he had burst asunder; and no man could subdue him.
B041C005V005	41	5	5	And at all time, by night and by day, he was in the place of tombs, and in the mountains, crying out, and bruising himself with stones.
B041C005V006	41	5	6	But when he saw Jeshu from afar, he ran, worshipped him,
B041C005V007	41	5	7	and cried with a high voice, and said, What to me and to thee, Jeshu, Son of Aloha the Most High? I adjure thee by Aloha, that thou torment me not!
B041C005V008	41	5	8	For he had said to him, Come forth from the man, unclean spirit!
B041C005V009	41	5	9	And he questioned him, How is thy name? And he said to him, Legion is our name, because we are many.
B041C005V010	41	5	10	And he besought him much that he would not send him out of the region.
B041C005V011	41	5	11	Now at the mountain there was a great herd of swine feeding.
B041C005V012	41	5	12	And the devils besought him, saying, Send us into those swine, that into them we may enter.
B041C005V013	41	5	13	And he suffered them. And those unclean spirits went forth and entered into the swine; and that herd ran to the rock, and plunged into the sea, as two thousand, and were drowned in the waters.
B041C005V014	41	5	14	And they who kept them fled, and told in the city, and also in the hamlets; and they came forth to see what was done.
B041C005V015	41	5	15	And they came to Jeshu, and saw him who (had had) the devils, sitting, clothed, and sane; him, who had had in him the legion and they were afraid.
B041C005V016	41	5	16	And they who had seen, related to them what had been done to him who had had the devils, and also concerning those swine.
B041C005V017	41	5	17	And they began to beg of him to go from their coast.
B041C005V018	41	5	18	And when he had ascended the vessel, he in whom had been the devils besought him that he might be with him.
B041C005V019	41	5	19	But he permitted him not; but said to him, Go to thy house, to thy men, and show them what the Lord hath done for thee, and (how he) hath had mercy on thee.
B041C005V020	41	5	20	And he went, and began to preach in the ten cities what Jeshu had done for him: and all marvelled.
B041C005V021	41	5	21	AND when Jeshu had passed in the vessel to the opposite side, there were again congregated unto him great gatherings, while he was upon the shore of the sea.
B041C005V022	41	5	22	And there came one whose name was Jorosh, one of the masters of the synagogue; and when he saw him, he fell at his feet,
B041C005V023	41	5	23	and besought him much, saying to him, My daughter is greatly afflicted; come, lay thy hand upon her, and she will be healed, and live.
B041C005V024	41	5	24	And Jeshu went with him; and a great multitude adhered to him, and oppressed him.
B041C005V025	41	5	25	But a certain woman, who had a defluxion of blood twelve years,
B041C005V026	41	5	26	who much had suffered from many physicians, and had expended all whatever she had, and was nothing helped, but also the more afflicted,
B041C005V027	41	5	27	having heard of Jeshu, came in the press of the crowd behind him, and touched his vestment.
B041C005V028	41	5	28	For she said, If I but touch his vestment, I shall live.
B041C005V029	41	5	29	And immediately the fountain of her blood was dried; and she felt in her body that she had been healed from her plague.
B041C005V030	41	5	30	But Jeshu at once knew within himself that power had gone forth from him, and he turned to the crowd, and said, Who touched my garments?
B041C005V031	41	5	31	His disciples say to him, Thou seest the crowds that oppress thee, and sayest thou, Who touched me?
B041C005V032	41	5	32	And he looked round to see who this had done.
B041C005V033	41	5	33	But the woman herself, fearing and trembling, because she knew what had been done for her, came, fell before him, and told him all the truth.
B041C005V034	41	5	34	But he said to her, My daughter, thy faith hath saved thee; go in peace, and be healed from thy plague.
B041C005V035	41	5	35	And while he was speaking, there came some of the house of the master of the synagogue, saying, Thy daughter is dead: for what then art thou wearying the Teacher?
B041C005V036	41	5	36	But Jeshu heard the word which they spake, and said to the master of the synagogue, Fear not, only believe.
B041C005V037	41	5	37	And he did not permit any one to go with him, except Shemun Kipha, and Jacub, and Juchanon, brother of Jacub.
B041C005V038	41	5	38	And they came to the house of that master of the synagogue, and he saw how they made a tumult, and wept and bewailed.
B041C005V039	41	5	39	And he entered, and said to them, Why make you a tumult, and weep? the damsel is not dead, but asleep.
B041C005V040	41	5	40	And they derided him. But Jeshu put them all forth, and took the father of the damsel, and her mother, and those who were with her, and went in where the damsel was lying.
B041C005V041	41	5	41	And he took the hand of the damsel, and said to her, Damsel, arise.
B041C005V042	41	5	42	And forthwith the damsel arose, and walked; for she was a daughter of twelve years. And they wondered with great admiration.
B041C005V043	41	5	43	And he charged them greatly that no one should know this, and spake that they should give her (somewhat) to eat.
B041C006V001	41	6	1	AND Jeshu went forth from thence, and came to his city; and his disciples adhered to him.
B041C006V002	41	6	2	And when it was shabath, he began to teach in the house of the congregation: and many who heard wondered, and said, Whence to him are these? and what is this wisdom which hath been given him, that miracles such as these by his hands should be done?
B041C006V003	41	6	3	Is not this the carpenter, the son of Mariam, and the brother of Jacub, and of Josi, and of Jehuda, and of Shemun? and are not his sisters here with us? And they were offended with him.
B041C006V004	41	6	4	And Jeshu said to them, No prophet is despised, unless in his own city, and among his kinsfolk, and in his own house.
B041C006V005	41	6	5	And he could not do there any miracle, except that upon a few sick he laid his hands, and healed them
B041C006V006	41	6	6	And he wondered at the defectiveness of their faith. AND he itinerated through the villages, teaching.
B041C006V007	41	6	7	And he called his twelve, and began to send them two and two; and gave them power over unclean spirits to cast them out.
B041C006V008	41	6	8	And he instructed them to take nothing for the journey, except a staff only; not a wallet, nor bread, nor brass in their purses;
B041C006V009	41	6	9	but be shod with sandals, and not to be clothed with two tunics.
B041C006V010	41	6	10	And he said to them, Into whatsoever house you enter, there be until you go forth from thence.
B041C006V011	41	6	11	And every one who will not receive you, nor hear you, when you are going out from thence, beat off the dust that is beneath your feet for their testimony. And Amen I say to you, That it shall be more tolerable for Sadum and for Amura in the day of the judgment, than for that city.
B041C006V012	41	6	12	And they went forth, and preached that they should repent.
B041C006V013	41	6	13	And many devils they cast out, and anointed with oil the sick, and healed many.
B041C006V014	41	6	14	AND Herodes the king heard concerning Jeshu, for his name had become known; and he said, Juchanon the Baptizer hath risen from among the dead; therefore works of power are wrought by him.
B041C006V015	41	6	15	Others said, He is Elia; and others, A prophet as one from the prophets.
B041C006V016	41	6	16	But when Herodes heard, he said, It is Juchanon whom I beheaded; he hath risen from among the dead.
B041C006V017	41	6	17	For Herodes had sent and had taken Juchanon, and had cast him into the house of the bound, on account of Herodia, wife of Philipos his brother, whom he had taken.
B041C006V018	41	6	18	For Juchanon had said to Herodes, It is not lawful to thee to take the wife of thy brother.
B041C006V019	41	6	19	But Herodia herself was adverse to him, and wished to kill him, but she could not.
B041C006V020	41	6	20	For Herodes feared Juchanon, because he knew that he was a man righteous and holy, and he protected him, and was many (times) hearing him, doing, and hearing him favourably.
B041C006V021	41	6	21	And there was a notable day when Herodes, in the house of his nativity, (b'beth yaldeh,) made a feast to his chiefs and kiliarchs and the heads of Galila;
B041C006V022	41	6	22	and the daughter of Herodia came in (and) danced; and she pleased Herodes and them who reclined with him. And the king said to the damsel, Ask of me whatever thou wilt, and I will give to thee.
B041C006V023	41	6	23	And he sware to her, Whatever thou shalt ask (of) me, I will give thee, unto the dividing of my kingdom.
B041C006V024	41	6	24	Then went she out and said to her mother, What shall I ask of him? She saith to her, The head of Juchanon the Baptizer.
B041C006V025	41	6	25	And immediately she entered with solicitude unto the king, and saith to him, I will this hour that thou give me, upon a dish, the head of Juchanon the Baptizer.
B041C006V026	41	6	26	And greatly grieved was the king; but, for the sake of the oath, and the sake of the guests, he could not deprive her.
B041C006V027	41	6	27	But the king despatched at once a sentinel, and commanded that he should bring the head of Juchanon. And he went and cut off the head of Juchanon in the house of the bound,
B041C006V028	41	6	28	and brought (it) in a dish and gave to the damsel, and the damsel herself gave to her mother.
B041C006V029	41	6	29	And his disciples heard and went, took up his corpse, and laid it in the place of the buried.
B041C006V030	41	6	30	AND the disciples gathered unto Jeshu, and told him all whatever they had done, and whatever they had taught.
B041C006V031	41	6	31	And he said to them, Come and let us go into the desert alone, and rest a little while; for there were multitudes going and coming, (so that) they had not space even to eat;
B041C006V032	41	6	32	and they went to a wilderness district in a vessel by themselves.
B041C006V033	41	6	33	And many saw them as they went, and knew them; and into the waste ran they from all the cities, and were there before him.
B041C006V034	41	6	34	And Jeshu coming forth beheld the great assemblies, and had compassion upon them, they being like sheep which had no shepherd; and he began to teach them many things.
B041C006V035	41	6	35	And when much time had passed, the disciples came to him and said to him, This place is waste, and the time is great;
B041C006V036	41	6	36	send them away to go to the farms around us and into the villages, and buy for themselves bread, for they have nothing to eat.
B041C006V037	41	6	37	But he said to them, Give you them to eat. They said to him, Shall we go and buy bread for two hundred dinoreen, and give them to eat?
B041C006V038	41	6	38	But he said, Go see how many loaves you have here; and when they had seen, they said to him, Five loaves and two fishes.
B041C006V039	41	6	39	And he directed that they should make them all recline in companies upon the herbage;
B041C006V040	41	6	40	and they reclined in companies, by hundreds and by fifties.
B041C006V041	41	6	41	And he took the five loaves and the two fishes, and looked up to heaven, and blessed, and brake the bread, and gave to his disciples to set before them: and those two fishes they divided among them all,
B041C006V042	41	6	42	and they all did eat and were satisfied.
B041C006V043	41	6	43	And they took up the broken pieces, twelve baskets full, and from the fishes.
B041C006V044	41	6	44	Now they who had eaten bread were five thousand men.
B041C006V045	41	6	45	And immediately he constrained his disciples to ascend into the bark, and to go before him across to Beth-tsaida, while he dismissed the assemblies;
B041C006V046	41	6	46	and when he had sent them away, he went to a mountain to pray.
B041C006V047	41	6	47	BUT when it was eventide, the bark was in the midst of the sea, and himself alone upon the land.
B041C006V048	41	6	48	And he saw them that they were distressed with rowing; for the wind was against them. And in the fourth watch of the night Jeshu came to them walking upon the waters, (as though) he willed to pass by them:
B041C006V049	41	6	49	but they beheld him walking upon the waters, and thought it was a spectre, and they cried out;
B041C006V050	41	6	50	for all saw him and were afraid. But he immediately spoke to them and said to them, Take heart, I am, fear not.
B041C006V051	41	6	51	And he ascended to them into the ship, and the wind was still: and they wondered greatly, and were astonished among themselves.
B041C006V052	41	6	52	For they understood not from that bread, because their heart was gross.
B041C006V053	41	6	53	And when they had crossed over, they came to the land of Genesar.
B041C006V054	41	6	54	And when they had gone forth from the bark, the men of the place at once recognised him.
B041C006V055	41	6	55	And they ran throughout all that land, and began to bring those who were greatly afflicted, bearing them on couchettes, to where they heard that he was.
B041C006V056	41	6	56	And wherever he entered, into villages and cities, they placed the sick in the streets, and besought from him that they might touch only the edge of his mantle; and all they who touched him were healed.
B041C007V001	41	7	1	AND there gathered to him Pharishee and Sophree, who had come from Urishlem;
B041C007V002	41	7	2	and they saw some of his disciples eating bread with their hands not washed; and they complained.
B041C007V003	41	7	3	For all the Jihudoyee and Pharishee, unless they carefully wash their hands, do not eat, because they hold the tradition of the elders;
B041C007V004	41	7	4	and (coming) from the market, unless they lave, they eat not. And many other of those (things) there are which they have received to observe, (as) the baptisms of cups, and of measures, and of brasen utensils, and of beds.
B041C007V005	41	7	5	And the Sophree and Pharishee questioned him, Why do not your disciples walk according to the tradition of the elders; but, while their hands are not washed, eat bread?
B041C007V006	41	7	6	But he said to them, Well prophesied concerning you Eshaia the prophet, you hypocrites; as it is written, This people with their lips honour me, but their heart is very far from me.
B041C007V007	41	7	7	But in vain do they reverence me while they teach the teachings of the commandments of men.
B041C007V008	41	7	8	For you have abandoned the commandment of God and hold the tradition of men, as the baptisms of cups and measures, and many things like these.
B041C007V009	41	7	9	He said to them (moreover), You decently suppress the commandment of God, that you may establish your tradition.
B041C007V010	41	7	10	For Musha hath said, Honour thy father and thy mother; and whosoever curseth father and mother, the death he shall die.
B041C007V011	41	7	11	But you say, If a man shall say to his father, or to his mother, My oblation, (be that) whatever from me thou mayest profit;
B041C007V012	41	7	12	and you permit him not to do any thing for his father and his mother.
B041C007V013	41	7	13	But you reject the word of Aloha for the sake of the tradition which you have delivered: and many similar (observances) to these you practise.
B041C007V014	41	7	14	And Jeshu called the whole multitude, and said to them, Hear me, all of you, and understand:
B041C007V015	41	7	15	It is not that which is without the man, and which entereth into him, that can defile him: but that which proceedeth from him, that defileth a man.
B041C007V016	41	7	16	He who hath ears to hear, let him hear.
B041C007V017	41	7	17	But when Jeshu had gone into the house (apart) from the multitude, his disciples asked him concerning that parable.
B041C007V018	41	7	18	He said to them, How dull are even you! Know you not, that nothing from without that entereth a man can defile him,
B041C007V019	41	7	19	because it entereth not into his heart, but into his belly, and is cast out in the purgation which all food purgeth?
B041C007V020	41	7	20	But that which proceedeth from a man, that polluteth a man.
B041C007V021	41	7	21	For from within, from the heart of the sons of men, go forth evil thoughts, adultery, fornication, robbery, murder,
B041C007V022	41	7	22	rapacity, malice, fraud, obscenity, an evil eye, blasphemy, vain-glory, folly;
B041C007V023	41	7	23	all these evils come from within, and they defile a man.
B041C007V024	41	7	24	FROM thence Jeshu arose and went to the confine of Tsur and of Tsaidon, and entered into a certain house: and he was unwilling that any man should know of him, but he could not conceal.
B041C007V025	41	7	25	For immediately heard a certain woman concerning him, whose daughter had an unclean spirit; and she came, (and) fell before his feet.
B041C007V026	41	7	26	But that woman was a Gentile of Phuniki of Suria, and she prayed of him to cast out the demon from her daughter.
B041C007V027	41	7	27	But Jeshu said to her, Let the children first be filled; for it is not well to take the bread of the children and cast it to the dogs.
B041C007V028	41	7	28	But she answering said to him, Yes, my Lord, yet the dogs also from beneath the table eat the crumbs of the children.
B041C007V029	41	7	29	Jeshu saith to her, Go; on account of that word, the demon hath gone forth from thy daughter.
B041C007V030	41	7	30	And she went to her house, and found her daughter lying on the couch, and the demon had gone out from her.
B041C007V031	41	7	31	Jeshu again departed from the confine of Tsur and of Tsaidon, and came to the sea of Galila, on the confine of the Ten Cities;
B041C007V032	41	7	32	and they brought to him a blind man, a stammerer, and besought him to lay upon him the hand.
B041C007V033	41	7	33	And he took him aside from the crowd by himself, and put his fingers in his ears, and spat, and touched his tongue.
B041C007V034	41	7	34	And he looked up to heaven, and sighed, and said to him, Be opened:
B041C007V035	41	7	35	and in that hour his ears were opened, and the bond of his tongue was loosed, and he spake plainly.
B041C007V036	41	7	36	And he charged them that to no man they should tell this. But so much as he charged them, they the more proclaimed it;
B041C007V037	41	7	37	and they were exceedingly astonished, and said, He doeth every thing well; the deaf he maketh to hear, and them who spoke not, to speak.
B041C008V001	41	8	1	BUT in those days when the multitude was great and there was nothing for them to eat, he called his disciples, and said to them,
B041C008V002	41	8	2	I have compassion on this multitude, for behold three days have they continued with me, and there is nothing which they may eat.
B041C008V003	41	8	3	And if it be that I send them away fasting to their houses, they will faint in the way; for some of them come from afar.
B041C008V004	41	8	4	His disciples say to him, Whence can any one here in the wilderness satisfy with bread all these?
B041C008V005	41	8	5	And he asked them, How many loaves have you? They say to him, Seven;
B041C008V006	41	8	6	and he directed the multitudes to recline upon the ground, and he took those seven loaves, and blessed and brake and gave to his disciples that they should set, and they set before the assemblies.
B041C008V007	41	8	7	And there were fishes, a few: and also over them he blessed, and said that they should set them.
B041C008V008	41	8	8	And they all ate and were satisfied, and took up the abundancies of the fragments, seven panniers.
B041C008V009	41	8	9	Now the men who had eaten were about four thousand: and he dismissed them,
B041C008V010	41	8	10	and immediately ascended into a vessel with his disciples, and came to the region of Dalmanutha.
B041C008V011	41	8	11	AND there came forth Pharishee, and began to question with him, and they demanded of him the sign from heaven, tempting him.
B041C008V012	41	8	12	And he groaned in his spirit, and said, Why seeketh this generation the sign? Amen I say to you, There shall not be given the sign unto this generation.
B041C008V013	41	8	13	And he left them, and ascended into the ship, and went to that overland.
B041C008V014	41	8	14	And they had forgotten to take with them bread, and but one cake was with them in the ship.
B041C008V015	41	8	15	And he counselled them, and said to them, Look and beware of the leaven of the Pharishee, and of the leaven of Herodes.
B041C008V016	41	8	16	And they reasoned one with another, saying, Because we have no bread.
B041C008V017	41	8	17	But Jeshu knew, and said to them, Why reason you because you have no bread? do you not yet know nor under stand? is your heart still hard?
B041C008V018	41	8	18	and eyes have you, and not see? and ears have you, and not hear? neither remember you?
B041C008V019	41	8	19	When those five loaves I brake to five thousand, how many baskets full of fragments did you take up? They said to him, Twelve.
B041C008V020	41	8	20	He saith to them. And when seven to four thousand, how many panniers of fragments when filled took you up? They say, Seven.
B041C008V021	41	8	21	He saith to them, How do you not yet understand?
B041C008V022	41	8	22	And he came to Beth-tsaida; and they brought to him a blind man, and prayed of him to touch him.
B041C008V023	41	8	23	And he took the hand of the blind man, and led him forth without from the village; and spat in his eyes, and laid (on them) his hand, and inquired whether he saw.
B041C008V024	41	8	24	And he looked, and said, I see the sons of man as the trees, walking.
B041C008V025	41	8	25	Again he laid his hand upon his eyes, and he was restored, and he saw every thing clearly.
B041C008V026	41	8	26	And he sent him to his house, and told him to go not into the village, nor to inform any man in the village.
B041C008V027	41	8	27	And Jeshu went forth and his disciples into the villages of Kesarea of Philipos, and he interrogated his disciples by the way, saying to them, What say men concerning me that I am?
B041C008V028	41	8	28	But they answered, That (thou art) Juchanon the Baptizer; and others, that (thou art) Elia; and others, one from the prophets.
B041C008V029	41	8	29	Jeshu said to them, But you, what say you concerning me that I am? Shemun Kipha answered and said to him, Thus art the Meshicha, the Son of Aloha the Living.
B041C008V030	41	8	30	And he charged them that to any one they should not tell concerning him.
B041C008V031	41	8	31	And he began to teach them, that it was to be that the Son of man should suffer much, and be rejected by the elders, and by the chief priests, and by the Sophree, and be killed, and that the third day he should arise!
B041C008V032	41	8	32	And he spake the word with them fully. And Kipha took him, and began to chide him.
B041C008V033	41	8	33	But he turned, and, beholding his disciples, reprehended Shemun, and said, Get thee behind me, Satana, for thou thinkest not that which is of Aloha, but that which is of the sons of men.
B041C008V034	41	8	34	AND Jeshu called to the assemblies with his disciples, and said to them, Whoever will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and come after me.
B041C008V035	41	8	35	For every one who willeth to save his life shall lose it; and every one who shall lose his life on account of me and on account of my gospel, shall save it.
B041C008V036	41	8	36	For what is a man profited, if the whole world he gain, and his soul be lost?
B041C008V037	41	8	37	Or what shall a son of man give (as) the compensation for his soul?
B041C008V038	41	8	38	For whoever shall be ashamed of me and of my words in this generation, sinful and adulterous, the Son of man will also be ashamed of him, when he cometh in the glory of his Father with the holy angels.
B041C009V001	41	9	1	AND he said to them, Amen I say to you, There are some who are standing here, who shall not taste death, until they shall have seen the kingdom of Aloha come with power.
B041C009V002	41	9	2	And after six days Jeshu took Kipha, and Jacub, and Juchanon, and led them up to a high mountain by themselves. And he was altered before their eyes:
B041C009V003	41	9	3	and his raiment shone, and became exceeding white as the snow; as the sons of man on earth could not make white.
B041C009V004	41	9	4	And there were seen with them Musha and Elia discoursing with Jeshu.
B041C009V005	41	9	5	And Kipha said to him, Rabi, it is good for us here to be: and let us make three tabernacles; for thee one, and for Musha one, and for Elia one.
B041C009V006	41	9	6	But he knew not what he said, for they were in fear.
B041C009V007	41	9	7	And there was the cloud, and it shadowed over them: and the voice was from the cloud, saying, This is my Son, the Beloved, him hear.
B041C009V008	41	9	8	And instantly, while the disciples looked, they saw no man, but Jeshu alone with them.
B041C009V009	41	9	9	And while they were descending from the mountain, he charged them to tell no man what they had seen, until the Son of man should have arisen from the dead.
B041C009V010	41	9	10	And they held discourse among themselves, and inquired what was this word, when he should have arisen from among the dead.
B041C009V011	41	9	11	And they asked him, saying, How then say the Sophree that Elia must come before?
B041C009V012	41	9	12	He said to them, Elia doth come before, to restore all things; and how it is written concerning the Son of man, that much he should suffer, and be rejected.
B041C009V013	41	9	13	But I tell you, Elia hath also come, and they have done to him whatever they would, as it is written concerning him.
B041C009V014	41	9	14	AND when he came to his disciples, he saw with them a great crowd, and the Sophree questioning with them.
B041C009V015	41	9	15	And immediately all the crowd saw him, and wondered, and ran to salute him.
B041C009V016	41	9	16	And he inquired of the Sophree, What dispute you with them?
B041C009V017	41	9	17	And one from the company answered and said, Malphona, I had brought my son to thee, because he hath a spirit which speaketh not;
B041C009V018	41	9	18	and when he seizeth him, he dasheth him, and teareth and grindeth his teeth, and he becometh dry. And I spake to thy disciples that they should cast him out, but they could not.
B041C009V019	41	9	19	Jeshu answered, and said to him, O generation that believeth not! how long shall I be with you? how long shall I tolerate you? bring him to me.
B041C009V020	41	9	20	And they brought him unto him: and when the spirit saw him, he immediately dashed him, and he fell upon the ground; and was convulsed, and was torn.
B041C009V021	41	9	21	And Jeshu asked the father, How long is it from the time from which it was thus? He saith to him, Behold, from his childhood.
B041C009V022	41	9	22	And many times he casteth him into the fire, and into the waters, to destroy him: but whatever thou canst, help me, and have mercy upon me.
B041C009V023	41	9	23	Jeshu saith to him, If thou canst believe, every thing can be to him who believeth.
B041C009V024	41	9	24	And in a moment the father of the youth cried out, weeping and saying, I am believing; help the defect of my faith.
B041C009V025	41	9	25	But when Jeshu saw the people running together, and assembling to him, he rebuked the unclean spirit, and said to him, Spirit, deaf and unspeaking! I command thee, come forth from him, and enter not into him again!
B041C009V026	41	9	26	And that devil cried greatly, and crushed him, and went forth. And he became as the dead; as that many would say, He is dead.
B041C009V027	41	9	27	But Jeshu took him by the hand, and raised him.
B041C009V028	41	9	28	But when Jeshu had gone into the house, his disciples inquired of him by themselves, Why could not we cast him out?
B041C009V029	41	9	29	Jeshu said to them, This kind with nothing can be cast out, but by fasting and prayer.
B041C009V030	41	9	30	And when he had gone forth from thence, they passed into Galila: and he was not willing that any man should know of him.
B041C009V031	41	9	31	And he taught his disciples, and told them, That the Son of man would be delivered into the hands of men, and they would kill him; and that when he was slain, on the third day he should arise.
B041C009V032	41	9	32	But they understood not his word, and feared to ask him.
B041C009V033	41	9	33	AND they came to Kapher-nachum: and when they had entered the house, he asked them of what they had argued in the way among themselves.
B041C009V034	41	9	34	But they were silent: for they had contended in the way one with another, who should be greatest among them.
B041C009V035	41	9	35	And Jeshu sat, and he called the twelve, and said to them, Whoever wills to be the first, shall be the last of all, and the servant of all.
B041C009V036	41	9	36	And he took a certain child, and made him stand in the midst: and he took him upon his arms, and said to them,
B041C009V037	41	9	37	Every one who receiveth (one who is) as this child in my name, me he receiveth: and whoever me receiveth, not me he receiveth, but Him who sent me.
B041C009V038	41	9	38	Juchanon said to him, Rabi, we saw a man casting out devils in thy name; and we forbad him, because he did not adhere to us.
B041C009V039	41	9	39	Jeshu saith to them, Forbid him not; for no man who doeth powerful works in my name, can soon speak of me that which is evil.
B041C009V040	41	9	40	He therefore who is not against you is for you.
B041C009V041	41	9	41	For every one who shall give you only a cup of waters to drink in the name that you are of the Meshicha, Amen I say to you, He shall not lose his reward.
B041C009V042	41	9	42	And every one who shall offend one of these little ones who believe in me, it had been better for him that an ass-millstone had been set to his neck, and he had been cast forth into the sea.
B041C009V043	41	9	43	But if thy hand offend thee, cut it off: better for thee mutilated to go into life, than having two hands to go into gihana;
B041C009V044	41	9	44	where their worm dieth not, and their fire is not quenched.
B041C009V045	41	9	45	And if thy foot offend thee, cut it off: better for thee to go into life lame, than having two feet to fall into gihana:
B041C009V046	41	9	46	where their worm dieth not, and their fire is not quenched.
B041C009V047	41	9	47	And if thine eye offend thee, root it out: better for thee that with one eye thou enter the kingdom of Aloha, than having two eyes to fall into the gihana of fire:
B041C009V048	41	9	48	where their worm dieth not, and their fire is not quenched.
B041C009V049	41	9	49	For every (thing) with fire is salted, and every victim with salt shall be salted.
B041C009V050	41	9	50	Good is salt: but if the salt shall (become) insipid, how shall it be salted? Let there be in you salt, and in peace be one with another.
B041C010V001	41	10	1	AND he arose from thence, and came to the borders of Jehud on the other side of the Jurdan: and great multitudes went thither to him; and he taught them again as he was accustomed.
B041C010V002	41	10	2	And the Pharishee drew nigh, tempting him, and demanding whether it were lawful for a man to dismiss his wife.
B041C010V003	41	10	3	He saith to them, What hath Musha prescribed?
B041C010V004	41	10	4	But they say, Musha permitted us to write a writing of dismissal, and to send away.
B041C010V005	41	10	5	Jeshu answered and said to them, On account of the hardness of your heart he wrote for you this commandment.
B041C010V006	41	10	6	But from the beginning the male and the female Aloha made them.
B041C010V007	41	10	7	For this cause a man shall leave his father and his mother,
B041C010V008	41	10	8	and shall cleave unto his wife; and they two shall be one flesh: henceforth they are not two, but one flesh.
B041C010V009	41	10	9	What Aloha therefore hath conjoined, man may not separate.
B041C010V010	41	10	10	And his disciples asked him again in the house concerning this (matter).
B041C010V011	41	10	11	And he said to them, Every one who shall send away his wife, and take another, adulterizeth.
B041C010V012	41	10	12	And if the wife shall leave her husband, and shall become another's, she adulterizeth.
B041C010V013	41	10	13	And they presented unto him children, that he should touch them: but his disciples rebuked those who presented them.
B041C010V014	41	10	14	But Jeshu, when he saw, was displeased, and said to them, Permit the children to come to me, and forbid them not: for of those who are as these is the kingdom of Aloha.
B041C010V015	41	10	15	Amen I say to you, That whoever shall not receive the kingdom of Aloha as a child, shall not enter into it.
B041C010V016	41	10	16	And he took them on his arms, and laid his hand upon them, and blessed them.
B041C010V017	41	10	17	AND as he journeyed in the way, one ran, fell upon his knees, and asked him, saying, Good Teacher, what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?
B041C010V018	41	10	18	Jeshu said to him, Why callest thou me good? none is good but one, Aloha.
B041C010V019	41	10	19	Thou knowest the commandments, Thou shalt not commit adultery, Thou shalt not steal, Thou shalt not kill, Thou shalt not witness false testimony, Thou shalt not injure, Honour thy father and thy mother.
B041C010V020	41	10	20	But he answered and said to him, Malphona, these all have I kept from my childhood.
B041C010V021	41	10	21	And Jeshu beheld him and loved him, and said to him, One thing is wanting to thee: go, sell all whatever thou hast, and give to the poor, and thou shalt have a treasure in heaven: and take up thy cross and come after me.
B041C010V022	41	10	22	But he was grieved at that word, and went away sorrowful: for he had great riches.
B041C010V023	41	10	23	And Jeshu beheld his disciples, and said to them, How hard to those who have riches to enter the kingdom of Aloha!
B041C010V024	41	10	24	But his disciples were astonished at his words. And Jeshu answered again, and said to them, My sons, how hard (is it) for those who trust on their riches to enter into the kingdom of Aloha!
B041C010V025	41	10	25	It is easier for a camel to go through the hole of a needle, than for a rich to enter into the kingdom of Aloha.
B041C010V026	41	10	26	And they were the more astonished, and said among themselves, Who can be saved?
B041C010V027	41	10	27	Jeshu beheld them and said to them, With the sons of men this is not possible, but with Aloha: for every thing is possible with Aloha.
B041C010V028	41	10	28	THEN began Kipha to say, Behold, we have forsaken every thing, and have cleaved to thee.
B041C010V029	41	10	29	Jeshu responded and said, Amen I say to you, There is no man who forsaketh houses, or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or fields, on account of me, and on account of my gospel,
B041C010V030	41	10	30	who shall not receive a hundred-fold now in this time, houses, and brethren, and sisters, and mothers, and children, and fields, with persecution; and in the world which cometh the life that is eternal.
B041C010V031	41	10	31	But many (are) first who will be last, and last (who will be) first.
B041C010V032	41	10	32	Now when they were going up in the way to Urishlem, Jeshu himself preceded them; and they were amazed, and came after him, fearing. And he took his twelve, and began to tell them what it was which was to happen to him.
B041C010V033	41	10	33	Behold, we go up to Urishlem; and the Son of man (will be) betrayed to the chief priests, and to the Sophree; and they shall condemn him to the death, and shall deliver him to the Gentiles;
B041C010V034	41	10	34	and shall mock him, and scourge him, and spit in his face, and kill him: and the third day he shall arise.
B041C010V035	41	10	35	AND Jacub and Juchanon, sons of Zabdai, approached him, saying to him, Malphona, we would that whatever we ask thou wilt do for us.
B041C010V036	41	10	36	He saith to them, What will you that I should do for you?
B041C010V037	41	10	37	They say to him, Give us that one may sit at thy right hand, and one at thy left, in thy glory.
B041C010V038	41	10	38	But he said to them, You know not what you ask: can you drink the cup that I drink? and (with) the baptism that I am baptized (with) can you be baptized?
B041C010V039	41	10	39	They say to him, We can. Jeshu saith to them, The cup that I drink you shall drink; and (with) the baptism that I am baptized (with) you shall be baptized:
B041C010V040	41	10	40	but that you sit on my right hand and on my left, is not mine to give, except for those for whom it is prepared.
B041C010V041	41	10	41	And when the ten heard, they began to murmur against Jacub and Juchanon.
B041C010V042	41	10	42	And Jeshu called them and said to them, You know that they who are considered the princes of the Gentiles are lords of them; and their great ones exercise power over them:
B041C010V043	41	10	43	but not thus shall it be among you. But if any one among you willeth to be great, let him be to you the servant;
B041C010V044	41	10	44	and whoever of you willeth to be the first, he shall be the labourer for all.
B041C010V045	41	10	45	For even the Son of man came not to be served, but to serve, and to give his life the ransom for many.
B041C010V046	41	10	46	And they came unto Jirichu. And as Jeshu went forth from Jirichu, he and his disciples and a great multitude, Timai bar Timai, the blind man, was sitting by the side of the way begging.
B041C010V047	41	10	47	And he heard that it was Jeshu Natsroia; and he began to cry out, and to say, Son of David, have mercy on me!
B041C010V048	41	10	48	And many rebuked him, that he should be silent: but he cried out the more, saying, Son of David, have mercy on me!
B041C010V049	41	10	49	And Jeshu stood, and commanded that they should bring him. And they called the blind man, saying to him, Be of heart, rise, he calleth thee.
B041C010V050	41	10	50	But he, the blind, loosed his garment, and rose up, (and) came to Jeshu.
B041C010V051	41	10	51	Saith to him Jeshu, What wilt thou that I do for thee? And he, the blind, said to him, Rabi, that I may see.
B041C010V052	41	10	52	And Jeshu said to him, SEE: thy faith hath saved thee. And instantly he saw, and he went in the way.
B041C011V001	41	11	1	AND when they drew nigh to Urishlem, against Bethphage and Beth-ania, at the mount of Olives, he sent two from his disciples,
B041C011V002	41	11	2	and said to them, Go to that village which is over against you; and forthwith as you enter it, you will find a colt tied, which no man hath ridden; loose, bring him.
B041C011V003	41	11	3	And if any man shall say to you, Why do you this? say to him, Because for our Lord it is requested, and at once he will send him hither.
B041C011V004	41	11	4	And they went, and found the colt tied at the gate without in the street. And as they were loosing,
B041C011V005	41	11	5	some of those who were standing said to them, What are you doing that you loosen the colt?
B041C011V006	41	11	6	But they said to them as Jeshu had instructed them; and they permitted them.
B041C011V007	41	11	7	And they brought the colt to Jeshu, and threw upon him their garments; and Jeshu rode upon him.
B041C011V008	41	11	8	But many spread their vestments in the way, and others cut branches from the trees and spread them in the way;
B041C011V009	41	11	9	and these who went before him, and these who came after him, cried, saying, Save now!
B041C011V010	41	11	10	and blessed be the coming kingdom of our father David: Save now, in the heights!
B041C011V011	41	11	11	And Jeshu entered Urishlem, into the temple, and surveyed every thing. And when it was the time of the evening, he went forth to Beth-ania with the twelve.
B041C011V012	41	11	12	And the day after, when he went from Beth-ania, he hungered.
B041C011V013	41	11	13	And he saw a certain fig-tree from afar which had leaves on it, and he came to it, if he might find upon it somewhat; but when he came, he found on it only the leaves, for the time was not for figs (to have been ingathered).
B041C011V014	41	11	14	And he said to it, Henceforth and for ever man from thee fruit shall not eat. And his disciples heard.
B041C011V015	41	11	15	And they came to Urishlem. And Jeshu went into the temple of Aloha, and began to cast forth those who sold and bought in the temple, and he overthrew the tables of the money-changers, and the seats of them who sold doves:
B041C011V016	41	11	16	and he would not suffer any man to carry goods through the temple.
B041C011V017	41	11	17	And he taught, and said to them, Is it not written, That my house the house of prayer shall be called of all nations? but you have made it a den of thieves.
B041C011V018	41	11	18	And the chief priests and Sophree heard it, and inquired how they might destroy him; for they feared from him, because all the people admired his doctrine.
B041C011V019	41	11	19	AND when it was evening, they went without from the city.
B041C011V020	41	11	20	And in the morning, while they passed by, they saw that fig-tree that it was dry from its root.
B041C011V021	41	11	21	And Shemun remembered and said to him, Rabi, behold, that fig-tree which thou didst curse hath dried.
B041C011V022	41	11	22	And Jeshu answered and said to them, Let there be in you the faith of Aloha.
B041C011V023	41	11	23	Amen I say to you, That whosoever shall say to this mountain, Be lifted up, and fall into the sea, and shall not be divided in his heart, but shall believe that that thing which he speaketh is, he shall have the thing that he saith.
B041C011V024	41	11	24	On this account I tell you, that every thing whatever you supplicate and ask, believe that you receive, and it shall be unto you.
B041C011V025	41	11	25	And when you stand to pray, forgive whatever you have against any man; and your Father who is in heaven will also forgive you your transgressions.
B041C011V026	41	11	26	But if you do not forgive, your Father who is in heaven will also not forgive you your transgressions.
B041C011V027	41	11	27	And they came again to Urishlem: and as he walked in the temple, the chief priests and the Sophree and the elders came to him,
B041C011V028	41	11	28	and said to him, By what authority these things doest thou? and who gave thee the authority to do them?
B041C011V029	41	11	29	But Jeshu said to them, I also will ask you one word, that you may tell me, and I tell you by what authority I these things do.
B041C011V030	41	11	30	The baptism of Juchanon, from whence was it? from heaven, or from the sons of man? Tell me.
B041C011V031	41	11	31	And they reasoned among themselves, and said, If we say to him, that (it was) from heaven, he saith to us, And why did you not believe him?
B041C011V032	41	11	32	And if we should say, From the sons of man, there is fear from the people; for all have held Juchanon that he was truly a prophet.
B041C011V033	41	11	33	And they answered, saying to Jeshu, We know not. He saith to them, I also do not tell you by what authority I these things do.
B041C012V001	41	12	1	And he began to discourse with them in parables. A certain man planted a vinery, and surrounded it with an enclosure, and dug in it a wine-press, and built in it a tower, and gave it to be held by husbandmen, and journeyed.
B041C012V002	41	12	2	And he sent to the husbandmen his servant in the time to receive the fruits of the vinery.
B041C012V003	41	12	3	But they beat him, and sent him away empty.
B041C012V004	41	12	4	He sent to them again another servant; and also that one they stoned, and bruised him, and sent him away with dishonour.
B041C012V005	41	12	5	And he sent again another, and him they killed; and many other servants he sent, and of them they beat, (and) of them they killed.
B041C012V006	41	12	6	But at last having one son, the beloved, he sent him to them; for he said, Now will they be confounded by my son.
B041C012V007	41	12	7	But those husbandmen said among themselves, This is the heir; come let us kill him, and the inheritance will be ours.
B041C012V008	41	12	8	And they took and killed him, and cast him without from the vinery.
B041C012V009	41	12	9	What therefore shall the Lord of the vinery do? He will come, destroy those labourers, and will give the vinery to others.
B041C012V010	41	12	10	And also that scripture have you not read, The stone which the builders rejected is become the head of the corner?
B041C012V011	41	12	11	from the Lord is this done, and it is wondrous in our eyes.
B041C012V012	41	12	12	And they sought to apprehend him, but feared from the people: for they knew that concerning themselves he had spoken this parable. And he left them, and went.
B041C012V013	41	12	13	And they sent to him men from the Sophree and from the house of Herodes, that they should ensnare him in discourse.
B041C012V014	41	12	14	And they came and questioned him: Malphona, we know that thou art true, and that thou bearest not care for man: for thou regardest not the person of the sons of man, but in truth the way of Aloha thou teachest: Is it lawful to give headmoney to Caesar, or not?
B041C012V015	41	12	15	shall we give, or shall we not give? But he knew their deceit, and said to them, Why do you tempt me? bring me the dinara, (that) I may see it.
B041C012V016	41	12	16	And they brought it to him. He said to them, Of whom (is) this image and writing? And they said, Of Caesar.
B041C012V017	41	12	17	Jeshu said to them, Of Caesar give to Caesar, and of Aloha to Aloha. And they were astonished at him.
B041C012V018	41	12	18	AND the Zadukoyee came to him, those who say that (there is) no resurrection; and they questioned him, saying,
B041C012V019	41	12	19	Malphona, Musha has written for us, That if the brother of a man die, and leave a wife, and leave not children, his brother shall take his wife and raise up seed unto his brother.
B041C012V020	41	12	20	Seven brethren there were. The first took a wife, and died, and left not seed.
B041C012V021	41	12	21	And the second took her, and died, and he also left not seed: and the third likewise.
B041C012V022	41	12	22	And the seven of them took her, and did not leave seed: last of all died also that woman.
B041C012V023	41	12	23	In the resurrection therefore, whose from them shall she be the wife? for the seven of them had her.
B041C012V024	41	12	24	Jeshu saith to them, Do you not on this account err, because you know not the scripture, nor the power of Aloha?
B041C012V025	41	12	25	For when they rise from the dead, they take not wives, neither are wives (given) unto husbands; but as the angels that are in heaven are they.
B041C012V026	41	12	26	But concerning the dead, that they rise: have you not read in the book of Musha, how from the bush Aloha said to him, I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Ishok, and the God of Jacub?
B041C012V027	41	12	27	And Aloha is not of the dead, but of the living. You therefore do greatly err.
B041C012V028	41	12	28	AND one from the Sophree approached and heard how they disputed, and, perceiving that he had well rendered to them the answer, inquired of him, Which is the first commandment of all?
B041C012V029	41	12	29	Jeshu saith to him, The first of all the commandments (is), Hear, Israel, The Lord our Aloha is one Lord:
B041C012V030	41	12	30	and thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind, and with all thy strength: this is the first commandment.
B041C012V031	41	12	31	And the second, which is like it, (is) that thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself. Another commandment greater than these there is not.
B041C012V032	41	12	32	That Sophra said to him, Well, Rabi, and truly hast thou spoken: for One there is and no other than He:
B041C012V033	41	12	33	and that a man love Him with all the heart, and with all the understanding, and with all the soul, and with all the strength, and that he love his neighbour as himself, is better than all burnt-offerings and sacrifices.
B041C012V034	41	12	34	Jeshu, seeing that he had wisely returned the word, answered and said to him, Thou art not far from the kingdom of Aloha. And no man dared again to question him.
B041C012V035	41	12	35	And Jeshu answered and said, while he taught in the temple, How say the Sophree that the Meshicha is son of David?
B041C012V036	41	12	36	For David himself saith by the Spirit of Holiness, The Lord said to my Lord, Sit thou at my right hand, until I set thy adversaries a footstool beneath thy feet.
B041C012V037	41	12	37	David therefore himself calleth him My Lord; and how is he then his son? And all the multitude heard him gladly.
B041C012V038	41	12	38	And in his doctrine he said to them, Beware of the Sophree, who will to walk in long robes, and love the shaloma in public places,
B041C012V039	41	12	39	and the chief seats in the congregations, and the head couches at suppers:
B041C012V040	41	12	40	they who devour the houses of widows, and for the occasion prolong their prayers: they shall receive the greater judgment.
B041C012V041	41	12	41	AND as Jeshu sat before the house of treasure, he beheld how the multitude cast money into the place of treasure; and many rich threw in much.
B041C012V042	41	12	42	And there came a certain poor widow, and threw in two menin, which are a shemona.
B041C012V043	41	12	43	And Jeshu called to his disciples, and said to them, Amen I tell you, That this poor widow more than all the men who throw hath thrown into the house of treasure.
B041C012V044	41	12	44	For all they from what is (super)abundant to them have thrown (in), but this from her deficiency all whatever she had; she hath thrown in her whole possession.
B041C013V001	41	13	1	And as Jeshu went forth from the temple, one of his disciples said to him, Malphona, behold, see those stones and those buildings?
B041C013V002	41	13	2	But Jeshu said to him, Seest thou these great buildings? There will not be left here a stone upon a stone which (will) not be destroyed.
B041C013V003	41	13	3	And while Jeshu sat on the Mount of Olives before the temple, Kipha and Jacub and Juchanon and Andreas asked him by themselves,
B041C013V004	41	13	4	Tell us when (these events) shall be, and what is the sign when these all draw nigh to be accomplished.
B041C013V005	41	13	5	But he, Jeshu, began to say to them, See that no man deceive you.
B041C013V006	41	13	6	For many will come in my name, and will say, I am (He); and many will be deceived.
B041C013V007	41	13	7	But when you hear of battles and the rumour of wars, fear not: for it is that they are to be; but not yet is the end.
B041C013V008	41	13	8	For people shall rise against people, and kingdom against kingdom; and earthquakes will he in various places; and there will be famines and convulsions. These are the beginning of sorrows.
B041C013V009	41	13	9	But look (to) yourselves; for they will deliver you to the judgments; and in their assemblies will they scourge you, and before kings and governors you shall stand on account of their testimony.
B041C013V010	41	13	10	But first will be preached my gospel among all the nations.
B041C013V011	41	13	11	But when they lead you to deliver you up, be not previously anxious what you shall say, nor premeditate; but that, whatever is given you in that hour, that say. For it is not you speaking, but the Spirit of Holiness.
B041C013V012	41	13	12	But the brother will betray his brother to the death, and the father his son; and children will rise up against their fathers, and shall put them to death;
B041C013V013	41	13	13	and you will be hated by all men on account of my name: but he who shall persevere to the end, he shall be saved.
B041C013V014	41	13	14	But when you see the unclean sign of desolation, that which is spoken of by Daniel the prophet, standing where it ought not, (he who readeth, let him understand!) then let those who are in Jehud flee to the mountain
B041C013V015	41	13	15	And he who is upon the roof, let him not descend nor enter in to carry any thing from his house;
B041C013V016	41	13	16	and he who is in the field, let him not turn back to take up his garments.
B041C013V017	41	13	17	But woe to those who are with child, and to those who give suck, in those days!
B041C013V018	41	13	18	But pray that your flight may not be in the winter:
B041C013V019	41	13	19	for in those days shall be affliction such as hath not been from the beginning of the creation which Aloha created, and until now, nor shall be.
B041C013V020	41	13	20	And unless the Lord cut short those days, no flesh would live; but on account of the elect whom he hath chosen, those days he hath cut short.
B041C013V021	41	13	21	Then, if any man shall say to you, Behold, here is the Meshicha! and, Behold, (he is) there! believe not.
B041C013V022	41	13	22	For there will arise false Meshichas and prophets of a lie, and will give forth signs and wonders, to deceive, if possible, the elect also. But you, beware.
B041C013V023	41	13	23	Behold, I have told you every thing before.
B041C013V024	41	13	24	But in those days after that affliction the sun will be darkened, and the moon will not give forth her light,
B041C013V025	41	13	25	and the stars will fall from heaven, and the powers of the heavens will be moved.
B041C013V026	41	13	26	And then will they see the Son of Man coming in the cloud with great power and with glory.
B041C013V027	41	13	27	And then will he send his angels, and will assemble his chosen ones from the four winds, from the extremity of the earth to the extremity of the heavens.
B041C013V028	41	13	28	But from the fig-tree learn a parable. When her branches are tender, and she shoots forth her leaves, you know that the summer draws nigh:
B041C013V029	41	13	29	so also you, when you see that these things are done, understand that it is near, (even) at the door.
B041C013V030	41	13	30	Amen I tell you, That this race shall not pass until these all shall be.
B041C013V031	41	13	31	Heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away.
B041C013V032	41	13	32	But of that day and of that hour man knoweth not, nor the angels of heaven, nor the Son, but only the Father.
B041C013V033	41	13	33	Look: be watchful and pray; for you know not when the time is.
B041C013V034	41	13	34	For as a man who hath journeyed, and left his house, and hath given authority to his servants, and to every man his work, and the door-keeper he hath instructed to be watchful;
B041C013V035	41	13	35	(so) watch you, therefore, because you know not when cometh the Lord of the house,-in the evening, or in the dividing of the night, or at cock-crowing, or in the morning;
B041C013V036	41	13	36	lest he should come suddenly, and find you sleeping.
B041C013V037	41	13	37	But what to you I say, that unto all I say, Be watchful.
B041C014V001	41	14	1	BUT after two days was the Petscha of unleavened cakes: and the chief priests and the Sophree sought how with guile they might apprehend and kill him.
B041C014V002	41	14	2	And they said, Not on the festival, lest there be a commotion among the people.
B041C014V003	41	14	3	And when he was at Bethania in the house of Shemun the leper, as he reclined, there came a woman who had with her a vase of the balsam of the choicest nard of great prices; and she opened it, and poured it upon the head of Jeshu.
B041C014V004	41	14	4	But there were men of the disciples who were displeased among themselves, and said, Why make destruction of this balsam?
B041C014V005	41	14	5	for it could have been sold for more than three hundred dinoreen, and given to the poor. And they were angry with her.
B041C014V006	41	14	6	But he, Jeshu, said, Let her alone; why do you trouble her? A good work hath she wrought upon me.
B041C014V007	41	14	7	For in all time you have the poor with you, and, when you will, you can do them good; but I am not at all time with you.
B041C014V008	41	14	8	(With) that which was hers she hath done this, and beforehand as for the funeral she hath anointed my body.
B041C014V009	41	14	9	And Amen I say to you, That wheresoever my gospel shall be preached in the whole world, this also which she hath now done shall be told in memorial of her.
B041C014V010	41	14	10	But Jihuda Scarjuta, one of the twelve, went to the chief priests, to betray Jeshu to them:
B041C014V011	41	14	11	and they when they had heard rejoiced, and promised silver to give him. And he sought to him opportunity to betray him.
B041C014V012	41	14	12	And the first day of the unleavened bread, in which the Jihudoyee sacrifice the Petscha, the disciples say to him, Where wilt thou that we go to prepare for thee to eat the Petscha?
B041C014V013	41	14	13	And he sent two of his disciples, and said to them, Go to the city, and, observe, a man meeteth you bearing a vessel of waters. Go after him;
B041C014V014	41	14	14	and when he hath entered, say to the house-lord, Our Master saith, Where is the place of feasting, where I can eat with my disciples the Petscha?
B041C014V015	41	14	15	And, behold, he showeth you a large upper room furnished and prepared: there make ready for us.
B041C014V016	41	14	16	And the disciples went forth, and came into the city, and found as he had told them: and they prepared the Petscha.
B041C014V017	41	14	17	And when it was evening he came with his twelve.
B041C014V018	41	14	18	And as they reclined and ate, Jeshu said to them, Amen I tell you, That one of you who eateth with me shall betray me.
B041C014V019	41	14	19	But they began to be sad, and said to him one, one, Is it I?
B041C014V020	41	14	20	But he said to them, One of the twelve who dippeth with me in the dish.
B041C014V021	41	14	21	And the Son of man goeth, as it is written concerning him; but woe to that man by whom is betrayed the Son of man! It had been better for that man if he had not been born.
B041C014V022	41	14	22	And while they were eating, Jeshu took bread, and blessed, and brake, and gave to them, and said to them, Take; this is my body.
B041C014V023	41	14	23	And he took the cup, and praised and blessed, and gave to them; and they drank of it, all of them.
B041C014V024	41	14	24	And he said to them, This is my blood of the new Covenant, which for many is shed.
B041C014V025	41	14	25	Amen I say to you, That again I will not drink from the fruit of the vine till that day in which I will drink it newly in the kingdom of Aloha.
B041C014V026	41	14	26	And they praised, and went forth to the mount of Olives.
B041C014V027	41	14	27	AND Jeshu said to them, All of you will be offended with me in this night: for it is written, I will strike the Shepherd, and scattered shall be his sheep.
B041C014V028	41	14	28	But when I have arisen, I go before you into Galila.
B041C014V029	41	14	29	Kipha saith to him, If all shall be offended with thee, yet I (will) not.
B041C014V030	41	14	30	Jeshu saith to him, Amen I tell thee, That thou, to-day, in this (very) night, before the cock shall crow, three times wilt deny me.
B041C014V031	41	14	31	But he the more said, If I shall die with thee, I will not deny thee, my Lord. And so also all of the disciples said.
B041C014V032	41	14	32	And they came to the place which is called Gedsimon; and he said to his disciples, Sit here until I have prayed.
B041C014V033	41	14	33	And he took with him Kipha and Jacub and Juchanon, and began to be sorrowful and agonized.
B041C014V034	41	14	34	And he said to them, My soul is afflicted unto death; wait for me here, and be watchful.
B041C014V035	41	14	35	And he removed a little, and fell upon the earth, and prayed that, if it were possible, the hour might pass from him.
B041C014V036	41	14	36	And he said, Father, my Father, thou canst (do) every thing, cause to pass from me this cup: but not my will, but thine.
B041C014V037	41	14	37	And he came and found them sleeping: and he said to Kipha, Shemun, dost thou sleep? couldst thou not one hour watch?
B041C014V038	41	14	38	Be wakeful and pray, that you enter not into temptation: the spirit is willing and ready, but the body is infirm.
B041C014V039	41	14	39	And he went again, prayed, and said that word.
B041C014V040	41	14	40	And he turned again, came and found them sleeping, because their eyes were made heavy, and they knew not what to say to him.
B041C014V041	41	14	41	And he came three times (the third time), and said to them, Sleep on, and be at rest. The end approacheth, and the hour cometh, and, behold, the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.
B041C014V042	41	14	42	Arise, we will go; behold, he draweth nigh who betrayeth me.
B041C014V043	41	14	43	And while he was speaking, Jihuda Scarjuta, one of the twelve, came, and with him a multitude with swords and staves, from the chief priests and the Sophree and the elders.
B041C014V044	41	14	44	And the traitor who betrayed had given to them a sign, and said, He whom I shall kiss is He: take him carefully and lead him.
B041C014V045	41	14	45	And immediately he approached, and said to him, Rabi, Rabi, and kissed him.
B041C014V046	41	14	46	Then they laid on him their hands and seized him.
B041C014V047	41	14	47	But one of those who stood drew a sword, and struck the servant of the high priest, and took off his ear.
B041C014V048	41	14	48	But Jeshu answered and said to them, As against a robber are you come out against me, with swords and with staves to apprehend me?
B041C014V049	41	14	49	Every day with you was I teaching in the temple, and ye did not take me; but to fulfil the scriptures this is done.
B041C014V050	41	14	50	Then his disciples forsook him and fled.
B041C014V051	41	14	51	But a certain youth followed him, and he was covered (with) a linen cloth, naked; and they laid hold on him:
B041C014V052	41	14	52	but he left the linen cloth, and escaped naked.
B041C014V053	41	14	53	And they led Jeshu to Kaiapha, chief of the priests: and were gathered together to him all the chief priests and the scribes and the elders.
B041C014V054	41	14	54	But Shemun from afar came after him, until within the court of the chief of the priests: and he sat with the servants, and warmed (himself) at the fire.
B041C014V055	41	14	55	But the chief priests and all the assembly of them sought against Jeshu testimony to put him to death, but they found not.
B041C014V056	41	14	56	For when many bore witness against him, their testimonies were not equal.
B041C014V057	41	14	57	But men rose up against him, witnesses of falsehood, and said,
B041C014V058	41	14	58	We heard him say, I dissolve this temple which is made with hands, and in three days I build another not made with hands.
B041C014V059	41	14	59	But neither so was their testimony equal.
B041C014V060	41	14	60	And the chief of the priests arose in the midst, and questioned Jeshu, and said, Returnest thou no answer? what witness against thee these?
B041C014V061	41	14	61	But Jeshu was silent, and answered him nothing. And again the chief of the priests demanded, and said, Art thou the Meshicha, the Son of the Blessed?
B041C014V062	41	14	62	And he, Jeshu, said to him, I am: and you shall see the Son of man sitting at the right hand of the Power, and coming upon the clouds of heaven.
B041C014V063	41	14	63	Then the chief of the priests tore his robe, and said, Why now seek we witnesses?
B041C014V064	41	14	64	Behold, from his own lips you have heard the blasphemy: how is it seen by you? And they all judged that he was guilty of death.
B041C014V065	41	14	65	And some began to spit on his person, and they struck him on his face, and did buffet him, saying, Prophesy! and the servitors struck him upon his cheeks.
B041C014V066	41	14	66	And Shemun being below in the court, there came a certain damsel of the chief of the priests.
B041C014V067	41	14	67	She saw him as he warmed (himself), and knew him, saying to him, Thou also wast with Jeshu Natsroia.
B041C014V068	41	14	68	But he denied, and said, I know not what thou sayest. And he went without into the vestibule; and the cock crew.
B041C014V069	41	14	69	And again that damsel saw him, and she began to say to those who were standing, This man is also of them.
B041C014V070	41	14	70	But he again denied. And after a little while those who stood said to Kipha, Assuredly thou art from them, for thou art also a Galiloia, and thy speech is similar.
B041C014V071	41	14	71	But he began to imprecate and to swear, I know not this man of whom thou speakest. And in the hour the cock crew the second time.
B041C014V072	41	14	72	And Shemun remembered the word that Jeshu had spoken to him, That before the cock should crow twice, three times thou shalt deny me. And he began to weep.
B041C015V001	41	15	1	AND forthwith in the morning the chief priests with the elders and with the scribes and with the whole congregation made council; and they bound Jeshu, and led him and delivered him to Pilatos the governor.
B041C015V002	41	15	2	And Pilatos asked him, Art thou the King of the Jihudoyee? And he replied and said to him, Thou hast said.
B041C015V003	41	15	3	And the chief priests accused him of many (things):
B041C015V004	41	15	4	but he, Pilatos, asked him again and said to him, Returnest thou not an answer? see how many are witnessing against thee.
B041C015V005	41	15	5	But he, Jeshu, did not give any answer; so that Pilatos admired.
B041C015V006	41	15	6	But he was accustomed at every festival to release to them of the bound one whom they requested;
B041C015V007	41	15	7	and there was one who was called Bar-aba, who was bound with the makers of sedition, they who murder in the sedition had committed.
B041C015V008	41	15	8	And the people cried out and began to demand, that as he was used he would do to them.
B041C015V009	41	15	9	But Pilatos answered and said, Will you that I release to you the King of the Jihudoyee?
B041C015V010	41	15	10	For Pilatos knew that for envy the chief priests had delivered him.
B041C015V011	41	15	11	But the chief priests the more incited the multitude, that Bar-aba he should release to them.
B041C015V012	41	15	12	But he, Pilatos, said to them, What then will you that I do to this, whom ye call King of the Jihudoyee?
B041C015V013	41	15	13	And they again cried, Crucify him!
B041C015V014	41	15	14	Pilatos said to them, Why? what evil hath he done? And they the more exceedingly cried, Crucify him.
B041C015V015	41	15	15	But Pilatos was willing to serve the will of the people, and released to them Bar-aba, and delivered up to them Jeshu, scourged, to be crucified.
B041C015V016	41	15	16	And the soldiers led him into the court which is the praetorium, and called the whole band;
B041C015V017	41	15	17	and they robed him in purple, and twisted and set upon him a crown of thorns,
B041C015V018	41	15	18	and they began to salute him, Hail, King of the Jihudoyee!
B041C015V019	41	15	19	and they struck him upon the head with a cane, and spat in his face, and kneeled upon their knees and worshipped him.
B041C015V020	41	15	20	And when they had mocked him, they stripped him of the purple, and clothed him with his own vestments, and led him forth to crucify him.
B041C015V021	41	15	21	AND they constrained one who was passing, Shemun Kurinoia, who was coming from the field, the father of Alexander and of Rufus, to bear his cross.
B041C015V022	41	15	22	And they brought him to Gogultha, a place which is interpreted A skull.
B041C015V023	41	15	23	And they gave him to drink wine which was mixed with myrrh; but he would not receive.
B041C015V024	41	15	24	And when they had crucified him, they parted his garments, and cast for them lots who should take them.
B041C015V025	41	15	25	And it was the third hour when they crucified him.
B041C015V026	41	15	26	And there was written the occasion of his death in the inscription, This is the King of the Jihudoyee.
B041C015V027	41	15	27	And they crucified with him two thieves, one on his right and one on his left;
B041C015V028	41	15	28	and was accomplished the Scripture which said, That with the wicked he was reckoned.
B041C015V029	41	15	29	AND they also who passed by blasphemed against him, wagging their heads and saying, Ho, undoer of the temple and builder of it in three days,
B041C015V030	41	15	30	deliver thyself and come down from the cross!
B041C015V031	41	15	31	And so also the chief priests laughing one with one, and the Sophree, and saying, Others he saved, himself he cannot save.
B041C015V032	41	15	32	The Meshicha King of Isroel, let him descend now from the cross, that we may see and believe on him; and they also who were crucified with him reviled him.
B041C015V033	41	15	33	AND when it was the sixth hour, there was darkness over all the land until the ninth hour.
B041C015V034	41	15	34	And in the ninth hour Jeshu cried with a high voice and said, Il, Il, Lamona Shabaktoni! Which is, Alohi! Alohi! why hast thou forsaken me?
B041C015V035	41	15	35	And certain who heard, of them who were standing, said, Elia he calleth;
B041C015V036	41	15	36	but one ran and filled a sponge with vinegar, and bound it on a rod that he might drink. And they said, Let alone, we will see if Elia cometh to take him down.
B041C015V037	41	15	37	But he, Jeshu, cried with a high voice, and completed:
B041C015V038	41	15	38	and the veil of the temple was rent in twain from the top to the bottom.
B041C015V039	41	15	39	But when that centurion who stood near him saw that he cried thus, and ended, (he) said, Assuredly this man was the Son of Aloha.
B041C015V040	41	15	40	And there were women from afar who were beholding; Mariam Magdalitha, and Mariam mother of Jacub the less and of Josi, and Shaloom;
B041C015V041	41	15	41	those who, when he was in Galila, adhered to him, and ministered to him, and many others who went up with him to Urishlem.
B041C015V042	41	15	42	AND when it was evening of the preparation which is before the shabath,
B041C015V043	41	15	43	came Jauseph, he who was from Rometha, an honourable counsellor, who also himself waited for the kingdom of Aloha. And he took courage, and went in to Pilatos and requested the body of Jeshu.
B041C015V044	41	15	44	But Pilatos wondered if he were now dead; and he called the centurion and asked him whether before the time he was dead:
B041C015V045	41	15	45	and when he had learned, he gave the body to Jauseph.
B041C015V046	41	15	46	And Jauseph bought linen, and took him down and wrapped him in it, and laid him in a sepulchre which was hewn in the rock, and rolled a stone against the door of the sepulchre.
B041C015V047	41	15	47	But Mariam Magdalitha and Mariam, she who was (the mother) of Josi, beheld where he was laid.
B041C016V001	41	16	1	And when the shabath had passed Mariam Magdalitha and Mariam, (the mother) of Jacub and Shaloom, bought aromatics, and came to anoint him.
B041C016V002	41	16	2	BUT in the morning of the first day in the week, they came to the sepulchre when the sun had risen,
B041C016V003	41	16	3	and they said between themselves, Who will roll away the stone for us from the door of the sepulchre?
B041C016V004	41	16	4	And they looked and saw that the stone was rolled away, for it was very great.
B041C016V005	41	16	5	And they went into the sepulchre, and saw a youth sitting on the right. And he was clothed in a white robe. And they were astonished.
B041C016V006	41	16	6	But he said to them, Fear not! Jeshu Natsroia you seek, he who was crucified, he has risen; he is not here. Behold the place where he lay.
B041C016V007	41	16	7	But go, tell his disciples and Kipha that, behold, he goeth before you into Galila; there shall you see him as he told you.
B041C016V008	41	16	8	And when they had heard, they fled, and went forth from the sepulchre, for astonishment and tremor had seized them; and they said nothing to any one, for they were afraid.
B041C016V009	41	16	9	But in the morning of the first day of the week he arose, and was first seen by Mariam Magdalitha, she who had seven devils cast out from her.
B041C016V010	41	16	10	And she went and declared to them who were with her, who mourned and wept.
B041C016V011	41	16	11	And they, when they had heard what they told, that he lived and had appeared to them, believed them not.
B041C016V012	41	16	12	After these things he appeared to two of them in another fashion as they walked and went to a village.
B041C016V013	41	16	13	And they went and told the rest, neither did they believe.
B041C016V014	41	16	14	BUT afterward he appeared to the eleven as they reclined, and he reproved the littleness of their faith and the hardness of their heart, because those who had seen that he had arisen they had not believed.
B041C016V015	41	16	15	And he said to them, Go into all the world, and proclaim my gospel to every creature:
B041C016V016	41	16	16	He who believeth and is baptized is saved; and he who believeth not is condemned.
B041C016V017	41	16	17	And these signs shall follow those who believe: In my name they shall cast out devils, and with new tongues shall they speak;
B041C016V018	41	16	18	and serpents they shalt take up; and if the poison of death they drink, it shall not hurt them; and their hands shall they lay upon the sick, and they shall be healed.
B041C016V019	41	16	19	But Jeshu our Lord, after he had spoken with them, unto the heavens ascended, and sat on the right hand of Aloha.
B041C016V020	41	16	20	And they went forth and preached in every place, and our Lord helped them, and confirmed their words by the signs which they wrought.
B042C001V001	42	1	1	BECAUSE many have willed to record histories of those transactions of which we are persuaded, according to that which they have delivered to us,
B042C001V002	42	1	2	(they) who from the first were eye-witnesses and ministers of his doctrine;
B042C001V003	42	1	3	it appeared also to me, that having been intimately near to them all, I should record every thing in its order for thee, illustrious Theophile,
B042C001V004	42	1	4	that thou mayest know the truth of those doctrines in which thou hast been instructed.
B042C001V005	42	1	5	THERE was in the days of Herodes, king of the Jihudoyee, a certain priest whose name was Zakaria, of the service of the house of Abia, and his wife (was) of the daughters of Aharun; her name was Elishaba.
B042C001V006	42	1	6	And they were both just before Aloha, and walked in all his commandments, and in the righteousness of the Lord, without blame.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	But they had no son because Elishaba was barren, and both had become many in their days.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	But it was while he was acting-as-priest in the order of his ministry before Aloha,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	according to the custom of the priesthood he came to set on incense, and entered into the temple of the Lord.
B042C001V010	42	1	10	And all the congregation of the people were praying without at the time of incense.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	And there appeared to him, to Zakaria, the angel of the Lord, standing on the right hand of the altar of incense.
B042C001V012	42	1	12	And Zakaria trembled when he saw him, and fear fell upon him.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	And the angel said to him, Fear not, Zakaria, for thy prayer is heard, and thy wife Elishaba shall bear thee a son, and thou shalt call his name Juchanon.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	And to thee shall be joy and exultation, and many shall rejoice in his birth:
B042C001V015	42	1	15	for he shall be great before the Lord, and wine and strong liquor shall he not drink, and with the Spirit of Holiness shall he be filled, from the womb of his mother.
B042C001V016	42	1	16	And many of the sons of Isroel shall he convert to the Lord their Aloha.
B042C001V017	42	1	17	And he shall go before him in the spirit and the power of Elia the prophet, to turn the hearts of the fathers unto the children, and those who believe not to the knowledge of the righteous, and to prepare for the Lord a perfect people.
B042C001V018	42	1	18	And Zakaria said to the angel, How shall I know this? for I am old, and my wife many in her days.
B042C001V019	42	1	19	And the angel answered and said to him, I am Gabriel, I stand before Aloha, and I have been sent to speak with thee and to announce to thee these things.
B042C001V020	42	1	20	From henceforth thou shalt be dumb, and shalt not be able to speak, till the day when these things shall be done, because thou hast not believed these words, which shall be fulfilled in their time.
B042C001V021	42	1	21	But the people were standing, and expecting Zakaria. and were wondering at his delay in the temple.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	But when Zakaria had come forth, he could not speak to them; and he made them understand that he had seen a vision in the temple, and signing he signed to them, and remained dumb.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	And when the days of his service were fulfilled, he came to his house.
B042C001V024	42	1	24	And it was after those days Elishaba his wife conceived, and she secluded herself five months.
B042C001V025	42	1	25	And she said, These things hath the Lord done for me in the days of my desolation, to take away my reproach from among the children of men.
B042C001V026	42	1	26	BUT in the sixth month Gabriel the angel was sent from before Aloha to Galila, to a city whose name (is) Natsrath,
B042C001V027	42	1	27	unto a Virgin espoused to a man whose name was Jauseph, of the house of David, and the name of the Virgin was Mariam.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	And the angel entered to her, and said to her, Peace to thee, full of grace! our Lord is with thee, thou blessed among women!
B042C001V029	42	1	29	But she, when she saw, was troubled at his words, and reasoned what this salutation was.
B042C001V030	42	1	30	And the angel said to her, Fear not, Mariam, for thou hast found favour with Aloha.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	For, behold, thou shalt conceive, and shalt bring forth a son, and thou shalt call his name Jeshu.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	He will be great, and the Son of the Most High shall he be called, and Aloha the Lord shall give unto him the throne of David his father.
B042C001V033	42	1	33	And he shall reign over the house of Jakub for ever, and of his kingdom there shall be no end.
B042C001V034	42	1	34	And Mariam said to the angel, How shall this be, because a man is not known to me?
B042C001V035	42	1	35	The angel answered and said to her, The Spirit of Holiness shall come, and the Power of the Most High shall shadow over thee; on account of this He who (shall be) born from thee is the Holy, and the Son of Aloha shall be called.
B042C001V036	42	1	36	And behold, Elishaba thy kinswoman, she also beareth a son in her old age, and this is the sixth month to her,-to her who is called the barren.
B042C001V037	42	1	37	For nothing is difficult to Aloha.
B042C001V038	42	1	38	And Mariam said, Behold, I am the handmaid of the Lord, be it unto me as thou hast said. And the angel went from her.
B042C001V039	42	1	39	AND Mariam arose in those days, and went with haste to the mountain to a city of Jehud;
B042C001V040	42	1	40	and she entered into the house of Zakaria, and saluted Elishaba.
B042C001V041	42	1	41	And it was that when Elishaba heard the salutation of Mariam, the infant leaped in her womb. And she was filled with the Spirit of Holiness;
B042C001V042	42	1	42	and she cried with a loud voice, and said unto Mariam, Blessed art thou among women, And blessed is the fruit of thy womb!
B042C001V043	42	1	43	Whence unto me is this, That the mother of my Lord should come to me?
B042C001V044	42	1	44	For, lo, as fell the voice of thy salutation on my ears, For great Joy leaped the infant in my womb.
B042C001V045	42	1	45	And happy is she who hath believed, For there is a fulfilment of those things which have been spoken to her from the Lord.
B042C001V046	42	1	46	And Mariam said: My soul doth magnify the Lord,
B042C001V047	42	1	47	And my spirit rejoiceth in Aloha my Saviour,
B042C001V048	42	1	48	Who hath looked upon the lowliness of his handmaid: For, behold, from now all generations shall give blessedness to me.
B042C001V049	42	1	49	Because he hath done for me great things, he who is mighty, And holy is his name.
B042C001V050	42	1	50	And his grace is for ages and generations Upon those who fear him.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	He hath wrought victory with his arm; He hath scattered the proud in the thoughts of their hearts.
B042C001V052	42	1	52	He hath overturned the mighty from their thrones, And hath exalted the humble.
B042C001V053	42	1	53	The hungry he hath satisfied with good things, And the rich he hath sent away empty.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	He hath helped Isroel his servant, And hath remembered his mercy;
B042C001V055	42	1	55	As he spake with our fathers, With Abraham and with his seed for ever.
B042C001V056	42	1	56	And Mariam stayed with Elishaba three months, and returned to her house.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	BUT to Elishaba had come the time that she should give birth, and she gave birth to a son.
B042C001V058	42	1	58	And her neighbours and the sons of her family heard that Aloha had magnified his grace upon her; and they rejoiced with her.
B042C001V059	42	1	59	And it was the eighth day, and they came to circumcise the child; and they called him by the name of his father, Zakaria.
B042C001V060	42	1	60	And his mother answered and said to them, Not so; but he shall be called Juchanon.
B042C001V061	42	1	61	And they said to her, No man in thy kindred is called by this name.
B042C001V062	42	1	62	And they signed to his father (to show) how he willed they should call him.
B042C001V063	42	1	63	And he requested a tablet, and wrote, and said, Juchanan is his name. And every man wondered.
B042C001V064	42	1	64	And immediately his mouth and his tongue were opened, and he spake, and blessed Aloha.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	And there was fear upon all around them; and in all the hill country of Jehud were these things spoken.
B042C001V066	42	1	66	And all who heard reasoned in their hearts, and said, What is this child to be? And the hand of the Lord was with him.
B042C001V067	42	1	67	And Zakaria his father was filled with the Spirit of Holiness, and he prophesied, and said:
B042C001V068	42	1	68	Blessed be the Lord, the Aloha of Israel; For he hath visited his people, and wrought for him redemption,
B042C001V069	42	1	69	And hath raised up for us the horn of redemption In the house of David his servant;
B042C001V070	42	1	70	As he spake by the mouth of his holy prophets, Who have been from of old,
B042C001V071	42	1	71	That we should be delivered from our adversaries, And from the hand of all who hate us;
B042C001V072	42	1	72	To perform his grace with our fathers, And to remember his holy covenant;
B042C001V073	42	1	73	The oath which he sware to Abraham our father,-
B042C001V074	42	1	74	That to us he would grant That, being delivered from the hand of our adversaries, Without fear we might serve before him
B042C001V075	42	1	75	All our days in righteousness.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	And thou, child, the Prophet of the Most High Shalt thou be called; For thou shalt go before the face of the Lord, And thou shalt prepare his way;
B042C001V077	42	1	77	To give the knowledge of salvation to his people In the forgiveness of their sins,
B042C001V078	42	1	78	Through the compassions of the grace of our Aloha; Whereby the morn-splendour shall visit us from on high,
B042C001V079	42	1	79	To illumine those who sit in darkness and the shadow of death. And to direct our feet into the way of peace.
B042C001V080	42	1	80	And the child grew, and was strong in the spirit, and was in the desert till the day of his manifestation unto Isroel.
B042C002V001	42	2	1	NOW it was in those days that there went forth a mandate from Augustus Caesar to enrol the people of his dominion.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	This enrolment was first made under the government of Qurinos in Suria.
B042C002V003	42	2	3	And every man went to be enrolled in his city.
B042C002V004	42	2	4	And Jauseph also went up from Natsrath of Galila, unto Jehud, to the city of David, which is called Beth-lechem, because he was of the house and of the family of David,
B042C002V005	42	2	5	with Mariam his espoused while with child, there to be enrolled.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	And it was that while they were there, the days were fulfilled that she should give birth:
B042C002V007	42	2	7	and she brought forth her son, the first-born, and wrapped him in bandages, and laid him in the manger; because there was no place for them where they stayed.
B042C002V008	42	2	8	But there were shepherds in the country who were staying there, and keeping watch by night over their flocks.
B042C002V009	42	2	9	And, behold, the angel of Aloha came to them, and the glory of the Lord shone upon them; and they feared with great fear.
B042C002V010	42	2	10	And the angel said to them, Fear not; for, behold, I announce to you great joy, which shall be to all people:
B042C002V011	42	2	11	for there is born for you to-day the Redeemer, who is the Lord the Meshicha, in the city of David.
B042C002V012	42	2	12	And this is to you the sign, You shall find the infant wrapped in bandages, and laid in a manger.
B042C002V013	42	2	13	And instantly there were seen with the angel many hosts of the heavens, glorifying Aloha,
B042C002V014	42	2	14	and saying, Glory to Aloha in the heights, and upon earth peace and good hope for the sons of men.
B042C002V015	42	2	15	And when the angels were gone from them into heaven, the shepherds spake one with another, and said, Let us go unto Beth-lechem, and see the thing which the Lord hath made known to us.
B042C002V016	42	2	16	And they came with speed, and found Mariam, and Jauseph, and the infant who was laid in the manger;
B042C002V017	42	2	17	and when they saw, they showed the word which had been spoken to them concerning the child.
B042C002V018	42	2	18	And all who heard wondered at those (things) which were told them by the shepherds.
B042C002V019	42	2	19	But Mariam kept all these words, and compared them in her heart.
B042C002V020	42	2	20	And those shepherds returned, glorifying and praising Aloha for all that they had seen and heard as they had been spoken to them.
B042C002V021	42	2	21	AND when the eight days completed to circumcise the child, his name was called Jeshu, for he was so called by the angel before he was conceived in the womb
B042C002V022	42	2	22	And when were completed, the days of their purification according to the law of Musha, they carried him up to Urishlem, to present him before the Lord:
B042C002V023	42	2	23	(as it is written in the law of the Lord, That every male openeth the matrix the holy to the Lord shall be called:)
B042C002V024	42	2	24	and to offer the sacrifice as it is said in the law of the Lord, A pair of turtle-doves, or two of the young of pigeons.
B042C002V025	42	2	25	But there was a certain man in Urishlem, whose name was Shemun; and this man was just and righteous, and he had waited for the consolation of Isroel, and the Spirit of Holiness was upon him.
B042C002V026	42	2	26	And it was said to him from the Spirit of Holiness, that he should not see death, until he had seen the Meshicha of the Lord.
B042C002V027	42	2	27	Behold, this man came in the Spirit to the temple, and when his parents brought in Jeshu the child, to do for him as it is commanded in the law,
B042C002V028	42	2	28	he took him upon his arms and blessed Aloha, and said,
B042C002V029	42	2	29	Now dismiss thy servant, my Lord, according to thy word, in peace;
B042C002V030	42	2	30	For lo, mine eyes have seen thy grace,
B042C002V031	42	2	31	Which thou hast prepared in the face of all the nations;
B042C002V032	42	2	32	A light for the revelation of the peoples, And the glory of thy people Isroel.
B042C002V033	42	2	33	But Jauseph and his mother wondered at these words which were spoken concerning him.
B042C002V034	42	2	34	And Shemun blessed them, and said to Mariam his mother, Behold, this child is set for the ruin and uprising of many in Isroel, for the sign of contention.
B042C002V035	42	2	35	And through thine own soul shall pass a spear, that may be revealed the reasonings of the hearts of many.
B042C002V036	42	2	36	NOW Chana, the prophetess, (was) the daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Asher; she was aged also in her days, and seven years with her husband had lived from her virginity.
B042C002V037	42	2	37	And she was a widow as of years eighty and four, and she removed not from the temple, and with fasting and with prayer she worshipped in the day and in the night.
B042C002V038	42	2	38	And she also arose in that hour and confessed the Lord, and discoursed concerning him with all who were expecting the redemption of Urishlem.
B042C002V039	42	2	39	And when they had fulfilled every thing according to the law of the Lord, they returned unto Galila, to Natsrath their city.
B042C002V040	42	2	40	But the child grew, and was strengthened in spirit, and was filled with wisdom; and the grace of Aloha was upon him.
B042C002V041	42	2	41	And his relatives every year went unto Urishlem at the feast of Petscha.
B042C002V042	42	2	42	AND when he was a son of twelve years, they went up, as they were used, to the festival.
B042C002V043	42	2	43	And when the days (were) fulfilled, they returned. But Jeshu, the child, remained in Urishlem, and Jauseph and his mother knew not.
B042C002V044	42	2	44	For they thought that he was with the sons of the company; and when they had gone the journey of one day, they sought him with the men and with any who knew him.
B042C002V045	42	2	45	And they found him not: and they returned again to Urishlem, and sought him.
B042C002V046	42	2	46	And after three days they found him in the temple, sitting in the midst of the doctors, hearing them and questioning them.
B042C002V047	42	2	47	And all of them were astonished, as they heard him, at his wisdom and at his answers.
B042C002V048	42	2	48	And when they saw him, they wondered; and his mother said to him, My son, why hast thou done with us thus? for, behold, I and thy father with great anxiety have sought thee.
B042C002V049	42	2	49	He saith to them, Why have you sought me (elsewhere)? Knew you not that (in) the house of my Father it behoveth me to be?
B042C002V050	42	2	50	But they did not comprehend the word that he spake to them.
B042C002V051	42	2	51	And he went down with them, and came to Natsrath, and was subject to them. But his mother kept all these words in her heart.
B042C002V052	42	2	52	But Jeshu increased in his stature, and in his wisdom, and in favour with Aloha and men.
B042C003V001	42	3	1	NOW in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberios Cesar, in the government of Pontios Pilatos in Jehud, Herodes being chief of the Fourth in Galila, and Philipos his brother chief of the Fourth in Ituria and in the region of Trakona, and Lusania chief of the Fourth of Abilini;
B042C003V002	42	3	2	in the high priesthood of Chanan and of Kaiopha, was the word of Aloha unto Juchanon bar Zakaria in the desert.
B042C003V003	42	3	3	And he came into the whole country about the Jurdan, preaching the baptism of repentance for the remission of sins.
B042C003V004	42	3	4	As it is written in the book of the words of Eshaia the prophet, who said, The voice which crieth in the desert, Prepare the way of the Lord, And make straight in the plain the highways for our Aloha.
B042C003V005	42	3	5	All valleys shall be filled, And all mountains and heights be brought low, And the mound shall be a level (place), And the rough place a plain,
B042C003V006	42	3	6	And all flesh shall see the salvation of Aloha.
B042C003V007	42	3	7	And he said to those multitudes who came to him to be baptized, O brood of vipers, who hath showed you to flee from the wrath that cometh?
B042C003V008	42	3	8	Work therefore fruits which are worthy of repentance. And begin not to say within yourselves that Abraham is father to us; for I tell you, that from these stones Aloha is able to raise up sons unto Abraham.
B042C003V009	42	3	9	But, behold, the axe is laid at the root of the trees. Every tree therefore which good fruit maketh not, is cut down and into the fire falleth.
B042C003V010	42	3	10	And the assemblies inquired of him, saying, What then shall we do?
B042C003V011	42	3	11	He answered and said to them, Whoever hath two tunics, let him give to him who hath none; and whoever hath food, so let him do (likewise).
B042C003V012	42	3	12	The publicans also came to be baptized, and they said to him, Malphona, what shall we do?
B042C003V013	42	3	13	But he said to them, Demand not any thing more upon what is prescribed to you to require.
B042C003V014	42	3	14	And the military servants asked of him and said, What shall we also do? And he said to them, Molest no man, oppress no man, and let your wages satisfy you.
B042C003V015	42	3	15	But while the people thought concerning Juchanon, and all of them reasoned in their hearts whether he were the Meshicha,
B042C003V016	42	3	16	Juchanon answered and said to them, Behold, I baptize you with waters, but there cometh after me He who is mightier than I; He, the latchet of whose sandals I am not worthy to unloose; He shall baptize you with the Spirit of Holiness and with fire:
B042C003V017	42	3	17	He who, holding the fan in his hand, and cleansing his floors, gathereth the wheat into his garners, and the chaff he will burn in the fire which is not quenched.
B042C003V018	42	3	18	But many other things he also taught and preached to the people.
B042C003V019	42	3	19	But Herodes Tetrarka, because he was reproved by Juchanon concerning Herodia the wife of Philipos his brother, and concerning all the evil things which he had done,
B042C003V020	42	3	20	added this also upon all, and shut up Juchanon in the house of the chained.
B042C003V021	42	3	21	But it was when he had baptized all the people, and also Jeshu he baptized. And while he prayed,
B042C003V022	42	3	22	the heavens were opened, and the Spirit of Holiness descended upon him in the bodily likeness of a dove: and the voice was from the heavens, which said, Thou art my Son the Beloved One, in thee I have delighted.
B042C003V023	42	3	23	NOW Jeshu himself was as a son of thirty years, and was considered the son of Jauseph bar Heli,
B042C003V024	42	3	24	bar Mattath, bar Levi, bar Malki, bar Jani, bar Jauseph,
B042C003V025	42	3	25	bar Mattha, bar Amuts, bar Nachum, bar Chesli, bar Nagi,
B042C003V026	42	3	26	bar Math, bar Matath, bar Shemri, bar Jauseph, bar Jihuda,
B042C003V027	42	3	27	bar Juchanon, bar Rosa, bar Zurbobel, bar Shelathiel, bar Niri,
B042C003V028	42	3	28	bar Malki, bar Adi, bar Kusam, bar Elmudod, bar Ir,
B042C003V029	42	3	29	bar Jose, bar Eleazar, bar Juram, bar Mathitha, bar Levi,
B042C003V030	42	3	30	bar Shemun, bar Jihuda, bar Jauseph, bar Jonam, bar Eliakim,
B042C003V031	42	3	31	bar Malia, bar Mani, bar Mattha, bar Nathan, bar David,
B042C003V032	42	3	32	bar Jeshi, bar Ubid, bar Boos, bar Salmon, bar Nachshun,
B042C003V033	42	3	33	bar Aminodob, bar Aram, bar Chetsrun, bar Pharets, bar Jihuda,
B042C003V034	42	3	34	bar Jakub, bar Ishok, bar Abraham, bar Tarach, bar Nachur,
B042C003V035	42	3	35	bar Soruk, bar Aru, bar Pholeg, bar Ebor, bar Shaloch,
B042C003V036	42	3	36	bar Kainan, bar Arphakshad, bar Shim, bar Nuch, bar Lamek,
B042C003V037	42	3	37	bar Mathushalach, bar Chanuk, bar Jared, bar Mahloleel, bar Kainan,
B042C003V038	42	3	38	bar Anush, bar Sheth, bar Adom, who was from Aloha.
B042C004V001	42	4	1	BUT Jeshu, being full of the Spirit of Holiness, returned from the Jurdan, and the Spirit led him into the desert,
B042C004V002	42	4	2	to be tempted forty days by the accuser. And he ate nothing in those days; and when they were fulfilled, afterwards he hungered.
B042C004V003	42	4	3	And the accuser said to him, If thou art the Son of Aloha, tell this stone to become bread.
B042C004V004	42	4	4	Jeshu answered and said to him, It is written, It is not by bread alone that the son of man liveth, but by every word of Aloha.
B042C004V005	42	4	5	And Satana carried him up into a high mountain, and showed him all the kingdoms of the earth in a little time.
B042C004V006	42	4	6	And the accuser said to him, To thee will I give all this power and the glory of it, which to me is delivered; and to whomsoever that I will, I give it unto him.
B042C004V007	42	4	7	If therefore thou wilt worship before me, thine shall be all.
B042C004V008	42	4	8	But Jeshu answered and said to him, It is written, That the Lord thy Aloha thou shalt worship, and him only shalt thou serve.
B042C004V009	42	4	9	And he caused him to be at Urishlem, and to stand on the pinnacle of the temple, and said to him, If thou art the Son of Aloha, throw thyself from hence beneath:
B042C004V010	42	4	10	for it is written, His angels he shall charge concerning thee to keep thee,
B042C004V011	42	4	11	and upon their arms to bear thee up, that thou strike not thy foot against a stone.
B042C004V012	42	4	12	But Jeshu answered and said to him, It is spoken, Thou shalt not tempt the Lord thy Aloha.
B042C004V013	42	4	13	And when the accuser had accomplished all his temptations, he removed from him for a time.
B042C004V014	42	4	14	AND Jeshu returned in the power of the Spirit into Galila, and there went forth a report concerning him in all the region about them,
B042C004V015	42	4	15	and he taught in their assemblies, and was glorified of every one.
B042C004V016	42	4	16	And he came to Natsrath where he had grown up; and he went out, as his custom was, into the synagogue on the day of shabath, and he stood up to read.
B042C004V017	42	4	17	And there was given to him the book of Eshaia the prophet, and Jeshu opened the book and found the place where it is written,
B042C004V018	42	4	18	The Spirit of the Lord is upon me, Because he hath anointed me to evangelize to the poor, And hath sent me to heal the contrite in heart, To proclaim to the captives release, And to the blind, vision, And to assure the contrite by remission,
B042C004V019	42	4	19	And to proclaim the year of acceptance of the Lord.
B042C004V020	42	4	20	And he rolled the book, and gave it to the minister, and went and sat down; but the eyes of all them in the synagogue beheld him.
B042C004V021	42	4	21	And he began to say to them, Today is fulfilled this scripture which is in your ears.
B042C004V022	42	4	22	And all witnessed him and wondered at the words of grace which proceeded from his mouth. And they said, Is not this the son of Jauseph?
B042C004V023	42	4	23	Jeshu said to them, You will perhaps say to me this proverb, Physician, heal thyself; and all that we have heard that you have done in Kapher-nachum do also here in your own city.
B042C004V024	42	4	24	But he said, I tell you assuredly, There is no prophet who is received in his (own) city.
B042C004V025	42	4	25	For I say to you the truth, that many widows were in the house of Isroel in the days of Elia the prophet, when the heavens were shut up for three years and six months, and great famine was in all the land;
B042C004V026	42	4	26	and to none of them was Elia sent, but to Sarephath of Tsaidon, unto a woman a widow:
B042C004V027	42	4	27	and many lepers were in the house of Israel, in the days of Elisha the prophet, and not one of them was cleansed only Namon the Aramian.
B042C004V028	42	4	28	And when they heard these things, they who were in the synagogue were all of them filled with anger,
B042C004V029	42	4	29	and they arose, forced him without from the city, and brought him to the brow of the hill on which their city was built to throw him from the rock:
B042C004V030	42	4	30	but he passed through them and went.
B042C004V031	42	4	31	AND he went down to Kapher-nachum, a city of Galila, and instructed them on the shabath.
B042C004V032	42	4	32	And they were astonished at his doctrine, for with power was his word.
B042C004V033	42	4	33	And there was in the synagogue a man who had the spirit of an unclean devil, and he cried with a high voice,
B042C004V034	42	4	34	and said, Leave me, what to us and to thee, Jeshu Natsroia? art thou come to destroy us? I know thee who thou art, the Holy One of Aloha.
B042C004V035	42	4	35	And Jeshu rebuked him, and said, Close thy mouth, and come forth from him. And the devil cast him down in the midst, and came forth from him, and hurt him not any thing.
B042C004V036	42	4	36	And wonder seized on every man, and they spake with each other and said, What thing is this? for with authority and with power he commandeth the unclean spirits, and they go forth.
B042C004V037	42	4	37	And there went out the fame concerning him into all the region which surrounded them.
B042C004V038	42	4	38	And when Jeshu had gone forth from the synagogue, he entered into the house of Shemun; and the mother-in-law of Shemun was afflicted with a great fever, and they besought him on behalf of her;
B042C004V039	42	4	39	and he stood over her and rebuked the fever, and it left her, and she rose up at once and ministered to them.
B042C004V040	42	4	40	But at the setting of the sun all they who had diseased ones, who were diseased with various diseases, brought them to him, and he upon every one of them laid his hand, and healed them.
B042C004V041	42	4	41	And he cast forth also devils from many, (they) crying out, and saying, Thou art the Meshicha, the Son of Aloha. And he rebuked them, and suffered them not to speak, for they knew that he was the Meshicha.
B042C004V042	42	4	42	And at the dawn of day he departed, and went to a desert place; and the people sought him, and came to him, and held him, that he should not go from them:
B042C004V043	42	4	43	but Jeshu said to them, To other cities also must I go to announce the kingdom of Aloha, for concerning this I have been sent.
B042C004V044	42	4	44	And he preached in the synagogues of Galila.
B042C005V001	42	5	1	AND it was while the assembly gathered upon him to hear the word of Aloha, he stood upon the bank of the sea of Genesar;
B042C005V002	42	5	2	and he saw two vessels standing by the sea-side, and the fishermen who had gone up from them, and were washing their nets.
B042C005V003	42	5	3	And one of them was of Shemun Kipha; and Jeshu ascended, sat in it, and directed that they should take it a little from the land into the waters; and he sat, and taught the multitudes from the vessel.
B042C005V004	42	5	4	And when he was silent from his discourses, he said to Shemun, Lead into the deep, and cast forth your nets for a draught.
B042C005V005	42	5	5	Shemun answered and said to him, Rabi, the whole night we have laboured and nothing have we taken; but at thy word I throw the net.
B042C005V006	42	5	6	And when they had this done, they enclosed great multitudes of fishes, and their net brake.
B042C005V007	42	5	7	And they signed to their companions, who were in another vessel, to come and help them. And when they had come, they filled those two vessels, so that they were nigh to be swallowed up.
B042C005V008	42	5	8	But when Shemun Kipha saw, he fell before the feet of Jeshu and said to him, I pray from thee, my Lord, remove thee from me, for I am a man a sinner.
B042C005V009	42	5	9	For amazement had seized him, and all who were with him, on account of the draught of fishes which they had taken.
B042C005V010	42	5	10	Even so also Jacub and Juchanon, sons of Zabdai, who were partners of Shemun. But Jeshu said, Fear not, from henceforth the sons of men shalt thou catch unto life.
B042C005V011	42	5	11	And they brought the vessels to land, and forsook every thing, and went after him.
B042C005V012	42	5	12	AND when Jeshu was in one of the cities, there came a certain man who was wholly filled with leprosy; he saw Jeshu, and fell upon his face, and prayed of him, and said to him, My Lord, if thou art willing, thou canst make me clean.
B042C005V013	42	5	13	And Jeshu extended his hand, touched him, and said to him, I am willing; be clean. And in an instant his leprosy went from him.
B042C005V014	42	5	14	And he commanded him, Tell no man, but go show thyself to the priests, and offer the oblation for thy cleansing, as Musha ordained for their testimony.
B042C005V015	42	5	15	And the fame concerning him went forth the more, and much people were gathered together to hear him and to be healed from their diseases.
B042C005V016	42	5	16	And he passed away into the desert, and prayed.
B042C005V017	42	5	17	And it was on one of the days, while Jeshu was teaching, (certain) Pharishee and doctors of the law were sitting. And they had come from all the villages of Galila and of Jehud, and from Urishlem: and the power of the Lord was (there) to heal them.
B042C005V018	42	5	18	And some brought on a couch a certain man a paralytic; and they sought to enter, that they might set him before him.
B042C005V019	42	5	19	And when they found not how to bring him in because of the multitude of people, they ascended to the house-top, and sent him with his couch from the roof into the midst before Jeshu.
B042C005V020	42	5	20	And when Jeshu saw their faith, he said to the paralytic, Man, forgiven to thee are thy sins.
B042C005V021	42	5	21	And the Sophree and Pharishee began to reason and to say, Who is this who speaketh blasphemy? Who can forgive sins but Aloha only?
B042C005V022	42	5	22	But Jeshu knew their reasoning, and said to them, What reason you in your hearts?
B042C005V023	42	5	23	Which is easier, to say, Forgiven to thee are thy sins; or to say, Arise, walk?
B042C005V024	42	5	24	But that you may know that authority hath the Son of man in the earth to forgive sins,-he saith to the paralytic,-To thee I say, Arise, take up thy couch, and go to thine house.
B042C005V025	42	5	25	And immediately he arose before them, and took up his couch, and went to his house, glorifying Aloha.
B042C005V026	42	5	26	And amazement held every man; and they glorified Aloha, and were filled with fear, saying, We have seen today wonders.
B042C005V027	42	5	27	After these things Jeshu went forth, and saw a tribute-taker, whose name was Levi, sitting at the house of tribute. And he said to him, Come after me:
B042C005V028	42	5	28	and he left every thing, and arose, and went after him.
B042C005V029	42	5	29	And Levi made in his house a great feast; and there was a large company of tribute-takers, and of others that reclined with them.
B042C005V030	42	5	30	And the Sophree and Pharishee murmured, saying to his disciples, Why with tribute-takers and sinners eat you and drink?
B042C005V031	42	5	31	Jeshu answered and said to them, The whole do not require the physician, but they who are grievously ill.
B042C005V032	42	5	32	I am not come to call the just, but the sinners, to repentance.
B042C005V033	42	5	33	But they say to him, Why do the disciples of Juchanon constantly fast, and pray also as the Pharishee, but thine eat and drink?
B042C005V034	42	5	34	But he said to them, How can you make the sons of the chamber fast, while the bridegroom is with them?
B042C005V035	42	5	35	But the days will come when the bridegroom will be taken up from them: then shall they fast in those days.
B042C005V036	42	5	36	He spake to them a parable: No man cutteth a piece from a new material, and fasteneth it upon an old garment; lest he rend the new, without completing the old with the piece that is new.
B042C005V037	42	5	37	And no man poureth new wine into old bottles; lest the new wine burst forth, and the wine be shed, and the bottles perish.
B042C005V038	42	5	38	But they pour new wine into new bottles, and both are preserved.
B042C005V039	42	5	39	And no man, drinking old wine, immediately asketh new: for he saith, The old is softer.
B042C006V001	42	6	1	IT was on the shabath, while Jeshu was walking among the corn, and his disciples gathered the ears, and rubbed in their hands and ate (them).
B042C006V002	42	6	2	But some of the Pharishee said to them, Why do you a thing which it is not lawful on the shabuth to do?
B042C006V003	42	6	3	Jeshu answered and said to them, And this have you not read, what David did when he hungered, and they who were with him?
B042C006V004	42	6	4	that he went into the house of Aloha, and the bread of the table of the Lord he took, ate, and gave to them who were with him, that (bread) which was not lawful to eat, except by the priests only?
B042C006V005	42	6	5	And he said to them, That the Lord of the shabath is the Son of man.
B042C006V006	42	6	6	And it was on another shabath (that) he entered into the synagogue, and taught. And there was a man whose right hand was dried:
B042C006V007	42	6	7	and the Sophree and Pharishee watched him, if he would heal on the shabath, that they might accuse him.
B042C006V008	42	6	8	But he knew their thoughts, and said to the man whose hand was dried, Rise (and) come into the midst of the assembly.
B042C006V009	42	6	9	And when he had come and stood, Jeshu said to them, I ask you which is lawful to do on the shabath, good or evil, life to save or to destroy?
B042C006V010	42	6	10	And he beheld them all, and said to him, Stretch forth thine hand: and he stretched it forth, and his hand was restored as its fellow.
B042C006V011	42	6	11	But they were filled with envy, and spake one with another what they should do with Jeshu.
B042C006V012	42	6	12	BUT it was in those days that Jeshu went forth into a mountain to pray; and there remained he all night in the prayer of Aloha.
B042C006V013	42	6	13	And when the day brake, he called his disciples, and chose from them twelve, those whom he named Apostles,
B042C006V014	42	6	14	Shemun, he whose name was Kipha, and Andreas his brother, and Jacub, and Juchanon, and Philipos, and Bar Tholmai,
B042C006V015	42	6	15	and Mathai, and Thoma, and Jakub bar Chalphai, and Shemun who was called the Zealous,
B042C006V016	42	6	16	and Jihuda bar Jakub, and Jihuda Scaruta, he who was the traitor.
B042C006V017	42	6	17	And Jeshu descended with them, and stood in the plain, and a great assembly of his disciples and a multitude of people from all Jehud, and from Urishlem, and from the sea-coast of Tsur and Tsaidon,
B042C006V018	42	6	18	who had come to hear his words, and to be healed of their diseases; and they who were vexed by unclean spirits, and they were healed.
B042C006V019	42	6	19	And all the multitudes sought to approach to him, for the power went forth from him, and all of them he healed.
B042C006V020	42	6	20	AND he lifted up his eyes upon his disciples, and said, Blessed are you poor, for yours is the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C006V021	42	6	21	Blessed are you who hunger now, for you shall be satisfied. Blessed are you who weep now, for you shall laugh.
B042C006V022	42	6	22	Blessed are you when the sons of man hate you, and separate you, and revile you, and cast out your name as evil, for the sake of the Son of man.
B042C006V023	42	6	23	Rejoice in that day, and exult, for your reward is great in heaven; for thus did they to your fathers the prophets.
B042C006V024	42	6	24	But woe to you (who are) rich, because you have received your consolation.
B042C006V025	42	6	25	Woe to you (who are) full, for you shall hunger. Woe to you who laugh now, for you shall weep and lament.
B042C006V026	42	6	26	Woe to you when the sons of men shall speak well of you, for so did to the prophets of falsity their fathers.
B042C006V027	42	6	27	But I say to you who hear, Love your adversaries, and do good to those who hate you,
B042C006V028	42	6	28	and bless those who execrate you, and pray for those who lead you by violence.
B042C006V029	42	6	29	And to one who striketh you on your cheek, offer to him the other: and whosoever taketh your cloak, forbid him not your coat also.
B042C006V030	42	6	30	To every one who asketh of you give; and from him who taketh of yours demand not (again).
B042C006V031	42	6	31	And as you will that the sons of man should do to you, so do you also to them.
B042C006V032	42	6	32	For if you love them who love you, what is your grace? for sinners also love those who love them.
B042C006V033	42	6	33	And if you do good to those who benefit you, what is your grace? for the sinners also thus do.
B042C006V034	42	6	34	And if you lend to them from whom you expect to be recompensed, what is your grace? for sinners also lend to sinners, that they might be profited.
B042C006V035	42	6	35	But love your adversaries, and do good to them, and lend, and cut not off the hope of any one; and great shall be your reward, and you shall be the children of the Most High; for he is benign to the evil and to the ungrateful.
B042C006V036	42	6	36	Be you therefore merciful, as also your Father is merciful.
B042C006V037	42	6	37	JUDGE not, and you shall not be judged; condemn not, and you shall not be condemned; release, and you shall be released;
B042C006V038	42	6	38	give, and it shall be given to you; in good measure, compressed, redundant, shall they pour into your bosoms. For in that measure you mete, it shall be measured to you.
B042C006V039	42	6	39	And he spake to them a parable: How can the blind lead the blind, and not fall into the ditch?
B042C006V040	42	6	40	The disciple than his master is not greater; but every man who is perfect shall be as his master.
B042C006V041	42	6	41	For why behold you the rod that is in the eye of your brother, but the rafter in your (own) eye is not seen by you?
B042C006V042	42	6	42	Or how can you say to your brother, My brother, permit (that) I pull out the rod that is in your eye, and behold the rafter in your own eye is not seen by you? Hypocrite! first take out the rafter from your own eye, and then shall you see to take out the rod that is in the eye of your brother.
B042C006V043	42	6	43	A good tree maketh not evil fruits; also an evil tree maketh not good fruits:
B042C006V044	42	6	44	for every tree by its fruits is known. For how gather they from thorns figs? neither also from the bramble do they gather in grapes.
B042C006V045	42	6	45	The good man, from the good treasures which are in his heart, bringeth forth good things; and the evil man, from the evil treasures which are in his heart, bringeth forth evil things; for from the adundancies of the heart the lips speak.
B042C006V046	42	6	46	Why call you me, My Lord, my Lord, and the things which I say do not?
B042C006V047	42	6	47	Every man who cometh to me and heareth my words, and doeth them, I will show you to whom he is like.
B042C006V048	42	6	48	He is like a man who built a house, and digged deep, and laid the foundations upon the rock: but when there was an inundation, the inundation beat against that house, and it could not shake it, for its foundations were set upon a rock.
B042C006V049	42	6	49	And he who heareth and doeth not, is like a man who built his house upon the dust, without a foundation: and when the river beat against it, it immediately fell, and the ruin was great of that house.
B042C007V001	42	7	1	AND when he had finished all these words in the hearing of the people, Jeshu entered into Kapher-nachum.
B042C007V002	42	7	2	But the servant of a certain centurion, who was valued by him, was sick, and nigh unto dying.
B042C007V003	42	7	3	And he heard of Jeshu, and sent to him the elders of the Jihudoyee, and besought him to come (and) save his servant.
B042C007V004	42	7	4	And they, when they came to Jeshu, besought of him earnestly, saying, He is worthy that thou do this for him;
B042C007V005	42	7	5	for he loveth our people, and also a synagogue he hath built for us.
B042C007V006	42	7	6	And Jeshu went with them. But when he was not greatly distant from the house, the centurion sent to him his friends, saying to him, My Lord, labour not, for I am not worthy that thou shouldst enter beneath my roof.
B042C007V007	42	7	7	Wherefore I was not worthy to come to thee; but speak by a word, and my youth shall be healed.
B042C007V008	42	7	8	For I also am a man who am subjected under authority; and there are under my hand soldiers, and I say to this one, Go, and he goeth; and to another, Come, and he cometh; and to my servant, Do this, and he doeth.
B042C007V009	42	7	9	Now when Jeshu heard these (words), he admired, and turned and said to the company who came after him, I tell you, that not also in the house of Isroel have I found faith like this.
B042C007V010	42	7	10	And they who had been sent, returned to the house, and found the servant who had been sick now well.
B042C007V011	42	7	11	AND it was the day after, that he went to a city whose name was Nain, and his disciples with him, and a great multitude.
B042C007V012	42	7	12	And as he approached the gate of the city, he saw (them) following (one) dead, who was the only born of his mother, and she his mother was a widow: and a great multitude of the people of the city were with her.
B042C007V013	42	7	13	And Jeshu beheld her, and had compassion upon her, and said to her, Weep not.
B042C007V014	42	7	14	And he went and touched the bier; and they who were carrying it stood. And he said, Young man, to thee I say, Arise.
B042C007V015	42	7	15	And the dead sat up, and began to speak. And he gave him to his mother.
B042C007V016	42	7	16	And fear seized all men; and they glorified Aloha, saying, A great prophet hath arisen among us, and Aloha hath visited his people.
B042C007V017	42	7	17	And this word concerning him went forth into all Jihud, and into the whole region around them.
B042C007V018	42	7	18	And the disciples of Juchanon showed him all these.
B042C007V019	42	7	19	AND Juchanon called two from his disciples,
B042C007V020	42	7	20	and sent them to Jeshu, saying, Art thou He who cometh! or another should we expect?
B042C007V021	42	7	21	But in that very hour he healed many from diseases, and from plagues, and from evil spirits; and to many blind he gave to see.
B042C007V022	42	7	22	And Jeshu answered and said to them, Go tell Juchanon every thing you have seen and heard: that the blind see, and the lame walk, and the lepers are cleansed, and the deaf hear, and the dead arise, and the poor are evangelized;
B042C007V023	42	7	23	and blessed is he whosoever is not offended in me.
B042C007V024	42	7	24	But when the disciples of Juchanon were gone, Jeshu began to speak to the people concerning Juchanon: What went you forth into the wilderness to see? a reed from the wind shaken?
B042C007V025	42	7	25	If not, what went you forth to see? a man clothed in soft raiment? Behold, they who are clothed in bright vestments, and are (living) in pleasures, are in the house of kings.
B042C007V026	42	7	26	If not, what went you forth to see? a prophet? Yes, I tell you, and more than a prophet:
B042C007V027	42	7	27	he, concerning whom it is written, Behold, I send mine angel before thy face, Who shall prepare the way before thee.
B042C007V028	42	7	28	I tell you, that no prophet among those born of women (hath been) greater than Juchanon the Baptizer. Yet the least in the kingdom of Aloha is greater than he.
B042C007V029	42	7	29	(And all the people that heard him, and the tribute-gatherers also, justified Aloha, because they were baptized with the baptism of Juchanon.
B042C007V030	42	7	30	But the Pharishee and Sophree rejected against themselves the will of Aloha, because they were not baptized of him.)
B042C007V031	42	7	31	With what therefore shall I compare the men of this generation, and to what are they like?
B042C007V032	42	7	32	They are like children sitting in the public place, and crying to their companions, and saying, We have sung to you, and you have not danced; we have wailed to you, and you have not wept.
B042C007V033	42	7	33	For Juchanon the Baptizer came, neither eating bread nor drinking wine, and you say, A devil is in him.
B042C007V034	42	7	34	The Son of man came eating and drinking, and you say, Behold a man a devourer and a drinker of wine, and a friend of tribute-takers and of sinners!
B042C007V035	42	7	35	But justified is wisdom of her sons.
B042C007V036	42	7	36	NOW there came one of the Pharishee requesting of him to eat with him: and he entered into the house of the Pharisha, and reclined.
B042C007V037	42	7	37	And a woman, a sinner, was in that city; and when she knew that in the house of the Pharisha he reclined, she took a vase of ointment,
B042C007V038	42	7	38	and stood behind him at his feet and wept, and began with her tears to bedrop his feet, and with the hair of her head to wipe them, and she kissed his feet, and anointed (them) with the ointment.
B042C007V039	42	7	39	But when the Pharisha who had invited him saw (this), he thought within himself and said, Were this a prophet, he would know who this is and what is her report, for this woman is a sinner who toucheth him.
B042C007V040	42	7	40	But Jeshu answered and said to him, Shemun, I have somewhat to say to thee. He said to him, Say, Rabi.
B042C007V041	42	7	41	Jeshu said to him, A certain creditor had two debtors: the one owed him five hundred dinoree, and the other fifty dinoree.
B042C007V042	42	7	42	And when they had nothing to pay, he forgave them both. Which, therefore, of them the most would love him?
B042C007V043	42	7	43	Shemun answered and said, I think he to whom much was forgiven. Jeshu said to him, Thou hast judged rightly.
B042C007V044	42	7	44	And he turned to that woman, and said to Shemun, Thou seest this woman: I entered thy house; waters for my feet thou gavest me not; but this with her tears hath bedropped my feet, and with her hair hath wiped them.
B042C007V045	42	7	45	Thou didst not kiss me; but, behold, this from (the time) I entered hath not ceased my feet to kiss.
B042C007V046	42	7	46	Thou with ointment my feet didst not anoint, but this with ointment of balsam my feet hath anointed.
B042C007V047	42	7	47	Therefore I tell thee, That forgiven to her are her many sins, because she hath loved much. For he to whom little is forgiven, little loveth.
B042C007V048	42	7	48	And he said to her, Woman, forgiven to thee (are) thy sins.
B042C007V049	42	7	49	But they who reclined said among themselves, Who is this who also sins forgiveth?
B042C007V050	42	7	50	But Jeshu said to that woman, Thy faith hath saved thee; go in peace.
B042C008V001	42	8	1	AND it was after these things that Jeshu itinerated among the cities and villages, and preached and announced the kingdom of Aloha, and his twelve with him,
B042C008V002	42	8	2	and those women who had been healed from infirmities and from evil spirits, Mariam who was called Magdalitha, she from whom he had cast out seven devils,
B042C008V003	42	8	3	and Juchana the wife of Kusa, chief of the household of Herodes, and Shushan, and many others, who ministered unto him from their possessions.
B042C008V004	42	8	4	And when a great multitude had assembled, and from all the cities had come to him, he discoursed in parables.
B042C008V005	42	8	5	A sower went forth to sow his seed. And as he sowed, some fell by the road-side; and it was trodden down, and the fowl devoured it.
B042C008V006	42	8	6	And other fell upon the rock; and it immediately sprang up, and, because it had no moisture, it withered.
B042C008V007	42	8	7	And other fell among thorns, and they sprang up with it, and choked it.
B042C008V008	42	8	8	And other fell into ground good and fair, and sprang up, and made fruit an hundredfold. And when he had said these (words), he cried, Whoever hath ears to hear, let him hear.
B042C008V009	42	8	9	And his disciples asked him, What is (the signification of) this parable?
B042C008V010	42	8	10	But he said to them, To you it is given to know the mysteries of the kingdom of Aloha; but to those who are the rest in similitudes is it spoken; that while seeing they may not see, and while hearing they may not understand.
B042C008V011	42	8	11	But this is the parable: The seed is the word of Aloha.
B042C008V012	42	8	12	Now they by the road-side are they who hear the word; and the adversary cometh, and taketh up the word from their hearts, that they should not believe and be saved.
B042C008V013	42	8	13	But those who fell upon the rock are those who, when they hear, with joy receive the word; yet root they have not, but for a time is their faith, and in the time of temptation they are offended.
B042C008V014	42	8	14	But that which fell among thorns are they who hear the word, and by the cares, and by the riches, and by the lusts of the world, they are choked, and fruit they give not.
B042C008V015	42	8	15	But that which (was) in good ground are they who, with hearts humble and good, hear the word and retain, and give fruits with perseverance.
B042C008V016	42	8	16	NO man lighteth a lamp, and covereth it with a measure, or setteth it under a bed; but setteth it upon a candlestick, that every one who cometh in may see the light of it.
B042C008V017	42	8	17	For there is nothing hidden which shall not be revealed, and nothing secret that shall not be known and come into openness.
B042C008V018	42	8	18	Take heed how you hear: for unto him who hath, it shall be given; and from him who hath not, that also which he thinketh that he hath shall be taken from him.
B042C008V019	42	8	19	Now came to him his mother and his brethren, and could not speak with him on account of the assembly.
B042C008V020	42	8	20	And they said to him, Thy mother and thy brethren are standing without, desiring to see thee.
B042C008V021	42	8	21	But he answered and said to them, These are my mother and my brethren, they who hear the word of Aloha, and do it.
B042C008V022	42	8	22	NOW it was on one of the days that Jeshu ascended and sat in a vessel and his disciples: and he said to them, Let us pass to the other side of the water.
B042C008V023	42	8	23	But as they went, Jeshu himself slept. And there became a storm of wind on the water, and nigh was the vessel to be swallowed up.
B042C008V024	42	8	24	And they approached (and) awoke him, saying to him, Our master, our master, we perish! But he arose and rebuked the winds and the waves of the sea; and they quieted, and there was a calm.
B042C008V025	42	8	25	And he said to them, Where is your faith? But they, afraid, wondered, saying one with another, Who is this that also commandeth the winds, and to whom the waves and the sea are obedient?
B042C008V026	42	8	26	And they went forward and came to the country of the Godroyee, which is over against Galila.
B042C008V027	42	8	27	And when he had gone forth to the land, there met him a certain man from the city, who had a devil in him a great time, and (who) wore no clothes, and in a house dwelt not, but in the place of the buried.
B042C008V028	42	8	28	But when he saw Jeshu, he cried out, and fell before him, and said in a high voice, What to us and to thee, Jeshu, son of Aloha Marima? I beseech of thee, torment me not.
B042C008V029	42	8	29	For Jeshu commanded the unclean spirit to come forth from the man. For long was the time that he had been enthralled of him; and (when) bound with chains, and kept with fetters, he had burst asunder his bonds, and had been driven by the demon into the waste.
B042C008V030	42	8	30	And Jeshu demanded of him, What is thy name? He saith to him, Legion: because that many devils had entered into him.
B042C008V031	42	8	31	And they besought from him that he would not cast them out to go into the abyss.
B042C008V032	42	8	32	Now there was there a great herd of many swine which fed on the hill: and they besought from him that he would permit them to enter into the swine. And he permitted them.
B042C008V033	42	8	33	And the demons went forth from the man, and entered into the swine; and the whole herd went directly to the precipice, and plunged into the waters, and were suffocated.
B042C008V034	42	8	34	And when the herdmen saw the thing that was done, they fled, and made known in the city and in the villages.
B042C008V035	42	8	35	And the men went forth to see the thing which was done. And they came to Jeshu, and found the man from whom the demons had gone out, clothed, sober, and sitting at the feet of Jeshu. And they feared.
B042C008V036	42	8	36	And they who had seen it showed to them how the man of the demon had been healed.
B042C008V037	42	8	37	And the whole multitude of the Godroyee besought of Jeshu that he would go from them, because great fear had taken them. And he, Jeshu, ascended the ship, and returned from them.
B042C008V038	42	8	38	But he, the man from whom had gone forth the demons, besought of him that he might be with him. But Jeshu dismissed him, and said to him,
B042C008V039	42	8	39	Return to thine house, and show what Aloha hath done for thee. And he went and proclaimed in every city what Jeshu had done for him.
B042C008V040	42	8	40	WHEN Jeshu returned, a great multitude received him: for they were all expecting him.
B042C008V041	42	8	41	And a certain man whose name was Jorush, head of the synagogue, fell before the feet of Jeshu, and besought him to enter into his house;
B042C008V042	42	8	42	for he had an only daughter, as a daughter of twelve years, and she was nigh unto death. And as Jeshu went with him, the great multitude pressed him.
B042C008V043	42	8	43	And a certain woman whose blood had gushed forth twelve years, she who among the physicians had spent all her substance, but could not be healed by any one,
B042C008V044	42	8	44	approached him from behind, and touched the border of his garment, and immediately stood the flowing of her blood.
B042C008V045	42	8	45	And Jeshu said, Who touched me? And when all denied, Shemun Kipha and those with him said, Raban, the crowd straiteneth and presseth thee, and sayest thou, Who touched me?
B042C008V046	42	8	46	But he said, Some one hath touched me, for I know that power hath gone forth from me.
B042C008V047	42	8	47	And she, the woman, when she saw that she was not hid, came trembling and fell (and) worshipped him. And she told before all the people for what cause she had touched him, and how at once she had been healed.
B042C008V048	42	8	48	But he, Jeshu, said to her, Be comforted, my daughter: thy faith hath saved thee, go in peace.
B042C008V049	42	8	49	And while he was speaking, there came a man from the chief of the synagogue and said to him, Thy daughter is dead, weary not the Malphona.
B042C008V050	42	8	50	But Jeshu heard, and said to the father of the damsel, Fear not, only believe, and she lives!
B042C008V051	42	8	51	But Jeshu came to the house, and he suffered no man to enter with him, save Shemun, and Jakub, and Juchanon, and the father of the damsel, and her mother.
B042C008V052	42	8	52	And they were all weeping and wailing for her; but Jeshu said, Weep not, for she is not dead, but asleep.
B042C008V053	42	8	53	And they laughed at him, for they knew that she was dead.
B042C008V054	42	8	54	But he put every man forth without. And he took her by the hand, and called and said, Damsel, arise.
B042C008V055	42	8	55	And her spirit returned, and she arose. And he directed that they should give her to eat.
B042C008V056	42	8	56	And her parents were astonished; but he cautioned them that no man they should tell what he had done.
B042C009V001	42	9	1	AND Jeshu called his twelve, and gave them power and authority over all demons and diseases, to heal.
B042C009V002	42	9	2	And he sent them to proclaim the kingdom of Aloha, and to heal the diseased.
B042C009V003	42	9	3	And he said to them, Take nothing for the way, neither staff, nor bag, nor bread, nor silver; nor two tunics shall you have.
B042C009V004	42	9	4	And into whatever house you enter, there be, and from thence go forth.
B042C009V005	42	9	5	And whoever will not receive you, when you depart from that city the dust also from your feet shake off as a testimony against them.
B042C009V006	42	9	6	And the apostles went forth and itinerated in the villages and the cities, and evangelized and healed in every place.
B042C009V007	42	9	7	But Herodes, Tetrarka, heard all that was done by his hand, and was astonished; for men said that Juchanon had risen from the house of the dead.
B042C009V008	42	9	8	But others said that Elia had appeared, and others that a prophet from the former prophets had risen.
B042C009V009	42	9	9	And Herodes said, The head of Juchanon I have cut off; but who is this of whom I hear these (things)? And he willed to see him.
B042C009V010	42	9	10	And when the apostles returned, they showed Jeshu all that they had done. And he took them by themselves to a desert place of Bethtsaida.
B042C009V011	42	9	11	But the multitudes, when they knew it, went after him, and he received them, and discoursed to them concerning the kingdom of Aloha. And those who had need of healing he healed.
B042C009V012	42	9	12	BUT when the day began to decline, the disciples drew near and said to him, Send away the multitudes, that they may go to the villages and hamlets that are around, to lodge in them and to find for themselves victuals, because we are in a desert place.
B042C009V013	42	9	13	Jeshu said to them, Give you them to eat. But they said, We have nothing more than five loaves and two fishes, unless we go and buy food for all this people:
B042C009V014	42	9	14	for they were about five thousand men. Jeshu said to them, Make them recline in reclining companies, fifty men in a company.
B042C009V015	42	9	15	And the disciples did so. And they all reclined.
B042C009V016	42	9	16	And Jeshu took those five loaves and two fishes, and looked up to heaven and blessed and brake and gave to his disciples, that they should set before the multitude.
B042C009V017	42	9	17	And all did eat and were filled. And they took up fragments which abounded, twelve baskets.
B042C009V018	42	9	18	AND as he was praying alone, and his disciples with him, he asked them and said, What say concerning me the multitude, that I am?
B042C009V019	42	9	19	They answered and say to him, Juchanon the Baptizer; and others that (thou art) Elia; but others that a prophet from the former prophets hath arisen.
B042C009V020	42	9	20	He saith to them, But what do you say that I am? Shemun answered and said, The Meshicha of Aloha!
B042C009V021	42	9	21	But he forbade them and cautioned them that this they should tell no man.
B042C009V022	42	9	22	And he told them how it was to be (that) he the Son of man should suffer many things and be rejected by the elders and the chief priests and Sophree, and (that) they would kill him; and that on the third day he would arise.
B042C009V023	42	9	23	And he said before all, Whoever willeth to come after me, must deny himself, and take up his cross daily, and come after me.
B042C009V024	42	9	24	For whoever willeth to save his life, loseth it; but whoever (is willing) to lose his life, for my sake, he saveth it.
B042C009V025	42	9	25	For what is helped a son of man, if he shall gain the whole world and lose his soul, or perish?
B042C009V026	42	9	26	For whoever shall be ashamed of me and of my words, the Son of man will be ashamed of him, when he cometh in the glory of his Father with the holy angels.
B042C009V027	42	9	27	THE truth I say to you, that some who are standing here shall not taste death, until they have seen the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C009V028	42	9	28	And it was after these words about eight days, that Jeshu took Shemun and Jakub and Juchanon, and went up into a mountain to pray.
B042C009V029	42	9	29	And while he prayed, the appearance of his countenance was changed, and his garments became white and shone.
B042C009V030	42	9	30	And, behold, two men talked with him, who were Musha and Elia,
B042C009V031	42	9	31	who appeared in glory; but they spake concerning his going forth which should be accomplished at Urishlem.
B042C009V032	42	9	32	And Shemun, and they who were with him, had been heavy with sleep, and were scarcely awaked when they saw his glory and those two men who stood with him.
B042C009V033	42	9	33	And when they began to depart from him, Shemun said to Jeshu, Rabi, it is good for us to be here: and let us make three tabernacles; for thee one, and for Musha one, and for Elia one. But he knew not what he said.
B042C009V034	42	9	34	And as he spoke these (words) there was a cloud which shadowed over them, and they feared when they saw that Musha and Elia entered into the cloud.i
B042C009V035	42	9	35	And the voice was from the cloud, saying, This is my Son, the Beloved, Him hear.
B042C009V036	42	9	36	And when the voice had been, Jeshu was found alone. And they were silent, and told no man in those days what they had seen.
B042C009V037	42	9	37	AND the day after when they had descended from the mountain, a great multitude met them.
B042C009V038	42	9	38	And a certain man from the multitude cried and said, Malphona, I beseech thee, turn unto me; (there is) my son, my only one,
B042C009V039	42	9	39	and a spirit passeth upon him, and he suddenly crieth, and gnasheth his teeth, and lacerateth, and hardly removeth from him when he hath bruised him.
B042C009V040	42	9	40	And I besought thy disciples to cast him out, but they could not.
B042C009V041	42	9	41	Then Jeshu answered and said, Ah generation unbelieving and perverse! how long shall I be with you and bear with you? Bring thy son hither.
B042C009V042	42	9	42	And as they brought him near, the devil cast him down and bruised him: and Jeshu rebuked that unclean spirit and healed the youth and gave him to his father.
B042C009V043	42	9	43	And they all wondered at the majesty of Aloha. And while every one wondered at all which Jeshu did, he said to his disciples,
B042C009V044	42	9	44	Treasure these words in your ears; for the Son of man is to be delivered into the hands of men.
B042C009V045	42	9	45	But they understood not that saying, because it was hidden from them that they should not know it: and they feared to ask of him concerning that saying.
B042C009V046	42	9	46	And there entered among them the thought, Who should be greatest among them?
B042C009V047	42	9	47	But Jeshu knew the thought of their heart; and he took a child and made him stand with him.
B042C009V048	42	9	48	And he said to them, Every one who receiveth a child like this in my name, receiveth me. And whosoever receiveth me, he receiveth Him who sent me. For he who is least among you, he shall be greatest.
B042C009V049	42	9	49	And Juchanon answered and said, Raban, we saw a man who was casting out demons in thy name, and we forbade him, because he came not with us after thee.
B042C009V050	42	9	50	Jeshu saith to them, Forbid him not; for he who is not against us, he is for us.
B042C009V051	42	9	51	AND it was that when the days were fulfilled for his Assumption, he directed his face to go to Urishlem.
B042C009V052	42	9	52	And he sent messengers before his face, and they went and entered into a village of the Shomroyee, so as to prepare for him.
B042C009V053	42	9	53	And they would not receive him, because his face unto Urishlem was set to go.
B042C009V054	42	9	54	And when Jacub and Juchanon his disciples saw it, they say to him, Maran, art thou willing that we call fire to descend from heaven to consume them, as Elia did?
B042C009V055	42	9	55	But he turned and reproved them, and said, You know not of what spirit you are: for the Son of man is not come to destroy lives, but to save.
B042C009V056	42	9	56	And they went to another village.
B042C009V057	42	9	57	And while they went in the way, a certain man said to him, I will follow thee to the place whither thou goest, my Lord.
B042C009V058	42	9	58	Jeshu saith to him, The foxes have holes and the fowls of the heaven a shadow, but the Son of man hath not where to lay his head.
B042C009V059	42	9	59	And he said to another, Come after me. But he said to him, My Lord, permit me first to go bury my father.
B042C009V060	42	9	60	Jeshu said to him, Leave the dead burying their dead; and thou, go and preach the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C009V061	42	9	61	And another said to him, I will come after thee, my Lord, but first permit me to go to salute the sons of my house, and I will come.
B042C009V062	42	9	62	Jeshu saith to him, No man putting his hand upon the coulter of the yoke, and looking behind him, is fit for the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C010V001	42	10	1	AFTER these Jeshu separated from his disciples seventy others, and sent them by two and two before his face to every place and city whither he was himself to come.
B042C010V002	42	10	2	And he said to them, The harvest is great, but the labourers (are) few; pray therefore from the Lord of the harvest to send forth labourers into his harvest.
B042C010V003	42	10	3	Go; behold, I send you as sheep among wolves.
B042C010V004	42	10	4	Take with you neither purses, nor bags, nor sandals, neither with the salutation (shaloma) shall you salute any man in the way.
B042C010V005	42	10	5	But into whatever house you enter, first say, Peace to the house!
B042C010V006	42	10	6	And if a son of peace be there, your peace shall descend upon him; but if not, your peace upon you shall return.
B042C010V007	42	10	7	But in that house be, eating and drinking of theirs: for worthy is the labourer of his hire. And remove not from house to house.
B042C010V008	42	10	8	And into whatever city you enter and they receive you, eat such things as are set to you.
B042C010V009	42	10	9	And heal those who are sick, and say to them, There hath drawn nigh upon you the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C010V010	42	10	10	But if any city which you enter will not receive you, go you out into the street and say,
B042C010V011	42	10	11	Even the dust which cleaveth to our feet from your city we shake off against you; nevertheless know this, that hath come nigh upon you the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C010V012	42	10	12	I tell you that for Sadum it shall be more tolerable in that day than for that city.
B042C010V013	42	10	13	Woe to thee, Kurazin! woe to thee, Bethtsaida! for if in Tsur and Tsaidon had been wrought the miracles which were wrought in you, now long since in sackcloth and in ashes would they have repented.
B042C010V014	42	10	14	Nevertheless for Tsur and for Tsaidon it shall be more tolerable in the day of the judgment, than for you.
B042C010V015	42	10	15	And thou, Kapher-nachum, which unto heaven art lifted up, unto Shiul shalt thou be abased.
B042C010V016	42	10	16	He that you heareth, me heareth; and he who you rejecteth, me he rejecteth; and he who me rejecteth, he rejecteth him who sent me.
B042C010V017	42	10	17	And the seventy whom he had sent, returned with great joy, saying to him, Our Lord, the demons also are subjected to us through thy name.
B042C010V018	42	10	18	Then he said to them, I saw him, Satana, when he fell as lightning from heaven.
B042C010V019	42	10	19	Behold, I give you power to tread upon serpents and scorpions, and all the strength of the enemy, and nothing shall hurt you.
B042C010V020	42	10	20	Nevertheless in this rejoice not, that the demons are subject to you; but rejoice that your names are written in heaven.
B042C010V021	42	10	21	In that hour Jeshu exulted in the Holy Spirit, and said, I praise thee, my Father, Lord of heaven and of earth, that thou hast hid these things from the wise and the intellectual, and hast revealed them unto children. Yes, my Father, for so was thy will.
B042C010V022	42	10	22	And he turned to his disciples, and said to them, Every thing is delivered to me by my Father: and no man knoweth who the Son is but the Father; and who the Father is but the Son, and he to whom the Son willeth to reveal.
B042C010V023	42	10	23	And he turned to his disciples by themselves, and said, Blessed are your eyes because they see what you see;
B042C010V024	42	10	24	for I tell you that prophets many and kings have desired to see what you see, and have not seen, and to hear what you hear, and have not heard.
B042C010V025	42	10	25	AND, behold, a certain Sophra stood up to try him, saying, Malphona, what shall I do to inherit everlasting life?
B042C010V026	42	10	26	But Jeshu said to him, In the law how is it written, how readest thou?
B042C010V027	42	10	27	He answered and said to him, Thou shalt love the Lord thy Aloha with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy strength, and with all thy mind, and thy neighbour as thyself,
B042C010V028	42	10	28	Jeshu said to him, Thou hast said correctly. This do, and thou shalt live.
B042C010V029	42	10	29	But he, willing to justify himself, said to him, And who is my neighbour?
B042C010V030	42	10	30	Jeshu saith to him, A certain man went down from Urishlem to Jerichu, and fell among robbers, who stripped him and wounded him, and left him with little life subsisting in him, and went.
B042C010V031	42	10	31	And a certain priest happened to go down by that way, and he saw him and passed over.
B042C010V032	42	10	32	And likewise also a Levoia, being come to that place, beheld him, and passed over.
B042C010V033	42	10	33	But a man, a Shomroya, while he journeyed, came where he was, and saw him, and had compassion on him,
B042C010V034	42	10	34	and went near, and bound up his wounds, and poured in upon them wine and oil, and set him upon his ass, and brought him to the inn, and was anxious for him.
B042C010V035	42	10	35	And on the morning of the day, he took out two dinoreen, gave to the host, and said to him, Take care of him; and if more thou layest out, when I return I will give to thee.
B042C010V036	42	10	36	Which therefore of these three doth it appear to thee was neighbour to him who fell into the hands of the thieves?
B042C010V037	42	10	37	And he said, He who had compassion on him. Jeshu saith to him, Go thou also and do likewise.
B042C010V038	42	10	38	AND it was that as they went in the way, he entered into a certain village, and a woman whose name was Martha received him into her house.
B042C010V039	42	10	39	And she had a sister whose name was Mariam, and she came, sat at the feet of our Lord, and heard his words.
B042C010V040	42	10	40	But Martha was occupied with much serving. And she came and said to him, My Lord, carest thou not that my sister leave me alone to serve? Tell her to help me.
B042C010V041	42	10	41	Jeshu answered and said to her, Martha, Martha, thou art careful and disturbed about many,
B042C010V042	42	10	42	but (there) is the one that is needed. And Mariam the good portion hath chosen, that which shall not be taken from her.
B042C011V001	42	11	1	AND it was that while he was praying in a certain place, when he had finished, one of his disciples said to him, Our Lord, teach us to pray as also Juchanon taught his disciples.
B042C011V002	42	11	2	Jeshu said to them, When you pray, thus be saying, Our Father who (art) in the heavens, be sanctified thy name. Come thy kingdom. Be done thy will as in the heavens also upon earth.
B042C011V003	42	11	3	Give to us the bread of our need every day,
B042C011V004	42	11	4	and forgive us our sins, for we also forgive all who are indebted to us. And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil.
B042C011V005	42	11	5	And he said to them, Who of you that has a friend, and shall go to him at midnight, and shall say to him, My friend, lend me three loaves,
B042C011V006	42	11	6	because a friend has come to me from the way, and I have nothing to set to him?
B042C011V007	42	11	7	and that friend from within shall answer and say unto him, Disturb me not, for the door is shut, and my children are with me in bed: I cannot rise and give to you.
B042C011V008	42	11	8	I tell you if for friendship's sake he will not give him, (yet) because of importunity he will arise and give him as many as he needeth.
B042C011V009	42	11	9	I say also to you, Ask, and it shall be given to you; seek, and you shall find; knock, and it shall be opened to you.
B042C011V010	42	11	10	For every one who asketh receiveth, and who seeketh findeth, and who knocketh hath it opened to him.
B042C011V011	42	11	11	For what father (is there) among you who, if his son shall ask bread, will reach to him a stone? or should he ask a fish, how instead of a fish will he reach to him a serpent?
B042C011V012	42	11	12	or if an egg he shall ask, will he a scorpion reach to him?
B042C011V013	42	11	13	And if you, who are evil, know to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father from the heavens give the Spirit of Holiness to those who ask him!
B042C011V014	42	11	14	AND he was casting out a demon which was dumb; and when he had cast out the demon, the dumb spake, and the multitudes wondered.
B042C011V015	42	11	15	But some from them said, By Beelzebub, the prince of the devils, he casteth out devils;
B042C011V016	42	11	16	while others, tempting him, the sign from heaven demanded of him.
B042C011V017	42	11	17	But Jeshu, who knew their thoughts, said to them, Every kingdom which is divided against itself will be desolated; and a house that against its own self is divided falleth;
B042C011V018	42	11	18	and if Satana against himself be divided, how will his kingdom stand? Because you say that through Beelzebub I cast out devils.
B042C011V019	42	11	19	But if I by Beelzebub cast out devils, your sons, by what do they cast (them) out? On account of this they shall be your judges.
B042C011V020	42	11	20	But if by the finger of Aloha I cast out devils, there hath drawn nigh upon you the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C011V021	42	11	21	When the strong one armed keepeth his court, his possession is in peace;
B042C011V022	42	11	22	but if a stronger than he shall come, he shall overcome him; all his armour he taketh on which he depended, and he divideth his spoils.
B042C011V023	42	11	23	He who is not with me is against me; and he who does not collect with me, by scattering he scattereth.
B042C011V024	42	11	24	The unclean spirit, when he hath gone out from a son of man, goeth about through regions which have no waters in them, because he seeketh to him rest. And when he cannot find it he saith, I will return to my house from whence I went out.
B042C011V025	42	11	25	And when he cometh he findeth it swept and ornamented.
B042C011V026	42	11	26	Then he goeth, taketh seven other spirits who are more wicked than himself, and they enter and dwell there, and the last of that man is worse than his first.
B042C011V027	42	11	27	AND while he spake these words, a certain woman lifted up her voice from the crowd, and said to him, Blessed is the womb that bare thee, and the breasts which thou hast sucked!
B042C011V028	42	11	28	He said to her, Blessed are they who hear the word of Aloha and keep it.
B042C011V029	42	11	29	And when the assemblies had gathered together, he began to say, This evil generation requireth a sign; but no sign shall be given to it save the sign of Jaunon the prophet.
B042C011V030	42	11	30	For as was Jaunon a sign to the Ninvoyee, so shall also the Son of man be to this generation.
B042C011V031	42	11	31	The queen of the south shall rise in judgment with the men of this generation, and shall condemn them; for she came from the confines of the earth to hear the wisdom of Shelemun, and, lo, a greater than Shelemun is here.
B042C011V032	42	11	32	The men of Nineveh shall rise in judgment with this generation and shall condemn it: for they repented at the preaching of Jaunon, and, lo, a greater than Jaunon is here.
B042C011V033	42	11	33	No man lighteth a lamp and setteth it in a secret (place) or under a measure, but upon a candlestick, that they who enter may see the light of it.
B042C011V034	42	11	34	The lamp of thy body is thine eye; when therefore thine eye is simple, thy whole body also will be illuminated; but if it be evil, thy body also will be darkness.
B042C011V035	42	11	35	Beware, therefore, lest the light that is in thee become darkness.
B042C011V036	42	11	36	But if thy whole body be illuminated, and no part whatever in it be darkness, the whole will be light, as when a lamp with its flame enlighteneth thee.
B042C011V037	42	11	37	AND as he was speaking, a certain Pharisha requested of him to dine with him, and he went in to recline.
B042C011V038	42	11	38	But he, the Pharisha, when he saw him, wondered that he had not first washed before his dinner.
B042C011V039	42	11	39	But Jeshu said to him, Now you Pharishee cleanse the outside of the cup and the dish, but within you are full of rapine and wickedness.
B042C011V040	42	11	40	Wanting in understanding! did not he who made that which is without, make also that which is within?
B042C011V041	42	11	41	But of whatever there is, give in alms, and, behold, every thing is clean to you.
B042C011V042	42	11	42	But woe to you, Pharishee! for you tithe mint, and rue, and every herb, and pass by judgment and the love of Aloha. These hath it behoved you to do, and those not to have omitted.
B042C011V043	42	11	43	Woe to you, Pharishee! for you love the chief seats in the assemblies, and the salutation in the public places.
B042C011V044	42	11	44	Woe to you, scribes and Pharishee, hypocrites! for you are like tombs that are not known, and men walk upon them, and do not know.
B042C011V045	42	11	45	And one of the Sophree answered and said to him, Doctor, while you say these things, you vilify us also!
B042C011V046	42	11	46	But he said, Also unto you, Sophree, woe! because you lade men with heavy burdens, and you with one of your fingers will not touch those burdens.
B042C011V047	42	11	47	Woe to you! for you build the tombs of the prophets whom your fathers killed:
B042C011V048	42	11	48	thus you bear witness that you consent in the deeds of your fathers; for they killed them, and you build their sepulchres.
B042C011V049	42	11	49	ON this account also Wisdom saith, Behold, I will send to them prophets and apostles; and of them they will persecute and kill;
B042C011V050	42	11	50	that the blood of all the prophets which hath been shed from the creation of the world may be required from this generation.
B042C011V051	42	11	51	From the blood of Habil unto the blood of Zakaria who was killed between the temple and the altar: yes, I tell you, It shall be required of this generation.
B042C011V052	42	11	52	Woe to you, Sophree; for you have taken away the key of knowledge; you enter not in (yourselves), and they who are entering you prohibit.
B042C011V053	42	11	53	And while he spoke these (words) to them, the Sophree and Pharishee began to be displeased, and they were wrathful, and controverted his words, and enticed him on many (points),
B042C011V054	42	11	54	seeking to lay hold on something from his mouth that they might be able to accuse him.
B042C012V001	42	12	1	AND when (there) had gathered (by) myriads great assemblies, so that they would have trodden upon one another, Jeshu began to say to his disciples, Beware for yourselves before all things of the leaven of the Pharishee, which is hypocrisy.
B042C012V002	42	12	2	For nothing is hidden which shall not be revealed, and nothing secreted which shall not be made known.
B042C012V003	42	12	3	For all that you say in darknesses in the light shall be heard, and what you whisper in the ear in closets shall be proclaimed on the housetops.
B042C012V004	42	12	4	But I say to you, my beloved ones, Fear not them who kill the body, and who afterward can do nothing more;
B042C012V005	42	12	5	but I will show you whom you shall fear; Him who, after he hath killed, hath power to cast into gihana, yes, I say to you, Fear this (one).
B042C012V006	42	12	6	Are not five sparrows sold for two asorin; and one of them is not forgotten before Aloha.
B042C012V007	42	12	7	But of you, the numbers of the hairs of your head are all numbered. Fear not, therefore; than many sparrows more precious are you.
B042C012V008	42	12	8	But I tell you that every one who shall confess me before men, the Son of man will also confess him before the angels of Aloha.
B042C012V009	42	12	9	But he who denieth me before men, I will deny him before the angels of Aloha.
B042C012V010	42	12	10	And every one who shall speak a word against the Son of man, it may be forgiven him; but whoever against the Spirit of Holiness shall blaspheme, it shall not be forgiven him.
B042C012V011	42	12	11	And when they bring you into the synagogues, before heads and authorities, be not anxious how you shall express yourselves, or what you shall say;
B042C012V012	42	12	12	for the Spirit of Holiness will teach you in that hour what you ought to say.
B042C012V013	42	12	13	AND a man from the assembly said to him, Malphona, tell my brother to divide with me the inheritance.
B042C012V014	42	12	14	But Jeshu said to him, Man, who established me over you a judge and a divider?
B042C012V015	42	12	15	And he said to his disciples, Beware of all avarice: for life is not in the abundance of riches.
B042C012V016	42	12	16	And he spake a parable to them: The ground of a certain rich man produced him much provisions.
B042C012V017	42	12	17	And he thought within himself, and said, What shall I do? for I have not where to collect my provisions.
B042C012V018	42	12	18	And he said, This will I do: I will destroy my house of stores, and will build and enlarge it; and there will I collect all my provender and my good things:
B042C012V019	42	12	19	and I will say to my soul, My soul, thou hast many good things laid up for many years: be at ease, eat, drink, and be merry.
B042C012V020	42	12	20	But Aloha said to him, Reasonless (man)! this night thy soul they shall require of thee; and then, (the things) which thou hast prepared,
B042C012V021	42	12	21	whose shall they be? So is he who layeth up to himself treasures, and towards Aloha is not rich.
B042C012V022	42	12	22	And he said to his disciples, Therefore I tell you, Be not anxious for yourselves, what you shall eat; neither for the body, how you shall dress:
B042C012V023	42	12	23	for the soul is more precious than food, and the body than raiment.
B042C012V024	42	12	24	Consider the ravens, which sow not nor reap, which have no chambers or barns, yet Aloha feeds them. How much, therefore, are you better than the fowls!
B042C012V025	42	12	25	And which of you by being anxious could add to his stature one cubit?
B042C012V026	42	12	26	But if indeed you are not capable of (that which is) the least, why concerning the rest are you anxious?
B042C012V027	42	12	27	Consider the lilies, how they grow, which toil not nor spin; but I tell you that even Shelemun in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these.
B042C012V028	42	12	28	But if the herbage, which today is in the field, and to-morrow is cast into the furnace, Aloha thus clothes, how much more you, little in faith!
B042C012V029	42	12	29	And seek you not what you shall eat, and what you shall drink; nor let your mind be distracted for these:
B042C012V030	42	12	30	for all these the nations of the world seek; but to you also your Father knoweth that these are needful.
B042C012V031	42	12	31	But seek the kingdom of Aloha, and these all shall be added to you.
B042C012V032	42	12	32	FEAR not, little flock; for your Father hath willed to give you the kingdom.
B042C012V033	42	12	33	Sell your substance, and give alms: make to you bags which become not old, and a treasure which is not transient, in the heavens, where the thief does not approach, and the moth destroys not.
B042C012V034	42	12	34	For where your treasure is, there will be also your heart.
B042C012V035	42	12	35	Let your loins be bound, and your lamps be burning,
B042C012V036	42	12	36	and be you like men who wait for their lord, when he shall return from the place of festivity, that, when he hath come and knocked, immediately they may open to him.
B042C012V037	42	12	37	Blessed those servants who, when their lord shall come, shall be found watching. Amen I tell you, He will gird his loins, and make them recline, and will come over and serve them.
B042C012V038	42	12	38	And if in the second or the third watch he shall come and find them thus, blessed will be those servants.
B042C012V039	42	12	39	But this know, that if the lord of the house had known in what watch the thief would come, he would have watched, and not have permitted his house to be dug through.
B042C012V040	42	12	40	Also you, be you therefore ready: for, in that hour that you think not, cometh the Son of man.
B042C012V041	42	12	41	Shemun Kipha said to him, Our Lord, to us speakest thou this parable, or to all men also?
B042C012V042	42	12	42	Jeshu said to him, Who then is that steward, faithful and wise, whom his lord hath established over his service, to give the portion in its time?
B042C012V043	42	12	43	Blessed that servant whom, when his lord shall come, he shall find so doing.
B042C012V044	42	12	44	Assuredly I tell you, He will establish him over all his substance.
B042C012V045	42	12	45	But if that servant shall say in his heart, My lord withholdeth to come, and shall begin to beat the servants and the handmaids of his lord, and shall begin to eat and to drink and be drunken;
B042C012V046	42	12	46	the lord of that servant will come in a day when he thinketh not, and in an hour which he knoweth not; and shall sunder him, and set him his portion with those who are not faithful.
B042C012V047	42	12	47	And that servant who knew the will of his lord, and prepared not himself according to his will, shall be beaten with many
B042C012V048	42	12	48	But he who knew not, and did that which was worthy of stripes, shall be beaten with few stripes. For every one to whom much is given, much will be required from him; and to whom much is committed, the more will they require at his hand.
B042C012V049	42	12	49	FIRE have I come to send forth upon the earth, and I would that it already burned:
B042C012V050	42	12	50	and I have a baptism (wherewith) to be baptized, and greatly am I pressed till it be completed.
B042C012V051	42	12	51	Suppose you that peace I have come to send forth on the earth? I tell you, not (peace), but divisions.
B042C012V052	42	12	52	For from henceforth there will be five in one house, who (will be) divided, three against two, and two against three.
B042C012V053	42	12	53	For the father will be divided against his son, and the son against his father; the mother against her daughter, and the daughter against her mother; the mother-in-law against the daughter-in-law and the daughter-in-law against the mother-in-law.
B042C012V054	42	12	54	And he said to the assembly, When you see a cloud arisen from the west, immediately you say, The rain cometh; and it is so:
B042C012V055	42	12	55	and when bloweth the south, you say, It becomes heat; and it is so.
B042C012V056	42	12	56	You hypocrites, the aspect of the sky and of the earth you know to distinguish; but this Time how do you not distinguish?
B042C012V057	42	12	57	But why of yourselves judge you not the truth?
B042C012V058	42	12	58	When thou art going with thine adversary to the magistrate, while in the way, negotiate, and be freed from him; lest he bring thee to the judge, and the judge deliver thee to the exactor, and the exactor cast thee into the house of the bound;
B042C012V059	42	12	59	and Amen I tell thee, Thou wilt not be delivered from thence till thou shalt have given the last shomona.
B042C013V001	42	13	1	NOW at that time came some and told him of the Galiloyee, they whose blood Pilatos had mingled with their sacrifices.
B042C013V002	42	13	2	Jeshu answered and said to them, Think you that these Galiloyee were sinners more than all the Galiloyee, that thus it was (with) them?
B042C013V003	42	13	3	No; but I tell you that all of you also, if you repent not, will thus perish.
B042C013V004	42	13	4	Or those eighteen on whom fell the tower in Silucha, and killed them; think you that they were sinners above all men who dwell in Urishlem?
B042C013V005	42	13	5	No; but I tell you that, if you repent not, all of you likewise shall perish.
B042C013V006	42	13	6	And he spake this parable: A man had a fig-tree which was planted in his vinery: and he came and sought fruits on it, but did not find.
B042C013V007	42	13	7	And he said to the husbandman, Behold, three years come I seeking fruits from this fig-tree, but I have not found: cut it down; why maketh it the ground useless?
B042C013V008	42	13	8	The husbandman saith to him, My lord, suffer it also this year, until I tend it and manure it:
B042C013V009	42	13	9	and if it produce fruits, (well): but if not, then afterwards I will cut it down.
B042C013V010	42	13	10	AS Jeshu was teaching on a shabath in one of the synagogues,
B042C013V011	42	13	11	a woman was there who had a spirit of infirmity eighteen years; and she was bowed down, and could not be straight at all.
B042C013V012	42	13	12	But Jeshu saw her, and called her, and said to her, Woman, thou art loosed from thine infirmity.
B042C013V013	42	13	13	And he laid his hand upon her; and at once she was made straight, and glorified Aloha.
B042C013V014	42	13	14	But the chief of the synagogue answered, being angry that Jeshu had healed on the shabath, and said to the congregation, Six days there are in which it is lawful to work: in them come and be healed, and not on the day of shabath.
B042C013V015	42	13	15	But Jeshu answered and said to him, Hypocrite, doth not any one of you on the shabath loose his ox or his ass from the manger, and going giveth to drink?
B042C013V016	42	13	16	But this daughter of Abraham, whom, behold, the Accuser hath bound eighteen years, is it not lawful to loose from this binding on the day of shabath?
B042C013V017	42	13	17	And as he said these things, ashamed were all they who had risen up against him; and all the people rejoiced in all these wonders that were done by his hand.
B042C013V018	42	13	18	Jeshu said, What doth the kingdom of Aloha resemble, and to what shall I compare it?
B042C013V019	42	13	19	It resembles a grain of mustard, which a man took (and) cast into his garden: and it grew, and became a great tree; and the fowl of the heaven built in its branches.
B042C013V020	42	13	20	Jeshu said again, To what shall I compare the kingdom of Aloha?
B042C013V021	42	13	21	It is like leaven which a woman took; (and) hid in three satas of meal, until all had leavened.
B042C013V022	42	13	22	And he journeyed, teaching in the villages and in the cities, and going forwards to Urishlem.
B042C013V023	42	13	23	ONE had demanded (of) him if they are few who are saved. But Jeshu said to them,
B042C013V024	42	13	24	Strive to enter in at the strait gate: for I say to you that many will seek to enter in, but shall not be able.
B042C013V025	42	13	25	From the hour that the Lord of the house shall have risen up and have shut the door, you may stand without, knocking at the door, and may begin to say, Our Lord, our Lord, open to us! But he will answer and say, I tell you that I know not whence you are.
B042C013V026	42	13	26	And you shall begin to say, Before thee we have eaten and drunk, and in our streets thou hast taught.
B042C013V027	42	13	27	And he shall say to you, I know you not whence you are: depart from me, workers of falsity.
B042C013V028	42	13	28	There will be weeping and gnashing of teeth, when you shall see Abraham and Ishok and Jakub and all the prophets in the kingdom of Aloha, but you be cast forth without.
B042C013V029	42	13	29	And they shall come from the east, and from the west, and from the south, and from the north, and shall recline in the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C013V030	42	13	30	And, behold, there are last who shall be first, and there are first who shall be last.
B042C013V031	42	13	31	In that day came men from the Pharishee, saying to him, Remove, go from hence, because Herodes desireth to kill thee.
B042C013V032	42	13	32	Jeshu saith to them, Go, tell that fox, Behold, I cast out devils and perform cures to-day and to-morrow, and the third day I am perfected.
B042C013V033	42	13	33	Nevertheless it behoveth me to-day and to-morrow to work and the (day) after I shall go; because it cannot be that a prophet perish out of Urishlem.
B042C013V034	42	13	34	Urishlem, Urishlem! killing the prophets, and stoning them that are sent to her, what times would I have gathered thy sons as the hen gathereth her chickens under her wings, and you willed not!
B042C013V035	42	13	35	Behold, left to you is your house a desert; for I say to you, that you will not see me until you shall say, Blessed is he who cometh in the name of the Lord.
B042C014V001	42	14	1	AND it was that while he went into the house of one of the chief Pharishee to eat bread, on the day of shabath, they watched him.
B042C014V002	42	14	2	And, behold, a certain man who had gathered waters was before him.
B042C014V003	42	14	3	And Jeshu answered and said to the Sophree and the Pharishee, Is it lawful on the shabath to heal?
B042C014V004	42	14	4	But they were silent. And he took him, and healed him, and dismissed him.
B042C014V005	42	14	5	And he said to them, Who from you, whose son or his ox hath fallen into a pit on the day of shabath, doth not at once bring him forth?
B042C014V006	42	14	6	And they could not give him the answer concerning this.
B042C014V007	42	14	7	And he spoke a parable to them who had been invited there, forasmuch as he had observed them, that they chose the chief places of reclining:
B042C014V008	42	14	8	When thou art invited by one into the house of festivity, go not to recline on the principal seat, lest there be invited thither one more honourable than thou;
B042C014V009	42	14	9	and he come who thyself and him had called, and say to thee, Give place to this; and thou be ashamed as thou arisest to take another place.
B042C014V010	42	14	10	But when thou art invited, go, recline thee in the last (seat), that when he who called thee cometh, he may say to thee, My friend, ascend and recline above, and thou shalt have honour before all of them who recline with thee.
B042C014V011	42	14	11	For every one who exalteth himself shall be humbled; and every one who humbleth himself shall be exalted.
B042C014V012	42	14	12	And he said to him who had called him, When thou makest a dinner or a supper, thou shouldest not call thy friends, nor thy brethren, nor thy kinsmen, nor thy rich neighbours, lest they also call thee, and thou have this recompence.
B042C014V013	42	14	13	But when thou makest a feast, call the poor, the maimed, the lame, the blind,
B042C014V014	42	14	14	and thou shalt be blessed, because they cannot recompense thee; for thy recompence shall be in the resurrection of the just.
B042C014V015	42	14	15	But when one of those who reclined heard these (words), he said to him, Blessed he who shall eat bread in the kingdom of Aloha!
B042C014V016	42	14	16	Jeshu saith to him, A certain man made a great supper, and called many. And he sent his servant,
B042C014V017	42	14	17	at the time of the supper, to say to them who were called, Behold, every thing is prepared for you, come.
B042C014V018	42	14	18	And every one of them began to excuse himself. The first said to him, I have bought an estate, and am constrained to go forth to see it: I beseech thee, permit me to be excused.
B042C014V019	42	14	19	Another said, Five yoke of oxen have I bought, and I go to prove them: I beseech thee, permit me to be excused.
B042C014V020	42	14	20	Another said, A wife have I taken, and therefore I cannot come.
B042C014V021	42	14	21	And the servant came and told his lord these things. Then the lord of the house was angry, and said to his servant, Go into the streets and outskirts of the city, and bring hither the poor, and the afflicted, and the lame, and the sightless.
B042C014V022	42	14	22	And the servant said, My lord, it is done as thou hast commanded, and yet there is place.
B042C014V023	42	14	23	And the lord said to his servant, Go forth into the ways, and among the hedges, and constrain them to come in, that my house may be filled:
B042C014V024	42	14	24	for I tell you, that not one of those men who were called shall taste of my supper.
B042C014V025	42	14	25	AND while great multitudes were going with him, he turned and said to them,
B042C014V026	42	14	26	Whoever cometh with me, and doth not hate his father and his mother, and his brethren and his sisters, and his wife and his children, and himself also, a disciple he cannot be of mine.
B042C014V027	42	14	27	And whoever doth not take up his cross and come after me, a disciple he cannot be of mine.
B042C014V028	42	14	28	For who of you that willeth to build a tower, and doth not first sit down and reckon the expense of it, whether he have (wherewith) to finish it?
B042C014V029	42	14	29	lest, when he shall have laid the foundation, and shall not be able to finish, all who see shall deride him,
B042C014V030	42	14	30	saying, This man began to build, and was not able to finish.
B042C014V031	42	14	31	Or, what king, going to war with a king his neighbour, doth not first consider, whether he be able with ten thousand to meet him who cometh against him with twenty thousand?
B042C014V032	42	14	32	and if not, while he is distant from him, he may send legates, and pray for peace.
B042C014V033	42	14	33	So every one of you who doth not leave all his possession, cannot be unto me a disciple.
B042C014V034	42	14	34	Salt is good; but if the salt also shall become insipid, with what shall it be seasoned?
B042C014V035	42	14	35	Not for the earth, nor for the dunghill, it goeth. They cast it out. Who hath ears to hear, let him hear.
B042C015V001	42	15	1	Then drew near to him the publicans and sinners to hear him.
B042C015V002	42	15	2	And the Sophree and Pharishee murmured, and said, This (man) receiveth sinners, and eateth with them.
B042C015V003	42	15	3	And Jeshu spake to them this parable:
B042C015V004	42	15	4	What man of you, who hath a hundred sheep, if he shall lose one from them, does not leave the ninety and nine in the wilderness, and, going, seeketh that which was lost until he shall have found it?
B042C015V005	42	15	5	And when he hath found it, he rejoiceth and carrieth it upon his shoulders.
B042C015V006	42	15	6	And, coming to his house, he calleth his friends and his neighbours, and saith to them, Rejoice with me; for I have found the sheep which was lost.
B042C015V007	42	15	7	I say to you, that thus shall there be joy in heaven over one sinner who repenteth, more than over the ninety and nine just ones who have no need of repentance.
B042C015V008	42	15	8	Or, who is the woman that hath ten zuzis, and shall lose one of them, (and) does not light a lamp and sweep the house, and seek it diligently, until she shall have found it?
B042C015V009	42	15	9	And when she hath found it, she calleth her friends and her neighbours, and saith to them, Rejoice with me; for I have found my zuzi that I had lost.
B042C015V010	42	15	10	I say to you, that so shall there be joy before the angels of God over one sinner that repenteth.
B042C015V011	42	15	11	AND Jeshu said to them again, A certain man had two sons;
B042C015V012	42	15	12	and his minor son said to him, My father, give to me my division of the goods of thy house. And he divided to them his substance.
B042C015V013	42	15	13	And after a few days the minor son gathered together his all whatsoever, and went into a distant country, and there dispersed his substance in living profusely.
B042C015V014	42	15	14	And when every thing he had was finished, there was a great famine in that country; and he began to want.
B042C015V015	42	15	15	And he went and joined himself to one of the sons of the city of that place; and he sent him into the field to tend the swine.
B042C015V016	42	15	16	And he had a desire to fill his belly with those karubs which the swine did eat; and no man gave to him.
B042C015V017	42	15	17	And when he came to himself, he said, How many hirelings are there now in my father's house, who have abundance of bread, and I here with hunger am perishing!
B042C015V018	42	15	18	I will arise, go to my father, and say to him, My father, I have sinned against heaven and before thee,
B042C015V019	42	15	19	and am no more worthy thy son to be called: make me as one of thy hirelings.
B042C015V020	42	15	20	And he arose, (and) went to his father. And while he was (yet) afar, his father saw him, and had compassion upon him, and ran, fell upon his neck, and kissed him.
B042C015V021	42	15	21	And his son said to him, My father, I have sinned against heaven and before thee, and am not worthy thy son to be called.
B042C015V022	42	15	22	But his father said to his servants, Bring forth the first robe to clothe him, and put a ring upon his hand, and let him be, shod with sandals,
B042C015V023	42	15	23	and bring, kill the calf that is fat, and let us eat and be glad;
B042C015V024	42	15	24	for this my son was dead, and he is alive; he was lost, and is found. And they began to rejoice.
B042C015V025	42	15	25	But he, the elder son, was in the field; and as he came and drew near to the house, he heard the voice of music;
B042C015V026	42	15	26	and he called one of the youths, and asked him what this was.
B042C015V027	42	15	27	He said to him, Thy brother hath come, and thy father hath killed the calf that was fat, because he hath received him well.
B042C015V028	42	15	28	And he was angry, and would not go in. And his father came forth and besought him.
B042C015V029	42	15	29	But he said to his father, Behold, how many years have I wrought thee service, and never have I transgressed thy commandment: yet never hast thou given me a kid, that I might feast with my friends.
B042C015V030	42	15	30	But this thy son, when he hath wasted thy substance with harlots, and hath come, thou hast killed for him the fatted calf.
B042C015V031	42	15	31	His father saith to him, My son, thou in all time art with me, and every thing that I have is thine.
B042C015V032	42	15	32	But to rejoice it behoves us, and to be glad, because this thy brother was dead, and is alive; and was lost, and is found.
B042C016V001	42	16	1	AND he spake a parable to his disciples: There was a certain rich man who had a house-chief; and he was accused to him that his substance he wasted.
B042C016V002	42	16	2	And his lord called him, and said to him, What is this that I hear of thee? give me the account of thy house-headship; for thou canst no longer be house-chief unto me.
B042C016V003	42	16	3	And the house-chief said within himself, What shall I do? for my lord taketh from me the house-headship. I cannot dig, and to beg I am ashamed.
B042C016V004	42	16	4	I know what I will do, that when I shall be put out of the house-headship, they may receive me into their houses.
B042C016V005	42	16	5	And he called one by one from the debtors of his lord, and said to the first, How much owest thou to my lord?
B042C016V006	42	16	6	And he said to him, An hundred metres of oil. He saith to him, Take thy book, and sit down quickly, and write fifty metres.
B042C016V007	42	16	7	And he said to another, And thou, how much owest thou to my lord? He saith to him, An hundred kureen of wheat. He saith to him, Take thy book, and sit down, write eighty kureen.
B042C016V008	42	16	8	And praised our Lord the house-chief who was unjust, in that he had done wisely; for the sons of this world are wiser than the sons of light in this their generation.
B042C016V009	42	16	9	Also I say unto you, Make to you friends from this wealth of unrighteousness, that, when perfect, they may receive you into the tabernacles of eternity.
B042C016V010	42	16	10	Whoever in the little is faithful, in the great also is faithful; and he who in the little is unjust, in the great also is unjust.
B042C016V011	42	16	11	If, therefore, in the wealth of unrighteousness you have not been faithful, the truth to you who will confide?
B042C016V012	42	16	12	And if in that which is not yours you are not found faithful, your own who will give to you?
B042C016V013	42	16	13	No man can serve two lords; for either the one he will hate, and the other he will love; or the one he will honour, and the other despise. You cannot serve Aloha and wealth.
B042C016V014	42	16	14	But the Pharishee, when they heard all these things, because they loved money, derided him.
B042C016V015	42	16	15	But Jeshu said to them, You are they who justify yourselves before the sons of men; but Aloha knoweth your hearts. For, what is exalted among men, before Aloha is abominable.
B042C016V016	42	16	16	The law and the prophets were until Juchanon; from thenceforth the kingdom of Aloha is preached, and every one presseth to enter.
B042C016V017	42	16	17	But it is easier for heaven and earth to pass away than one letter from the law to pass away.
B042C016V018	42	16	18	Every one who looseth his wife, and taketh another, committeth adultery; and every one who taketh the dismissed, committeth adultery.
B042C016V019	42	16	19	NOW there was a certain rich man, and he was clothed in byssos and purple, and every day feasted gaily.
B042C016V020	42	16	20	And there was a certain poor man, whose name was Loózar; and he lay at the gate of him who was rich, bruised with wounds,
B042C016V021	42	16	21	and desired to fill his belly with the crumbs which fell from the table of that rich. And also the dogs came and licked his wounds.
B042C016V022	42	16	22	Now that poor man died, and angels conducted him to the bosom of Abraham: but that rich man also died, and was buried.
B042C016V023	42	16	23	And, tormented in shiul, he lifted up his eyes afar, and seeth Abraham, and Loózar in his bosom.
B042C016V024	42	16	24	And he cried with a high voice, and said, My father Abraham, have compassion upon me, and send Loózar, that he may dip the top of his finger in waters, and moisten my tongue; for, behold, I am tormented in this flame.
B042C016V025	42	16	25	Abraham said to him, My son, remember that thou didst receive thy goods in thy life, and Loózar his evils, and now, behold, he reposeth here, and thou art tormented.
B042C016V026	42	16	26	And with all these, there is a great void set between us and you, that they who would pass from hence unto you are not able, nor they also who would pass from thence to us.
B042C016V027	42	16	27	He said to him, I pray thee, then, my father, to send him unto my father's house:
B042C016V028	42	16	28	for five brethren have I; let him go and testify unto them, that they also come not to this place of torment.
B042C016V029	42	16	29	Abraham said to him, They have Musha and the prophets, let them hear them.
B042C016V030	42	16	30	But he said to him, No, my father Abraham, but if one from the dead shall go unto them, they repent.
B042C016V031	42	16	31	Abraham saith to him, If Musha and the prophets they hear not, neither, if one from the dead should rise, would they believe him.
B042C017V001	42	17	1	AND Jeshu said to his disciples, It cannot be that offences should not come, but woe to him by whom they shall come.
B042C017V002	42	17	2	It were better for him that an ass-millstone were hanged on his neck, and he be cast into the sea. Woe (to him) who shall offend one of these little ones!
B042C017V003	42	17	3	Take heed to yourselves; if thy brother transgress, reprove him, and if he repent, forgive him.
B042C017V004	42	17	4	And if seven times in the day he shall trespass against thee, and seven times in the day return to thee and say, I repent, forgive him.
B042C017V005	42	17	5	And the apostles said unto our Lord, Increase to us faith.
B042C017V006	42	17	6	He saith to them, If you had faith as a grain of mustard, you should say to this mulberry tree, Be rooted up and planted in the sea, and it would obey you.
B042C017V007	42	17	7	Which of you, having a servant who leadeth a yoke (of oxen) or who tendeth the flock, and when he cometh from the field, saith to him at once, Pass on and recline thyself?
B042C017V008	42	17	8	but (rather) saith to him, Prepare me something that I may sup, and gird thy loins, serve me until I have eaten and drunk, and afterwards thou also shalt eat and drink.
B042C017V009	42	17	9	Does that servant receive thanks because he hath done what was required of him? I consider not.
B042C017V010	42	17	10	Thus also you, when you have done all those things which are required of you, have said, We are unprofitable servants, because what we were obligated to do, (that) have we done.
B042C017V011	42	17	11	AND it was that as Jeshu was going to Urishlem, he passed among the Shomroyee from Galila.
B042C017V012	42	17	12	And as he drew near to enter a certain village, there met him ten men, lepers, and they stood from afar,
B042C017V013	42	17	13	and lifted up their voice and said, Our Lord Jeshu, have mercy upon us!
B042C017V014	42	17	14	And when he saw them, he said to them, Go show yourselves to the priests. And as they went, they were cleansed.
B042C017V015	42	17	15	Then one of them, when he saw that he was cleansed, returned to him, and with a high voice glorified Aloha.
B042C017V016	42	17	16	And he fell upon his face before the feet of Jeshu, and thanked him. And, behold, this was a Shomroya.
B042C017V017	42	17	17	And Jeshu answered and said, Were not they who were cleansed ten? Where are the nine?
B042C017V018	42	17	18	None have separated to come (and) give praise to Aloha, but this, who is from a strange people.
B042C017V019	42	17	19	And he said to him, Arise, go; thy faith hath saved thee.
B042C017V020	42	17	20	AND when Jeshu was questioned from the Pharishee, When cometh the kingdom of Aloha? he answered and said to them, The kingdom of Aloha cometh not with watchings:
B042C017V021	42	17	21	nor say they, Behold, it is here! and, Behold, it is there! for the kingdom of Aloha is within you.
B042C017V022	42	17	22	And he said to his disciples, The days will come, when you will desire to see one of the days of the Son of man, and you will not see.
B042C017V023	42	17	23	And if they say to you, Behold here, and, Behold there, go not.
B042C017V024	42	17	24	For as the lightning lighteneth from heaven, and illuminateth all beneath the heaven, so shall be the Son of man in his day.
B042C017V025	42	17	25	But first it will be that he shall suffer many (things), and be rejected of this generation.
B042C017V026	42	17	26	And as it was in the days of Nuch, so will it be in the days of the Son of man;
B042C017V027	42	17	27	when they ate and drank and took wives and gave to husbands, until the day when Nuch entered into the ark, and the deluge came, and destroyed every one.
B042C017V028	42	17	28	So also as it was in the days of Lut; they ate and drank, and bought and sold, and planted and builded;
B042C017V029	42	17	29	but in the day that Lut went forth from Sadum, the Lord rained fire and brimstone from heaven and destroyed them all.
B042C017V030	42	17	30	Thus will it be in the day when the Son of man shall be revealed.
B042C017V031	42	17	31	In that day, he who is on the roof and his garments in the house, let him not go down and take them. And he who is in the field, let him not turn his back.
B042C017V032	42	17	32	Remember the wife of Lut.
B042C017V033	42	17	33	Whoever willeth to save his life shall lose it, and whoever is willing to lose his life shall save it.
B042C017V034	42	17	34	I tell you, that in that night two shall be in one bed; the one shall be taken and the other left.
B042C017V035	42	17	35	Two shall be grinding together, one shall be taken and the other left.
B042C017V036	42	17	36	Two shall be in the field, one shall be taken and the other left.
B042C017V037	42	17	37	They answered and said to him, Where, our Lord? He saith to them, Where the body is, there will be assembled the eagles.
B042C018V001	42	18	1	AND he spake also a parable to them, that in all time (men) should pray and not weary.
B042C018V002	42	18	2	There was a judge in a certain city who of Aloha was not afraid, and of men was not regardful.
B042C018V003	42	18	3	But a certain widow was in that city, who came to him, saying, Avenge me of my adversary.
B042C018V004	42	18	4	And he was not willing long time; but afterward he said within himself, If of Aloha I am not afraid, and of men am not regardful,
B042C018V005	42	18	5	yet, because this widow wearies me, I will avenge her, that in all time she come not molesting me.
B042C018V006	42	18	6	And our Lord said, Hear what saith the unrighteous judge.
B042C018V007	42	18	7	But shall not Aloha do vengeance for his chosen, who cry to him by day and by night, and prolong his spirit towards them?
B042C018V008	42	18	8	I tell you he will avenge them speedily. Nevertheless, when the Son of man shall come, will he find faith upon the earth?
B042C018V009	42	18	9	And he spake this parable against some who trusted in themselves that they were just, and despised all (men):
B042C018V010	42	18	10	Two men went up to the temple to pray, the one a Pharisha, the other a publican;
B042C018V011	42	18	11	and, behold, the Pharisha stood (and) within himself these words prayed: Aloha, I thank thee that I am not as the rest of men, rapacious and unjust, and adulterers; nor as this publican.
B042C018V012	42	18	12	But I fast twice in the week, and tithe whatever I possess.
B042C018V013	42	18	13	But that publican stood from afar, and would not even his eyes lift up to heaven, but smote upon his breast, saying, Aloha, be merciful to me a sinner!
B042C018V014	42	18	14	I tell you that this one went down justified to his house, rather than that Pharisha. For every man who exalteth himself shall be humbled, and every one who humbleth himself shall be exalted.
B042C018V015	42	18	15	Then they brought to him infants, that he should touch them: and the disciples saw it, and rebuked them.
B042C018V016	42	18	16	But Jeshu called them, and said to them, Suffer children to come to me, and forbid them not; for of those who are as these,
B042C018V017	42	18	17	of them is the kingdom of heaven. Amen I say to you, That whoever does not receive the kingdom of Aloha as a child, shall not enter into it.
B042C018V018	42	18	18	AND one of the rulers asked him, saying, Good Teacher, what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?
B042C018V019	42	18	19	Jeshu saith to him, Why callest thou me good, and none is good but one, Aloha?
B042C018V020	42	18	20	The commandments thou knowest, Thou shalt not kill, and, Thou shalt not commit adultery, and, Thou shalt not steal, and, Thou shalt not witness false testimony, Honour thy father and thy mother.
B042C018V021	42	18	21	He saith to him, These all have I kept from my childhood.
B042C018V022	42	18	22	But when Jeshu heard this, he said to him, One thing is lacking with thee; go, sell whatever thou hast, and give to the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in heaven, and come after me.
B042C018V023	42	18	23	But he, when he heard these words, was grieved; for he was very rich.
B042C018V024	42	18	24	And when Jeshu saw that he was grieved, he said, How difficult is it to those who have riches to enter into the kingdom of Aloha!
B042C018V025	42	18	25	It is easier for a camel into the aperture of a needle to enter, than the rich into the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C018V026	42	18	26	They who heard said to him, And who can be saved?
B042C018V027	42	18	27	But Jeshu said, Those (things) which with the sons of men are not possible, with Aloha are possible to be done.
B042C018V028	42	18	28	Shemun Kipha said to him, Behold, we have forsaken every thing, and have come after thee.
B042C018V029	42	18	29	Jeshu saith to him, Amen I say to you, That no man who leaveth houses, or fathers, or brethren, or wife, or children, for the kingdom of Aloha,
B042C018V030	42	18	30	and shall not receive by two-fold (as) many in this time, and in the world that cometh the life that is eternal.
B042C018V031	42	18	31	AND Jeshu took the twelve, and said to them, Behold, we go up to Urishlem, and shall be fulfilled all (things) that are written in the prophets concerning the Son of man.
B042C018V032	42	18	32	For he will be delivered to the Gentiles; and they will deride him, and spit in his face,
B042C018V033	42	18	33	and will scourge him, and maltreat him, and kill him; and the third day he shall arise.
B042C018V034	42	18	34	But not one of these understood they: for this word was hidden from them, and they knew not those sayings which were spoken with them.
B042C018V035	42	18	35	And as he drew nigh to Jirichu, a certain blind man was sitting by the road-side, and begging.
B042C018V036	42	18	36	And he heard the voice of the multitude as it was passing, and asked what was this.
B042C018V037	42	18	37	They say to him, Jeshu Natsroya passeth.
B042C018V038	42	18	38	And he cried and said, Jeshu bar David, have mercy on me!
B042C018V039	42	18	39	And they who went before Jeshu rebuked him, that he might be silent: but he cried out the more, Son of David, have mercy on me!
B042C018V040	42	18	40	And Jeshu stood, and commanded that they should lead him unto him. And when he, approached him, he asked him and said to him,
B042C018V041	42	18	41	What wilt thou I shall do for thee? And he said, My Lord, that I may see.
B042C018V042	42	18	42	And Jeshu said to him, See! thy faith hath saved thee.
B042C018V043	42	18	43	And in an instant he saw, and came after him, and glorified Aloha: and all the people, when they saw, gave praise to Aloha.
B042C019V001	42	19	1	And as Jeshu entered and passed through Jirichu,
B042C019V002	42	19	2	there was a certain man whose name was Zakai; he was rich and chief of the publicans:
B042C019V003	42	19	3	and he wished to see Jeshu, who he was, and could not for the crowd, because in his stature Zakai was small.
B042C019V004	42	19	4	And he ran before Jeshu, and ascended a wild fig-tree to see him, because so he was about to pass.
B042C019V005	42	19	5	And when Jeshu came to that place, he saw him, and said to him, Be in haste, descend, Zakai; for to-day I must be at thy house.
B042C019V006	42	19	6	And he was in haste, and descended, and received him rejoicing.
B042C019V007	42	19	7	But when they all saw (this), they murmured, and said that with a man a sinner he hath gone in to abide.
B042C019V008	42	19	8	But Zakai stood, and said to Jeshu, Behold, my Lord, the dividing of my wealth give I to the poor; and to every man, whatever I have wrongfully taken, fourfold I restore.
B042C019V009	42	19	9	Jeshu saith to him, To-day is there salvation to this house, because this (man) also (is a) son of Abraham.
B042C019V010	42	19	10	For the Son of man came to save that which was lost.
B042C019V011	42	19	11	And when they had heard these things, he added to speak a parable; because he had drawn nigh to Urishlem, and they expected that in that hour would be revealed the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C019V012	42	19	12	And he said, A certain man of a noble house went into a distant country, to receive for himself a kingdom, and to return.
B042C019V013	42	19	13	And he called his ten servants, and gave to them ten minin, and said to them, Trade till I come.
B042C019V014	42	19	14	But his citizens hated him, and sent messengers after him, saying, We are not willing that this should reign over us.
B042C019V015	42	19	15	And having received the kingdom and returned, he spake to call to him those servants to whom he had given the silver, that he might know how every one of them had traded.
B042C019V016	42	19	16	And the first came and said, My lord, thy mani ten minin hath gained.
B042C019V017	42	19	17	He saith to him, Well, good servant: because in a little thou art found faithful, thou shalt have rule over ten towns.
B042C019V018	42	19	18	And the second came and said, My lord, thy mani five minin hath made.
B042C019V019	42	19	19	He saith also to this, Thou also shalt have rule over five towns.
B042C019V020	42	19	20	And the other came and said, My lord, behold thy mani which I have had with me, laid up in a napkin.
B042C019V021	42	19	21	For I feared thee, because thou art a hard man, taking up what thou hadst not laid down, and reaping what thou sowedst not.
B042C019V022	42	19	22	He said to him, From thy own mouth I will judge thee, evil servant: thou didst know that I was a hard man, taking up what I had not laid down, and reaping what I sowed not:
B042C019V023	42	19	23	why (then) gavest thou not my silver upon the table, that when I came I might require it with its increase?
B042C019V024	42	19	24	And to those who stood before him he said, Take from him the mani, and give to him who hath the ten minin.
B042C019V025	42	19	25	They say to him, Our lord, he hath ten minin.
B042C019V026	42	19	26	He saith to them, I tell you, that to every one who hath (it) shall be given; and from him who hath not, that also which he hath shall be taken.
B042C019V027	42	19	27	But those adversaries who would not that I should reign over them, bring them, and slay them before me.
B042C019V028	42	19	28	AND when Jeshu had said these things, he went forward to go to Urishlem.
B042C019V029	42	19	29	And when he came to Bethphage and Beth-ania, at the mount that is called the Place of Olives, he sent two from his disciples,
B042C019V030	42	19	30	and said to them, Go to the village over against us; and as you enter, behold, you will find a colt tied, whereon no man hath ridden: loose and bring him.
B042C019V031	42	19	31	And if any man demand why you loose him, thus say: It is requested by our Lord.
B042C019V032	42	19	32	And they who were sent went and found as he had told them.
B042C019V033	42	19	33	And as they were loosing the colt, the owners of him said to them, Why loose you the colt?
B042C019V034	42	19	34	And they said to them, Because by our Lord it is requested.
B042C019V035	42	19	35	And they brought him to Jeshu; and they cast upon the colt their garments, and Jeshu rode upon him.
B042C019V036	42	19	36	And as they went, they spread their clothes in the way.
B042C019V037	42	19	37	And when he had come nigh to the declivity of the Mount of Olives, the whole assembly of the disciples began to rejoice, and praise Aloha with a high voice, for all the mighty acts which they had seen:
B042C019V038	42	19	38	and they said, Blessed be the King who cometh in the name of the Lord! Peace in the heavens, and glory in the highest!
B042C019V039	42	19	39	But some of the Pharishee from among the multitudes say to him, Rabi, rebuke thy disciples.
B042C019V040	42	19	40	He saith to them, I tell you, if these should be silent, the stones would cry out.
B042C019V041	42	19	41	AND when he approached, and saw the city, he wept over her, saying,
B042C019V042	42	19	42	If thou hadst known these things which are for thy peace, and in this thy day! But now they are hidden from thine eyes.
B042C019V043	42	19	43	But the days will come to thee when thine enemies shall encompass thee and straiten thee on every side,
B042C019V044	42	19	44	and they shall overthrow thee, and thy children within thee, and not leave in thee one stone upon another, because thou knewest not the time of thy visitation.
B042C019V045	42	19	45	And as he went into the temple, he began to cast out those who bought in it and sold,
B042C019V046	42	19	46	and said to them, It is written that my house is the house of prayer; but you have made it a den of thieves.
B042C019V047	42	19	47	And he taught every day in the temple; but the chief priests and the scribes and the elders of the people sought to destroy him,
B042C019V048	42	19	48	but could not find what they might do to him; for all the people hung upon him to hear him.
B042C020V001	42	20	1	AND it was on one of the days, while he taught the people in the temple and evangelized, the chief priests and scribes with the elders rose up against him,
B042C020V002	42	20	2	and said to him, Tell us by what authority thou doest these, and who is he who gave thee this authority?
B042C020V003	42	20	3	Jeshu answered and said to them, I will also ask of you a word, and tell you me:
B042C020V004	42	20	4	the baptism of Juchanon, from heaven was it, or from the sons of men?
B042C020V005	42	20	5	But they reasoned within themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven, he saith to us, Why did you not believe him?
B042C020V006	42	20	6	But if we shall say, From men, all the people will stone us; for they are persuaded that Juchanon was a prophet.
B042C020V007	42	20	7	And they said to him, We know not from whence it is.
B042C020V008	42	20	8	Jeshu saith to them, Nor tell I you by what authority I do these.
B042C020V009	42	20	9	And he began to speak to the people this parable: A certain man planted a vinery, and let it to husbandmen, and removed for a great time.
B042C020V010	42	20	10	And at the season he sent his servant to the husbandmen that they should give him of the fruit of the vinery. But the husbandmen beat him, and sent him away empty.
B042C020V011	42	20	11	And he added and sent another servant; but they beat him also, and maltreated him, and sent him away empty.
B042C020V012	42	20	12	And he added and sent a third; but they also wounded him, and cast him out.
B042C020V013	42	20	13	The lord of the vinery saith, What shall I do? I will send my son, the beloved; now will they see him and reverence him.
B042C020V014	42	20	14	But when the husbandmen saw him, they reasoned among themselves, saying, This is the heir: come, let us kill him, and the inheritance will be ours.
B042C020V015	42	20	15	And they cast him out of the vinery, and killed him. What therefore shall the lord of the vinery do to them?
B042C020V016	42	20	16	He will come and destroy those husbandmen, and will give the vinery to others. But when they heard, they said, May this not be!
B042C020V017	42	20	17	But he beheld them, and said, And what is that which is written, The stone which the builders rejected is become the head of the corner?
B042C020V018	42	20	18	And every one who shall fall upon this stone shall be broken; and every one on whom it shall fall it will scatter him.
B042C020V019	42	20	19	But the chief priests and Sophree sought to lay hands on him in that very hour; but they feared the people, for they knew that concerning them(selves) he had spoken this parable.
B042C020V020	42	20	20	And they sent to him spies, who should resemble just men, that they might take him in discourse, and deliver him to the judgment and to the authority of the governor.
B042C020V021	42	20	21	And they asked him, and said to him, Doctor, we know that thou speakest and teachest rightly, neither dost thou deceive, but with integrity thou teachest the way of Aloha.
B042C020V022	42	20	22	Is it lawful for us to give head-silver to Cesar or not?
B042C020V023	42	20	23	But he understood their subtilty, and said, Why tempt you me?
B042C020V024	42	20	24	Show me a dinara. Of whom upon it is the image and the inscription? But they said, Of Cesar.
B042C020V025	42	20	25	Jeshu saith to them, Give then of Cesar's to Cesar, and of Aloha's unto Aloha.
B042C020V026	42	20	26	And they could not take hold of his words before the people; and they wondered at his answer, and were silent.
B042C020V027	42	20	27	BUT some of the Zadukoyee approached, they who say that there is no resurrection;
B042C020V028	42	20	28	and they questioned him, and said to him, Doctor, Musha wrote to us that if a man's brother die having a wife who hath not children, his brother shall take his wife, and raise up seed unto his brother.
B042C020V029	42	20	29	But there were seven brethren; and the first took; a wife, and died without children.
B042C020V030	42	20	30	And the second took his wife, and he died without children.
B042C020V031	42	20	31	And the third also took her; and so also the seven of them: and they died and left no children.
B042C020V032	42	20	32	Died in the end also the woman.
B042C020V033	42	20	33	In the resurrection therefore, whose of them shall she be the wife? for the seven of them had taken her.
B042C020V034	42	20	34	Jeshu saith to them, The sons of this world take wives, and women become (the wives) of men:
B042C020V035	42	20	35	but they who of that world are worthy, and of the resurrection which is from among the dead, take not wives, neither do women become (the wives) of men.
B042C020V036	42	20	36	Neither again can they die, for they are as the angels; and the children are they of Aloha, because they have become the children of the resurrection.
B042C020V037	42	20	37	But that the dead arise, Musha also showeth; for he commemorateth at the bush, while he saith, The Lord the God of Abraham, and the God of Ishok, and the God of Jakub.
B042C020V038	42	20	38	But he was not the God of the dead, but of the living: for they all live unto him.
B042C020V039	42	20	39	And some of the Sophree answered and said to him, Doctor, thou hast well said.
B042C020V040	42	20	40	And they dared not question him again of any thing.
B042C020V041	42	20	41	AND he said to them, How say the Sophree concerning the Meshicha, that he is the Son of David?
B042C020V042	42	20	42	And David himself saith in the book of Psalms, The Lord said unto my Lord, Sit thou at my right hand,
B042C020V043	42	20	43	until I put thine adversaries beneath thy feet.
B042C020V044	42	20	44	If David therefore calleth him Lord, how is he his son?
B042C020V045	42	20	45	And while all the people heard, he said to his disciples,
B042C020V046	42	20	46	Beware of the Sophree, who will to walk in stoles, and love the shaloma in public places, and the chief seats in the synagogues, and the chief reclining-places at evening feasts;
B042C020V047	42	20	47	who devour the houses of widows, and for the occasion prolong their prayers: these shall receive the greater judgment.
B042C021V001	42	21	1	Jeshu looked at those rich (persons) who were throwing into the house of treasure their oblations.
B042C021V002	42	21	2	And he saw also a certain poor widow who threw in two shomonee.
B042C021V003	42	21	3	And he said, Truth I say to you, That this poor widow hath thrown in more than every one:
B042C021V004	42	21	4	for all those from what abounded to them have thrown into the house of the oblation of Aloha: but this from her penury all that she possessed hath she thrown in.
B042C021V005	42	21	5	AND as some spake of the temple, (with) what beautiful stones and gifts it was adorned, Jeshu said to them,
B042C021V006	42	21	6	These that you see, the days shall come (when) of them there will not be found a stone upon a stone that shall not be destroyed.
B042C021V007	42	21	7	And they inquired of him, and said, Malphona, when shall these be? and what is the sign that these are nigh to be?
B042C021V008	42	21	8	But he said to them, Beware lest you be seduced: for many will come in my name, and will say, I am the Meshicha; and the time hath drawn nigh: but go not you after them.
B042C021V009	42	21	9	And when you hear of wars and commotions, fear not: for these are first to be; but not yet cometh the end.
B042C021V010	42	21	10	For nation shall rise up against nation, and kingdom against kingdom:
B042C021V011	42	21	11	and great earthquakes will be in divers places, and famines, and plagues; and there will be portents, and terrors, and great signs from the heavens will appear, and great tempests shall there be.
B042C021V012	42	21	12	But before all these, they will lay hands upon you, and persecute you, and deliver you up to the synagogues, and to the house of the bound. And they will bring you before kings and governors on account of my name.
B042C021V013	42	21	13	And it shall be to you for a testimony.
B042C021V014	42	21	14	But lay it up in your hearts that you may not be learned for the answer;
B042C021V015	42	21	15	for I will give you a mouth and wisdom which all your adversaries cannot stand against.
B042C021V016	42	21	16	But your fathers, and your brethren, and your kinsfolk, and your friends will betray you, and some of you they shall put to death.
B042C021V017	42	21	17	And you will be hated of all men on account of my name:
B042C021V018	42	21	18	yet a hair of your head shall not perish,
B042C021V019	42	21	19	but in your perseverance you shall possess your souls.
B042C021V020	42	21	20	But when you see Urishlem encompassed by an army, then know that its destruction hath drawn nigh.
B042C021V021	42	21	21	Then let them who are in Jihud escape to the mountain, and they who are within her escape, and let not them who are in the country places enter into her.
B042C021V022	42	21	22	For those (will be) the days of retribution, that all which is written may be fulfilled.
B042C021V023	42	21	23	But woe to those who are with child and to those who suckle in those days! for there will be great distress in the land, and wrath upon this people.
B042C021V024	42	21	24	And they shall fall by the edge of the sword, and be led captive into every place, and Urishlem shall be trodden down of the Gentiles, until shall be fulfilled the times of the Gentiles.
B042C021V025	42	21	25	And there will be signs in the sun, and in the moon, and in the stars, and on earth distress of nations, and smiting of hands from astonishment at the voice of the sea,
B042C021V026	42	21	26	the commotion hurrying forth the souls of the sons of men from fear of what is about to come upon the earth; and the powers of the heavens shall be commoved.
B042C021V027	42	21	27	And then shall they see the Son of man coming in the clouds, with power and great glory.
B042C021V028	42	21	28	But when these things begin to be, take courage, and lift up your heads, because your redemption hath drawn nigh.
B042C021V029	42	21	29	AND he spake to them a parable, Behold the fig-tree and all the trees;
B042C021V030	42	21	30	when they bud forth, immediately from them you know that summer hath drawn nigh.
B042C021V031	42	21	31	Thus also you, when you see that these are, know that nigh is the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C021V032	42	21	32	Amen I say to you, That this race shall not pass away till all these things shall be.
B042C021V033	42	21	33	Heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away.
B042C021V034	42	21	34	But take heed to yourselves, that at any time your hearts be not heavy with excess and drunkenness, and the care of the world, and unawares shall come upon you that day.
B042C021V035	42	21	35	For as a net it will overtake all them who dwell upon the faces of the whole earth.
B042C021V036	42	21	36	Be therefore wakeful at all time, and pray that you may be worthy to escape from those things that are about to be, and that you may stand before the Son of man.
B042C021V037	42	21	37	So in the day (time) he taught in the temple, and at night he went forth and lodged in the mount which is called the Place of Olives.
B042C021V038	42	21	38	And all the people were early with him at the temple to hear his word.
B042C022V001	42	22	1	BUT the feast of the Phatiree, which is called Petscha, drew on.
B042C022V002	42	22	2	And the chief priests and the Sophree sought how they might kill him; for they feared from the people.
B042C022V003	42	22	3	But Satana entered into Jihuda called Scarjuta, who was of the number of the twelve.
B042C022V004	42	22	4	And he went, and spoke with the chief priests, and the Sophree, and the chief authorities of the temple, how he would deliver him to them.
B042C022V005	42	22	5	And they were glad, and confirmed to give him silver.
B042C022V006	42	22	6	And he promised to them, and sought him opportunity to betray him apart from the multitude.
B042C022V007	42	22	7	And the day of unleavened bread came, on which it was the custom to slay the petscha.
B042C022V008	42	22	8	And Jeshu sent Kipha and Juchanon, and said to them, Go prepare for us the petscha, that we may eat.
B042C022V009	42	22	9	But they said to him, Where wilt thou that we prepare?
B042C022V010	42	22	10	He saith to them, When, you have entered into the city, a man meeteth you, bearing a pitcher of waters; go after him, and when he hath gone in,
B042C022V011	42	22	11	say to the lord of the house, Our Master saith, Is there a dining-place where I may eat the petscha with my disciples?
B042C022V012	42	22	12	And he will show you a certain large upper chamber which is furnished: there make ready.
B042C022V013	42	22	13	And they went, and found as he had told them: and they prepared the petscha.
B042C022V014	42	22	14	And when it was time, Jeshu came and reclined, and the twelve apostles with him.
B042C022V015	42	22	15	And he said to them, With desire have I desired to eat this petscha with you before I suffer:
B042C022V016	42	22	16	for I tell you that from henceforth I shall not eat it, until it shall have been fulfilled in the kingdom of Aloha.
B042C022V017	42	22	17	And he took the cup, and praised, and said, Take this, and divide it among yourselves:
B042C022V018	42	22	18	for I tell you that I shall not drink of the fruit of the vine, until the kingdom of Aloha shall have come.
B042C022V019	42	22	19	And he took bread, and praised, and brake, and gave to them, and said, This is my body which for you is given: this do in my memory.
B042C022V020	42	22	20	And thus also respecting the cup, when, after they had supped, he said, This cup is the new covenant in my blood, which for you is shed.
B042C022V021	42	22	21	Nevertheless, the hand of him who betrayeth me is on the table.
B042C022V022	42	22	22	And the Son of man goeth, as he was set apart: nevertheless woe to that man by whom he is betrayed!
B042C022V023	42	22	23	And they began to inquire among themselves, who it was of them who this should do.
B042C022V024	42	22	24	But there was also a contention among them, who of them was the greatest.
B042C022V025	42	22	25	And Jeshu said to them, The kings of the Gentiles are their lords; and they who exercise authority over them, doers of good are called.
B042C022V026	42	22	26	But you, not so: yea, he who is great among you, let him be as the least; and he who is chief, as one who serveth.
B042C022V027	42	22	27	For who is greatest, he who reclineth, or he who serveth? Is not he who reclineth? But I am among you as he who serveth.
B042C022V028	42	22	28	You are they who have remained with me in my temptations.
B042C022V029	42	22	29	And I promise to you, as hath promised to me my Father, a kingdom;
B042C022V030	42	22	30	that you may eat and drink at the table in my kingdom, and may sit upon thrones, and judge the twelve tribes of Isroel.
B042C022V031	42	22	31	AND Jeshu said to Shemun, Shemun, behold, Satana, demandeth to sift thee as wheat;
B042C022V032	42	22	32	but I have prayed for thee, that thy faith may not fail: and thou also, in the time that thou art converted, confirm thy brethren.
B042C022V033	42	22	33	But Shemun said to him, My Lord, with thee I am prepared, and for the house of the bound, and for death.
B042C022V034	42	22	34	Jeshu saith to him, I tell thee, Shemun, that the cock will not crow to-day, till three times thou hast denied that thou knowest me.
B042C022V035	42	22	35	And he said to them, When I sent you without purse, or scrip, or shoes, was any thing wanting to you? They say to him, Nothing.
B042C022V036	42	22	36	He saith to them, Henceforth, he who hath a purse, let him take it, and likewise a scrip also; and he who hath not a sword, let him sell his garment and buy a sword.
B042C022V037	42	22	37	For I tell you also, that what is written must be fulfilled in me, that with the transgressors he was numbered: for all which concerns me must be accomplished.
B042C022V038	42	22	38	And they say to him, Our Lord, behold, here are two swords. He saith to them, They suffice.
B042C022V039	42	22	39	And he came forth, and went, as he was used, to the mount of the Place of Olives; and his disciples also went after him.
B042C022V040	42	22	40	And when come unto the spot, he said to them, Pray that you enter not into temptation.
B042C022V041	42	22	41	And he removed from them as (about the distance of) a stone's throw, and bowed the knee, and prayed,
B042C022V042	42	22	42	and said, Father, if thou wilt, let this cup pass: nevertheless not my will, but thine be done.
B042C022V043	42	22	43	And an angel appeared to him from heaven, who strengthened him.
B042C022V044	42	22	44	And being in terror, more vehemently he prayed, and his sweat was as drops of blood, and fell upon the ground.
B042C022V045	42	22	45	And he arose from prayer, and came to his disciples, and found them asleep, from sorrow.
B042C022V046	42	22	46	And he said to them, Why sleep you? arise and pray, that you enter not into temptation.
B042C022V047	42	22	47	And as he was speaking, behold a multitude, and behold him who was called Jihuda, one of the twelve, coming before them, and he came nigh to Jeshu, and kissed him: for this was the sign he had given to them, He whom I shall kiss is he.
B042C022V048	42	22	48	Jeshu saith to him, Jihuda, with the kiss betrayest thou the Son of man?
B042C022V049	42	22	49	But when they who were with him saw what was done, they say to him, Our Lord, shall we strike with the sword?
B042C022V050	42	22	50	And one of them struck the servant of the high priest, and took off his right ear.
B042C022V051	42	22	51	Jeshu answered and said, It sufficeth until this; and he touched his ear which he had struck, and healed it.
B042C022V052	42	22	52	And Jeshu said to them who had come against him, the chief priests, and elders, and the chiefs of the forces of the temple, As against a thief are you come forth against me, with swords and clubs to take me?
B042C022V053	42	22	53	Every day with you have I been in the temple, and you did not stretch forth upon me (your) hands; but this is your hour and the power of darkness.
B042C022V054	42	22	54	And they took (and) brought him to the house of the chief of the priests; and Shemun came after him from afar.
B042C022V055	42	22	55	Now they had kindled a fire in the midst of the hall, and were sitting around it, and Shemun also sat with them.
B042C022V056	42	22	56	And a certain damsel saw him as he sat by the fire, and, looking at him, she said, This also was with him.
B042C022V057	42	22	57	But he denied, and said, Woman, I know him not.
B042C022V058	42	22	58	And after a little while, another saw him, and said, Thou also art of them. But Kipha said, I am not.
B042C022V059	42	22	59	And after one hour another contended and said, Assuredly this also was with him, for he is also a Galiloya.
B042C022V060	42	22	60	Kipha saith, Man, I know not what thou sayest. And at once, while he was speaking, the cock crew.
B042C022V061	42	22	61	And Jeshu turned, and looked upon Kipha; and Shemun remembered his word which our Lord had spoken to him, that before the cock shall crow thou wilt have denied me three times.
B042C022V062	42	22	62	And Shemun went without and wept bitterly.
B042C022V063	42	22	63	And the men who held Jeshu mocked him,
B042C022V064	42	22	64	and veiled him, and they struck him upon the face, saying, Prophesy, who struck thee.
B042C022V065	42	22	65	And many other things they blasphemed and spake against him.
B042C022V066	42	22	66	AND when it dawned, the elders and chief priests and the Sophree came together, and took him into the house of their assembly; saying to him,
B042C022V067	42	22	67	Art thou the Meshicha? tell us. He saith to them, Should I tell you, you would not believe me;
B042C022V068	42	22	68	and were I to ask you, you would not return me a word, nor release me.
B042C022V069	42	22	69	Henceforth the Son of man sitteth at the right hand of the power of Aloha.
B042C022V070	42	22	70	Then said they all, Thou art, then, the Son of Aloha? Jeshu saith to them, You say that I am.
B042C022V071	42	22	71	They say, Why yet need we witnesses? for we have heard from his mouth.
B042C023V001	42	23	1	And the whole assembly of them arose, and brought him to Pilatos.
B042C023V002	42	23	2	And they began to accuse him, saying, We have found this who deludeth our people, and forbiddeth that tribute unto Caesar we should give, saying of himself that he is the King Meshicha.
B042C023V003	42	23	3	But Pilatos asked him, and said to him, Art thou the king of the Jihudoyee? He saith to him, Thou hast said.
B042C023V004	42	23	4	And Pilatos said to the chief priests and to the assembly, I find no occasion against this man.
B042C023V005	42	23	5	But they cried out and said, He commoveth our people while he teacheth throughout all Jihud, beginning from Galila unto this place.
B042C023V006	42	23	6	Pilatos, however, when he heard the name of Galila, asked if the man were a Galiloya.
B042C023V007	42	23	7	And when he knew that he was from the limit of the jurisdiction of Herodes, he sent him unto Herodes, because that in Urishlem he was in those days.
B042C023V008	42	23	8	And Herodes, when he saw Jeshu, was very glad; for he had desired to see him of a great time: for he had heard concerning him many things, and hoped that some sign he should see from him.
B042C023V009	42	23	9	And many words he asked him; but Jeshu gave him no answer whatever.
B042C023V010	42	23	10	And the chief priests and scribes stood and strenuously accused him.
B042C023V011	42	23	11	Then Herodes and his soldiers treated him as a fool; and when he had derided him, he dressed him in a robe of crimson, and sent him to Pilatos.
B042C023V012	42	23	12	And in that day Pilatos and Herodes were friends with each other; for before there had been enmity between them.
B042C023V013	42	23	13	And Pilatos called the chief priests and the rulers of the people,
B042C023V014	42	23	14	and said to them, You have brought to me this man as a perverter of your people; and, behold, I have examined him in your sight, and have found no cause in this man of all that you accuse him:
B042C023V015	42	23	15	nor also Herodes; for I sent him unto him, and, behold, nothing worthy of death is done to him:
B042C023V016	42	23	16	I will therefore chastise him, and dismiss him.
B042C023V017	42	23	17	For a custom had he to release to them one at the festival.
B042C023V018	42	23	18	But all the multitude cried out, saying, Take this, and release to us Baraba;
B042C023V019	42	23	19	he who, for insurrection and murder which had been done in the city, had been thrown into the house of the chained.
B042C023V020	42	23	20	But Pilatos spake with them again, being willing to release Jeshu.
B042C023V021	42	23	21	But they cried out, saying, Crucify him! Crucify him!
B042C023V022	42	23	22	He the third time also said to them, Why, what evil hath this done? Cause whatever that is worthy of death, I find not in him: I will therefore chastise him, and dismiss him.
B042C023V023	42	23	23	But they were urgent with a high voice, demanding that they might crucify him; and theirs and the voices of the high priests prevailed.
B042C023V024	42	23	24	And Pilatos commanded that their requirement should be done.
B042C023V025	42	23	25	And he released to them him who, for insurrection and murder, had been thrown into the house of the chained, whom they had asked: but Jeshu he delivered to their will.
B042C023V026	42	23	26	AND as they led him away, they laid hold on Shemun Kurinoya, who was coming from the country, and they laid on him the cross, that he might bear (it) after Jeshu.
B042C023V027	42	23	27	And there followed him much people, and those women who mourned and wailed for him.
B042C023V028	42	23	28	And Jeshu turned to them, and said, Daughters of Urishlem, weep not for me, but for yourselves weep, and for your children.
B042C023V029	42	23	29	For, behold, coming are the days in which they shall say, Blessed are the barren, and the wombs which have not borne, and the breasts that have not suckled.
B042C023V030	42	23	30	Then shall they begin to say to the mountains, Fall on us! and to the heights, Cover us!
B042C023V031	42	23	31	For if to the tree which is good they do these things, unto the dry what shall be?
B042C023V032	42	23	32	And there went with him two others, workers of evil, to be put to death.
B042C023V033	42	23	33	And when they came to a certain place called Karkaphtha, there they crucified him, and those workers of evil, one on his right hand, and one on his left.
B042C023V034	42	23	34	BUT Jeshu himself said, Father, forgive them; for they know not what they do. And they divided his garments, and cast for them lots.
B042C023V035	42	23	35	But the people stood beholding, and the rulers also, mocking him, and saying, He saved others, let him save himself, if he be the Meshicha, the Chosen of God.
B042C023V036	42	23	36	And the soldiers also, deriding him, approaching him, and offering to him vinegar,
B042C023V037	42	23	37	said to him, If thou art the King of the Jihudoyee, save thyself.
B042C023V038	42	23	38	And there was also an inscription which was written over him in Greek and Roman and Hebrew, THIS IS THE KING OF THE JIHUDOYEE.
B042C023V039	42	23	39	And one of those workers of evil who were hanged with him, blasphemed against him, saying, If thou art the Meshicha, deliver thyself, and deliver us also.
B042C023V040	42	23	40	And his companion rebuked him, and said to him, Dost thou not fear (even) Aloha? for thou also art in this judgment.
B042C023V041	42	23	41	And we righteously, forasmuch as we have been deserving, and as we are punished for that which we have done;
B042C023V042	42	23	42	but this hath done nothing that is abominable. And he said to Jeshu, Remember me, my Lord, when thou art come into thy kingdom!
B042C023V043	42	23	43	Jeshu saith to him, Amen I say to thee, That to-day with me thou shalt be in Paradise.
B042C023V044	42	23	44	NOW it was about six hours, and there was darkness over all the earth until nine hours.
B042C023V045	42	23	45	And the sun darkened, and rent was the vail of the temple through the midst of it.
B042C023V046	42	23	46	And Jeshu cried with a high voice, and said, My Father, in thy hands I place my spirit. This he said, and completed.
B042C023V047	42	23	47	But when the centurion saw what was done, he glorified Aloha, saying, Assuredly this was a just man.
B042C023V048	42	23	48	And all the multitude, they who were assembled to see this, when they saw what was done, returned, smiting upon their breasts.
B042C023V049	42	23	49	And there were standing afar off all the acquaintances of Jeshu, and those women who came with him from Galila; and they saw these things.
B042C023V050	42	23	50	BUT a certain man, whose name was Jauseph, a senator from Rometha, a city of Jehud, a man (who) was good and just:
B042C023V051	42	23	51	(this had not consented to the counsel and deed of them; and he was waiting for the kingdom of Aloha:)
B042C023V052	42	23	52	this approached Pilatos, and begged the body of Jeshu;
B042C023V053	42	23	53	and he took it down, and wrapped it in a cloth of linen, and laid it in a hewn sepulchre, in which no one had hitherto been laid.
B042C023V054	42	23	54	And it was the day of the preparation; and the shabath had lighted.
B042C023V055	42	23	55	And the women also drew near, they who had come with him from Galila; and they saw the sepulchre, and where the body was laid;
B042C023V056	42	23	56	and, returned, they prepared balsams and aromatics, and on the shabath rested, as it is commanded.
B042C024V001	42	24	1	But on the first (day) in the week, in the morning, while yet dark, they came to the sepulchre, and brought those aromatics which they had prepared;
B042C024V002	42	24	2	and with them there were other women. And they found the stone rolled from the sepulchre,
B042C024V003	42	24	3	and entered, but found not the body of Jeshu.
B042C024V004	42	24	4	And it was that while they were amazed at this, behold, two men stood over against them, and whose raiment shined;
B042C024V005	42	24	5	and they were in fear, and bowed their faces to the earth. And they said to them, Why are you seeking the living with the dead?
B042C024V006	42	24	6	He is not here, he is risen. Remember what he spake with you while he was in Galila,
B042C024V007	42	24	7	and (when he) said, The Son of man must be delivered into the hands of men of sins, and he will be crucified, and (in) the third of the days he will arise.
B042C024V008	42	24	8	And they remembered his words,
B042C024V009	42	24	9	and returned from the sepulchre, and told all these (things) unto the eleven, and to the rest.
B042C024V010	42	24	10	Now it was Mariam Magdalitha, Juchanon, and Mariam his mother, and Jacub, and the rest who were with them, who told these (occurrences) to the apostles.
B042C024V011	42	24	11	And these words appeared in their eyes as dreams, and they believed them not.
B042C024V012	42	24	12	But Shemun arose, and ran to the sepulchre, and, looking in, he saw the linen clothes lying apart; and he went away, wondering in himself at what was done.
B042C024V013	42	24	13	AND, behold, two of them in that day went to a village whose name was Emaos, and distant from Urishlem sixty stadia.
B042C024V014	42	24	14	And they talked one with the other of all these (events) which had happened.
B042C024V015	42	24	15	And while they discoursed and investigated one with the other, Jeshu himself came and went with them, and walked with them.
B042C024V016	42	24	16	And their eyes were holden, that they should not know him.
B042C024V017	42	24	17	And he said to them, What are these words that you speak with each other, as you walk and are sad?
B042C024V018	42	24	18	And one of them answered, whose name was Kleopha, and said to him, Art thou only a stranger from Urishlem, who knowest not what hath been done in it in these days?
B042C024V019	42	24	19	He saith to them, What? They say to him, Concerning Jeshu, who was of Natsrath, a man who was a prophet, and mighty in word and in deed before Aloha, and before all the people.
B042C024V020	42	24	20	And the chief priests and elders delivered him to the judgment of death, and crucified him.
B042C024V021	42	24	21	But we had hoped that it was he who shall redeem Isroel; and, lo, three days (have passed) since all these things were done.
B042C024V022	42	24	22	But women also of us have astonished us; for they were before at the sepulchre;
B042C024V023	42	24	23	and when they found not his body, they came and told us that angels they had seen there, and (that) they had said concerning him that he was alive.
B042C024V024	42	24	24	And some also of us went to the sepulchre, and found even as the women had said, but him they saw not.
B042C024V025	42	24	25	Then said Jeshu to them, O wanting in understanding, and hard of heart to believe all the things which the prophets have spoken!
B042C024V026	42	24	26	Was it not to be that these the Meshicha should suffer, and enter into his glory?
B042C024V027	42	24	27	And, beginning from Musha and all the prophets, he explained to them concerning himself from all the scriptures.
B042C024V028	42	24	28	And they drew near to that village to which they were going; and he made them suppose that to a more distant place he was going.
B042C024V029	42	24	29	And they constrained him, and said to him, Abide with us, because the day now inclines to darken. And he went in to remain with them.
B042C024V030	42	24	30	And it was that, while he reclined with them, he took bread, and blessed, and brake, and gave to them.
B042C024V031	42	24	31	And at once their eyes were opened, and they knew him; and he was taken from them.
B042C024V032	42	24	32	And they said one to the other, Did not our hearts burn within us, while he spake with us by the way, and explained to us the scriptures?
B042C024V033	42	24	33	And they arose in the same hour, and returned to Urishlem, and found the eleven, who were assembled, and they who were with them,
B042C024V034	42	24	34	saying, Assuredly our Lord is risen, and hath appeared unto Shemun.
B042C024V035	42	24	35	And they also declared those things which had happened in the way, and how he was made known to them while he brake the bread.
B042C024V036	42	24	36	AND while they were discoursing, Jeshu stood among them, and said to them, Peace be with you!
B042C024V037	42	24	37	I am; fear not. And they were troubled, and were in fear; for they thought they beheld a spirit.
B042C024V038	42	24	38	Jeshu saith to them, Why are you perturbed, and why arise thoughts in your hearts?
B042C024V039	42	24	39	Behold my hands and my feet, that it is I: feel me, and see; for a spirit hath not flesh and bones, as you see that I have.
B042C024V040	42	24	40	And while these words he spake, he showed them his hands and his feet.
B042C024V041	42	24	41	And while they as yet believed not for joy, and wondered, he said to them, Have you here somewhat to eat?
B042C024V042	42	24	42	And they gave to him a portion of broiled fish, and of the comb of honey;
B042C024V043	42	24	43	and he took (and) did eat before their eyes.
B042C024V044	42	24	44	And he said to them, These are the words that I spoke with you while I was with you, that every thing must be fulfilled which is written in the law of Musha, and in the Prophets, and in the Psalms, concerning me.
B042C024V045	42	24	45	Then opened he their minds, that they might understand the scriptures.
B042C024V046	42	24	46	And he said to them, that so it is written, and so it was just, that the Meshicha should suffer, and should rise from among the dead in the three days,
B042C024V047	42	24	47	and that in his name should be preached repentance and the forgiveness of sins among all nations, and that the commencement should be from Urishlem.
B042C024V048	42	24	48	And you are the witnesses of these. And I will send upon you the promise of my Father.
B042C024V049	42	24	49	But await you in Urishlem the city until you be clothed with power from on high.
B042C024V050	42	24	50	And he brought them out unto Bethania, and lifted up his hands, and blessed them.
B042C024V051	42	24	51	And it was that while he blessed them, he was separated from them, and he ascended to the heavens.
B042C024V052	42	24	52	And they worshipped him, and returned to Urishlem with great joy. And at all time were they in the temple,
B042C024V053	42	24	53	praising and blessing Aloha. Amen.
B043C001V001	43	1	1	IN the beginning was the Word, and the Word himself was with Aloha, and Aloha was the Word himself.
B043C001V002	43	1	2	This was in the beginning with Aloha.
B043C001V003	43	1	3	Every thing by his hand was made; and without him also was not one thing made that was made.
B043C001V004	43	1	4	In him was life, and the life is the light of the sons of man;
B043C001V005	43	1	5	and the Light himself in the darkness shineth, and the darkness perceived him not.
B043C001V006	43	1	6	There was a man who was sent from Aloha, his name (was) Juchanon.
B043C001V007	43	1	7	He came for the testimony, to testify concerning the Light, that all men might believe through his ministry.
B043C001V008	43	1	8	He was not the Light himself, but came to testify concerning the Light.
B043C001V009	43	1	9	For that was the true Light that enlighteneth every man who cometh into the world.
B043C001V010	43	1	10	In the world was he, and the world by his hand had been made, and the world knew him not.
B043C001V011	43	1	11	He came to his own, and his own received him not.
B043C001V012	43	1	12	But they who received him, he gave to them power, that the sons of Aloha they should become, to those who believe in his name.
B043C001V013	43	1	13	These, not from blood, nor from the will of the flesh, nor from the will of man, but from Aloha, are born.
B043C001V014	43	1	14	And the Word flesh was made, and tabernacled with us; and we saw his glory, the glory as of the one-begotten who (was) from the Father, full of grace and truth.
B043C001V015	43	1	15	Juchanon testified concerning him, and cried, and said, This is he of whom I said, that he cometh after me, and was before me, because he is anterior to me.
B043C001V016	43	1	16	And from his fulness we all have received, and grace for grace.
B043C001V017	43	1	17	For the law by the hand of Musha was given; but the truth and the grace were by Jeshu Meshicha.
B043C001V018	43	1	18	ALOHA no man hath ever seen: the one-begotten God, he who is in the bosom of his Father, he hath declared him.
B043C001V019	43	1	19	And this was the testimony of Juchanon, when the Jihudoyee sent to him from Urishlem priests and Levoyee to demand of him, Who art thou?
B043C001V020	43	1	20	And he confessed, and denied not, but confessed, I am not the Meshicha.
B043C001V021	43	1	21	And they asked him again, What then? art thou Elia? And he said, I am not. Art thou the Prophet? And he said, No.
B043C001V022	43	1	22	And they said to him, And who art thou? that we may give an answer to those who sent us. What sayest thou of thyself?
B043C001V023	43	1	23	He saith, I am the voice which crieth in the wilderness, Make plain the way of the Lord, as said Eshaia the prophet.
B043C001V024	43	1	24	But they who were sent were from the Pharishee.
B043C001V025	43	1	25	And they demanded and said to him, Why then baptizest thou, if thou art not the Meshicha, nor Elia, nor the Prophet?
B043C001V026	43	1	26	Juchanon answered and said to them, I baptize you with waters; but he standeth among you whom you know not:
B043C001V027	43	1	27	he it is who cometh after me, and he was before me; he, the latchets of whose shoes I am not worthy to unloose.
B043C001V028	43	1	28	These things were done in Bethania, at the passage of the Jurdan, where Juchanon was baptizing.
B043C001V029	43	1	29	AND the day after, Juchanon seeth Jeshu, who was coming to him; and he said, Behold the Lamb of Aloha, who beareth the sin of the world!
B043C001V030	43	1	30	This is he concerning whom I said, After me cometh a man, and he was before me, because he is anterior to me.
B043C001V031	43	1	31	And I knew him not, but that he should be made known unto Isroel, therefore have I come with waters to baptize.
B043C001V032	43	1	32	And Juchanon testified and said, I saw the Spirit descending from heaven as a dove, and it remained upon him.
B043C001V033	43	1	33	And I knew him not: but he who sent me to baptize with water, he said to me, He upon whom thou seest the Spirit descend and remain, this baptizeth with the Spirit of Holiness:
B043C001V034	43	1	34	and I saw, and bare witness that this is the Son of Aloha
B043C001V035	43	1	35	And the day after Juchanon stood, and two of his disciples;
B043C001V036	43	1	36	and, contemplating Jeshu as he walked, he said, Behold the Lamb of Aloha!
B043C001V037	43	1	37	And his two disciples heard him as he spake, and they went after Jeshu.
B043C001V038	43	1	38	And Jeshu turned (himself), and saw them coming after him, and said to them, Whom seek you? They say to him, Raban, where dwellest thou?
B043C001V039	43	1	39	He saith to them, Come and see. And they went and saw where he dwelt; and they were with him that day: and it was about the tenth hour.
B043C001V040	43	1	40	Now one of those who heard Juchanon and went after Jeshu, was Andreas, the brother of Shemun.
B043C001V041	43	1	41	This saw first Shemun his brother, and said to him, We have found the Meshicha;
B043C001V042	43	1	42	and he brought him to Jeshu. And Jeshu saw him, and said, Thou art Shemun bar Jona; thou shalt be called Kipha.
B043C001V043	43	1	43	AND the day following Jeshu willed to go forth into Galila. And he found Philipos, and said to him, Come after me.
B043C001V044	43	1	44	Now Philipos was from Beth-tsaida, from the city of Andreas and of Shemun.
B043C001V045	43	1	45	Philipos found Nathanael, and said to him, Him of whom Musha in the law, and the prophets, did write we have found, (and) that Jeshu (is) he, the son of Jauseph who is from Natsrath.
B043C001V046	43	1	46	Saith to him Nathanael, From Natsrath can any good thing be? Philipos saith to him, Come and see.
B043C001V047	43	1	47	And Jeshu saw Nathanael as he was coming to him, and said of him, Behold truly a son of Isroel who hath no guile in him.
B043C001V048	43	1	48	Nathanael saith to him, Whence knowest thou me? Jeshu saith to him, While yet Philipos had not called thee, while thou wast under the fig-tree, I saw thee.
B043C001V049	43	1	49	Nathanael answered and said to him, Rabi, thou art the Son of Aloha himself, thou art the very King of Isroel.
B043C001V050	43	1	50	Jeshu saith to him, Upon my telling thee that I saw thee under the fig-tree, believest thou? Greater things than these thou shalt see.
B043C001V051	43	1	51	He saith to him, Amen, amen, I say to you, Hereafter you shall see the heavens opened, and the angels of Aloha ascending and descending unto the Son of man.
B043C002V001	43	2	1	AND on the third day there was a feast in Kotna, a city of Galila; and the mother of Jeshu was there:
B043C002V002	43	2	2	and Jeshu and his disciples were called to the feast.
B043C002V003	43	2	3	And the wine failed, and his mother saith to him, to Jeshu, They have no wine.
B043C002V004	43	2	4	Jeshu saith to her, What (is it) to me and to thee, woman? Not yet hath come mine hour.
B043C002V005	43	2	5	His mother saith to the servitors, Whatever he telleth you, do.
B043C002V006	43	2	6	Now there were six waterpots of stone set there, unto the purification of the Jihudoyee, which contained each two quarantals or three.
B043C002V007	43	2	7	Jeshu saith to them, Fill these water-pots with waters; and they filled them to the top.
B043C002V008	43	2	8	He saith to them, Draw now, and carry to the chief of the guests. And they carried.
B043C002V009	43	2	9	And when that chief of the guests had tasted those waters which were made wine, and knew not whence it was, (but the servitors knew, who had filled them with waters,) the chief of the guests called the bridegroom,
B043C002V010	43	2	10	and said to him, Every man at first the good wine produceth, and when they are satisfied, then that which is inferior; but thou hast kept the good wine until now.
B043C002V011	43	2	11	This is the first sign that Jeshu wrought in Kotna of Galila, and manifested his glory; and his disciples believed in him.
B043C002V012	43	2	12	AFTER this he went to Kapher-nachum, he and his mother and his brethren and his disciples. And they were there a few days.
B043C002V013	43	2	13	And the petscha of the Jihudoyee was nigh, and Jeshu went up to Urishlem.
B043C002V014	43	2	14	And he found in the temple those who sold oxen and sheep and doves, and the money-changers sitting.
B043C002V015	43	2	15	And he made him a scourge of cord, and drove them all from the temple, and the sheep and the oxen and the money-changers; and he shed their money, and their tables he overturned.
B043C002V016	43	2	16	And to those who sold doves he said, Take these hence; make not the house of my Father a house of merchandise.
B043C002V017	43	2	17	And his disciples remembered that it was written, The zeal of thy house hath devoured me.
B043C002V018	43	2	18	The Jihudoyee answered and said to him, What sign showest thou to us, as these things thou doest?
B043C002V019	43	2	19	Jeshu answered, Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it.
B043C002V020	43	2	20	The Jihudoyee say to him, Forty-and six years was this temple being built, and wilt thou in three days raise it?
B043C002V021	43	2	21	But he spake of the temple of his body.
B043C002V022	43	2	22	But when he was risen from the house of the dead, his disciples remembered that this he had said; and they believed the scriptures, and the word which Jeshu had spoken.
B043C002V023	43	2	23	WHILE Jeshu was in Jerusalem at the petscha, at the feast, Many believed in him who saw the signs which he wrought.
B043C002V024	43	2	24	But he, Jeshu, did not confide himself to them, because he knew every man,
B043C002V025	43	2	25	and needed not that any should testify to him concerning any man, because he knew what is in man.
B043C003V001	43	3	1	But there was one of the Pharishee whose name was Nikodimos, a ruler of the Jihudoyee:
B043C003V002	43	3	2	this came to Jeshu in the night, and said to him, Rabi, we know that from Aloha thou art sent a teacher; for no man can these signs perform which thou doest, unless Aloha be with him.
B043C003V003	43	3	3	Jeshu answered and said to him, Amen, amen, I say to thee, Except a man be born anew, he cannot see the kingdom of Aloha.
B043C003V004	43	3	4	Nikodimos said to him, How can an old man be born? Who can again the womb of his mother the second time enter, and be born?
B043C003V005	43	3	5	Jeshu answered and said to him, Amen, amen, I say to thee, That if a man be not born of waters and the Spirit, he cannot enter into the kingdom of Aloha.
B043C003V006	43	3	6	Whatever is born of the flesh, is flesh; and whatever is born of the Spirit, is spirit.
B043C003V007	43	3	7	Wonder not that I have said to thee, that it behoves you to be born anew.
B043C003V008	43	3	8	The wind bloweth where she willeth, and her voice thou hearest; but thou knowest not whence she cometh, nor whither she goeth: so is every man who is born of the Spirit.
B043C003V009	43	3	9	Nikodimos answered and said to him, How can these things be?
B043C003V010	43	3	10	Jeshu answered and said to him, Art thou Malphona of Israel, and these knowest not?
B043C003V011	43	3	11	Amen, amen, I say to thee, What we know we speak, and what we have seen we testify; but our testimony you receive not.
B043C003V012	43	3	12	If of (what is) on earth I tell you, and you believe not, how if I tell you of (what is) in heaven, could you believe me?
B043C003V013	43	3	13	AND no man hath ascended into heaven, but he who descended from heaven, the Son of man, he who is in heaven.
B043C003V014	43	3	14	And as Musha elevated the serpent in the wilderness, so is to be elevated the Son of man,
B043C003V015	43	3	15	that every man who believeth in him might not perish, but have the life which is eternal.
B043C003V016	43	3	16	For so loved Aloha the world, as his Son, the Only-begotten, he would give, that every one who believeth in him might not perish, but have the life which is eternal.
B043C003V017	43	3	17	For Aloha sent not his Son into the world to condemn the world, but that the world might live by him.
B043C003V018	43	3	18	He who believeth on him is not judged, and he who believeth not is judged already, because he believeth not in the name of the only-begotten Son of Aloha.
B043C003V019	43	3	19	And this is the judgment, that the light hath come into the world, and the sons of men have loved darkness rather than the light, for their deeds have been evil.
B043C003V020	43	3	20	For every one who doeth abominable things hateth the light, and cometh not to the light, lest his deeds should be reproved.
B043C003V021	43	3	21	But he who doeth the truth cometh to the light, that his works may be known that in Aloha they are wrought.
B043C003V022	43	3	22	AFTER these came Jeshu and his disciples into the land of Jihuda, and there conversed with them and baptized.
B043C003V023	43	3	23	But Juchanon also was baptizing in Ein-yon, near Sholim, because the waters were there many; and they came and were baptized;
B043C003V024	43	3	24	for not yet was Juchanon cast into the house of the bound.
B043C003V025	43	3	25	But there was a question with some of the disciples of Juchanon (and) a certain Jihudoya, upon purification.
B043C003V026	43	3	26	And they came to Juchanon, and said to him, Raban, he who was with thee at the passage of Jurdan, (and) concerning whom thou didst give witness, he also baptizeth, and many come to him.
B043C003V027	43	3	27	Juchanon answered and said to them, A man cannot receive of his own will any thing, unless it be given to him from heaven.
B043C003V028	43	3	28	You bear me witness that I said, I am not the Meshicha, but I am an apostle before him.
B043C003V029	43	3	29	He that hath the bride is the bridegroom; but the friend of the bridegroom, who standeth and attendeth him, with great joy rejoiceth on account of the voice of the bridegroom: this my joy therefore, behold, is complete.
B043C003V030	43	3	30	To him it must be to increase, and to me to decrease.
B043C003V031	43	3	31	For he who from above hath come, is above all; and he who is from the earth, is of the earth, and of the earth speaketh: he who from heaven hath come, is above all.
B043C003V032	43	3	32	And what he hath seen and heard he testifieth, and his testimony no man receiveth.
B043C003V033	43	3	33	But he who hath received his testimony, hath sealed that the true Aloha is he.
B043C003V034	43	3	34	For he whom Aloha hath sent, the very words of Aloha speaketh; for it was not in measure that Aloha gave the Spirit.
B043C003V035	43	3	35	The Father loveth the Son, and every thing hath he given into his hands.
B043C003V036	43	3	36	He who believeth in the Son hath the life which is eternal; and he who obeyeth not the Son shall not see life, but the wrath of Aloha remaineth on him.
B043C004V001	43	4	1	But when Jeshu knew that the Pharishee had heard that he had made many disciples, and baptized more than Juchanon,
B043C004V002	43	4	2	(though it was not Jeshu himself baptized, but his disciples,)
B043C004V003	43	4	3	he left Jihuda, and came again into Galila.
B043C004V004	43	4	4	AND he needed that in going he should pass through among the Shomroyee;
B043C004V005	43	4	5	and he came to a city of the Shomroyee which is called Shokar, nigh to the field which Jakub gave unto Jauseph his son.
B043C004V006	43	4	6	And the fountain of water of Jakub was there. But Jeshu was wearied with the labour of the way, and sat by the fountain; and it was six hours.
B043C004V007	43	4	7	There came a woman from Shomreen to draw waters, and Jeshu said to her, Give me waters to drink.
B043C004V008	43	4	8	Now his disciples had gone into the city to buy for them meat.
B043C004V009	43	4	9	The woman, the Shomroytha, saith to him, How (canst) thou who art a Jihudoya ask drink of me who am a woman, a Shomroytha? For the Jihudoyee have no accommodation with the Shomroyee.
B043C004V010	43	4	10	Jeshu answered and said to her, If thou hadst known the gift of Aloha, and who He is who hath said to thee, Give me to drink, thou wouldst have asked of him, and he had given thee living waters.
B043C004V011	43	4	11	That woman saith to him, My Lord, thou hast no vessel, and the well is deep; whence hast thou living waters?
B043C004V012	43	4	12	Art thou greater than our father Jakub, he who gave us this well, and himself drank of it, and his children, and his flocks?
B043C004V013	43	4	13	Jeshu answered and said to her, Every one who shall drink of these waters again will thirst;
B043C004V014	43	4	14	but every one who shall drink of the waters that I will give him shall never thirst; but those waters that I shall give him shall be in him a fountain of waters, that shall spring forth to the life of eternity.
B043C004V015	43	4	15	That woman saith to him, My Lord, give me of those waters, that I thirst not again, nor come to draw from hence.
B043C004V016	43	4	16	Jeshu saith to her, Go, call thy husband, and come hither.
B043C004V017	43	4	17	She saith to him, I have no husband. Jeshu saith to her, Well hast thou said, I have no husband;
B043C004V018	43	4	18	for five husbands hast thou had, and this whom thou now hast is not thy husband; this hast thou said truly.
B043C004V019	43	4	19	That woman saith to him, My Lord, I perceive that thou art a prophet.
B043C004V020	43	4	20	Our fathers in this mountain worshipped, and you say that in Urishlem is the place where it behoves to worship.
B043C004V021	43	4	21	Jeshu saith to her, Woman, believe me that the hour cometh when neither in this mountain, nor at Urishlem, you shall worship the Father:
B043C004V022	43	4	22	you worship something you know not; but we worship whom we know; for salvation is from the Jihudoyee.
B043C004V023	43	4	23	But the hour cometh, and now is, when the true worshippers will worship the Father in spirit and in truth; for the Father also requireth worshippers such as these.
B043C004V024	43	4	24	For Aloha is a Spirit; and they who worship him, in spirit and in truth must worship.
B043C004V025	43	4	25	That woman saith to him, I know that the Meshicha cometh; and when he hath come, he will teach us all things.
B043C004V026	43	4	26	Jeshu saith to her, I am (he), I who speak with thee.
B043C004V027	43	4	27	And as he spoke, his disciples came, and they wondered that with the woman he spoke; but no man said, What inquirest thou? or, Why speakest thou with her?
B043C004V028	43	4	28	The woman left her water-pot, and went into the city, and saith,
B043C004V029	43	4	29	Come, see a man who hath told me every thing that I have done: is not this the Meshicha?
B043C004V030	43	4	30	And the men went out of the city, and came with her.
B043C004V031	43	4	31	Between these things his disciples entreated of him, saying to him, Raban, eat.
B043C004V032	43	4	32	But he said to them, I have food to eat of which you know not.
B043C004V033	43	4	33	The disciples say among themselves, Has any man brought him somewhat to eat?
B043C004V034	43	4	34	Jeshu saith to them, My meat is to do the will of Him who sent me, and to accomplish his work.
B043C004V035	43	4	35	Say you not, that after four moons cometh harvest? Behold, I tell you, Lift up your eyes, and see the lands which have become white for the harvest already.
B043C004V036	43	4	36	And he who reapeth receiveth wages, and gathereth fruit unto life eternal; and the sower and the reaper shall rejoice together.
B043C004V037	43	4	37	For in this is the proverb true, One soweth, and another reapeth.
B043C004V038	43	4	38	I sent you to reap that (for) which you did not toil; for others toiled, and you have entered upon their labour.
B043C004V039	43	4	39	Now of that city many Shomroyee believed in him, because of the saying of that woman, who testified, He told me every thing that I have done.
B043C004V040	43	4	40	And when those Shomroyee came to him, they besought him to be with them. And he was with them two days,
B043C004V041	43	4	41	and many believed through his word.
B043C004V042	43	4	42	And they said to the woman, Now not through thy word believe we in him; for we have heard and known that this is truly the Meshicha, the Saviour of the world.
B043C004V043	43	4	43	AND after two days Jeshu went forth from thence, and came into Galila;
B043C004V044	43	4	44	for he himself testified, that a prophet in his own city is not honoured.
B043C004V045	43	4	45	But when he came to Galila, the Galiloyee received him, because they had seen all the signs which he had done in Urishlem at the feast; for they also went to the feast.
B043C004V046	43	4	46	So Jeshu came again into Kotna of Galila, where he had made the waters wine. And there was at Kapher-nachum the servant of a certain king, whose son was ill.
B043C004V047	43	4	47	This (man) heard that Jeshu had come from Jihuda into Galila; and he came to him, and besought him that he would come down and heal his son, for he was near to die.
B043C004V048	43	4	48	Jeshu saith to him, If signs and wonders you do not SEE, you will not believe.
B043C004V049	43	4	49	The servant of the king saith to him, My lord, come down ere my child die!
B043C004V050	43	4	50	Jeshu saith to him, Go, thy son liveth. And the man believed in the word which Jeshu had spoken to him, and went.
B043C004V051	43	4	51	But as he was going down, his servants met him, and gave him good news, saying to him, Thy son liveth.
B043C004V052	43	4	52	And he asked at what time he was healed. They say to him, Yesterday, at seven hours, the fever left him.
B043C004V053	43	4	53	And his father knew that in that hour it was in which Jeshu said to him, Thy son liveth; and he believed, and all his house.
B043C004V054	43	4	54	This is again the second sign (which) Jeshu did when he had come from Jihuda into Galila.
B043C005V001	43	5	1	AFTER these there was a feast of the Jihudoyee, and Jeshu went up to Urishlem.
B043C005V002	43	5	2	Now there was there in Urishlem a certain place of ablution, which was called in Hebrew Bethchesda, and having in it five porticoes.
B043C005V003	43	5	3	And in these were many infirm people, blind and lame and withered, awaiting the moving of the waters.
B043C005V004	43	5	4	For an angel at times descended to the pool and moved the waters; and he who first descended after the movement of the waters was healed of whatever disease he had.
B043C005V005	43	5	5	But a certain man was there who for thirtyand-eight years had been in a disease.
B043C005V006	43	5	6	Jeshu saw this (man) as he lay, and knew that for a long time he had (been thus), and said to him, Art thou willing to be healed?
B043C005V007	43	5	7	The diseased man answered and said, Yes, my Lord; but I have no man who, when the waters are moved, shall cast me into the pool: but while I am coming, another before me descendeth.
B043C005V008	43	5	8	Jeshu saith to him, Arise, take up thy bed, and walk.
B043C005V009	43	5	9	And in the instant that man was healed, and, arising, he took up his bed, and walked: and that day was the shabath.
B043C005V010	43	5	10	And the Jihudoyee said to him who had been healed, This is the shabath: it is not lawful for thee to carry thy bed.
B043C005V011	43	5	11	But he answered and said to them, He who made me whole, he said to me, Take up thy bed, and walk.
B043C005V012	43	5	12	And they said to him, What man is this who told thee to take up thy bed, and walk?
B043C005V013	43	5	13	But he who had been healed knew not who it was; for Jeshu had retired among the great multitude which was in that place.
B043C005V014	43	5	14	After a time Jeshu found him in the temple, and said to him, Behold, thou art healed: sin not again, lest there be to thee that which is worse than the first.
B043C005V015	43	5	15	And that man went away, and told the Jihudoyee, that it was Jeshu who had healed him.
B043C005V016	43	5	16	On account of this the Jihudoyee persecuted Jeshu, and sought to kill him, because these things he had done on the shabath.
B043C005V017	43	5	17	But he, Jeshu, said to them, My Father until now worketh, I also work.
B043C005V018	43	5	18	But on this account the more sought the Jihudoyee to kill him, not only because he had loosed the shabath, but also that of Aloha he had said that he was his Father, and had made himself equal with Aloha.
B043C005V019	43	5	19	BUT Jeshu answered and said to them, Amen, amen, I say to you, The Son cannot do any thing from the will of himself, but that which he seeth the Father do.
B043C005V020	43	5	20	For those which the Father doeth, these also the Son likewise doeth. For the Father loveth the Son, and every thing that he doeth he showeth him; and greater than these works he showeth him, that you may wonder.
B043C005V021	43	5	21	For as the Father raiseth the dead, and quickeneth, so also the Son quickeneth those whom he willeth.
B043C005V022	43	5	22	For the Father judgeth no man, but all judgment he hath given to the Son;
B043C005V023	43	5	23	that all men should honour the Son, as they honour the Father. He who honoureth not the Son, honoureth not the Father who sent him.
B043C005V024	43	5	24	Amen, amen, I say to you, He who heareth my word and believeth on him who sent me, hath the life that is eternal, and into condemnation he cometh not, but hath passed from death unto life.
B043C005V025	43	5	25	Amen, amen, I say to you, That the hour cometh and also now is, when the dead shall hear the voice of the Son of Aloha; and they who hear shall live
B043C005V026	43	5	26	For as the Father hath life in his person, so hath he given also to the Son to have life in his person,
B043C005V027	43	5	27	and hath empowered him also to execute judgment. Because he is the Son of man,
B043C005V028	43	5	28	marvel not at this; for the hour cometh when all they who are in the sepulchres shall hear his voice,
B043C005V029	43	5	29	and shall come forth; they who have done good unto the resurrection of life, and they who have done evil unto the resurrection of condemnation.
B043C005V030	43	5	30	I CANNOT of the will of myself do any thing; but as I hear I judge, and my judgment is just; for I seek not my will, but the will of Him who sent me.
B043C005V031	43	5	31	If I should witness concerning myself, my testimony would not be (regarded as) truth:
B043C005V032	43	5	32	there is another who witnesseth of me, and I know that true is his testimony which he hath witnessed of me.
B043C005V033	43	5	33	You sent to Juchanon, and he witnessed of the truth.
B043C005V034	43	5	34	But I do not from man (only) receive testimony. But these (things) speak I that you may be saved.
B043C005V035	43	5	35	He was a lamp that burneth and shineth, and you were willing to glory for the hour in his light.
B043C005V036	43	5	36	But I have a testimony which is greater than that of Juchanon; for the works that the Father hath given me to accomplish, these works that I do testify of me that the Father hath sent me.
B043C005V037	43	5	37	And the Father who hath sent me, he testifieth of me: but his voice you have never heard, nor his appearance seen.
B043C005V038	43	5	38	And his word abideth not in you, because in Him whom he hath sent you do not believe.
B043C005V039	43	5	39	Investigate the scriptures; for in them you think you have the life that is eternal, and they testify of me.
B043C005V040	43	5	40	And you will not come to me that the life that is eternal you might have.
B043C005V041	43	5	41	Glory from the sons of men I receive not.
B043C005V042	43	5	42	But I know you, that the love of Aloha is not in you.
B043C005V043	43	5	43	I have come in the name of my Father, and you have not received me.
B043C005V044	43	5	44	If another should come in his own name, him you would receive. How can you believe, who glory one from another are receiving, and the glory which is from one, Aloha, you seek not?
B043C005V045	43	5	45	How think you that I will accuse you before the Father? There is one who accuseth you, Musha himself, in whom you hope.
B043C005V046	43	5	46	For if in Musha you had believed, you would also have believed in me; for Musha of me hath written.
B043C005V047	43	5	47	But if his writings you believe not, how my words will you believe?
B043C006V001	43	6	1	AFTER these Jeshu went over the Sea of Galila of Tiberios,
B043C006V002	43	6	2	and great multitudes went after him, because they had seen the signs which he wrought on the diseased.
B043C006V003	43	6	3	And Jeshu ascended a mountain, and there sat with his disciples.
B043C006V004	43	6	4	Now the feast of the petscha of the Jihudoyee drew nigh.
B043C006V005	43	6	5	And Jeshu lifted up his eyes, and saw the great assembly which had come to him; and he said to Philipos, Whence shall we buy bread, that these may eat?
B043C006V006	43	6	6	But this he said trying him; for he knew what he was about to do.
B043C006V007	43	6	7	Philipos saith to him, Two hundred dinoreen of bread is not sufficient for them, that a little every one of them may take.
B043C006V008	43	6	8	Saith to him one of his disciples, Andreas, brother of Shemun Kipha,
B043C006V009	43	6	9	There is here a certain youth, who hath with him five cakes of barley and two fishes; but these what are they for these all?
B043C006V010	43	6	10	Jeshu saith to them, Make all the men recline; for there was much herbage in that place. And the men reclined, in number five thousand.
B043C006V011	43	6	11	And Jeshu took the bread, and blessed, and divided unto those who reclined, and likewise also of the fishes, as much as they willed.
B043C006V012	43	6	12	And when they were satisfied, he said to his disciples, Gather the fragments that abound, that nothing be lost;
B043C006V013	43	6	13	and they gathered and filled twelve baskets of fragments, those which abounded unto them who had eaten of the five loaves of barley.
B043C006V014	43	6	14	But those men, when they had seen the sign which Jeshu had wrought, said, Truly this is the Prophet that cometh into the world.
B043C006V015	43	6	15	But when Jeshu knew that they were about to come to seize him and make him the King, he passed away to a mountain alone.
B043C006V016	43	6	16	AND when it was eventide, his disciples went down to the sea.
B043C006V017	43	6	17	And they sat in a vessel, and went over for Kapher-nachum. And it was dark, and Jeshu had not come to them.
B043C006V018	43	6	18	But the sea had risen against them, because a great wind blew.
B043C006V019	43	6	19	And they had led stadia twentyfive or thirty, and they saw Jeshu walking upon the sea, and drawing nigh to the vessel; and they feared.
B043C006V020	43	6	20	But Jeshu himself said to them, I am, fear not.
B043C006V021	43	6	21	And they willed to receive him into the vessel, and soon that vessel was at that land to which they were going.
B043C006V022	43	6	22	The day after the people that stood on the opposite shore of the sea saw that there was not another vessel there except that into which the disciples had ascended, and that Jeshu had not entered with his disciples into the vessel;
B043C006V023	43	6	23	but there came other boats from Tiberios near the place, where they did eat bread when Jeshu had blessed.
B043C006V024	43	6	24	And when that company saw that Jeshu was not there nor his disciples, they ascended into those boats, and came to Kapher-nachum. And they sought Jeshu;
B043C006V025	43	6	25	and when they had found him on the opposite side of the sea, they say to him, Raban, when camest thou hither?
B043C006V026	43	6	26	Jeshu answered and said to them, Amen, amen, I tell you, You seek me, not because you considered the signs, but because you did eat the bread, and were satisfied.
B043C006V027	43	6	27	Work not (for) the food which perisheth, but (for) the food that endureth unto the life that is eternal, which the Son of man shall give to you: for this hath the Father sealed, (even) Aloha.
B043C006V028	43	6	28	They say to him, What shall we do that we may work the works of Aloha?
B043C006V029	43	6	29	Jeshu answered and said to them, This is the work of Aloha, that you believe in Him whom he hath sent.
B043C006V030	43	6	30	THEY say to him, What sign doest thou that we may see, and believe in thee? What performest thou?
B043C006V031	43	6	31	Our fathers manna did eat in the desert, as it is written, that bread from heaven be gave them to eat.
B043C006V032	43	6	32	Jeshu saith to them, Amen, amen, I tell you, That Musha gave you not that bread from heaven, but my Father giveth you the true bread from heaven:
B043C006V033	43	6	33	for the bread of Aloha is He who hath descended from heaven, and giveth life to the world.
B043C006V034	43	6	34	They say to him, Our Lord, at all time give us this bread.
B043C006V035	43	6	35	Jeshu saith to them, I am the bread of life: he who cometh to me shall not hunger, and he who believeth in me shall not thirst, for ever.
B043C006V036	43	6	36	But I have told you that you have seen me, and have not believed.
B043C006V037	43	6	37	Every one whom the Father hath given me, unto me will come; and him who unto me shall come, I will not cast out.
B043C006V038	43	6	38	I descended from heaven not to do mine own will, but the will of Him who sent me.
B043C006V039	43	6	39	But this is the will of my Father who sent me, that of all whom he hath given me I shall lose not of him, but shall raise him at the last day.
B043C006V040	43	6	40	For this is the will of my Father, that every one who seeth the Son and believeth on him, shall have the life that is eternal, and I will raise him at the last day.
B043C006V041	43	6	41	But the Jihudoyee murmured against him because he said, I am the bread which hath descended from heaven.
B043C006V042	43	6	42	And they said, Is not this Jeshu bar Jauseph, he whose father and mother we know? and how saith this, From heaven I have descended?
B043C006V043	43	6	43	Jeshu answered and said to them, Murmur not one with another.
B043C006V044	43	6	44	No man can come to me unless the Father who sent me shall attract him, and I will raise him at the last day.
B043C006V045	43	6	45	It is written in the prophet, that they shall be all taught of Aloha: every one, therefore, who hath heard from the Father and learned of him, cometh unto me.
B043C006V046	43	6	46	There is no man who hath seen the Father, but he who is from Aloha, he hath seen the Father.
B043C006V047	43	6	47	AMEN, amen, I say to you, Whosoever believeth in me hath the life which is eternal.
B043C006V048	43	6	48	I am the bread of life.
B043C006V049	43	6	49	Your fathers did eat manna in the desert, and are dead:
B043C006V050	43	6	50	but this is the bread which hath descended from heaven, that man may eat of it, and die not.
B043C006V051	43	6	51	I am the bread of life that from heaven hath descended; and if man shall eat of this bread, he shall live for ever; and the bread that I will give is my body, which for the life of the world I give.
B043C006V052	43	6	52	The Jihudoyee contended one with another, saying, How can this his body give to us to eat?
B043C006V053	43	6	53	And Jeshu said to them, Amen, amen, I tell you, That unless you eat the body of the Son of man, and drink his blood, you have no life in yourselves.
B043C006V054	43	6	54	He who eateth of my body, and drinketh of my blood, hath the life which is eternal, and I will raise him at the last day.
B043C006V055	43	6	55	For my body is truly food, and my blood is truly drink.
B043C006V056	43	6	56	He who eateth my body, and drinketh my blood, abideth in me, and I in him.
B043C006V057	43	6	57	As the Father the Living (one) who hath sent me, and I live by the Father, even so he who shall eat me, shall live, too, by me.
B043C006V058	43	6	58	This is the bread which hath descended from heaven. Not as was the manna that your fathers ate, and are dead; he who eateth of this bread shall live for ever.
B043C006V059	43	6	59	These things he spake in the synagogue, as he taught in Kapher-nachum.
B043C006V060	43	6	60	And many of his disciples who heard said, A hard word is this: who can hear it?
B043C006V061	43	6	61	BUT Jeshu knew in himself that his disciples murmured concerning this; and he said to them, Does this stumble you?
B043C006V062	43	6	62	If you shall see then the Son of man ascend up to the place where he was from the first?
B043C006V063	43	6	63	It is the Spirit that maketh alive, the body profiteth nothing: the words which I have spoken to you, they are spirit and they are life.
B043C006V064	43	6	64	But there are some of you who do not believe. For Jeshu knew from the first who they were who believed not, and who it was who would betray him.
B043C006V065	43	6	65	And he said to them, On account of this I told you that no man can come to me, unless it be given him of my Father.
B043C006V066	43	6	66	On account of this word many of his disciples went back, and walked not with him.
B043C006V067	43	6	67	Jeshu said to the twelve, Do you also will to go?
B043C006V068	43	6	68	Shemun Kipha answered and said, My Lord, unto whom shall we go? thou hast the words of eternal life;
B043C006V069	43	6	69	and we believe and know that thou art the Meshicha, the Son of Aloha the Living.
B043C006V070	43	6	70	Jeshu saith to them, Have I not chosen you twelve, and from you one is Satana?
B043C006V071	43	6	71	He spake concerning Jihuda bar Shemun Scarjuta; for he it was who would betray him, one from the twelve.
B043C007V001	43	7	1	AFTER these Jeshu walked in Galila; for he would not walk in Jihuda, because the Jihudoyee had sought to kill him.
B043C007V002	43	7	2	And the feast of tabernacles of the Jihudoyee drew nigh.
B043C007V003	43	7	3	And his brethren said to Jeshu, Remove thee hence, and go into Jihuda, that thy disciples may see the works which thou doest.
B043C007V004	43	7	4	For there is no man who doeth any thing in concealment, and willeth himself to be in openness: if these things thou doest, show thyself to the world.
B043C007V005	43	7	5	For neither did his brethren believe in him, in Jeshu.
B043C007V006	43	7	6	Jeshu saith to them, My time until now cometh not, but your time is always ready.
B043C007V007	43	7	7	The world cannot hate you: but me it hateth, because I bear witness against it that the works of it are evil.
B043C007V008	43	7	8	Go you up to this feast: I do not ascend now to this feast, because my time is not yet complete.
B043C007V009	43	7	9	These things said he, and remained in Galila.
B043C007V010	43	7	10	But when his brethren had ascended to the feast, then also he ascended; not in openness, but as in concealment.
B043C007V011	43	7	11	But the Jihudoyee sought him at the feast, and said, Where is he?
B043C007V012	43	7	12	and there was great murmuring concerning him among the people; for some said that he was good, and others said, No; but he deceiveth the people.
B043C007V013	43	7	13	But no man openly spoke of him, for fear of the Jihudoyee.
B043C007V014	43	7	14	But when the days of the feast divided, Jeshu ascended to the temple, and taught.
B043C007V015	43	7	15	And the Jihudoyee wondered and said, How knoweth this man the scripture, when he hath not learned?
B043C007V016	43	7	16	Jeshu answered and said, My doctrine is not mine, but his who sent me.
B043C007V017	43	7	17	Whosoever willeth to do his will understandeth my doctrine, if it be from Aloha, or (if) from the will of myself I speak.
B043C007V018	43	7	18	He who from the will of his (own) mind speaketh, the glory of himself seeketh; but he who the glory of him who hath sent him seeketh, is true, and no iniquity is in him.
B043C007V019	43	7	19	Did not Musha give you the law? But no man of you keepeth the law. Why seek you to kill me?
B043C007V020	43	7	20	The people answered, saying, Thou hast a demon: who seeketh to kill thee?
B043C007V021	43	7	21	Jeshu answered and said to them, One work have I performed, and all of you wondered on this account.
B043C007V022	43	7	22	Musha gave you circumcision, not because it was from the fathers, and on the shabath you circumcise a man.
B043C007V023	43	7	23	But if a man is circumcised on the day of shabath because the law of Musha may not be broken, why against me do you murmur, because I have altogether healed a man on the day of shabath?
B043C007V024	43	7	24	Judge not with acceptance of persons, but righteous judgment judge you.
B043C007V025	43	7	25	And some of Urishlem said, Is not this he whom they seek to kill?
B043C007V026	43	7	26	and, behold, openly he discourseth, and nothing say they to him. Do the elders know that this is truly the Meshicha?
B043C007V027	43	7	27	Yet of this we know from whence he is; but when the Meshicha cometh, no man knoweth from whence he is.
B043C007V028	43	7	28	Jeshu lifted up his voice as he taught in the temple, and said, You know me, and from whence I am you know: and of myself I am not come; but true is he who sent me, he whom you know not.
B043C007V029	43	7	29	But I know him who am from him; and he hath sent me.
B043C007V030	43	7	30	And they sought to apprehend him; but no man laid hands on him, because not yet was come his hour.
B043C007V031	43	7	31	But many of the multitude believed in him, and said, When the Meshicha is come, will he exceed the miracles which this doeth?
B043C007V032	43	7	32	The Pharishee heard the assembly, that they said these things of him, and the chief priests sent officers to apprehend him.
B043C007V033	43	7	33	Jeshu said, Yet a little while am I with you, and I go unto him who sent me:
B043C007V034	43	7	34	and you will seek me, and shall not find me: and where I am you cannot come.
B043C007V035	43	7	35	The Jihudoyee say among themselves, Whither is this about to go, that we cannot find him? To the countries of the nations is he to go, and to teach the Heathens?
B043C007V036	43	7	36	What is this word he hath said, You shall seek me, and not find me; and where I am you cannot come?
B043C007V037	43	7	37	BUT in the great day, which was the last of the feast, stood Jeshu and cried, and said, If (any) man thirst, let him come unto me and drink;
B043C007V038	43	7	38	for whosoever believeth in me, as have said the scriptures, rivers of living waters shall flow from his belly.
B043C007V039	43	7	39	But this he spake of the Spirit which they should receive who believe in him. For not yet was the Spirit given, because not yet was Jeshu glorified.
B043C007V040	43	7	40	Now many of the assemblies who heard his words said, This is truly the Prophet.
B043C007V041	43	7	41	Others said, This is the Meshicha. Others said, How from Galila cometh the Meshicha?
B043C007V042	43	7	42	Hath not the scripture said, That from the seed of David, and from Beth-lechem the town of David, cometh the Meshicha?
B043C007V043	43	7	43	And there was a division concerning him among the assemblies;
B043C007V044	43	7	44	and there were men of them who would have apprehended him; but no man laid hands on him.
B043C007V045	43	7	45	AND those officers came to the chief priests and the Pharishee; and the priests said to them, Why have you not brought him?
B043C007V046	43	7	46	The officers say to them, Never so spake a son of man as speaks this man!
B043C007V047	43	7	47	The Pharishee say to them, Are you also deceived?
B043C007V048	43	7	48	Have any of the heads, or of the Pharishee, believed in him?
B043C007V049	43	7	49	But if this people who know not the law (believe in him), they are accursed.
B043C007V050	43	7	50	One of them, Nikodimos, he who came to Jeshu by night, saith to them,
B043C007V051	43	7	51	Does our law condemn a man unless it shall hear from him first, and know what he hath done?
B043C007V052	43	7	52	They answered and said to him, Art thou also of Galila? Investigate, and see, that the Prophet from Galila ariseth not.
B043C008V012	43	8	12	BUT again spake Jeshu with them, and said, I am the Light of the world: he who followeth me shall not walk in darkness, but shall find the light of life.
B043C008V013	43	8	13	The Pharishee say to him, Thou of thyself testifiest: thy testimony is not the truth.
B043C008V014	43	8	14	Jeshu answered and said to them, Though I testify of myself, my testimony is the truth: because I know from whence I am, and whither I go.
B043C008V015	43	8	15	But you know not from whence I am, nor whither I go. You judge carnally; but I judge no man.
B043C008V016	43	8	16	Yet if I judge, my judgment is true: because I am not alone, but I and my Father who sent me.
B043C008V017	43	8	17	So in your law it is written, that the testimony of two men is truth:
B043C008V018	43	8	18	I am (one) who testify of myself, and my Father who sent me testifieth (also) of me.
B043C008V019	43	8	19	They say to him, Where is thy Father? Jeshu answered and said to them, You know neither me, nor my Father; for if me you had known, my Father also would you have known.
B043C008V020	43	8	20	These words spake Jeshu in the house of treasure, as he taught in the temple: and no man apprehended him; for not yet had come his hour.
B043C008V021	43	8	21	Jeshu said again, I go, and you will seek me, and will die in your sins; and where I go you cannot come.
B043C008V022	43	8	22	The Jihudoyee say, Will he kill himself then? for he saith, Whither I go you cannot come.
B043C008V023	43	8	23	And he said to them, From beneath are you; but I am from above: you are of this world;
B043C008V024	43	8	24	but I am not of this world. I said to you, that you will die in your sins: for if you believe not that I AM, you will die in your sins.
B043C008V025	43	8	25	The Jihudoyee say, Who art thou? Jeshu saith to them, The same that I began to tell you.
B043C008V026	43	8	26	Much have I against you to say and to judge: but he who hath sent me is true; and those (things) which I have heard from him these speak I in the world.
B043C008V027	43	8	27	But they knew not that of the Father he spake to them.
B043C008V028	43	8	28	JESHU saith to them again, When you have lifted up the Son of man, then shall you know that I am (he), and (that) nothing from myself I do; but as the Father hath taught me, so I speak.
B043C008V029	43	8	29	And he who sent me is with me: my Father hath not left me alone; for whatever is pleasing to him I do at all time.
B043C008V030	43	8	30	And as these (words) he spake, many believed on him.
B043C008V031	43	8	31	And Jeshu said to those Jihudoyee who believed on him, If you persevere in my doctrine, you shall be truly my disciples;
B043C008V032	43	8	32	and you shall know the truth, and the truth shall liberate you.
B043C008V033	43	8	33	They say to him, We are the seed of Abraham, and never service to man have we performed; how sayest thou that we shall be sons of freedom?
B043C008V034	43	8	34	Jeshu saith to them, Amen I tell you, Whoever doeth sin is the servant of sin.
B043C008V035	43	8	35	And the servant abideth not for ever in the house, but the Son for ever abideth.
B043C008V036	43	8	36	If He therefore, the Son, shall liberate you, truly shall you be sons of freedom.
B043C008V037	43	8	37	I know that you are the seed of Abraham; but you seek to kill me, because in my word you do not concur.
B043C008V038	43	8	38	That which I have seen with my Father I speak, and that which you have seen with your father you do.
B043C008V039	43	8	39	They answered and said to him, Our father is Abraham. Jeshu saith to them, If you were the sons of Abraham, the works of Abraham you would do.
B043C008V040	43	8	40	But now you seek to kill me, the man who the truth has spoken with you, which I have heard from Aloha. This Abraham did not.
B043C008V041	43	8	41	But you do the deeds of your father. They say to him, We from fornication are not; one Father have we, Aloha.
B043C008V042	43	8	42	Jeshu saith to them, If Aloha were your Father, you would love me; for I from Aloha came forth, and I came not of myself, but he sent me.
B043C008V043	43	8	43	Wherefore my word do you not acknowledge? Because you cannot hear my word.
B043C008V044	43	8	44	You are from your father the accuser, and the desires of your father you are willing to do. He from the beginning was the killer of men, and in the truth he stood not; therefore the truth is not in him. And when he speaketh a lie, of his own he speaketh, because of falsity he is also the father.
B043C008V045	43	8	45	But I (speak the truth, and) because the truth I speak, you believe me not.
B043C008V046	43	8	46	Who of you convicteth me of sin? Yet if the truth I speak, why do you not believe me?
B043C008V047	43	8	47	He who is of Aloha the words of Aloha heareth: therefore you hear not, because you are not of Aloha.
B043C008V048	43	8	48	The Jihudoyee answered and say to him, Did we not well say, Thou art a Shomroya, and hast a devil?
B043C008V049	43	8	49	Jeshu said to them, I have no devil; but my Father I honour, and you debase me.
B043C008V050	43	8	50	But I seek not my own glory; He is, who seeketh and judgeth.
B043C008V051	43	8	51	Amen, amen, I say to you, That he who my word keepeth, death shall not see for ever.
B043C008V052	43	8	52	The Jihudoyee say to him, Now we know that thou hast a devil. Abraham is dead, and the prophets; and thou sayest, that he who thy word keepeth, death shall not taste for ever.
B043C008V053	43	8	53	Art thou greater than our father Abraham, who is dead; and than the prophets, who are dead? What makest thou thyself?
B043C008V054	43	8	54	Jeshu said to them, If I glorify myself, my glory is nothing: it is my Father who glorifieth me; he, of whom you say that he is your God.
B043C008V055	43	8	55	But you know him not; but I know him: and should I say that I know him not, I should be a liar like you. But I know him, and keep his words.
B043C008V056	43	8	56	Abraham, your father, desired to see my day, and he saw, and was glad.
B043C008V057	43	8	57	The Jihudoyee said to him, Yet the son of fifty years thou art not, and Abraham hast thou seen?
B043C008V058	43	8	58	Jeshu saith to them, Amen, amen, I say to you, Before Abraham was, I AM.
B043C008V059	43	8	59	And they took up stones to stone him; but Jeshu concealed himself, and went from the temple, and passed among them, and went.
B043C009V001	43	9	1	AND as he was passing, he saw a man blind from the womb of his mother.
B043C009V002	43	9	2	And his disciples asked him, saying, Raban, who sinned, this or his parents, that blind he should have been born?
B043C009V003	43	9	3	Jeshu saith to them, Neither he sinned, nor his parents; but that there might be seen in him the works of Aloha.
B043C009V004	43	9	4	Me it behoveth to do the works of Him who sent me, while it is to-day: the night cometh when man cannot work.
B043C009V005	43	9	5	So long as I am in the world, I am the Light of the world.
B043C009V006	43	9	6	And when he had said these things, he spat upon the ground, and formed clay from his spittle, and rubbed upon the eyes of the blind,
B043C009V007	43	9	7	and said to him, Go, wash in the pool of Shilucha. And he went, washed, and came seeing.
B043C009V008	43	9	8	But his neighbours, and they who had seen (him) aforetime as he begged, said, Is not this he who sat and begged?
B043C009V009	43	9	9	Some said, It is he; and some said, It is not, but one like him; but he said, I am he.
B043C009V010	43	9	10	They say to him, How were thine eyes opened?
B043C009V011	43	9	11	He answered and said to them, The man whose name is Jeshu made clay, and rubbed upon mine eyes, and said to me, Go, wash in the waters of Shilucha; and I went, washed, and received sight.
B043C009V012	43	9	12	They say to him, Where is he? He saith to them, I know not.
B043C009V013	43	9	13	They brought him who from the beginning was blind to the Pharishee.
B043C009V014	43	9	14	Now it was shabath when Jeshu made the clay and opened his eyes:
B043C009V015	43	9	15	and again the Pharishee questioned him, How didst thou receive sight? He said to them, He put clay upon mine eyes, and I washed, and received sight.
B043C009V016	43	9	16	And some of the Pharishee said, This man is not from Aloha; for the shabath he keepeth not. But others said, How can a man, a sinner, perform these signs? And there was a division among them.
B043C009V017	43	9	17	They say again to the blind, What sayest thou concerning him, because he hath opened thine eyes? He saith to them, I say that he is the Prophet.
B043C009V018	43	9	18	But believed not concerning him the Jihudoyee that blind he had been and made-to-see, until they called the parents of him who had been made to see,
B043C009V019	43	9	19	and asked them, If this is your son who, you say, was born blind, how now doth he see?
B043C009V020	43	9	20	His parents answered and said, We know that this (is) our son, and that blind he was born.
B043C009V021	43	9	21	But how he now seeth, or who hath opened his eyes, we know not. He also hath entered on his years, ask him: he for himself shall speak.
B043C009V022	43	9	22	These words said his parents, because they feared the Jihudoyee; for the Jihudoyee had determined that if any man should confess him that he was the Meshicha, they would cast him out of the synagogue:
B043C009V023	43	9	23	on this account said his parents, He hath entered on his years, ask him.
B043C009V024	43	9	24	And they called the second time the man who had been blind, and said to him, Glorify Aloha: for we know that this man is a sinner.
B043C009V025	43	9	25	He answered and said to them, Whether he be a sinner, I know not; but one (thing) I know, that I have been blind, and now, behold, I see.
B043C009V026	43	9	26	They say to him again, What did he to thee? how opened he to thee thine eyes?
B043C009V027	43	9	27	He saith to them, I told you, and you heard not: what will you hear? Are you also willing disciples to him to become?
B043C009V028	43	9	28	But they reviled him, and said to him, Thou art the disciple of him; but we are the disciples of Musha.
B043C009V029	43	9	29	And we know that with Musha Aloha spake; but for this, we know not whence he is.
B043C009V030	43	9	30	Answered the man and said to them, At this then we must wonder, that you know not from whence he is, and (yet) mine eyes he hath opened!
B043C009V031	43	9	31	But we know that Aloha the voice of sinners heareth not; but if any man fear him and do his will, him he heareth.
B043C009V032	43	9	32	From of old it hath not been heard that a man hath opened the eyes of one born blind.
B043C009V033	43	9	33	If this were not from Aloha, he could not this have done.
B043C009V034	43	9	34	They answered and say to him, Thou altogether wast born in sins, and art thou teaching us? And they cast him without.
B043C009V035	43	9	35	Jeshu heard that they had cast him without, and he found him, and said to him, Dost thou believe on the Son of Aloha?
B043C009V036	43	9	36	He who had been cured answered and said, Who (is he), my Lord, that I may believe in him?
B043C009V037	43	9	37	Jeshu said to him, Thou hast SEEN him, and He who talketh with thee is He.
B043C009V038	43	9	38	He said, I believe, my Lord! And, falling, he adored him.
B043C009V039	43	9	39	Jeshu said to them, For the judgment of this world am I come, that they who see not may see, and they who see may be made blind.
B043C009V040	43	9	40	And some of the Pharishee who were with him heard these (words), and they said to him, Are we blind also?
B043C009V041	43	9	41	Jeshu saith to them, If blind you were, you would have no sin; but now you say, We see: therefore your sin is confirmed.
B043C010V001	43	10	1	AMEN, amen, I say to you, Whosoever entereth not by the door into the fold of the flock, but ascendeth by another place, he is a thief and a robber.
B043C010V002	43	10	2	But he who entereth by the door, he is the shepherd of the flock.
B043C010V003	43	10	3	And to him the keeper of the gate openeth the gate, and the flock heareth his voice, and his sheep he calleth by their names, and he leadeth them forth;
B043C010V004	43	10	4	and when his flock hath gone forth, he goeth before it, and his sheep follow him, because they know his voice.
B043C010V005	43	10	5	But after a stranger the flock goeth not, but it fleeth from him; for it knoweth not the voice of a stranger.
B043C010V006	43	10	6	This parable spake Jeshu to them, but they knew not what he said with them.
B043C010V007	43	10	7	Jeshu saith to them again, Amen, amen, I say to you, I am the gate of the flock;
B043C010V008	43	10	8	and all those who have come were thieves and robbers, but the flock heard them not.
B043C010V009	43	10	9	I am the gate; by me if any man enter, he shall live and shall come in, and go out, and find pasture.
B043C010V010	43	10	10	The thief cometh not but to steal and to kill and destroy: I am come that they may have life, and that which is more.
B043C010V011	43	10	11	I am the good shepherd, and the good shepherd his life layeth down for his flock.
B043C010V012	43	10	12	The hireling who is not the shepherd, and whose the sheep are not, when he seeth the wolf coming, leaveth the flock and fleeth; and the wolf cometh ravaging and destroying the flock.
B043C010V013	43	10	13	But the hireling fleeth because he is an hireling, and careth not for the flock.
B043C010V014	43	10	14	I am the good shepherd, and know my own, and am known of my own.
B043C010V015	43	10	15	As my Father knoweth me (and) I know my Father, and my life I lay down for the flock.
B043C010V016	43	10	16	But I have other sheep also which are not of this fold; and these also it behoveth me to bring, and they will hear my voice, and all shall become one flock and one shepherd.
B043C010V017	43	10	17	On this account my Father loveth me, because I lay down my life again to take it.
B043C010V018	43	10	18	No man taketh it away from me, but I lay it down from my will; for I am able to lay it down, and I am able to take it again; for this commandment have I received from my Father.
B043C010V019	43	10	19	And there was again a division among the Jihudoyee because of his words:
B043C010V020	43	10	20	and many of them said, He has a devil, and is altogether insane, why do you hear him?
B043C010V021	43	10	21	But others said, These words are not of a demoniac: how can a devil open the eyes of the blind?
B043C010V022	43	10	22	IT was the feast of the renovation at Urishlem,
B043C010V023	43	10	23	and it was winter. And Jeshu walked in the temple in the portico of Shelumun.
B043C010V024	43	10	24	And the Jihudoyee surrounded him, saying to him, How long takest thou our souls? If thou art the Meshicha, tell us openly.
B043C010V025	43	10	25	Jeshu answered and said to them, I have told you, and you believe not. The works that I do in the name of my Father, these witness for me.
B043C010V026	43	10	26	But you believe not, because you are not of my sheep, (even) as I told you.
B043C010V027	43	10	27	My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me;
B043C010V028	43	10	28	and I give to them the life which is eternal, and they shall not perish for ever, and no man shall snatch them from my hands.
B043C010V029	43	10	29	For my Father who gave them to me than all is greater; and no man from the hand of my Father can snatch them.
B043C010V030	43	10	30	I and my Father are One.
B043C010V031	43	10	31	And again the Jihudoyee took up stones to stone him.
B043C010V032	43	10	32	Jeshu saith to them, Many good works from my Father have I showed you: on account of which of these works do you stone me?
B043C010V033	43	10	33	The Jihudoyee say to him, Not on account of the good works do we stone thee, but because thou blasphemest; thou, being a son of man, making thyself Aloha.
B043C010V034	43	10	34	Jeshu saith to them, Is it not written in your law, I said, Ye are Alohee?
B043C010V035	43	10	35	If them he calleth Alohee, because with them was the word of Aloha, and the scripture cannot be loosed,
B043C010V036	43	10	36	to him whom the Father hath sanctified and sent into the world, say you, Thou blasphemest, because I have said to you, I am the Son of Aloha?
B043C010V037	43	10	37	And if I do not the works of my Father, believe me not;
B043C010V038	43	10	38	but if I do, though you believe not me, the works believe, that you may know and believe that the Father is in me, and (that) I (am) in the Father.
B043C010V039	43	10	39	And they sought again to apprehend him; but he went forth from among their hands:
B043C010V040	43	10	40	and he went beyond Jurdan, to the place where Juchanon at first had baptized, and was there.
B043C010V041	43	10	41	And many came to him, and said, Juchanon did not one sign; but every thing which Juchanon said concerning this man was true.
B043C010V042	43	10	42	And many believed in him.
B043C011V001	43	11	1	BUT a certain man was sick, Loozar, of the village Bethania: (he was) the brother of Mariam and of Martha.
B043C011V002	43	11	2	It was that Mariam who anointed with balsam the feet of Jeshu, and wiped (them) with her hair, whose brother this Loozar was who was sick.
B043C011V003	43	11	3	And his two sisters sent unto Jeshu, saying, Our Lord, he whom thou lovest is sick.
B043C011V004	43	11	4	But Jeshu said, This sickness is not of death, but for the glory of Aloha, that the Son of Aloha may be glorified on account of it.
B043C011V005	43	11	5	But Jeshu loved Martha and Mariam and Loozar.
B043C011V006	43	11	6	And when he heard that he was sick, he remained in the place where he was two days.
B043C011V007	43	11	7	And afterwards he saith to his disciples, Come, we will go again into Jihud.
B043C011V008	43	11	8	His disciples say to him, Raban, now have the Jihudoyee sought to stone thee; and again goest thou thither?
B043C011V009	43	11	9	Jeshu saith to them, Are there not twelve hours in the day? If a man walk in the day, he stumbleth not, because he seeth the light of this world;
B043C011V010	43	11	10	but if a man walk in the night, he stumbleth, because no light is in him.
B043C011V011	43	11	11	These spake Jeshu; and afterwards he said to them, Loozar our friend reposeth; but I go to awake him.
B043C011V012	43	11	12	His disciples say to him, Our Lord, if he sleep he is healed.
B043C011V013	43	11	13	But Jeshu spake concerning his death; and they thought that concerning the repose of sleep he spake.
B043C011V014	43	11	14	Then said Jeshu to them explicatively, Loozar is dead.
B043C011V015	43	11	15	And I am glad I was not there for your sakes, that you may believe. But let us walk thither.
B043C011V016	43	11	16	Thoma, who is called the Twin, saith to his fellow-disciples, Let us also go, that we may die with him.
B043C011V017	43	11	17	And Jeshu came to Bethania, and found that he had been four days in the house of burial.
B043C011V018	43	11	18	Now Bethania was nigh to Urishlem, being a distance from it of about fifteen stadia.
B043C011V019	43	11	19	And many of the Jihudoyee had come to Martha and Mariam, that they might speak to their hearts concerning their brother.
B043C011V020	43	11	20	Then Martha, when she heard that Jeshu had come, went forth to meet him; but Mariam sat in the house.
B043C011V021	43	11	21	And Martha said to Jeshu, My Lord, if thou hadst been here, my brother had not died.
B043C011V022	43	11	22	But even now know I that whatsoever thou wilt ask of Aloha, he giveth to thee.
B043C011V023	43	11	23	Jeshu saith to her, Thy brother ariseth.
B043C011V024	43	11	24	Martha saith to him, I know that he ariseth in the resurrection at the last day.
B043C011V025	43	11	25	Jeshu saith to her, I am the Resurrection and the Life; and (he) who believeth in me, although he will die, shall live.
B043C011V026	43	11	26	And every one who liveth and believeth in me, for ever shall not die. Believest thou this?
B043C011V027	43	11	27	She saith to him, Yes, my Lord; I believe that thou art the Meshicha, the Son of Aloha, who cometh into the world.
B043C011V028	43	11	28	And when she had said these, she went, called Mariam her sister in secret, and said to her, Our Master hath come, and calleth for thee.
B043C011V029	43	11	29	When Mariam heard, she arose quickly, and came to him.
B043C011V030	43	11	30	But Jeshu himself had not yet come into the village, but was in that place where Martha met him.
B043C011V031	43	11	31	But those Jihudoyee who were also with her in the house to console her, when they saw that Mariam rose up hastily to go forth, went themselves after her; for they thought that to the sepulchre she went to weep.
B043C011V032	43	11	32	But she, Mariam, when she was come where Jeshu was, and saw him, fell down at his feet, saying, If thou hadst been here, my Lord, my brother had not died.
B043C011V033	43	11	33	But Jeshu, when he saw her weeping, and those Jihudoyee who came with her weeping, he was moved in his spirit, and was troubled,
B043C011V034	43	11	34	and said, Where have you laid him? And they said to him, Our Lord, come and see.
B043C011V035	43	11	35	And the tears of Jeshu came.
B043C011V036	43	11	36	And the Jihudoyee said, See how he loved him!
B043C011V037	43	11	37	But some of them said, Could not this who opened the eyes of that blind have caused also that this should not have died?
B043C011V038	43	11	38	Jeshu, groaning within himself, came to the house of burial; and that house of burial was a cave, and a stone was laid at the gate of it.
B043C011V039	43	11	39	And Jeshu said, Take up this stone. Martha, the sister of him (who was) dead, saith to him, My Lord, he now stinketh; for four days are to him.
B043C011V040	43	11	40	Jeshu said to her, Said I not to thee, that if thou wilt believe, thou shalt see the glory of Aloha?
B043C011V041	43	11	41	And they took up the stone. And Jeshu lifted his eye upward, and said, Father, I give thanks to thee that thou hast heard me;
B043C011V042	43	11	42	and I know that at all times thou hearest me: yet, because of this assembly which standeth, I say these (words), that they may believe that thou hast sent me.
B043C011V043	43	11	43	And when he had said these (words), he cried with a high voice, Loozar, come without!
B043C011V044	43	11	44	And he, the dead, came forth, his hands and his feet being bound with bandages, and his face in a linen cloth. Jeshu saith to them, Release him, and let (him) go.
B043C011V045	43	11	45	And many of the Jihudoyee who came with Mariam, when they saw the thing which Jeshu did, believed on him.
B043C011V046	43	11	46	And some of them went to the Pharishee, and told them every thing that Jeshu had done.
B043C011V047	43	11	47	AND the chief priests and Pharishee assembled, and said, What shall we do? because this man doeth many signs;
B043C011V048	43	11	48	and if we leave him thus, all men will believe on him, and the Rumoyee, coming, take away our country and our people.
B043C011V049	43	11	49	But one of them, whose name was Kaiapha, was the high priest of that year; and he said to them, You know not any thing,
B043C011V050	43	11	50	nor reason that it is expedient for us that one man die for the people, and not all the people perish.
B043C011V051	43	11	51	But this from himself he spake not, but because he was high priest of that year, he prophesied that Jeshu should die for the people,
B043C011V052	43	11	52	and not only for (that) people, but also that the children of Aloha who are dispersed he should gather into one.
B043C011V053	43	11	53	And from that day they determined to kill him.
B043C011V054	43	11	54	But Jeshu himself walked not openly among the Jihudoyee, but went from thence to the region near the wilderness, to a region which was called Ephrem, and there conversed with his disciples.
B043C011V055	43	11	55	NOW the petscha of the Jihudoyee drew nigh; and many went up from the country places to Urishlem before the festival, to purify themselves.
B043C011V056	43	11	56	And they sought for Jeshu, and said one to another in the temple, What think you, that he cometh to the feast?
B043C011V057	43	11	57	But the chief priests and Pharishee had commanded that if any man knew where (he was), he should declare it to them, as that they might apprehend him.
B043C012V001	43	12	1	But Jeshu six days before the petscha came to Bethania, where Loozar was, he whom Jeshu had raised from among the dead.
B043C012V002	43	12	2	And they made him there a supper and Martha served, and Loozar was one of those who reclined with him.
B043C012V003	43	12	3	But Mariam took a vase of balsam of the finest nard, great in price, and anointed the feet of Jeshu, and wiped with her hair his feet, and the house was filled with the fragrance of the balsam.
B043C012V004	43	12	4	And Jihuda Scarjuta, one of his disciples, he who would betray him said,
B043C012V005	43	12	5	Why was not this ointment sold for three hundred dinoreen, and given to the poor?
B043C012V006	43	12	6	But this he said, not because for the poor he had care, but because he was a thief, and the purse was with him, and whatever fell into it he carried.
B043C012V007	43	12	7	But Jeshu said, Let her alone. For the day of my burial had she kept it.
B043C012V008	43	12	8	In all time the poor you have with you; but me you have not at all time.
B043C012V009	43	12	9	And a great company of Jihudoyee who were there heard Jeshu. And they had come not on Jeshu's account only, but also to see Loozar, he whom he had raised from among the dead.
B043C012V010	43	12	10	But the chief priests were minded to slay Loozar also,
B043C012V011	43	12	11	because many of the Jihudoyee on account of him had gone and believed in Jeshu.
B043C012V012	43	12	12	THE day after, a great gathering of those who had come to the feast, when they heard that Jeshu was coming to Urishlem,
B043C012V013	43	12	13	took branches of palms, and went forth to meet him. And they cried out, saying, Aushana! Blessed is he who cometh in the name of the Lord, the King of Israel.
B043C012V014	43	12	14	And Jeshu caused to be found an ass, and sat upon him; as it is written,
B043C012V015	43	12	15	Fear not, daughter of Tseun: behold, thy King cometh to thee, and riding on a colt, the foal of an ass.
B043C012V016	43	12	16	But these the disciples knew not at that time; but when Jeshu was glorified, the disciples remembered that these were written concerning him, and (that) these (things) they had done unto him.
B043C012V017	43	12	17	But the assembly that was with him when he called Loozar from the sepulchre, and raised him from among the dead, bare witness.
B043C012V018	43	12	18	And on account of this, great multitudes went forth to receive him; for they had heard that this sign he had done.
B043C012V019	43	12	19	But the Pharishee said one to another, See you that you do not profit any thing! For, behold, the whole world is gone after him.
B043C012V020	43	12	20	Now there were also from the Gentiles men who had ascended to worship at the feast.
B043C012V021	43	12	21	These came and drew near to Philipos, who was of Beth-tsaida of Galila; and they requested of him, and said to him, Mari, we desire to see Jeshu.
B043C012V022	43	12	22	And Philipos came and told Andreas, and Andreas and Philipos told Jeshu.
B043C012V023	43	12	23	BUT Jeshu answered and said to them, The hour hath come that the Son of man may be glorified.
B043C012V024	43	12	24	Amen, amen, I say to you, That a grain of wheat if it fall not and die in the earth remaineth alone; but if it die, it bringeth much fruits.
B043C012V025	43	12	25	He who loveth his life shall lose it; and he who hateth his life in this world shall keep it to the life which is eternal.
B043C012V026	43	12	26	If any man serve me, let him come after me; and where I am, there shall be also my servant: whoever serveth me, him will my Father honour.
B043C012V027	43	12	27	Now my soul, behold it is commoved; and what shall I say? My Father, deliver me from this hour:
B043C012V028	43	12	28	but on account of this have I come unto this hour. Father, glorify thy name. And the voice was heard from heaven, I have glorified, and again I glorify.
B043C012V029	43	12	29	And the company who stood, heard, and they said there was thunder. But others said, An angel spake with him.
B043C012V030	43	12	30	Jeshu answered and said to them, Not on my account was this voice, but on your account.
B043C012V031	43	12	31	Now is the judgment of this world; now is the ruler of this world cast out.
B043C012V032	43	12	32	And I, when I have been lifted up from the earth, will draw all men unto me.
B043C012V033	43	12	33	But this he said to show by what death he should die.
B043C012V034	43	12	34	The people said to him, We have heard from the law that the Meshicha for ever abideth: how sayest thou that the Son of man is to be lifted up? Who is this Son of man?
B043C012V035	43	12	35	Jeshu saith to them, A little further time is the light with you. Walk while you have the light, that the darkness overtake you not. And whoever walketh in darkness knoweth not whither he goeth.
B043C012V036	43	12	36	While you have the light, believe in the light, that the sons of light you may become. These spake Jeshu, and went (and) concealed himself from them.
B043C012V037	43	12	37	Yet though all these signs he had done before them, they believed not in him:
B043C012V038	43	12	38	that the word of the prophet Eshaia might be fulfilled, who said, My Lord, who hath believed our report, And the arm of the Lord, to whom hath it been revealed?
B043C012V039	43	12	39	Because of this they were not able to believe: Wherefore again Eshaia had said,
B043C012V040	43	12	40	He hath blinded their eyes, And darkened their heart, That they should not see with their eyes, And understand with their heart, And be turned, and I should heal them.
B043C012V041	43	12	41	These said Eshaia when he saw his glory, and spake concerning him.
B043C012V042	43	12	42	Yet of the chiefs also many believed in him: but because of the Pharishee they did not confess, that they might not be put out of the synagogue:
B043C012V043	43	12	43	for they loved the glory of men more than the glory of Aloha.
B043C012V044	43	12	44	But Jeshu cried and said, He who believeth in me, believeth not in me, but in him who sent me.
B043C012V045	43	12	45	And he who seeth me seeth him who sent me.
B043C012V046	43	12	46	I the light am come into the world, that every one who believeth in me might not abide in darkness.
B043C012V047	43	12	47	And he who heareth my words, and doth not keep them, I judge him not: for I came not to judge the world, but to save the world.
B043C012V048	43	12	48	He who rejecteth me, and receiveth not my word, hath that which judgeth him: the word which I speak, that judgeth him in the last day.
B043C012V049	43	12	49	For I of myself have not spoken, but the Father who sent me, he gave me a commandment, what I should say, and what I should speak.
B043C012V050	43	12	50	And I know that his commandments are life everlasting: these therefore which I speak, as said to me my Father, so I speak.
B043C013V001	43	13	1	NOW before the feast of petscha, Jeshu knew that his hour was come, and that he should pass from this world unto his Father, and he had loved his who were in this world, and unto the end he had loved them.
B043C013V002	43	13	2	And when was the supper, Satana had cast it into the heart of Jihuda bar Shemun Scarjuta to betray him.
B043C013V003	43	13	3	But Jeshu himself, because he knew that the Father had given all things into his hands, and that from Aloha he had come forth, and unto Aloha he was going,
B043C013V004	43	13	4	riseth from supper, and setteth his garments apart, and took a towel, (and) bound (it) upon his loins;
B043C013V005	43	13	5	and he poured water into a basin, and began to wash the feet of his disciples, and wiped (them) with the towel that he had bound upon his loins.
B043C013V006	43	13	6	But when he came to Shemun Kipha, Shemun said to him, Dost thou, my Lord, wash my feet for me?
B043C013V007	43	13	7	Jeshu answered and said to him, What I do, thou knowest not now; but afterward thou shalt know.
B043C013V008	43	13	8	Shemun Kipha saith to him, Never shalt thou wash for me my feet. Jeshu saith to him, If I do not wash thee, thou hast with me no part.
B043C013V009	43	13	9	Shemun Kipha saith to him, Then, my Lord, not only my feet shalt thou wash for me, but also my hands, also my head.
B043C013V010	43	13	10	Jeshu saith, He that hath bathed needeth not but his feet only to wash, for all of him he hath cleansed: also you are clean, but not all of you.
B043C013V011	43	13	11	For Jeshu knew who was betraying him; therefore he said, Ye are not all of you clean.
B043C013V012	43	13	12	But when he had washed their feet, he took up his garments and reclined, and said to them, Know you what I have done for you?
B043C013V013	43	13	13	You call me Our Master, and Our Lord; and well say you, for I am.
B043C013V014	43	13	14	If I then, your Lord and your Master, have washed for you your feet, how much more ought you to wash the feet of one another?
B043C013V015	43	13	15	For this pattern have I given you, that as I have done to you, you also should do.
B043C013V016	43	13	16	Amen, amen, I say to you, The servant is not greater than his lord; nor (is) the apostle greater than he who sent him.
B043C013V017	43	13	17	If these you know, happy are you if you do them.
B043C013V018	43	13	18	Not of all of you do I speak; for I know those whom I have chosen; but that the scripture might be fulfilled, that he who eateth bread with me hath lifted against me his heel.
B043C013V019	43	13	19	Now I tell you before it shall be, that when it is done you may believe that I am.
B043C013V020	43	13	20	Amen, amen, I say to you, Whoever receiveth him whom I send receiveth me; and whoever receiveth me receiveth him who sent me.
B043C013V021	43	13	21	These said Jeshu, and was agitated in his spirit, and testified, and said, Amen, amen, I say to you, That one of you shall betray me.
B043C013V022	43	13	22	But the disciples looked one on the other, because they knew not concerning whom he spake.
B043C013V023	43	13	23	Now there was of his disciples one who reclined on his bosom; he whom Jeshu loved.
B043C013V024	43	13	24	To this signed Shemun Kipha that he would ask of whom it was that he spake.
B043C013V025	43	13	25	And that disciple fell upon the bosom of Jeshu, and said to him, My Lord, who is this?
B043C013V026	43	13	26	Jeshu answered and said to him, He to whom I give the dipped bread. And Jeshu dipped the bread and gave it to Jihuda bar Shemun Scarjuta.
B043C013V027	43	13	27	Then after the bread Satana entered into him. And Jeshu said to him, What thou doest, do with speed!
B043C013V028	43	13	28	But this no man knew of those who reclined of what he spake to him.
B043C013V029	43	13	29	For some of them thought that as Jihuda had the purse, he had instructed him to buy something that should be required at the feast, or that he should give somewhat to the poor.
B043C013V030	43	13	30	But he, Jihuda, received the bread and immediately went out: and it was night when he went out.
B043C013V031	43	13	31	AND Jeshu said, Now is glorified the Son of man, and Aloha is glorified in him.
B043C013V032	43	13	32	And if Aloha is glorified in him, Aloha shall glorify him in himself, and at once doth glorify him.
B043C013V033	43	13	33	My sons, a little longer I am with you, and you will seek me; and, as I said to the Jihudoyee, Whither I go you cannot come, so to you say I now.
B043C013V034	43	13	34	A new commandment give I to you, that you should love one another; as I have loved you, so do you also love one another.
B043C013V035	43	13	35	By this shall all men know that you are my disciples, if love be in you one for another.
B043C013V036	43	13	36	Shemun Kipha said to him, Our Lord, whither goest thou? Jeshu said to him, Whither I go, thou canst not now come after me; but at the last thou shalt come.
B043C013V037	43	13	37	Shemun Kipha saith to him, My Lord, why cannot I come after thee now? My life for thee lay I down.
B043C013V038	43	13	38	Jeshu saith to him, Dost thou lay down thy life for me! Amen, amen, I tell thee, That the cock will not crow, until thou shalt have denied me three times.
B043C014V001	43	14	1	LET not your heart be troubled: believe in Aloha, and in me believe.
B043C014V002	43	14	2	Many are the mansions of my Father's house: and if not, I would have told you; for I go to prepare for you a place.
B043C014V003	43	14	3	And if I go to prepare for you a place, I will come again and take you with me, that where I am you also may be.
B043C014V004	43	14	4	And whither I go you know, and the way you know.
B043C014V005	43	14	5	Thoma saith to him, Our Lord, we know not whither thou goest, and how can we know the way?
B043C014V006	43	14	6	Jeshu saith to him, I (am) the way, and the truth, and the life. No man cometh unto my Father unless by me.
B043C014V007	43	14	7	But if me you had known, my Father also would you have known: and henceforth you know him and have seen him.
B043C014V008	43	14	8	Philipos saith to him, Our Lord, show us the Father, and it sufficeth us.
B043C014V009	43	14	9	Jeshu saith to him, All this time have I been with you, and hast thou not known me, Philipé? He who me seeth, seeth the Father; and how sayest thou, Show us the Father?
B043C014V010	43	14	10	Believest thou not that I am in my Father and my Father in me? And these words that I speak, I speak not from myself, but my Father who dwelleth in me, he doeth these works.
B043C014V011	43	14	11	Believe that I am in my Father and my Father in me; and if not, even on account of the works, believe.
B043C014V012	43	14	12	Amen, amen, I say to you, That whosoever believeth in me, these works that I do shall he do also; and more than these shall he do, because I go unto my Father.
B043C014V013	43	14	13	And whatsoever you shall ask in my name, I will do for you, that the Father may be glorified in his Son.
B043C014V014	43	14	14	And if you shall ask (of) me in my name, I will do.
B043C014V015	43	14	15	IF you love me, keep my commandments;
B043C014V016	43	14	16	and I will pray of my Father, and another Paraclete will he give you, who will be with you for ever,
B043C014V017	43	14	17	the Spirit of truth, he whom the world cannot receive, because it doth not see him, nor know him. But you know him; for with you he dwelleth, and in you is.
B043C014V018	43	14	18	I will not leave you orphans; for I will come to you a little after.
B043C014V019	43	14	19	And the world seeth me not, but you shall see me; for because I live, you also shall live.
B043C014V020	43	14	20	In that day you will know that I am in my Father, and you in me, and I in you.
B043C014V021	43	14	21	He who hath my commandments and keepeth them is he who loveth me; and he who loveth me shall be loved of my Father, and I will love him, and will manifest to him myself.
B043C014V022	43	14	22	Jihuda saith to him, (it was not Scarjuta,) My Lord, how to us wilt thou manifest thyself, and not to the world?
B043C014V023	43	14	23	Jeshu replied, and said to him, He who loveth me, my word keepeth, and my Father will love him, and unto him we come, and a dwelling-place with him we make.
B043C014V024	43	14	24	But he who loveth me not, keepeth not my word. And the word that you hear is not mine, but of the Father who sent me.
B043C014V025	43	14	25	These have I spoken with you while I am with you.
B043C014V026	43	14	26	But he, the Paraclete, the Spirit of Holiness, whom the Father sendeth in my name, he shall teach you every thing, and he shall remind you of all that I have said to you.
B043C014V027	43	14	27	PEACE I leave with you; my peace I give to you: not as the world giveth, give I unto you. Let not your heart be troubled, nor be afraid.
B043C014V028	43	14	28	You have heard what I have told you, that I go, and come to you (again). If you had loved me, you would have rejoiced, because I go to my Father; for my Father is greater than I.
B043C014V029	43	14	29	And now, behold, I have told you while it is not done, that when it has been you may believe.
B043C014V030	43	14	30	Henceforth I will not speak with you much; for the ruler of the world cometh, and in me hath he nothing.
B043C014V031	43	14	31	But that the world may know that I love my Father, and as my Father hath commanded, so I do. Arise, let us go hence!
B043C015V001	43	15	1	I am the true vine, and my Father is the husbandman.
B043C015V002	43	15	2	Every branch which in me giveth not fruits he taketh away; and that which giveth fruits he cleanseth, that more fruits it may give.
B043C015V003	43	15	3	Now are you clean because of the word which I have spoken with you.
B043C015V004	43	15	4	Abide in me, and I in you. As the branch cannot give fruits of itself if it abide not in the vine, so also cannot you, if you abide not in me.
B043C015V005	43	15	5	I am the vine, and you the branches. Whoso abideth in me, and I in him, this produceth much fruits, because without me you cannot do any thing.
B043C015V006	43	15	6	But if a man abide not in me, he is cast without, as a withered branch; and, gathering, they cast it into the fire to burn.
B043C015V007	43	15	7	But if you abide in me, and my words abide in you, all whatever you will to ask shall be unto you.
B043C015V008	43	15	8	IN this is glorified my Father, that much fruit you give, and be my disciples.
B043C015V009	43	15	9	As my Father hath loved me, so I have loved you: continue in the love of me.
B043C015V010	43	15	10	If my commandments you will keep, you shall abide in my love; as I have kept the commandments of my Father, and abide in his love.
B043C015V011	43	15	11	These have I spoken with you, that my joy may be in you, and that your joy may be full.
B043C015V012	43	15	12	This is my commandment, That you love one another, as I have loved you.
B043C015V013	43	15	13	Love which is greater than this is not, that a man lay down his life for his friends.
B043C015V014	43	15	14	You are my friends, if you do all that I command you.
B043C015V015	43	15	15	No more I call you servants, for the servant knoweth not what doeth his Lord; but my friends have I called you; wherefore all that I have heard from my Father, I have made known unto you.
B043C015V016	43	15	16	You have not chosen me, but I have chosen you, and placed you, that you also may go (and) yield much fruit; and your fruit shall remain, because all that you shall ask the Father in my name, he will give to you.
B043C015V017	43	15	17	These I command you, That you love one another.
B043C015V018	43	15	18	And if the world hate you, know that, before you, it hated me.
B043C015V019	43	15	19	And if of the world you were, the world its own would have loved; but you are not of the world, for I have chosen you from the world; on which account the world hateth you.
B043C015V020	43	15	20	Remember the word which I spake with you, That there is no servant who is greater than his lord. If me they have persecuted, you also will they persecute; and if my word they had kept, yours also would they keep.
B043C015V021	43	15	21	But these all will they do to you on account of my name, because they know not Him who sent me.
B043C015V022	43	15	22	If I had not come and spoken with them, they had not had sin; but now have they no pretext for their sins.
B043C015V023	43	15	23	He who hateth me, my Father also hateth.
B043C015V024	43	15	24	And if the works I had not done before their eyes which no other man hath done, they had not had sin; but now they have seen and hated both me and my Father;
B043C015V025	43	15	25	that the word may be fulfilled which is written in their law, They hated me undeservedly.
B043C015V026	43	15	26	But when the Paraclete cometh, He whom I will send unto you from my Father, the Spirit of Truth, He who from my Father cometh forth, He shall testify of me.
B043C015V027	43	15	27	You also testify, because from the beginning are you with me.
B043C016V001	43	16	1	These have I spoken with you, that you may not be offended.
B043C016V002	43	16	2	They shall cast you out from their synagogues; and the hour cometh when every one who shall kill you will think that a sacrifice he offereth unto Aloha.
B043C016V003	43	16	3	And these will they do, because they have not known either my Father or me.
B043C016V004	43	16	4	THESE have I spoken with you, that when their time hath come you may remember that I told you. But these at first I did not tell you, because with you I was.
B043C016V005	43	16	5	But now I go unto Him who sent me; and no man of you asketh me, Whither goest thou?
B043C016V006	43	16	6	For I have told you these, and sorrow hath come and filled your hearts.
B043C016V007	43	16	7	But I the truth say to you, That it is needful for you that I go; for if I go not, the Paraclete cometh not to you. But if I go, I will send him to you.
B043C016V008	43	16	8	And when he hath come, he will convict the world of sin, and of righteousness, and of judgment.
B043C016V009	43	16	9	Of sin, because they believe not in me;
B043C016V010	43	16	10	but of righteousness, because unto my Father I go, and you see me not again;
B043C016V011	43	16	11	but of judgment, because the ruler of this world is judged.
B043C016V012	43	16	12	I have yet much to tell you, but you cannot now apprehend;
B043C016V013	43	16	13	but when the Spirit of Truth hath come, he will lead you into all the truth; for he will not speak of himself; but all that he shall hear he will speak, and the things to come will he make known to you.
B043C016V014	43	16	14	He will glorify me, because of mine he will take and will show you.
B043C016V015	43	16	15	All whatever that the Father hath is mine: on this account I have said to you, That of mine he will take, and will show you.
B043C016V016	43	16	16	A LITTLE (time), and you will not see me; and again a little, and you shall see me, because I go to the Father.
B043C016V017	43	16	17	And the disciples said one to another, What is this that he saith to us? A little (time), and you will not see me; and again a little (while), and you shall see me, and because I go to my Father.
B043C016V018	43	16	18	And they said, What is this little (time of) which he hath spoken?
B043C016V019	43	16	19	We know not what he saith. But Jeshu knew that they sought to ask him; and he said to them, Concerning this do you inquire together that I told you, A little (time), and you will not see me; and again a little, and you shall see me?
B043C016V020	43	16	20	Amen, amen, I tell you, That you will weep and lament, and the world will rejoice; and to you shall be sorrow; but your sorrow shall become joy.
B043C016V021	43	16	21	A woman, when she travaileth, hath sorrow, that the day hath come for her giving birth; but when she hath borne a son, she remembereth not her anguish, for joy that a child of man hath been born into the world.
B043C016V022	43	16	22	You also now have sorrow; but again I will see you, and your heart shall rejoice, and your joy no man taketh from you.
B043C016V023	43	16	23	And in that day you will ask me nothing. Amen, amen, I tell you, That whatsoever you shall ask my Father in my name, he will give you.
B043C016V024	43	16	24	Hitherto you have not asked any thing in my name: ask, and receive, that your joy may be full.
B043C016V025	43	16	25	These in parables I have spoken with you; but the hour cometh when I will not speak with you in parables, but manifestly; and I will announce to you concerning the Father.
B043C016V026	43	16	26	In that day you shall ask in my name; and I say not to you that I will ask of the Father for you;
B043C016V027	43	16	27	for the Father himself loveth you, because you have loved me, and have believed that from the Father I came forth.
B043C016V028	43	16	28	I came forth from the Father, and came into the world; and again I leave the world, and go unto the Father.
B043C016V029	43	16	29	His disciples say to him, Behold, now openly speakest thou, and not one parable hast thou spoken.
B043C016V030	43	16	30	Now know we that every thing thou knowest, and thou needest not that any man should ask thee. By this we believe that from Aloha thou hast come forth.
B043C016V031	43	16	31	JESHU saith to them, Believe!
B043C016V032	43	16	32	Behold, the hour shall come, and now cometh, that you will be dispersed (every) man to his place, and you will have left me alone. But I am not alone, because the Father is with me.
B043C016V033	43	16	33	These have I said to you, that in me you may have peace. In the world you shall have distress; but be of heart, I have conquered the world.
B043C017V001	43	17	1	These spake Jeshu; and, uplifting his eyes to heaven, he said, My Father, the hour hath come; glorify thy Son, that thy Son may glorify thee.
B043C017V002	43	17	2	As thou hast given him power over all flesh, that to all whom thou hast given him he should give the life which is eternal.
B043C017V003	43	17	3	But this is the life which is eternal, that they know thee, who art the true Aloha, and Him whom thou hast sent, Jeshu Meshicha.
B043C017V004	43	17	4	I have glorified thee on the earth; the work which thou didst give me to do, I have finished it.
B043C017V005	43	17	5	And now glorify thou me, my Father, with thyself, in that glory which I had with thee before the world was.
B043C017V006	43	17	6	I have made known thy name unto the sons of man; those whom thou gavest me from the world: thine they were, and to me didst thou give them; and they have kept thy word.
B043C017V007	43	17	7	Now have they known that whatsoever thou hast given me is from thee.
B043C017V008	43	17	8	And the words that thou gavest me I have given them, and they have received, and have known assuredly that from thee I came forth, and have believed that thou didst send me.
B043C017V009	43	17	9	And for them I pray; not for the world I pray, but for them whom thou hast given me, because they are thine.
B043C017V010	43	17	10	And every thing of mine is thine, and thine is mine, and I am glorified in them.
B043C017V011	43	17	11	Henceforth I am not in the world; but these are in the world, and I come to thee. Holy Father, keep them through thy name, that (name) which thou hast given to me, that they may be one as we are.
B043C017V012	43	17	12	While I was with them in the world, I kept them through thy name: those whom thou gavest me I have kept, and a man of them is not lost, but the son of perdition, that the scripture may be fulfilled.
B043C017V013	43	17	13	BUT now I come to thee, and these (things) I speak in the world, that they may have my joy completed in themselves.
B043C017V014	43	17	14	I have given them thy word, and the world hath hated them, because they are not of the world, as I am not of the world.
B043C017V015	43	17	15	Not that thou wouldest take them out of the world do I pray, but that thou wouldest keep them from the evil;
B043C017V016	43	17	16	for they are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.
B043C017V017	43	17	17	Father, sanctify them through thy truth; for thy word is truth.
B043C017V018	43	17	18	As me thou hast sent into the world, I also have sent them into the world.
B043C017V019	43	17	19	And for their sakes I consecrate myself, that they also may be consecrated for the truth.
B043C017V020	43	17	20	Nor for these do I pray only, but also for those who shall believe in me through their word;
B043C017V021	43	17	21	that they all may be one, as thou, my Father, (art) in me, and I in thee, that they also in us one may be; that the world may believe that thou hast sent me.
B043C017V022	43	17	22	And the glory which thou hast given me have I given unto them, that they may be one as we are one;
B043C017V023	43	17	23	I in them, and thou in me, that they may be perfected in one; and that the world may know that thou hast sent me, and that thou hast loved them, as me also thou hast loved.
B043C017V024	43	17	24	Father, those whom thou hast given I will that where I am they also may be with me, that they may see that glory of mine, which thou hast given to me; for thou lovedst me before the foundations of the world.
B043C017V025	43	17	25	My righteous Father, the world hath not known thee; but I have known thee, and these have known that thou hast sent me.
B043C017V026	43	17	26	And I have made known unto them thy name, and I make it known that the love itself, wherewith thou hast loved me, may be in them, and I may be in them.
B043C018V001	43	18	1	THESE said Jeshu, and went forth with his disciples over the ford of Kedrun, where there was a garden, which he entered with his disciples.
B043C018V002	43	18	2	But Jihuda, the traitor, also knew that place, because many-a-time had Jeshu there with his disciples convened.
B043C018V003	43	18	3	Jihuda then took a band, and from the chief priests and Pharishee he took officers, and came thither with lanterns and lamps and arms.
B043C018V004	43	18	4	But Jeshu, who knew every thing that should come upon him, went forth and said to them, Whom seek you?
B043C018V005	43	18	5	They say to him, Jeshu Natsroia. Jeshu saith to them, I am. And Jihuda the traitor was also standing with them.
B043C018V006	43	18	6	And when Jeshu had said to them, I am, they went backward and fell upon the ground.
B043C018V007	43	18	7	And Jeshu again asked them, Whom seek you? Then they said, Jeshu Natsroia.
B043C018V008	43	18	8	Jeshu saith to them, I have told you that I am; and if me you seek, let these go.
B043C018V009	43	18	9	That the word might be fulfilled which he spake, Of those whom thou hast given me I have not lost even one.
B043C018V010	43	18	10	But Shemun Kipha had a sword upon him, and he drew it, and smote the servant of the high priest, and took off his right ear.
B043C018V011	43	18	11	And the name of the servant was Molek. Jeshu said to Kipha, Put up the sword into its sheath; the cup which my Father hath given me shall I not drink it?
B043C018V012	43	18	12	Then the band and the captains and the officials of the Jihudoyee took Jeshu and bound him,
B043C018V013	43	18	13	and brought him unto Chanan first, because he was father-in-law of Kaiapha, he who was the high priest of that year.
B043C018V014	43	18	14	Now it was Kaiapha, he, who had counselled the Jihudoyee that it was expedient that one man should die for the people.
B043C018V015	43	18	15	But Shemun Kipha, and one of the other disciples, came after Jeshu. And that disciple knew the chief of the priests, and went in with Jeshu into the hall.
B043C018V016	43	18	16	But Shemun stood without at the door. And that other disciple, who knew the chief of the priests, went out and told the keeper of the door to admit Shemun.
B043C018V017	43	18	17	But the damsel keeping the door said to Shemun, Art thou also of the disciples of this man? He saith to her, No.
B043C018V018	43	18	18	And the servants and officials were standing, and they had set a fire to warm them, because it was cold; and Shemun stood also with them and warmed himself.
B043C018V019	43	18	19	And the high priest questioned Jeshu concerning his disciples, and concerning his doctrine.
B043C018V020	43	18	20	And Jeshu said to him, I openly discoursed with the people, and, at all time, taught in the synagogue and in the temple, where all the Jihudoyee assemble. And nothing in secret have I spoken.
B043C018V021	43	18	21	Why askest thou me? Ask them who have heard what I have said with them. Behold, they know every thing that I have said.
B043C018V022	43	18	22	And as these (words) he spake, one of the officers who stood (by) struck Jeshu upon his cheek, and said to him, Thus givest thou the answer to the chief of the priests?
B043C018V023	43	18	23	Jeshu replied and said to him, If wickedly I have spoken, bear witness of the evil; but if well, why hast thou struck me?
B043C018V024	43	18	24	But Chanan had sent Jeshu bound unto Kaiapha, chief of the priests.
B043C018V025	43	18	25	And Shemun Kipha stood and warmed (himself), and they say to him, Thou art also one of his disciples? And he denied and said, I am not.
B043C018V026	43	18	26	One of the servants of the chief of the priests said to him, the brother of him whose ear Shemun had cut off, Did not I see thee with him in the garden?
B043C018V027	43	18	27	And again Shemun denied. And in the same hour the cock crowed.
B043C018V028	43	18	28	NOW they led Jeshu from Kaiapha into the praetorium, and it was early. But they would not enter the praetorium, that they might not be defiled, until they should have eaten the petscha.
B043C018V029	43	18	29	But Pilatos came forth to them without, and said to them, What accusation have you against this man?
B043C018V030	43	18	30	They answered and said to him, If he were not a worker of evils, we would not to thee have delivered him.
B043C018V031	43	18	31	Pilatos saith to them, Take you him, and judge him according to your law.
B043C018V032	43	18	32	The Jihudoyee say to him, It is not lawful for us to put any one to death. That the word that Jeshu spake might be accomplished, when he declared by what death he should die.
B043C018V033	43	18	33	But Pilatos entered the Praetorium, and called Jeshu, and said to him, Art thou the king of the Jihudoyee?
B043C018V034	43	18	34	Jeshu saith to him, Of thyself sayest thou this, or did others tell thee concerning me?
B043C018V035	43	18	35	Pilatos saith to him, Am I a Jihudoya? The sons of thy people and the chief priests have delivered thee to me: what hast thou done?
B043C018V036	43	18	36	Jeshu saith to him, My kingdom is not from this world. If from this world were my kingdom, my servants would have fought, that I should not have been delivered to the Jihudoyee. But now my kingdom is not from hence.
B043C018V037	43	18	37	Pilatos saith to him, Then thou art a king? Jeshu saith to him, Thou hast said that I am a king. For this am I born, and for this I came into the world, to testify of the truth. Every one who is of the truth heareth my voice.
B043C018V038	43	18	38	Pilatos said to him, What is the truth? And when he had said this, he went forth again to the Jihudoyee, and said to them, I find not one cause in him.
B043C018V039	43	18	39	But you have a custom that one I should release to you at the petscha. Will you, therefore, that I release to you this King of the Jihudoyee?
B043C018V040	43	18	40	And they all cried and said, Not this, but Bar Aba. Now this Bar Aba was a robber.
B043C019V001	43	19	1	Then Pilatos scourged Jeshu.
B043C019V002	43	19	2	And the soldiers entwined a crown of thorns, and set it on his head; and they covered him with robes of purple,
B043C019V003	43	19	3	and said, Hail to thee, King of the Jihudoyee! and struck him upon his cheeks.
B043C019V004	43	19	4	And Pilatos came again forth, and said to them, Behold, I bring him to you forth, that you may know that I find nothing against him, nor one cause (of death).
B043C019V005	43	19	5	AND Jeshu came forth, having on him the crown of thorns and the robes of purple. And Pilatos said to them, Behold the man!
B043C019V006	43	19	6	But when the chief priests and officials saw him, they cried out, saying, Crucify him, crucify him! Pilatos saith to them, Take you him and crucify him; for I find in him no cause.
B043C019V007	43	19	7	The Jihudoyee say to him, We have a law, and, according to our law, he is guilty of death, because he made himself the son of Aloha.
B043C019V008	43	19	8	When Pilatos heard that word, he the more feared.
B043C019V009	43	19	9	And he entered again the praetorium, and said to Jeshu, Whence art thou? But Jeshu gave him no answer.
B043C019V010	43	19	10	Pilatos saith to him, With me speakest thou not? Knowest thou not that I have power to release thee, and power to crucify thee?
B043C019V011	43	19	11	Jeshu saith to him, Thou against ME hast no power, no not any, unless it hath been given to thee from above: wherefore he who delivered me to thee hath a sin greater than thine.
B043C019V012	43	19	12	On this account Pilatos willed to release him: but the Jihudoyee cried out, If this (man) thou releasest, thou art not the friend of Cesar: for whosoever maketh himself a king is the adversary of Cesar.
B043C019V013	43	19	13	But when Pilatos heard that word, he brought Jeshu without, and sat down upon the tribunal in the place which is called the Pavement of Stones, but in Hebrew it is called Gaphiphtha.
B043C019V014	43	19	14	And it was the preparation for the petscha. AND it was about the sixth hour. And he said to the Jihudoyee, Behold your king!
B043C019V015	43	19	15	But they cried out, Take him away, take him away! crucify him, crucify him! Pilatos saith to them, Your king shall I crucify? The chief priests say to him, We have no king but Cesar.
B043C019V016	43	19	16	Then delivered he him to them, that they might crucify him.
B043C019V017	43	19	17	And they took Jeshu, and led him forth, bearing his cross to a place which is called A Skull, but in Hebrew is Gogultha:
B043C019V018	43	19	18	there they crucified him, and with him two others, one on either side, and Jeshu in the midst.
B043C019V019	43	19	19	And a tablet also wrote Pilatos, and set it on the cross; and it was thus written, This is Jeshu Natsroya, King of the Jihudoyee.
B043C019V020	43	19	20	And this title many of the Jihudoyee read; for nigh to the city was the place where Jeshu was crucified; and the writing was in Hebrew and Greek and Roman.
B043C019V021	43	19	21	And the chief priests said to Pilatos, Do not write that he is king of the Jihudoyee, but that he said, I am the king of the Jihudoyee.
B043C019V022	43	19	22	Pilatos saith, That which I have written, I have written.
B043C019V023	43	19	23	BUT the soldiers, when they had crucified Jeshu, took his vestments and made four parts, a part unto each one of the soldiers: but his tunic was without seam, from the top woven all of it.
B043C019V024	43	19	24	And they said one to another, Let us not rend it, but play for it by playing, (to decide) whose it shall be: and fulfilled was the scripture which had said,
B043C019V025	43	19	25	They divided my garments among them, And upon my raiment did they cast the lot. These things did the soldiers. But there stood by the cross of Jeshu his mother, and the sister of his mother, and Mariam, she who was (the wife) of Cleopha, and Mariam Magdalitha.
B043C019V026	43	19	26	Jeshu seeth his mother, and that disciple whom he loved, standing; and he said to his mother, Woman, behold thy son!
B043C019V027	43	19	27	and he said to that disciple, Behold thy mother! And from that hour that disciple received her to be with him.
B043C019V028	43	19	28	After these Jeshu knew that every thing would be accomplished, and, that the scripture might be fulfilled, said, I thirst.
B043C019V029	43	19	29	And a vessel was set (there) filled with vinegar: then they filled a sponge from the vinegar, and put it upon hyssop, and offered it to his mouth.
B043C019V030	43	19	30	And when Jeshu had taken the vinegar, he said, Behold, it is finished! And he bowed his head, and delivered up his spirit.
B043C019V031	43	19	31	THE Jihudoyee, because it was the preparation, said, Let not these bodies remain-all-night upon the cross, because the shabath has lighted: for a great day was the day of that shabath. And they besought of Pilatos that they should break the legs of those (who had been) crucified, and take them down.
B043C019V032	43	19	32	And the soldiers came, and brake the legs of the first, and of that other who was crucified with him;
B043C019V033	43	19	33	but when they came unto Jeshu, they saw that he was dead already, and they brake not his legs.
B043C019V034	43	19	34	But one of the soldiers struck him in his side with the lance, and forthwith there came out blood and water.
B043C019V035	43	19	35	And he who SAW testifieth, and the truth is his testimony; and he knoweth that the truth he hath said, that you also may believe.
B043C019V036	43	19	36	For these things were done, that the scripture might be fulfilled, which said, that A bone shall not be broken in him.
B043C019V037	43	19	37	And again another scripture which said, They shall look upon him whom they pierced.
B043C019V038	43	19	38	After these Jauseph, he who was of Rometha, begged of Pilatos, for he was a disciple of Jeshu, but secretly for fear of the Jihudoyee, that he might take the body of Jeshu: and Pilatos permitted. And he came and took the body of Jeshu.
B043C019V039	43	19	39	And Nikodimos also came, he who at first had come to Jeshu by night, and he brought with him a condiment of myrrh and aloes, as a hundred lithreen.
B043C019V040	43	19	40	And they took the body of Jeshu, and wrapped it in cloths and in balsams, as is the manner of the Jihudoyee to bury.
B043C019V041	43	19	41	Now in that place where Jeshu was crucified was a garden, and in the garden a new sepulchre where one yet had not been laid.
B043C019V042	43	19	42	And they laid there Jeshu, because the shabath was coming in and the sepulchre was near.
B043C020V001	43	20	1	BUT in the first in the week came Mariam Magdalitha in the early-morn, (while it was) yet dark, unto the house of burial.
B043C020V002	43	20	2	And she saw the stone that it was taken from the sepulchre. And she ran, and came to Shemun Kipha, and to that other disciple, whom Jeshu loved, saying to them, They have taken away our Lord from that house of burial, and I know not where they have laid him.
B043C020V003	43	20	3	And Shemun went forth, and that other disciple, and they came to the house of burial.
B043C020V004	43	20	4	And they ran both of them together; but that disciple ran before Shemun, and came first to the house of burial.
B043C020V005	43	20	5	And looking, he saw the cloths lying, but entering he entered not.
B043C020V006	43	20	6	But Shemun came after him, and went into the house of burial, and saw the cloths set,
B043C020V007	43	20	7	and the napkin that had been bound upon his head, not with the cloths, but folded up, and laid apart in one place.
B043C020V008	43	20	8	Then went in also that disciple who came first to the house of burial, and he saw, and believed.
B043C020V009	43	20	9	For not yet knew they the scriptures, that he was to rise from the dead.
B043C020V010	43	20	10	And those disciples went again to their place.
B043C020V011	43	20	11	But Mariam stood at the sepulchre weeping: and while weeping, she looked into the sepulchre,
B043C020V012	43	20	12	and saw two angels in white, who were sitting, one at his pillows, and one at his feet, where the body of Jeshu had lain.
B043C020V013	43	20	13	And they say to her, Woman, why weepest thou? She saith to them, Because they have taken away my Lord, and I know not where they have laid him.
B043C020V014	43	20	14	This said she, and turned herself back, and saw Jeshu standing, and knew not that it was Jeshu.
B043C020V015	43	20	15	Jeshu saith to her, Woman, why weepest thou? and whom seekest thou? But she thought he was the gardener, and said to him, Sir, if thou have taken him away, tell me where thou hast laid him, and I will go (and) take him away.
B043C020V016	43	20	16	Jeshu saith to her, Mariam. She turned and saith to him in Hebrew, Rabuni, which is saying, Malphona.
B043C020V017	43	20	17	Jeshu saith to her, Touch me not; for not yet have I ascended to my Father: but go to my brethren, and say to them, I ascend to my Father, and to your Father, to my God, and to your God.
B043C020V018	43	20	18	Then went Mariam Magdalitha, and announced to the disciples that she had seen our Lord, and (that) these (words) he had spoken to her.
B043C020V019	43	20	19	WHEN it was the evening of that day which (was) the first in the week, and the doors were shut where the disciples were, for fear of the Jihudoyee, came Jeshu, stood among them, and said to them, Peace (be) with you.
B043C020V020	43	20	20	This he said, and showed them his hands and his side. And the disciples rejoiced when they saw our Lord.
B043C020V021	43	20	21	Then said Jeshu unto them, Peace (be) with you: as my Father sent me, I also send you.
B043C020V022	43	20	22	And when he had said these, he breathed on them, and said to them, Receive the Spirit of Holiness:
B043C020V023	43	20	23	if you forgive sins to a man, they shall be forgiven to him; and if you retain (the sins) of a man, they are retained.
B043C020V024	43	20	24	But Thoma, one of the twelve, he who was called the Twin, was not there with them when Jeshu came.
B043C020V025	43	20	25	And the disciples say to him, We have seen our Lord. But he said to them, Unless I see in his hands the places of the nails, and put into them my fingers, and extend my hand into his side, I believe not.
B043C020V026	43	20	26	AND after eight days again within were the disciples, and Thoma with them. And Jeshu came, while the doors were shut, stood in the midst, and said to them, Peace (be) with you.
B043C020V027	43	20	27	And he said to Thoma, Bring thy finger hither and see my hands, and bring thy hand and thrust it into my side, and be not unbelieving but believing.
B043C020V028	43	20	28	And Thoma answered and said to him, My Lord, and my God!
B043C020V029	43	20	29	Jeshu saith to him, Now that thou hast seen, thou hast believed: blessed are they who have not seen me, and have believed.
B043C020V030	43	20	30	But many other signs did Jeshu before his disciples: those are not written in this record;
B043C020V031	43	20	31	but these are written, that you may believe that Jeshu is the Meshicha, the Son of Aloha, and that when you have believed you may have in his name the life which is eternal.
B043C021V001	43	21	1	AFTER these Jeshu again showed himself to his disciples at the sea of Tiberios; and he showed (himself) thus.
B043C021V002	43	21	2	There were together Shemun Kipha, and Thoma who was called the Twin, and Nathanael, he who was of Kotna of Galila, and the sons of Zabdai, and two other of the disciples.
B043C021V003	43	21	3	Shemun Kipha saith to them, I go to net fishes. They say to him, We also go with thee. And they went forth and ascended into a vessel; and through that night they netted nothing.
B043C021V004	43	21	4	But when it was morning Jeshu stood on the sea shore; but the disciples knew not that it was Jeshu.
B043C021V005	43	21	5	And Jeshu said to them, Children, have you any thing to eat? They say to him, No.
B043C021V006	43	21	6	He saith to them, Cast your net on the right side of the vessel, and you shall find. And they cast (it), and could not draw the net for the multitude of fishes which it held.
B043C021V007	43	21	7	And that disciple whom Jeshu loved said to Kipha, This is our Lord. But Shemun, when he heard that it was our Lord, took his tunic, and threw it over his loins, for he was naked, and cast himself into the sea to come to Jeshu.
B043C021V008	43	21	8	But the other disciples came in the vessel, for they were not far from the land, but as two hundred ameen, and they drew that net of fishes.
B043C021V009	43	21	9	Then when they had ascended the land, they saw coals laid, and fish laid upon them, and bread.
B043C021V010	43	21	10	And Jeshu said, Bring of the fish which you have now caught.
B043C021V011	43	21	11	And Shemun Kipha went up, and drew the net to land full of great fishes, an hundred and fifty and three: yet for all this weight that net was not broken.
B043C021V012	43	21	12	And Jeshu said to them, Come, dine. But one of the disciples did not dare to ask him, Who is he? for they knew that it was our Lord.
B043C021V013	43	21	13	And Jeshu drew near, and took bread, and fish, and gave to them.
B043C021V014	43	21	14	This is the third time that Jeshu was seen by his disciples when he had risen from among the dead.
B043C021V015	43	21	15	WHEN they had dined, Jeshu said to Shemun Kipha, Shemun bar Jona, lovest thou me more than these? He saith to him, Yes, my Lord, thou knowest that I love thee. Jeshu saith to him, Feed my lambs.
B043C021V016	43	21	16	He saith to him again the second time, Shemun bar Jona, lovest thou me? He saith to him, Yes, my Lord, thou knowest that I love thee. Jeshu saith to him, Feed my sheep.
B043C021V017	43	21	17	Jeshu saith to him again the third time, Shemun bar Jona, lovest thou me? And it grieved Kipha that he said to him the third time, Lovest thou me? And he said to him, My Lord, all things thou understandest, thou knowest that I love thee. Jeshu saith to him, Feed my sheep.
B043C021V018	43	21	18	Amen, I say to thee, When thou wast young, thou didst gird thy loins and walk whithersoever thou willedst; but when thou art old, thou shalt stretch forth thy hands, and another will bind thy loins, and conduct thee whither thou willest not.
B043C021V019	43	21	19	But this he said, to show by what death he was to glorify Aloha. And when he had said these, he said to him, Come after me.
B043C021V020	43	21	20	AND Shemun turned, and saw the disciple whom Jeshu loved following; he, who leaned at the supper upon the bosom of Jeshu, and said, My Lord, who is he that betrayeth thee?
B043C021V021	43	21	21	This when Kipha saw, he said to Jeshu, My Lord, and this, what?
B043C021V022	43	21	22	Jeshu saith to him, If I will that this wait until I come, what (is that) to thee? Come thou after me.
B043C021V023	43	21	23	And that word went forth among the brethren, that that disciple dieth not. But Jeshu did not say, He dieth not, but, If I will that this (man) wait until I come, what (is that) to thee?
B043C021V024	43	21	24	This is the disciple who hath testified of all these, and hath also written them: and we know that the truth is his testimony.
B043C021V025	43	21	25	There are also many other things which Jeshu hath done, those that if one by one they were written, not the world also itself, as I think, would suffice for the books that could be written.
B044C001V001	44	1	1	THE former writing, O Theophilus, I wrote concerning all those (things) which our Lord Jeshu Meshiha began to do and to teach,
B044C001V002	44	1	2	until that day in which he was taken up, after that he had instructed those apostles whom he had chosen by the Holy Spirit:
B044C001V003	44	1	3	to whom also he showed himself alive, after he had suffered, with many signs, for forty days, appearing to them, and discoursing on the kingdom of Aloha.
B044C001V004	44	1	4	And when he had eaten bread with them, he directed them that from Urishlem they should not remove; but await the promise of the Father, which, you have heard from me.
B044C001V005	44	1	5	For Juhanon baptized with waters, but you shall be baptized with the Spirit of Holiness after days not many.
B044C001V006	44	1	6	But they when assembled asked him, and said to him, Our Lord, at this time wilt thou restore the kingdom to Israel?
B044C001V007	44	1	7	He saith to them, This is not yours to know the time or the times which the Father hath reposed in his own authority:
B044C001V008	44	1	8	but when the Spirit of Holiness hath come upon you, you shall receive power to be made unto me the witnesses, in Urishlem and in all Jehud, and also among the Shomroyee, and unto the confines of the earth.
B044C001V009	44	1	9	And as these he said, while they beheld him, he was taken up, and the cloud received him, and he was covered from their eyes.
B044C001V010	44	1	10	And while they looked to the heavens as he went, two men were found standing with them in white vestments;
B044C001V011	44	1	11	and they said to them, Men, Galiloyee, why stand you looking to the heavens 3? this Jeshu who is taken up from you into the heavens will so come as you have seen him ascend into the heavens.
B044C001V012	44	1	12	And afterward they returned to Urishlem from the mount which is called the place of Olives, which is over against Urishlem, and distant from her as seven stadias.
B044C001V013	44	1	13	And after they had entered, they ascended to that upper room in which were Petros, and Juhanon, and Jakub, and Andros, and Philipos, and Thoma, and Mathai, and Bar Tolmai, and Jakub bar Halphai, and Shemun the Zealous, and Jihuda bar Jakub.
B044C001V014	44	1	14	These altogether persevered in prayer with one soul, with the women, and with Mariam the mother of Jeshu, and with his brethren.
B044C001V015	44	1	15	AND in those days arose Shemun Kipha in the midst of the disciples;-now there was there an assembly of men as an hundred and twenty;-and said,
B044C001V016	44	1	16	Men, brethren, it was right for that scripture to be fulfilled which the Spirit of Holiness had before spoken, by the mouth of David, concerning Jihuda, who was the leader of them who took Jeshu.
B044C001V017	44	1	17	For he had numbered with us, and had part in this ministry.
B044C001V018	44	1	18	This is he who obtained the field with the wages of sin, and fell upon his face on the ground, and was severed in his middle, and all his bowels were shed forth.
B044C001V019	44	1	19	And this hath been known of all who dwell in Urishlem; and so is called that field in the language of the country Hakel-damo, the interpretation of which is, A field of blood.
B044C001V020	44	1	20	For it is written in the book of Psalms: Let his habitation be desert, And no inhabitant be therein, And his ministry let another take.
B044C001V021	44	1	21	There needeth therefore one from these men who have been with us in all this time in which our Lord Jeshu hath come in and gone out among us,
B044C001V022	44	1	22	which went forth from the baptism of Juhanon until the day that he was taken up from (being) with us, to be with us a witness of his resurrection.
B044C001V023	44	1	23	And they set up two: Jauseph, who is called Barshaba, who is surnamed Justus, and Mathia.
B044C001V024	44	1	24	And praying, they said, Thou, Lord, (who) knowest the hearts of all, show the one whom thou choosest of these two,
B044C001V025	44	1	25	that he may receive the part in the ministry and the apostleship from which Jihuda separated, to go unto his place.
B044C001V026	44	1	26	And they cast the lots, and it came up unto Mathia; and he was numbered with the eleven apostles.
B044C002V001	44	2	1	AND when the days of pentecost were fulfilled, while they were assembled all together,
B044C002V002	44	2	2	there was suddenly from heaven the voice as of a mighty wind, and all that house in which they were sitting was filled with it;
B044C002V003	44	2	3	and tongues that were divided like fire appeared to them, and sat upon each one of them.
B044C002V004	44	2	4	And they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and they began to speak in several tongues as the Spirit gave them to speak.
B044C002V005	44	2	5	But there were men dwelling in Urishlem who feared Aloha; Jihudoyee, from all the peoples who are under heaven.
B044C002V006	44	2	6	And when that voice was made, the whole people assembled and were perturbed, because every man of them heard as they spoke in their (several) tongues.
B044C002V007	44	2	7	(And) they were all astonished, and wondered, saying one to another, These all who speak, behold, are they not Galiloyee?
B044C002V008	44	2	8	How hear we (then) each in his own tongue in which we were born?
B044C002V009	44	2	9	Parthoyee and Medoyee and Alanoyee, and they who dwell in the Place of Rivers, Jihudoyee and Kapadukoyee, and of the region of Pontos and of Asia;
B044C002V010	44	2	10	and from the land of Phrygia and of Pamphylia and of Metsreen, and the regions of Lybi neighbouring upon Kyrine, and those who come from Rumi, Jihudoyee, and Proselytes,
B044C002V011	44	2	11	and from Krete and Arabia, behold, we hear them speaking in our tongues the wonders of Aloha.
B044C002V012	44	2	12	But all of them were amazed and admired, saying one to another, Of whom is this thing?
B044C002V013	44	2	13	But others mocked them, saying, These have drunk new wine, and are inebriate.
B044C002V014	44	2	14	And afterwards arose Shemun Kipha with the eleven apostles, and lifted up his voice and said to them: Men, Jihudoyee, and all who dwell at Urishlem, be this known to you, and hearken to my words.
B044C002V015	44	2	15	For not as you suppose are these drunken; for, behold, until now are three hours.
B044C002V016	44	2	16	But this is that spoken of by Joel the prophet:
B044C002V017	44	2	17	It shall be in the last days, saith Aloha, I will pour my Spirit upon all flesh: And your sons and your daughters shall prophesy, And your youths shall see visions,
B044C002V018	44	2	18	And your elders shall dream dreams: And upon the servants and upon the handmaids Will I pour my Spirit in those days; And they shall prophesy.
B044C002V019	44	2	19	And I will give signs in heaven, And mighty (deeds) on earth; Blood and fire and clouds of smoke:
B044C002V020	44	2	20	The sun shall be turned into darkness, And the moon into blood, Before shall come the day of the Lord, great and fearful;
B044C002V021	44	2	21	And every one who shall call the name Of the Lord shall be saved.
B044C002V022	44	2	22	MEN, sons of Israel, hear these words; Jeshu Natsroya, the man who from Aloha appeared with you, with powers and mighty acts, which Aloha wrought among you by his hand, (even) as you know,
B044C002V023	44	2	23	This, who was separated thereunto by the foreknowledge and by the will of Aloha, you delivered into the hands of the wicked, and crucified and slew.
B044C002V024	44	2	24	But Aloha raised him, and loosed the bands of Shiul, because it was not possible that he should be holden in Shiul.
B044C002V025	44	2	25	For David said concerning him, I have foreseen my Lord at all time, Who is at my right hand that I should not be moved;
B044C002V026	44	2	26	Wherefore my heart is glad, And my glory rejoiceth: And also my body shall sojourn in hope;
B044C002V027	44	2	27	For thou wilt not leave my soul in Shiul, Nor give thy Saint to see corruption.
B044C002V028	44	2	28	Thou wilt reveal to me the way of life, Thou wilt fill me with joy with thy presence.
B044C002V029	44	2	29	Men, brethren, suffer me to speak openly with you concerning the chief-father David, that he is dead and also buried, and his sepulchre is with us till this day.
B044C002V030	44	2	30	For he was a prophet, and knew that the oath Aloha had sworn to him, Of the fruit of thy loins I will cause to sit upon thy throne:
B044C002V031	44	2	31	And he foresaw and spake concerning, the resurrection of the Meshiha, that He would not be left in Shiul, nor would his body see corruption.
B044C002V032	44	2	32	This Jeshu hath Aloha raised, and we all are his witnesses.
B044C002V033	44	2	33	And he it is who at the right hand of Aloha is exalted, and hath received of the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit, and hath shed forth this gift, which, behold, you see and you hear.
B044C002V034	44	2	34	For David hath not ascended into heaven, because he himself hath said, The Lord said unto my Lord, Sit thou at my right hand
B044C002V035	44	2	35	Until I place thine adversaries the stool of thy feet.
B044C002V036	44	2	36	Assuredly, then, let all the house of Israel know, that Lord and Meshiha hath Aloha made this Jeshu, whom you crucified.
B044C002V037	44	2	37	AND when they heard, they were pierced in their heart, and said to Shemun and to the rest of the apostles, What shall we do, brethren?
B044C002V038	44	2	38	Shemun saith to them, Repent, and be baptized, every man of you, in the name of the Lord Jeshu, for the remission of sins, and you shall receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.
B044C002V039	44	2	39	For to you is the promise, and to your children, and to all them who are afar off, whom Aloha himself shall call.
B044C002V040	44	2	40	And with many other words he testified to them and entreated of them, saying, Save (yourselves) from this perverse generation.
B044C002V041	44	2	41	And some of them eagerly received his word and believed and were baptized, and there were added in that day as three thousand souls.
B044C002V042	44	2	42	And they were faithful in the doctrine of the apostles, and participated in prayer and in the breaking of the eucharist.
B044C002V043	44	2	43	And solemnity was on every soul; and many signs and mighty acts were done by the hand of the apostles in Urishlem.
B044C002V044	44	2	44	And all those who believed were together, and every thing they had was in common.
B044C002V045	44	2	45	And they who had property sold it, and divided to each according to that which he needed.
B044C002V046	44	2	46	And every day they continued in the temple with one soul, and in the house they brake the bread, and took their food rejoicing and in the cleanness of their hearts,
B044C002V047	44	2	47	praising Aloha, (and) given (to be) in favour before all the people. And our Lord added daily them who were saved into the church.
B044C003V001	44	3	1	AND it was that as Shemun Kipha and Juhanon ascended together to the temple at the time of prayer, which is the ninth hour,
B044C003V002	44	3	2	behold a certain man lame from the womb of his mother, (whom) they carried, who were used to bring and set at the gate of the temple which is called the Beautiful, to beg alms of those who entered into the temple.
B044C003V003	44	3	3	He, when he saw Shemun and Juhanon entering the temple, prayed of them to give him alms.
B044C003V004	44	3	4	And Shemun and Juhanon beheld him, and said to him, Regard us.
B044C003V005	44	3	5	But he regarded them, expecting to receive from them somewhat.
B044C003V006	44	3	6	Shemun saith to him, Gold and silver I have not, but what I have I give thee: In the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha Natsroya, rise and walk.
B044C003V007	44	3	7	And he took him by his right hand and raised him: and instantly his feet strengthened and his heels.
B044C003V008	44	3	8	And he leaped and arose and walked, and entered with them into the temple, walking, and leaping, and glorifying Aloha.
B044C003V009	44	3	9	And all the people saw him walking and glorifying Aloha.
B044C003V010	44	3	10	And they knew that it was he, the beggar, who had sat daily and asked alms at the gate which is called the Beautiful. And they were filled with wonder and astonishment at what had been done.
B044C003V011	44	3	11	AND as he held Shemun and Juhanon, all the people ran wondering unto them to the portico which is called Of Shelemun.
B044C003V012	44	3	12	And when Shemun saw, he answered and said to them, Men, sons of Israel, why wonder you at this? or why gaze you at us, as by power of ours, or by our (own) authority, we had done this, that this (man) should walk?
B044C003V013	44	3	13	The God of Abraham, and of Ishok, and of Jakub, the God of our fathers, hath glorified his son Jeshu, him whom you delivered up, and denied before the face of Pilatos, when he had justified (him) and would have released him;
B044C003V014	44	3	14	but you the Holy and the Just denied, and demanded for you the man the murderer to be given to you.
B044C003V015	44	3	15	And Him the Prince of life you killed, whom Aloha hath raised from among the dead; and we all are his witnesses.
B044C003V016	44	3	16	And by faith in his name, this, whom you see and know, he hath strengthened and healed; and faith which is in him hath given to him this soundness before you all.
B044C003V017	44	3	17	Now, however, my brethren, I know that through delusion you did this, as also did your princes;
B044C003V018	44	3	18	and Aloha, according to that which he had before proclaimed by the mouth of all the prophets, that his Meshiha should suffer, hath fulfilled this.
B044C003V019	44	3	19	Repent therefore, and be converted, that your sins may be blotted out, and that the times of repose may come to you from before the presence of the Lord;
B044C003V020	44	3	20	and he may send to you Him whom he hath ordained for you, Jeshu Meshiha,
B044C003V021	44	3	21	whom the heavens must receive until the completion of the times of all those which Aloha hath spoken by the mouth of his holy prophets, who (have been) from of old.
B044C003V022	44	3	22	For Musha hath said, A prophet shall the Lord raise up unto you from your brethren, like to me; him hear in all (things) which he shall speak with you.
B044C003V023	44	3	23	And it shall be that every soul who will not hear that prophet, perish shall that soul from his people.
B044C003V024	44	3	24	And the prophets, all of them from Shamuel and they who were after him, spake and proclaimed concerning these days.
B044C003V025	44	3	25	You are the sons of the prophets; and the covenant which Aloha set with our fathers, saying unto Abraham, In thy seed shall be blessed all the generations of the earth,
B044C003V026	44	3	26	with you from the first he hath established; and Aloha hath sent his Son, blessing you, if you will return and repent of your iniquities.
B044C004V001	44	4	1	AND while they spake these words to the people, the priests, and Zadukoyee, and the governors of the temple, arose against them,
B044C004V002	44	4	2	being angered against them because they taught the people, and preached through the Meshiha the resurrection from the dead.
B044C004V003	44	4	3	And they laid upon them hands, and kept them unto the day after, because the evening had drawn nigh.
B044C004V004	44	4	4	And many who heard the word believed; and they were in number as five thousand men.
B044C004V005	44	4	5	And the day after, the rulers, and elders, and sophree, assembled,
B044C004V006	44	4	6	and also Hanan chief of the priests, and Kaiapha, and Juhanon, and Alexandros, and they who were of the race of the chief priests.
B044C004V007	44	4	7	And when they had made them stand in the midst, they questioned them, By what power, or in what name, have you done this?
B044C004V008	44	4	8	Then Shemun Kipha was filled with the Spirit of Holiness, and said to them, Rulers of the people, and elders of the house of Israel,
B044C004V009	44	4	9	hear: If we this day are judged of you concerning the good which has been done to the infirm man, insomuch that he is cured;
B044C004V010	44	4	10	be this known to you, and to all the people of Israel, that in the name of Jeshu Meshiha Natsroya, whom you crucified, whom Aloha hath raised from among the dead, through this Himself, behold, this (man) standeth before you well.
B044C004V011	44	4	11	This is the stone which you builders rejected, and he is become the head of the corner.
B044C004V012	44	4	12	And in no other one is redemption: for there is no other name under heaven given to mankind, by which we must be saved.
B044C004V013	44	4	13	And when they heard the words of Shemun and of Juhanon, which they had confidently spoken, they perceived that they knew not literature and were common-men, and wondered at them; and they recognised them, that with Jeshu they had been conversant.
B044C004V014	44	4	14	And they saw that the lame man who had been healed was standing with them, and they could not say any thing against them.
B044C004V015	44	4	15	Then they commanded that they should lead them from their assembly, and said one to another,
B044C004V016	44	4	16	What shall we do with these men? For, behold, a conspicuous sign which hath been done by their hands to all the inhabitants of Urishlem is known, and we cannot deny.
B044C004V017	44	4	17	But that this report may not go forth more, we will threaten them that again they shall not speak in This Name to any man.
B044C004V018	44	4	18	And they called them, and commanded them that not at all they should speak and teach in the name of Jeshu.
B044C004V019	44	4	19	SHEMUN KIPHA and Juhanon answered and said to them, If it be right before Aloha that you we obey rather than Aloha, judge you.
B044C004V020	44	4	20	For what we have seen and heard we cannot but speak.
B044C004V021	44	4	21	And they threatened them, and dismissed them; for they could not find cause to lay upon their head, because of the people; for every one glorified Aloha for that which had been done.
B044C004V022	44	4	22	For a son of more than forty years was that man in whom had been wrought this sign of healing.
B044C004V023	44	4	23	And when they were dismissed they came to their brethren, and made known to them whatever the priests and elders had said.
B044C004V024	44	4	24	And they, when they had heard, with one accord lifted up their voice unto Aloha, and said, Lord, thou art God who hast made heaven and earth and the seas, and all that is in them:
B044C004V025	44	4	25	And thou art he who hast spoken by the Spirit of Holiness in the mouth of David thy servant: Why rage the Heathen, And the peoples imagine vanity?
B044C004V026	44	4	26	The kings and powers of the earth arise And counsel together against the Lord, And against his Meshiha.
B044C004V027	44	4	27	For verily they are assembled in this city against thy holy Son Jeshu, whom thou hast anointed,-Herodes and Pilatos with the Gentiles and the synagogue of Israel,
B044C004V028	44	4	28	to work whatsoever thy hand and thy will have signified before should be done.
B044C004V029	44	4	29	And now also, Lord, behold and see their threatenings, and give unto thy servants with boldness to preach thy word,
B044C004V030	44	4	30	while thy hand thou outstretchest unto healings and mighty works which they shall do in the name of thy holy Son Jeshu.
B044C004V031	44	4	31	And as they prayed and supplicated, the place in which they were assembled was moved, and they were all filled with the Spirit of Holiness, and they spake with openness the word of Aloha.
B044C004V032	44	4	32	BUT to the assembly of the men who believed there was one soul and one mind; and no man of them said of the goods which he possessed that they were his own, but all whatever they had was in common.
B044C004V033	44	4	33	And with great power did those apostles testify concerning the resurrection of Jeshu Meshiha, and great grace was with all of them.
B044C004V034	44	4	34	And no man of them had want; for they who possessed fields and houses sold, and brought the prices of whatever was sold
B044C004V035	44	4	35	and laid at the feet of the apostles, and there was given to each according to that which was needed.
B044C004V036	44	4	36	But Jauseph, who was entitled Bar Naba by the apostles, which is interpreted, A son of consolation, a Levoya from the Isle of Kypros,
B044C004V037	44	4	37	had a field, and he sold it, and brought its price and laid before the feet of the apostles.
B044C005V001	44	5	1	AND a certain man whose name was Hanania, with his wife whose name was Shaphira, sold a field,
B044C005V002	44	5	2	and took from its value and concealed, while his wife consented, and brought of it silver and laid before the feet of the apostles.
B044C005V003	44	5	3	And Shemun said to him, Hanania, how hath Satana thus filled thine heart that thou shouldest lie to the Spirit of Holiness, and conceal from the silver of the price of the field?
B044C005V004	44	5	4	Was it not thine own until it should be sold? and when it was sold thou hadst yet power over the price of it. Why hast thou laid up in thy heart to do this thing? Thou hast not lied unto men, but unto Aloha!
B044C005V005	44	5	5	And when Hanania heard these words he fell and died. And there was great fear upon all those who heard.
B044C005V006	44	5	6	And they who were young men among them arose and composed him, carried him forth and buried him.
B044C005V007	44	5	7	And after there had been three hours, his wife also entered, not knowing what had been done.
B044C005V008	44	5	8	Shemun said to her, Tell me if for these prices you sold the field? But she said, Yes: for these prices.
B044C005V009	44	5	9	Shemun said to her, Why have you agreed to tempt the Spirit of the Lord? Lo, the feet of the buriers of thy husband are at the door, and they will carry thee out!
B044C005V010	44	5	10	And at once she fell before their feet and died. And those young men entered and found her dead, and they laid her out, and brought her forth and buried her by the side of her husband.
B044C005V011	44	5	11	And there was great fear upon all the church and in all them who heard.
B044C005V012	44	5	12	AND by the hand of the apostles were done great signs and mighty works among the people: and all gathered together at the portico of Shelemun.
B044C005V013	44	5	13	And from the others not a man dared to come near them; but the people magnified them.
B044C005V014	44	5	14	And the more were they who believed added to the Lord, an assemblage of men and of women;
B044C005V015	44	5	15	so that into the streets they brought forth the diseased lying on beds, that, when Shemun should come, even his shadow might overshadow them.
B044C005V016	44	5	16	But there came many to them from the other cities round about Urishlem, bringing the diseased and those who had unclean spirits: and they were healed, all of them.
B044C005V017	44	5	17	And the chief of the priests, and they who were with him, who were of the doctrine of the Zadukoyee, were filled with envy,
B044C005V018	44	5	18	and they laid hands on the apostles, and apprehended and bound them in the house of the bound.
B044C005V019	44	5	19	Then in the night the angel of the Lord opened the gate of the house of the bound, and brought them forth, and said to them,
B044C005V020	44	5	20	Go stand in the temple and speak to the people all these words of salvation.
B044C005V021	44	5	21	And they went forth in the time of morning, and entered the temple, and taught. But the chief of the priests and they who were with him arose (and) convoked their associates and the elders of Israel, and sent to the house of the bound to bring the apostles.
B044C005V022	44	5	22	And when they who were sent from them went, they found them not (in) the house of the bound; and they returned, and came,
B044C005V023	44	5	23	and said, We found the house of the bound shut carefully, and the keepers standing at the gates: and we opened, but no man found we there.
B044C005V024	44	5	24	And when the chief priests and rulers of the temple heard these words, they were astounded by them, and reasoned, what this was.
B044C005V025	44	5	25	And one came and declared to them, Those men whom you shut up in the house of the bound, behold, they are standing in the temple and teaching the people.
B044C005V026	44	5	26	Then went the rulers with the satellites to bring them, not with violence, for they feared lest the people should stone them;
B044C005V027	44	5	27	and when they had brought them they made them stand before all the assembly, and the chief of the priests began to say to them,
B044C005V028	44	5	28	Did we not commanding command you, that you should teach no man in this name? But, behold, you have filled Urishlem with your doctrine, and you will to bring upon us the blood of this man!
B044C005V029	44	5	29	SHEMUN answered with the apostles and said to them, Aloha must we obey rather than men.
B044C005V030	44	5	30	The God of our fathers hath raised up Jeshu whom you killed and hanged on the tree.
B044C005V031	44	5	31	Him hath Aloha constituted a Prince and a Saviour, and elevated him at his right hand, to give repentance and remission of sins unto Israel.
B044C005V032	44	5	32	And we are witnesses of these words, and the Spirit of Holiness himself, whom Aloha hath given to them who believe in him.
B044C005V033	44	5	33	And when they heard these words they were transported with rage, and were mindful to kill them.
B044C005V034	44	5	34	And one of the Pharishee arose, whose name was Gamaliel, a doctor of the law, and honoured by all the people, and commanded to take the apostles without a little time.
B044C005V035	44	5	35	And he said to them, Men, sons of Israel, beware of yourselves, and consider what it behoves you to do concerning these men.
B044C005V036	44	5	36	For before this time arose Thuda, and said of himself that he was something great, and there went after him four hundred men: and he was slain, and they who went after him were scattered and became as nothing.
B044C005V037	44	5	37	Afterward arose Jihuda Galiloya in the days when men were enregistered for the head-silver, and tempted much people after him; and he died, and all they who went after him were scattered.
B044C005V038	44	5	38	And now I say to you, keep aloof from these men, and dismiss them; for if from men be this imagination and this work, it will be dissolved and end;
B044C005V039	44	5	39	but if it be from Aloha, there is no power in your hands to bring it to an end: lest you should be found to have arisen against Aloha.
B044C005V040	44	5	40	And they were persuaded by him, and called the apostles, and scourged them, and commanded them that they should not teach in the name of Jeshu, and loosed them.
B044C005V041	44	5	41	And they went out from before them, rejoicing to be worthy for the sake of the Name to be ill treated.
B044C005V042	44	5	42	And they ceased not daily to teach in the temple, and in the house, and to preach concerning our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B044C006V001	44	6	1	AND in those days the disciples being many, the Javnoyee disciples murmured against the Ebroyee because their widows were slighted in the daily ministration.
B044C006V002	44	6	2	And the twelve apostles called all the assembly of the disciples and said to them, It is not fit that we should leave the word of Aloha, and serve tables.
B044C006V003	44	6	3	Look out therefore, brethren, and choose seven men from you who have testimony concerning them, and are full of the Spirit of the Lord and wisdom, and we will appoint them over this matter.
B044C006V004	44	6	4	And we will be constant in prayer, and in the ministration of the word.
B044C006V005	44	6	5	And this saying was pleasing before all the people; and they chose Estephanos, a man who was full of faith and the Spirit of Holiness; and Philipos, and Prokoros, and Nicanor, and Timon, and Parmena, and Nikolos, a proselyte of Antiokia.
B044C006V006	44	6	6	And these they set before the apostles: and while praying they laid upon them the hand.
B044C006V007	44	6	7	And the word of Aloha increased, and the number of the disciples increased in Urishlem greatly: and much people of the Jihudoyee were obedient to the faith.
B044C006V008	44	6	8	But Estephanos was filled with grace and power, and wrought signs and miracles among the people.
B044C006V009	44	6	9	And men arose from the congregation which was called Libertinu, Kyrainoyee, and Aleksandroyee, and from Cilicia, and from Asia, and disputed with Estephanos,
B044C006V010	44	6	10	and were not able to stand against the wisdom and the spirit which spake in him.
B044C006V011	44	6	11	Then they sent men and instructed them to say, We have heard him speak words of blasphemy against Musha and against Aloha.
B044C006V012	44	6	12	And they stirred up the people and the elders and the sophree, and came and rose upon him, and carried him away and brought him into the midst of the assembly.
B044C006V013	44	6	13	AND witnesses of falsehood arose, and said, This man ceases not from speaking words contrary to the law and against this holy place.
B044C006V014	44	6	14	For we have heard him say that this Jeshu Natsroya shall destroy this place, and shall change the customs which Musha delivered unto us.
B044C006V015	44	6	15	And all they who sat in the assembly looked upon him, and saw his face as the face of an angel.
B044C007V001	44	7	1	And the chief of the priests demanded if these (things) were so?
B044C007V002	44	7	2	But he said, Men, brethren, and fathers, hear! The God of glory appeared to our father Abraham while he was between the rivers, he had not yet come to dwell in Charan,
B044C007V003	44	7	3	and said to him, Go forth from thy country and from (being) with the sons of thy family, and come to the land that I will show thee.
B044C007V004	44	7	4	Then went forth Abraham from the land of the Kaldoyee, and came and dwelt in Charan: and from thence, his father being dead, Aloha caused him to pass into this land in which you dwell to-day.
B044C007V005	44	7	5	And (yet) he gave him no inheritance in it, nor a place of the feet, but he promised to give it to him for an heritage to himself and to his seed, while as yet he had not a son.
B044C007V006	44	7	6	And Aloha spake with him, telling him that his seed should be a sojourner in a strange land, and that they would enslave and ill-treat them four hundred years.
B044C007V007	44	7	7	And the nation whom they will serve (in) bondage will I judge, saith Aloha: and afterward they shall come forth and serve me in this place.
B044C007V008	44	7	8	And he gave to him the covenant of circumcision. And then begat he Ishok, and circumcised him on the eighth day, and Ishok begat Jakub, and Jakub begat our twelve fathers.
B044C007V009	44	7	9	And these our fathers were incited against Jauseph, and sold him into Mitsreen. And Aloha was with him:
B044C007V010	44	7	10	and he delivered him from all his afflictions, and gave him grace and wisdom before Pherun king of Mitsreen, and he appointed him prince over Mitsreen, and over all his house.
B044C007V011	44	7	11	AND there was a famine and great affliction in all Mitsreen, and in the land of Kenaan, and our fathers had nothing to satisfy them.
B044C007V012	44	7	12	And when Jakub heard that there was corn in Mitsreen, he sent forth our fathers before.
B044C007V013	44	7	13	And when they had gone the second time, Jauseph made himself known to his brethren, and the family of Jauseph were made known unto Pherun.
B044C007V014	44	7	14	And Jauseph sent and brought his father Jakub and all his family, and they were in number seventy and five souls.
B044C007V015	44	7	15	And Jakub went down into Mitsreen and died there; he and our fathers.
B044C007V016	44	7	16	And he was removed to Shechem, and laid in the sepulchre that Abraham bought with silver from the B'nai Chamur.
B044C007V017	44	7	17	And when was come the time of that which Aloha promised with an oath unto Abraham, the people had multiplied and increased in Mitsreen
B044C007V018	44	7	18	until another king had arisen over Mitsreen, who knew not Jauseph,
B044C007V019	44	7	19	and he dealt fraudulently against our kindred, and shamefully entreated our fathers, and commanded that their children should be cast away, that they might not live.
B044C007V020	44	7	20	In that time Musha was born, and was beloved of Aloha, and was brought up three months in the house of his father.
B044C007V021	44	7	21	And when he was outcast from his people, the daughter of Pherun found him, and brought him up unto her for a son.
B044C007V022	44	7	22	And Musha was instructed in all the wisdom of the Mitsroyee, and was excellent in words (and) also in deeds.
B044C007V023	44	7	23	And when he became a son of forty years, it arose upon his heart to visit his brethren the sons of Israel.
B044C007V024	44	7	24	And he saw one of the sons of his tribe treated with violence, and he avenged him, and did him justice, and he killed the Mitsroya who had offended him and
B044C007V025	44	7	25	hoped that his brethren, the sons of Israel, would understand that Aloha by his hand would give them deliverance; but they understood not.
B044C007V026	44	7	26	And the day after he appeared to them while they strove one with another: and he persuaded them to be pacified, saying, Men, you are brethren; why offend you one the other?
B044C007V027	44	7	27	But he who had offended his neighbour removed himself from him, and said to him, Who appointed thee over us a prince and a judge?
B044C007V028	44	7	28	Seekest thou to kill me as thou killedst the Mitsroya yesterday?
B044C007V029	44	7	29	And Musha fled at that word, and became a sojourner in the land of Median, and there were to him two sons.
B044C007V030	44	7	30	AND when forty years were there fulfilled to him, there appeared to him in the desert of Mount Sinai the angel of the Lord in a flame that burned in a bush.
B044C007V031	44	7	31	And while Musha looked, he wondered at the sight. And as he drew near to gaze, the Lord spake to him with the voice:
B044C007V032	44	7	32	I am the God of thy fathers, the God of Abraham and of Ishok and of Jakub. And Musha, trembling, dared not look upon the sight.
B044C007V033	44	7	33	And the Lord said to him, Loose thy sandals from thy feet: for the ground on which thou standest is holy.
B044C007V034	44	7	34	Seeing I have seen the affliction of my people who in Mitsreen, and his groaning I have heard, and I have descended that I may deliver them. And now come, I will send thee into Mitsreen.
B044C007V035	44	7	35	This Musha whom they denied, when they said, Who appointed thee over us a prince and a judge? this, sent Aloha unto them a prince and a deliverer by the hand of the angel who appeared to him at the bush.
B044C007V036	44	7	36	This brought them out, when he had wrought signs and wonders and mighty deeds in the land of Mitsreen, and at the Sea of Suph, and in the desert forty years.
B044C007V037	44	7	37	THIS is that Musha, who said to the sons of Israel, A Prophet will Aloha the Lord raise up unto you from your brethren, like me; him shall you hear.
B044C007V038	44	7	38	This is he who was with the congregation in the desert, with the angel himself who spake with him and with our fathers at the mountain of Sinai; and he it was who received the words of life to give (them) to us.
B044C007V039	44	7	39	And our fathers willed not to give heed to him, but left him, and in their hearts turned back to Mitsreen,
B044C007V040	44	7	40	saying to Aharun, Make us alohee that may go before us, because this Musha, who brought us forth from the land of Mitsreen, we know not what is become of him.
B044C007V041	44	7	41	And he made them the calf in those days, and they sacrificed sacrifices to idols, and were delighted with the work of their hands.
B044C007V042	44	7	42	And Aloha turned, and delivered them up to be worshippers of the hosts of heaven; as it is written in the book of the prophets, Forty years in the desert Victims or sacrifices did you offer to me, Sons of Israel?
B044C007V043	44	7	43	But you took up the tabernacle of Malkum, And the star of the god of Raphan, Images you have made to worship them; I will remove you beyond Babel.
B044C007V044	44	7	44	BEHOLD, the tabernacle of testimony of our fathers was in the desert, as He who spake with Musha had commanded to make it after the pattern which he had seen.
B044C007V045	44	7	45	And this tabernacle also our fathers bringing brought in with Jeshu to the land which Aloha had given to them, an inheritance from those peoples whom he had expelled from before them, and it was carried until the days of David;
B044C007V046	44	7	46	who found favour before Aloha, and asked to find a tabernacle for the God of Jakub.
B044C007V047	44	7	47	But Shelemun builded the house.
B044C007V048	44	7	48	But the Most High dwelleth not in the work of hands, as saith the prophet,
B044C007V049	44	7	49	Heaven is my throne, And earth the footstool beneath my feet: What house will you build me? saith the Lord: Or what is the place of my rest?
B044C007V050	44	7	50	Hath not my hand made all these?
B044C007V051	44	7	51	O, hardened of neck and uncircumcised in your hearts and in your hearing, you at all times against the Spirit of Holiness stand up; as your fathers, so you also.
B044C007V052	44	7	52	For which of the prophets have not your fathers persecuted and slain? they who before announced the coming of the Righteous; him whom you delivered up and slew.
B044C007V053	44	7	53	And you have received the law by the precept of angels. and have not kept it.
B044C007V054	44	7	54	AND when they heard these they were filled with wrath in themselves, and they gnashed their teeth upon him.
B044C007V055	44	7	55	And he, being full of faith and of the Spirit of Holiness, looked up to heaven, and saw the glory of Aloha, and Jeshu standing at the right hand of Aloha.
B044C007V056	44	7	56	And he said, Behold, I see the heavens opened, and the Son of man standing at the right hand of Aloha.
B044C007V057	44	7	57	And they cried with a high voice, and stopped their ears, and rushed upon him, all of them,
B044C007V058	44	7	58	and seizing they brought him out of the city and stoned him. And they who witnessed against him laid their garments before the feet of a certain young man named Shaol.
B044C007V059	44	7	59	And they stoned Estephanos, (he) praying and saying, Our Lord Jeshu, receive my spirit.
B044C007V060	44	7	60	And kneeling down, he cried with a high voice, and said, Our Lord, let not this sin arise against them. And when this he had said, he slept.
B044C008V001	44	8	1	But Shaol willed to take part in his killing. And there was made in those days a great persecution against the church that was in Urishlem; and they were all dispersed in the country of Jihud and also among the Shomroyee, excepting only the apostles.
B044C008V002	44	8	2	And faithful men laid Estephanos in his tomb, and mourned over him greatly.
B044C008V003	44	8	3	BUT Shaol persecuted the church of Aloha, going to the houses, and drawing men and women delivered them to the house of the bound.
B044C008V004	44	8	4	And they who were dispersed went about and preached the word of Aloha.
B044C008V005	44	8	5	But Philipos descended to a city of the Shomroyee, and preached concerning the Meshiha.
B044C008V006	44	8	6	And when they heard his word, the men who were there attended to him, and were persuaded of all that he said: for they saw the signs that he wrought.
B044C008V007	44	8	7	For many whom unclean spirits possessed cried with a high voice, and they came out from them; and others, palsied and lame, were healed:
B044C008V008	44	8	8	and great joy was in that city.
B044C008V009	44	8	9	But a certain man was there whose name was Simon, who had dwelt in that city much time, and with his sorceries had deceived the people of the Shomroyee, magnifying himself, and saying, I am the Great.
B044C008V010	44	8	10	And all inclined to him, great and small, and said, This is the great Power of Aloha.
B044C008V011	44	8	11	And they were persuaded by him, because that much time by his sorceries he had astonished them.
B044C008V012	44	8	12	But when they believed Philipos, who evangelized the kingdom of Aloha in the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, they were baptized, men and women.
B044C008V013	44	8	13	And Simon also himself believed, and was baptized, and adhered to Philipos. And when he saw the signs and great works which were done by his hands, he wondered and was astonished.
B044C008V014	44	8	14	AND when the apostles who were at Urishlem heard that the people of the Shomroyee had received the word of Aloha, they sent to them Kipha and Juhanon.
B044C008V015	44	8	15	And they went down and prayed for them, that they might receive the Spirit of Holiness:
B044C008V016	44	8	16	for he was not upon one of them yet; but they were only baptized in the name of our Lord Jeshu.
B044C008V017	44	8	17	Then they laid upon them the hand, and they received the Spirit of Holiness.
B044C008V018	44	8	18	And when Simon saw that by the hand-laying of the apostles the Spirit of Holiness was given, he offered to them silver,
B044C008V019	44	8	19	saying, Give also to me this power, that he on whom I shall lay the hand may receive the Spirit of Holiness.
B044C008V020	44	8	20	Shemun Kipha said to him, Thy silver go with thee into perdition, because thou thoughtest that the gift of Aloha with the possessions of the world might he obtained.
B044C008V021	44	8	21	Thou hast neither part nor lot in this faith, because thine heart hath not been right before Aloha.
B044C008V022	44	8	22	Nevertheless, repent of this thy wickedness, and pray of Aloha, that the guile of thy heart may haply be forgiven thee;
B044C008V023	44	8	23	for in bitter gall and in the bonds of iniquity I see that thou art.
B044C008V024	44	8	24	Simon answered and said, Pray you on my behalf, of Aloha, that not any of these things which you have spoken may come upon me.
B044C008V025	44	8	25	But Shemun and Juhanon, when they had testified and taught the word of Aloha, returned to Urishlem, and evangelized in many villages of the Shomroyee.
B044C008V026	44	8	26	AND the angel of the Lord spake with Philipos, and said to him, Arise, go to the south, in the desert way which goeth down from Urishlem to Gaza.
B044C008V027	44	8	27	And arising he went. And there met him a certain eunuch who had come from Cush, an officer of Kandak, queen of the Cushoyee; and he was officer over all her treasure. And he had been to worship at Urishlem;
B044C008V028	44	8	28	and while returning that he might go, he sat in the chariot and read in Eshaia the prophet.
B044C008V029	44	8	29	And the Spirit of Holiness said to Philipos, Approach, and join the chariot.
B044C008V030	44	8	30	And being near, he heard that he read in Eshaia the prophet; and he said to him, Understandest thou what thou readest?
B044C008V031	44	8	31	And he said, How can I understand, unless one teach me? And he prayed of him, of Philipos, to ascend and sit with him.
B044C008V032	44	8	32	But the section (phosuka) of the scripture in which he was reading is this: As a lamb to the slaughter was he led; And as a sheep before the shearer is silent, So opened not he his mouth in his humiliation.
B044C008V033	44	8	33	From oppression and from judgment was he led; And his age who shall recount? For his life is taken from the earth.
B044C008V034	44	8	34	That eunuch said Unto Philipos, I pray thee, of whom speaketh this the prophet? of himself, or of another man?
B044C008V035	44	8	35	Then Philipos opened his mouth and began, from that very scripture, preaching to him concerning our Lord Jeshu.
B044C008V036	44	8	36	And as they went in the way they came to a certain place which had water in it, and that eunuch said, Behold the water; what is the hinderance that I should be baptized?
B044C008V038	44	8	38	And he commanded that the chariot should stand; and they descended both of them to the water, and Philipos baptized that eunuch.
B044C008V039	44	8	39	And when they had ascended from the water, the Spirit of the Lord rapt away Philipos, and the eunuch again saw him not; but he went on his way rejoicing.
B044C008V040	44	8	40	But Philipos was found at Azotos, and from thence he itinerated and evangelized in all the cities until he came to Cesarea.
B044C009V001	44	9	1	BUT Shaol was yet full of threatenings and murderous wrath against the disciples of our Lord.
B044C009V002	44	9	2	And he demanded letters from the chief priests which he should give at Darmsuk to the synagogues, that if he found (any) who walked in this way, men or women, he might bind and bring them to Urishlem.
B044C009V003	44	9	3	And as he went and began to come nigh to Darmsuk, suddenly there shone forth upon him a light from heaven;
B044C009V004	44	9	4	and he fell upon the earth, and heard a voice which said to him, Shaol, Shaol, why persecutest thou me? It is hard to thee to kick against the pricks.
B044C009V005	44	9	5	He answered and said, Who art thou, my Lord? And our Lord said, I am Jeshu Natsroya, whom thou persecutest;
B044C009V006	44	9	6	but arise, go into Darmsuk, and there it will be spoken with thee concerning what thou must do.
B044C009V007	44	9	7	And the men who went with him in the way stood astonished, because the voice alone they heard, but a man was not seen by them.
B044C009V008	44	9	8	And Shaol arose from the earth, and could not see any thing when his eyes were opened. And they took him by his hand and brought him into Darmsuk;
B044C009V009	44	9	9	and he saw not for three days, neither did he eat or drink.
B044C009V010	44	9	10	But there was in Darmsuk a certain disciple whose name was Hanania. And the Lord said to him in a vision, Hanania. And he said, Behold me, my Lord.
B044C009V011	44	9	11	And our Lord said to him, Arise, go to the street which is called the Straight, and inquire in the house of Jihuda for Shaol, who is from Tarsos the city. For, behold, while praying,
B044C009V012	44	9	12	he hath seen in a vision a man whose name is Hanania, who entered and laid upon him the hand that his eyes might be opened.
B044C009V013	44	9	13	And Hanania said, My Lord, I have heard from many concerning this man, of how much evil he hath brought upon thy saints in Urishlem.
B044C009V014	44	9	14	And behold, here also he hath authority from the chief priests to bind all those who invoke thy name.
B044C009V015	44	9	15	And the Lord said to him, Arise, go; for a vessel is he to me, chosen to bear my name to the nations, and to kings, and to the house of the sons of Israel.
B044C009V016	44	9	16	For I will show him what he is to suffer on account of my name.
B044C009V017	44	9	17	Then Hanania went to the house unto him, and he laid upon him the hand, and said to him, Shaol, my brother, our Lord Jeshu hath sent me; He who appeared to thee in the way while thou wast coming, that thine eyes may be opened, and thou mayest be filled with the Spirit of Holiness.
B044C009V018	44	9	18	And instantly there fell from his eyes something which was like to scales; and his eyes were opened, and, arising, he was baptized.
B044C009V019	44	9	19	And he took food and was strengthened,
B044C009V020	44	9	20	and was (certain) days with those disciples who were in Darmsuk. And at once he preached in the synagogues of the Jihudoyee concerning Jeshu, that he is the Son of Aloha.
B044C009V021	44	9	21	And all they who heard him wondered, and they said, Is not this he who persecuted all those who call upon this name in Urishlem? And behold, also, hither upon the self-same (object) was he sent to bind and take them to the chief priests.
B044C009V022	44	9	22	BUT Shaol was the more strengthened, and moved those Jihudoyee who dwelt at Darmsuk, while he showed that this is the Meshiha.
B044C009V023	44	9	23	And when days were many to him there, the Jihudoyee wrought treachery against him to kill him.
B044C009V024	44	9	24	But their treachery was showed to Shaol, which they sought to do to him; and that they kept the gates of the city day and night to kill him.
B044C009V025	44	9	25	Then the disciples set him in a pannier, and dismissed him from the wall by night.
B044C009V026	44	9	26	And he went to Urishlem, and willed to be attached to the disciples. And all of them were afraid of him, and believed not that he was a disciple.
B044C009V027	44	9	27	But Bar Naba took him and brought him to the apostles, and recounted to them how in the way he had seen the Lord, and what he had spoken with him; and how in Darmsuk with boldness he had spoken in the name of Jeshu.
B044C009V028	44	9	28	And he went in with them and went out in Urishlem. And he spake in the name of Jeshu with boldness,
B044C009V029	44	9	29	and disputed with those Jihudoyee who knew Greek; but they were wishful to kill him.
B044C009V030	44	9	30	And when the brethren knew, they brought him by night to Cesarea, and from thence sent him to Tarsos.
B044C009V031	44	9	31	Nevertheless, in the church which was in Jihud, and in Galila, and Shomreen, there was peace, while (it) was edified; and going forward in the fear of Aloha, and in the consolation of the Spirit of Holiness, was multiplied.
B044C009V032	44	9	32	And it was that while Shemun itinerated among the cities, he went down also to the saints who dwelt in Lud the city.
B044C009V033	44	9	33	And he found a certain man whose name was Ania, who had lain upon a bed paralyzed eight years.
B044C009V034	44	9	34	And Shemun said to him, Ania, Jeshu Meshiha healeth thee; arise, and make thy bed. And instantly he arose.
B044C009V035	44	9	35	And all who dwelt in Lud and in Sarona saw him, and turned to Aloha.
B044C009V036	44	9	36	BUT there was a certain disciple in Joppa the city, whose name was Tabitha. This was rich in good works and in alms which she had done.
B044C009V037	44	9	37	But she became afflicted in those days, and died. And they washed her and laid her in an upper room.
B044C009V038	44	9	38	And the disciples heard that Shemun was in Lud the city, because it is over against Joppa, and they sent to him two men, who should pray of him not to delay to come among them.
B044C009V039	44	9	39	And Shemun arose and went with them. And when he was come, they brought him up to the upper room, and assembled (and) stood around him all the widows, weeping, and showing him those vestments and mantles which Tabitha had given them, while living.
B044C009V040	44	9	40	But Shemun put forth all the men without, and fell upon his knees and prayed; and he turned towards the corpse and said Tabitha, arise. And she opened her eyes;
B044C009V041	44	9	41	and when she beheld Shemun, she sat. And he reached his hand and raised her, and called the saints and widows, and gave her to them living.
B044C009V042	44	9	42	And this was known to all the city, and many believed in our Lord.
B044C009V043	44	9	43	And he was in Joppa days not a few, sojourning in the house of Shemun the tanner.
B044C010V001	44	10	1	BUT in Cesarea was a certain man, a centurion, whose name was Cornelius, of the cohort which was called the Italic.
B044C010V002	44	10	2	And he was just, and feared Aloha, he and all his house: he did much alms among the people, and in all time prayed of Aloha.
B044C010V003	44	10	3	This saw an angel of Aloha in a vision manifestly about the ninth hour of the day, who came in to him, and said to him, Cornelius!
B044C010V004	44	10	4	And he beheld him, and feared, and said, What, my Lord? And the angel said to him, Thy prayers and thy alms have ascended for a memorial before Aloha.
B044C010V005	44	10	5	And now send men to Joppa the city, and bring Shemun who is called Kipha:
B044C010V006	44	10	6	behold, he sojourneth in the house of Shemun the tanner, which is hard by the sea.
B044C010V007	44	10	7	And when the angel who had spoken with him had gone, he called two from the sons of his house, and a certain soldier who feared Aloha (and) who was obedient to him;
B044C010V008	44	10	8	and he made known to them every thing he had seen, and sent them to Joppa.
B044C010V009	44	10	9	AND the day after while they went on the way, and drew nigh to the city, Shemun ascended to the roof to pray, at the sixth hour.
B044C010V010	44	10	10	And he hungered, and desired to eat: and while they were preparing for him, there fell upon him an entrancement,
B044C010V011	44	10	11	and he saw the heavens opened, and a certain vessel bound at the four corners, and like to a great sheet, and it was let down from heaven upon the earth:
B044C010V012	44	10	12	and in it were all animals of four feet, and reptiles of the earth, and fowls of the heaven.
B044C010V013	44	10	13	And a voice came to him, which said, Shemun, arise, slay, and eat.
B044C010V014	44	10	14	And Shemun said, Not so, my Lord: for never have I eaten any thing that is profane and unclean.
B044C010V015	44	10	15	And again the second time was to him, Those (things) which Aloha cleanseth make not thou profane.
B044C010V016	44	10	16	This was three times done: and the vessel was elevated to heaven.
B044C010V017	44	10	17	And while Shemun wondered in himself for what (was) the vision he had seen, those men came who had been sent by Cornelius, and inquired for the house where Shemun sojourned, and they came and stood at the gate of the court.
B044C010V018	44	10	18	And they called there, and inquired, whether Shemun who was called Kipha there sojourned.
B044C010V019	44	10	19	And while Shemun thought on the vision, the Spirit said to him, Behold, three men seek thee:
B044C010V020	44	10	20	arise, descend and go with them, not being divided in thy mind: for I have sent them.
B044C010V021	44	10	21	Then Shemun descended to those men, and said to them, I am he whom you seek: what is the occasion on which you have come?
B044C010V022	44	10	22	They said to him, A certain man whose name is Cornelius, a centurion, who feareth Aloha, and of whom all the people of the Jihudoyee give witness, hath been told in a vision by an holy angel to send and bring thee to his house, and to hear words from thee.
B044C010V023	44	10	23	And Shemun brought them in, and received them while they tarried; and he arose the day after, and went forth, and proceeded with them; and certain of the brethren of Joppa went with them.
B044C010V024	44	10	24	And the next day they entered Cesarea: but Cornelius was waiting for them, while all the sons of his family, and the friends and beloved ones whom he had, were assembled with him.
B044C010V025	44	10	25	AND when Shemun entered Cornelius met him, and fell and worshipped at his feet.
B044C010V026	44	10	26	And Shemun raised him, and said to him, Arise, I also am a man.
B044C010V027	44	10	27	And while speaking with him he entered, and found many who had come thither.
B044C010V028	44	10	28	And he said to them, You know that it is not lawful for a man a Jihudoya to attach to a foreign man who is not a son of his tribe. But me hath Aloha showed that I should not declare any man unclean or profane.
B044C010V029	44	10	29	Wherefore I the more diligently came when you sent for me. But I ask you, on what account you have sent for me?
B044C010V030	44	10	30	And Cornelius said to him, Four days are unto this from when, behold, I am fasting; and at nine hours, while praying in my house, a certain man stood before me clothed in white.
B044C010V031	44	10	31	And he said to me, Cornelius, thy prayer is heard, and thy alms have made memorial before Aloha.
B044C010V032	44	10	32	But send to Joppa the city, and bring Shemun who is called Kipha; behold, he abideth in the house of Shemun a tanner, which is by the sea;
B044C010V033	44	10	33	and he will come and speak with thee. And immediately I sent to thee, and thou hast well done to have come. And, behold, we are all before thee, and desire to hear every thing that hath been commanded thee by Aloha.
B044C010V034	44	10	34	BUT Shemun opened his mouth, and said, In truth I comprehend that Aloha is no respecter of persons:
B044C010V035	44	10	35	but in all nations whoever feareth him and worketh righteousness is accepted of him.
B044C010V036	44	10	36	For (this is) the word which he hath sent to the sons of Israel, and hath announced to them peace and repose through Jeshu Meshiha,-this is the Lord of all.
B044C010V037	44	10	37	And you also know by the word which hath been in all Jihud (which began) from Galila after the baptism which Juhanon preached,
B044C010V038	44	10	38	concerning Jeshu who was of Natsrath, whom Aloha anointed with the Spirit of Holiness and with power: he who went about and healed those who were worn out with evil, because Aloha was with him.
B044C010V039	44	10	39	And we are his witnesses of all which he did in the land of Jihud and of Urishlem. This (one) himself did the Jihudoyee hang upon the tree and kill;
B044C010V040	44	10	40	and him did Aloha raise up on the third day, and gave him to be seen openly;
B044C010V041	44	10	41	yet not to all the people, but to us who by Aloha were chosen to be unto him the witnesses, who ate with him and drank after his resurrection from among the dead.
B044C010V042	44	10	42	And he commanded us to preach and to testify to the people that this is he who hath been separated by Aloha (to be) the Judge of the living and of the dead.
B044C010V043	44	10	43	And of him all the prophets testify, that whoever believeth in his name shall receive remission of sins.
B044C010V044	44	10	44	And while Shemun spake these words the Spirit of Holiness overspread all who heard the word.
B044C010V045	44	10	45	And the circumcised brethren who had come with him were astonished and amazed, because upon the Gentiles also the gift of the Spirit of Holiness was poured out.
B044C010V046	44	10	46	For they heard them speaking with tongues; and they magnified Aloha. And Shemun said,
B044C010V047	44	10	47	Can any one forbid waters that they should not be baptized, they who, behold, have received the Spirit of Holiness as well as we?
B044C010V048	44	10	48	Then he commanded them to be baptized in the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha. And they prayed of him to remain with them (certain) days.
B044C011V001	44	11	1	And the apostles and brethren who were in Jihud heard that the Gentiles also had received the word of Aloha.
B044C011V002	44	11	2	AND when Shemun had gone up to Urishlem, they who were of the circumcision contended with him,
B044C011V003	44	11	3	saying, that unto men uncircumcised he had entered, and had eaten with them.
B044C011V004	44	11	4	And Shemun put forth in order to say to them,
B044C011V005	44	11	5	That while praying in Joppa I saw a vision; a certain vessel descended which was like to a sheet, and bound at the four corners: and it came down from heaven and came unto me.
B044C011V006	44	11	6	And gazing at it I beheld in it animals of four feet, and reptiles of the earth, and fowls of the heaven.
B044C011V007	44	11	7	And I heard a voice which said to me, Shemun, arise, slay, and eat.
B044C011V008	44	11	8	And I said, Not so, my Lord; for nothing hath entered my mouth that is unclean or profane.
B044C011V009	44	11	9	And again the voice said to me from heaven, What Aloha hath cleansed make not thou to be polluted.
B044C011V010	44	11	10	This was done three times, and every thing was taken up into heaven.
B044C011V011	44	11	11	And at that moment three men, who had been sent to me by Cornelius from Cesarea, came and stood at the gate of the court where I was sojourning.
B044C011V012	44	11	12	And the Spirit said to me, Go with them without doubting. And there went also with me these six brethren, and we entered into the man's house.
B044C011V013	44	11	13	And he related to us how he had seen in his house an angel, who stood and said to him, Send to the city Joppa, and bring Shemun who is called Kipha,
B044C011V014	44	11	14	and he will speak with thee words by which thou wilt be saved, thou and all thy house.
B044C011V015	44	11	15	And when I proceeded to speak there, the Spirit of Holiness overshadowed them, as upon us from the beginning.
B044C011V016	44	11	16	And I remembered the word of our Lord, who said, Juhanon baptized you with waters, but you shall be baptized with the Spirit of Holiness.
B044C011V017	44	11	17	If then Aloha equally hath given the gift to the Gentiles who have believed in our Lord Jeshu Meshiha as we, who was I, that I should be sufficient to prohibit Aloha?
B044C011V018	44	11	18	And when these words they had heard they were silent, and they praised Aloha, and said, Now also unto the Gentiles Aloha hath given repentance unto life.
B044C011V019	44	11	19	BUT they who had been dispersed by the tribulation that was concerning Estephanos went unto Punika, also to the region of Kypros and to Antiokia, but with any one not speaking the word unless only with the Jihudoyee.
B044C011V020	44	11	20	But of them were men of Kypros and of Kyrine; these entered into Antiokia, and discoursed with the Javnoyee, and evangelized concerning our Lord Jeshu.
B044C011V021	44	11	21	And the hand of the Lord was with them, and many believed, and were converted unto the Lord.
B044C011V022	44	11	22	And this was heard by the ears of the sons of the church which was at Urishlem, and they sent Bar Naba to Antiokia.
B044C011V023	44	11	23	And when he came thither, and beheld the grace of Aloha, he rejoiced, and entreated them with all their heart to cleave to our Lord.
B044C011V024	44	11	24	For he was a good man, and full of the Spirit of Holiness and of faith, and there was added much people to our Lord.
B044C011V025	44	11	25	And he went forth to Tarsos to seek for Shaol;
B044C011V026	44	11	26	and when he had found him he brought him with him to Antiokia. And a whole year together they assembled in the church, and taught much people: from thence first in Antiokia the disciples were called Christianee.
B044C011V027	44	11	27	And in those days there came from Urishlem thither prophets.
B044C011V028	44	11	28	And one of them arose whose name was Agabos: and he made known to them by the Spirit that a great famine would be in all the land. And that famine was in the days of Claudios Caesar.
B044C011V029	44	11	29	Therefore the disciples, according as each of them had, determined to send for the service of those brethren who dwelt in Jihud;
B044C011V030	44	11	30	and they sent by the hand of Bar Naba and Shaol to the presbyters who were there.
B044C012V001	44	12	1	BUT at that time Herodes the king, he who was surnamed Agripos, stretched forth hands upon some who were in the church, to ill-treat them.
B044C012V002	44	12	2	And he killed with the sword Jakub the brother of Juhanon.
B044C012V003	44	12	3	And when he saw that this pleased the Jihudoyee, he added to apprehend also Shemun Kipha. And they were the days of the Phatiree.
B044C012V004	44	12	4	And he apprehended him and cast him into the house of the bound, and delivered him to sixteen soldiers to keep him, that after the Petscha he might deliver him to the people of the Jihudoyee.
B044C012V005	44	12	5	And while Shemun was kept in the house of the bound, constant prayer was offered by the church on his behalf unto Aloha.
B044C012V006	44	12	6	And in that night of the coming morning when he should be delivered up, while Shemun slept between two soldiers, and bound with two chains, and the others were watching the gates of the house of the bound,
B044C012V007	44	12	7	the angel of the Lord stood over him, and light shined in all the house.
B044C012V008	44	12	8	And he smote him on his side, and said to him, Arise quickly. And the chains fell from his hands. And the angel said to him, bind thy loins, and put on thy sandals. And he did so. And again he said to him, Wrap thy mantle, and come after me.
B044C012V009	44	12	9	And he went forth, and came after him; not knowing that what was done by the hand of the angel was reality, for he thought that he saw a vision.
B044C012V010	44	12	10	And when he had passed the first and second guard, they came to the gate of iron, and it was opened to them of its own accord. And when they went forth and had passed one street, the angel departed from him.
B044C012V011	44	12	11	Then acknowledged Shemun, and said, Now know I in truth that the Lord hath sent his angel, and hath delivered me from the hand of Herodes the king, and from that which the Jihudoyee had calculated against me.
B044C012V012	44	12	12	And when he had understood, he came to the house of Mariam the mother of Juhanon, he who is surnamed Markos; because many brethren were assembled there and praying.
B044C012V013	44	12	13	And he knocked at the gate of the court, and there came forth to answer him a damsel whose name was Roda.
B044C012V014	44	12	14	And she knew the voice of Shemun; and for joy she opened not the gate, but returned with running, and said to them, Shemun, behold, stands at the gate of the court.
B044C012V015	44	12	15	And they said to her, Thou art altogether moved. And she contended that it was so. And they said, It may be that it is his angel.
B044C012V016	44	12	16	And Shemun knocked at the gate; and they went forth, and seeing him they were astonished.
B044C012V017	44	12	17	And he beckoned to them with his hand to be silent; and entered, and showed them how the Lord had brought him out from the house of the bound. And he said to them, Show these to Jakub and to the brethren; and he departed and went to another place.
B044C012V018	44	12	18	And when it was morning there was made a great tumult among the soldiers concerning Shemun, what was become of him?
B044C012V019	44	12	19	But Herodes when he inquired and found him not, condemned the guards, and commanded that they should die. And he went forth from Jihud and came to Cesarea.
B044C012V020	44	12	20	And because he was angry with the Tsuroyee and with the Tsaidonoyee, they gathered together and came to him by persuasion of Blestos the chamberlain of the king, and prayed of him that peace should be to them, because the sustenance of their country was from the kingdom of Herodes.
B044C012V021	44	12	21	But upon a public day Herodes was clothed with the robe of royalty, and sat upon the tribunal, and he discoursed to an assembly.
B044C012V022	44	12	22	But all the people exclaimed, and said, These are the words of a god, and not of a man.
B044C012V023	44	12	23	And on this account, because he gave not the glory to Aloha, in that hour the angel of the Lord smote him, and he was corroded with worms, and died.
B044C012V024	44	12	24	And the gospel of Aloha was proclaimed, and was great.
B044C012V025	44	12	25	BUT Bar Naba and Shaol returned from Urishlem to Antiokia after they had accomplished their ministry; and they took with them Juhanon who was called Markos.
B044C013V001	44	13	1	But there were in the church of Antiokia prophets and teachers, Bar Naba and Shemun who was called Niger, and Lukios who was from the city of Kyrene, and Manael, a fosterbrother of Herodes Tetrarka, and Shaol.
B044C013V002	44	13	2	And as they fasted and supplicated Aloha, the Spirit of Holiness said to them, Separate to me Shaol and Bar Naba for the work to which I have called them.
B044C013V003	44	13	3	And after they had fasted and prayed, they laid upon them the hand, and dismissed them.
B044C013V004	44	13	4	And they, being sent by the Spirit of Holiness, went down to Selukia, and from thence proceeded by sea to Cyprus.
B044C013V005	44	13	5	And when they had entered the city Salamina, they preached the word of our Lord in the congregations of the Jihudoyee, and Juhanon ministered to them.
B044C013V006	44	13	6	And when they had itinerated through the whole island unto the city Paphos, they found a man, a certain sorcerer, a Jihudoya, who was a false prophet, whose name was Bar Shuma.
B044C013V007	44	13	7	This adhered to a wise man who was proconsul, and was called Sergius Paulos. And the proconsul called Shaol and Bar Naba and requested to hear from them the word of Aloha.
B044C013V008	44	13	8	But this sorcerer, Bar Shuma, whose name interpreted is Elymos, stood against them, because he desired to avert the proconsul from faith.
B044C013V009	44	13	9	But Shaol, he who is called PAULOS, was filled with the Spirit of Holiness, and beheld him,
B044C013V010	44	13	10	and said, O full of all deceits and all wickednesses, thou son of the devil, and adversary of all righteousness, ceasest thou not to pervert the right ways of the Lord?
B044C013V011	44	13	11	And now the hand of the Lord is upon thee, and thou shalt be blind, and not see the sun until the time. And in the hour there fell upon him obscurity and darkness, and he went about asking some one to hold him by the hand.
B044C013V012	44	13	12	But when the proconsul saw what had been done, he wondered, and believed in the doctrine of the Lord.
B044C013V013	44	13	13	BUT Paulos and Bar Naba went on by sea from the City Paphos, and came to Perga, a city of Pamphylia; and Juhanon separated from them, and went to Urishlem.
B044C013V014	44	13	14	But they went forth from Perga, and came to Antiokia, the city of Pisidia. And they entered the synagogue, and sat on the day of shabath.
B044C013V015	44	13	15	And after the law and the prophets had been read, the presbyters of the synagogue sent to them, and said, Men, brethren, have you a word of exhortation to say to the people?
B044C013V016	44	13	16	And Paulos arose, and signed with his hand, and said to them:
B044C013V017	44	13	17	Men, sons of Israel, and those who fear Aloha, hearken! The God of this people elected our fathers, and exalted and magnified them, when they were sojourners in the land of Metsreen, and with uplifted arm brought them out therefrom
B044C013V018	44	13	18	And he nourished them in the desert forty years.
B044C013V019	44	13	19	And he destroyed seven nations in the land of Canaan, and gave them their land an inheritance. And four hundred and fifty years
B044C013V020	44	13	20	he gave them judges, until Shamuel the prophet;
B044C013V021	44	13	21	and then prayed they for themselves a king; and Aloha gave to them Shaol-bar-Kish, a man of the tribe of Benjamin, forty years.
B044C013V022	44	13	22	And he took him, and raised unto them David the king, and testified of him, and said, I have found David, the son of Jeshai, a man according to my heart; he will perform all my will.
B044C013V023	44	13	23	From the seed of this (man) the God of Israel, as he had promised, raised up Jeshu the Redeemer.
B044C013V024	44	13	24	And he sent Juhanon to proclaim before his coming the baptism of repentance to the whole people of Israel.
B044C013V025	44	13	25	And while Juhanon accomplished his ministry, he said, Whom think you that I am? I am not (he), but, behold, he cometh after me, he, the latchet of whose sandals I am not worthy to unloose.
B044C013V026	44	13	26	MEN, brethren, sons of the race of Abraham, and they among you who fear Aloha, unto you is sent the word of life.
B044C013V027	44	13	27	For they, the inhabitants of Urishlem and their princes, have not consented thereto, nor also to the writings of the prophets which are read on every shabath; but condemned him, and accomplished all that was written.
B044C013V028	44	13	28	And while they found not any cause of death, they requested Pilatos that they might kill him.
B044C013V029	44	13	29	And when they had fulfilled every thing that was written concerning him, they took him from the cross, and laid him in a sepulchre.
B044C013V030	44	13	30	But Aloha raised him from among the dead.
B044C013V031	44	13	31	And he was seen days many by those who had come up with him from Galila to Urishlem, and they are now his witnesses unto the people.
B044C013V032	44	13	32	And we also, behold, we preach to you that that promise which was made to our fathers,
B044C013V033	44	13	33	behold, Aloha hath fulfilled it to their children, (in) that he hath raised up Jeshu; as it is written in the second psalm, Thou art my Son; This day have I begotten thee.
B044C013V034	44	13	34	And thus did Aloha raise him from among the dead, that again he should not return thither to see corruption; as he had said, I will give you the sure grace of David.
B044C013V035	44	13	35	And again he hath said in another place, Thou hast not given thy Saint to see corruption.
B044C013V036	44	13	36	For David in his generation served the will of Aloha, and slept, and was added to his fathers, and saw corruption.
B044C013V037	44	13	37	But This whom Aloha raised saw no corruption.
B044C013V038	44	13	38	Know then, brethren, that through This himself is preached to you the remission of sins;
B044C013V039	44	13	39	and from all (from) which we could not by the law of Musha be justified, through This all who believe are justified.
B044C013V040	44	13	40	Beware, then, lest there come upon you that which is written in the prophets:
B044C013V041	44	13	41	Behold, despisers, and wonder, and perish: For a work I work in your days Which you will not believe if one should declare it to you.
B044C013V042	44	13	42	And when they had gone out from among them, they besought of them that the next shabath they would speak to them these words.
B044C013V043	44	13	43	And when the congregation was dissolved, many Jihudoyee went after them; and also the proselytes who worshipped Aloha. And they discoursed (with) and persuaded them to cleave to the grace of Aloha.
B044C013V044	44	13	44	AND on the next shabath the whole city gathered to hear the word of Aloha.
B044C013V045	44	13	45	And when the Jihudoyee saw the great assemblage, they were filled with envy, and arose against the words which Paulos spake, and blasphemed.
B044C013V046	44	13	46	But Paulos and Bar Naba said to them openly, To you it behoved first to speak the word of Aloha; but because you repel it from you, and determine against yourselves that you are not worthy of eternal life, behold, we turn to the Gentiles.
B044C013V047	44	13	47	For so hath our Lord commanded, as it is written, I have set thee a light to the Gentiles, To be for salvation to the ends of the earth.
B044C013V048	44	13	48	And when the Gentiles heard, they rejoiced and glorified Aloha; and they believed who were disposed unto eternal life.
B044C013V049	44	13	49	And the word of Aloha was spoken in all that region.
B044C013V050	44	13	50	But the Jihudoyee excited the principal men of the city and rich women, who with them feared Aloha, and raised a persecution against Paulos and against Bar Naba, and cast them out from their bounds.
B044C013V051	44	13	51	And as they went forth, they shook off against them the dust of their feet; and they came to Ikanon, a city.
B044C013V052	44	13	52	And the disciples were filled with joy and with the Spirit of Holiness.
B044C014V001	44	14	1	And they came and entered into the synagogue of the Jihudoyee, and so spake with them as that many believed of Jihudoyee and of Javanoyee.
B044C014V002	44	14	2	But Jihudoyee, of those who were not persuaded, excited the Gentiles to ill-treat the brethren.
B044C014V003	44	14	3	But they much time were there, and openly discoursed concerning the Lord; and He testified of the word of his grace by the signs and the wonders which he wrought by their hands.
B044C014V004	44	14	4	And all the society of the city was divided: of them some were with the Jihudoyee, and of them (some) adhered to the apostles.
B044C014V005	44	14	5	But there was made a movement by the Gentiles and by the Jihudoyee and their chiefs to maltreat them, and to crush them with stones.
B044C014V006	44	14	6	And when they knew, they passed away, and escaped to the cities of Lykania, Lystra, and Derbe, and the villages which surround them,
B044C014V007	44	14	7	and there evangelized.
B044C014V008	44	14	8	AND a certain man dwelt in the city of Lystra who was afflicted in his feet, lame from the womb of his mother, (and) who had never walked.
B044C014V009	44	14	9	This heard Paulos discourse. And when Paulos saw him, and knew that there was faith in him to be saved,
B044C014V010	44	14	10	he said to him with a high voice, To thee I say, in the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, Stand upon thy feet.
B044C014V011	44	14	11	And leaping, he stood and walked. And the assembly of the people, when they saw what Paulos had done, lifted up their voice in the language of the country, and said, Gods in the likeness of men have come down unto us.
B044C014V012	44	14	12	And they named Bar Naba, lord of the gods; and Paulos, Hermis, because he was foremost in discourse.
B044C014V013	44	14	13	And the priest of the lord of the gods, who was without the city, brought oxen and garlands to the gates of the court of the place where they dwelt, and willed to sacrifice to them.
B044C014V014	44	14	14	But Bar Naba and Paulos, when they heard, rent their garments, and sprang up, and came out to the crowd. And they cried,
B044C014V015	44	14	15	and said, Men, what do you? We also are children of men liable to sufferings like you, (and) who preach to you that from these vanities you should turn unto Aloha the living, who made heaven and earth, and the seas, and all that is in them:
B044C014V016	44	14	16	who in former generations left all nations to walk in ways of their own;
B044C014V017	44	14	17	yet leaving not himself without witness, while he did them good from heaven, and sent down rain, and multiplied the fruits in their times, and filled with food and gladness their hearts.
B044C014V018	44	14	18	And when these they had said, they scarcely restrained the people that some one should not sacrifice to them.
B044C014V019	44	14	19	But there came thither Jihudoyee from Ikanon and from Antiokia, and stirred up against them the people; and they stoned Paulos, and dragged him out of the city, because they thought that he was dead.
B044C014V020	44	14	20	And the disciples gathered to him, and, arising, he entered the city. AND the day after he went forth from thence with Bar Naba, and came to Derbe the city.
B044C014V021	44	14	21	And when they had preached to the sons of the city, they discipled many. And they returned and came to Lystra the city, and to Ikanon, and to Antiokia,
B044C014V022	44	14	22	confirming the souls of the disciples, and exhorting them to persevere in the faith. And they said to them, that through much tribulation it behoveth to enter the kingdom of Aloha.
B044C014V023	44	14	23	And they constituted for them in all the churches presbyters, having fasted with them and prayed, and commended them to our Lord in whom they had believed.
B044C014V024	44	14	24	And when they had gone through the country of Pisidia, they came to Pamphylia,
B044C014V025	44	14	25	and when they had preached in the city Perga the word of the Lord, they went down to Atalia,
B044C014V026	44	14	26	and from thence voyaged by sea and came to Antiokia, because from thence they had been commended to the grace of the Lord for the work which they had accomplished.
B044C014V027	44	14	27	And when all the church had convened, they recounted every thing which Aloha had done with them, and that he had opened the door of the faith unto the Gentiles.
B044C014V028	44	14	28	And much time were they there with the disciples.
B044C015V001	44	15	1	But men from Jihud came down and taught the brethren, If you be not circumcised after the custom of the law, you cannot be saved.
B044C015V002	44	15	2	And there were great agitation and disputation for Paulos and Bar Naba with them; and it was that Paulos and Bar Naba, and others with them, went up to the apostles and presbyters who were in Urishlem on account of this question.
B044C015V003	44	15	3	And conducting, the church dismissed them; and they went through all Punika, and also among the Shomroyee, declaring the conversion of the Gentiles; and they caused great joy unto all the brethren.
B044C015V004	44	15	4	AND when they came to Urishlem, they were received by the church, and by the apostles, and by the presbyters. And they recounted to them how much Aloha had done with them;
B044C015V005	44	15	5	but (that) certain had arisen who had believed from the doctrine of the Pharishee, and said, It behoved you to circumcise them, and require them to keep the law of Musha.
B044C015V006	44	15	6	But the apostles and presbyters assembled to consider this doctrine.
B044C015V007	44	15	7	And when there had been much investigation, Shemun arose, and said to them, Men, brethren, you know that from the first days from my mouth did Aloha choose that the Gentiles should hear the word of the gospel and believe.
B044C015V008	44	15	8	And Aloha, who knoweth what is in the hearts, testified of them, and gave them the Spirit of Holiness, as to us.
B044C015V009	44	15	9	And nothing distinguished between us and them, because he had purified by faith their hearts.
B044C015V010	44	15	10	And now why tempt you Aloha, that you would lay a yoke upon the necks of the disciples, which nor our fathers nor we could bear?
B044C015V011	44	15	11	But by the grace of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, we believe that we shall be saved, as they.
B044C015V012	44	15	12	And all the assembly were silent. And they listened to Paulos and Bar Naba, who related how Aloha had done by their hands signs and mighty works among the Gentiles.
B044C015V013	44	15	13	AND after they were silent, Jakub arose, and said, Men, brethren, hear me:
B044C015V014	44	15	14	Shemun hath related to you how Aloha hath begun to elect from the Gentiles a people to his name.
B044C015V015	44	15	15	And with this accord the words of the prophets; as when it is written,
B044C015V016	44	15	16	After these I will return, And raise the dwelling of David which hath fallen; And I will build that which hath fallen from it, And will raise it up:
B044C015V017	44	15	17	That the residue of men may seek the Lord, And all the Gentiles, on whom my name is called,
B044C015V018	44	15	18	Saith the Lord, who doeth all these. Known from eternity are the works of Aloha.
B044C015V019	44	15	19	On this account I say, that we should not molest those who from the Gentiles have been converted unto Aloha;
B044C015V020	44	15	20	but that we send to them, that they shall separate from the uncleanness of (idol) sacrifice, and from fornication, and from the strangled, and from blood.
B044C015V021	44	15	21	For Musha from former generations in all cities hath had preachers in the synagogues who on all shabaths read him.
B044C015V022	44	15	22	Then the apostles and presbyters, with all the church, elected men from them, and sent to Antiokia with Paulos and Bar Naba Jihuda, who was called Bar Shaba, and Shilo, men who were chief among the brethren.
B044C015V023	44	15	23	AND they wrote an epistle by their hands, thus: The apostles and presbyters and brethren, to those who are in Antiokia and in Syria and in Cilicia, the brethren who are of the Gentiles; peace.
B044C015V024	44	15	24	It hath been heard by us, that men from us have gone forth and disturbed you with words, and have subverted your souls by saying, that you should be circumcised and observe the law, whom we have not commanded.
B044C015V025	44	15	25	On account of this we have deliberated, all being assembled, and have chosen men and sent them to you, with Paulos and Bar Naba, our beloved;
B044C015V026	44	15	26	men who have delivered their lives for the sake of the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B044C015V027	44	15	27	And we have sent with them Jihuda and Shilo, that by word they may tell you the same things.
B044C015V028	44	15	28	For it hath been the will of the Spirit of Holiness, and also of us, not to lay upon you greater burden beyond these things which are constraining;
B044C015V029	44	15	29	that you abstain from that which hath been sacrificed (to idols), and from blood, and from that which is strangled, and from fornication; and while you keep yourselves from these, you will be well. Be confirmed in our Lord.
B044C015V030	44	15	30	Now they who were sent came to Antiokia, and they assembled all the people and gave the epistle.
B044C015V031	44	15	31	And when they had read, they rejoiced and were comforted.
B044C015V032	44	15	32	And by the word the brethren were the more strengthened, and Jihuda and Shilo established them because they were prophets also.
B044C015V033	44	15	33	And when they had been there a time, the brethren dismissed them with peace unto the apostles.
B044C015V035	44	15	35	BUT Paulos and Bar Naba remained in Antiokia, and taught and preached, with many others, the word of Aloha.
B044C015V036	44	15	36	And after (certain) days Paulos said to Bar Naba, Let us return and visit the brethren in every city in which we have preached the word of Aloha, and see what they do.
B044C015V037	44	15	37	But Bar Naba willed to take Juhanon, he who is surnamed Markos.
B044C015V038	44	15	38	But Paulos willed not to take him with them, because he had forsaken them when they were in Pamphylia, and had not come with them.
B044C015V039	44	15	39	On account of this contention they separated one from the other; and Bar Naba took Markos, and they went by sea and came to Cypros.
B044C015V040	44	15	40	But Paulos chose for him Shilo, and went forth commended by the brethren to the grace of Aloha.
B044C015V041	44	15	41	And he went through Syria and Cilicia, confirming the churches. And he came to Derbe the city, and to Lystra.
B044C016V001	44	16	1	BUT a certain disciple was there whose name was Timotheus, the son of a certain Jihudoytha, a believer, and his father an Aramoya.
B044C016V002	44	16	2	And all the disciples who were of Lystra and Ikonia testified concerning him.
B044C016V003	44	16	3	This Paulos willed to take with him; and he took and circumcised him because of the Jihudoyee who were in the place; for they all knew his father that he was an Aramoya.
B044C016V004	44	16	4	And when they had gone into the cities they preached and instructed them to keep those statutes which the apostles and presbyters who were in Urishlem had written.
B044C016V005	44	16	5	So were the churches confirmed in the faith, and multiplied in number every day.
B044C016V006	44	16	6	But they went through the countries of Phrygia and Galatia; and the Spirit of Holiness forbad them, that they should not preach the word of Aloha in Asia.
B044C016V007	44	16	7	And when they came to the region of Mysia they willed to go from thence to Bithynia; and the Spirit of Jeshu permitted them not.
B044C016V008	44	16	8	AND when they had gone forth from Mysia they came to the region of Troas.
B044C016V009	44	16	9	And in a vision of the night, Paulos saw as a certain man, a Makedonoia, who stood and besought him, saying, Come unto Makedunia and help me.
B044C016V010	44	16	10	But when Paulos had seen this vision, he immediately willed to go forth to Makedunia, for he understood that our Lord called us to evangelize them.
B044C016V011	44	16	11	And we went from Troas and proceeded directly to Samuthracia, and from thence the day after we came to Neapolis the city,
B044C016V012	44	16	12	and from thence to Philippos, which is the head of Makedunia, and is a colony. But we were in that city certain days.
B044C016V013	44	16	13	And we went out on the day of shabath without the gate of the city to the bank of the river, because there was seen a house of prayer; and sitting down we discoursed with the women who assembled there.
B044C016V014	44	16	14	And a certain female, a seller of purple, who feared Aloha, her name was Lydia, of Theatira the city, (was there,) whose heart our Lord opened, and she heard that which Paulos spake.
B044C016V015	44	16	15	And she was baptized, she and the sons of her house. And she besought us and said, If it be that you truly think that I have believed in our Lord, come, remain in my house; and she constrained us much.
B044C016V016	44	16	16	AND it was while we went to the house of prayer, a certain damsel met us in whom was a spirit of divination, and she had produced her lords much gain by her divination.
B044C016V017	44	16	17	And she came after Paulos and after us, and cried and said, These men are the servants of Aloha the Most High, and announce to us the way of salvation.
B044C016V018	44	16	18	And this she did many days. And Paulos was indignant, and said to that spirit, I command thee in the name of Jeshu Meshiha to come out of her. And in that hour it came out.
B044C016V019	44	16	19	And when her lords saw that the hope of their gain had gone from her, they laid hold on Paulos and Shilo and drew them to the public place, and brought them unto the prefects and to the chiefs of the city,
B044C016V020	44	16	20	and said, These men are troubling our city, because they are Jihudoyee,
B044C016V021	44	16	21	and are preaching to us those rites which it is not permitted us to receive and perform, because we are Rumoyee.
B044C016V022	44	16	22	And a great gathering assembled against them. Then the prefects rent their vestments, and commanded to scourge them.
B044C016V023	44	16	23	And when they had scourged them much, they cast them into the house of the bound, and commanded the keeper of the house of the bound to keep them watchfully.
B044C016V024	44	16	24	But he, having received this command, brought in and shut them in the inner house of the house of the bound, and fastened their feet in the stocks.
B044C016V025	44	16	25	And in the dividing of the night, Paulos and Shilo prayed and glorified Aloha, and the chained-ones heard them.
B044C016V026	44	16	26	And suddenly there was a great trembling, and the foundations of the house of the bound trembled, and at once the doors of all were opened, and the chains of all were loosened.
B044C016V027	44	16	27	And when the keeper of the house of the bound awoke, and saw that the doors of the house of the bound were open, he took a sword and sought to kill himself, because he thought that the chained-ones had fled.
B044C016V028	44	16	28	And Paulos cried with a high voice and said to him, Do thyself no harm, for we are all here.
B044C016V029	44	16	29	And he kindled for himself a lamp, and sprang, and came, perturbed, and fell at the feet of Paulos and of Shilo:
B044C016V030	44	16	30	and he brought them without, and said to them, My lords, what behoveth me to do that I may be saved?
B044C016V031	44	16	31	And they said to him, Believe in our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, and thou shalt be saved, and thy house.
B044C016V032	44	16	32	And they spoke with him the words of the Lord, and with all the sons of his house.
B044C016V033	44	16	33	And in the same hour of that night, he took and washed them from their stripes, and was forthwith baptized, and all the sons of his house.
B044C016V034	44	16	34	And he took and brought them up into his house, and set for them the table, and exulted, he and the sons of his house, in the faith of Aloha.
B044C016V035	44	16	35	And when it was morning the prefects sent to the bearers of rods to say to the chief of the house of the bound, Loose those men.
B044C016V036	44	16	36	AND when the chief of the house of the bound heard, he entered and spoke that word to Paulos, that the prefects have sent that you might he dismissed; and now go forth (and) proceed in peace.
B044C016V037	44	16	37	Paulos saith to him, They scourged us in the eyes of the world, (we) being innocent, (and) Roman men, and threw us into the house of the bound; and now would they bring us forth secretly? No, indeed, but they shall come and bring us out.
B044C016V038	44	16	38	And the bearers of rods went and told the prefects these words which had been spoken to them. And when they heard that they were Rumoyee, they feared.
B044C016V039	44	16	39	And they came to them, and besought them to come forth and depart from the city.
B044C016V040	44	16	40	And when they had gone forth from the house of the bound, they entered with Lydia, and there saw the brethren, and consoled them. And they went forth
B044C017V001	44	17	1	and passed by Amphipolis and Apolonia, cities, and came to Thessalonika, where was a synagogue of the Jihudoyee.
B044C017V002	44	17	2	AND Paulos entered, as his custom was, with them, and three shabaths spoke to them from the scriptures,
B044C017V003	44	17	3	expounding, and showing, That Meshiha was to suffer and to rise from the house of the dead, and he is Jeshu the Meshiha whom I preach to you.
B044C017V004	44	17	4	And men of them believed and adhered to Paulos and Shilo, and many of the Javnoyee who feared Aloha, and distinguished women not a few.
B044C017V005	44	17	5	And the Jihudoyee envied, and joined to them evil men from the public place of the city, and made a great multitude, and conturbed the city. And they came and stood at the house of Jason, and demanded that they should bring them out from thence and deliver them to the multitude.
B044C017V006	44	17	6	And when they could not find them there, they drew Jason and the brethren who were there, and brought them to the chiefs of the city, crying, These are they who have troubled the whole land; and behold again have they come here;
B044C017V007	44	17	7	and their receiver is this Jason; and all these against the commands of Cesar are risen, in saying that there is another king, Jeshu.
B044C017V008	44	17	8	And the chiefs of the city and all the people were troubled when they heard these things;
B044C017V009	44	17	9	and they took pledges from Jason and also from the brethren, and then dismissed them.
B044C017V010	44	17	10	But the brethren immediately in that night dismissed Paulos and Shilo unto Beroa the city; and when they were come thither they entered into the synagogue of the Jihudoyee:
B044C017V011	44	17	11	for more noble were those Jihudoyee who were there than those Jihudoyee who were in Thessalonika; and they heard from them the word daily with joy, while they decided from the scriptures whether these things were so.
B044C017V012	44	17	12	And many of them believed, and so also of the Javnoyee, men many, and distinguished women.
B044C017V013	44	17	13	And when those Jihudoyee who were of Thessalonika knew that the word of Aloha was preached by Paulos in Beroa the city, they came there also, and ceased not to move and trouble the people.
B044C017V014	44	17	14	And the brethren dismissed Paulos that he should go down by sea; and Shilo and Timotheos remained in that city.
B044C017V015	44	17	15	AND they who accompanied Paulos came unto Athinos the city; and when they departed from the midst of it they took from him an epistle to Shilo and Timotheos, that they should speedily come to him.
B044C017V016	44	17	16	But he, Paulos, while he waited in Athinos, was embittered in his spirit, (for he) saw how the whole city was filled with idols.
B044C017V017	44	17	17	And he spake in the synagogue with the Jihudoyee, and with those who worshipped Aloha, and in the public place with those who met there daily;
B044C017V018	44	17	18	and the philosophers also who were of the doctrine of Epikuros, and others who were called Estoiku, disputed with him. And some of them said, What willeth this accumulator of words? And others said, He preaches foreign gods; because Jeshu and his resurrection he preached unto them.
B044C017V019	44	17	19	And they took him and brought him to the house of judgment which is called Arios-pagos, saying to him, Can we know what this new doctrine is which thou art preaching?
B044C017V020	44	17	20	for thou sowest foreign words in our hearing, and we desire to know what these things are.
B044C017V021	44	17	21	But all the Athinoyee, and those foreigners who are there, of no other thing are careful, but to say and to hear something new.
B044C017V022	44	17	22	AND as Paulos stood on Arios-pagos he said, Men of Athinos, I observe you that in all (things) you exceed in the worship of demons.
B044C017V023	44	17	23	As I walked about and saw the place of your worship, I found a certain altar on which was inscribed, To GOD THE HIDDEN: him then whom while not known you worship, This I declare to you.
B044C017V024	44	17	24	For ALOHA who made the world and all that is in it, and is himself the Lord of heaven and of earth, in temples made with hands resideth not.
B044C017V025	44	17	25	Neither is he served by the hands of men, nor needeth he any thing, for it is he who giveth to every man life and soul.
B044C017V026	44	17	26	And of one blood hath he made the whole world of men to dwell upon the face of all the earth, and he hath distinguished the times by his decree, and set the limits of the dwelling of mankind,
B044C017V027	44	17	27	that they should seek Aloha and inquire, and from his creatures find himself, because he is not far from every one of us.
B044C017V028	44	17	28	For in him we live, and are moved, and are; as also one of your sages hath said, From him is our descent.
B044C017V029	44	17	29	Men, therefore, whose descent is from Aloha, should not think that gold or silver or stone sculptured by the art and skill of man is like the Divinity.
B044C017V030	44	17	30	For the times of error Aloha hath made to pass away; and in this time he commandeth all men, that every man in every place should repent;
B044C017V031	44	17	31	because he hath set a day in which he will judge the whole earth in righteousness by that Man whom he hath ordained; and he will convert every man to the faith of him in having raised him from among the dead.
B044C017V032	44	17	32	And when they heard of resurrection from among the dead, (some) of them mocked, and (some) of them said, At another time we will hear thee concerning this.
B044C017V033	44	17	33	And so Paulos went forth from among them.
B044C017V034	44	17	34	And certain of them adhered to him and believed: but one of them was Dionosios of the judges of Arios-pagos, and a certain woman whose name was Damaris, and others with them.
B044C018V001	44	18	1	AND when Paulos had gone forth from Athinos, he came unto Kurinthos.
B044C018V002	44	18	2	And he found there a certain man, a Jihudoya, whose name was Akilos, who was from the country of Pontos, (and) who at that time had come from the country of Italia, himself and Priskila his wife, because Klaudios Cesar had commanded that all the Jihudoyee should go out from Ruma; and he drew near to them:
B044C018V003	44	18	3	(and) because he was a son of their art, he dwelt with them and wrought with them: but in their art they were tentmakers.
B044C018V004	44	18	4	And he discoursed in the synagogue every shabath, and persuaded the Jihudoyee and the Heathens.
B044C018V005	44	18	5	And when from Makedunia Shilo and Timotheos had come, Paulos was constrained in his speech, because the Jihudoyee arose against him and blasphemed, while he testified to them that Jeshu is the Meshiha.
B044C018V006	44	18	6	And he shook his garments and said to them, From now I am clean: I go unto the Gentiles.
B044C018V007	44	18	7	And he went forth from thence, and entered into the house of a man named Titos, who worshipped Aloha; and his house adjoined the synagogue.
B044C018V008	44	18	8	And Krispos, master of the synagogue, believed in our Lord, he and all the sons of his house. And many of the Kurinthoyee heard and believed in Aloha, and were baptized.
B044C018V009	44	18	9	And the Lord said in a vision unto Paulos, Fear not, but speak and be not silent;
B044C018V010	44	18	10	for I am with thee, and no man can do thee harm; and I have much people in this city.
B044C018V011	44	18	11	But he abode a year and six months in Kurinthos, and taught them the word of Aloha.
B044C018V012	44	18	12	AND when Galion was proconsul of Akaia, they gathered together against Paulos, and brought him before the tribunal,
B044C018V013	44	18	13	saying, This (man) part from the law persuadeth men to worship Aloha.
B044C018V014	44	18	14	And when Paulos sought to open his mouth and speak, Galion said to the Jihudoyee, If it were concerning some thing of evil, or of wickedness, or of abomination, you would complain, O Jihudoyee, it would be proper for me to receive you;
B044C018V015	44	18	15	but if they be questions concerning language and names, and concerning your law, let them be known among yourselves; for I am not willing to be a judge of these matters.
B044C018V016	44	18	16	And he drove them from his tribunal.
B044C018V017	44	18	17	And all the Heathens seized Sosthenis the presbyter of the synagogue, and beat him before the tribunal. And Galion was careless of these.
B044C018V018	44	18	18	And when Paulos had been there many days, he gave the salutation to the brethren, and proceeded by sea to go to Syria: and Priskila and Akilos went with him, when he had shaved his head at Kankreos, because he had vowed a vow.
B044C018V019	44	18	19	And they came to Ephesos. And Paulos entered the synagogue and discoursed with the Jihudoyee;
B044C018V020	44	18	20	and they requested of him to tarry with them; and he was not willing;
B044C018V021	44	18	21	for he said, It behoveth me faithfully to perform the feast which cometh at Urishlem; and if Aloha willeth, I will come again to you. And Akilos and Priskila he left at Ephesos;
B044C018V022	44	18	22	and he voyaged by sea and came to Cesarea: and he went up and wished the peace of the sons of the church, and went unto Antiokia.
B044C018V023	44	18	23	And when he had been there certain days, he went forth and itinerated successively through Phrygia and Galatia, confirming all the disciples.
B044C018V024	44	18	24	And a certain man whose name was Apolu, a Jihudoya, who was by family of Aleksandria, and erudite in speech, and accurate in the scriptures, came to Ephesos.
B044C018V025	44	18	25	This was discipled in the way of the Lord, and was fervid in spirit, and he spake and taught freely concerning Jeshu, while knowing not any thing but the baptism of Juhanon.
B044C018V026	44	18	26	And he began boldly to speak in the synagogue. And when Akilos and Priskila heard him, they brought him to their house, and fully showed to him the way of the Lord.
B044C018V027	44	18	27	And when he willed to go to Akaia, the brethren were careful of him, and wrote to the disciples to receive him. And when he had gone he helped much, through grace, all the believers.
B044C018V028	44	18	28	For he disputed forcibly against the Jihudoyee before the assemblies, while he showed from the scriptures concerning Jeshu, that he is the Meshiha.
B044C019V001	44	19	1	AND while Apolu was in Kurinthos, Paulos itinerated through the upper countries unto Ephesos; and he asked those disciples whom he found there,
B044C019V002	44	19	2	Have you received the Spirit of Holiness from that you believed? They answered and said to him, It hath not been heard by us whether there be the Spirit.
B044C019V003	44	19	3	He saith to them, And into what were you baptized? They said, Into the baptism of Juhanon.
B044C019V004	44	19	4	Paulos saith to them, Juhanon baptized the people with the baptism of repentance, saying that they should believe in him who was coming after him, who is Jeshu Meshiha.
B044C019V005	44	19	5	And when they heard these (words), they were baptized in the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B044C019V006	44	19	6	And Paulos laid on them the hand, and the Spirit of Holiness came upon them, and they spake with tongues, and prophesied.
B044C019V007	44	19	7	But all the men were twelve.
B044C019V008	44	19	8	And Paulos entered the synagogue, and discoursed boldly three months, and persuaded concerning the kingdom of Aloha.
B044C019V009	44	19	9	And men of them were obdurate, and contended, and reviled the way of Aloha, before the assembly of the people. Then Paulos removed and separated from them the disciples, and every day discoursed with them in the school of a man whose name was Tyranos.
B044C019V010	44	19	10	And this was done two years, until all who dwelt in Asia, Jihudoyee and Aramoyee, had heard the word of the Lord.
B044C019V011	44	19	11	And great power-works wrought Aloha by the hand of Paulos;
B044C019V012	44	19	12	so that they brought even from the garments that were upon his body napkins or wrappings, and laid them upon the sick, and the diseases went from them; and demons also went forth.
B044C019V013	44	19	13	BUT men, Jihudoyee, also, who went about and adjured demons, willed to adjure in the name of our Lord Jeshu over those who had unclean spirits, saying, We adjure you in the name of Jeshu whom Paulos preacheth.
B044C019V014	44	19	14	There were seven sons of a man, a certain Jihudoya, chief of the priests, whose name was Skeva, who did this.
B044C019V015	44	19	15	And that evil demon answered and said to them, Jeshu I acknowledge, and Paulos I know; but who are you?
B044C019V016	44	19	16	And the man in whom was the evil spirit sprang upon them, and was strong against them, and threw them, and they, naked and wounded, fled from that house.
B044C019V017	44	19	17	And this was known to all the Jihudoyee and Aramoyee who dwelt in Ephesos: and fear fell upon them all, and the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha was exalted.
B044C019V018	44	19	18	And many of those who believed came and acknowledged their sins, and confessed whatever they had done.
B044C019V019	44	19	19	Many also of the magicians collected their writings and brought and burned them before all men; and they reckoned the price of them, and it ascended to silver five myriads.
B044C019V020	44	19	20	And thus with great power prevailed and increased the faith of Aloha.
B044C019V021	44	19	21	But when these were fulfilled, Paulos set in his mind to itinerate throughout all Makedunia and Akaia, and to go into Urishlem. And he said, When I shall have gone thither, it behoveth me Ruma also to see.
B044C019V022	44	19	22	And he sent two men of those who ministered to him to Makedunia, Timotheos and Aristos; but he remained a time in Asia.
B044C019V023	44	19	23	BUT there was made at that time a great tumult on account of the way of Aloha.
B044C019V024	44	19	24	For there was a certain worker of silver there whose name was Dimitrios, who made shrines of silver of Artemis, and he produced for the sons of his art great gains.
B044C019V025	44	19	25	This (man) assembled all the sons of his art and those who wrought with them, and said to them, Men, you know that all our merchandise is from this work;
B044C019V026	44	19	26	and you also hear and see, that not only the sons of Ephesos, but also many of all Asia, this Paulos persuadeth, and hath perverted them, saying, that there be no gods which by the hands of men are made.
B044C019V027	44	19	27	And not only is this business defamed and brought to an end, but also the temple of Artemis the great goddess is reputed as nothing, and she also, the goddess of all Asia, and (whom) all the nations worship, is despised.
B044C019V028	44	19	28	And when they heard these (words) they were filled with wrath; and they cried, and said, Great is Artemis of the Ephesoyee.
B044C019V029	44	19	29	And the whole city was perturbed, and they ran together and came to the theatre; and seizing, they led with them Gaios and Aristarkos, men of Makedunia, companions of Paulos.
B044C019V030	44	19	30	AND Paulos willed to enter the theatre, and the disciples restrained him.
B044C019V031	44	19	31	And the chiefs of Asia, because they were his friends, sent, praying of him not to deliver himself by going into the theatre.
B044C019V032	44	19	32	But the crowd who were in the theatre were greatly commoved, and others cried other things; for many of them knew not on what account they were assembled.
B044C019V033	44	19	33	But the people of the Jihudoyee who were there appointed of them a man a Jihudoya, whose name was Aleksandros; and when he stood (forth) he signed that he would apologize to the people.
B044C019V034	44	19	34	And when they knew that he was a Jihudoya, all of them cried with one voice, as two hours, Great is Artemis of the Ephesoyee!
B044C019V035	44	19	35	And the chief of the city stilled them, saying, Men, Ephesoyee, who is there of mankind who knoweth not that the city of the Ephesoyee is a votaress of the great Artemis, and of her image which descended from heaven?
B044C019V036	44	19	36	Therefore, since no man can contradict this, it behoves you to be silent, and to do nothing in haste.
B044C019V037	44	19	37	Yet have you brought these men who have neither spoiled temples nor blasphemed our goddess.
B044C019V038	44	19	38	But if this Dimitrios and the sons of his craft have strife with any man, behold, the proconsul is in the city, (and) there are officers: let them go nigh and judge one with another.
B044C019V039	44	19	39	And if you require other (procedure), in the place which is given by the law for an assembly it shall be resolved.
B044C019V040	44	19	40	For now also are we standing in peril of being accused as disturbers, because we cannot make excuse for the concourse of this day, inasmuch as we have met uselessly, and have made a tumult without cause.
B044C019V041	44	19	41	And when these he had said, he dissolved the assembly.
B044C020V001	44	20	1	And after the tumult had stilled, Paulos called the disciples and consoled them and kissed them, and going forth went unto Makedunia.
B044C020V002	44	20	2	And when he had itinerated those regions, and had consoled them with many words, he came into the country of Hales,
B044C020V003	44	20	3	and was there three months. But the Jihudoyee wrought treachery against him, when he was about to go into Syria, and had thought to return into Makedunia.
B044C020V004	44	20	4	And (there) went forth with him into Asia Supatros who was from Berula, the city; and Aristarkos and Sakundos, who (were) from Thessalonika; and Gaios, who was from Derbe the city; and Timotheos, who was from Lystra; and from Asia, Tukikos and Trophimos.
B044C020V005	44	20	5	These went before us, and waited for us in Troas.
B044C020V006	44	20	6	But we went forth from Philipos, a city of the Makedunoyee, after the days of the Phatiree, and voyaged by sea and came to Troas in five days, and there were we seven days.
B044C020V007	44	20	7	AND on the first day in the week, when we were assembled to break the eucharist, Paulos discoursed with them, because the day following he was to depart; and he prolonged his discourse until the dividing of the night.
B044C020V008	44	20	8	And there were many lamps of fire in the high-room where we were assembled.
B044C020V009	44	20	9	And a certain youth whose name was Eutikos sat in a window and heard. And he had sunk into a heavy sleep while Paulos prolonged his discourse, and in his sleep he fell from the third floor, and was taken up as dead.
B044C020V010	44	20	10	And Paulos descended, and fell upon him and embraced him, and said, Be not agitated, for his life is in him.
B044C020V011	44	20	11	When he had gone up, he broke bread and tasted, speaking with them until the morning arose; and then went he forth to proceed by land.
B044C020V012	44	20	12	And they brought the young man alive, and rejoiced over him greatly.
B044C020V013	44	20	13	But we went down to the ship, and voyaged to the port of Thesos, because there we were to receive Paulos, for thus he had instructed us, while he himself would proceed by land.
B044C020V014	44	20	14	But when we had received him from Thesos, we took him up into the ship and came to Mitylene.
B044C020V015	44	20	15	And from thence the day after we voyaged over against Kios the island, and again the day after we came to Samos; and we tarried at Trogalium, and the day after we came to Militos:
B044C020V016	44	20	16	for Paulos had decided with himself to pass by Ephesos, that he might not be hindered there, because he hastened, that, if it were possible, on the day of the Pentecost in Urishlem he might work.
B044C020V017	44	20	17	AND from Militos he sent to bring the presbyters of the church of Ephesos;
B044C020V018	44	20	18	and when they came to him, he said to them: You know, that from the first day that I entered Asia, how I was with you all time,
B044C020V019	44	20	19	serving Aloha in much lowliness and with tears, and in those temptations which passed upon me through the devices of the Jihudoyee.
B044C020V020	44	20	20	Neither neglected I any thing that was profitable for your souls, that I might preach to you and teach in public places and in houses,
B044C020V021	44	20	21	while I testified to Jihudoyee and to Aramoyee concerning repentance that is toward Aloha, and faith which is in our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B044C020V022	44	20	22	And now I, bound in the Spirit, go to Urishlem; not knowing what I shall know in her.
B044C020V023	44	20	23	Nevertheless, the Spirit of Holiness in every city testifieth to me and saith, that bonds and afflictions are for me.
B044C020V024	44	20	24	But by me my life is reckoned nothing, so that I may accomplish my course, and the ministry I have received from our Lord Jeshu, to bear witness concerning the gospel of the grace of Aloha.
B044C020V025	44	20	25	And now, I know that again my face you will not see, you, all, among whom I have gone about, preaching to you the kingdom of Aloha.
B044C020V026	44	20	26	I testify to you this very day, that I am pure from the blood of you all.
B044C020V027	44	20	27	For I have not shunned to make known to you all the will of Aloha.
B044C020V028	44	20	28	Take heed therefore to yourselves, and to the whole flock over which the Spirit of Holiness hath constituted you the bishops; to pasture the church of the Meshiha which he hath purchased with his blood.
B044C020V029	44	20	29	For I know that after I shall have gone, there will enter with you furious wolves which will not spare the flock.
B044C020V030	44	20	30	And also from you, of yourselves, will men arise speaking perverse things to turn away disciples to go after them.
B044C020V031	44	20	31	On account of this be watchful, and remember, that for three years I ceased not by night and by day with tears to instruct every one of you.
B044C020V032	44	20	32	And now I commend you to Aloha, and to the word of his grace, who is able to build you up, and to give you an inheritance with all the saints.
B044C020V033	44	20	33	Silver, or gold, or raiment have I not coveted;
B044C020V034	44	20	34	and you know to the necessity of myself, and of those who are with me, these hands have ministered.
B044C020V035	44	20	35	And I have shown you every thing, (that) so it behoveth to labour, and to be careful of those who are infirm, and to remember the word of our Lord Jeshu, that he said, He is blessed who giveth, more than he who receiveth.
B044C020V036	44	20	36	And when these he had said, he kneeled on his knees and prayed, and all the men with him.
B044C020V037	44	20	37	And there was a great weeping with all of them, and they embraced him and kissed him;
B044C020V038	44	20	38	but most agonized (were they) by that word which he had spoken, that again they were not to see his face. And they accompanied him to the ship.
B044C021V001	44	21	1	And we separated from them and voyaged directly unto Ko the island, and the day after we came to Rodos, and from thence to Patara;
B044C021V002	44	21	2	and we found there a ship which was going to Punike, and we ascended into her and voyaged.
B044C021V003	44	21	3	And coming near Kypros the island, we left it on the left hand and came unto Syria, and thence came we to Tsur: for there was the ship to relieve from her burden.
B044C021V004	44	21	4	And having found disciples there, we sojourned with them seven days. And these said daily unto Paulos in the Spirit, That he should not go unto Urishlem.
B044C021V005	44	21	5	And after those days we departed to go on the way. And they accompanied us, all of them, they and their wives and their children, till without the city, and kneeled upon their knees on the sea shore, and prayed. And we kissed one another,
B044C021V006	44	21	6	and we ascended to the ship, and they returned to their homes.
B044C021V007	44	21	7	But we voyaged from Tsur, and came to Aku the city, and gave the salutation to the brethren who were there, and abode among them one day.
B044C021V008	44	21	8	And the day after we departed and came to Cesarea; and we entered and abode in the house of Philipos the preacher, he who was of the seven.
B044C021V009	44	21	9	And he had four virgin daughters who prophesied.
B044C021V010	44	21	10	And when we had been there many days, there came down from Jihud a certain prophet whose name was Agabos.
B044C021V011	44	21	11	And he came in to us, and took the loins'-girdle of Paulos, and bound his own feet and his hands, and said, Thus saith the Spirit of Holiness, So the man the master of this girdle will the Jihudoyee bind in Urishlem; and they will deliver him into the hands of the Gentiles.
B044C021V012	44	21	12	And when we heard these words, we and the sons of the place entreated of him not to go unto Urishlem.
B044C021V013	44	21	13	THEN answered Paulos and said, What do you, weeping and bruising my heart? For not to be bound only am I prepared, but also to die in Urishlem, for the sake of the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B044C021V014	44	21	14	And when he would not be persuaded by us, we desisted, and said, The will of our Lord be done.
B044C021V015	44	21	15	And after those days we prepared and went up to Urishlem.
B044C021V016	44	21	16	And there went with us men, disciples, from Cesarea, who conducted with them a certain brother of the first disciples whose name was Mnason, and he was from Kypros, to receive us into his house.
B044C021V017	44	21	17	And when we were come to Urishlem, the brethren received us joyfully.
B044C021V018	44	21	18	And the day following we entered with Paulos to Jakub, while all the presbyters were with him.
B044C021V019	44	21	19	And we gave them salutation. And Paulos recounted to them in order what Aloha had done among the Gentiles by his ministry.
B044C021V020	44	21	20	And when they heard, they glorified Aloha. And they said to him, Thou seest, our brother, how many myriads there are in Jihud who believe, and all of them are zealous for the law.
B044C021V021	44	21	21	But it hath been said to them of thee, that thou teachest all the Jihudoyee who are among the Gentiles to remove from Musha; telling them that they should not circumcise their sons, nor walk in the customs of the law.
B044C021V022	44	21	22	On this account, when they hear that thou art come hither, do that which we tell thee.
B044C021V023	44	21	23	We have four men who have a vow to be purified.
B044C021V024	44	21	24	Take them, and go, purify with them, and lay out upon them the expenses, that they may shave their heads; and it will be known to every man that what hath been said against thee is false, and that thou fulfillest and keepest the law.
B044C021V025	44	21	25	Concerning those of the Gentiles who believe, we wrote that they should keep themselves from sacrifices, and from fornication, and from the strangled, and from blood.
B044C021V026	44	21	26	Then Paul took those men the day after, and was purified with them. And he entered and went into the temple, making known to them the fulfillment of the days of the purification, so that an oblation might be offered for each man of them.
B044C021V027	44	21	27	And when the seventh day was come the Jihudoyee who were from Asia saw him in the temple, and stirred up against him all the people. And they lifted their hands against him,
B044C021V028	44	21	28	crying out, and saying, Men, sons of Israel, help! This is the man who contrary to our people teacheth every where, and contrary to the law, and against this place. And also Aramoyee hath he brought into the temple, and profaned this holy place.
B044C021V029	44	21	29	For they had before seen with him Trophimus the Ephesian in the city, and supposed that with Paulos he had entered the temple.
B044C021V030	44	21	30	And the whole city was commoved, and all the people assembled, and they laid hold of Paulos, and dragged him without from the temple; and instantly the gates were shut.
B044C021V031	44	21	31	And while the multitude sought to kill him, the tribune of the cohort heard that the whole city was agitated.
B044C021V032	44	21	32	And forthwith took he a centurion and many soldiers and ran upon them; and when they saw the tribune and the soldiers, they desisted from beating Paulos.
B044C021V033	44	21	33	And the tribune drew near and took him, and commanded them to bind him with two chains. And he asked concerning him who (he was), and what he had done?
B044C021V034	44	21	34	And men from the crowd cried against him variously, and because of their crying he was not able to know what was the truth; and he commanded that they should lead him to the fortress.
B044C021V035	44	21	35	And as Paulos came to the stairs the soldiers carried him, on account of the violence of the people:
B044C021V036	44	21	36	for after him was much people; and they cried, and said, Away with him!
B044C021V037	44	21	37	And as they came to enter into the fortress, Paulos himself said to the tribune, May I be permitted to speak to the people?
B044C021V038	44	21	38	But he said to him, Javanith knowest thou? Art thou not that Metsroya who before these days stirred up and led forth into the waste four thousand men workers of evils?
B044C021V039	44	21	39	Paulos said to him, I am a man a Jihudoya from Tarsos of Cilicia, an illustrious city in which I was born: I pray you permit me to speak to the people.
B044C021V040	44	21	40	And when he had permitted him, Paulos stood upon the stairs, and signed to them with his hand; and when they had ceased, he spoke to them in Hebrew, and said to them,
B044C022V001	44	22	1	Brethren and fathers, hear the defence which I make to you.
B044C022V002	44	22	2	And when they heard that Hebrew he was speaking with them, the more they ceased; and he said to them,
B044C022V003	44	22	3	I am a man a Jihudoya; and I was born in Tarsos of Cilicia, but was brought up in this city at the feet of Gamaliel, and instructed perfectly in the law of our fathers. And I was zealous for Aloha, even as all of you are also.
B044C022V004	44	22	4	And this way I persecuted unto the death, while I bound and delivered to the house of the bound both men and women;
B044C022V005	44	22	5	as the chief of the priests can testify of me, and all the elders, that from them I received letters to go to the brethren who were in Darmsuk, that also them who were there I should bring to Urishlem bound, that they might be fined.
B044C022V006	44	22	6	And as I went, and began to approach Darmsuk in the dividing of the day, suddenly from heaven there shone upon me a great light,
B044C022V007	44	22	7	and I fell upon the earth, and heard a voice, which said to me, Shaol, Shaol, why persecutest thou me?
B044C022V008	44	22	8	But I answered and said, Who art thou, my Lord? And he said to me, I am Jeshu Natsroya, whom thou persecutest!
B044C022V009	44	22	9	And the men who were with me saw the light, but the voice they understood not which spake with me.
B044C022V010	44	22	10	And I said, What shall I do, my Lord? And he said to me, Arise, go into Darmsuk, and there shall it be told thee of whatever it is commanded thee to do.
B044C022V011	44	22	11	And while I could not see because of the glory of that light, they who were with me took me by my hands, and I entered Darmsuk.
B044C022V012	44	22	12	And a man, one Hanania, righteous in the law, as the Jihudoyee who were there testified of him,
B044C022V013	44	22	13	came to me, and said to me, Shaol, my brother, open thine eyes. And in a moment my eyes were opened, and I beheld him.
B044C022V014	44	22	14	And he said to me, The God of our fathers hath appointed thee to know his will, and to see that Just One, and to hear the voice from his lips,
B044C022V015	44	22	15	that thou mayest be a witness to all men of all that thou hast seen and heard.
B044C022V016	44	22	16	And now why delayest thou? Arise, baptize, and be washed from thy sins, while thou callest his Name.
B044C022V017	44	22	17	And being returned, I came hither to Urishlem. And I prayed in the temple.
B044C022V018	44	22	18	And I saw him in a vision, when he said to me, Hasten, and remove thee from Urishlem: for they will not receive thy testimony concerning me.
B044C022V019	44	22	19	And I said, My Lord, they know also how I delivered to the house of the bound, and smote in all the synagogues, those who have believed in thee.
B044C022V020	44	22	20	And when the blood of thy martyr Estephanos was shed, I also stood with them, and fulfilled the will of his murderers, and kept the garments of them who stoned him.
B044C022V021	44	22	21	And he said to me, Go: for I send thee far away to preach to the Gentiles.
B044C022V022	44	22	22	And when they had heard Paulos until this word, they lifted up their voice, and cried, Take from the earth one like this; for he ought not to live.
B044C022V023	44	22	23	And as they shouted and cast their garments and threw dust to the heaven,
B044C022V024	44	22	24	the tribune commanded that he should be brought into the fortress, and commanded him to be questioned by scourging, that he might know for what cause they cried against him.
B044C022V025	44	22	25	And as they exposed him with thongs, Paulos said to the centurion who stood near him, Is it allowed you to scourge a Roman man who is not condemned?
B044C022V026	44	22	26	And when the centurion heard, he approached the tribune, and said to him, What doest thou? For this is a Roman man.
B044C022V027	44	22	27	And the tribune approached him, and said to him, Tell me, art thou a Roman? He said to him, Yes.
B044C022V028	44	22	28	The tribune answered, and said to him, I with much money purchased the Roman-right. Paulos said to him, But I was born in it.
B044C022V029	44	22	29	And immediately those who had sought to scourge him desisted from him; and the tribune feared when he learned that he was a Roman, because he had bound him.
B044C022V030	44	22	30	AND the day after he willed to know truly what was the accusation which the Jihudoyee brought against him. And he ordered him and commanded the great priests and all the synagogue of their rulers to come; and he took Paulos and brought (him) down, and stood him among them.
B044C023V001	44	23	1	And Paulos, looking upon their assembly, said, Men, brethren, I in all good conscience have conversed before Aloha, unto this day.
B044C023V002	44	23	2	And Hanania the priest commanded them who stood by him to smite Paulos upon his mouth.
B044C023V003	44	23	3	And Paulos said to him, It will be that Aloha will smite thee, (thou) whitened wall: thou sittest to judge me according to the law, while thou transgressest the law, and commandest that they smite me!
B044C023V004	44	23	4	And they who stood there said to him, The priest of Aloha revilest thou?
B044C023V005	44	23	5	Paulos said to them, I knew not, my brethren, that he is the priest; for it is written, Of the chief of thy people thou shalt not speak evil.
B044C023V006	44	23	6	And when Paulos knew that (part) of the people were of the Zadukoyee and (part) of it of the Pharishee, he cried in the assembly, Men, my brethren, I am a Pharisha, the son of Pharishee; and for the hope of the resurrection of the dead am I judged.
B044C023V007	44	23	7	And when he had said this, the Pharishee and the Zadukoyee fell on one another, and the people was divided.
B044C023V008	44	23	8	For the Zadukoyee say that there is no resurrection, nor angels, nor spirit; but the Pharishee confess all these.
B044C023V009	44	23	9	And there was made a great noise. And certain sophree of the choice of the Pharishee arose and contended with them, and said, We have not found any thing of evil in this man; but if a spirit or an angel hath spoken with him, what is there in this?
B044C023V010	44	23	10	And when there was a great commotion among them, the tribune feared lest they should tear Paulos in pieces, and he sent to the Rumoyee to come and carry him away from the midst of them, and take him into the fortress.
B044C023V011	44	23	11	And when it was night our Lord appeared unto Paulos, and said to him, Be strong: for as thou hast testified of me in Urishlem, so is it to be that thou also in Ruma shalt testify.
B044C023V012	44	23	12	AND when it became morning, men of the Jihudoyee gathered and bound a vow upon themselves, that they would not eat or drink till they had killed Paulos.
B044C023V013	44	23	13	But there were of those who established by oath this compact more than forty men.
B044C023V014	44	23	14	And they drew nigh to the priests and to the elders, and said, A vow we have vowed upon us, that nothing will we taste until we have killed Paulos.
B044C023V015	44	23	15	And now do you and the princes of the synagogue request from the tribune to bring him to you, as if you sought to investigate more truly his work, and we are prepared to kill him while he shall come to you.
B044C023V016	44	23	16	And the son of the sister of Paulos heard this plot, and he entered the fortress and informed Paulos.
B044C023V017	44	23	17	And Paulos sent (and) called one of the centurions, and said to him, Bring this youth to the tribune, for he has somewhat to tell him.
B044C023V018	44	23	18	And the centurion conducted the youth, and introduced him to the tribune, and said, Paulos the prisoner called me, and requested of me to bring this youth to thee, because he hath somewhat to tell thee.
B044C023V019	44	23	19	And the tribune took the youth by his hand, and led him on one side, and asked him, What hast thou to tell me?
B044C023V020	44	23	20	And the youth said to him, The Jihudoyee have determined to request of thee to send down Paulos, tomorrow, to their synagogue, as if willing to learn somewhat more from him:
B044C023V021	44	23	21	thou therefore yield not to them; for, behold, more than forty men of them watch for him in ambush, and have bound a curse upon themselves, that they will neither eat nor drink till they have killed him: and, behold, they are ready, and wait thy promise.
B044C023V022	44	23	22	And the tribune dismissed the youth, when he had admonished him, Let no man know that these thou hast informed me.
B044C023V023	44	23	23	And he called two centurions, and said to them, Go, prepare two hundred Romans to go to Cesarea, and seventy horsemen and right-handed spearmen two hundred, to go forth at the third hour of the night;
B044C023V024	44	23	24	but provide also a beast to carry Paulos, and escape to Felix the governor.
B044C023V025	44	23	25	And he wrote a letter, and gave it to them, which was thus:
B044C023V026	44	23	26	Klaudios Lusios unto Felix the victorious governor, peace.
B044C023V027	44	23	27	The Jihudoyee had seized this man to kill him; and I arose with the Romans and rescued him, when I had learned that he is a Roman.
B044C023V028	44	23	28	And when I sought to know the occasion of which they accused him, I brought him down to their synagogue.
B044C023V029	44	23	29	And I found that concerning questions of their law they accused him; and a cause worthy of bonds or of death was not in him.
B044C023V030	44	23	30	And when it was told me of the treachery of a plot which the Jihudoyee wrought against him, I straightway sent him to thee; and I have commanded his accusers to come and speak with him before thee. Farewell.
B044C023V031	44	23	31	Then the Rumoyee, as they had been commanded, took Paulos by night, and brought him to Antipatros the city;
B044C023V032	44	23	32	and the day after the horsemen sent away their foot-companions to return to the fortress.
B044C023V033	44	23	33	And they came to Cesarea. And they gave the letter to the governor, and made Paulos stand before him.
B044C023V034	44	23	34	And when he had read the letter, he asked him from what province he was. And when he had heard that (he was) from Cilicia,
B044C023V035	44	23	35	he said to him, I will hear thee when thy accusers have come. And he commanded that they should keep him in the pretorium of Herodes.
B044C024V001	44	24	1	AND after five days Hanania the great priest came down with the elders, and with Tartelos a rhetor, and informed the governor against Paulos.
B044C024V002	44	24	2	And being called, Tartelos came forth to accuse him, and said, For many years have we dwelt (in peace) through thee, and many reformations have been made for this people in the bearing of thy office;
B044C024V003	44	24	3	and all we in every place receive thy bounty, victorious Felix.
B044C024V004	44	24	4	But, not to weary thee with many (words), I pray thee to hear our humbleness with brevity.
B044C024V005	44	24	5	For we have found this man to be a destroyer, and an exciter of agitation among all the Jihudoyee, and in all the land: for he is a chief of the doctrine of the Natsroyee,
B044C024V006	44	24	6	and he willed to pollute our temple; and having apprehended him, we sought to judge him according to our law;
B044C024V007	44	24	7	but Lusios the tribune came, and with great force transferred him from our hands,
B044C024V008	44	24	8	and hath sent him unto thee, and commanded his accusers to come to thee; and thou canst by questioning him learn from him concerning all these things of which we accuse him.
B044C024V009	44	24	9	The Jihudoyee themselves also contended against him, saying, that so these things were.
B044C024V010	44	24	10	And the governor signed to Paulos to speak. And Paulos answered, and said, For many years I know that thou hast been the judge of this people, and on this account I joyfully make defence for myself;
B044C024V011	44	24	11	while thou shouldst know that it hath not been more than twelve days since I went up to Urishlem to worship.
B044C024V012	44	24	12	Neither found they me speaking with any man in the temple, neither have I gathered an assembly in their synagogue nor in the city;
B044C024V013	44	24	13	nor is it in their power to demonstrate before thee any thing of what they accuse me.
B044C024V014	44	24	14	Nevertheless, this do I confess, that in that very doctrine of which they speak, in it serve I the God of my fathers, believing in all that is written in the law and in the prophets,
B044C024V015	44	24	15	and having hope in Aloha that which they also hope: that there shall be a resurrection from the house of the dead, of the just and of the evil.
B044C024V016	44	24	16	Because of this also I labour to have a good conscience before Aloha and before men, continually.
B044C024V017	44	24	17	But after many years I came to the sons of my people to bestow alms, and to present an oblation.
B044C024V018	44	24	18	And these found me in the temple being purified, not with a concourse nor with tumult; but men Jihudoyee who had come from Asia raised a tumult;
B044C024V019	44	24	19	(and) these it behoved to stand with me before thee, and to accuse of that whatever they have (against me).
B044C024V020	44	24	20	Or let these themselves declare, what crime they found in me, when I stood before their assembly,
B044C024V021	44	24	21	unless for this one word which I proclaimed while standing in the midst of them, For the resurrection of the dead am I judged this day before you.
B044C024V022	44	24	22	But Felix, because he knew this way fully, delayed them, saying, When the tribune comes I will hear between you.
B044C024V023	44	24	23	And he commanded the centurion to keep Paulos in quietude, and that none of his acquaintances should be hindered from ministering to him.
B044C024V024	44	24	24	And after a few days Felix, and Drusilla his wife, who was a Jihudoytha, sent and called Paulos, and they heard from him concerning the faith of the Meshiha.
B044C024V025	44	24	25	And as he discoursed with them of righteousness, and of holiness, and of the judgment which is to come, Felix was filled with fear, and he said, Now go, and when I have opportunity I will send for thee.
B044C024V026	44	24	26	For he hoped that a bribe would be given him by Paulos, and on this account he continually sent to bring him, and to speak with him.
B044C024V027	44	24	27	And when two years were fulfilled to him, another governor came in his place, who was called Porcios Festos. But Felix, as to do a favour to the Jihudoyee, left Paulos bound.
B044C025V001	44	25	1	And when Festos came to Cesarea, after three days he went up to Urishlem.
B044C025V002	44	25	2	And the chief priest and elders showed him concerning Paulos, and besought from him,
B044C025V003	44	25	3	asking of him this favour, that he would bring him to Urishlem, while they would act treacherously in the way by killing him.
B044C025V004	44	25	4	And Festos returned the word, That Paulos was kept in Cesarea, and I am hastening to proceed;
B044C025V005	44	25	5	let those therefore of you who are able, go down with us, and accuse him of whatever guilt there is in the man.
B044C025V006	44	25	6	And when he had been there eight days or ten, he went down to Cesarea. And the day after he sat on the tribunal, and commanded to bring Paulos.
B044C025V007	44	25	7	And when he had come, the Jihudoyee who had come down from Urishlem surrounded him, and accusations many and hard brought against him, which they were not able to prove;
B044C025V008	44	25	8	while Paulos put forth the mind, that he had not offended in any thing, neither against the law of the Jihudoyee, nor against the temple, nor against Caesar.
B044C025V009	44	25	9	But Festos, because he willed to accord a favour to the Jihudoyee, said to Paulos, Art thou willing to go up to Urishlem, and there concerning these things to be judged before me?
B044C025V010	44	25	10	Paulos answered, and said, At the tribunal of Caesar stand I. There it is right for me to be judged. Not any thing have I transgressed against the Jihudoyee, as also thou knowest;
B044C025V011	44	25	11	and if a crime I have committed, or any thing worthy of death, I ask not (to be exempted) from death. But, if there be nothing in me of which these accuse me, no man shall give me to them as a gift. I invoke the appeals of Caesar.
B044C025V012	44	25	12	Then Festos, having spoken with the sons of his council, said, The appeals of Caesar hast thou invoked? To Caesar goest thou.
B044C025V013	44	25	13	AND when days had been, Agripos the king and Bernike came down to Cesarea to salute Festos.
B044C025V014	44	25	14	And when they had been with him (some) days, Festos recounted to the king the judgment of Paulos, saying, A certain man has been left bound by Felix;
B044C025V015	44	25	15	and when I was at Urishlem, the chief priests and elders of the Jihudoyee informed me against him, and begged that I would do for them judgment against him.
B044C025V016	44	25	16	And I told them, it was not the custom of the Romans to give any man as a gift to be killed, until his adversaries have come and accused him to his face, and there be given him place to defend himself against that of which he is accused.
B044C025V017	44	25	17	And when I had come hither, without delay, the day after I sat on the tribunal, and commanded to bring the man to me.
B044C025V018	44	25	18	And his accusers stood up with him, but could not find any evil accusation to prove against him, (such) as I had expected,
B044C025V019	44	25	19	but (had) various questions with him regarding their worship, and concerning Jeshu, a man who was dead, of whom Paulos said that he was alive.
B044C025V020	44	25	20	And because I stood not upon the investigation of these (matters), I said to Paulos, Dost thou require to go to Urishlem, and there be judged concerning these?
B044C025V021	44	25	21	But he required to be kept unto the judgment of Caesar; and I commanded that he should be kept until I may send him to Caesar.
B044C025V022	44	25	22	And Agripos said, I would hear this man. And Festos said, To-morrow thou shalt hear him.
B044C025V023	44	25	23	And the day after came Agripos and Bernike with great pomp, and entered the house of judgment, with the tribunes and the chiefs of the city. And Festos commanded, and Paulos came.
B044C025V024	44	25	24	And Festos said, King Agripos, and all men who are with us, concerning this man whom you see have all the people of the Jihudoyee taken me at Urishlem and here, crying, that This ought not further to live;
B044C025V025	44	25	25	but I perceived not that he had done any thing worthy of death. And because he required to be reserved for the judgment of Caesar, I have commanded that he should be sent.
B044C025V026	44	25	26	But (as) I know not what to write of him unto Caesar, therefore have I willed to bring him before you, and especially before thee, king Agripos, that, having inquired into his case, I may find what to write.
B044C025V027	44	25	27	For it is not fit when we send a man bound, not to record his transgression.
B044C026V001	44	26	1	And Agripos said to Paulos, It is permitted thee to speak for thyself. Then Paulos stretched forth his hand and made defence, and said,
B044C026V002	44	26	2	Of all that I am accused by the Jihudoyee, king Agripos, I consider myself happy, that before you I (have to) make defence.
B044C026V003	44	26	3	Especially because I know that you are conversant with all questions and laws of the Jihudoyee; therefore, I pray you with patient mind to hear me.
B044C026V004	44	26	4	For the Jihudoyee themselves-if they would testify-know my manners from my youth, which were mine from the beginning among my people at Urishlem;
B044C026V005	44	26	5	because they of a long time were assured of me, and they know that in the high doctrine of the Pharishee I lived.
B044C026V006	44	26	6	And now, concerning the hope of the promise that was made to our fathers by Aloha, stand I, and am judged.
B044C026V007	44	26	7	And for this hope (to which) our twelve tribes, with diligent prayers by day and night, are expecting to come, for this very hope am I accused by the Jihudoyee, king Agripos!
B044C026V008	44	26	8	What judge you; ought we not to believe that Aloha will raise the dead?
B044C026V009	44	26	9	For I, at the first, proposed in my mind to do many things against the name of Jeshu Natsroya.
B044C026V010	44	26	10	This I also did in Urishlem. And many holy ones I cast into the house of the bound, by the authority which I had received from the great priests; and when they were killed by them, I participated with those who condemned them.
B044C026V011	44	26	11	And in every synagogue I was furious against them, while I constrained them to blaspheme the name of Jeshu; and, being filled with great wrath against them, I went forth unto other cities also to persecute them.
B044C026V012	44	26	12	And while going on this account to Darmsuk, with authority and permission from the great priests,
B044C026V013	44	26	13	at the dividing of the day, in the way, I saw from heaven, O king, shining upon me and upon all who were with me, a light which (was) more excellent than the sun.
B044C026V014	44	26	14	And we fell all of us upon the earth; and I heard a voice that said to me in Hebrew, Shaol, Shaol, why persecutest thou me? It is hard to thee to kick against the pricks!
B044C026V015	44	26	15	And I said, Who art thou, my Lord? And he said, I am Jeshu Natsroya, whom thou persecutest.
B044C026V016	44	26	16	And he said to me, Stand upon thy feet, because for this I have appeared to thee, to appoint thee a minister and witness of that (for) which thou hast seen me, and (for) which thou shalt see me.
B044C026V017	44	26	17	And I will deliver thee from the people of the Jihudoyee, and from the other nations to whom I send thee,
B044C026V018	44	26	18	to open their eyes, that they may turn from darkness to light, and from the power of Satan unto Aloha, and receive the forgiveness of sins, and a lot with the saints through faith, which (is) in me.
B044C026V019	44	26	19	Wherefore, king Agripos, I withstood not with perversity the heavenly vision,
B044C026V020	44	26	20	but preached, at first to them who were in Darmsuk, and to them who were at Urishlem, and in all the districts of Jihud, and also to the Gentiles have I preached, that they should repent, and turn to Aloha, and do works worthy of repentance.
B044C026V021	44	26	21	And for these things the Jihudoyee seized me in the temple, and would have killed me;
B044C026V022	44	26	22	but Aloha hath helped me until this day; and, behold, I stand and testify to the small and to the great, yet nothing beyond Musha and the prophets do I speak, but those things which they said should come to pass;
B044C026V023	44	26	23	that the Meshiha should suffer, and should be the chief of the resurrection from the house of the dead, and should preach light to the people and to the nations.
B044C026V024	44	26	24	AND as Paulos was thus making defence, Festos cried with a high voice, Thou art mad, Paulos; much learning hath made thee mad!
B044C026V025	44	26	25	Paulos said to him, I am not mad, victorious Festos, but words of truth and righteousness I speak.
B044C026V026	44	26	26	And king Agripos also, especially, knoweth concerning these things; and therefore speak I with openness before him; because not one of these things I think have been hidden from him; for they were not done in secrecy.
B044C026V027	44	26	27	Believest thou, king Agripos, the prophets? I know that thou believest.
B044C026V028	44	26	28	King Agripos said to him, (Within) a little thou persuadest me to become a Christian.
B044C026V029	44	26	29	And Paulos said, I would from Aloha that in little and in much, not only thou, but also all who hear me to-day, were as I am, except these bonds.
B044C026V030	44	26	30	And the king arose, and the governor, and Bernike, and those who sat with them:
B044C026V031	44	26	31	and when they were removed thence they spake one with another, and said, Nothing that is worthy of death or of bonds hath this man done.
B044C026V032	44	26	32	And Agripos said to Festos, This man could have been dismissed, if he had not called the appeal of Caesar.
B044C027V001	44	27	1	And Festos commanded concerning him that he should be sent unto Caesar in Italia. And he delivered Paulos, and other prisoners with him, to a certain man, a centurion of the band of Sebaste, whose name was Julios.
B044C027V002	44	27	2	And when he would proceed, we went down to a ship which was from Adramantos the city, to go to the region of Asia. And Aristarkos, a Makedonoya who was of Thessalunike the city,
B044C027V003	44	27	3	entered the ship with us. And the day after we came to Tsaidon. And the centurion behaved with kindness towards Paulos, and permitted him to go to his friends and be refreshed.
B044C027V004	44	27	4	And from thence we voyaged; and because the winds were contrary we made a circuit unto Cypros.
B044C027V005	44	27	5	And we went through the sea of Cilicia and of Pamphulia, and came to Mura, a city of Lukia.
B044C027V006	44	27	6	And the centurion found there a ship from Aleksandria which was going to Italia, and he placed us in her.
B044C027V007	44	27	7	And because she sailed heavily, (after) many days we had scarce come over against Knidos the island, and as the wind did not permit us to go directly, we went round by Kreta against Salmona the city;
B044C027V008	44	27	8	and hardly voyaging we passing around it came to the place which is called the Fair Havens. AND it was nigh to the city named Lasia.
B044C027V009	44	27	9	And we were there much time, until the day when the day of the fast of the Jihudoyee had also passed, and there had become danger for one to voyage by sea. And Paulos counselled them
B044C027V010	44	27	10	and said, Men, I perceive that with distress and much loss we are to voyage, not only to the burden of the ship, but also to our own lives.
B044C027V011	44	27	11	But the centurion hearkened to the governor and to the lord of the ship rather than to the counsel of Paulos.
B044C027V012	44	27	12	And because that haven was not convenient to winter in, many of us desired to proceed thence, and if possible to come and winter in a certain harbour in Kreta, called Phoniks, and which looked to the south.
B044C027V013	44	27	13	And when the wind of the south blew, and we thought we could come as we desired, we sailed round Kreta.
B044C027V014	44	27	14	And after a little there came forth against us a blowing of the tempest which is called Tuphonikos Euroklidon;
B044C027V015	44	27	15	and the ship was carried away, and could not stand against the wind, and we gave her into its hand.
B044C027V016	44	27	16	And when we had passed a certain isle that is called Cyra; we could scarcely take up the boat.
B044C027V017	44	27	17	And when we had uplifted her, we girded and strengthened the ship. And because we feared lest we should fall into the precipitancy of the sea, we brought down the sails, and so went forward.i
B044C027V018	44	27	18	And while there rose against us the hard tempest, the next day we threw the goods into the sea.
B044C027V019	44	27	19	And the third day the things of the ship itself we cast forth. And when the storm had held more days,
B044C027V020	44	27	20	and neither the sun was seen, nor the moon, nor stars, the hope that we should be saved at all was cut off.
B044C027V021	44	27	21	And while no man had taken any food, then stood Paulos among them, and said, Men, if you had been persuaded by me, you would not have voyaged from Kreta, and we should have been exempted from loss, and from this distress.
B044C027V022	44	27	22	Yet now I counsel you to be without anxiety; for not one of you will perish, but the ship only.
B044C027V023	44	27	23	For in this night there appeared to me the angel of Aloha, (of) him whose I am, and whom I serve.
B044C027V024	44	27	24	And he said to me, Fear not, Paulos, for thou art to stand before Caesar; and, behold, Aloha hath given thee the gift of all who voyage with thee.
B044C027V025	44	27	25	Therefore, men, take courage; for I believe Aloha, that so it shall be as he hath told me.
B044C027V026	44	27	26	Nevertheless, upon a certain island we have to be cast.
B044C027V027	44	27	27	AND after fourteen days (in) which we had wandered and been beaten in the sea of Hadrios, in the dividing of the night, the mariners thought that we drew nigh to land.
B044C027V028	44	27	28	And they cast the lead, and found twenty cubits; and again a little they proceeded, and found fifteen cubits.
B044C027V029	44	27	29	And fearing lest we should be found in a place in which were rocks, they cast forth from the hinder part of the ship four anchors, and prayed that it would become day.
B044C027V030	44	27	30	But the mariners sought to escape from the ship, and lowered from her the boat into the sea, on the pretext that they would go in her, and bind the ship to the land.
B044C027V031	44	27	31	And when Paulos saw, he said to the centurion and to the soldiers, If these in the ship remain not, you cannot be saved.
B044C027V032	44	27	32	Then cut the soldiers the cable of the boat from the ship, and let her drive.
B044C027V033	44	27	33	But Paulos himself, until it was morning, persuaded all of them to take food, saying to them, To-day it is fourteen days (in which) from danger you have tasted nothing.
B044C027V034	44	27	34	Wherefore I beseech you receive meat for the establishment of your lives; for a hair of the head of one of you will not perish.
B044C027V035	44	27	35	And when these he had said, he took bread, and praised Aloha before them all, and he broke and began to eat.
B044C027V036	44	27	36	And they were all comforted, and received food.
B044C027V037	44	27	37	But we were in the ship two hundred and seventy and six souls.
B044C027V038	44	27	38	And when they were satisfied with food, they lightened the ship, and took up the wheat and sent it into the sea.
B044C027V039	44	27	39	And when it was day, the sailors knew not what land it was; but they saw along the coast a certain inlet of the sea, (into) which they purposed if possible to drive the ship.
B044C027V040	44	27	40	And they cut the anchors from the ship, and left them in the sea, and they loosed the bands of the oars, and raised a small sail to the wind which blew, and went forward to the face of the land.
B044C027V041	44	27	41	And the ship struck on a high place between two depths of the sea, and infixed herself in it; and her forepart stood upon it, and was immovable, but her afterpart was loosed from the violence of the waves.
B044C027V042	44	27	42	And the soldiers would have killed the prisoners, lest they should cast forth to swim, and escape from them;
B044C027V043	44	27	43	and the centurion restrained them from this, because he was willing to save Paulos. And those who could cast forth to swim he commanded to be the first to swim, and to pass to the land.
B044C027V044	44	27	44	And the rest, on boards, and on other timbers of the ship, passed; and thus all of them escaped to land.
B044C028V001	44	28	1	AND afterwards we learned that Melita was called that island.
B044C028V002	44	28	2	And the Barbaroyee who dwelt in it many kindnesses showed us. And they kindled a fire, and called all of us to warm, because there was great rain and cold.
B044C028V003	44	28	3	And Paulos took many sticks and placed upon the fire; and there came forth a viper from the heat of the fire, and bit (him) in his hand.
B044C028V004	44	28	4	And when the Barbaroyee saw it hang upon his hand, they said, Perhaps this man is a murderer, whom, though he is escaped from the sea, justice suffereth not to live.
B044C028V005	44	28	5	But Paulos shook his hand, and cast the viper into the fire, and nothing of evil befell him.
B044C028V006	44	28	6	But the Barbaroyee expected that he would immediately have swelled and fallen dead upon the ground; and when they had for a great while expected and saw that nothing of evil befell him, they changed their words, and said he was a god.
B044C028V007	44	28	7	But there were possessions in that place (belonging) to a certain man whose name was Publios, who himself was the chief of the island; and he cheerfully received us into his house three days.
B044C028V008	44	28	8	But the father of Publios was ill in a fever, and a disease of the bowels. And Paulos went in to him, and prayed and laid his hand on him, and healed him.
B044C028V009	44	28	9	And when this was done, the rest also of them who were diseased in the island came to him and were cured.
B044C028V010	44	28	10	And with great honours they honoured us; and when we went forth from thence they supplied us.
B044C028V011	44	28	11	But we went forth after three months and voyaged in an Alexandrine ship which had wintered at the island; and she had upon her the sign of the Twins.
B044C028V012	44	28	12	And we came to Sarakosa the city, and remained there three days.
B044C028V013	44	28	13	And from thence we went round and came to Regium the city. And after one day the south wind blew, and in two days we came to Putialos, a city of Italia.
B044C028V014	44	28	14	And we found there brethren, and they prayed of us, and we were with them seven days, and then went we unto Ruma.
B044C028V015	44	28	15	And when the brethren who were there heard, they came forth to meet us unto the street that is called Apios Foros, and unto the Three Taverns. And when Paulos saw them he thanked Aloha, and was strengthened.
B044C028V016	44	28	16	And we entered Ruma. And the centurion allowed Paulos to sojourn where he willed, with the soldier, him who guarded him.
B044C028V017	44	28	17	And after three days Paulos sent to convoke the principal men of the Jihudoyee; and when they were assembled, he said to them, Men, brethren, I, who in nothing have risen against the people, nor the law of our fathers, in bonds was delivered from Urishlem into the hands of the Rumoyee.
B044C028V018	44	28	18	And they who examined me willed to dismiss me, because they found not in me any fault worthy of death.
B044C028V019	44	28	19	And when the Jihudoyee had risen against me, I was constrained to call the appeal of Caesar; (yet) not as though I had in any thing to be the accuser of the sons of my people.
B044C028V020	44	28	20	Wherefore I have besought you to come, that I might see you, and declare to you these things; for on account of the hope of Israel am I bound with this chain.
B044C028V021	44	28	21	They said to him, We have not received letters concerning thee from Jihud, and none of the brethren who have come from Urishlem have spoken any thing evil of thee.
B044C028V022	44	28	22	But we are willing to hear from thee what it is that thou thinkest; for we know that this doctrine is by no man received.
B044C028V023	44	28	23	AND they appointed him a day; and many assembled and came where he sojourned; and he explained to them concerning the kingdom of Aloha, testifying and persuading them concerning Jeshu, from the law of Musha and from the prophets, from the morning until the evening.
B044C028V024	44	28	24	And some of them were persuaded by his words, and others were not persuaded.
B044C028V025	44	28	25	And they removed from him, while not agreeing together. And Paulos said to them this word, Well spake the Spirit of Holiness, by the mouth of Eshaia the prophet, against your fathers,
B044C028V026	44	28	26	saying, Go unto this people, and say unto them, Hearing, you will hear and will not understand. And you will see, but not discern:
B044C028V027	44	28	27	For stupified is the heart of this people, And their hearing they have made heavy, And their eyes have they closed, Lest they should see with their eyes, And hear with their ears, And understand with their hearts, And be turned unto me, and I should forgive them.
B044C028V028	44	28	28	Be this therefore known to you, that to the Gentiles is sent this redemption, for they will also hear it.
B044C028V030	44	28	30	And Paulos hired his own house, and was in it two years, and received there all those who came to him.
B044C028V031	44	28	31	And he preached concerning the kingdom of Aloha, and taught with confidence concerning our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, none forbidding.
B045C001V001	45	1	1	PAULOS, a servant of Jeshu Meshiha, called, and an apostle, who hath been separated unto the gospel of Aloha,
B045C001V002	45	1	2	which from of old he had promised by the hand of the prophets, in the holy writings,
B045C001V003	45	1	3	concerning his Son, who was born, according to the flesh, of the seed of the house of David,
B045C001V004	45	1	4	and is known (to be) the Son of Aloha by power, and by the Holy Spirit, who raised him from among the dead, Jeshu Meshiha our Lord:
B045C001V005	45	1	5	by whom we have received grace and apostleship among all nations, that they should become obedient unto the faith of his name:
B045C001V006	45	1	6	and you also are of them, called in Jeshu Meshiha:
B045C001V007	45	1	7	To all who are in Ruma, beloved of Aloha, called and saints; peace and grace be with you from Aloha our Father, and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C001V008	45	1	8	First, I praise my God through Jeshu Meshiha on behalf of you all, that your faith is heard (of) in all the world.
B045C001V009	45	1	9	For a witness unto me is Aloha, whom I serve in the spirit in the gospel of his Son, that without ceasing at all time I remember you in my prayers.
B045C001V010	45	1	10	And I pray that from now there may be opened unto me the way, by the will of Aloha, to come to you.
B045C001V011	45	1	11	For I greatly desire to see you, and to impart to you the gift of the Spirit,
B045C001V012	45	1	12	that thereby you may be established, and that together we may be comforted by your faith and mine.
B045C001V013	45	1	13	BUT I will that you know, my brethren, that many times I have willed to come to you, and have been hindered until this;
B045C001V014	45	1	14	that among you also I may have fruit as among the rest of the nations of the Javnoyee and Barbaroyee, the wise and the foolish,
B045C001V015	45	1	15	because to every man am I obligated to preach; and so am I urged to evangelize unto you also who are in Ruma.
B045C001V016	45	1	16	For I am not ashamed of the gospel, because it is the power of Aloha for the salvation of all who believe in him, whether of the Jihudoyee first, or of the Aramoyee:
B045C001V017	45	1	17	for the righteousness of Aloha in it is revealed from faith to faith, as it is written, The righteous by faith shall live.
B045C001V018	45	1	18	For the wrath of Aloha is revealed from heaven against all the unrighteousness and depravity of the sons of men, who the truth in unrighteousness detain.
B045C001V019	45	1	19	Because the knowledge of Aloha is revealed in them; for Aloha revealed it in them.
B045C001V020	45	1	20	For the occult things of Aloha from the foundations of the world, unto his creatures by intelligence are apparent, and his power and his Godhead eternal, that they may be without excuse.
B045C001V021	45	1	21	For when they knew Aloha, they did not as Aloha glorify him and praise him, but became vain in their imaginations, and their heart was darkened, that they understood not.
B045C001V022	45	1	22	And while thinking in themselves that they were wise, they were fools.
B045C001V023	45	1	23	And they changed the glory of Aloha the Incorruptible into the likeness of the image of corruptible man, and into the likeness of birds and of four-footed (beasts) and of reptiles of the earth.
B045C001V024	45	1	24	Because of this Aloha delivered them up to the unclean lusts of their hearts, that they would debase their bodies among them.
B045C001V025	45	1	25	And they changed the truth of Aloha into a lie, and worshipped and served the creatures rather than their Creator, to whom be praises and blessings for ever and ever. Amen.
B045C001V026	45	1	26	WHEREFORE Aloha delivered them up to passions of vileness: for their females changed the use of their nature, and to what is not natural were used.
B045C001V027	45	1	27	And also their males likewise left the natural use of their females, and were inflamed with concupiscence one with another, and male with male wrought shamefulness, and the just retribution for their perverseness in themselves received.
B045C001V028	45	1	28	And as they did not decide in themselves to know Aloha, so did Aloha cause them to be delivered up to a mind of vainness, and to do what is not fit;
B045C001V029	45	1	29	being filled with all wickedness, and uncleanness, and rancour, and malice, and rapacity, and envy, and murder, and contention, and deceit, and evil imaginings, and murmurings,
B045C001V030	45	1	30	and slanders, and hating of Aloha: vilifiers, inflated ones, boasters, inventors of evil things, mindless, disobedient to parents,
B045C001V031	45	1	31	(men) to whom a compact is nothing, and (who) neither love peace nor (have) mercy in them; who,
B045C001V032	45	1	32	knowing the judgment of Aloha, that they who these things do, unto death are condemned, (yet) not only do them, but also participate with those who do them.
B045C002V001	45	2	1	Wherefore thou hast no excuse, O man, who judgest thy neighbour; for in that for which thou judgest thy neighbour, thou condemnest thyself; for in those which thou judgest, thou also art conversant.
B045C002V002	45	2	2	AND we know what is the judgment of Aloha in truth against them who in these things converse.
B045C002V003	45	2	3	But thinkest thou, O man, who judgest them who in these converse, while thou also conversest in them, that thou wilt escape the judgment of Aloha?
B045C002V004	45	2	4	Or upon the riches of his goodness, and upon his long-suffering, and upon the space he giveth thee, presumest thou? and knowest not that the goodness of Aloha unto repentance leadeth thee?
B045C002V005	45	2	5	Yet, through the hardness of thy unrepenting heart, layest thou up the treasure of wrath for the day of wrath, and the revelation of the just judgment of Aloha,
B045C002V006	45	2	6	who rendereth to every man according to his works.
B045C002V007	45	2	7	To them who seek, in perseverance of good works, glory and honour and incorruption, he giveth eternal life;
B045C002V008	45	2	8	but to them who are rebellious, and obey not the truth, but unrighteousness obey, he will render wrath and indignation
B045C002V009	45	2	9	and affliction and distress, upon every man who worketh evils; to Jihudoyee first, and to Aramoyee;
B045C002V010	45	2	10	but glory and honour and peace to every one who worketh good, to the Jihudoya first, and also to the Aramoya;
B045C002V011	45	2	11	for there is no acceptance of faces with Aloha.
B045C002V012	45	2	12	For they who without the law have sinned, without the law also will perish: and they who in the law have sinned, by the law will be judged.
B045C002V013	45	2	13	For not the hearers of the law are righteous before Aloha, but the doers of the law are justified.
B045C002V014	45	2	14	FOR if the Gentiles, who have not the law, from their nature shall perform the law, these, while not having the law, unto themselves become a law.
B045C002V015	45	2	15	And these show the work of law written upon their hearts, and their conscience testifieth of them, while their reasonings accuse or excuse one another;
B045C002V016	45	2	16	in the day when Aloha judgeth the secrets of men according to my gospel by Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C002V017	45	2	17	But if thou (who) a Jihudoya art called, and reposest on the law, and boastest in Aloha,
B045C002V018	45	2	18	because thou knowest his will, and distinguishest the things that are fitting, because thou art learned from the law;
B045C002V019	45	2	19	and confidest upon thyself that thou art a guide of the blind, and a light to those who are in darkness,
B045C002V020	45	2	20	and an instructor of the wanting-in-mind, and a teacher of children, and hast a type of knowledge and of truth in the law:
B045C002V021	45	2	21	Thou, then, who teachest others, dost thou not teach thyself? and who preachest that men should not steal, dost thou steal?
B045C002V022	45	2	22	and who sayest they should not commit adultery, dost thou commit adultery? And thou who condemnest idols, dost thou despoil the sanctuary?
B045C002V023	45	2	23	And thou who boastest of the law, in this that thou transgressest against the law, Aloha himself despisest thou?
B045C002V024	45	2	24	For the name of Aloha through you is blasphemed among the Gentiles, as it is written.
B045C002V025	45	2	25	For circumcision profiteth, if thou accomplish the law; but if thou transgress the law, thy circumcision is become uncircumcisedness.
B045C002V026	45	2	26	But if the uncircumcision shall keep the commandment of the law, is not uncircumcisedness reckoned to him (as) circumcision?
B045C002V027	45	2	27	And the uncircumcision, who by nature accomplishes the law will judge thee, who with the scripture and with circumcision, transgressest against the law.
B045C002V028	45	2	28	FOR it is not in outwardness that he is a Jihudoya nor is that which is seen in the flesh circumcision:
B045C002V029	45	2	29	but he is a Jihudoya who is one in inwardness; and circumcision is that which is of the heart, in the spirit, and not in the letter; whose praise is not from the sons of men, but from Aloha.
B045C003V001	45	3	1	What then is the excellence of the Jihudoya, and what the profit of circumcision?
B045C003V002	45	3	2	Much in every thing: primarily that they had intrusted (to them) the words of Aloha.
B045C003V003	45	3	3	For if some of them believed not, would their unbelief abolish the faithfulness of Aloha?
B045C003V004	45	3	4	Not so: for Aloha is true, and every man a liar; as it is written, That thou mayest be just in thy words, And triumph when they judge thee.
B045C003V005	45	3	5	But if our iniquity the righteousness of Aloha establisheth, what shall we say? Is Aloha evil, who bringeth his wrath? As a man do I speak.
B045C003V006	45	3	6	Not so; otherwise how shall Aloha judge the world?
B045C003V007	45	3	7	For if the truth of Aloha is promoted by my lie unto his glory, why then am I judged as a sinner?
B045C003V008	45	3	8	Or why, as certain blaspheme concerning us, affirming that we say, Let us do evil, that good may come? they, whose condemnation is reserved by justice.
B045C003V009	45	3	9	What then, have we attained excellence? (No.) For before we decided of the Jihudoyee and of the Aramoyee that they are all under sin;
B045C003V010	45	3	10	as it is written, None is righteous, not one.
B045C003V011	45	3	11	None understandeth or seeketh Aloha.
B045C003V012	45	3	12	All have declined together and are reprobate, And there is none that doeth good, not one.
B045C003V013	45	3	13	Open sepulchres are their throats, Their tongues have deceived, And the venom of asps is under their lips.
B045C003V014	45	3	14	Their mouth is full of cursing and bitterness,
B045C003V015	45	3	15	And their feet are swift to shed blood.
B045C003V016	45	3	16	Crushing and misery are in their ways;
B045C003V017	45	3	17	And the way of peace they have not known;
B045C003V018	45	3	18	And the fear of Aloha is not before their eyes.
B045C003V019	45	3	19	BUT we know that whatever the law saith, to them who are under the law it saith: that every mouth may be shut, and all the world be guilty unto Aloha.
B045C003V020	45	3	20	Because by the works of the law no flesh is justified before him; for from the law sin is known.
B045C003V021	45	3	21	But now, without the law the righteousness of Aloha is revealed, and the law and the prophets (themselves) testify of it.
B045C003V022	45	3	22	But the righteousness of Aloha is by faith of Jeshu Meshiha, unto all and also upon all who believe in him. For there is no distinction:
B045C003V023	45	3	23	for all have sinned, and have failed of the glory of Aloha;
B045C003V024	45	3	24	and all are justified by grace freely, and (that) through the redemption which is in Jeshu Meshiha,
B045C003V025	45	3	25	whom Aloha before ordained (to be) a propitiation through faith in his blood for our sins which from the first we had sinned, within the space which Aloha hath given to us in his patience,
B045C003V026	45	3	26	unto the manifestation of his righteousness which (is) in this time: that he might be just, and might justify in righteousness him who is in the faith of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C003V027	45	3	27	Where, then, is boasting? It is abolished. By what law? of works? No, but by the law of faith.
B045C003V028	45	3	28	We comprehend, therefore, that by faith man is justified, and not by the works of the law.
B045C003V029	45	3	29	Is Aloha of the Jihudoyee only, and not of the Gentiles? Yes, of the Gentiles also
B045C003V030	45	3	30	Because one is Aloha, who justifieth the circumcision by faith, also the uncircumcision by the same faith.
B045C003V031	45	3	31	Do we therefore the law abolish by faith? Not so, but the law itself we establish.
B045C004V001	45	4	1	What then say we of Abraham, the chief of the fathers, that he found in the flesh?
B045C004V002	45	4	2	For if Abraham by works was justified, he had cause for boasting; but not with Aloha.
B045C004V003	45	4	3	For what saith the scripture? That Abraham believed Aloha, and he reckoned it to him for righteousness.
B045C004V004	45	4	4	But to him who worketh, his wages are not reckoned to him as of favour, but as that which is owing to him:
B045C004V005	45	4	5	but to him who worketh not, but believeth only in him who justifieth sinners, his faith is reckoned to him for righteousness.
B045C004V006	45	4	6	As also David hath spoken concerning the blessedness of the man to whom Aloha reckoneth righteousness without works, saying,
B045C004V007	45	4	7	Blessed are they whose iniquity is forgiven, And whose sins are covered.
B045C004V008	45	4	8	Blessed is the man to whom Aloha reckoneth not his sin.
B045C004V009	45	4	9	Is this blessedness, then, upon the circumcision (only), or upon the uncircumcision (also)? Now we have said, that his faith was reckoned to Abraham for righteousness.
B045C004V010	45	4	10	When, then, was it reckoned to him? In circumcision or in uncircumcision? It was not in circumcision, but in uncircumcision.
B045C004V011	45	4	11	For he received the sign of circumcision (as) a seal of the righteousness of his faith, which (was his) in uncircumcision, that he should be the father of all them who believe of the uncircumcision; that it might be accounted also to them for righteousness:
B045C004V012	45	4	12	and the father of the circumcision, not of them who are of the circumcision only, but of them who pursue the footsteps of the faith of uncircumcision of our father Abraham.
B045C004V013	45	4	13	FOR not through the law was the promise unto Abraham and to his seed that he should be the heir of the world, but through the righteousness of faith.
B045C004V014	45	4	14	For if they who are of the law were heirs, faith would be vain, and the promise be abolished.
B045C004V015	45	4	15	For the law is the worker of wrath. For where there is no law, there also is no transgression of the law.
B045C004V016	45	4	16	Therefore it is by faith, which is through grace, that we are justified, that the promise might be firm unto all his seed; not to that which is of the law only, but also to that which is of the faith of Abraham, who is the father of us all:
B045C004V017	45	4	17	(as it is written, I have ordained thee the father of many nations before Aloha, in whom thou hast believed, who maketh alive the dead, and calleth those who are not as though they were:)
B045C004V018	45	4	18	and who, without hope, unto hope believed that he should be the father of many nations, as it is written, that " so shall be thy seed."
B045C004V019	45	4	19	Nor was he weak in his faith, while considering his body dead, (for he was the son of an hundred years,) and the dead womb of Sara;
B045C004V020	45	4	20	and at the promise of Aloha he wavered not as deficient in faith, but was strong in faith, and gave glory to Aloha;
B045C004V021	45	4	21	and was sure that what he had promised to him Aloha could fulfil.
B045C004V022	45	4	22	Wherefore it was reckoned to him for righteousness.
B045C004V023	45	4	23	And not for his sake only was this written, that his faith was reckoned for righteousness,
B045C004V024	45	4	24	but for our sake, because it should be reckoned to us also who believe in Him who hath raised our Lord Jeshu Meshiha from among the dead;
B045C004V025	45	4	25	who was delivered for our sins, and rose that he might justify us.
B045C005V001	45	5	1	BECAUSE, then, we are justified by faith, we have peace with Aloha through our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C005V002	45	5	2	And by him we have been admitted through faith into this grace in which we stand, and exult in hope of the glory of Aloha.
B045C005V003	45	5	3	And not thus only, but also in afflictions we exult; for we know that affliction perfecteth patience in us,
B045C005V004	45	5	4	and patience experience, and experience hope:
B045C005V005	45	5	5	but hope maketh us not ashamed, because the love of Aloha is shed forth upon our hearts by the Spirit of Holiness who is given to us.
B045C005V006	45	5	6	But if the Meshiha on account of our infirmity in this time for the wicked hath died:
B045C005V007	45	5	7	for hardly for the wicked one dieth; for on account of the good one may perhaps dare to die.
B045C005V008	45	5	8	Nevertheless Aloha hath manifested his love for us, in that, when we were sinners, the Meshiha for us died:
B045C005V009	45	5	9	how much more, then, shall we be now justified through his blood, and by him be delivered from wrath?
B045C005V010	45	5	10	For if, while we were adversaries, Aloha was reconciled with us through the death of his Son, how much more, then, in reconciliation with him, shall we be saved by his life?
B045C005V011	45	5	11	And not thus only, but we also exult in Aloha through our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, by whom we have now received the reconciliation.
B045C005V012	45	5	12	As by one man sin entered into the world, and by sin death, so death hath passed upon all men through this, that all have sinned.
B045C005V013	45	5	13	For until the law, sin, while it was in the world, was not reckoned sin, because the law was not;
B045C005V014	45	5	14	yet death reigned from Adam until Musha on them also who had not sinned after the manner of the transgression of the law of Adam, who was the type of him who was to be.
B045C005V015	45	5	15	But not as was the fall, so is the gift; for if, on account of the fall of one, many died, how much more the grace of Aloha, and his gift, for the sake of one man, Jeshu Meshiha, in many will abound?
B045C005V016	45	5	16	And not as the transgression of one, so is the gift; for the judgment that was by one was unto condemnation, but the gift (which saves) from many sins was unto righteousness.
B045C005V017	45	5	17	For if because of the transgression of one death was made to reign, much more (shall) they who receive the abundance of the grace and of the gift and of righteousness, reign in life by one, Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C005V018	45	5	18	As then on account of the transgression of one was the condemnation of all men, so, on account of the righteousness of one shall there be acquittal unto the life of all men.
B045C005V019	45	5	19	For as on account of the disobedience of one man many became sinners, so also on account of the obedience of one many became righteous.
B045C005V020	45	5	20	But the entrance which was of the law, (made) sin to increase; and where sin increased, there grace hath abounded:
B045C005V021	45	5	21	that as sin hath reigned in death, so grace might reign in righteousness unto the life which is eternal, by the hand of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C006V001	45	6	1	WHAT, then, shall we say, Let us remain in sin, that grace may abound?
B045C006V002	45	6	2	Not so. For how shall they who are dead to sin live yet in it?
B045C006V003	45	6	3	Or do you not know, that they who have been baptized into Jeshu Meshiha, into his death have been baptized?
B045C006V004	45	6	4	For we are buried with him by baptism into death; that as Jeshu Meshiha arose from among the dead by the glory of his Father, so also we in a new life shall walk.
B045C006V005	45	6	5	For if together we have been planted with him in the likeness of his death, so also in his resurrection shall we be.
B045C006V006	45	6	6	For we know that our old man is crucified with him, that the body of sin might be abolished, that more we should not serve sin.
B045C006V007	45	6	7	For he who is dead is set free from sin.
B045C006V008	45	6	8	If then we are dead with the Meshiha, we believe that with him, with the Meshiha, we shall live:
B045C006V009	45	6	9	for we know that the Meshiha rose from among the dead, and no more dieth, nor hath death dominion over him.
B045C006V010	45	6	10	For he who died on account of sin died once, and he who liveth liveth unto Aloha;
B045C006V011	45	6	11	so also reckon yourselves to be dead unto sin, and alive unto Aloha by our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C006V012	45	6	12	Let not sin then reign in your dead body, as that you may obey the lusts of it:
B045C006V013	45	6	13	nor prepare your members the instruments of iniquity unto sin, but prepare yourselves for Aloha, as men who from the dead have been made alive, and your members instruments to be for the righteousness of Aloha.
B045C006V014	45	6	14	For sin shall not rule over you; for you are not under law, but under grace.
B045C006V015	45	6	15	What, then, shall we sin, because we are not under law, but under grace? Not so.
B045C006V016	45	6	16	Know you not, that to whomsoever you prepare yourselves to obey him unto service, of him you are the servants, of him whom you obey; whether of sin, or of the hearing of the ear of righteousness?
B045C006V017	45	6	17	But praise to Aloha that you were the servants of sin, but have obeyed from the heart the form of doctrine to which you have been delivered.
B045C006V018	45	6	18	And when you were made free from sin, you became obedient to righteousness.
B045C006V019	45	6	19	As among men I speak, because of the infirmity of your flesh, that as you have prepared your members for the service of uncleanness and of iniquity, so also now prepare ye your members for the service of righteousness and of holiness.
B045C006V020	45	6	20	For when you were the servants of sin, you were free from righteousness.
B045C006V021	45	6	21	And what product had you then from that of which to-day you are ashamed? For the end of it is death.
B045C006V022	45	6	22	And now made free from sin, and become servants to Aloha, you have holy fruits, of which the end is the life of eternity.
B045C006V023	45	6	23	For the wages of sin is death; and the gift of Aloha the life of eternity by our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C007V001	45	7	1	BUT know you not, my brethren, for to those who know the law I speak, that the law has authority over a man as long as he liveth?
B045C007V002	45	7	2	as a woman who is bound in law to her husband as long as he liveth; but if her husband be dead, she is freed from the law of her husband.
B045C007V003	45	7	3	But if, while her husband lives, she adhere to another man, she becometh an adulteress; but if her husband shall die, she is freed from the law, and is not an adulteress, though she become (the wife) of another man.
B045C007V004	45	7	4	And now, my brethren, you also are dead to the law, through the body of the Meshiha, that you should be married to another, (namely, to) him who rose from the dead, that you may render fruit unto Aloha.
B045C007V005	45	7	5	For while we were in the flesh, the affections of sin, which are against the law, wrought powerfully in our members to yield fruits unto death;
B045C007V006	45	7	6	but now we are loosed from the law, and are dead to that which held us, that we might serve henceforth in the newness of the spirit, and not in the oldness of the writing.
B045C007V007	45	7	7	What then, say we the law is sin? Not so. But sin I had not learned (to know) but by the law: for I had not known concupiscence (to be sinful), but (by) the law, which hath said, Thou shalt not covet.
B045C007V008	45	7	8	And by this commandment sin found for itself an occasion, and completed in me all concupiscence. For without the law sin was dead.
B045C007V009	45	7	9	But I was alive without the law formerly: but when the commandment came, sin lived, and I died.
B045C007V010	45	7	10	And that commandment of life was found to me (to tend) unto death.
B045C007V011	45	7	11	For sin, by the occasion it found through the commandment, deceived me, and thereby killed me.
B045C007V012	45	7	12	The law therefore is holy, and the commandment holy, and just, and good.
B045C007V013	45	7	13	The good, then, unto me, unto death was made? Not so. But sin, that it might be seen what sin is, by the good (law) effected death in me, that sin might be the more condemned by the commandment.
B045C007V014	45	7	14	For we know that the law is spiritual; but I am carnal, and sold unto sin.
B045C007V015	45	7	15	For what I work, I know not; and not that which I will, I do; but what I hate, that I do.
B045C007V016	45	7	16	And if the thing that I would not, I do, I witness of the law that it is good.
B045C007V017	45	7	17	But now it is not I who work this, but sin which dwelleth in me.
B045C007V018	45	7	18	For I know that in me, but that is in my flesh, good dwelleth not; because to will the good is easy to me, but to perform it I find not.
B045C007V019	45	7	19	For the good that I will to do, I do not; but the evil that I will not to do, that do I.
B045C007V020	45	7	20	And if the thing that I will not I do, it is not I who do it, but sin which dwelleth in me.
B045C007V021	45	7	21	I find then a law which accordeth with my mind, that willeth to do good, because evil is near to me.
B045C007V022	45	7	22	For I rejoice in the law of Aloha in the interior man;
B045C007V023	45	7	23	but I see another law in my members, which warreth against the law of my mind, making me captive to the law of sin that is in my members.
B045C007V025	45	7	25	I give thanks to Aloha! (it is) by the hand of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha. Now then, I in my mind am the servant of the law of Aloha, but in my flesh I am the servant of the law of sin.
B045C008V001	45	8	1	Hence, there is no condemnation to them who do not walk according to the flesh, in Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C008V002	45	8	2	For the law of the Spirit of life, which is in Jeshu Meshiha, hath set thee free from the law of sin and of death.
B045C008V003	45	8	3	Because the law was weak through the infirmity of the flesh, Aloha sent his Son in the likeness of the flesh of sin, on account of sin to condemn sin in his flesh;
B045C008V004	45	8	4	that the righteousness of the law might in us be fulfilled, who walk not in the flesh, but in the Spirit.
B045C008V005	45	8	5	For they who are in the flesh, of that flesh are mindful; and they who are of the Spirit, of that Spirit are mindful.
B045C008V006	45	8	6	For the mind of the flesh is death, and the mind of the Spirit life and peace.
B045C008V007	45	8	7	Because the mind of the flesh is enmity towards Aloha; for to the law of Aloha it is not subject, for it cannot be;
B045C008V008	45	8	8	and they who are in the flesh cannot please Aloha.
B045C008V009	45	8	9	But you are not in the flesh, but in the Spirit, if truly the Spirit of Aloha dwelleth in you. But if a man have not the Spirit of the Meshiha, this (man) is not his.
B045C008V010	45	8	10	And if the Meshiha be in you, the body is dead because of sin; but the Spirit is life because of righteousness.
B045C008V011	45	8	11	And if the Spirit of him who raised our Lord Jeshu Meshiha from among the dead dwell in you, he who raised our Lord Jeshu Meshiha from among the dead will also make alive your dead bodies, on account of his Spirit who dwelleth in you.
B045C008V012	45	8	12	Now, my brethren, we are debtors, not to the flesh, that according to the flesh we should walk.
B045C008V013	45	8	13	For if after the flesh you live, you must die: but if, after the Spirit, the habitudes of the body you mortify, you live.
B045C008V014	45	8	14	For they who by the Spirit of Aloha are led, they are the sons of Aloha.
B045C008V015	45	8	15	For we have not received the spirit of servitude again unto fear, but we have received the Spirit of the adoption of sons, by whom we cry, Father, our Father!
B045C008V016	45	8	16	And the Spirit himself witnesseth with our spirit, that we are the sons of Aloha.
B045C008V017	45	8	17	And if sons, heirs also; heirs of Aloha, and the sons of the inheritance of Jeshu Meshiha. For if we suffer with him, with him also shall we be glorified.
B045C008V018	45	8	18	For I consider that the sufferings of this time are not equal to that glory which is to be revealed in us.
B045C008V019	45	8	19	For the whole creation hopeth and waiteth for the manifestation of the sons of Aloha.
B045C008V020	45	8	20	For the creation hath been subjected to vanity, not willingly, but on account of him who subjected her, upon the hope
B045C008V021	45	8	21	that the creation herself also shall be made free from the servitude of corruption into the liberty of the glory of the sons of Aloha.
B045C008V022	45	8	22	For we know that all creatures groan and travail until this day;
B045C008V023	45	8	23	and not only they, but we also who have in us the first-fruit of the Spirit, groan within ourselves, and wait for the adoption, the redemption of our bodies.
B045C008V024	45	8	24	For in hope we live: but hope that is seen is not hope; for if we see it, why hope we for it?
B045C008V025	45	8	25	But if we hope for that which is not seen, in patience we wait.
B045C008V026	45	8	26	So also the Spirit helpeth our infirmity: for what to pray for as we ought we know not; but the Spirit himself prayeth on our behalf in groanings unspoken.
B045C008V027	45	8	27	But he who searcheth the hearts, he knoweth the mind of the Spirit, who, according to the will of Aloha, prayeth for the saints.
B045C008V028	45	8	28	BUT we know that those who love Aloha, in every thing he helpeth them for good; them whom he set before that they might be called.
B045C008V029	45	8	29	And from the first he knew them, and signified them in the likeness of the image of his Son, that he might be the first-born of many brethren.
B045C008V030	45	8	30	But whom he before signified, them he called; and whom he called, them he justified; and whom he justified, them he glorified.
B045C008V031	45	8	31	What then shall we say of these? If Aloha be for us, who is against us?
B045C008V032	45	8	32	And if his Son be spared not, but for all of us delivered him up, how will he not with him give us all things?
B045C008V033	45	8	33	Who is against the chosen of Aloha? Aloha justifieth.
B045C008V034	45	8	34	Who condemneth? The Meshiha hath died and arisen, and is at the right hand of Aloha, and prayeth for us.
B045C008V035	45	8	35	Who shall separate us from the love of Meshiha? Affliction, or sorrow, or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or peril, or the sword?
B045C008V036	45	8	36	As it is written: For thee all the day long are we killed, We are reckoned as sheep for the slaughter.
B045C008V037	45	8	37	But in these we all are victorious by the hand of him who hath loved us.
B045C008V038	45	8	38	For I am persuaded that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor authorities, nor powers, nor things subsisting, nor things to come,
B045C008V039	45	8	39	nor height, nor depth, nor any other creature, shall be able to separate me from the love of Aloha which is in our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C009V001	45	9	1	I say the truth in Meshiha, and lie not; my conscience witnesseth for me in the Spirit of Holiness,
B045C009V002	45	9	2	that I have great grief, and (that) the sorrow of my heart ceaseth not.
B045C009V003	45	9	3	For I could pray that I myself might be one accursed from Meshiha instead of my brethren and my kinsmen who are in the flesh;
B045C009V004	45	9	4	who are the sons of Israel, and whose was the adoption of sons, and the glory, and the covenants, and the law, and the ministry, and the promises,
B045C009V005	45	9	5	and the fathers; and from whom appeared the Meshiha in the flesh, who is Aloha over all: his be praises and benedictions to the age of ages. Amen.
B045C009V006	45	9	6	FOR the word of Aloha hath not really fallen: for not all who are of Israel are Israel;
B045C009V007	45	9	7	neither also are they who are of the seed of Abraham all children; because it was said, In Ishok shall be called unto thee the seed:
B045C009V008	45	9	8	but that is, the children of the flesh are not the children of Aloha, but the children of the promise are reckoned the seed.
B045C009V009	45	9	9	For the promise is this word, In this time I will come, and a son shall be unto Sara.
B045C009V010	45	9	10	And not this only, but also Raphka when with one, our father Ishok, she had association,
B045C009V011	45	9	11	before her sons were born, and had not wrought good or evil, the (choice) of Aloha was (made) known before that it should remain: not by works, but by him who called:
B045C009V012	45	9	12	for it was said, The elder shall be servant to the less;
B045C009V013	45	9	13	as it is written, Jakub have I loved, and Isu have I hated.
B045C009V014	45	9	14	What then say we? Is there iniquity with Aloha? Not so:
B045C009V015	45	9	15	behold, also, he said unto Musha, I will have mercy upon whom I will have mercy, and I will be gracious to whom I will be gracious.
B045C009V016	45	9	16	Therefore it is not by him who willeth, nor by him who runneth, but by Aloha the Merciful.
B045C009V017	45	9	17	For it is said in the scripture to Pherun, For this I have raised thee up, that I might show in thee my power, and that my name might be proclaimed in all the earth.
B045C009V018	45	9	18	Then upon whom he willeth he is merciful, and whom he willeth he hardeneth.
B045C009V019	45	9	19	Perhaps thou wilt say, Of what then doth he complain; for who shall arise against his will?
B045C009V020	45	9	20	Who then art thou, O man, who givest answer against Aloha? Will the mass say to him who formeth it, Why thus hast thou formed me?
B045C009V021	45	9	21	Or, hath not the potter power over his clay, that from the (same) mass he might make vessels, the one to honour, and the other to vileness?
B045C009V022	45	9	22	BUT if Aloha, willing to reveal his wrath, and to make known his power, in his much patience bore with the vessels of wrath who were perfected for destruction,
B045C009V023	45	9	23	and poured his mercy upon the vessels of mercy who were prepared of Aloha for glory,
B045C009V024	45	9	24	who are we, (ourselves) the called, not only of the Jihudoyee, but also of the Gentiles:
B045C009V025	45	9	25	so also in Husha he said, I will call them my people who were not my people, and on those on whom I was not merciful, will I be merciful:
B045C009V026	45	9	26	for it shall be in the place where they were not called my people, there shall they be called the children of Aloha the Living.
B045C009V027	45	9	27	But Eshaia proclaims of the sons of Israel: Though the number of the sons of Israel were as the sand which is on the sea, the residue of them shall be saved.
B045C009V028	45	9	28	The Lord hath decreed and determined the word, and will perform it upon the earth.
B045C009V029	45	9	29	And as that which Eshaia had said before: Unless the Lord of sebaoth had left to us a residue, as Sedum should we have been, and to Amura have been likened.
B045C009V030	45	9	30	WHAT then shall we say? That the Gentiles who have not followed after righteousness have attained righteousness, but that righteousness which is of faith:
B045C009V031	45	9	31	but Israel, who followed after the law of righteousness, unto the law of righteousness have not attained.
B045C009V032	45	9	32	For why? Because it was not by faith, but by the works of the law: for they stumbled at the stone of stumbling;
B045C009V033	45	9	33	as it is written, Behold, I lay in Zion a stone of stumbling And a rock of offence; And whosoever in him shall believe Shall not be ashamed.
B045C010V001	45	10	1	My brethren, (it is) the wish of my heart, and my prayer to Aloha concerning them, that they may be saved.
B045C010V002	45	10	2	For I testify of them that they have zeal for Aloha, but not in knowledge.
B045C010V003	45	10	3	But the righteousness of Aloha they know not, but seek the righteousness of themselves to establish, and on this account to the righteousness of Aloha they have not become subject.
B045C010V004	45	10	4	For the end of the law is the Meshiha unto righteousness in all who believe in him.
B045C010V005	45	10	5	FOR Musha thus describeth the righteousness which is of the law, that he who doeth these things shall live by them.
B045C010V006	45	10	6	But the righteousness which is by faith thus speaketh, Say not in thy heart, Who shall ascend into heaven, And bring down the Meshiha?
B045C010V007	45	10	7	And who shall descend into the deep of Sheul, And bring up the Meshiha from among the dead?
B045C010V008	45	10	8	But what saith it? Nigh thee is the word of thy mouth and of thy heart: that is, the word of faith, which we preach.
B045C010V009	45	10	9	And if thou wilt confess with thy mouth our Lord Jeshu, and wilt believe with thy heart that Aloha hath raised him from among the dead, thou shalt be saved.
B045C010V010	45	10	10	For the heart which believeth in him is justified, and the mouth which confesseth him is saved.
B045C010V011	45	10	11	For the scripture saith, that every one who believeth in him shall not be ashamed.
B045C010V012	45	10	12	And in this he hath not distinguished nor the Jihudoya nor the Aramoya; for one is the Lord of them all, who is rich toward every one who calleth on him.
B045C010V013	45	10	13	For every one who shall invoke the name of the Lord shall be saved.
B045C010V014	45	10	14	How then shall they invoke him in whom they have not believed? Or how shall they believe in him of whom they have not heard? Or how shall they hear without a preacher?
B045C010V015	45	10	15	Or how shall they preach if they are not sent? As it is written, How beautiful the feet of them who evangelize peace, And who evangelize good things!
B045C010V016	45	10	16	But all of them have not obeyed the preaching of the gospel: for Eshaia saith, My Lord, who hath believed our voice?
B045C010V017	45	10	17	Therefore faith is from the hearing of the ear, and the hearing of the ear from the word of Aloha.
B045C010V018	45	10	18	But I say, Have they not heard? Behold, in all the earth their voice hath gone forth, And to the ends of the world their words!
B045C010V019	45	10	19	But I say, Hath not Israel known? First, Musha thus speaketh, I will provoke you by a people who is not a people. And by the disobedient people will I make you angry.
B045C010V020	45	10	20	But Eshaia is bold, and saith, I am beheld by them who have not sought me, And found of them who for me have not inquired.
B045C010V021	45	10	21	But of Israel he saith, I have stretched out my hands all the day To a contentious and disobedient people.
B045C011V001	45	11	1	BUT I say, Hath Aloha put away his people? Not so. For I also am of Israel, of the seed of Abraham, of the tribe of Benyamen.
B045C011V002	45	11	2	Aloha hath not put away his people whom from before he knew. Or know you not what he saith in the scripture concerning Elia,
B045C011V003	45	11	3	when he cried unto Aloha against Israel, saying, My Lord, thy prophets have they killed, and thy altars overthrown, and I alone am left, and they seek my soul?
B045C011V004	45	11	4	And it was said to him by revelation, Behold, I have left to myself seven thousand men, who upon their knees have not kneeled nor worshipped Baal.
B045C011V005	45	11	5	So also, at this time, a residue is left by the election of grace.
B045C011V006	45	11	6	But if by grace, it is not of works; otherwise grace is not grace. But if by works, it is not of grace; otherwise work is not work.
B045C011V007	45	11	7	What then, That which Israel sought he hath not found; but the election hath found: but the rest of them are blinded in their hearts.
B045C011V008	45	11	8	As it is written, Aloha hath given them the spirit of trouble, And eyes that see not, and ears that hear not, until the present day.
B045C011V009	45	11	9	And David again saith, Let their table become a snare before them, And their reward be for a stumbling-block:
B045C011V010	45	11	10	Let their eyes be darkened, that they may not see, And their back at all times be bowed;
B045C011V011	45	11	11	But I say, Have they stumbled so as to fall? Not so: but, by their stumbling was salvation to the Gentiles, unto their zeal.
B045C011V012	45	11	12	And if their stumbling were wealth to the world, and their condemnation wealth to the Gentiles, how much then will their fulness be?
B045C011V013	45	11	13	To you, Gentiles, I speak, I, who am apostle of the Gentiles, in my ministry I glory,
B045C011V014	45	11	14	if I may provoke my fleshly kindred, and save some of them.
B045C011V015	45	11	15	For if their rejection was the reconciliation of the world, what (will) their conversion (be) but life from the dead?
B045C011V016	45	11	16	For if the first-fruits be holy, (so) also (will be) the mass; and if the root be holy, (so) also the branches.
B045C011V017	45	11	17	And if the branches were cut off, and thou who art a wild olive art engrafted in their place, and hast a participation of the root and fatness of the olive,
B045C011V018	45	11	18	boast not against the branches: but if thou boast, thou bearest not the root, but the root beareth thee.
B045C011V019	45	11	19	And perhaps thou wilt say, The branches were cut off, and I in their place am engrafted:
B045C011V020	45	11	20	Well, they on account of unbelief were cut off, and thou by faith standest: be not exalted in thy mind, but fear.
B045C011V021	45	11	21	If Aloha spared not them who were branches by nature, (take heed) lest he spare not thee.
B045C011V022	45	11	22	Behold, then, the goodness and the severity of Aloha: towards them who fell, severity; but towards thee, goodness, if thou continue in his goodness; if not, thou also wilt be cut off.
B045C011V023	45	11	23	And they, if they continue not in their want of faith, they also shall be engrafted; for Aloha is able again to engraft them.
B045C011V024	45	11	24	For if thou who art of the wild olive which is thy nature, wast cut off, and, which was not thy nature, art engrafted into the good olive, how much more they, if they are engrafted into the olive of their nature?
B045C011V025	45	11	25	But I would have you know, my brethren, this mystery, that you may not be wise in your own mind,-that blindness of heart for a little space is unto Israel until the fulness of the Gentiles be brought in:
B045C011V026	45	11	26	and then all Israel shall be saved. As it is written, The Redeemer shall come from Sion, And turn iniquity from Jakub;
B045C011V027	45	11	27	And then shall be to them my covenant, When I have forgiven them their sins.
B045C011V028	45	11	28	But, in (regard of) the gospel, they are enemies on your account; and, in the election, they are beloved on account of the fathers.
B045C011V029	45	11	29	For Aloha turneth not in his gift and in his vocation.
B045C011V030	45	11	30	For as you also were not obedient unto Aloha at the first, and now have received mercy through their disobedience;
B045C011V031	45	11	31	so also these are now disobedient for the mercy that is upon you, that upon them also might be mercy.
B045C011V032	45	11	32	For Aloha hath included them all in disobedience, that upon all he might show mercy.
B045C011V033	45	11	33	O the depth of the riches of the wisdom and knowledge of Aloha, whose judgments man searcheth not, and whose ways are inscrutable!
B045C011V034	45	11	34	For who hath known the mind of the Lord, or who hath been his counsellor?
B045C011V035	45	11	35	Or who hath first given to him, that so he should receive from him?
B045C011V036	45	11	36	For all is of him, and all in him, and all by him. To him be praises and benedictions unto the age of ages. Amen.
B045C012V001	45	12	1	I BESEECH then of you, my brethren, by the mercies of Aloha, that you present your bodies a sacrifice, living and holy and acceptable unto Aloha, in a rational service.
B045C012V002	45	12	2	And be not likened unto this world, but be changed by the renewing of your minds, that you may discern what is the will of Aloha, good, and acceptable, and perfect.
B045C012V003	45	12	3	But I tell you all through the grace which is given to me, that you are not to think beyond what it is proper to think; but that you think with sobriety, every man as Aloha hath divided to him faith in measure.
B045C012V004	45	12	4	For as in one body we have many members, and as all the members have not one work,
B045C012V005	45	12	5	so also we who are many are one body in the Meshiha; but we are each of us members one of another.
B045C012V006	45	12	6	But we have various gifts according to the grace that is given to us: is it prophecy? (let him who has received it) prophesy according to the measure of the faith.
B045C012V007	45	12	7	Hath (another the gift) of ministry? (let him be employed) in his ministry; he who is a teacher, (let him labour) in his teaching;
B045C012V008	45	12	8	he who is an exhorter, in his exhorting; as he who giveth, (let him give with simplicity;) and he who presideth, (let it be) with diligence; and he who (is engaged in works) of mercy, with cheerfulness.
B045C012V009	45	12	9	And let not your love be guileful; abhor things evil, cleave to the good.
B045C012V010	45	12	10	Be tender to your brethren, and love one another, being forward to honour one another.
B045C012V011	45	12	11	Be diligent, and not slothful, be fervent in spirit, be serving your Lord.
B045C012V012	45	12	12	Rejoice in your hope, sustain your afflictions, be constant in prayer;
B045C012V013	45	12	13	distributing to the necessity of the saints. Be kind to strangers.
B045C012V014	45	12	14	Bless your persecutors; bless, and curse not.
B045C012V015	45	12	15	Rejoice with them who rejoice, and weep with them who weep.
B045C012V016	45	12	16	And what you think of yourselves, (that) also think of your brethren; nor think with a high mind, but incline to them who are humble; and be not wise in the conceit of your own mind.
B045C012V017	45	12	17	And repay to no man evil for evil, but be careful to do good before all men.
B045C012V018	45	12	18	And if possible, as much as is in you, with all men make peace.
B045C012V019	45	12	19	And avenge not yourselves, my beloved, but give place unto wrath; for it is written, that if thou execute not judgment for thyself, I will execute thy judgment, saith Aloha.
B045C012V020	45	12	20	And if thy adversary hunger, feed him; and if he thirst, give him drink: and if these things thou do unto him, coals of fire thou wilt heap upon his head.
B045C012V021	45	12	21	Let not evil overcome you, but overcome evil with good.
B045C013V001	45	13	1	LET every soul to the powers of dominion be subject. For there is no power that is not from Aloha, and the powers that be, of Aloha are they instituted.
B045C013V002	45	13	2	Whoever then riseth up against the power, against the institution of Aloha he riseth; and they who arise against them will receive judgment.
B045C013V003	45	13	3	For judges are not a terror to the workers of good, but to the evil. Wilt thou then not be afraid of the power? do good, and thou shalt have praise from him.
B045C013V004	45	13	4	For he is the servant of Aloha, but to thee for good: and if thou do evil, fear; for not in vain is he girded with the sword; for he is the servant of Aloha, and the dispenser of wrath to them who do evil.
B045C013V005	45	13	5	And because of this are we bound to be subject, not for the wrath only, but also because of conscience.
B045C013V006	45	13	6	On this account also give we tribute to them; for they are the servants of Aloha over these things constituted.
B045C013V007	45	13	7	Render therefore to every man as is due to him: to whom tribute (is due,) tribute; and to whom custom, custom; and to whom reverence, reverence; and to whom honour, honour.
B045C013V008	45	13	8	And to no man owe any thing, but one another to love. For whoever loveth his neighbour fulfilleth the law:
B045C013V009	45	13	9	for that also which it hath said, Thou shalt not kill; and, Thou shalt not commit adultery; and, Thou shalt not steal; and, Thou shalt not covet; and if there be any other commandment, in this word it is accomplished, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.
B045C013V010	45	13	10	Love unto his neighbour evil worketh not: therefore love is the fulfilling of the law.
B045C013V011	45	13	11	AND also this know, that the time is, and the hour is, when we should be awake from our sleep; for now hath drawn nearer to us our salvation than when we believed.
B045C013V012	45	13	12	The night now passeth away, and the day hath drawn nigh; put we away then from us the works of darkness, and let us clothe with the arms of light.
B045C013V013	45	13	13	And as in the day, let us walk decorously, not with the song, nor with drunkenness, nor in the unclean chamber, nor in envy and in contention;
B045C013V014	45	13	14	but let (every one) clothe himself with our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, and care not for your flesh unto the lusts (thereof).
B045C014V001	45	14	1	But to him who is weak in the faith give the hand, and be not divided in your thoughts.
B045C014V002	45	14	2	For there are some who believe that one may eat every thing, and he who is weak; eateth (only) the herb.
B045C014V003	45	14	3	But let not him who eateth despise him who eateth not; and he who eateth not, let him not judge him who eateth; for Aloha hath received him.
B045C014V004	45	14	4	Who art thou that judgest a servant who is not thine? who, if he stand, unto his Lord he standeth, and if he fall, falleth unto his Lord. But standing, he standeth; for there is power in the hands of his Lord to make him stand.
B045C014V005	45	14	5	There is who distinguisheth day from day, and there is who judgeth all days (to be alike); but let every man in the conviction of his (own) mind be confirmed.
B045C014V006	45	14	6	He who thinketh of the day, to his Lord he thinketh; and every one who thinketh not of the day, unto his Lord he thinketh not (of it). He who eateth, to his Lord he eateth, and to Aloha giveth thanks;
B045C014V007	45	14	7	and he who eateth not, to his Lord he eateth not, and giveth thanks to Aloha. For there is no one of us who to himself liveth and no one who to himself dieth.
B045C014V008	45	14	8	For if we live, to our Lord we live; and if we die, to our Lord we die: and if we live, then, or if we die, our Lord's are we.
B045C014V009	45	14	9	Because of this also the Meshiha died and lived and arose, that he might be Lord of the dead and of the living. But thou, why dost thou judge thy brother?
B045C014V010	45	14	10	Or thou, also, why despisest thou thy brother? For we shall all stand before the tribunal of the Meshiha:
B045C014V011	45	14	11	as it is written, As I live, saith the Lord, unto me every knee shall bow, and to me shall every tongue confess.
B045C014V012	45	14	12	Therefore, every one of us the answer for himself shall give unto Aloha.
B045C014V013	45	14	13	Then judge not one another, but this determine rather, to lay not a stumbling-block for thy brother.
B045C014V014	45	14	14	For I know, and am persuaded in the Lord Jeshu, that a thing which is unclean from itself is not (so); but to him who judgeth of any thing that it is polluted, to him only it is polluted.
B045C014V015	45	14	15	But if on account of meat thou grievest thy brother, thou walkest not in love: destroy not by thy meat him on account of whom the Meshiha died.
B045C014V016	45	14	16	Let not our good (things) be blasphemed.
B045C014V017	45	14	17	For the kingdom of Aloha is not meat and drink, but righteousness and peace and joy in the Spirit of Holiness.
B045C014V018	45	14	18	For who in these things serveth the Meshiha pleaseth Aloha, and before men is approved.
B045C014V019	45	14	19	Now, after peace let us pursue, and after the edification of one another,
B045C014V020	45	14	20	and not for the sake of meats undo the work of Aloha. For each thing is pure, yet evil is it to the man who eateth with offence.
B045C014V021	45	14	21	It is well not to eat flesh, nor to drink wine, nor any thing by which our brother is offended.
B045C014V022	45	14	22	Hast thou confidence? In thyself retain it before Aloha. Blessed is he who condemneth not himself in what he distinguisheth.
B045C014V023	45	14	23	For he who doubteth and eateth is made guilty, because he eateth not with confidence. For every thing that is not of confidence is sin.
B045C015V001	45	15	1	WE then, the strong, are obligated to bear up the infirmities of the weak, and not ourselves to please.
B045C015V002	45	15	2	But let every one of us please his neighbour in good things as unto edification.
B045C015V003	45	15	3	Because the Meshiha also pleased not himself; but as it is written, The reproach of thy reproachers hath fallen upon me.
B045C015V004	45	15	4	For every thing that hath before been written for our instruction was written, that by the patience and consolation of the scriptures we might have hope.
B045C015V005	45	15	5	But the God of patience and of consolation give to you that with impartiality you may think one of another in Jeshu Meshiha,
B045C015V006	45	15	6	that with one mind and with one mouth you may glorify Aloha, the Father of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B045C015V007	45	15	7	Therefore, receive and bear with one another, as also the Meshiha hath received you, to the glory of Aloha.
B045C015V008	45	15	8	But I say that Jeshu Meshiha ministered the circumcision, on behalf of the truth of Aloha, that he might confirm the promise of the fathers,
B045C015V009	45	15	9	and the Gentiles might glorify Aloha for his mercy that was upon them. As it is written, I will confess thee among the Gentiles, And to thy name will I sing.
B045C015V010	45	15	10	And again he hath said, Be glad, ye Gentiles, with his people.
B045C015V011	45	15	11	And again he hath said, Praise the Lord, all (ye) Gentiles; Let all peoples praise him.
B045C015V012	45	15	12	And again, Eshaia hath said, There shall be a root of Jeshai, And he who shall arise shall be the chief of the peoples; And upon him will the Gentiles hope.
B045C015V013	45	15	13	But the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace, through faith, that you may abound in hope through the power of the Spirit of Holiness.
B045C015V014	45	15	14	BUT I am persuaded also concerning you, my brethren, that you are also full of good, and filled with all knowledge, and able also to instruct others.
B045C015V015	45	15	15	But I have somewhat boldly written to you, my brethren, as that I may put you in remembrance, through the grace which is given to me from Aloha,
B045C015V016	45	15	16	to be a minister of Jeshu Meshiha among the Gentiles, and to labour in the gospel of Aloha, that there may be an oblation of the Gentiles, acceptable and holy through the Spirit of Holiness.
B045C015V017	45	15	17	I have, then, exultation in Jeshu Meshiha with Aloha.
B045C015V018	45	15	18	For I dare not speak any thing which the Meshiha hath not done by my hands, unto the obedience of the Gentiles, in word and in deeds,
B045C015V019	45	15	19	with the power of signs and miracles, and with the power of the Spirit of Aloha; as that I have itinerated from Urishlem unto Illyrikum, to fulfil the preaching of Meshiha;
B045C015V020	45	15	20	being anxious to preach, not where the name of Meshiha had been called, that I might not build upon another foundation,
B045C015V021	45	15	21	but as it is written, They to whom it hath not been told of him, they shall see him; and they who have not heard shall be persuaded.
B045C015V022	45	15	22	On this account I have been hindered many times when I would have come to you.
B045C015V023	45	15	23	But now, because I have no place in these countries, and have desired for many years to come to you,
B045C015V024	45	15	24	when I go into Ispania, I hope to come and see you; and you shall lead me thitherward, when I shall in some measure have been gladdened with the sight of you.
B045C015V025	45	15	25	But now I go to Urishlem to minister to the saints.
B045C015V026	45	15	26	For they in Makedunia and in Akaia have desired that a communication should be made from themselves with the poor and the saints who are at Urishlem.
B045C015V027	45	15	27	They have desired (this), because they also are indebted to them. For if the Gentiles have participated with them in the Spirit, they are indebted to serve them in the flesh.
B045C015V028	45	15	28	This, then, when I have accomplished, and have sealed to them this fruit, I (intend to) pass by you into Ispania.
B045C015V029	45	15	29	And I know that when I come to you, with the plenitude of the blessing of the gospel of Meshiha I (shall) come.
B045C015V030	45	15	30	Now I entreat of you, my brethren, by our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, and by the love of the Spirit, to labour with me in prayer on my behalf, with Aloha,
B045C015V031	45	15	31	that I may be delivered from them who believe not in Jihud, and (that) the service which I bear to the saints may be well received,
B045C015V032	45	15	32	and I may come to you with joy in the will of Aloha, and be rested with you.
B045C015V033	45	15	33	The God of peace be with all of you. Amen.
B045C016V001	45	16	1	I COMMEND to you Phebe our sister, who is a deaconess of the church of Kancreos,
B045C016V002	45	16	2	that you receive her in the Lord, as is right for saints; and, in every thing which she requests from you, assist her; because she also hath assisted many, and myself also.
B045C016V003	45	16	3	Ask for the peace of Priskela and Akulos, labourers with me in Jeshu Meshiha;
B045C016V004	45	16	4	for they themselves for my life have given their necks; and not only do I praise them, but also all the churches of the Gentiles.
B045C016V005	45	16	5	And give salutation to the church which is in their house. Ask the peace of Epenetos, my beloved, who was the first-fruits of Akaia in the Meshiha.
B045C016V006	45	16	6	Ask the peace of Maria, who hath laboured much with you.
B045C016V007	45	16	7	Ask for the peace of Andronikos and Junia, my kindred, who were captives with me, and are known among the apostles, and in Meshiha were before me.
B045C016V008	45	16	8	Ask for the peace of Ampleos, my beloved in our Lord.
B045C016V009	45	16	9	Ask for the peace of Urbanos, a labourer with us in Meshiha, and of Estakos my beloved.
B045C016V010	45	16	10	Ask the peace of Apella, chosen in our Lord. Ask for the peace of the sons of the house of Aristobulos.
B045C016V011	45	16	11	Ask the peace of Herodion, my relative. Ask for the peace of the sons of the house of Narkisos, who are in our Lord.
B045C016V012	45	16	12	Ask for the peace of Tryphena and Tryphosa, who labour in our Lord. Ask for the peace of Parsis, my beloved, who much hath laboured in our Lord.
B045C016V013	45	16	13	Ask for the peace of Rufus, the chosen in our Lord, and of his mother and mine.
B045C016V014	45	16	14	Ask the peace of Asynkritos, and of Phlegun, and of Arma, and of Patroba, and of Herma, and of the brethren who are with them.
B045C016V015	45	16	15	Ask the peace of Philologos, and of Julia, and of Niros, and of his sister, and of Olympa, and all the saints who are with them.
B045C016V016	45	16	16	Ask for the peace one of another with the holy kiss. All the churches of the Meshiha ask for your peace.
B045C016V017	45	16	17	But I beseech of you, my brethren, beware of them who make divisions and scandals apart from the doctrine which you have learned; and be distant from them.
B045C016V018	45	16	18	For they who are thus serve not our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, but their bellies; and with sweet words and benedictions seduce the hearts of the simple.
B045C016V019	45	16	19	But your obedience is known to every one; I rejoice therefore in you, and I wish you to be wise unto good (works), and pure with regard to evil.
B045C016V020	45	16	20	But the God of peace will soon bruise Satana beneath your feet. The grace of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha be with you!
B045C016V021	45	16	21	Timotheos, a labourer with me, and Lukios and Iason and Sosipatros my kinsmen ask for your peace.
B045C016V022	45	16	22	I, Tertios, who have inscribed this epistle in our Lord, ask for your peace.
B045C016V023	45	16	23	Gaios my entertainer, and of all the church, asketh for your peace; (as do) Erastos steward of the city, and Quartos a brother.
B045C016V024	45	16	24	The grace of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha be with you all. Amen.
B045C016V025	45	16	25	TO ALOHA, who is able to confirm you in my gospel which is proclaimed concerning Jeshu the Meshiha, through revelation of the mystery, which from the times of the ages was hidden,
B045C016V026	45	16	26	but is revealed in this time by means of the scriptures of the prophets, and by the commandment of the Everlasting Aloha is made known to all the nations for the obedience of faith;
B045C016V027	45	16	27	(to Him) who alone is wise, BE GLORY BY JESHU MESHIHA, UNTO THE AGE OF AGES. AMEN.
B046C001V001	46	1	1	PAULOS the called, and the apostle of Jeshu Meshiha by the will of Aloha, and Sosthenis a brother,
B046C001V002	46	1	2	to the church of Aloha which is in Kurinthos, the called, and the saints who in Jeshu Meshiha are sanctified; and to all them who invoke the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha in every place, theirs and ours:
B046C001V003	46	1	3	Grace be with you and peace from Aloha our Father, and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B046C001V004	46	1	4	I give thanks to Aloha at all times on your behalf for the grace of Aloha which is given to you through Jeshu Meshiha,
B046C001V005	46	1	5	because in every thing you are enriched in him in all utterance and in all knowledge,
B046C001V006	46	1	6	according to the testimony of the Meshiha, which is confirmed in you.
B046C001V007	46	1	7	That you may not be deficient in one of his gifts, but be expecting the revelation of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha,
B046C001V008	46	1	8	who will confirm you to the end, that you may be without fault in the day of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B046C001V009	46	1	9	Faithful is Aloha, by whom you have been called to the fellowship of his Son Jeshu Meshiha our Lord.
B046C001V010	46	1	10	But I beseech of you, my brethren, in the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, that you have all one doctrine, and that there be no divisions among you, but that you be perfect in one mind and one sentiment.
B046C001V011	46	1	11	For they of the house of Kloë have sent to me concerning you, my brethren, that there are contentions among you.
B046C001V012	46	1	12	For this I say, that there are some of you who say, I am of Paulos; and some who say, I am of Apollo; and some who say, I am of Kipha; and some who say, I am of the Meshiha!
B046C001V013	46	1	13	Is the Meshiha divided? Or was Paulos crucified for you? Or in the name of Paulos were you baptized?
B046C001V014	46	1	14	I thank Aloha that no man of you I have baptized, but only Krispos and Gaios;
B046C001V015	46	1	15	lest any man should say, that in my name I have baptized.
B046C001V016	46	1	16	But I baptized also the house of Estepana; beyond (these) I know not that any other man I have baptized.
B046C001V017	46	1	17	For the Meshiha sent me not to baptize, but to preach; not with the wisdom of words, lest the cross of the Meshiha should be nullified.
B046C001V018	46	1	18	FOR the doctrine of the cross to those who perish is foolishness, but to us who are saved it is the power of Aloha.
B046C001V019	46	1	19	For it is written, I will destroy the wisdom of the wise, And I will take away the understanding of the prudent.
B046C001V020	46	1	20	Where is the wise? Where is the scribe? Or where is the disputer of this world? Hath not . Aloha made foolish the wisdom of this world?
B046C001V021	46	1	21	For inasmuch as in the wisdom of Aloha, the world by wisdom hath not known Aloha, it hath pleased Aloha, by the foolishness of preaching, to save them who believe.
B046C001V022	46	1	22	For the Jihudoyee demand signs, and the Aramoyee require wisdom;
B046C001V023	46	1	23	but we preach the Meshiha crucified, a scandal to the Jihudoyee, and to the Aramoyee foolishness;
B046C001V024	46	1	24	but to them who are called, Jihudoyee and Aramoyee, the Meshiha is the power of Aloha, and the wisdom of Aloha.
B046C001V025	46	1	25	For the foolishness of Aloha is wiser than men, and the weakness of Aloha is stronger than men.
B046C001V026	46	1	26	For you see also your calling, my brethren, that not many among you are wise after the flesh, and not many among you are powerful, and not many among you are of noble birth;
B046C001V027	46	1	27	but Aloha hath chosen the simple of the world, to shame the wise, and he hath chosen the weak of the world, to shame the mighty,
B046C001V028	46	1	28	and he hath chosen those of low birth in the world, and the outcasts, and those who are nothing, to bring to nothing those who are;
B046C001V029	46	1	29	that no flesh may boast before him.
B046C001V030	46	1	30	But you are of him in Jeshu Meshiha, who hath been made unto us wisdom, of Aloha, and righteousness and sanctification and redemption;
B046C001V031	46	1	31	according as it is written, He who boasteth, in the Lord let him boast.
B046C002V001	46	2	1	And I, my brethren, when I came to you, not with grandeur of speech, nor with wisdom, did I evangelize to you the mystery of Aloha.
B046C002V002	46	2	2	And I considered myself among you as not knowing any thing unless Jeshu Meshiha, and him also as crucified.
B046C002V003	46	2	3	And I in much fear and trembling was with you.
B046C002V004	46	2	4	And my speech and my preaching were not with the persuasion of the words of wisdom, but with the demonstration of the Spirit and of power;
B046C002V005	46	2	5	that your faith might not be through the wisdom of men, but through the power of Aloha.
B046C002V006	46	2	6	But we speak wisdom among the perfect: not the wisdom of this world, nor the authorities of this world, which are abolished;
B046C002V007	46	2	7	but we speak the wisdom of Aloha in the mystery which was hidden, and which Aloha predetermined from before the worlds unto our glorification;
B046C002V008	46	2	8	which not one of the authorities of this world hath known; for if they had known it, the Lord of glory they would not have crucified.
B046C002V009	46	2	9	But as it is written, The eye hath not seen, Nor the ear heard, Nor the heart of man hath risen (to), That which Aloha hath prepared for those who love him.
B046C002V010	46	2	10	BUT unto us hath Aloha revealed, by his Spirit. For the Spirit all things searcheth, also the depths of Aloha.
B046C002V011	46	2	11	For what man knoweth what is in man, save the spirit of a man which is in him? so also that which is in Aloha man knoweth not, but only the Spirit of Aloha.
B046C002V012	46	2	12	But we not the spirit of this world have received, but the Spirit who is from Aloha, that we might know that the gifts from Aloha are given unto us;
B046C002V013	46	2	13	which also we speak, not with the learning of words of wisdom of men, but with the learning of the Spirit; and with spirituals the spirituals we compare.
B046C002V014	46	2	14	For the man who is animal receiveth not spirituals, for they are foolishness to him, and he cannot know them, because they by the Spirit are judged of;
B046C002V015	46	2	15	but the spiritual judgeth of every thing, and he of man is not judged.
B046C002V016	46	2	16	For who hath known the mind of the Lord to teach him? But we have the mind of the Meshiha.
B046C003V001	46	3	1	AND I, my brethren, could not speak with you as with the spiritual, but as with the carnal, and as with babes in the Meshiha.
B046C003V002	46	3	2	I have sustained you with milk, and have not given you meat; for as yet you could not, nor can you now, (bear it).
B046C003V003	46	3	3	For as yet you are in the flesh. For while there are among you envy and contentions and divisions, are you not carnal, and walking in the flesh?
B046C003V004	46	3	4	For while some of you say, I am of Paulos, and another, I am of Apollo, are you not carnal?
B046C003V005	46	3	5	For who is Paulos, or who Apollo, but ministers by whom you have believed and each as the Lord gave to him?
B046C003V006	46	3	6	I have planted, and Apollo watered, but Aloha made to increase.
B046C003V007	46	3	7	He then who planteth is not any thing nor he who watereth; but Aloha who maketh to increase.
B046C003V008	46	3	8	But he who planteth and he who watereth are one, (and) each according to his labour his recompence receiveth.
B046C003V009	46	3	9	For with Aloha we work; and the work of Aloha and the edifice of Aloha are you.
B046C003V010	46	3	10	And according to the grace of Aloha which is given to me, I have laid the foundation as a wise architect; but another hath built upon it.
B046C003V011	46	3	11	But let every man beware how he buildeth upon it. For another foundation besides this which is laid no man can lay, (that, namely,) which is Jeshu the Meshiha.
B046C003V012	46	3	12	And if any man build upon this foundation gold, or silver, or precious stones; or wood, or hay, or stubble;
B046C003V013	46	3	13	the work of every one shall be revealed, for that day shall reveal it; for by the fire shall it be revealed, and the work of every man as it is the fire shall distinguish.
B046C003V014	46	3	14	And he whose work which he builded shall abide, will receive his recompense;
B046C003V015	46	3	15	and he whose work shall be burned, shall fail; but he (himself) shall be rescued, but so as from fire.
B046C003V016	46	3	16	KNOW YOU not that you are the temple of Aloha, and (that) the Spirit of Aloha inhabiteth in you?
B046C003V017	46	3	17	Whoso destroyeth the temple of Aloha, him will Aloha destroy for the temple of Aloha is holy, which you are.
B046C003V018	46	3	18	Let no man deceive himself. Whoever among you supposeth himself wise in this world, let him become foolish, that he may be wise.
B046C003V019	46	3	19	For the wisdom of this world is folly with Aloha; for it is written, He hath taken the wise in their own craftiness.
B046C003V020	46	3	20	And again, The Lord knoweth the thoughts of the wise, that they are vain.
B046C003V021	46	3	21	On this account let no one boast in men: for every thing is yours;
B046C003V022	46	3	22	whether Paulos, or Apolo, or Kipha, or the world, or life, or death, or things standing, or things to be; every thing is yours,
B046C003V023	46	3	23	and you are of the Meshiha, and the Meshiha of Aloha.
B046C004V001	46	4	1	Thus let us be accounted of you as ministers of the Meshiha, and stewards of the mysteries of Aloha.
B046C004V002	46	4	2	So now is it required of a steward that he be one found faithful.
B046C004V003	46	4	3	But to me it is a little thing to be Judged by you, or by any man; neither do I judge myself,
B046C004V004	46	4	4	for of nothing in myself am I conscious; but not by this am I justified, but my judge is the Lord.
B046C004V005	46	4	5	Therefore, do not judge before the time, until the Lord come, who will bring to light the hidden things of darkness, and reveal the thoughts of hearts. Then will there be praise to each man from Aloha.
B046C004V006	46	4	6	BUT these things, my brethren, for your sakes I have applied to the person of myself and of Apolo, that through us you may learn not to think of us beyond what is written; and that one above his neighbour may not be exalted on account of any thing.
B046C004V007	46	4	7	For who distinguisheth thee? Or, what hast thou which thou hast not received? And if thou hast received, why dost thou boast as if thou hadst not received?
B046C004V008	46	4	8	Now you are satiated, and are rich, and without us have reigned. But I would that you did reign, that we might also reign with you!
B046C004V009	46	4	9	But I consider that us, the apostles, Aloha hath set last, as unto death, to be a spectacle to the world, to angels, and to men,
B046C004V010	46	4	10	We are fools for the sake of the Meshiha, but we are wise in the Meshiha; we are the weak, but you are the mighty; you are glorified, and we abased.
B046C004V011	46	4	11	Until this hour we hunger and thirst, we are naked and beaten and have no fixed dwelling;
B046C004V012	46	4	12	and we labour, working with our hands. They revile us, and we bless; they persecute us, and we endure;
B046C004V013	46	4	13	they maltreat us, and we pray for them; as the refuse of the world are we made and the execration of all men until now.
B046C004V014	46	4	14	Not as to shame you write I these things, but as my beloved children I admonish (you).
B046C004V015	46	4	15	For if you have ten thousand teachers in the Meshiha, yet not many fathers; for in Jeshu Meshiha I have begotten you through the gospel.
B046C004V016	46	4	16	I entreat then of you that you be like me.
B046C004V017	46	4	17	WHEREFORE I have sent to you Timotheos, who is my beloved son, and faithful in the Lord, that he may remind you of my ways in the Meshiha, according to that which I teach in all the churches.
B046C004V018	46	4	18	But as if I were not coming to you, some of you are inflated.
B046C004V019	46	4	19	But if the Lord will, quickly come I unto you; and I will know not the words of them who exalt themselves, but their power.
B046C004V020	46	4	20	For the kingdom of Aloha is not in word, but in power.
B046C004V021	46	4	21	How are you willing? with a rod shall I come to you, or with love and with the spirit of kindliness?
B046C005V001	46	5	1	Fornication is commonly reported among you; and such fornication as is not heard among the Heathens, that the son should take the wife of his father.
B046C005V002	46	5	2	And you are inflated; but should you not rather sit in grief that he who hath wrought this work might be put away from you?
B046C005V003	46	5	3	But I, while distant from you in body, am near you in spirit, and now judge, as if near you, him who hath done this;
B046C005V004	46	5	4	that in the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha all of you be assembled, and I with you in spirit, with the power of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha,
B046C005V005	46	5	5	and you deliver this (man) to Satana for the destruction of his body, that in spirit he may be saved in the day of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B046C005V006	46	5	6	MY brethren, your boasting is not seemly. Know you not that a little leaven the whole mass leaveneth?
B046C005V007	46	5	7	Purge from you the old leaven, that you may be a new mass; so that you may be (as) unleavened bread. For our Pascha is the Meshiha, who hath been slain for us.
B046C005V008	46	5	8	Therefore, let us perform the festival, not with the old leaven, nor with the leaven of wickedness and animosity, but with the unleavened bread of purity and of holiness.
B046C005V009	46	5	9	I have written to you by epistle, not to be mixed with fornicators;
B046C005V010	46	5	10	but I do not say with fornicators who are in this world, nor speak I concerning the covetous, or the rapacious, or the servers of idols; otherwise you would be obligated from the world also to go forth.
B046C005V011	46	5	11	But this which I have written to you, Be not mixed, (is,) If any one who is called a brother be a fornicator, or covetous, or a worshipper of idols, or a reviler, or a drunkard, or rapacious, with one who is such as he not to eat bread.
B046C005V012	46	5	12	For what had I to judge those who are without? But you judge those who are within;
B046C005V013	46	5	13	but those who are without, Aloha judgeth: and put away the wicked one from among you.
B046C006V001	46	6	1	DARE any of you, having a suit with his brother, to litigate before the evil, and not before the saints?
B046C006V002	46	6	2	Or know you not that the saints shall judge the world? And if the world by you is judged, are you not worthy to judge small matters?
B046C006V003	46	6	3	Know you not that you are to judge angels? How much more those (matters) which are of this world?
B046C006V004	46	6	4	But if you have matters to be judged regarding the world, those who are little-esteemed in the church make you to sit in judgment.
B046C006V005	46	6	5	But to your reproach am I to say to you, So there is not among you even one wise man, who is able to adjust between a brother and his brother?
B046C006V006	46	6	6	But a brother with his brother litigates, and, moreover, before those who are unbelievers!
B046C006V007	46	6	7	Now, therefore, you make yourselves guilty while you have litigation one with another. For why do you not bear injury? and why do you not suffer fraud?
B046C006V008	46	6	8	But you injure, and you defraud, also your brethren!
B046C006V009	46	6	9	Or, know you not that the unjust the kingdom of Aloha cannot inherit? Do not err; neither fornicators, nor the servers of idols, nor adulterers, nor corrupters, nor liers with men, nor the oppressive,
B046C006V010	46	6	10	nor thieves, nor drunkards, nor revilers, nor the rapacious, the kingdom of Aloha can inherit.
B046C006V011	46	6	11	And these were some of you but you are washed, and sanctified, and justified in the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, and by the Spirit of our God.
B046C006V012	46	6	12	ALL (food) is lawful to me, but all is not expedient for me. All is lawful to me, but over me no one shall have power.
B046C006V013	46	6	13	Food is for the belly, and the belly for food; but Aloha will abolish them both. But the body was not for fornication, but for our Lord, and our Lord for the body.
B046C006V014	46	6	14	And Aloha hath raised up our Lord, and us will raise by his power.
B046C006V015	46	6	15	Know you not that your bodies are members of the Meshiha? Shall one take a member of the Meshiha to make it a member of a harlot? Never!
B046C006V016	46	6	16	Know you not that whosoever attacheth to a harlot is one body? For it is said, The two shall be one body.
B046C006V017	46	6	17	But, he who attacheth to our Lord is with him one spirit.
B046C006V018	46	6	18	Flee from fornication: for every sin which a man committeth is without his body; but he who committeth fornication against his own body sinneth.
B046C006V019	46	6	19	Or, know you not that your body is the temple of the Spirit of Holiness, who dwelleth in you, (even) Him whom you have received from Aloha? And you are not your own,
B046C006V020	46	6	20	for you are bought with the price; therefore glorify Aloha in your body and in your spirit, which are of Aloha.
B046C007V001	46	7	1	BUT concerning those (questions) of which you wrote to me, It is well for a man unto a woman not to come nigh;
B046C007V002	46	7	2	but, because of fornication, let a man take his wife, and let a woman take her husband.
B046C007V003	46	7	3	And let a man render the love that is due unto his wife;
B046C007V004	46	7	4	so also the wife to her husband. For the wife hath not authority over her body, but the husband; so also the man hath not authority over his body, but his wife.
B046C007V005	46	7	5	Defraud not then one the other, unless you both agree for a time, that you may humble yourselves by fasting and by prayer; and return again unto the same will, that Satana may not tempt you on account of the desire of your bodies.
B046C007V006	46	7	6	But this I speak as to the infirm; (and) not from commandment.
B046C007V007	46	7	7	For I would that all men were as I am, in chastity. But every man hath the gift given to him from Aloha, this one thus, and the other thus.
B046C007V008	46	7	8	But I say to those who have no wives, and to the widows, that it is expedient for them to remain as I do.
B046C007V009	46	7	9	Yet, if they persevere not, they should marry; for it is better to take a wife than to burn with concupiscence.
B046C007V010	46	7	10	But those who have wives I command, yet not I, but my Lord, that the wife from her husband separate not.
B046C007V011	46	7	11	Yet, if she separate, let her remain without a man, or unto her husband be reconciled. And let not a man put away his wife.
B046C007V012	46	7	12	But to the rest I say, not my Lord, If a brother hath a wife who is not a believer, and she be willing to dwell with him, let him not put her away.
B046C007V013	46	7	13	And any woman who has an husband unbelieving, and he willeth to dwell with her, let her not put away her husband.
B046C007V014	46	7	14	For the man who believeth not is sanctified by the wife who believeth; and any wife who believeth not is sanctified by the husband who believeth; otherwise their children would be unclean; but now are they clean.
B046C007V015	46	7	15	But if he who believeth not separate, let him separate; a brother or a sister is not in servitude to these: unto peace Aloha hath called us.
B046C007V016	46	7	16	For how knowest thou, wife, whether thou mayest save thy husband? Or knowest thou, man, if thy wife thou mayest save?
B046C007V017	46	7	17	But (according as) the Lord hath distributed to every one, as Aloha hath called, so let him walk; and thus in all the churches, so I direct.
B046C007V018	46	7	18	If a man circumcised hath been called, let him not turn to uncircumcision; and if in uncircumcision he hath been called, let him not be circumcised.
B046C007V019	46	7	19	For circumcision is not any thing, nor uncircumcision, but the observances of the commandments of Aloha.
B046C007V020	46	7	20	Let every man in the calling in which he hath been called remain.
B046C007V021	46	7	21	If a servant thou wast called, be not careful, but, if also thou canst be made free, choose that thou shouldest serve.
B046C007V022	46	7	22	For he who a servant is called in the Lord, is the freeman of Aloha, so he who as a son of freedom is called, is a servant of the Meshiha.
B046C007V023	46	7	23	With a price are you bought; you will not be servants of men.
B046C007V024	46	7	24	Every one in that in which he was called, my brethren, in it let him remain unto Aloha.
B046C007V025	46	7	25	BUT respecting virginity, a commandment from Aloha I have not received; but I give counsel as a man who hath had grace from Aloha to be faithful.
B046C007V026	46	7	26	And I consider that this is good, on account of the necessity of the time, that it is expedient for a man so to be.
B046C007V027	46	7	27	Art thou bound to a wife? seek not to be loosed. Art thou loosed from a wife? seek not a wife.
B046C007V028	46	7	28	Yet, if thou takest a wife, thou sinnest not; and if a virgin shall be to a husband, she sinneth not. Yet affliction in the body will be to them who are such; but I am sparing over you.
B046C007V029	46	7	29	And this I say, my brethren, that the time now becomes contracted; and they who have wives should be as not having them;
B046C007V030	46	7	30	and they who weep, as not weeping; and they who rejoice, as not rejoicing; and they who buy, as not possessing;
B046C007V031	46	7	31	and they who use this world should not exceed the just use; for the fashion of this world passeth away.
B046C007V032	46	7	32	Wherefore I would that you be without anxiety; for he who hath not a wife thinketh of the things of his Lord, that so he may please his Lord;
B046C007V033	46	7	33	and he who hath a wife is anxious for the world, that so he may please his wife.
B046C007V034	46	7	34	But there is a distinction between the wife and the virgin. She who hath no man is thoughtful of the things of her Lord, that she may be holy in her body and in her spirit; and she who hath a husband is thoughtful of the world, that so she may please her husband.
B046C007V035	46	7	35	But this for your own profit speak I; not to throw a snare over you, but that you may be constant towards your Lord in a comely manner, while not thoughtful of the world.
B046C007V036	46	7	36	But if a man consider it to be dishonourable toward his virgin, who hath passed her time, that he hath not given her to the man, (and) that it is proper that he should give her; as he willeth let him act, he sinneth not: let them marry.
B046C007V037	46	7	37	But he who hath firmly decided in his own mind, and nothing constraineth him, and (who hath) power in his will, and thus judgeth in his heart, that he will keep his virgin, doeth well.
B046C007V038	46	7	38	And he then who giveth his virgin doeth well, and he who giveth not his virgin doeth better.
B046C007V039	46	7	39	The wife, so long as her husband liveth, is bound by the law; but if her husband shall die, she is free, that she may do what she willeth, only in our Lord.
B046C007V040	46	7	40	But it is good if thus she remain, according to my own mind. But I think also that the Spirit of Aloha is in me.
B046C008V001	46	8	1	RESPECTING the sacrifices of idols, we know that in all of us there is knowledge; and knowledge inflateth, but love buildeth up.
B046C008V002	46	8	2	But if a man think that he knows any thing, he knows nothing yet as it behoves him to know:
B046C008V003	46	8	3	but if a man love Aloha, this (one) is acknowledged of him.
B046C008V004	46	8	4	Concerning the meat of the sacrifices of idols, then, we know that an idol is nothing in the world, and that there is no other God but one.
B046C008V005	46	8	5	For there are also who are called gods, whether in heaven or in earth, as that there are gods many and lords many:
B046C008V006	46	8	6	but to us our One is Aloha the Father, of whom are all, and we in him; and one Lord Jeshu Meshiha, by whom are all, and we by him.
B046C008V007	46	8	7	But not in every man is this knowledge; for there are some who in their conscience until now (believe) that, with respect to idols, as of that which hath been sacrificed we eat. And because of weakness their conscience is defiled.
B046C008V008	46	8	8	But meat doth not bring us nigh to Aloha. For if we eat, we excel not; nor if we eat not, are we deficient.
B046C008V009	46	8	9	But beware that this your power become not a stumbling-block to the infirm ones.
B046C008V010	46	8	10	For if a man shall see thee in whom is knowledge reclining in the house of idols, will not his conscience, because he is weak, be confirmed to eat that which is sacrificed,
B046C008V011	46	8	11	and he will perish through thy knowledge? he who is weak, and on account of whom the Meshiha died.
B046C008V012	46	8	12	And if so you transgress against your brethren, and wound their weak consciences, do you not transgress against the Meshiha?
B046C008V013	46	8	13	On this account, if meat cause my brother to stumble, I will never (more) eat flesh, that I may not cause my brother to stumble.
B046C009V001	46	9	1	Am I not a son of freedom? am I not an apostle? or have I not seen Jeshu Meshiha our Lord? or are not you my work in my Lord?
B046C009V002	46	9	2	And if to others I be not an apostle, yet am I (such) to you; and the seal of my apostleship are you.
B046C009V003	46	9	3	My apology to them who judge me is this:
B046C009V004	46	9	4	Have we not authority to eat and to drink?
B046C009V005	46	9	5	or have we not authority a sister, a wife, to lead about with us, as the rest of the apostles, and as the brethren of our Lord, and as Kipha?
B046C009V006	46	9	6	Or have I only, and Bar Naba, not authority to forbear from labour?
B046C009V007	46	9	7	Who serveth at service at the expenses of himself? or who planteth the vinery, and from the fruits thereof eateth not? or who pastureth sheep, and from the milk of the flock eateth not?
B046C009V008	46	9	8	Do I as a man speak these things? Behold, the law also saith these things.
B046C009V009	46	9	9	For it is written in the law of Musha, Thou shalt not muzzle the ox that treadeth out (the corn). But of oxen is Aloha careful?
B046C009V010	46	9	10	But it is evident that on our account this is said; for on our account it is written, because that in hope it behoveth the ploughman to plough, and him who thresheth, in hope of provision (to thresh).
B046C009V011	46	9	11	If we of the spirit have sown among you, is it a great thing if we from you of the body shall reap?
B046C009V012	46	9	12	And if others have this power over you, much more have we. But we are not used in this power; but we bear all, lest in any thing we should hinder the gospel of the Meshiha.
B046C009V013	46	9	13	KNOW you not that they who serve in the sanctuary from the sanctuary are sustained? And they who at the altar serve share with the altar?
B046C009V014	46	9	14	So also our Lord hath commanded, that they who his gospel preach, by his gospel shall live.
B046C009V015	46	9	15	But I am not used in one of these; nor on this account have I thus written, that so it should be done unto me: for it were better for me that dying I should die, than that any man my glorying should make void.
B046C009V016	46	9	16	Yet also in preaching I have no cause to glory: for necessity lieth upon me; for woe to me unless I preach!
B046C009V017	46	9	17	For if with my will I do this, I have a reward. But if without my will, (yet) a stewardship is confided to me.
B046C009V018	46	9	18	What, then, is my reward? That while preaching without expenses I may perform the annunciation of the Meshiha, and not abuse the power that is given to me in the gospel.
B046C009V019	46	9	19	For while free of all men, to all men I subject myself, that the many I may gain.
B046C009V020	46	9	20	And I become with the Jihudoyee as a Jihudoya, that the Jihudoyee I may gain; and with them who are under the law, I become as one under the law, that them who are under the law I may gain;
B046C009V021	46	9	21	and to those who have not the law I become as one without law, while I am not unto Aloha without law, but in the law of the Meshiha, that them also who have not law I may gain.
B046C009V022	46	9	22	I become with the weak as weak, that the weak I may gain. To all men all become I, that every man I may save.
B046C009V023	46	9	23	But this I do that I may be a participator in the gospel.
B046C009V024	46	9	24	Know you not, that they who run in the course, run all, but one taketh to him the victory? So run, that you may take hold.
B046C009V025	46	9	25	For every man who contendeth from every thing (besides with) holdeth his mind; and they who run (do it) that they may receive a crown that is corruptible, but we one that is incorruptible.
B046C009V026	46	9	26	I therefore so run, not as about a thing unknown; and so smite I, as not smiting the air;
B046C009V027	46	9	27	but my body I subdue and make subservient, lest when to others I shall have preached, I my very self shall be rejected.
B046C010V001	46	10	1	BUT I would that you know, my brethren, that all our fathers were under the cloud,
B046C010V002	46	10	2	and all of them in the sea were baptized, and all by
B046C010V003	46	10	3	Musha were baptized in the cloud and in the sea, and all of them ate one spiritual food, and all of them drank one spiritual drink;
B046C010V004	46	10	4	for they drank of that spiritual Rock which went with them,-but that Rock was the Meshiha himself.
B046C010V005	46	10	5	But not with many of them was Aloha pleased; for they fell in the desert.
B046C010V006	46	10	6	But these became an example for us; that we should not desire evils, as they desired;
B046C010V007	46	10	7	nor also be servers of idols, as some of them served; as it is written, The people sat down to eat and to drink, and rose up to play;
B046C010V008	46	10	8	nor commit fornication, as some of them committed, and fell, in one day, twenty and three thousand;
B046C010V009	46	10	9	nor tempt the Meshiha, as also (some) of them tempted, and perished by serpents.
B046C010V010	46	10	10	Neither murmur you, as some of them murmured, and perished by the hand of the destroyer.
B046C010V011	46	10	11	For all these which happened to them were unto us an example, and were written for our instruction, upon whom come the ends of the world.
B046C010V012	46	10	12	Whoever then thinketh he standeth, let him beware that he fall not.
B046C010V013	46	10	13	Temptation cometh not (upon) you but what cometh on mankind; but faithful is Aloha, who will not permit you to be tempted more than you are able, but will make to your temptation a departure, that you may be able to endure.
B046C010V014	46	10	14	WHEREFORE, my beloved, flee from the worship of idols.
B046C010V015	46	10	15	As to the wise I speak; judge what I say.
B046C010V016	46	10	16	The cup of thanksgiving which we bless, is it not the participation of the blood of the Meshiha? And the bread that we break, is it not the participation of the body of the Meshiha?
B046C010V017	46	10	17	As, then, one is that bread, so are we one body: for all we that one bread receive.
B046C010V018	46	10	18	Consider Israel who are in the flesh: are not they who eat of the sacrifices participators of the altar?
B046C010V019	46	10	19	What then do I say? that an idol is any thing, or (that) the sacrifice of an idol is any thing?
B046C010V020	46	10	20	No: but that which the Heathens sacrifice, unto demons they sacrifice, and not unto Aloha. But I would not that you be participators with demons!
B046C010V021	46	10	21	You cannot drink the cup of our Lord, and the cup of demons; and you cannot participate in the table of our Lord, and in the table of demons.
B046C010V022	46	10	22	Or, do we provoke the Lord? are we stronger than he?
B046C010V023	46	10	23	Every thing is lawful for me, but every thing is not expedient; every thing is lawful, but every thing doth not edify.
B046C010V024	46	10	24	Let no man seek his own (only), but every man also (the profit) of his neighbour.
B046C010V025	46	10	25	Whatsoever is sold in the shambles eat, without inquiry on account of conscience:
B046C010V026	46	10	26	for the earth is the Lord's, and its fulness.
B046C010V027	46	10	27	But if a man of the Heathens invite you, and you be willing to go, whatever is set before you eat, without inquiry on account of conscience.
B046C010V028	46	10	28	But, if one tell you, This is of a sacrifice, eat not, for his sake who hath told you, and on account of conscience;
B046C010V029	46	10	29	but I say, the conscience, not yours, but his who told you. But why is my liberty to be ruled by the conscience of others?
B046C010V030	46	10	30	But if I use (these things) by grace, why am I calumniated concerning that for which I give thanks?
B046C010V031	46	10	31	Whether therefore you eat or drink, or whatsoever you do, do all to the glory of Aloha.
B046C010V032	46	10	32	Give no offence to Jihudoyee, or to Aramoyee, or to the church of Aloha.
B046C010V033	46	10	33	As also I in every thing please all men, not seeking what is expedient for myself, but what is expedient for the many, that they may be saved.
B046C011V001	46	11	1	Be imitators of me, as I am of the Meshiha.
B046C011V002	46	11	2	But I commend you, my brethren, that in every thing you remember me; and that as I have delivered to you precepts, you hold them.
B046C011V003	46	11	3	But I would that you know that the Meshiha is the head of every man; and the head of the woman is the man, and the head of the Meshiha is Aloha.
B046C011V004	46	11	4	Every man who prayeth or prophesieth having his head covered, dishonoureth his head.
B046C011V005	46	11	5	And every woman who prayeth or prophesieth having her head uncovered, dishonoureth her head, for she is similar to one whose head is shaven.
B046C011V006	46	11	6	For if a woman be not covered, let her be shorn; but if it be shameful for a woman to be shorn or shaven, let her be covered.
B046C011V007	46	11	7	For a man is not obligated to cover his head, because he is the likeness and the glory of Aloha; but woman is the glory of man.
B046C011V008	46	11	8	For the man is not from woman, but the woman is from man.
B046C011V009	46	11	9	Neither was the man created for the sake of woman, but woman for the sake of man.
B046C011V010	46	11	10	Because of this the woman is a debtor, that the power shall be upon her head, on account of the angels.
B046C011V011	46	11	11	Nevertheless man is not without woman, neither is woman without man, in our Lord.
B046C011V012	46	11	12	For as a woman is from man, so is man by woman; but every thing is from Aloha.
B046C011V013	46	11	13	Judge among yourselves, Is it comely for a woman with her head revealed to pray to Aloha?
B046C011V014	46	11	14	Does not nature itself teach you, that when a man's hair standeth, it is a disgrace to him?
B046C011V015	46	11	15	But when a woman increaseth her hair, it is a glory to her; because her hair for a covering was given to her.
B046C011V016	46	11	16	But if any man contendeth about these things, we have no such usage as this, neither the church of Aloha.
B046C011V017	46	11	17	But this I prescribe not as praising you, because you go not forward, but to the less you descend.
B046C011V018	46	11	18	For, first, when you are assembled in the church, there are divisions, (as) I hear, among you, and in some measure I believe.
B046C011V019	46	11	19	For it is to be that contentions be among you, that they who are approved with you may be known.
B046C011V020	46	11	20	When then you are assembled, not as befitteth the day of the Lord you eat and drink,
B046C011V021	46	11	21	but each man his own supper before eateth, and one is hungry, and one drunken.
B046C011V022	46	11	22	What? have you not houses (in) which to eat and drink? Or do you despise the church of Aloha, and shame those who have nothing to eat? What do I say to you? Do I praise you in this? I praise you not.
B046C011V023	46	11	23	FOR I received from our Lord that which I have delivered unto you: that our Lord Jeshu in that night when he was betrayed took bread;
B046C011V024	46	11	24	and he blessed and brake, and said, Take, eat, this (is) my body which for you is broken: so do to my remembrance.
B046C011V025	46	11	25	Likewise after they had supped he gave also the cup, and said, This cup is the new covenant in my blood; so do, whensoever you shall drink (it) to my remembrance.
B046C011V026	46	11	26	For whensoever you eat this bread, and drink this cup, the death of our Lord you commemorate until his advent.
B046C011V027	46	11	27	Whoever then eateth of the bread of the Lord, and drinketh of his cup, and is not worthy of it, is guilty of the blood of the Lord and of his body.
B046C011V028	46	11	28	On this account a man should prove himself, and then eat of this bread, and drink of this cup.
B046C011V029	46	11	29	For whoever eateth and drinketh of it while not worthy, condemnation to himself he eateth and drinketh, because he hath not distinguished the body of the Lord.
B046C011V030	46	11	30	On this account many among you are sick and infirm, and many who sleep.
B046C011V031	46	11	31	For if we judge ourselves, we shall not be judged.
B046C011V032	46	11	32	But when we are judged of our Lord, we are chastised, that not with the world we might be condemned.
B046C011V033	46	11	33	Wherefore, my brethren, when you assemble to eat, wait for one another.
B046C011V034	46	11	34	But whoever hungereth, in his (own) house let him feed; that you may not assemble unto condemnation. Concerning the rest, when I come I will direct you.
B046C012V001	46	12	1	BUT concerning spirituals, my brethren, I wish you to know
B046C012V002	46	12	2	that you were Heathens, and unto idols which have no voice you were led without discernment .
B046C012V003	46	12	3	I therefore make known to you, that there is no man who by the Spirit of Aloha speaketh, and saith that Jeshu is accursed; and no man also can say that Jeshu is THE LORD unless by the Spirit of Holiness.
B046C012V004	46	12	4	Now, there are distributions of gifts, but one is the Spirit;
B046C012V005	46	12	5	and there are distributions of ministries, but one is the Lord;
B046C012V006	46	12	6	and distributions of powers, but one is Aloha, who worketh all in every man.
B046C012V007	46	12	7	But to each is given (such) a revelation of the Spirit as is profitable to him.
B046C012V008	46	12	8	To one is given by the Spirit the word of wisdom, but to another the word of knowledge by the same Spirit;
B046C012V009	46	12	9	and to another, faith by the same Spirit; and to another, the gifts of healing by the same Spirit;
B046C012V010	46	12	10	but to another, powers; to another, prophecy; to another, the discernment of spirits; but to another, kinds of tongues; and to another, the interpretation of tongues.
B046C012V011	46	12	11	But all these one Spirit effecteth, and divideth unto every man as he willeth.
B046C012V012	46	12	12	For, as the body is one, and in it are many members, but all the members of the body, though many, are one body; so also is the Meshiha.
B046C012V013	46	12	13	For we all by one Spirit into one body are baptized; whether Jihudoyee or Aramoyee; whether servants or sons of freedom; and all of us have imbibed one Spirit.
B046C012V014	46	12	14	For the body also is not one member, but many.
B046C012V015	46	12	15	For if the foot should say, Because I am not the hand, I am not of the body itself, would it therefore not be of the body itself?
B046C012V016	46	12	16	And if the ear should say, Because I am not the eye, I am not of the body itself, would it therefore not be of the body itself?
B046C012V017	46	12	17	For if the whole body were the eye, where would be the hearing? And if the whole were hearing, where would be the smelling?
B046C012V018	46	12	18	But now hath Aloha set all the members severally in the body as he willed.
B046C012V019	46	12	19	But if all were one member, where would be the body?
B046C012V020	46	12	20	But now the members are many, but the body one.
B046C012V021	46	12	21	The eye is not able to say to the hand, Thou art not needful to me; nor is the hand able to say to the feet, You are not needful to me.
B046C012V022	46	12	22	But those members which are considered to be feeble, of them is the more especial need;
B046C012V023	46	12	23	and those which we consider contemptible in the body, to these the more we increase the honour; and on those which are of shame we bestow the greater decoration.
B046C012V024	46	12	24	But those members that are honourable in us have no need of adornment: but Aloha hath contempered the body, and given the more honour to the member which is inconsiderable;
B046C012V025	46	12	25	that there should be no divisions in the body, but all the members equally one of the other should have care:
B046C012V026	46	12	26	as that when one member shall be diseased, all may suffer; and if one member be glorified, all the members may be glorified.
B046C012V027	46	12	27	But you are the body of the Meshiha, and members in your place.
B046C012V028	46	12	28	FOR Aloha hath placed in the church, first, apostles; after them, prophets; after them, teachers; after them, workers of miracles; after them, gifts of healing, and helpers, and leaders, and kinds of tongues.
B046C012V029	46	12	29	Are all apostles? Are all prophets? Are all teachers? Are all workers of miracles?
B046C012V030	46	12	30	Have all the gifts of healing? Do all speak with tongues, or do all interpret?
B046C012V031	46	12	31	But if you are emulous of great gifts, I will yet show you a way more admirable.
B046C013V001	46	13	1	Though in every tongue of men and of angels I spoke, and had not love, I should be as brass which soundeth, or a cymbal which giveth voice.
B046C013V002	46	13	2	And though there were in me prophecy, and I knew all mysteries, and all knowledge, and though there were in me all faith, as that I could remove the mountain, and love were not in me, I should be nothing.
B046C013V003	46	13	3	And if all I have I make to feed the poor, and I deliver my body to burn, and love be not in me, I profit nothing.
B046C013V004	46	13	4	LOVE is patient and benign; love envieth not; love is not tumultuous, nor inflated;
B046C013V005	46	13	5	it acteth not with unseemliness, nor seeketh its own; it is not angry, nor thoughtful of evil;
B046C013V006	46	13	6	it rejoiceth not in iniquity, but rejoiceth in the truth.
B046C013V007	46	13	7	It endureth every thing, believeth every thing; it hopeth all, endureth all.
B046C013V008	46	13	8	Love never falleth; for prophecies shall be abolished, and tongues be silent, and knowledge be abolished:
B046C013V009	46	13	9	for it is a little of much that we know, and a little of much we prophesy;
B046C013V010	46	13	10	but when the perfection shall have come, then shall be abolished that which is little.
B046C013V011	46	13	11	When I was a child, as a child I spake, and as a child I thought, and as a child I reasoned; but when I had become a man I abolished these things of childhood.
B046C013V012	46	13	12	But now as in a mirror we see in a figure; but then- the face before the face. Now I know a little of much; but then shall I know even as I am known.
B046C013V013	46	13	13	For these are the three that remain, faith and hope and love; but the greatest of these is love.
B046C014V001	46	14	1	Follow (then) after love, and be emulous of the gifts of the Spirit, but especially that you may prophesy.
B046C014V002	46	14	2	For whoever speaketh in a tongue speaketh not to men but to Aloha; for man heareth nothing that he speaketh but in the Spirit he speaketh mysteries.
B046C014V003	46	14	3	But he who prophesieth speaketh to men, edification and encouragement and consolation.
B046C014V004	46	14	4	He who speaketh in a tongue himself edifieth, and he who prophesieth the church edifieth.
B046C014V005	46	14	5	But I would that all of you could speak with tongues, but especially that you could prophesy. For greater is he who prophesieth than he who speaketh with tongues, unless he interpret. But if he interpret, he edifieth the church.
B046C014V006	46	14	6	And now, my brethren, if I come to you and speak with you in tongues, what do I profit you, unless I speak with you, or by revelation, or by knowledge, or by prophecy, or by doctrine?
B046C014V007	46	14	7	For those also which have no life in them, and give voice, whether pipe or harp, if distinction be not made between a tone and its fellow, how can it be known what is sung, or what is played?
B046C014V008	46	14	8	And if the trumpet call a voice which is not distinguished, who will prepare for the battle?
B046C014V009	46	14	9	So you also, if you speak the word in a tongue, and there be no interpretation, how will it be known what you say? Will you not be as if speaking with the air?
B046C014V010	46	14	10	For, behold, there are many kinds of tongues in the world, and not one of them hath not signification;
B046C014V011	46	14	11	but if I do not know the power of the voice, I become as a barbarian to him who speaks, and he also who speaks is a barbarian to me.
B046C014V012	46	14	12	So also you, while you are emulous of the gifts of the Spirit for the edification of the church, seek that you may excel.
B046C014V013	46	14	13	And let him who speaketh with tongues pray that he may interpret.
B046C014V014	46	14	14	For if I am praying in a tongue, my spirit prayeth, but my mind is without fruit.
B046C014V015	46	14	15	What shall I do then? I will pray with my spirit, and I will pray with my mind; and I will sing with my spirit, and I will sing with my mind.
B046C014V016	46	14	16	Otherwise, if thou bless with the spirit, how shall he who filleth the place of the unlearned say Amen to thy thanksgiving? for he knoweth not what thou sayest.
B046C014V017	46	14	17	For thou blessest well, but thy neighbour is not edified.
B046C014V018	46	14	18	I praise Aloha that more than all of you I speak with tongues;
B046C014V019	46	14	19	but in the church I would rather speak five words with my mind, that others also may learn, than ten thousand words in a tongue.
B046C014V020	46	14	20	MY brethren, be not children in your minds, but in evils be you babes, and in your minds be perfect.
B046C014V021	46	14	21	In the law it is written, In a strange language and in another tongue Will I speak with this people; Yet so will they not hear me, saith the Lord.
B046C014V022	46	14	22	Hence, tongues are appointed for a sign, not to the believing, but to those who believe not: but prophecy, not for those who believe not, but for those who believe.
B046C014V023	46	14	23	If then all the church be assembled, and all of you speak with tongues, and the ignorant, or those who believe not enter, will they not say you are insane?
B046C014V024	46	14	24	And if all should prophesy, and there come in to you the ignorant, or of those who believe not, he is convicted by you all, and reproved by you all;
B046C014V025	46	14	25	and the secrets of his heart are revealed; and then will he fall upon his face and worship Aloha, and say, Truly Aloha is in you.
B046C014V026	46	14	26	I say then, my brethren, that when you are assembled, if any one of you hath a psalm, let him speak; and (so too) he who hath doctrine, and he who hath a revelation, and he who hath a tongue, and he who hath the interpretation: let all be done unto edification.
B046C014V027	46	14	27	And if with a tongue any one speak, two shall speak, or at most three, and each shall (separately) speak, and one interpret.
B046C014V028	46	14	28	And if there be no one who interpreteth, let him who speaketh with a tongue be silent in the church, and between himself and Aloha let him speak.
B046C014V029	46	14	29	Let the prophets speak, two or three, and let the rest discern.
B046C014V030	46	14	30	And if to another be revealed while sitting, let the first be silent.
B046C014V031	46	14	31	For one by one you can all prophesy, that each may learn, and each be edified.
B046C014V032	46	14	32	For the spirit of the prophets to the prophets is subject.
B046C014V033	46	14	33	Because Aloha is not of tumult, but of peace, as in all the churches of the saints.
B046C014V034	46	14	34	LET your women in the church be silent; for it is not permitted to them to speak, but to be subject, as also saith the law.
B046C014V035	46	14	35	But if any wish to learn, in their houses let them ask their husbands; for it is a shame for a woman to speak in the church.
B046C014V036	46	14	36	Was it from you that the word of Aloha went forth? Or did it come only to you?
B046C014V037	46	14	37	But if any man of you think that he is a prophet, or that he is spiritual, let him acknowledge these which I write to you to be the commandments of our Lord.
B046C014V038	46	14	38	But if any man know not, let him not know.
B046C014V039	46	14	39	Be emulous, therefore, my brethren, to prophesy, and to speak with tongues forbid not;
B046C014V040	46	14	40	but let every thing be done with decency and in order.
B046C015V001	46	15	1	BUT I make known to you, my brethren, the gospel which I have announced to you, and you have received, and in which you stand,
B046C015V002	46	15	2	and by which you are saved; of which, the word I have preached to you, you are mindful, unless you have vainly believed.
B046C015V003	46	15	3	For I delivered to you from the first, according as I had received: That the Meshiha died for our sins, as it is written;
B046C015V004	46	15	4	and that he was buried, and arose the third day, as it is written.
B046C015V005	46	15	5	And he was seen of Kipha, and after him, of the twelve,
B046C015V006	46	15	6	and after them, he was seen of more than five hundred brethren together, many of whom survive till now, and some of them have slept.
B046C015V007	46	15	7	And afterward he was seen of Jakub, and after him of all the apostles:
B046C015V008	46	15	8	but last of them all, as of an abortion, he was seen also of me.
B046C015V009	46	15	9	I am the least of the apostles, and am not worthy to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the church of Aloha:
B046C015V010	46	15	10	but by the grace of Aloha I am what I am; and his grace in me was not in vain; but more than all have I laboured, (yet) not I, but his grace which is with me.
B046C015V011	46	15	11	Whether I then, or they, so we have proclaimed, and so have you believed.
B046C015V012	46	15	12	But if the Meshiha is proclaimed that he rose from the dead, how are there among you some who say that there is no life for the dead?
B046C015V013	46	15	13	And if there be no life for the dead, (then) neither hath the Meshiha risen.
B046C015V014	46	15	14	And if the Meshiha hath not risen, vain is our proclamation, and vain also your faith.
B046C015V015	46	15	15	But we are also found false witnesses of Aloha; for we have testified of Aloha that he hath raised the Meshiha, while he hath not raised (him).
B046C015V016	46	15	16	For if the dead rise not, Meshiha also hath not risen
B046C015V017	46	15	17	and if Meshiha hath not risen, your faith is made void and you are still in your sins.
B046C015V018	46	15	18	And already have they too who have slept in Meshiha perished.
B046C015V019	46	15	19	And if in this life only we hope in the Meshiha, more miserable are we than all men.
B046C015V020	46	15	20	BUT now hath the Meshiha risen from among the dead, and become the first-fruits of those who sleep.
B046C015V021	46	15	21	And as by man was death, so also by man is the life of the dead.
B046C015V022	46	15	22	For as in Adam all men die, so also in the Meshiha are all made alive:
B046C015V023	46	15	23	every one in his order: the first-fruits was the Meshiha; afterward they who are of the Meshiha at his coming.
B046C015V024	46	15	24	And then will be the end, when he delivereth the kingdom unto Aloha the Father; when he abolisheth every head, and all authority and all powers.
B046C015V025	46	15	25	For it is to be that he shall reign until he hath set all his adversaries beneath his feet,
B046C015V026	46	15	26	and the last enemy be abolished, (which is) death.
B046C015V027	46	15	27	For every thing he subjecteth beneath his feet. But when he saith that every thing is subjected to him, it is evident that (it is) with the exception of him who hath subjected to him all.
B046C015V028	46	15	28	And when all shall have been subjected to him, then the Son himself will be subjected to him who had made subject to him all, that Aloha may be all in all.
B046C015V029	46	15	29	Else what shall they do who are baptized for the dead, if the dead arise not? Why are they baptized for the dead?
B046C015V030	46	15	30	And why also every hour are we standing in peril?
B046C015V031	46	15	31	I asseverate, by your glorying, my brethren, which is mine in our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, that daily I die!
B046C015V032	46	15	32	If as among men I have been thrown to beasts at Ephesus, what have I profited if the dead do not arise? Let us eat and drink, for to-morrow we die.
B046C015V033	46	15	33	Mistake not; for Evil narrations corrupt well-disposed minds.
B046C015V034	46	15	34	AWAKEN your hearts rightly, and sin not; for there are some who have not the knowledge of Aloha; to your shame I say it.
B046C015V035	46	15	35	Some one of you will say, How arise the dead, and with what body come they?
B046C015V036	46	15	36	Fool, the seed which thou sowest, unless it die, lives not:
B046C015V037	46	15	37	and that thing which thou sowest is not the body that is to be, but thou sowest naked grain, of wheat, or of barley, or of the rest of seeds;
B046C015V038	46	15	38	but Aloha giveth it a body as he willeth, and to each of the seeds a body of its own nature.
B046C015V039	46	15	39	For every body is not alike: for there is one body of man, and another of the beast, and another of the fowl, and another of fishes.
B046C015V040	46	15	40	There are heavenly bodies, and there are earthly bodies; but one is the glory of the heavenly, and another of the earthly.
B046C015V041	46	15	41	There is one glory of the sun, and another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars; and star excelleth star in glory.
B046C015V042	46	15	42	So also is the life of the dead. They are sown in corruption, they arise without corruption.
B046C015V043	46	15	43	They are sown in baseness, they arise in glory. They are sown in weakness, they arise in power.
B046C015V044	46	15	44	It is sown an animal body, it ariseth a body spiritual. For there is a body of the animal, and there is a body of the spirit;
B046C015V045	46	15	45	as also it is written, Adam the first man became a living soul, and the last Adam a life-giving spirit.
B046C015V046	46	15	46	But the spiritual was not first, but the animal; and then the spiritual.
B046C015V047	46	15	47	The first man who is of the earth is dust, the second man the Lord from heaven.
B046C015V048	46	15	48	As was he who was dust, so also are they who are dust: as is he who is from heaven, so also are the heavenly ones.
B046C015V049	46	15	49	And as we have worn the likeness of him who was dust, so shall we wear the likeness of him who is from heaven.
B046C015V050	46	15	50	But this I say, my brethren, that flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of heaven; nor doth corruption inherit incorruption.
B046C015V051	46	15	51	Behold, I tell you the mystery; We shall not all sleep, but we all shall be changed:
B046C015V052	46	15	52	suddenly, as in the twinkling of the eye, at the last trumpet, while it calleth; and the dead will arise without corruption, and we shall be changed.
B046C015V053	46	15	53	For this which is corruptible shall put on incorruption, and likewise (this) which dieth shall put on immortality.
B046C015V054	46	15	54	But when this which is corruptible shall put on incorruptibleness, and this which dieth, immortality, then shall be done that word which is written, Death is swallowed up in victory!
B046C015V055	46	15	55	Where is thy sting, Death? and where is thy victory Shiul?
B046C015V056	46	15	56	But the sting of death is sin, and the strength of sin is the law.
B046C015V057	46	15	57	But thanks be to Aloha, who giveth us the victory by the hand of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B046C015V058	46	15	58	Wherefore, my brethren, my beloved, be steadfast, be not moved, but be abounding in all time in the work of the Lord, while you know that your labour is not in vain in the Lord.
B046C016V001	46	16	1	BUT concerning what is collected for the saints, as I have instructed the churches of Galatia, so also do you.
B046C016V002	46	16	2	On each first day of the week let every one of you at his own house lay by and keep something of that which cometh unto his hands, lest when I come there be then collections.
B046C016V003	46	16	3	And when I come, those whom you shall choose, them will I send with an epistle, that they may take your bounty to Urishlem.
B046C016V004	46	16	4	But if it be a fit work that I too go (thither), they also shall go with me.
B046C016V005	46	16	5	But I will come to you when I shall have passed (round) from Makedunia: for I pass unto it, unto Makedunia.
B046C016V006	46	16	6	And perhaps also I may remain with you, or I may winter with you, that you may lead me on to the place to which I shall go.
B046C016V007	46	16	7	For I will not now see you as I pass the way; for I hope to abide a time with you, if my Lord permit me.
B046C016V008	46	16	8	For I remain at Ephesos until the Pentecost.
B046C016V009	46	16	9	For a great door is opened to me, which is full of labours, and the opposers are many.
B046C016V010	46	16	10	But if Timotheos come among you, see that he may be with you without fear; for he doeth the work of the Lord, as I .
B046C016V011	46	16	11	Wherefore let no man despise him, but conduct him in peace, that he may come to me; for I wait for him with the brethren.
B046C016V012	46	16	12	But of Apolo, my brethren, I begged much to come to you with the brethren; nevertheless it was not his will to come to you; but when there shall be opportunity he will come to you.
B046C016V013	46	16	13	WATCH, and stand in the faith; be manful and be strong.
B046C016V014	46	16	14	And let all your affairs be done in love.
B046C016V015	46	16	15	But I entreat of you, my brethren, for the house of Stephano, because you know they are the first-fruits of Akaia, and have disposed themselves for the service of the saints,
B046C016V016	46	16	16	that you be submissive to such as they, and to every one who laboureth with us and helpeth.
B046C016V017	46	16	17	But I am glad of the coming of Stephano, and of Fortunatos, and of Akaiakos, because your deficiency with me they have fulfilled.
B046C016V018	46	16	18	For they have refreshed my spirit and yours. Wherefore acknowledge those who are such.
B046C016V019	46	16	19	All the churches of Asia ask for your peace; Akilos and Priskila, with the church which is in their house, ask for your peace greatly in our Lord.
B046C016V020	46	16	20	All the brethren ask for your peace. Ask the peace of one another with the holy kiss.
B046C016V021	46	16	21	Peace, by the writing of my hand, of PAULOS.
B046C016V022	46	16	22	Whosoever loveth not our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, let him be accursed. Our Lord cometh.
B046C016V023	46	16	23	The grace of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha be with you.
B046C016V024	46	16	24	And my love be with you all in the Meshiha Jeshu Amen.
B047C001V001	47	1	1	PAULOS, apostle of Jeshu Meshiha, by the will of Aloha; and Timotheos a brother: to the church of Aloha which is in Kurinthos, and to all the saints who are in all Akaia.
B047C001V002	47	1	2	Grace be with you and peace, from Aloha our Father, and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B047C001V003	47	1	3	Blessed be Aloha, the Father of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, the Father of mercies, and the God of all consolation, who consoleth us in all our afflictions,
B047C001V004	47	1	4	that we may be able to console those who are in all afflictions by that consolation by which we are consoled of Aloha.
B047C001V005	47	1	5	For as the sufferings of the Meshiha abound in us, so, through the Meshiha, our consolation aboundeth also.
B047C001V006	47	1	6	But if we are afflicted, it is for your consolation and for your salvation that we be afflicted: and if we are consoled, it is that you may be consoled, that there may be in you perseverance to endure those sufferings which we also suffer.
B047C001V007	47	1	7	And our hope concerning you is steadfast: for we know that if you participate in the sufferings, you also participate in the consolation.
B047C001V008	47	1	8	FOR I would have you to know, my brethren, of the affliction that befell us in Asia: for we were greatly pressed beyond our strength, until our life was nigh to be dissolved,
B047C001V009	47	1	9	and because of these we had concluded (for) death; that we should not have hope in ourselves, but in Aloha, who raiseth the dead:
B047C001V010	47	1	10	who from deaths of violence delivered us, and who will again, we trust, deliver us,
B047C001V011	47	1	11	through the help of your prayers for us; that his gift towards us may be a benefit effected for many, and many may praise him on our behalf.
B047C001V012	47	1	12	For our glorying is this, the testimony of our conscience, that in simplicity and purity, and by the grace of Aloha, we are conversant in the world; and not with the wisdom of the flesh, and especially with you yourselves.
B047C001V013	47	1	13	For we write no other (things) to you than those which you know and acknowledge, and which I am confident you will acknowledge unto the end:
B047C001V014	47	1	14	even as you have in part acknowledged that we are your glorying, as you also are ours in the day of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B047C001V015	47	1	15	And in this confidence I have willed from the first to come to you, that doubly you may receive benefit,
B047C001V016	47	1	16	and that I may pass by you to Makedunia, and again from Makedunia I may come to you, and you may lead me forth unto Jihud.
B047C001V017	47	1	17	This then that I have purposed, have I purposed boastingly? or are they things of the flesh that I purpose, that I should have in them Yes, yes, or No, no?
B047C001V018	47	1	18	Faithful is Aloha that our word with you was not Yes and No.
B047C001V019	47	1	19	For the Son of Aloha, Jeshu Meshiha, who by us hath been preached unto you, by me and by Sylvanas and by Timotheos, was not Yes and No, but it was Yes in him.
B047C001V020	47	1	20	For all the promises of Aloha in him, in the Meshiha, are Yes; for which by him we give Amen to the glory of Aloha.
B047C001V021	47	1	21	But Aloha himself confirmeth us with you in the Meshiha, who himself hath anointed us,
B047C001V022	47	1	22	and hath sealed us, and given us the earnest-pledge of his Spirit in our hearts.
B047C001V023	47	1	23	BUT I testify to Aloha on my soul that because I am sparing of you, I have not come to Kurinthos.
B047C001V024	47	1	24	Not because we are lords of your faith, but are helpers of your joy; for by faith you stand.
B047C002V001	47	2	1	But I have determined this in myself, that I will not with sorrow again come to you.
B047C002V002	47	2	2	For if I grieve you, who shall refresh me, but he whom I had grieved?
B047C002V003	47	2	3	And I have written to you this very, lest when I come they grieve me, they who ought to refresh me. But I confide in you, that my joy is that of all of you.
B047C002V004	47	2	4	And from great affliction and anxiety of heart I wrote those things to you with many tears, not that you might grieve, but (also) that you might know the abundant love I have towards you.
B047C002V005	47	2	5	But if any one hath caused grief, he hath not grieved me (only), but a part of you all: that the word may not weigh upon you.
B047C002V006	47	2	6	But sufficient for him was this chastisement, which was from many.
B047C002V007	47	2	7	And now on the other hand it behoves you to forgive him and console him, lest he who is such an one be swallowed up of excessive grief.
B047C002V008	47	2	8	Therefore I entreat of you to confirm to him your love.
B047C002V009	47	2	9	On this account also I have written, to ascertain by experiment whether in every thing you will obey me.
B047C002V010	47	2	10	But to whom you forgive, I also. For I, too, what I have forgiven, have on your account forgiven in the presence of the Meshiha:
B047C002V011	47	2	11	lest Satana get the advantage of you; for we know his devices.
B047C002V012	47	2	12	WHEN, in preaching the gospel of the Meshiha, I had come to Troas, and a door was opened to me by the Lord,
B047C002V013	47	2	13	I had no rest in my spirit because I found not Titos my brother. But leaving them, I went forth to Makedunia.
B047C002V014	47	2	14	But thanks unto Aloha, who in all time maketh us a triumph in the Meshiha, and maketh manifest by us the perfume of his knowledge in every place.
B047C002V015	47	2	15	For we are a fragrant perfume in the Meshiha unto Aloha in those who are saved, and in those who perish.
B047C002V016	47	2	16	To these as a perfume of death unto death, and to those as a perfume of life unto life. And unto these who is equal?
B047C002V017	47	2	17	For we are not as the rest who commix the word of Aloha; but as in truth, and as from Aloha, before Aloha in the Meshiha do we speak.
B047C003V001	47	3	1	Do we begin again anew to show who we are? or do we need as others to write epistles of commendation to you concerning ourselves, or that you should write to commend us?
B047C003V002	47	3	2	But you yourselves are our epistle, written in our hearts, and known and read of every man.
B047C003V003	47	3	3	For you know that you are an epistle of the Meshiha, who hath been ministered by us; written, not with ink but by the Spirit of Aloha the Living; not on tablets of stone, but on the fleshly tablets of the heart.
B047C003V004	47	3	4	BUT such confidence we have through the Meshiha toward Aloha.
B047C003V005	47	3	5	For we are not sufficient to think any thing as of ourselves; but our power is from Aloha,
B047C003V006	47	3	6	who hath made us fit to be ministers of the new covenant, not in the writing, but in the spirit. For the writing killeth, but the Spirit maketh alive.
B047C003V007	47	3	7	But if the ministry of death in the writing engraven on stones was with glory, as that the sons of Israel could not look on the face of Musha because of the glory of his face which is abolished,
B047C003V008	47	3	8	how much more then doth not the ministry Of the Spirit excel in glory?
B047C003V009	47	3	9	For if the ministry of condemnation was glorious, how much more doth not the ministry of justification excel in glory?
B047C003V010	47	3	10	For that which was glorified had no glory, in comparison of this excelling glory.
B047C003V011	47	3	11	For if that which was abolished was with glory, how much more shall that which endureth be with glory?
B047C003V012	47	3	12	Therefore because we have this hope, we speak the more boldly,
B047C003V013	47	3	13	and (are) not as Musha, who threw the veil upon his face, that the sons of Israel might not look upon the End of that which was to be abolished.
B047C003V014	47	3	14	But they are blinded in their minds unto this day. For when the old covenant is read, that very veil standeth upon them, nor is it apparent (to them) that in the Meshiha it hath been abolished.
B047C003V015	47	3	15	And unto this day, when Musha is read, the veil is thrown upon their heart.
B047C003V016	47	3	16	And when any one of them is converted unto the Lord, the veil from him is uplifted.
B047C003V017	47	3	17	But the Lord himself is the Spirit; and where the Spirit of the Lord, (there) is liberty.
B047C003V018	47	3	18	But we all with disclosed faces behold the glory of the Lord as in a mirror, and into the resemblance of it are changed from brightness to brightness, as by the Lord the Spirit.
B047C004V001	47	4	1	ON this account we have not weariness in this ministry which we have received, according to the mercies that are upon us.
B047C004V002	47	4	2	But we have rejected the secrets of shamefulness; and walk not with craft, nor deal deceitfully (with) the word of Aloha; but by the revelation of the truth make we ourselves manifest to the minds of all men before Aloha.
B047C004V003	47	4	3	But if our gospel is hid, to those who perish is it hid:
B047C004V004	47	4	4	(to) them whose minds the god of this world hath blinded because they believe not; lest the light of the gospel of the glory of Meshiha, who is the image of Aloha, should arise upon them.
B047C004V005	47	4	5	For we preach not ourselves, but the Meshiha, Jeshu our Lord; but ourselves that we are your servants for the sake of Jeshu.
B047C004V006	47	4	6	For Aloha, who said, Let light arise from darkness, hath arisen in our hearts; that we should be illuminated by the knowledge of the glory of Aloha in the face of Jeshu Meshiha.
B047C004V007	47	4	7	BUT we have this treasure in a vase of earth, that the greatness of the power might be from Aloha, and not from us.
B047C004V008	47	4	8	But in every thing we are afflicted, yet not strangled; we are beaten, yet not condemned;
B047C004V009	47	4	9	persecuted, yet not forsaken; cast down, yet we perish not.
B047C004V010	47	4	10	In all time the dying of Jeshu in our bodies we bear, that the life also of Jeshu might in our bodies be revealed.
B047C004V011	47	4	11	For if we, the living, unto death are delivered on account of Jeshu, so also will the life of Jeshu be revealed in this our body of death.
B047C004V012	47	4	12	Now death in us worketh earnestly, but life in you.
B047C004V013	47	4	13	We then also who have one spirit of faith, as it is written, I have believed, and therefore also spoken; we believe, therefore also we speak.
B047C004V014	47	4	14	And we know that He who raised up our Lord Jeshu, will by Jeshu raise us also, and will present us with you unto himself.
B047C004V015	47	4	15	For every thing is for your sake, that grace, abounding by many, may multiply praise to the glory of Aloha.
B047C004V016	47	4	16	For this cause we have not weariness; for if our outward man is wasted, yet the interior man is renovated day by day.
B047C004V017	47	4	17	For the affliction of this time, while small and light, a glory without end for ever and ever prepareth for us.
B047C004V018	47	4	18	While we look not on these which are seen, but at those which are unseen. For the seen are of time, but the unseen are of eternity.
B047C005V001	47	5	1	FOR we know that if our earthly house of this body were dissolved, we have nevertheless a building that is by Aloha; a house which is not made with hands, in the heaven, eternal.
B047C005V002	47	5	2	For concerning this also we groan, and long to put on our house which is from heaven,
B047C005V003	47	5	3	if, when that we have clothed, we may not be found naked.
B047C005V004	47	5	4	For now while we are in this house, we groan from the weight of it: yet are we not willing to cast it off, but to be clothed upon of it, that its mortality might be swallowed up in life.
B047C005V005	47	5	5	And he who prepareth us for this is Aloha, who hath given to us the earnest-pledge of his Spirit.
B047C005V006	47	5	6	For therefore do we know and are persuaded, that so long as we remain in the body we are in pilgrimage from our Lord.
B047C005V007	47	5	7	For by faith we walk, and not by sight.
B047C005V008	47	5	8	On this account we confide, and long to pass away from the body, and to be with our Lord.
B047C005V009	47	5	9	We give diligence, that whether we are pilgrims or inhabitants, we may be pleasing unto Him.
B047C005V010	47	5	10	For we are all to stand before the tribunal of the Meshiha, that every man may be recompensed in his body (for) that which is done in it, whether of good or of evil.
B047C005V011	47	5	11	THEREFORE, because we know the terror of our Lord, we persuade men; and to Aloha we are manifest; but I hope that to your minds also we are manifest.
B047C005V012	47	5	12	For we commend not ourselves again to you, but we give you cause to be boastful of us to them who in appearance boast, but not in heart.
B047C005V013	47	5	13	For if we be beside ourselves, (it is) unto Aloha; and if we be right, (it is) unto you.
B047C005V014	47	5	14	For the love of the Meshiha constraineth us, because we judge this, That if one for every man hath died, then (was) every man dead.
B047C005V015	47	5	15	And for every man he died, that they who live should not live to themselves, but to him who on their behalf died and arose.
B047C005V016	47	5	16	And henceforth we no man know according to the flesh; and if we have known the Meshiha according to the flesh, yet from now we know not.
B047C005V017	47	5	17	Whoever therefore is in the Meshiha is a new creature; the old things have passed, and every thing hath become new
B047C005V018	47	5	18	from Aloha, who hath reconciled us to himself in the Meshiha, and given to us the ministry of reconciliation.
B047C005V019	47	5	19	For Aloha is in the Meshiha, who hath reconciled the world with his greatness; and he hath not reckoned unto them their sins, and hath put in us the word of reconciliation.
B047C005V020	47	5	20	WE are ambassadors then for the Meshiha, and as if Aloha himself besought you by us: instead of the Meshiha, therefore, we beseech, Be you reconciled unto Aloha.
B047C005V021	47	5	21	For Him who knew not sin, on our account hath he made sin, that we might be in him the righteousness of Aloha.
B047C006V001	47	6	1	And as helpers, we beseech of you that the grace of Aloha which you have received be not made ineffectual in you.
B047C006V002	47	6	2	For he hath said, In the time acceptable I have heard thee, And in the day of salvation I have helped thee. Behold, Now is the time acceptable; behold, Now is the day of salvation.
B047C006V003	47	6	3	Nor in any thing give to any man occasion of stumbling, that no blemish may be upon our ministry;
B047C006V004	47	6	4	but in every thing will we demonstrate ourselves that we are the ministers of Aloha; by much patience, by afflictions, by necessity, by imprisonments,
B047C006V005	47	6	5	by stripes, by chains, by tumults, by labour, by watching, by fasting,
B047C006V006	47	6	6	by purity, by knowledge, by prolonging the mind, by benignity, by the Spirit of Holiness, by love without deceit,
B047C006V007	47	6	7	by the doctrine of truth, by the power of Aloha, by the arms of righteousness for the right hand and for the left,
B047C006V008	47	6	8	by glory and by shame, by praise and by abuse; as deceivers, and true;
B047C006V009	47	6	9	as unknown, and yet we are known; as dead, yet, lo, we live; as chastened, yet we die not;
B047C006V010	47	6	10	as sorrowful, yet always rejoicing; as poor, yet many making rich; as having nothing, yet possessing every thing.
B047C006V011	47	6	11	OUR mouth is opened to you, Kurinthoyee, and our heart expanded.
B047C006V012	47	6	12	You are not constrained in us, but you are constrained in your own bowels.
B047C006V013	47	6	13	But as unto (my) children, I say to you, Render to me my gains which are with you, and expand your love towards me.
B047C006V014	47	6	14	And be not sons of the yoke with them who believe not. For what participation hath righteousness with iniquity? Or what commixture hath the light with darkness?
B047C006V015	47	6	15	Or what concord hath the Meshiha with Satana? Or what portion hath the believer with the unbeliever?
B047C006V016	47	6	16	Or what union hath the temple of Aloha with (that) of demons? For you are the temple of Aloha the living; as it is written, I will dwell in them, and walk in them; And I will be their God, And they shall be to me a people.
B047C006V017	47	6	17	Wherefore come out from among them, And be separate from them, (saith the Lord,) And the impure touch not; And I will receive you,
B047C006V018	47	6	18	And I will be to you a Father, And you shall be to me for sons and daughters, Saith the Lord, who holdeth all.
B047C007V001	47	7	1	Because then we have these promises, my beloved, let us cleanse ourselves from all impurity of the flesh and of the spirit, and accomplish sanctification in the fear of Aloha.
B047C007V002	47	7	2	Bear with us, my brethren; we have wronged no man, we have corrupted no man, we have injured no man.
B047C007V003	47	7	3	I speak not to your condemnation; for I have said already, that you are laid up in our hearts to die together and to live.
B047C007V004	47	7	4	GREAT is the freedom I have with you, and great in you is my glorying; I am full of consolation, and my joy greatly aboundeth in me in all my afflictions.
B047C007V005	47	7	5	When, also, we had come into Makedunia, no repose had we for our body, but in every thing were we afflicted; without fighting, and within, fear.
B047C007V006	47	7	6	But Aloha, who consoleth the humble, consoled us by the coming of Titos;
B047C007V007	47	7	7	and not only by his coming, but also by his refreshment wherewith he had been refreshed among you. For he told us of your love toward us, and of your lamentation and your zeal on our behalf. And when I heard, my joy was great.
B047C007V008	47	7	8	For though I grieved you in an epistle, I repent me not, though I did repent. For I perceive how that epistle, though for an hour, did make you sorry;
B047C007V009	47	7	9	but now I exercise joy, not because you were made sorry, but because your sorrow hath brought you to repentance. For you were sorry towards Aloha; so that in nothing will you suffer loss from us.
B047C007V010	47	7	10	For the sorrow that is for the sake of Aloha worketh soul-penitence, which turneth not and converteth, unto salvation; but the sorrow of the world worketh death.
B047C007V011	47	7	11	For, behold, (in) this very (case) that you were made contrite for the sake of Aloha; what carefulness it wrought in you, and vindication, and displeasure, and fear, and love, and zeal, and punishment! And by every thing have you shown yourselves to be pure in this matter.
B047C007V012	47	7	12	But, it was for this we wrote to you; not on account of the injurer, nor on account of the injured one, but that you may know before Aloha our carefulness over you.
B047C007V013	47	7	13	For this cause we were consoled, and with our consolation more abundantly did we rejoice in the joy of Titos; because his spirit had been refreshed with you all.
B047C007V014	47	7	14	Because in whatever I had boasted to him concerning you, I have not been ashamed; but, as of every thing we had spoken truth with you, so also our boasting unto Titos hath been found in truth.
B047C007V015	47	7	15	And his affection is greatly enlarged toward you, when he remembers your obedience; because with fear and with trembling you received him.
B047C007V016	47	7	16	I rejoice that in every thing I can confide in you.
B047C008V001	47	8	1	BUT we make known to you, my brethren, the grace of Aloha which hath been given to the churches of Makedunia;
B047C008V002	47	8	2	that in the great trial of their affliction there hath been an abounding of their joy; and the depth of their poverty hath been exceeded by the riches of their simplicity.
B047C008V003	47	8	3	For I testify, that according to their power, and more than their power, in the willingness of their soul,
B047C008V004	47	8	4	they besought of us, with much supplication, that they might participate in the beneficence of the ministry for the saints.
B047C008V005	47	8	5	And not as we had supposed, but they gave themselves up first to the Lord, and also to us by the will of Aloha.
B047C008V006	47	8	6	For we would request of Titos, that as he had begun, so he would carry into accomplishment this beneficence among you also.
B047C008V007	47	8	7	But as you have excelled in every thing, in faith, and in doctrine, and in knowledge, and in all diligence, and in our love toward you, so also in this beneficence may you excel.
B047C008V008	47	8	8	Not as though commanding I command you, but, from the diligence of your companions, the truth of your love would I put to the test.
B047C008V009	47	8	9	FOR you know the beneficence of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, that for your sake he became poor, though he was rich, that you through his poverty might be enriched.
B047C008V010	47	8	10	But counselling I counsel you this which helpeth you; because from the last year you began not to will only, but also to do.
B047C008V011	47	8	11	But now accomplish in work that which you willed, that as there hath been an incitement to will, so accomplish it in work from what you have.
B047C008V012	47	8	12	For if there be the will, according to what one hath, so is (he) accepted, and not according to what he hath not.
B047C008V013	47	8	13	Neither must there be to others ease, and to you anxiety,
B047C008V014	47	8	14	but in equality be you at this time; that your abundance may be a supply to their want, that also their abundance may be for to your want, that there may be equality.
B047C008V015	47	8	15	As it is written, He who took up much had no superfluity, and he who took up little was not deficient.
B047C008V016	47	8	16	But praise to Aloha who in-gave this solicitude for you to the heart of Titos.
B047C008V017	47	8	17	For our request he accepted; and because he had great concern, of his own will he hath come forth among you.
B047C008V018	47	8	18	But we have sent with him our brother, whose praise in the gospel is in all the churches;
B047C008V019	47	8	19	who hath, moreover, been chosen by the churches to go forth with us with this bounty which is ministered by us to the glory of Aloha himself, and unto our cordiality.
B047C008V020	47	8	20	For we are precautious in this, that no one should lay upon us any imputation
B047C008V021	47	8	21	with regard to this great bounty which is to be administered by us. For we are careful for the things which are comely, not only before Aloha, but also before men.
B047C008V022	47	8	22	But we have also sent with them our brother, whom we have often proved in many to be diligent; but now still more diligent from the great confidence he hath concerning you.
B047C008V023	47	8	23	Whether, then, (you regard) Titos, he is my companion and helper among you, or the other brethren, they are the apostles of the churches of the glory of Meshiha.
B047C008V024	47	8	24	Wherefore the demonstration of your love, and of our boasting concerning you in these, make manifest in the sight of all the churches.
B047C009V001	47	9	1	BUT concerning the administration of the saints, I do more (than enough) if I write to you.
B047C009V002	47	9	2	For I know the goodness of your mind, of which I boasted of you to the Makedunoyee, that Akaia was ready since last year, and your zeal hath stirred up many.
B047C009V003	47	9	3	But I have sent the brethren to you, that our boasting which we boasted of you may not in this affair be vain; but, as I have said, you may be ready:
B047C009V004	47	9	4	lest, if the Makedunoyee should come with me, and find you not ready, we be shamed-that I may not say, you be shamed-of the boasting which we have boasted.
B047C009V005	47	9	5	For this cause I have been careful to entreat of these brethren to go before to you, to make ready that blessing of which you have caused to be heard before; that it may be prepared, so as that it may be a blessing, not as avarice.
B047C009V006	47	9	6	But this, He who soweth with scantiness, with scantiness also reapeth; and he who soweth with blessing, with blessing also shall reap.
B047C009V007	47	9	7	Every man as he hath in his mind: not as of vexation or as of constraint; for a cheerful giver the Lord loveth.
B047C009V008	47	9	8	For it is in the power of Aloha to increase in you every good, that you may always have every thing sufficient, and that you may abound in every good work.
B047C009V009	47	9	9	As it is written, He hath dispersed and given to the poor, And his righteousness standeth for ever.
B047C009V010	47	9	10	But may He who giveth seed to the sower and bread for food, himself give and multiply your seed, and increase the fruits of your righteousness,
B047C009V011	47	9	11	that in every thing you may be enriched in all simplicity, which worketh out through us, thanksgiving to Aloha.
B047C009V012	47	9	12	For, on account of the performance of this service, we not only supply the deficiency of the saints, but also cause many thanks givings to abound unto Aloha.
B047C009V013	47	9	13	For on account of the proof of this service we glorify Aloha, because you are subject to the confession of the gospel of Meshiha, and you have communicated in simplicity with them and with every man.
B047C009V014	47	9	14	And prayer they offer on your behalf in great love, on account of the greatness of the grace of Aloha which is upon you.
B047C009V015	47	9	15	But thanks to Aloha over his gift which is unspeakable.
B047C010V001	47	10	1	BUT I Paulos beseech of you by the peacefulness and humility of the Meshiha, (I) who also in presence am humble with you, but while far off am confident over you,
B047C010V002	47	10	2	beseech of you, that when I come I may not be constrained with the confidence I have to be bold, as I think, over those men who imagine that we walk in the flesh.
B047C010V003	47	10	3	For if we walk in the flesh, yet we war not according to the flesh.
B047C010V004	47	10	4	For the armour of our warfare is not of the flesh, but of the power of Aloha; and by it we cast down the strong-holds of rebels,
B047C010V005	47	10	5	and demolish reasonings and every lofty thing that is exalted against the knowledge of Aloha, and captivate all thoughts unto the obedience of the Meshiha.
B047C010V006	47	10	6	And we are prepared to execute the punishment of those who obey not, when your obedience shall be fulfilled.
B047C010V007	47	10	7	Do we regard persons? If any man confide in himself that he is of the Meshiha, let this one know of himself, that as he is of the Meshiha, so also are we.
B047C010V008	47	10	8	For if I should boast somewhat more of the authority which our Lord hath given me, I should not blush; because for your edification he gave it to me, and not for your destruction.
B047C010V009	47	10	9	But I insist not, that I may not be considered as one who would terrify you by my epistles.
B047C010V010	47	10	10	For there are men who say, His epistles are weighty and forcible; but his bodily presence is weak, and his speech contemptible.
B047C010V011	47	10	11	But he who after this manner speaks, shall conclude that what we are by the word of our epistle when absent, so are we in the deed when we are present.
B047C010V012	47	10	12	For we dare not value or compare ourselves with those who glorify themselves; but because they compare themselves with themselves, they do not understand.
B047C010V013	47	10	13	For we do not boast beyond our measure, but in the measure of the boundary which Aloha hath apportioned to us, that we might come also unto you.
B047C010V014	47	10	14	For it is not as not reaching to you we extend ourselves; for unto you we come with the gospel of the Meshiha.
B047C010V015	47	10	15	Neither boast we beyond our measure in the labour of others; but we have hope, that with the increase of your faith, we shall be enlarged according to our measure;
B047C010V016	47	10	16	and be progressive also beyond you to evangelize. Not as within the measure of others in the things that are prepared will we glory.
B047C010V017	47	10	17	But let him who glorieth glory in the Lord.
B047C010V018	47	10	18	For it is not he who glorifieth himself who is approved, but he who is glorified of the Lord.
B047C011V001	47	11	1	BUT I could desire that you could tolerate me a little that I may speak foolishly.
B047C011V002	47	11	2	Nevertheless tolerate me, for I am zealous towards you with the zeal of Aloha; for I have betrothed you to one man, a pure virgin, whom I would bring unto the Meshiha.
B047C011V003	47	11	3	But I fear lest, as the serpent deceived 'Hava by his guile, so your minds may be corrupted from the simplicity that is toward the Meshiha.
B047C011V004	47	11	4	For if he who hath come to you shall preach to you another Jeshu, whom we have not preached, or you receive another Spirit which you have not received or another gospel which you have not accepted, you would have been well persuaded.
B047C011V005	47	11	5	For I consider that I am nothing inferior to those apostles who are most excellent.
B047C011V006	47	11	6	For if I am rude in my speech, I yet am not in my knowledge; but in every thing we are manifest among you.
B047C011V007	47	11	7	Or, offending have I offended in humbling myself that you may be exalted, and have gratuitously preached to you the gospel of Aloha?
B047C011V008	47	11	8	And other churches have I despoiled, receiving of them expenses, for your service.
B047C011V009	47	11	9	And being come among you, I burdened no man of you; for my want the brethren who came from Makedunia supplied: and in every thing have I kept myself, and will keep, that I may not be burdensome to you.
B047C011V010	47	11	10	The truth of the Meshiha is in me, that this boasting shall not be abolished respecting me in the regions of Akaia.
B047C011V011	47	11	11	Why? because I love you not? Aloha himself knoweth!
B047C011V012	47	11	12	But I do this, and also will do it, to cut off the occasion of them who seek an occasion, that in the thing in which they boast they may be found as we are.
B047C011V013	47	11	13	For these are apostles of falsehood and workers of deceits, assimilating themselves to the apostles of the Meshiha.
B047C011V014	47	11	14	Nor in this may we wonder, if Satana himself be transformed into an angel of light.
B047C011V015	47	11	15	Nor is it a great thing if his ministers also are transformed into ministers of righteousness;-whose end will be according to their works.
B047C011V016	47	11	16	BUT I say again, Let no man think of me as a fool; or if otherwise, let him receive me as a fool, that I also may boast a little.
B047C011V017	47	11	17	The thing which I (now) speak, I do not speak in our Lord, but as in foolishness in this place of boasting.
B047C011V018	47	11	18	Because many boast in the flesh, I also will boast.
B047C011V019	47	11	19	For you are content to listen to the feebleminded, you yourselves being wise.
B047C011V020	47	11	20	For you are ruled by one who subjugates you, and by one who devours you, and by one who takes away from you, and by one who exalts himself over you, and by one who smites you on your faces!
B047C011V021	47	11	21	As in abasement I speak; as though we were weak through defectiveness of mind, I speak. In whatever any man dareth, I also dare.
B047C011V022	47	11	22	If they are Ebroyee, so am I; if they are Isroloyee, so am I; if they are the seed of Abraham, so am I;
B047C011V023	47	11	23	if they are ministers of the Meshiha,-I speak with defectiveness of mind,-I exceed then! In labours I exceed them, in stripes I exceed them, in chains I exceed them, in deaths many times.
B047C011V024	47	11	24	From the Jihudoyee, five times, forty (stripes) wanting one have I devoured;
B047C011V025	47	11	25	three times with staves have I been beaten, once was I stoned, three times have I been in shipwreck, a day and a night without a ship have I been in the sea.
B047C011V026	47	11	26	In journeys many, in danger of rivers, in danger of robbers, in danger from my own race, in danger from the Gentiles; I have been in danger in cities, I have been in danger in the waste, in danger by sea, in danger from false brethren;
B047C011V027	47	11	27	in labour and weariness, in much watching, in hunger and thirst, in much fasting, in cold and in nakedness;
B047C011V028	47	11	28	besides the aboundings and the gathering which are upon me daily even my care which is for all the churches.
B047C011V029	47	11	29	Who is weak, and I am not weak? Who is offended, and I burn not?
B047C011V030	47	11	30	If I must boast in my infirmities, I will boast.
B047C011V031	47	11	31	Aloha, the Father of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, the Blessed for ever and ever, knoweth that I lie not.
B047C011V032	47	11	32	In Darmsuk the great force of Aretos the king kept the city of the Darmsukoyee to apprehend me.
B047C011V033	47	11	33	And from a window in a basket they sent me from the wall, and I was delivered from his hands.
B047C012V001	47	12	1	I might boast, but it is not expedient; for I come to visions and revelations of the Lord.
B047C012V002	47	12	2	I knew a man in the Meshiha fourteen years ago, -whether in the body, or out of the body, I know not, Aloha himself knoweth, -who, this one himself, was rapt unto the third of heaven.
B047C012V003	47	12	3	And I know this man himself,-but whether in the body, or out of the body, I know not, Aloha himself knoweth,
B047C012V004	47	12	4	-and he was rapt into paradise, and heard words which are not uttered, those which it is not lawful for a man to utter.
B047C012V005	47	12	5	Of this I boast; but of myself I will not boast, except in my infirmities.
B047C012V006	47	12	6	Yet if I willed to boast, I should not be a fool, for I say the truth; but I spare, lest any one think of me beyond that which he seeth me (to be), and what he heareth of me.
B047C012V007	47	12	7	And that I might not be exalted by the abundance of revelations, there was delivered to me a stimulus of my flesh, an angel of Satana to buffet me, that I might not be exalted.
B047C012V008	47	12	8	Concerning this three times I entreated of my Lord that it might be removed from me.
B047C012V009	47	12	9	And he said to me, My grace sufficeth thee; for my power in weakness is perfected. Gladly therefore will I boast in my infirmities, that the power of the Meshiha may overshadow me.
B047C012V010	47	12	10	For this cause I am willing in infirmities, in reviling, in affliction, in persecutions, in distresses, for the sake of the Meshiha; for when I am weak, then am I strong.
B047C012V011	47	12	11	Behold, I have been deficient in mind in my boasting, because you have constrained me; for you were debtors to bear witness concerning me; because in nothing am I less than those apostles who are the most eminent, nevertheless I am not any thing.
B047C012V012	47	12	12	The signs of the apostles I have wrought among you in all patience, and with mighty acts and miracles and with powers.
B047C012V013	47	12	13	For in what have you been less than the other churches, except in this, that I have not burdened you? Forgive me this offence.
B047C012V014	47	12	14	Behold, this is three times that I prepare to come to you, and not to burden you; for I seek not yours, but you. For the children ought not to lay up treasures for the parents, but the parents for their children.
B047C012V015	47	12	15	But I gladly the expenses will spend, and also myself will I give for the sake of your souls: though, while the more I love you, you the less love me.
B047C012V016	47	12	16	And, perhaps, (though) I did not burden you, yet (it may be said), as a crafty man with deceit I have robbed you.
B047C012V017	47	12	17	By any other whom I have sent to you have I made prey of you?
B047C012V018	47	12	18	Of Titos I requested, and sent with him the brethren. In any thing has Titos made prey of you? Have we not walked in one spirit, and in the same steps?
B047C012V019	47	12	19	DO you again consider that we apologize to you? Before Aloha in the Meshiha do we speak; and all, my beloved, for the sake of your up-building.
B047C012V020	47	12	20	For I fear lest, when I come to you, I should not find you as I wish, but should find you what you would not wish: lest there be contention and envy, and wrath and angry talk, and accusations and murmurings, and pompousness and agitation:
B047C012V021	47	12	21	and lest, when I come to you, my God may humiliate me, and I may have to lament over many who have sinned, and have not repented of the uncleanness and of the fornication and of the lasciviousness which they have committed.
B047C013V001	47	13	1	This is the third time that I prepare to come to you; and in the mouth of two or three witnesses shall every word be established.
B047C013V002	47	13	2	I have foretold you, and again I foretell you; as also twice while I was with you I told you, (so) now also being distant I write to those who have sinned, and to the rest of the others; that if I come again I will not spare.
B047C013V003	47	13	3	Inasmuch as you demand the proof of the Meshiha who speaketh in me, (of) Him who is not weak among you, but is mighty among you:
B047C013V004	47	13	4	-for though he was crucified in weakness, yet he liveth with the power of Aloha:-so also we are weak with you, but we live with him through the power of Aloha which is among you.
B047C013V005	47	13	5	Prove yourselves, whether in the faith itself you stand; try yourselves. Are you not assured that Jeshu the Meshiha is in you, if you be not reprobates?
B047C013V006	47	13	6	But I trust you will know that we are not reprobate.
B047C013V007	47	13	7	But I implore of Aloha that there may not be any thing in you that is evil, that our proving may be seen; but that you may do good, and that we may be as unproved.
B047C013V008	47	13	8	For we are not able to do any thing against the truth, but for the truth.
B047C013V009	47	13	9	For we rejoice when we are weak, and you are strong: but this also we pray, that you may be perfect.
B047C013V010	47	13	10	Therefore while distant I write these (things), that when I am come I may not act severely, according to the power which my Lord hath given me for your edification, and not for your destruction.
B047C013V011	47	13	11	Wherefore, my brethren, rejoice, and be perfect, and be comforted, and let agreement and peace be among you; and the God of love and of peace shall be with you.
B047C013V012	47	13	12	Salute one another with the holy kiss.
B047C013V013	47	13	13	All the saints ask for your peace.
B047C013V014	47	13	14	THE PEACE OF OUR LORD JESHU MESHIHA, AND THE LOVE OF ALOHA, AND THE COMMUNION OF THE SPIRIT OF HOLINESS, BE WITH YOU ALL. AMEN.
B048C001V001	48	1	1	Paulos, an apostle, not from men, nor by men, but by Jeshu the Meshiha, and Aloha his Father, who raised him from among the dead,
B048C001V002	48	1	2	and all the brethren who are with me, to the churches which are in Galatia:
B048C001V003	48	1	3	Grace be with you and peace, from Aloha the Father, and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha,
B048C001V004	48	1	4	who gave himself for our sins to deliver us from this evil world, according to the will of Aloha our Father:
B048C001V005	48	1	5	to whom be glory to the age of ages. Amen.
B048C001V006	48	1	6	I am amazed how soon you have been turned from the Meshiha himself, who called you by his grace,
B048C001V007	48	1	7	unto another gospel, which it is not; but there are men who disturb you, and (who) wish to remove you from the gospel of the Meshiha.
B048C001V008	48	1	8	But if we also, or an angel from heaven, should preach to you other than what we have preached to you, let him be accursed.
B048C001V009	48	1	9	As I have said before, and now again say to you, If any man preach to you other than what you have received, let him be accursed.
B048C001V010	48	1	10	For now do I persuade men, or Aloha? or do I seek to please men? For if until now I had pleased men, I should not have been the servant of the Meshiha.
B048C001V011	48	1	11	But I make known to you, my brethren, that the gospel which is preached by me was not from man:
B048C001V012	48	1	12	for neither from man had I received it and taught it, but by the revelation of Jeshu the Meshiha.
B048C001V013	48	1	13	For you have heard of my former manners in Judaism, that I exceedingly persecuted the church of Aloha, and made it desolate.
B048C001V014	48	1	14	And I excelled in Judaism more than many of the sons of my years who were of my kindred, and was exceedingly zealous for the doctrine of my fathers.
B048C001V015	48	1	15	But, when He willed who separated me from my mother's womb, and called me by his grace,
B048C001V016	48	1	16	to reveal his Son in me, that I should preach among the nations, immediately I did not disclose to flesh and to blood;
B048C001V017	48	1	17	neither went I to Urishlem, to the apostles who were before me, but I went into Arabia, and again returned unto Darmsuk.
B048C001V018	48	1	18	And after three years I went unto Urishlem, that I might see Kipha, and I remained with him days fifteen.
B048C001V019	48	1	19	But others of the apostles I saw not, only Jakub, the brother of our Lord.
B048C001V020	48	1	20	But these which I write to you, behold, before Aloha, that I lie not.
B048C001V021	48	1	21	And after these I went to the regions of Syria and of Cilicia.
B048C001V022	48	1	22	Neither did the churches of Jihud which are in the Meshiha know me by face.
B048C001V023	48	1	23	But this only they had heard, that he who had formerly persecuted us, behold, now preacheth he that faith which he beforetime had overthrown.
B048C001V024	48	1	24	And in me they glorified Aloha.
B048C002V001	48	2	1	Again, from fourteen years I went up to Urishlem with Bar Naba, and took with me Titos.
B048C002V002	48	2	2	But I went up by revelation; and I disclosed to them the gospel which I proclaim among the nations; and I showed it to those who were considered to be somewhat between myself and them, lest in vain I had run or should run.
B048C002V003	48	2	3	Titos also who was with me, who was an Aramoya, was not constrained to be circumcised.
B048C002V004	48	2	4	But on account of false brethren, who entered upon us that they might espy the liberty which we have in Jeshu Meshiha as that they might bring me into subjection;
B048C002V005	48	2	5	yet not for the space of an hour did we cast ourselves down to be subject to them; that the truth of the gospel might continue with you.
B048C002V006	48	2	6	But, they who were considered to be somewhat,---but what they were I care not, for Aloha accepteth not men?s faces,---they themselves added nothing unto me;
B048C002V007	48	2	7	but otherwise: for seeing that I was intrusted with the gospel of the uncircumcision, as Kipha was intrusted with the circumcision;
B048C002V008	48	2	8	---for he who wrought effectually with Kipha for the apostleship of the circumcision, wrought effectually also with me for the apostleship of the Gentiles;
B048C002V009	48	2	9	---and knowing the grace which had been given to me, Jakub and Kipha and Juchanon, who were considered to be pillars, the right hand of fellowship gave to me and to Bar Naba, that we (should preach) among the Gentiles, and they among the circumcision:
B048C002V010	48	2	10	only (requiring) that of the poor we should be mindful; and I have been solicitous to do this same thing.
B048C002V011	48	2	11	But when Kipha had come to Antiokia, I rebuked him to his face, because they were offended by him.
B048C002V012	48	2	12	For until certain men came from Jakub, he had eaten with the Gentiles; but when they were come, he withdrew himself and separated, because he was afraid of those who were of the circumcision.
B048C002V013	48	2	13	And the rest of the Jihudoyee also were thrown with him in this, so that Bar Naba also was led away by their partiality.
B048C002V014	48	2	14	And when I saw that they were not walking rightly in the truth of the gospel, I said to Kipha in the presence of them all: If thou who art a Jihudoya live as an Aramoya and not Judaically, why forcest thou the Gentiles to live Judaically?
B048C002V015	48	2	15	If we who by our nature are Jihudoyee, and are not of the Gentile sinners,
B048C002V016	48	2	16	because we know that man is not justified by the works of the law, but by the faith of Jeshu Meshiha, also in him, in Jeshu Meshiha, have believed, that from the faith of the Meshiha we may be justified, and not from the works of the law; because from the works of the law shall no flesh be justified:
B048C002V017	48	2	17	---If, while we seek to be justified through the Meshiha, we also ourselves are found sinners, is Jeshu Meshiha therefore the minister of sin? It cannot be.
B048C002V018	48	2	18	For, if those things which I destroyed I build again, I make it manifest of myself that I transgress the commandment.
B048C002V019	48	2	19	For I by the law to the law am dead, that unto Aloha I may live:
B048C002V020	48	2	20	and with the Meshiha am I crucified, and from henceforth I live not, but in me liveth Meshiha; and this that I now live in the flesh I live by the faith of the Son of Aloha, who loved me and gave himself for me.
B048C002V021	48	2	21	I do not deny the grace of Aloha; for if righteousness is by the law, the Meshiha died in vain!
B048C003V001	48	3	1	O deficient-minded Galatoyee, who bewildereth you? For, behold, as if depicted before your eyes, hath Jeshu the Meshiha been crucified.
B048C003V002	48	3	2	This only would I know from you: Through the works of the law received you the Spirit, or through the hearing of faith?
B048C003V003	48	3	3	Are you so foolish that having begun in the Spirit you are now finishing in the flesh?
B048C003V004	48	3	4	And all these have you borne in vain? But would it be in vain?
B048C003V005	48	3	5	Then, he who imparted to you the Spirit, and wrought miracles among you, (did he so) through the works of the law, or through the hearing of faith?
B048C003V006	48	3	6	As Abraham believed Aloha, and it was reckoned to him for righteousness,
B048C003V007	48	3	7	know therefore that they who are of faith are the children of Abraham.
B048C003V008	48	3	8	For Aloha who knew before that he would justify the Gentiles through faith, evangelized before unto Abraham; as saith the holy scripture: In thee all the nations shall be blessed:
B048C003V009	48	3	9	therefore believers are blessed with Abraham the believer.
B048C003V010	48	3	10	For they who are of the works of the law are under the curse: for it is written, Cursed is every one who doeth not all that is written in this law.
B048C003V011	48	3	11	But that man is not justified by the law before Aloha, this maketh manifest: because it is written, The just by faith shall live.
B048C003V012	48	3	12	But the law is not of faith: but he who doeth those things that are written in it shall live by them.
B048C003V013	48	3	13	But us hath the Meshiha bought from the curse of the law, and hath been made a curse instead of us: for it is written, Accursed is every one who is hanged on the wood:
B048C003V014	48	3	14	in order that upon the nations there might be the blessing of Abraham in Jeshu the Meshiha, that we might receive the promise of the Spirit through faith.
B048C003V015	48	3	15	My brethren, I speak as among men: That a covenant of man because confirmed no one rejecteth, or changeth in any thing.
B048C003V016	48	3	16	But to Abraham was promised the promise, and to his seed. And he did not say to him, Unto thy seeds, as of many; but, To thy seed, as of one, him, (namely,) who is the Meshiha.
B048C003V017	48	3	17	But I say this, that the covenant which was confirmed before by Aloha, in the Meshiha, the law which was after, four hundred and thirty years, cannot nullify, nor (can it) abolish the promise.
B048C003V018	48	3	18	But if the inheritance was by the law, it could not have been by the promise; but Aloha gave it unto Abraham by promise.
B048C003V019	48	3	19	Wherefore then was the law? It was added on account of transgression, until the Seed should come, he, of whom was the promise; and the law was given by angels into the hand of a Mediator.
B048C003V020	48	3	20	But a Mediator is not of one; but Aloha is one.
B048C003V021	48	3	21	Is the law therefore against the promise of Aloha? Impossible: for if a law had been given which could make to live, certainly righteousness would have been by the law.
B048C003V022	48	3	22	But the scripture hath included all under sin, that the promise through faith of Jeshu Meshiha might be given to them who believe.
B048C003V023	48	3	23	But until (the dispensation of) faith came, the law kept us, as shut up unto the faith which was to be revealed.
B048C003V024	48	3	24	The law therefore was our conductor to the Meshiha, that we might be justified by faith.
B048C003V025	48	3	25	But faith being come, we are not under the conductor.
B048C003V026	48	3	26	For you are all the children of Aloha through the faith of Jeshu the Meshiha.
B048C003V027	48	3	27	For they who into the Meshiha are baptized have been clothed with the Meshiha.
B048C003V028	48	3	28	Jihudoya or Aramoya is not; the slave or the free is not; male or female is not; for you are all one in Jeshu Meshiha.
B048C003V029	48	3	29	And if you are of the Meshiha, therefore are you the seed of Abraham, and heirs by the promise.
B048C004V001	48	4	1	But I say that what time the heir is a child, he differeth not from a servant, though he be lord of all,
B048C004V002	48	4	2	but is under curators and stewards until the time which his father appointeth.
B048C004V003	48	4	3	So we also, while children, under the principles of the world were subjected.
B048C004V004	48	4	4	But when the fulness of the time had come, Aloha sent his Son, and made from a woman, and made under the law,
B048C004V005	48	4	5	that them who were under the law he might redeem, and we might receive the constitution of sons.
B048C004V006	48	4	6	And because you are sons, Aloha hath sent the Spirit of his Son into your hearts, who crieth, Father, our Father.
B048C004V007	48	4	7	Therefore you are not servants, but sons; and if sons, heirs also of Aloha, through Jeshu Meshiha.
B048C004V008	48	4	8	For, while not knowing Aloha, you served them who by their nature are not gods:
B048C004V009	48	4	9	but now that you have known Aloha, and especially that you have been acknowledged of Aloha, turn you again to those diseased and beggarly principles, and will to be subject to them afresh?
B048C004V010	48	4	10	Days, and months, and times, you observe.
B048C004V011	48	4	11	I am afraid, lest vain in I have laboured among you.
B048C004V012	48	4	12	Be you as I am, for I am as you are, my brethren, I beseech you. In nothing have you injured me.
B048C004V013	48	4	13	For you know that in infirmity of my flesh I preached to you at the first.
B048C004V014	48	4	14	And the temptation of my flesh you did not despise nor execrate; but as an angel of Aloha you received me, and as of Jeshu Meshiha.
B048C004V015	48	4	15	Where then is your happiness? For I testify of you, that had it been possible, your eye you would have plucked out and given to me.
B048C004V016	48	4	16	Have I become your adversary, because I have preached to you the truth?
B048C004V017	48	4	17	They are emulous of you not for good; but they would shut you in, that you might be emulous of them.
B048C004V018	48	4	18	But it is well to be emulous in good things at all time, and not only when I am with you.
B048C004V019	48	4	19	My children, with whom I travail afresh until the Meshiha be formed in you,
B048C004V020	48	4	20	I would be with you now, and change the sound of my voice, because I am astonished at you.
B048C004V021	48	4	21	Tell me, you who are willing to be under the law, do you not hear the law?
B048C004V022	48	4	22	For it is written, that Abraham had two sons, one of the bondmaid, and one of the free.
B048C004V023	48	4	23	But he who was of the bondmaid was born according to the flesh, and he who was of the free was by the promise.
B048C004V024	48	4	24	But these are parables of the two covenants: the one which was from Mount Sinai bringing forth into bondage, which is Hagar:
B048C004V025	48	4	25	for Hagar is Mount Sinai which is in Arabia, and answers to this Urishlem, and serves in bondage, she and her children.
B048C004V026	48	4	26	But she, Urishilem the high, is the free, who is our mother.
B048C004V027	48	4	27	For it is written, Be glad, O barren, who hast not borne; Exult and cry, thou who hast not travailed; Because multiplied are the sons of the desolate, More than the sons of the married wife.
B048C004V028	48	4	28	But we, my brethren, as Ishak, are the children of promise.
B048C004V029	48	4	29	And as then he who was born of the flesh persecuted him who was after the Spirit, so also now.
B048C004V030	48	4	30	But what saith the scripture? Cast out the bondmaid and her son; for the son of the bondmaid shall not inherit with the son of the free.
B048C004V031	48	4	31	We therefore, my brethren, are not the children of the bondmaid, but the children of the free.
B048C005V001	48	5	1	Stand therefore in that liberty with which the Meshiha hath freed you, and be not enthralled with the yoke of bondage.
B048C005V002	48	5	2	Behold, I, Paulos, tell you, that if you be circumcised, the Meshiha profiteth you nothing.
B048C005V003	48	5	3	But I attest again to every man who is circumcised, that he is obligated to fulfil the whole law.
B048C005V004	48	5	4	You have ceased from the Meshiha who are justified by the law, and from grace you have fallen.
B048C005V005	48	5	5	But we through the Spirit, who is from faith, expect the hope of righteousness.
B048C005V006	48	5	6	For, in the Meshiha Jeshu, circumcision is not any thing, nor uncircumcision, but faith which is made perfect by love.
B048C005V007	48	5	7	Well did you run; who hath impeded you, that to the truth you should not be in obedience?
B048C005V008	48	5	8	Your persuasion is not from him who called you.
B048C005V009	48	5	9	A little leaven the whole mass leaveneth.
B048C005V010	48	5	10	I am confident of you in our Lord, that no other thing you will think; and he who disturbeth you shall bear judgment, whoever he is.
B048C005V011	48	5	11	But I, my brethren, if yet I have preached for circumcision, why have I been persecuted? Hath the scandal of the cross ceased?
B048C005V012	48	5	12	But I would that they who disturb you were even cut off.
B048C005V013	48	5	13	But you have been called unto liberty, my brethren: only let not your liberty be for an occasion of the flesh; but in love be subjected one to another.
B048C005V014	48	5	14	For all the law in one word is fulfilled, in this: Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.
B048C005V015	48	5	15	But if you bite and devour one another, beware lest one by another you be consumed.
B048C005V016	48	5	16	But I say to you, Walk in the Spirit, and the desires of the flesh you will not work.
B048C005V017	48	5	17	For the flesh desireth that which is repugnant to the Spirit, and the Spirit desireth that which is repugnant to the flesh; and the two are adverse one to the other, that not any thing that you will you may do.
B048C005V018	48	5	18	But if by the Spirit you are led, you are not under the law.
B048C005V019	48	5	19	For the works of the flesh are known, which are (these), fornication, uncleanness, lasciviousness,
B048C005V020	48	5	20	the worship of idols, sorcery, enmity, contention, ambition, wrath, calumny, divisions, rendings,
B048C005V021	48	5	21	envy, murder, drunkenness, revelling, and all that are like these; and they who do them, as I told you before, so now I tell you, the kingdom of Aloha do not inherit.
B048C005V022	48	5	22	But the fruits of the Spirit are, love, joy, peace, prolonging of the spirit, benignity, goodness, fidelity,
B048C005V023	48	5	23	meekness, patience; against these the law is not set.
B048C005V024	48	5	24	But they who are of the Meshiha have crucified their flesh, with all its passions and its lusts:
B048C005V025	48	5	25	live we therefore in the Spirit,
B048C005V026	48	5	26	and let us not be vain-glorious, contemning one another, envying one another.
B048C006V001	48	6	1	My brethren, if a man of you be overtaken by a fault, you who are in the Spirit, regain him, in the spirit of meekness, and beware lest you also be tempted.
B048C006V002	48	6	2	And bear the burden of one another, and so fulfil the law of the Meshiha.
B048C006V003	48	6	3	For if a man consider that he is something, while he is not, he deceiveth himself.
B048C006V004	48	6	4	But let every man prove his work, and then in himself he shall exult, and not in others.
B048C006V005	48	6	5	For every man shall bear his own burden.
B048C006V006	48	6	6	But let him who heareth the word, communicate to him from whom he heareth it, in all good things.
B048C006V007	48	6	7	Do not err. Aloha is not mocked: for whatever a man soweth, that he reapeth.
B048C006V008	48	6	8	He who in the flesh soweth, from the flesh corruption reapeth; and he who in the Spirit soweth, from the Spirit the life that is eternal shall reap.
B048C006V009	48	6	9	And while we do that which is good, let it not weary us; for the time will be when we shall reap, and it will not weary us.
B048C006V010	48	6	10	Now, therefore, while the time is ours, let us do good unto every man, and especially to the sons of the house of the faith.
B048C006V011	48	6	11	You see these letters which I have written to you with my hands.
B048C006V012	48	6	12	They who would glory in the flesh would constrain you to be circumcised; only lest for the cross of the Meshiha they might be persecuted.
B048C006V013	48	6	13	For neither do these who are circumcised keep the law; but they will that you be circumcised, that in your flesh they may glory.
B048C006V014	48	6	14	But to me let it not be that I shall glory except in the cross of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, by which the world is crucified unto me, and I am crucified to the world.
B048C006V015	48	6	15	For circumcision is not any thing, nor uncircumcision, but the new creature.
B048C006V016	48	6	16	And they who this pathway accomplish, peace be upon them and mercy, and upon the Israel of Aloha.
B048C006V017	48	6	17	Henceforth upon me let no man throw a burden; for the signatures of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha in my body I bear.
B048C006V018	48	6	18	The grace of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha be with your spirit, my brethren. Amen.
B049C001V001	49	1	1	PAULOS, an apostle of Jeshu Meshiha by the will of Aloha, to those who are in Ephesos, saints and believers in Jeshu Meshiha:
B049C001V002	49	1	2	peace be with you, and grace from Aloha our Father, and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B049C001V003	49	1	3	Blessed be He, Aloha, the Father of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, who hath blessed us with all blessings of the Spirit in heaven, in the Meshiha;
B049C001V004	49	1	4	as he before elected us in him, from before the foundations of the world, that we should be saints, and without blemish before him,
B049C001V005	49	1	5	and in love predesignated us unto himself, and constituted us children in Jeshu Meshiha, according to the pleasure of his will;
B049C001V006	49	1	6	that the glory of his grace might be glorified, that (grace) which he hath poured upon us by the hand of his Beloved:
B049C001V007	49	1	7	in whom we have redemption, and by his blood the remission of sins, according to the riches of his grace
B049C001V008	49	1	8	which he hath made to abound in us in all wisdom and in all understanding of the Spirit;
B049C001V009	49	1	9	and hath made known to us the mystery of his will, which before he had determined in himself should be done:
B049C001V010	49	1	10	that in the dispensation of the fulness of the times, every thing from the first might be renovated in the Meshiha, in heaven and in earth. And by him
B049C001V011	49	1	11	we have been chosen, even as he predesignated and willed, who worketh all according to the mind of his will;
B049C001V012	49	1	12	that we who first hoped in the Meshiha, should be to the honour of his glory.
B049C001V013	49	1	13	In whom you also heard the word of truth, which is the gospel of your salvation; and in whom you believed and were sealed with the Spirit of Holiness who was promised;
B049C001V014	49	1	14	who is the earnest of our inheritance, until the redemption of those who are saved, and unto the praise of his majesty.
B049C001V015	49	1	15	ON account of this, behold, I also, since I heard of your faith in our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, and your love to all the saints,
B049C001V016	49	1	16	have not ceased to give thanks on your behalf, and to remember you in my prayers;
B049C001V017	49	1	17	that the God of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, the Father of glory, would give to you the Spirit of wisdom and of revelation in his knowledge,
B049C001V018	49	1	18	and would enlighten the eyes of your hearts to know what is the hope of his calling, and what the riches of the glory of his inheritance for the saints,
B049C001V019	49	1	19	and what is the inheritance of his power in us who believe, according to the operation of the might of his power,
B049C001V020	49	1	20	which he wrought in the Meshiha, and raised him from among the dead, and set him at his right hand in heaven, above all the principalities,
B049C001V021	49	1	21	and powers, and mighty ones, and rulers, and above every name that is named, not only in this world, but also in (that) to come;
B049C001V022	49	1	22	and subjected every thing beneath his feet: and Him who is over all he hath given to be the head of the church,
B049C001V023	49	1	23	which is His body, the completeness of Him who all in all completeth.
B049C002V001	49	2	1	You also who were dead in your sins and in your transgressions,
B049C002V002	49	2	2	in which from the first you walked according to the worldliness of this age, and according to the will of the prince of the power of the air, of that Spirit who urgeth in the sons of disobedience;
B049C002V003	49	2	3	in those works in which we also walked from the first in the lusts of our flesh, doing the will of our flesh and of our mind, and were the sons of wrath fully as the rest.
B049C002V004	49	2	4	BUT Aloha, who is rich in his mercies, for his great love wherewith he loved us
B049C002V005	49	2	5	while we were dead in our sins, made us alive with the Meshiha, and through his grace delivered us,
B049C002V006	49	2	6	and raised us with him, and made us to sit with him in heaven in Jeshu the Meshiha,
B049C002V007	49	2	7	that he might show to the ages to come the greatness of the riches of his grace and his goodness, which hath been upon us in Jeshu the Meshiha.
B049C002V008	49	2	8	For by his grace are we saved through faith, and this was not of you, but is the gift of Aloha,
B049C002V009	49	2	9	not of works, that no man should glory.
B049C002V010	49	2	10	For we are his creation, who are created in Jeshu Meshiha unto good works, which Aloha hath prepared before, that in them we should walk.
B049C002V011	49	2	11	Wherefore be mindful, that you Gentiles at first were carnal, and were called the Uncircumcision by that which is called the Circumcision, and is the work of the hands in the flesh;
B049C002V012	49	2	12	and were at that time without the Meshiha, and were aliens from the polity of Israel, and strangers to the covenant of the promise, and, without hope, were without Aloha in the world.
B049C002V013	49	2	13	But now, by Jeshu the Meshiha, you who before were far off, are brought nigh by the blood of the Meshiha.
B049C002V014	49	2	14	For he is our peace, he who hath made the two one, and hath destroyed the wall which stood in the midst,
B049C002V015	49	2	15	and the enmity, through his flesh; and the law of prescriptions, with its requirements, he hath abolished, that of the two he might create in himself one new man, and make peace;
B049C002V016	49	2	16	and hath reconciled the two in one body with Aloha, and by his cross hath slain the enmity.
B049C002V017	49	2	17	And coming, he preached peace to you, to the far off, and to the nigh; therefore,
B049C002V018	49	2	18	through Him there hath been made for us both an access by one Spirit unto the Father.
B049C002V019	49	2	19	THEREFORE are you no more strangers and sojourners but sons of the city of the saints, and sons of the house of Aloha;
B049C002V020	49	2	20	and you are builded upon the foundation of the apostles and of the prophets, and Jeshu the Meshiha himself is the chief corner of the building;
B049C002V021	49	2	21	and in him is the whole building increased and enlargeth into a holy temple in the Lord,
B049C002V022	49	2	22	while you also in him are being builded the dwelling of Aloha by the Spirit.
B049C003V001	49	3	1	On account of this I, Paulos, am bound for Jeshu Meshiha for the sake of you Gentiles:
B049C003V002	49	3	2	if you have heard the dispensation of the grace of Aloha which was given me for you;
B049C003V003	49	3	3	that by revelation he made known to me the mystery, as I have written to you in few (words);
B049C003V004	49	3	4	so that while you read you are able to understand my knowledge of the mystery of the Meshiha,
B049C003V005	49	3	5	which in other generations was not known to the sons of men, as it hath now been revealed to his holy apostles and to his prophets by the Spirit;
B049C003V006	49	3	6	that the Gentiles should be sons of his inheritance and partakers of his body, and in the promise which is given concerning him by the gospel,
B049C003V007	49	3	7	of which I am made a minister, according to the gift of the grace of Aloha, which he hath given me by the operation of his power.
B049C003V008	49	3	8	To me, who am the least of all the saints, is given this grace, that I should preach among the Gentiles the riches of the Meshiha,
B049C003V009	49	3	9	which are not searched; and to bring to light unto all men what is the dispensation of the mystery which was hidden from the ages in Aloha, who created all:
B049C003V010	49	3	10	that through the church might be made known the wisdom of Aloha, which is full of diversities, to the principalities and powers who are in heaven,
B049C003V011	49	3	11	that which he prepared from of old, and which he hath executed by Jeshu our Lord,
B049C003V012	49	3	12	by whom we have freedom and access with the confidence of the faith of him.
B049C003V013	49	3	13	WHEREFORE I pray that I may not weary in my affliction, which is on your account,
B049C003V014	49	3	14	for this is your glory; and I bow my knees unto the Father of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha,
B049C003V015	49	3	15	from whom is named the whole family who are in heaven and in earth;
B049C003V016	49	3	16	that he would give to you, according to the riches of his glory, with power to be confirmed by his Spirit in your interior man;
B049C003V017	49	3	17	that the Meshiha may dwell by faith in your hearts in love; your root and your foundations being confirmed,
B049C003V018	49	3	18	that you may be able to follow out with all the saints, what the height, and depth, and the length, and breadth;
B049C003V019	49	3	19	and know the grandeur of the love of the Meshiha, and be filled with all the fulness of Aloha.
B049C003V020	49	3	20	But to Him who is able with power beyond all to do for us above what we ask or conceive, according to his power which worketh in us,
B049C003V021	49	3	21	to Him be glory in his church, by Jeshu Meshiha, in all ages, for ever and ever. Amen.
B049C004V001	49	4	1	I BESEECH of you, therefore, I, the bound one for our Lord, that you walk as is worthy of the calling wherewith you are called,
B049C004V002	49	4	2	in all lowliness of mind, and composedness, and long-suffering; and be patient towards one another in love.
B049C004V003	49	4	3	And be diligent to keep the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace,
B049C004V004	49	4	4	that you may be in one body and in one Spirit, even as you are called in one hope of your calling.
B049C004V005	49	4	5	For one is the Lord, and one the faith, and one the baptism;
B049C004V006	49	4	6	and one is Aloha, the Father of all, and over all, and by all, and in us all.
B049C004V007	49	4	7	But unto each of us is given grace according to the measure of the gift of the Meshiha.
B049C004V008	49	4	8	Wherefore it is said, He ascended on high; He led captive captivity, And gave gifts unto men.
B049C004V009	49	4	9	But he who ascended, what is it but that he also descended first into the low places of the earth?
B049C004V010	49	4	10	He who descended, is he who also ascended above all the heavens, to fulfil all.
B049C004V011	49	4	11	And he gave some who (are) apostles, and some who (are) prophets, and some who (are) evangelists, and some who (are) pastors, and some who (are) doctors;
B049C004V012	49	4	12	for the perfecting of the saints, for the work of the ministry, for the edification of the (church of the) Meshiha,
B049C004V013	49	4	13	until we be all one in the faith and in the knowledge of the Son of Aloha, and one man perfect in the measure of the stature of his completeness;
B049C004V014	49	4	14	and that we be no children, agitated and altered by every wind of fraudulent doctrines of men, which in their craftiness they fabricate deceptively in order to seduce,
B049C004V015	49	4	15	but be confirmed in our love, that whatever is ours may increase in the Meshiha,
B049C004V016	49	4	16	who is the head, by whom the whole body is increased and compacted in all the limbs, according to the gift which is given in proportion to every member for the increase of the body itself, that in love its structure might be completed.
B049C004V017	49	4	17	BUT this I say and testify in the Lord, that from henceforth you may not walk as the rest of the Gentiles, who walk in the vanity of their minds,
B049C004V018	49	4	18	and are darkened in their understandings, and are alienated from the life of Aloha on account of their ignorance, and on account of the blindness of their hearts;
B049C004V019	49	4	19	who are cut off from their hope, and have delivered themselves up to lasciviousness and to the working of all uncleanness in their greediness.
B049C004V020	49	4	20	But you have not thus learned the Meshiha,
B049C004V021	49	4	21	if really you have heard him and learned as the truth is in Jeshu;
B049C004V022	49	4	22	but that you put from you your former habitudes, the old man who is corrupt in deceitful lusts,
B049C004V023	49	4	23	and be renewed in the spirit of your minds,
B049C004V024	49	4	24	and wear the new man, who by Aloha is created in righteousness and in the sanctity of truth.
B049C004V025	49	4	25	WHEREFORE let lying cease from you, and speak the truth every man with his neighbour: for we are members one of another.
B049C004V026	49	4	26	Be angry and sin not, and let not the sun set upon your wrath,
B049C004V027	49	4	27	and give no place to the accuser.
B049C004V028	49	4	28	And let him who hath stolen henceforth steal not, but labour with his hands and do good, that he may have to give to him who needeth.
B049C004V029	49	4	29	Let no hateful word come out of your mouth, but that which is comely and useful for edification, that it may communicate grace to those who hear.
B049C004V030	49	4	30	And grieve not the Holy Spirit of Aloha, by whom you have been sealed unto the day of redemption.
B049C004V031	49	4	31	Let all bitterness, and heat, and anger, and clamour, and scandal be taken from you, with all malice;
B049C004V032	49	4	32	and be gentle one with another, and affectionate, and forgive one another, even as Aloha in the Meshiha hath forgiven us.
B049C005V001	49	5	1	Be therefore imitators of Aloha, as beloved children;
B049C005V002	49	5	2	and walk in love, as the Meshiha also loved us, and delivered himself for us, an offering and a sacrifice to Aloha of a fragrant smell.
B049C005V003	49	5	3	BUT fornication and all uncleanness and covetousness, let them not be even heard among you, as it becometh the saints;
B049C005V004	49	5	4	neither filthiness, nor words of folly, or of jeering, or fables, which are not necessary, but, instead of these, thanksgiving.
B049C005V005	49	5	5	But this know, that any man who is a fornicator, or impure, or covetous, or an idolater, hath no inheritance in the kingdom of the Meshiha and of Aloha;
B049C005V006	49	5	6	lest any man deceive you with vain words; for because of these cometh the anger of Aloha upon the sons of disobedience.
B049C005V007	49	5	7	Be not, therefore, participators with them.
B049C005V008	49	5	8	For you were before darkness, but now you are light in our Lord. As the sons of light, then, so walk.
B049C005V009	49	5	9	For the fruits of the light are in all goodness and rectitude and truth.
B049C005V010	49	5	10	And be discerning of that which is good before our Lord.
B049C005V011	49	5	11	And have no communion with the works of darkness, which have no fruits, but reprove them.
B049C005V012	49	5	12	For that which in secrecy they do it is execrable even to mention.
B049C005V013	49	5	13	For every thing is exposed by the light, and is revealed, and whatever revealeth is light.
B049C005V014	49	5	14	Wherefore it is said, Awake thou who sleepest, And arise from the dead, And the Meshiha shall enlighten thee.
B049C005V015	49	5	15	See then that you walk vigilantly, not as fools,
B049C005V016	49	5	16	but as the wise who redeem their opportunity, because the days are evil.
B049C005V017	49	5	17	On account of this, be not wanting in mind, but understand what is the will of Aloha.
B049C005V018	49	5	18	And be not drunk with wine, in which is intemperance, but be filled with the Spirit.
B049C005V019	49	5	19	And discourse with yourselves with psalms and with hymns and with songs of the Spirit, singing with your hearts unto the Lord.
B049C005V020	49	5	20	And give thanks always on behalf of every man in the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha unto Aloha the Father.
B049C005V021	49	5	21	And be subject one to another in the love of the Meshiha.
B049C005V022	49	5	22	WIVES, be subject to your husbands as to our Lord.
B049C005V023	49	5	23	For the husband is the head of the wife, as the Meshiha is the head of the church, and he himself is the Saviour of the body.
B049C005V024	49	5	24	But as the church is subject to Meshiha, so also (should) wives be unto their husbands in every thing.
B049C005V025	49	5	25	Husbands, love your wives, as also the Meshiha loved his church, and gave himself for her,
B049C005V026	49	5	26	that he might sanctify her and purify her in the laver of waters and by the word,
B049C005V027	49	5	27	and that he might constitute her a church unto himself, being glorified, and not having blemish or wrinkle or any thing like these; but to be holy and spotless.
B049C005V028	49	5	28	So it becometh husbands to love their wives, as their own bodies. For he who his wife loveth, himself he loveth.
B049C005V029	49	5	29	For no man ever hated his own body, but nourisheth it, and taketh care of it; so also the Meshiha (taketh care) of the church.
B049C005V030	49	5	30	For we are members of his body, and of his flesh are we, and of his bones.
B049C005V031	49	5	31	Because of this a man leaveth his father and his mother, and cleaveth unto his wife, and they two become one flesh.
B049C005V032	49	5	32	This mystery is great; but I speak of the Meshiha and of his church.
B049C005V033	49	5	33	Nevertheless let every one of you so love his wife as his own self; but let the wife reverence her husband.
B049C006V001	49	6	1	Children, obey your parents in our Lord, for this is right; and this is the first commandment which promiseth.
B049C006V002	49	6	2	Honour thy father and thy mother,
B049C006V003	49	6	3	that it may be well with thee, and thy life be prolonged upon the earth.
B049C006V004	49	6	4	Parents, make not your children angry, but make them to grow in the discipline and in the doctrine of our Lord.
B049C006V005	49	6	5	Servants, be subject to your masters who are according to the flesh, with fear and trembling, and with simplicity of heart, as unto the Meshiha:
B049C006V006	49	6	6	not in the sight of the eyes, as if you were pleasing men (only), but as the servants of Meshiha who do the will of Aloha.
B049C006V007	49	6	7	And serve them from all your soul, in love, as unto our Lord, and not as unto men;
B049C006V008	49	6	8	knowing that whatever good a man doeth he is rewarded by our Lord, whether he be a servant or a son of freedom.
B049C006V009	49	6	9	So you, masters, do likewise to your servants; forgiving them a fault; for you know also that your Master is in heaven, and there is no respect of persons with him.
B049C006V010	49	6	10	HENCEFORTH, my brethren, be strong in our Lord, and in the power of his strength.
B049C006V011	49	6	11	And clothe you in all the armour of Aloha, that you may be able to stand against the wiles of the accuser.
B049C006V012	49	6	12	For your wrestling is not with flesh and blood (only), but with princes, and with powers, and with the possessors of this dark world, and with the evil spirits who are under heaven.
B049C006V013	49	6	13	Wherefore clothe you with all the armour of Aloha, that you may be able to meet the evil one, and being prepared in every thing you may stand.
B049C006V014	49	6	14	Stand, therefore, with your loins strengthened with the truth, and wear the breastplate of righteousness,
B049C006V015	49	6	15	and let your feet be shod with the preparation of the gospel of peace;
B049C006V016	49	6	16	and with these take to you the shield of faith, that therewith you may be empowered with strength to extinguish all the burning shafts of that evil one;
B049C006V017	49	6	17	and put on the helmet of salvation, and take the sword of the Spirit which is the word of Aloha.
B049C006V018	49	6	18	And with all prayers, and with all supplications, pray at all times in the Spirit, and in that prayer be watchful in all seasons,
B049C006V019	49	6	19	praying constantly and invoking on behalf of all the saints; and for me also, that the word may be given me with openness of my mouth, that I may boldly proclaim the mystery of the gospel,
B049C006V020	49	6	20	for which I am an ambassador in chains, that I may speak with freedom, as it behoveth me to speak it.
B049C006V021	49	6	21	But that you may know also what relateth to me, and what I am doing, behold, Tykikos, a brother beloved, and a faithful minister of our Lord, will make known to you;
B049C006V022	49	6	22	whom I have sent to you on account of this, that he may make you acquainted with what relateth to me, and may comfort your hearts.
B049C006V023	49	6	23	Peace be with the brethren, and love with faith from Aloha our Father, and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B049C006V024	49	6	24	Grace be with all them who love our Lord Jeshu Meshiha incorruptibly. Amen.
B050C001V001	50	1	1	PAULOS and Timotheus, servants of Jeshu the Meshiha, to all the saints who are in Jeshu Meshiha at Philipos, with the presbyters and deacons.
B050C001V002	50	1	2	Grace be with you and peace from Aloha our Father, and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B050C001V003	50	1	3	I offer thanks unto Aloha upon the remembrance of you constantly,
B050C001V004	50	1	4	in all my prayers on your behalf; and while rejoicing,
B050C001V005	50	1	5	I pray, for your fellowship which is in the gospel from the first day until now;
B050C001V006	50	1	6	because I am confident of this, that he who hath begun good workings in you will himself make perfect until the day of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B050C001V007	50	1	7	For so it is right for me to think concerning you all, because you are laid up in my heart; and in my bonds, and in the defence of the truth of the gospel, you are partakers with me in grace.
B050C001V008	50	1	8	For Aloha is my witness how I love you with the bowels of Jeshu Meshiha.
B050C001V009	50	1	9	And this I pray, that your love may still increase and abound in knowledge and in all spiritual understanding;
B050C001V010	50	1	10	that you may distinguish those things that are proper, and may be pure and without offence in the day of the Meshiha,
B050C001V011	50	1	11	and filled with the fruits of righteousness which are in Jeshu Meshiha, to the glory and the honour of Aloha.
B050C001V012	50	1	12	BUT I wish you to know, my brethren, that my business tendeth the more to the forwarding of the gospel.
B050C001V013	50	1	13	For so also my bonds are manifest for the Meshiha in the whole palace, and unto all besides.
B050C001V014	50	1	14	And a multitude of brethren who are in our Lord are strengthened on account of my bonds, and have dared the more fearlessly to speak the word of Aloha.
B050C001V015	50	1	15	Some preach from envy and contention, but some from good-will,
B050C001V016	50	1	16	and in the love of the Meshiha; for they know that for the defence of the gospel I am appointed.
B050C001V017	50	1	17	But those who preach the Meshiha from contention do it not sincerely, but think to add affliction to my bonds.
B050C001V018	50	1	18	Yet in this I have rejoiced, and do rejoice, that in every way, if for an occasion, or if in truth, the Meshiha shall be preached.
B050C001V019	50	1	19	For I know that these things shall be found unto my life by your prayers, and by the gift of the Spirit of Jeshu Meshiha;
B050C001V020	50	1	20	even as I hope and expect, that in nothing I shall be confounded, but manifestly, as at all times, so also now, the Meshiha shall be magnified in my body, whether by life or by death.
B050C001V021	50	1	21	For my life is the Meshiha; and if I die, it is gain to me.
B050C001V022	50	1	22	But if in this life of the flesh there be also fruit to me from my works, I know not what to choose.
B050C001V023	50	1	23	For these two straiten me. I desire to be set free, that I might be with the Meshiha, and this is greatly preferable to me;
B050C001V024	50	1	24	but also to remain in my body is the thing which constraineth me on your account.
B050C001V025	50	1	25	For I know this confidently, that I am to remain and tarry for your joy and for the increase of your faith:
B050C001V026	50	1	26	that when I come again to you, your glorying which is in Jeshu Meshiha alone shall abound in me.
B050C001V027	50	1	27	As it becometh the gospel of the Meshiha, so have your conversation; that if coming I see you, or absent, I may hear of you, that you stand in one spirit and in one soul, conquering together for the faith of the gospel;
B050C001V028	50	1	28	in nothing moved by them who stand against us, to the forthshowing of their perdition, and of our salvation,
B050C001V029	50	1	29	And this from Aloha hath been given to you, not only believing to believe in the Meshiha, but also for his sake to suffer,
B050C001V030	50	1	30	and to sustain a conflict, as you have seen in me, and now hear concerning me.
B050C002V001	50	2	1	IF, therefore, you have consolation in the Meshiha, and if there be comfort in love, and if communion of the Spirit, and if compassions and mercies,
B050C002V002	50	2	2	complete my gladness by having one sentiment and one love, and one soul and one mind.
B050C002V003	50	2	3	And do nothing in contention or vainglorying, but in meekness of mind let a man consider his neighbour as better than himself.
B050C002V004	50	2	4	And let no one care for himself (only), but every one for his neighbour also.
B050C002V005	50	2	5	And feel this in yourselves, which Jeshu the Meshiha (did) also:
B050C002V006	50	2	6	who, when he was in the form of Aloha, considered this not to be robbery, (this, namely,) that he was the co-equal of Aloha:
B050C002V007	50	2	7	yet emptied he himself, and took the form of a servant, and was made in the form of men;
B050C002V008	50	2	8	and in fashion was found as a man, and humbled himself, and was obedient unto death, but the death of the cross.
B050C002V009	50	2	9	Wherefore also Aloha greatly exalted him, and gave him a name that is more excellent than all names,
B050C002V010	50	2	10	that at the name of Jeshu every knee should kneel, of those in heaven, and on earth, and under the earth;
B050C002V011	50	2	11	and that every tongue should confess that Jeshu the Meshiha is the Lord, to the glory of Aloha his Father.
B050C002V012	50	2	12	WHEREFORE, my beloved, as you have all time obeyed, not while I am near you only, but now that I am far from you, the more with fear and trembling work the work of your salvation;
B050C002V013	50	2	13	for Aloha himself effectuates in you also to will, also to do, the thing which you will.
B050C002V014	50	2	14	Do every thing without murmuring and without division;
B050C002V015	50	2	15	that you may be perfect and without spot, as the pure children of Aloha, who dwell in a generation depraved and perverse; and be manifest among them as luminaries in the world,
B050C002V016	50	2	16	to be unto them for a place of salvation, for my exultation in the day of the Meshiha, that I may not have run in vain, nor laboured to no purpose.
B050C002V017	50	2	17	But, also, offered on the sacrifice and service of your faith, I am glad, and rejoice with you all;
B050C002V018	50	2	18	so also you be glad and rejoice with me.
B050C002V019	50	2	19	But I hope in our Lord Jeshu to send Timotheos to you soon, that I also may have quietness when I learn concerning you.
B050C002V020	50	2	20	For I have no other who is so as my (own) soul, who will diligently take care for yours.
B050C002V021	50	2	21	For all are seeking what is theirs, and not what is of Jeshu Meshiha.
B050C002V022	50	2	22	But the proof of this you know, that as a son with his father, so hath he wrought with me in the gospel.
B050C002V023	50	2	23	Him, therefore, I hope to send to you speedily, when I shall have seen what with me.
B050C002V024	50	2	24	And I confide on my Lord, that I also speedily shall come unto you.
B050C002V025	50	2	25	But now the matter hath pressed me to send to you the brother Epaphroditos, who is a helper and labourer with me, but your messenger and minister to my necessity;
B050C002V026	50	2	26	for he desired to see you all, and was anxious, because he knew that you had heard that he was sick.
B050C002V027	50	2	27	Yes, he was sick, unto death; but Aloha had mercy upon him; but not upon him only, but upon me also, lest I should have sorrow upon sorrow.
B050C002V028	50	2	28	Urgently, therefore, have I sent him to you, that when you have seen him again you may rejoice, and that I may have a little breathing.
B050C002V029	50	2	29	Receive him, then, in the Lord with all joy; and those who are such, hold in estimation:
B050C002V030	50	2	30	because for the work of the Meshiha he had come nigh unto death, and was disregardful of his life, that he might accomplish that which you had wanted in the service which concerned me.
B050C003V001	50	3	1	HENCEFORTH, my brethren, rejoice in our Lord. To write the very same (things) to you, to me is not weariness, because they make you cautious.
B050C003V002	50	3	2	Beware of dogs, beware of evil workers, beware of the cutting of the flesh.
B050C003V003	50	3	3	For the circumcision are we, who serve Aloha in the spirit, and glory in Jeshu the Meshiha, and confide not on the flesh.
B050C003V004	50	3	4	Yet I may have confidence on the flesh. For if any one consider that his confidence is in the flesh, I more than he.
B050C003V005	50	3	5	Circumcised the son of eight days, of the family of Israel, of the tribe of Benyomin, Ebroia of Ebroyee; in the law, Pharisha;
B050C003V006	50	3	6	in zeal, a persecutor of the church; and in the righteousness of the law, without fault have I been.
B050C003V007	50	3	7	But these things which were my gain, I have reckoned loss for the Meshiha;
B050C003V008	50	3	8	and I also (still) reckon them all loss, for the grandeur of the knowledge of Jeshu Meshiha my Lord; for whose sake I have lost all things, and have reckoned as dung, that the Meshiha I may gain,
B050C003V009	50	3	9	and be found in him, not having my own righteousness, which is of the law, but that which is by the faith of the Meshiha, which is righteousness that is from Aloha:
B050C003V010	50	3	10	that in it I may know Jeshu, and the power of his resurrection, and have fellowship in his sufferings, and be conformed into his death,
B050C003V011	50	3	11	that any how I may be able to come to the resurrection which is from among the dead.
B050C003V012	50	3	12	I have not yet received, nor (am I) yet perfected; but I run, that so I may lay hold on that for the sake of which Jeshu the Meshiha hath laid hold on me.
B050C003V013	50	3	13	MY brethren, I think not concerning myself that I have laid hold (of the final prize); but one (thing) I know, that what is behind me I forget, and to that which is before me
B050C003V014	50	3	14	I stretch, and run towards the sign, to obtain the victory of the high vocation of Aloha by Jeshu Meshiha.
B050C003V015	50	3	15	Let those, then, who are mature consider these things; and if otherwise you consider, this also will Aloha reveal to you.
B050C003V016	50	3	16	Nevertheless, that to this we may attain, in one way let us proceed, and with one consent.
B050C003V017	50	3	17	Be like me, my brethren, and consider them who so walk according to the pattern you have seen in us.
B050C003V018	50	3	18	For there are many who walk otherwise, of whom many times I have told you, but now weeping I tell you, they are adversaries of the cross of the Meshiha;
B050C003V019	50	3	19	they, whose end is perdition, whose god is their belly, and whose glory is their shame; they, whose mind is in the earth.
B050C003V020	50	3	20	But our employment is in heaven, and from thence we expect the Saviour, our Lord Jeshu Meshiha,
B050C003V021	50	3	21	who will change the body of our abasement to make (it) in the fashion of his glorious body, according to his great power, by which all is subjected unto him.
B050C004V001	50	4	1	Wherefore, my brethren, beloved and tenderly-regarded, my joy and my crown, so stand in our Lord, my beloved.
B050C004V002	50	4	2	Of Evhodia I beseech, and of Syntika, that one mind they have in our Lord.
B050C004V003	50	4	3	Also of thee I beseech, my true yokefellow, to be helpful to those who are labouring with me in the gospel, with Klimis, and with the rest of my helpers, whose names are written in the book of life.
B050C004V004	50	4	4	Rejoice in our Lord in all time, and again I say, Rejoice.
B050C004V005	50	4	5	And let your meekness be known unto every man: our Lord is near.
B050C004V006	50	4	6	For nothing be anxious; but in all time, with prayer and with supplication, let your requests be made known before Aloha:
B050C004V007	50	4	7	And the peace of Aloha, which is greater than all knowledge, shall keep your hearts and your minds, through Jeshu Meshiha.
B050C004V008	50	4	8	FINALLY, my brethren, those (things) which are true, and those which are honest, and those which are just, and those which are pure, and those which are lovely, and those which are laudable, and those (which are) works of praise and of celebration, these consider.
B050C004V009	50	4	9	These which you have learned, and received, and heard, and seen in me, these perform; and the God of peace will be with you.
B050C004V010	50	4	10	But greatly do I rejoice in our Lord, that you have begun to care (again) for me, as also you were careful, but you have not had ability.
B050C004V011	50	4	11	But I have not spoken because I have had need; for I have learned to make sufficient to me that which I have had.
B050C004V012	50	4	12	I know (how) to be abased, I know also how to abound in all; and in every thing I am trained with sufficiency and with hunger, with abundance and with destitution:
B050C004V013	50	4	13	for every thing I am empowered through the Meshiha who strengtheneth me.
B050C004V014	50	4	14	Nevertheless, you have done well to communicate unto my afflictions.
B050C004V015	50	4	15	Know also, you Philipisoyee, that in the commencement of the gospel, when I went forth from Makedunia, not one of the churches communicated to me in the account of receiving and giving, but you only.
B050C004V016	50	4	16	For also to Thessalonika one time and twice to my necessity you sent.
B050C004V017	50	4	17	Not because I seek the gift, but I seek that fruit may multiply unto you.
B050C004V018	50	4	18	But I have received every thing, I abound; and am full; and I have accepted all that you sent me by Epaphroditos, a sweet fragrance and a sacrifice, acceptable, which pleaseth Aloha.
B050C004V019	50	4	19	And my God shall supply all your necessity, according to his riches in the glory of Jeshu Meshiha.
B050C004V020	50	4	20	To Aloha our Father be praise and glory to the age of ages. Amen.
B050C004V021	50	4	21	Ask for the peace of all the saints who are in Jeshu the Meshiha. The brethren who are with me ask for your peace.
B050C004V022	50	4	22	All the saints ask for your peace, especially those who are of the house of Caesar.
B050C004V023	50	4	23	The grace of our Lord Jeshu the Meshiha be with you all. Amen.
B051C001V001	51	1	1	PAULOS, an apostle of Jeshu the Meshiha by the will of Aloha, and the brother Timotheos,
B051C001V002	51	1	2	to those who are in Kulosos, the holy brethren and believers in Jeshu Meshiha: peace be with you, and grace from Aloha our Father.
B051C001V003	51	1	3	We give thanks to Aloha the Father of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha in all time, and pray on your behalf,
B051C001V004	51	1	4	even from our hearing of your faith in Jeshu Meshiha, and of your love to all the saints;
B051C001V005	51	1	5	for the hope which is kept for you in heaven, which at the first you heard through the word of the truth of the gospel,
B051C001V006	51	1	6	which is preached to you, as also to all the world, and increaseth and giveth fruits, as also in you from the day that you heard, and knew the grace of Aloha in truth,
B051C001V007	51	1	7	as you learned from Epaphra our beloved companion, who is himself for you a faithful minister of the Meshiha,
B051C001V008	51	1	8	and who hath made known to us your love, which is in the Spirit.
B051C001V009	51	1	9	ON account of this also we, from the day that we heard, have not ceased to pray for you, and to supplicate that you may be filled with the knowledge of the will of Aloha in all wisdom and in all spiritual understanding,
B051C001V010	51	1	10	and may walk according to that which is just, and may please Aloha in all good works, and may yield fruit, and increase in the knowledge of Aloha;
B051C001V011	51	1	11	and in all power be empowered according to the greatness of his glory in all patience and prolongedness of spirit:
B051C001V012	51	1	12	and with joy may give thanks to Aloha the Father, who hath fitted us for a portion of the inheritance of the saints in light,
B051C001V013	51	1	13	and hath delivered us from the power of darkness, and brought us into the kingdom of his beloved Son,
B051C001V014	51	1	14	in whom we have redemption and the forgiveness of sins:
B051C001V015	51	1	15	who is the image of Aloha the unseen, and the first-born of all the creatures.
B051C001V016	51	1	16	And by him was every thing created that is in heaven and in earth; all that is seen, and all that is unseen, whether thrones or dominions, or princes or powers; all things by his hand and through him were created;
B051C001V017	51	1	17	and he is before all, and every thing by him subsisteth.
B051C001V018	51	1	18	And he is the head of the body of the church, (he) who is the chief and first-born from among the dead, that he should be preeminent in all.
B051C001V019	51	1	19	For in him (the Father) hath willed all fulness to dwell;
B051C001V020	51	1	20	and by him to reconcile all things to himself, and to make peace through the blood of his cross, (even) by him, whether they be inhabitants in earth or in heaven.
B051C001V021	51	1	21	YOU also, who before were aliens and adversaries in your minds by your evil works,
B051C001V022	51	1	22	hath he reconciled now in the body of his flesh and through his death, to constitute you saints before him without spot and without blame;
B051C001V023	51	1	23	if you continue in your faith, your foundation being firm, and be not moved from the hope of the gospel which you have heard, and which is proclaimed to every creature who is under heaven, of which I, Paulos, am made a minister.
B051C001V024	51	1	24	I rejoice in the sufferings which are on your account, and fulfil the void of the afflictions of the Meshiha in my flesh for the sake of his body,
B051C001V025	51	1	25	which is the church; of which I am made a minister according to the dispensation of Aloha, which was given to me for you, to accomplish the word of Aloha;
B051C001V026	51	1	26	that mystery which was hidden from ages and generations, but now hath been revealed unto his saints.
B051C001V027	51	1	27	To whom Aloha hath willed to make known what is the opulence of the glory of this mystery among the Gentiles; which is, The Meshiha, who in you (is) the hope of glory;
B051C001V028	51	1	28	whom we proclaim, and (concerning whom) we teach and inform every man in all wisdom, that we may present every man perfect in Jeshu Meshiha;
B051C001V029	51	1	29	for which also I labour and contend, according to the help of the power which is given to me.
B051C002V001	51	2	1	But I wish you to know what an agony I have for you and for those who are in Laodikia, and for the rest who have not seen my person in the flesh;
B051C002V002	51	2	2	that their hearts may be comforted, and that they may approach in love to all the riches of assurance, and to the understanding of the knowledge of the mystery of Aloha the Father and of the Meshiha,
B051C002V003	51	2	3	in whom are hidden all the treasures of wisdom and of knowledge.
B051C002V004	51	2	4	But this I say, Let no man deceive you with the persuasion of words.
B051C002V005	51	2	5	For though in the flesh I am far from you, yet in the spirit I am with you; and I rejoice to behold your order, and the firmness of your faith in the Meshiha.
B051C002V006	51	2	6	As, then, you have received Jeshu Meshiha our Lord, (so) in him walk,
B051C002V007	51	2	7	your roots strengthened, and you builded in him, and established in that faith which you have learned, that you may abound therein with thanksgiving.
B051C002V008	51	2	8	Beware lest any man strip you by philosophy and by vain deceit, according to the teaching of men, and according to the principles of the world, and not according to the Meshiha,
B051C002V009	51	2	9	in whom dwelleth all the fulness of the Godhead bodily.
B051C002V010	51	2	10	And in him also you are complete; for he is the head of all principalities and powers.
B051C002V011	51	2	11	And in him you have been circumcised with the circumcision which is not with hands, by the putting away of the flesh of sins, (even) by the circumcision of the Meshiha.
B051C002V012	51	2	12	And you have been buried with him by baptism, and in him have risen with him, who have believed in the power of Aloha who raised him from among the dead.
B051C002V013	51	2	13	And you who were dead in your sins, and in the uncircumcision of your flesh, he hath made alive with him, and forgiven us all our sins;
B051C002V014	51	2	14	and hath blotted out in his mandates the writing of our debts that was against us, and hath taken it from the midst, and affixed it to his cross;
B051C002V015	51	2	15	and by the yielding up of his body he hath prostrated principalities and powers, and hath shamed them openly by himself.
B051C002V016	51	2	16	LET no man therefore judge you in meat and in drink, or in the distinctions of festivals, and of new moons, and of shabeths,
B051C002V017	51	2	17	which are shadows of those to come, but the body is the Meshiha.
B051C002V018	51	2	18	And lest any man wish by abasement of mind to fetter you to be subject to the worship of angels, intruding upon that which he hath not seen, and vainly inflated in his fleshly mind;
B051C002V019	51	2	19	and not holding the Head, from whom all the body is composed and constituted in joints and limbs, and increaseth (with) the increase of Aloha.
B051C002V020	51	2	20	For if you are dead with the Meshiha from the principles of the world, why as if you lived in the world are you judged? as that
B051C002V021	51	2	21	you are not to touch, nor to taste, nor to handle?
B051C002V022	51	2	22	For these are of perishable use, and are ordinances and doctrines of men;
B051C002V023	51	2	23	and appear to have in them a reason of wisdom, with the look of humility and the fear of Aloha, (as) not sparing the body, (yet) not in that which is (really) of value, but in those (things) whose use pertains to the flesh.
B051C003V001	51	3	1	IF, then, you have risen with the Meshiha, seek (the realities) which are on high, where the Meshiha sitteth at the right hand of Aloha.
B051C003V002	51	3	2	Think of that which is on high, and not of that on earth.
B051C003V003	51	3	3	For you are dead, and your life is hid with the Meshiha in Aloha;
B051C003V004	51	3	4	and when the Meshiha, who is our life, shall be manifested, then also will you be manifested with him in glory.
B051C003V005	51	3	5	Put to death, then, your members that are upon the earth: fornication, uncleanness, and passions, and evil desires, and covetousness, which itself is idolatry.
B051C003V006	51	3	6	For on account of these cometh the anger of Aloha upon the sons of disobedience.
B051C003V007	51	3	7	In these also you walked aforetime, when you were conversant in them.
B051C003V008	51	3	8	But now cease you from all these; anger, wrath, malice, reviling, impure speech:
B051C003V009	51	3	9	and lie not one to another, but put off the old man with all his manners,
B051C003V010	51	3	10	and wear the new, who is renovated by knowledge in the image of his Creator,
B051C003V011	51	3	11	where there is not Jihudoya and Aramoya, nor circumcision and uncircumcision, nor Javanoya and Barbaroya, nor slave and freeman, but the Meshiha is all and in all.
B051C003V012	51	3	12	Wear, therefore, as the chosen of Aloha, saints and beloved, compassions and tenderness, and benignity, and lowliness of mind, and composure, and patience.
B051C003V013	51	3	13	And bear with one another, and forgive one another, if any man have a complaint against his neighbour; even as the Meshiha hath forgiven you, so also forgive;
B051C003V014	51	3	14	and with all these charity, which is the girdle of perfection.
B051C003V015	51	3	15	And let the peace of the Meshiha direct your hearts, for to it you have been called in one body; and give thanks to the Meshiha,
B051C003V016	51	3	16	whose word shall dwell in you abundantly, in all wisdom. And teach and admonish yourselves in psalms and in hymns and in songs of the Spirit, and with grace sing with your hearts unto Aloha.
B051C003V017	51	3	17	And whatsoever you do, either in word or work, do (it) in the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, and with thanksgiving through him unto Aloha the Father.
B051C003V018	51	3	18	WIVES, be subject to your husbands, as it is right in the Meshiha.
B051C003V019	51	3	19	Men, love your wives, and be not bitter against them.
B051C003V020	51	3	20	Children, obey your parents in every thing, for so it is pleasing before our Lord.
B051C003V021	51	3	21	Fathers, exasperate not your children, that they be not discouraged.
B051C003V022	51	3	22	Servants, obey in every thing your masters according to the flesh, not in the sight of the eye (only), as those who please men, but from a simple heart, and in the fear of the Lord.
B051C003V023	51	3	23	And all that you do, from all your heart do (it), as to our Lord, and not as to men.
B051C003V024	51	3	24	And know that from our Lord you receive the reward in the inheritance; for the Lord the Meshiha you serve.
B051C003V025	51	3	25	But he who injureth is recompensed as he had injured, and there is no acceptance of persons.
B051C004V001	51	4	1	Masters, do equity and justice to your servants, knowing that you also have a Master in heaven.
B051C004V002	51	4	2	In prayer be constant, and be watchful in it, and (in) giving thanks;
B051C004V003	51	4	3	praying also for us, that Aloha may open to us the gate of the word, to speak the mystery of the Meshiha, for the sake of which I am bound,
B051C004V004	51	4	4	that I may fully make it manifest, as it behoveth me.
B051C004V005	51	4	5	In wisdom walk towards the outward ones, and redeem your opportunity.
B051C004V006	51	4	6	And let your speech at all time be with grace as sprinkled with salt, each one knowing how it becometh him to return the answer.
B051C004V007	51	4	7	What concerneth me will Tykikos, a beloved brother and faithful minister, and our companion in the Lord, make known to you:
B051C004V008	51	4	8	whom I have sent to you for this, that he may know how it is with you, and may comfort your hearts;
B051C004V009	51	4	9	with Onesimos, the faithful and beloved brother who is of you. These will make you know what concerneth us.
B051C004V010	51	4	10	Aristarchos, a captive with me, asketh for your peace, and Markos, the nephew of Bar Naba, regarding whom you are directed, that if he come to you, receive him,
B051C004V011	51	4	11	and Jeshu who is called Justos: these are of the circumcision, and these only have helped me in the kingdom of Aloha, and these have been a consolation to me.
B051C004V012	51	4	12	Epaphra, who is of you, asketh for your peace; a servant of the Meshiha, who is always labouring on your behalf in prayer, that you may stand perfect and complete in all the will of Aloha.
B051C004V013	51	4	13	For I testify of him that he hath a great zeal for you and for those in Laodikia and in Iropolis.
B051C004V014	51	4	14	Lukos our beloved physician, and Dima, ask for your peace.
B051C004V015	51	4	15	Ask the peace of the brethren who are in Laodikia, and of Nymfa, and of the church which is in his house.
B051C004V016	51	4	16	And when this epistle shall have been read to you, cause it also to be read in the church of the Laodikoyee; and that which is written from the Laodikoyee, read you it.
B051C004V017	51	4	17	And say to Arkipos, Be vigilant in the ministry which thou hast received in our Lord, that thou fulfil it.
B051C004V018	51	4	18	This salutation with the hand of me, PAULOS. Remember my bonds. Grace be with you. Amen.
B052C001V001	52	1	1	PAULOS, and Sylvanos, and Timotheos, to the church of the Thesalonikoyee which (is) in Aloha the Father, and in our Lord Jeshu Meshiha. Grace be with you and peace.
B052C001V002	52	1	2	We give thanks to Aloha at all time for you all and are mindful of you in our prayers constantly,
B052C001V003	52	1	3	and remember before Aloha the Father the works of your faith, and the labour of your love, and the perseverance of your hope, which is in our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B052C001V004	52	1	4	For we know your election, my brethren, beloved of Aloha,
B052C001V005	52	1	5	because our preaching was not in words only with you, but with power, and with the Spirit of Holiness, and with the persuasion of truth. Also you know how we were among you, on account of you;
B052C001V006	52	1	6	and you became imitators of us and of our Lord, and you received the word in great affliction, and with the joy of the Spirit of Holiness,
B052C001V007	52	1	7	and became an example to all the believers who are in Makedunia and in Akaia.
B052C001V008	52	1	8	For from you was made to be heard the word of our Lord, not only in Makedunia and in Akaia, but in every place your faith which is in Aloha was made to be heard, so that we have no need to say of you any thing.
B052C001V009	52	1	9	For they learned what an entrance we had unto you, and how you turned to Aloha, from the fear of idols, to worship Aloha the living and the true;
B052C001V010	52	1	10	awaiting his Son from heaven, Jeshu himself, whom he raised from among the dead, and who delivered us from the wrath that cometh.
B052C002V001	52	2	1	And you know, my brethren, that our entrance unto you was not in vain,
B052C002V002	52	2	2	but having suffered before and been shamefully treated, as you know, in Philipos, and then (even) in great conflict we spoke with you with the confidence of our God the gospel of the Meshiha.
B052C002V003	52	2	3	For our exhortation was not from deceit, nor from uncleanness, nor from guile;
B052C002V004	52	2	4	but as approved of Aloha to be intrusted with his gospel, so speaking as not to please men, but Aloha who trieth our hearts.
B052C002V005	52	2	5	For never have we used flattering speech, as you know, nor for an occasion of covetousness, Aloha witnesseth.
B052C002V006	52	2	6	Neither have we sought glory from men, either from you or from others, though we could have been honoured ones, as the apostles of the Meshiha;
B052C002V007	52	2	7	but we were humble among you, and, as a nurse who loveth her children,
B052C002V008	52	2	8	so also we loved, and were desirous to impart to you, not only the gospel of Aloha, but also our life, because we loved you.
B052C002V009	52	2	9	Remember, therefore, my brethren, how we laboured and toiled in the work of our hands by night and by day, that we might not be a burden on one of you.
B052C002V010	52	2	10	You witness and Aloha, how we preached to you the gospel of Aloha, purely and justly, and were without blame with all the faithful.
B052C002V011	52	2	11	As you know how every one of you, as a father his children, we exhorted, and spoke with your hearts;
B052C002V012	52	2	12	and (now) we testify to you how you should walk worthy of Aloha himself who hath called you to his kingdom and to his glory.
B052C002V013	52	2	13	WHEREFORE we also give thanks constantly unto Aloha, that the word of Aloha which you received from us, was not as the word of man (that) you received (it), but, as it is truly, the word of Aloha, which in operation worketh (alike) in you and in all them who believe.
B052C002V014	52	2	14	But you, my brethren, have become like the churches of Aloha which are in Jihud, who are in Jeshu Meshiha, because you likewise suffer from your fellow-country-men, as they also from the Jihudoyee;
B052C002V015	52	2	15	who killed our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, and the prophets who were of them, and ourselves have persecuted, and Aloha have not pleased,
B052C002V016	52	2	16	and have acted adversely to all men; who forbid us to speak with the Gentiles that they might be saved; to fill up their sins for all time: but upon them cometh the wrath unto the end!
B052C002V017	52	2	17	BUT we, my brethren, having been bereaved-ones of you the time of an hour, as to our presence, but not in our heart, have been the more solicitous to see your faces with great love,
B052C002V018	52	2	18	and have wished to come to you (even) I, Paulos, one time and two; but Satana hindered me.
B052C002V019	52	2	19	For what is our hope and our joy, and the crown of our glorying, but you, before our Lord Jeshu at his coming?
B052C002V020	52	2	20	For you are our glory and our joy.
B052C003V001	52	3	1	And because we could not endure, we were willing to be left at Athinos alone,
B052C003V002	52	3	2	and to send to you Timotheos our brother, a minister of Aloha and our helper in the gospel of the Meshiha, to fortify you, and inquire of you concerning your faith,
B052C003V003	52	3	3	that none of you should be slain through these afflictions; for you know that to this we are set.
B052C003V004	52	3	4	For while also we were with you, we foretold you that we were to be afflicted, as you know that it hath been.
B052C003V005	52	3	5	On account of this also, I, not enduring until I had sent to know your faith, lest the tempter should tempt you, and we should have laboured in vain;
B052C003V006	52	3	6	but now when Timotheos came to us from among you, and gave us intelligence of your faith and of your love, and that you have a good remembrance of us in every season, and desire to see us as we also (to see) you;
B052C003V007	52	3	7	on this account we were comforted in you, my brethren, in all our anxieties and our afflictions because of your faith.
B052C003V008	52	3	8	And now we live, if you are established in our Lord.
B052C003V009	52	3	9	For what thanks giving can we render on account of you to Aloha, over all the joy with which we rejoice on your behalf,
B052C003V010	52	3	10	unless before Aloha we supplicate exceedingly by night and by day to see your faces, and to perfect what is wanting to your faith?
B052C003V011	52	3	11	But Aloha himself, the Father of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, will make straight our way to you,
B052C003V012	52	3	12	and he will cause your love to increase to one another, and to every man, even as we love you;
B052C003V013	52	3	13	and will establish your hearts without blame in holiness, before Aloha our Father, at the advent of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha with all his saints.
B052C004V001	52	4	1	HENCE then, my brethren, we pray of you, and beseech of you by our Lord Jeshu, that as you have received of us how it behoveth you to walk and to please Aloha, the more to increase.
B052C004V002	52	4	2	For you know those precepts we gave to you in our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B052C004V003	52	4	3	For this is the will of Aloha, your sanctification; and that you be distant from all fornication;
B052C004V004	52	4	4	and that every man of you know to possess his vessel in sanctification and in honour,
B052C004V005	52	4	5	and not in the passions of concupiscence, as the rest of the Gentiles who know not Aloha.
B052C004V006	52	4	6	And that you dare not transgress, and defraud the one man his brother in this matter, because our Lord is the avenger of all these, as we have also before told you and testified.
B052C004V007	52	4	7	For Aloha hath not called us to uncleanness, but unto sanctification.
B052C004V008	52	4	8	Therefore, whoever despiseth, not man he despiseth, but Aloha, who hath ingiven you his Holy Spirit.
B052C004V009	52	4	9	But concerning the love of the brethren, you need not (that I) write to you; for you yourselves are taught of Aloha to love one another.
B052C004V010	52	4	10	And so do you to all the brethren who are in all Makedunia; but I beseech of you, my brethren, to excel .
B052C004V011	52	4	11	And study to be quiet and be occupied with your own employments, and work with your hands, as we have admonished you;
B052C004V012	52	4	12	that you may walk becomingly towards the outward-ones, and of man you may not need.
B052C004V013	52	4	13	BUT I wish you to know, my brethren, that for those who are asleep you should not have sorrow, as the rest of men, who have no hope.
B052C004V014	52	4	14	For if we believe that Jeshu died and arose, so also Aloha those who have slept in Jeshu will bring with him.
B052C004V015	52	4	15	But this we say to you by the word of our Lord, that we who remaining at the coming of our Lord, who live, will not precede those who have slept.
B052C004V016	52	4	16	For our Lord himself with the mandate, and with the voice of the chief of angels, and with the trumpet of Aloha, will come down from heaven, and the dead who are in the Meshiha will arise first;
B052C004V017	52	4	17	and then we who remaining alive, shall be rapt with them together in clouds, to the meeting of our Lord in the expanse; and so always with our Lord shall we be.
B052C004V018	52	4	18	Wherefore comfort one another with these words.
B052C005V001	52	5	1	But of the times and the seasons, my brethren, you need not that I write to you;
B052C005V002	52	5	2	for you truly know that the day of our Lord as a thief in the night so cometh.
B052C005V003	52	5	3	While they shall be saying, Peace and tranquillity, then unawares will destruction arise against them, as distress upon the child-bearer, and they shall not escape.
B052C005V004	52	5	4	But you, my brethren, are not in darkness, that that day as a thief should overtake you.
B052C005V005	52	5	5	For all of you are sons of light, and sons of the day; and are not sons of the night, nor sons of darkness.
B052C005V006	52	5	6	Sleep we not, therefore, as the rest; but be wakeful and sober.
B052C005V007	52	5	7	For they who sleep, in the night sleep; and they who are drunken, in the night are drunken.
B052C005V008	52	5	8	But we who are sons of the day must be wakeful in our minds, and wear the mail-coat of faith and of love, and put on the helmet of the hope of salvation.
B052C005V009	52	5	9	For Aloha hath not appointed us to wrath, but to the possession of salvation in our Lord Jeshu Meshiha,
B052C005V010	52	5	10	who died on our behalf, that, whether we wake or sleep, together with him we may live.
B052C005V011	52	5	11	Wherefore comfort one another, and edify one another, as also you do.
B052C005V012	52	5	12	BUT I entreat of you, my brethren, to know them who labour among you, and stand before your faces teaching you,
B052C005V013	52	5	13	that they be esteemed by you in abundant love; and on account of their work be at peace with them.
B052C005V014	52	5	14	And I entreat of you, my brethren, (to) admonish the offenders, and encourage the little of soul, and bear the burden of the weak, and prolong your spirit toward every man.
B052C005V015	52	5	15	And beware, lest any of you evil render for evil; but always follow after (those things which are) good (pl.) toward one another, and toward every man.
B052C005V016	52	5	16	Be joyful always,
B052C005V017	52	5	17	and pray without ceasing,
B052C005V018	52	5	18	and in every thing give thanks; for this is the will of Aloha in Jeshu Meshiha concerning you.
B052C005V019	52	5	19	The Spirit quench not.
B052C005V020	52	5	20	Prophecy do not despise.
B052C005V021	52	5	21	Prove every thing, and what is good retain.
B052C005V022	52	5	22	And from every evil thing flee.
B052C005V023	52	5	23	But the God of peace himself will sanctify perfectly all of you; and your whole spirit, and your soul, and your body will he keep without fault, to the coming of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B052C005V024	52	5	24	Faithful is he who hath called you, who himself will do it!
B052C005V025	52	5	25	My brethren, pray for us.
B052C005V026	52	5	26	Ask the peace of all our brethren, with the holy kiss.
B052C005V027	52	5	27	I adjure you, by our Lord, that this epistle be read to all the holy brethren.
B052C005V028	52	5	28	The grace of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha be with you. Amen.
B053C001V001	53	1	1	PAULOS, and Sylvanos, and Timotheos, to the church of the Thesalonikoyee, which is in Aloha our Father, and our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B053C001V002	53	1	2	Grace be with you, and peace, from Aloha our Father, and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B053C001V003	53	1	3	To give thanks we owe to Aloha at all time on behalf of you, my brethren, as it is proper; because your faith greatly increaseth, and the love of you all, of every man toward his neighbour, enlargeth;
B053C001V004	53	1	4	as that we also boast of you in the churches of Aloha, of your faith and of your patience, in all your persecution and your affliction which you endure;
B053C001V005	53	1	5	for a demonstration of the just judgment of Aloha, that you may be worthy of his kingdom, for the sake of which you suffer;
B053C001V006	53	1	6	and whether it is (not) righteous to render afflictions to them who afflict you.
B053C001V007	53	1	7	And you who are afflicted will he save with us, at the revelation of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha from heaven, with the host Of his angels, when he executeth the punishment, with burning of fire,
B053C001V008	53	1	8	on them who have not known Aloha, and on them who have not acknowledged the gospel of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B053C001V009	53	1	9	For these in the judgment will be punished (with) the perdition of eternity, from the presence of our Lord, and from the glory of his power;
B053C001V010	53	1	10	when he cometh to be glorified in his saints, and to show his wonders in his faithful ones, that our testimony that was concerning you may be believed in that day.
B053C001V011	53	1	11	On account of this at all time pray we for you, that Aloha may make you meet for your calling, and complete in you all the will of good (things), and the operations of faith with power;
B053C001V012	53	1	12	that the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha may be glorified in you, and you also in him, according to the grace of Aloha and our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B053C002V001	53	2	1	But we beseech of you, my brethren, as it regards the coming of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, and our assemblage with him,
B053C002V002	53	2	2	that you be not soon moved in your minds, nor perturbed, nor by word, nor by spirit, nor by letter, which (may be) as (if it were) from us, that, Behold, the day of our Lord cometh!
B053C002V003	53	2	3	Let no one deceive you by any one of the methods, because unless there shall come first the rebellion, and there be revealed the man of sin, the son of perdition;
B053C002V004	53	2	4	He who is the adversary, and is exalted over all who is called God and Venerable; so that also in the temple of Aloha as Aloha he will sit, and will make manifest of himself as that he is Aloha.
B053C002V005	53	2	5	Do you not remember, that, when I was with you, these I told you?
B053C002V006	53	2	6	And now you know what holdeth, that he may be revealed in his time.
B053C002V007	53	2	7	For the mystery of iniquity already beginneth to be effective; only if that which now holdeth be taken from the midst,
B053C002V008	53	2	8	then will be revealed that evil one, whom our Lord Jeshu will consume by the spirit of his mouth, and will abolish by the revelation of his advent.
B053C002V009	53	2	9	For the coming of that (wicked one) is the working of Satana, with all power, and (with) signs and false miracles,
B053C002V010	53	2	10	and with all unrighteous deception which is done in them who perish, because they have not received the love of the truth by which they might have been saved.
B053C002V011	53	2	11	Wherefore Aloha will send them the working of deception,
B053C002V012	53	2	12	that they will believe the lie, and all of them will be judged who have not believed in the truth, but have had pleasure in unrighteousness.
B053C002V013	53	2	13	But we are bound to give thanks unto Aloha at all time for you, our brethren, beloved in our Lord, because Aloha hath chosen you from the beginning unto salvation, by sanctification of the Spirit, and by the belief of the truth.
B053C002V014	53	2	14	For unto these Aloha called you by our preaching, that you should be the glory of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B053C002V015	53	2	15	Wherefore, my brethren, stand fast, and persevere in the precepts which you have been taught, whether by word, or by our epistle.
B053C002V016	53	2	16	But our Lord Jeshu Meshiha himself, and Aloha our Father, who hath loved us, and given us everlasting consolation, and a good hope through grace,
B053C002V017	53	2	17	will comfort your hearts, and establish in every word and in every work of good.
B053C003V001	53	3	1	Henceforth, my brethren, pray for us, that the word of our Lord may run and be glorified in every place, as among you.
B053C003V002	53	3	2	And that we may be delivered from wicked men and perverse; for every man hath not faith.
B053C003V003	53	3	3	But the Lord is faithful, who will keep you and deliver you from evil.
B053C003V004	53	3	4	But we confide concerning you in our Lord, that what we have commanded you, you have done,
B053C003V005	53	3	5	and also are doing. And our Lord will direct your hearts to the love of Aloha, and to the patience of the Meshiha.
B053C003V006	53	3	6	But we command you, my brethren, in the name of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, that you remove from every brother who walketh wickedly, and not according to the precepts which he hath received from us.
B053C003V007	53	3	7	For you know how it behoveth to imitate us who walked not wickedly among you.
B053C003V008	53	3	8	Neither did we eat bread for nothing from any one of you; but with labour and weariness by night and by day we wrought, that upon no one of you we might be burdensome.
B053C003V009	53	3	9	Not because we had not power, but because in ourselves we would give you an example, that you may imitate us.
B053C003V010	53	3	10	For while we were with you, this we commanded you, that every one who willeth not to work, neither should he eat.
B053C003V011	53	3	11	For we hear that there are some among you who walk wickedly, and nothing work, unless vain things.
B053C003V012	53	3	12	But these we command, and entreat of them by our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, that with quietness they work, and eat their (own) bread.
B053C003V013	53	3	13	But you, my brethren, be not weary in doing what is good.
B053C003V014	53	3	14	And if any man hearken not to these our words in the epistle, let this be separate from you, and be not mixed with him, that he be shamed.
B053C003V015	53	3	15	Yet, not as an enemy hold him, but admonish him as a brother.
B053C003V016	53	3	16	But the Lord of peace himself will give you peace always, in every thing. Our Lord be with you all.
B053C003V017	53	3	17	Salutation, by the writing of my hand, I, PAULOS, have written; which is the sign in all my epistles, so I write.
B053C003V018	53	3	18	The grace of Jeshu Meshiha be with you all, my brethren. Amen.
B054C001V001	54	1	1	PAULOS, an apostle of Jeshu Meshiha, by the commandment of Aloha our Saviour, and of Jeshu Meshiha our hope;
B054C001V002	54	1	2	to Timotheos, my true son in the faith: grace and mercy and peace from Aloha our Father and Jeshu Meshiha our Lord.
B054C001V003	54	1	3	I requested of thee, when I would go into Makedunia, to remain at Ephesos, and instruct certain men that they teach not various doctrines,
B054C001V004	54	1	4	nor throw themselves (away) upon stories and tales of generations which have no end, (but) which rather subserve contentions, and not edification in the faith of Aloha.
B054C001V005	54	1	5	But the end of the commandment is love, from a pure heart, and from a good conscience, and from genuine faith.
B054C001V006	54	1	6	And from them that have erred, and have declined to vain words,
B054C001V007	54	1	7	seeking to become teachers of the law, while they understand not what they speak, nor that concerning which they contend.
B054C001V008	54	1	8	But we know that the law is good, if a man according to the law converse in it;
B054C001V009	54	1	9	knowing that against the righteous the law is not set, but against the evil, and rebels, and the wicked, and sinners, and the dishonest, and those who are not pure, and those who strike their fathers, and those who strike their mothers, and murderers,
B054C001V010	54	1	10	and fornicators, and liers with men, and stealers of the free, and liars, and doers against an oath
B054C001V011	54	1	11	and whatever (else) is opposed to the healthful doctrine of the gospel of the glory of the blessed Aloha, with which I have been intrusted.
B054C001V012	54	1	12	And I thank him who hath empowered me, our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, who accounted me faithful, and constituted me his minister; me,
B054C001V013	54	1	13	who before was a blasphemer, and a persecutor, and injurious; but I received mercy, because while ignorant I did it, without faith.
B054C001V014	54	1	14	But in me hath abounded the grace of our Lord, and faith and love which are in Jeshu Meshiha.
B054C001V015	54	1	15	Faithful is the word, and worthy of reception that Jeshu the Meshiha came into the world to save sinners, of whom I am first.
B054C001V016	54	1	16	But for this he had compassion upon me, that in me first Jeshu Meshiha might show all long-suffering, as an exhibition for them who should believe in him unto everlasting life.
B054C001V017	54	1	17	But to the King who is eternal, incorruptible, and unseen, who is one Aloha, be honour and glory for ever and ever. Amen.
B054C001V018	54	1	18	This commandment I commit to thee, my son Timotheos, according to the early prophecies which were concerning thee, that thou mayest war through them this good warfare with faith and with a good conscience.
B054C001V019	54	1	19	For those who this have put away from them of faith have been emptied;
B054C001V020	54	1	20	as Hymeneos and Alexandros, whom I have delivered to Satana, that they may not blaspheme.
B054C002V001	54	2	1	I REQUIRE then from thee, that, before every thing supplication be offered to Aloha, and prayer and intercession and thanksgiving for all men;
B054C002V002	54	2	2	for kings and princes, that an habitation quiet and tranquil we may inhabit in all the fear of Aloha and purity.
B054C002V003	54	2	3	For this is good and acceptable before Aloha our Saviour;
B054C002V004	54	2	4	who willeth that all men should be saved, and turn to the knowledge of the truth.
B054C002V005	54	2	5	For one is Aloha, and one is the Mediator of Aloha and of men; the man Jeshu Meshiha,
B054C002V006	54	2	6	who gave himself a ransom for every man; a testimony which cometh in its time,
B054C002V007	54	2	7	of which I am constituted an herald and an apostle, I say the truth and lie not, to be a teacher of the nations in the faith of the truth.
B054C002V008	54	2	8	I wish then for men to pray in every place, uplifting their hands purely and without wrath and without disputations.
B054C002V009	54	2	9	So also let women with decorous simplicity of apparel,with modesty and with chastity, adorn themselves, not with braidings, and with gold, and with pearls, and with fine vestments,
B054C002V010	54	2	10	but with good works, as becometh women who profess the fear of Aloha.
B054C002V011	54	2	11	Let the wife in quietude learn with all submission:
B054C002V012	54	2	12	for unto the wife to teach I permit not, neither to be authoritative over the husband, but to be in quietude.
B054C002V013	54	2	13	For Adam was formed first, then Hava;
B054C002V014	54	2	14	and Adam was not deceived, but the wife was deceived, and transgressed the commandment.
B054C002V015	54	2	15	But she is saved by her children, if they continue in faith, and in love, and in sanctification, and in chastity.
B054C003V001	54	3	1	This saying is faithful, that if a man desire the presbyterate, a good work he desireth.
B054C003V002	54	3	2	But it behoveth that a presbyter be as that blame be not found in him; and that he be the husband of one wife; (a man) who is of a vigilant mind, chaste, and orderly, and a lover of guests, and instructful;
B054C003V003	54	3	3	and not a transgressor over wine, nor (one) whose hand hastens to strike; but he is to be gentle and not contentious, nor a lover of money;
B054C003V004	54	3	4	and (one who) ruleth his house well, holding his children in subjection with all purity.
B054C003V005	54	3	5	For if his own house he know not to rule well, how is he able to rule the church of Aloha?
B054C003V006	54	3	6	Neither shall his discipleship be recent, lest he be lifted up, and fall into the judgment of Satana.
B054C003V007	54	3	7	But it is needful that he have also a good testimony from those without, that he may not fall into reproach, and into the net of Satana.
B054C003V008	54	3	8	And also the ministers must be pure, not speaking doubly, not inclined to much wine, nor shall they love unclean gains.
B054C003V009	54	3	9	But they shall hold the mystery of the faith with a pure conscience.
B054C003V010	54	3	10	And these are to be proved first, and then to minister, being without blame.
B054C003V011	54	3	11	Thus also must the woman be chaste, and they shall be vigilant (in their) minds, and faithful in every thing; and they shall not be accusers.
B054C003V012	54	3	12	The ministers shall be (of them) severally who have one wife, and shall rule each his children and his household well.
B054C003V013	54	3	13	For they who minister well, a good degree acquire for themselves, and much openness of face in the faith of Jeshu Meshiha.
B054C003V014	54	3	14	These I write to thee, hoping soon to come to thee;
B054C003V015	54	3	15	but if I should delay, that thou mayest know how to converse in the house of Aloha, which is the church of Aloha the Living, the column and foundation of the truth.
B054C003V016	54	3	16	And truly great is this mystery of righteousness, which was revealed in the flesh, and justified by the Spirit, and seen of angels, and preached among the peoples, and believed in the world, and taken up into glory.
B054C004V001	54	4	1	But the Spirit distinctly saith, that in the last times some will remove from the faith, and will go after deceiving spirits, and after doctrines of demons.
B054C004V002	54	4	2	These, with a false appearance, will deceive, speaking a lie, and seared in their conscience,
B054C004V003	54	4	3	and prohibiting to marry, and abstaining from meats, which Aloha created to be used with thanksgiving by them who believe and know the truth;
B054C004V004	54	4	4	because every creature of Aloha is good, and nothing to be abominated, if with thanksgiving it be received;
B054C004V005	54	4	5	for it is sanctified by the word of Aloha, and by prayer.
B054C004V006	54	4	6	These if thou shalt teach thy brethren, a good minister wilt thou be of Jeshu Meshiha, while thou wilt be enlarged with words of faith and of the good doctrine which thou hast learned.
B054C004V007	54	4	7	But from the foolish stories of old women abstain; and exercise thy soul in righteousness.
B054C004V008	54	4	8	For the exercise of the body a little time profiteth; but righteousness in every thing profiteth, and hath the promise of the life of this time, and of the future.
B054C004V009	54	4	9	FAITHFUL is the saying and worthy is it of reception:
B054C004V010	54	4	10	for on this account we labour and are reproached, because we hope in Aloha the Living, who is the Saviour of all men, and especially of the believers.
B054C004V011	54	4	11	These teach and command.
B054C004V012	54	4	12	And let no man despise thy youth; but be an example to the believers in word, and in conduct, and in charity, and in faith, and in purity.
B054C004V013	54	4	13	Till I come be diligent in reading, and in prayer, and in teaching.
B054C004V014	54	4	14	Neglect not the gift that is in thee, which was given thee with prophecy, and the hand-laying of the presbytery.
B054C004V015	54	4	15	In these meditate, and in them be, that it may be known to every man that thou goest onward.
B054C004V016	54	4	16	And take heed to thyself, and to thy doctrine, and persevere in them; for while these thou doest, thyself wilt thou save, and them who hear thee.
B054C005V001	54	5	1	An elder do not reprimand, but persuade him as a father, and those who are young as thy brethren,
B054C005V002	54	5	2	and the elderly women as mothers, and those who are young as thy sisters, with all purity.
B054C005V003	54	5	3	The widows honour them who are widows in truth.
B054C005V004	54	5	4	And if there be a widow who hath children, or children's children, let them learn first to do justly for their families, and to repay the debts (owing) to their parents; for this is acceptable before Aloha.
B054C005V005	54	5	5	But she who is truly a widow and solitary (is one) whose hope is in Aloha, and who persevereth in prayer and in supplication by night and by day.
B054C005V006	54	5	6	But she who serveth pleasure is dead while she liveth.
B054C005V007	54	5	7	These things prescribe to them, that they be without blame.
B054C005V008	54	5	8	For if a man hath not care of them who are his own, and especially of them who are children of the household of faith, he hath denied the faith, and is worse than those who believe not.
B054C005V009	54	5	9	Elect, then, the widow who is not less than sixty years, who hath had one husband,
B054C005V010	54	5	10	and who hath the testimony of good works: if she have brought up children, if she have received guests, if she have washed the feet of the saints, if she have cheered the afflicted, if she have walked in every gracious work.
B054C005V011	54	5	11	But from the widows who are young, withhold (the election); for these become schismatical against the Meshiha, and seek to marry,
B054C005V012	54	5	12	and their condemnation is confirmed, because they have rejected their first fidelity.
B054C005V013	54	5	13	They also learn idleness, wandering from house to house; and not only idleness, but also to multiply words, and to follow vain (pursuits), and to speak things which they ought not.
B054C005V014	54	5	14	I will therefore that those who are young should marry, and bear children, and conduct their households,
B054C005V015	54	5	15	and not give to the adversary any occasion to revile. For already have some begun to turn aside after Satana.
B054C005V016	54	5	16	If any believing man or believing woman have widows, let them support them, that they may not be burden-some on the church, that they who are widows indeed may have sufficient.
B054C005V017	54	5	17	Those presbyters who well conduct themselves shall be worthy of double honour, especially they who labour in the word and in doctrine.
B054C005V018	54	5	18	For the scripture saith, Thou shalt not muzzle the ox in the treading out; and, Worthy is the labourer of his hire.
B054C005V019	54	5	19	Against a presbyter an accusation receive not, except on the mouth of two or three witnesses.
B054C005V020	54	5	20	Those who sin before all men reprove, that the rest may be afraid.
B054C005V021	54	5	21	I attest thee before Aloha and our Lord Jeshu Meshiha and his elect angels, that thou keep these, (precepts,) and let not thy mind be pre-occupied by any thing, and do nothing with acceptance of persons.
B054C005V022	54	5	22	The hand suddenly on any man lay not, neither participate in others' sins. Keep thyself in purity.
B054C005V023	54	5	23	And henceforth water drink not, but wine a little drink, on account of thy stomach, and on account of thy constant infirmities.
B054C005V024	54	5	24	THERE are men whose sins are known, and they precede them to the place of judgment; and there are whose (sins) go after them.
B054C005V025	54	5	25	So also good men are known; and those who are otherwise cannot be hid.
B054C006V001	54	6	1	Let those who are under the yoke of servitude hold their masters in all honour, that the name of Aloha and his doctrine be not blasphemed.
B054C006V002	54	6	2	But let not those who have believing masters slight them, because they are their brethren; but serve them the more, because they are believers, and beloved who are refreshed by their ministry. These things teach and require of them.
B054C006V003	54	6	3	But if there be a man who teacheth other doctrine, and who accedeth not to the healthful words of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, and to the doctrine of the fear of Aloha,
B054C006V004	54	6	4	this (is one) who extolleth himself while knowing nothing, but is infirm with disputation and questioning of words, from which are envy, and contention, and evil speaking, and supposition in the evil mind,
B054C006V005	54	6	5	and conflicts of men whose minds are corrupt and deprived of the truth, and who consider that gain is the fear of Aloha.
B054C006V006	54	6	6	But thou, remove thyself from them. For our gain is great which is the fear of Aloha, with the use of our sufficiency.
B054C006V007	54	6	7	For nothing brought we into the world, and we know that nothing we are able to take from it.
B054C006V008	54	6	8	Therefore sufficient to us are food and raiment.
B054C006V009	54	6	9	But they who will be rich fall into temptations and snares, and many lusts which befool and injure, and which plunge men into destruction and perdition.
B054C006V010	54	6	10	For the root of all evil is the love of money; and there are who have coveted it, and from the faith have erred, and have made themselves enter into many sorrows.
B054C006V011	54	6	11	But thou, O man of God, from these things flee, and follow after righteousness, and after equity, and after faith, and after charity, and after patience, and after meekness.
B054C006V012	54	6	12	And contend in the good agony of faith, and lay hold of the life which is eternal, unto which thou art called, and hast confessed a good confession before many witnesses.
B054C006V013	54	6	13	I ATTEST thee before Aloha, who vivifieth all, and Jeshu Meshiha, who witnessed before Pontius Pilatos the good testimony,
B054C006V014	54	6	14	that thou keep (this) commandment without spot and without blemish, until the manifestation of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha,
B054C006V015	54	6	15	whom in his time will show Aloha the blessed and only Strong One, the King of kings, and Lord of lords;
B054C006V016	54	6	16	he who only is incorruptible, and (who) dwelleth in light which no man can approach; whom no man of men hath seen, nor is able to see: to him be honour and power for ever and ever. Amen.
B054C006V017	54	6	17	The rich of this world instruct, that they be not uplifted in their minds, nor be trustful upon riches which have no security, but upon Aloha the living, who giveth to us all abundantly for our comfort;
B054C006V018	54	6	18	and that they perform good works, and become rich in welldoings, and be ready to give and to communicate,
B054C006V019	54	6	19	and lay for themselves a good foundation for that which is to be, that they may lay hold on the true life.
B054C006V020	54	6	20	O Timothy, watch over that which is confided to thee, and fly from vain words, and the turnings of false knowledge.
B054C006V021	54	6	21	For they who pursue it err from the faith. Grace be with thee. Amen.
B055C001V001	55	1	1	PAULOS, an apostle of Jeshu Meshiha by the will of Aloha, and on account of the promise of life which is in Jeshu Meshiha,
B055C001V002	55	1	2	to Timotheos my beloved son: grace and mercies and peace from Aloha our Father, and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B055C001V003	55	1	3	I thank Aloha, whom I serve from my fathers with a pure conscience, that constantly I remember thee in my prayers of the night and of the day;
B055C001V004	55	1	4	and have longed to see thee, being mindful of thy tears, that I may be filled with joy:
B055C001V005	55	1	5	in remembrance of thee (and) of thy true faith which dwelt first in the mother of thy mother Lois, and in thy mother Eunika, and which, I am persuaded, (is) in thee also.
B055C001V006	55	1	6	On account of this I put thee in mind to keep awake the gift of Aloha, which is in thee by the laying on of my hands.
B055C001V007	55	1	7	For Aloha hath not given to us the spirit of fear, but of power and of love and of discipline.
B055C001V008	55	1	8	Wherefore be not thou ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, nor of me his prisoner; but sustain evil with the gospel, through the power of Aloha,
B055C001V009	55	1	9	who hath saved us, and called us with an holy calling; not according to our works, but according to his will, and that grace of his which was given to us in Jeshu Meshiha before the time of the worlds,
B055C001V010	55	1	10	and is now revealed by the revelation of our Saviour Jeshu Meshiha, who hath abolished death, and hath demonstrated life and incorruption, through the gospel,
B055C001V011	55	1	11	of which I am appointed an herald and an apostle and a teacher of the nations:
B055C001V012	55	1	12	on account of which I suffer these, and am not ashamed. I know in whom I have believed, and am persuaded that there is power in his hands my deposite to keep for me unto that day.
B055C001V013	55	1	13	Let the outline of sound words be with thee, which thou hast heard from me, with the faith and love which are in Jeshu Meshiha:
B055C001V014	55	1	14	that good deposite keep through the Spirit of Holiness who dwelleth in us.
B055C001V015	55	1	15	Know this, that all those of Asia are turned from me, of whom are Phygellos and Harmogenes.
B055C001V016	55	1	16	Our Lord give mercies to the house of Onesiphoros, who many times hath refreshed me, and of the chains of my bonds hath not been ashamed.
B055C001V017	55	1	17	But when also he came to Ruma, with diligence he sought me, and found me.
B055C001V018	55	1	18	Our Lord grant that he may find mercies with our Lord in that day: and how he ministered to me in Ephesos thou especially knowest.
B055C002V001	55	2	1	Thou therefore, my son, be strong in the grace of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B055C002V002	55	2	2	And those (doctrines) which thou hast heard from me by many witnesses, them commit to faithful men, who are also able to teach others.
B055C002V003	55	2	3	And endure evils as a good soldier of Jeshu Meshiha.
B055C002V004	55	2	4	No man serveth as a soldier, and entangleth himself with the affairs of the world, that he might please him who hath chosen him.
B055C002V005	55	2	5	And if one contendeth, he is not crowned, unless according to his law he contend.
B055C002V006	55	2	6	It becometh the husbandman who laboureth that he should first eat of his fruits.
B055C002V007	55	2	7	Understand what I say to thee. Our Lord give thee wisdom in all things.
B055C002V008	55	2	8	Remember Jeshu Meshiha, that he arose from among the dead, he who is of the seed of David, according to my gospel;
B055C002V009	55	2	9	for which I endure evils unto bonds, as an evil-doer: but the word of Aloha is not bound.
B055C002V010	55	2	10	Therefore I endure every thing on account of the elect, that they also may find salvation in Jeshu Meshiha, with the glory that is eternal.
B055C002V011	55	2	11	Faithful is the word: For if we be dead with him, With him also we shall live;
B055C002V012	55	2	12	And if we endure, We shall also reign with him; But, if we deny him, He also will deny us!
B055C002V013	55	2	13	And if we believe him not, He in his faithfulness abideth; For deny himself he cannot.
B055C002V014	55	2	14	Of these (truths) remind them, and testify before our Lord, that they contend not with unprofitable words, to the overturning of those who hear them.
B055C002V015	55	2	15	And be careful to establish thyself perfectly before Aloha, a workman without shame, preaching rightly the word of truth.
B055C002V016	55	2	16	From vain words which have no utility in them withdraw; for they add greatly to the wickedness of those who are occupied with them.
B055C002V017	55	2	17	And their words as an eating cancer will lay hold upon many: but one of them is Hymeneos, and another Philetos,
B055C002V018	55	2	18	who have erred from the truth, saying, that the resurrection of the dead hath been, and the faith of some overturning.
B055C002V019	55	2	19	But the true foundation of Aloha standeth; and it hath this signature: And the Lord knoweth them who are his. And, Let every one who invoketh the name of the Lord depart from iniquity.
B055C002V020	55	2	20	But in a great house there are not vessels of gold only or of silver, but also of wood, also of clay: of them (some are) to honour, and of them (some) to dishonour.
B055C002V021	55	2	21	If a man then purify himself from these, he will be a pure vessel unto honour, fitted for the use of his Lord, and prepared for every good work.
B055C002V022	55	2	22	From all the lusts of youth escape; and pursue after righteousness, and faith, and charity, and peace, with them who call upon the Lord with a pure heart.
B055C002V023	55	2	23	From foolish controversies which are without instruction withdraw; for thou knowest that they beget strifes.
B055C002V024	55	2	24	But a servant of the Lord oweth not to strive, but to be gentle towards every man, and teaching, and long-suffering,
B055C002V025	55	2	25	that he may instruct them who would contend against him with meekness, if by any means Aloha may give them conversion, and they may acknowledge the truth,
B055C002V026	55	2	26	and be mindful of themselves, and remove from the snare of Satana, by whom they have been entrapped at his will.
B055C003V001	55	3	1	But know this, that in the last days hard times will come;
B055C003V002	55	3	2	and men will be lovers of themselves, and lovers of money, boastful, lofty, blasphemous, to their men not obedient, deniers of grace, impious, calumniators,
B055C003V003	55	3	3	subjected to lust, brutal, haters of the good,
B055C003V004	55	3	4	traitors, impetuous, puffed up, lovers of lusts rather than the love of Aloha;
B055C003V005	55	3	5	having a form of the worship of Aloha, but from the power of Aloha afar off: (them) who are such put from thee.
B055C003V006	55	3	6	For of them are they who creep into houses, and captivate women who are overladen with sins, and led away by divers lusts;
B055C003V007	55	3	7	who, in all time learning, never to the knowledge of the truth are able to come.
B055C003V008	55	3	8	But as Yonis and Yanbris stood against Musha, so also these stand against the truth: men whose understanding is corrupted, and reprobate from the faith.
B055C003V009	55	3	9	But they shall not come further, for their folly is known to all men, as also of them it is known.
B055C003V010	55	3	10	BUT thou hast followed my doctrine and my manners, and my purpose, and my faith, and my prolongedness of mind, and my charity, and my patience,
B055C003V011	55	3	11	and my persecution, and my sufferings. And thou knowest what things I endured in Antioch, and in Ikonion, and in Lystra, what persecution I endured; and out of all these my Lord delivered me.
B055C003V012	55	3	12	But all they who will in the fear of Aloha to live in Jeshu Meshiha, are persecuted.
B055C003V013	55	3	13	But wicked men and seducers add to their wickedness, deceiving, and being deceived.
B055C003V014	55	3	14	But abide thou in those things that thou hast learned, and in which thou art confirmed; for thou knowest from whom thou hast learned:
B055C003V015	55	3	15	and that from thy childhood thou hast learned the holy writings, which are able to make thee wise to salvation, through faith which is in Jeshu Meshiha.
B055C003V016	55	3	16	FOR all scripture which from the Spirit is written, is profitable for doctrine, and for rebuke, and for correction, and for instruction which is in righteousness:
B055C003V017	55	3	17	that the man of God may be perfect unto every good work, and completed.
B055C004V001	55	4	1	I attest thee before Aloha, and our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, who is to judge the living and the dead at the revelation of his kingdom:
B055C004V002	55	4	2	preach the word, and stand with diligence in season, and (that) which is not season; confute, and rebuke with all prolongedness of mind and doctrine.
B055C004V003	55	4	3	For the time will come, when sound doctrine they will not hear; but according to their desires will multiply to themselves teachers, in the itching of their hearing.
B055C004V004	55	4	4	And from the truth they will turn away their ear, but to fables will decline.
B055C004V005	55	4	5	But watch thou in every thing, and endure evils, and work the work of an evangelist, and thy ministry fulfil.
B055C004V006	55	4	6	But I am sacrificed, and the time when I shall be dissolved cometh.
B055C004V007	55	4	7	The good agony I have fought, and my running I have completed, and my faith I have kept.
B055C004V008	55	4	8	And from now there is kept for me the crown of righteousness, which my Lord will give me in that day, because he is a righteous judge: yet, not only to me, but to all them who love his manifestation.
B055C004V009	55	4	9	BE careful to come to me speedily;
B055C004V010	55	4	10	for Dema hath left me, and hath loved this world, and is gone to Thessalonika; Krispos to Galatia, Titos to Dalmatia;
B055C004V011	55	4	11	Luka only is with me. Take Markos and bring him with thee; for helpful to me is he in the ministry.
B055C004V012	55	4	12	But Tykikos have I sent to Ephesos.
B055C004V013	55	4	13	The case (for) books which I left at Troas with Karpos, when thou comest bring, and the books, and especially the roll of parchments.
B055C004V014	55	4	14	Alexander the brass-worker many evils hath showed me: our Lord awardeth to him according to his deeds.
B055C004V015	55	4	15	But be thou also aware of him, for he is much uplifted against our words.
B055C004V016	55	4	16	In the first defence no man was with me, but all of them left me. May this not be reckoned to them!
B055C004V017	55	4	17	But my Lord stood with me, that by me the preaching might be fulfilled, and (that) all the Gentiles might hear: and I was delivered from the mouth of the lion.
B055C004V018	55	4	18	And my Lord will deliver me from every evil work, and will save me into his kingdom, which is in heaven. To Him be glory for ever and ever. Amen.
B055C004V019	55	4	19	Give salutation to Priskela, and to Akilos, and to the house of Onesiphoros.
B055C004V020	55	4	20	Erastos remains at Kurinthos; but Trophimos I left ill in Miletos the city.
B055C004V021	55	4	21	Be careful to come before winter. Ebulos and Pudis, and Linos, and Klaudia, and all the brethren, ask for your peace.
B055C004V022	55	4	22	Our Lord Jeshu Meshiha be with thy spirit. Grace be with thee. Amen.
B056C001V001	56	1	1	PAULOS, a servant of Aloha, and apostle of Jeshu Meshiha, for the faith of the chosen ones of Aloha, and the knowledge of the truth which is in the fear of Aloha;
B056C001V002	56	1	2	unto the hope of eternal life, which Aloha the true counselled before the times of the ages,
B056C001V003	56	1	3	and his word hath revealed in his time by our preaching, which was confided to me by the command of Aloha our Saviour:
B056C001V004	56	1	4	To Titos, my true son in the common faith. Grace and peace from Aloha the Father and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha our Saviour.
B056C001V005	56	1	5	For this I left thee in Kreta, that those things which were wanting thou mayest rectify, and constitute presbyters in every city as I commanded thee.
B056C001V006	56	1	6	Him who is without blame, and is the husband of one wife, and who hath believing children, who are not vicious nor addicted to intemperance.
B056C001V007	56	1	7	For a presbyter is bound to be without blame, as the steward of Aloha; he shall not be led by the will of self, nor be irascible, nor a transgressor over wine, neither shall his hand be hasty to strike, nor shall he be a lover of sordid gains.
B056C001V008	56	1	8	But he shall be a lover of guests, and a lover of the good, and be chaste, and equitable, and holy, and withholding himself from lusts;
B056C001V009	56	1	9	and careful over the doctrine of the word of faith, that he may be able also to comfort by his teaching the healthy, and to reprove those who are contentious.
B056C001V010	56	1	10	For there are many who are not in subjection, and whose words are vain, and make the minds of men to err, especially those of the circumcision,
B056C001V011	56	1	11	those, whose mouths it behoves to stop. Many houses they destroy, and teach what they ought not, for the sake of filthy gain.
B056C001V012	56	1	12	One of them, a prophet of their own, hath said, The sons of Kreta are always liars, evil beasts, and lazy bellies.
B056C001V013	56	1	13	And true is this testimony. Wherefore reprove them severely, that they may be sound in the faith,
B056C001V014	56	1	14	nor cast themselves to the fables of the Jihudoyee, and to the mandates of men who hate the truth.
B056C001V015	56	1	15	For every thing is pure to the pure; but to those who are polluted and unfaithful nothing is pure; but their understanding and their conscience are polluted.
B056C001V016	56	1	16	And they profess to know Aloha, but in their works they deny him, and are abominable and disobedient, and reprobate to every good work.
B056C002V001	56	2	1	But speak thou that which becometh sound doctrine,
B056C002V002	56	2	2	and teach, That the elders be watchful in their minds, and be chaste and pure, and sound in the faith, and in charity, and in patience.
B056C002V003	56	2	3	And so also the aged women, that they be in behaviour what becometh the fear of Aloha, and not slanderers, nor enslaved to much wine, and that they teach good things;
B056C002V004	56	2	4	making those who are young modest, to love their husbands and their children,
B056C002V005	56	2	5	and to be chaste and holy, well mindful of their houses, and submissive to their husbands, that no man blaspheme the word of Aloha.
B056C002V006	56	2	6	And of those who are young men, likewise, require that they be chaste.
B056C002V007	56	2	7	But in every thing show thyself the example in all good works, and in doctrine let there be with thee sound speech which is sincere and incorrupt,
B056C002V008	56	2	8	and which no man will despise, that he who riseth against us may be ashamed when he cannot say any thing hateful against us.
B056C002V009	56	2	9	Let servants to their masters be submissive in every thing, and please them, not contradicting,
B056C002V010	56	2	10	nor pilfering; but let them show their good-trustiness in every thing, that they may adorn in every thing the doctrine of Aloha our Saviour.
B056C002V011	56	2	11	FOR the all-saving grace of Aloha hath appeared to all men,
B056C002V012	56	2	12	and teacheth us to deny wickedness and the lusts of the world, and to live in this world in purity, and in rectitude, and in the fear of Aloha,
B056C002V013	56	2	13	while expecting the blessed hope and the manifestation of the glory of the great God and our Saviour Jeshu Meshiha;
B056C002V014	56	2	14	who gave himself for us, to redeem us from all iniquity, and to cleanse unto himself a new people, who are zealous of good works.
B056C002V015	56	2	15	These speak, and require, and maintain with all authority, and no man shall despise thee.
B056C003V001	56	3	1	Put them in mind that to princes and to powers they are to hearken and to be obedient, and to be prepared for every good work.
B056C003V002	56	3	2	And against no man to rail, nor be contentious, but gentle, and in every thing to show their benignity towards all men.
B056C003V003	56	3	3	For we also were afore-time without understanding, and disobedient and erring, and were subjected to various lusts; and in malice, and in envy we conversed, and were hateful, and also hating one another.
B056C003V004	56	3	4	But when appeared the goodness and mercy of Aloha our Saviour,
B056C003V005	56	3	5	not by works of righteousness which we had done, but by his own mercy he saved us, by the laving of the birth which is afresh, by the renewing of the Spirit of Holiness,
B056C003V006	56	3	6	which he shed upon us abundantly, by Jeshu Meshiha our Saviour;
B056C003V007	56	3	7	that by his grace we might be justified, and be made heirs according to the hope of the life which is eternal.
B056C003V008	56	3	8	Faithful is the word; and in this I will that thou also establish them, that they should be careful to perform good works, they who have believed in Aloha. These are good and profitable unto men.
B056C003V009	56	3	9	But from foolish disputations, and from tales of genealogies, and from contentions, and strifes of the sophree, withdraw; for profit is not in them, and they are vain.
B056C003V010	56	3	10	From an heretical man, after one time and twice thou hast admonished him, withdraw;
B056C003V011	56	3	11	and know that he who is such is perverse, and sinneth, and condemneth himself.
B056C003V012	56	3	12	When I have sent to thee Artema, or Tykikos, be careful to come to me at Nikopolis; for there I have determined in my mind to winter.
B056C003V013	56	3	13	But concerning Zina the sophra, and Apolo, be careful to provide them well, that nothing may be wanting to them.
B056C003V014	56	3	14	And let those also who are of us, learn to perform good works in things which are necessary, that they may not be without fruits.
B056C003V015	56	3	15	All they who are with me ask for thy peace. Ask for the peace of all who love us in the faith. Grace be with all of you. Amen.
B057C001V001	57	1	1	PAULOS, the bondman of Jeshu Meshiha, and the brother Timotheos, to the beloved Philemon, our fellow-labourer,
B057C001V002	57	1	2	and to our beloved Aphia, and to Arkipos our fellowlabourer,1 and to the church which is in thy house.
B057C001V003	57	1	3	Grace be with thee, and peace, from Aloha our Father, and from our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B057C001V004	57	1	4	I give thanks to Aloha at all time, and remember thee in my prayers.
B057C001V005	57	1	5	Behold, from (the time) when I heard of thy faith, and the love which thou hast to our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, and to all the saints,
B057C001V006	57	1	6	(I have prayed) that there may be communication of thy faith (in) yielding fruits, in works and in the (manifestation of the) knowledge of all good which thou hast in Jeshu Meshiha.
B057C001V007	57	1	7	For we have great joy and consolation, that by thy love the bowels of the saints are refreshed.
B057C001V008	57	1	8	Wherefore I have great confidence in the Meshiha to command thee those acts which are righteous,
B057C001V009	57	1	9	but for love's sake entreating I entreat of thee, I, Paulos, who am the aged as thou knowest, but now also the bondman of Jeshu Meshiha.
B057C001V010	57	1	10	And I entreat of thee for my son, whom I have begotten in my bonds, Onesimos,
B057C001V011	57	1	11	who once was of no use to thee, but (who will) now to thee, as also to me, be greatly useful;
B057C001V012	57	1	12	and I have sent him to thee. But thou, as (one) who is my offspring, so receive him.
B057C001V013	57	1	13	For I would have retained him with me, that he might have served me for thy sake in the bonds of the gospel;
B057C001V014	57	1	14	but without thy counsel I was not willing to do any thing, that thy goodness might not be as by constraint, but of thy will.
B057C001V015	57	1	15	But, perhaps, for this he passed away for an hour, that thou mayest hold him for ever;
B057C001V016	57	1	16	not henceforth as a servant, but as more than a servant, a beloved brother of mine, and how much more of thine, both in the flesh and in our Lord!
B057C001V017	57	1	17	If then thou art with me a partaker, receive him as mine.
B057C001V018	57	1	18	And if of any thing he hath deprived thee, or oweth, that reckon unto me.
B057C001V019	57	1	19	I, Paulos, have written with my hands, I will repay thee; for I will not tell thee that thou owest thyself to me.
B057C001V020	57	1	20	Yes, my brother, I will be refreshed by thee in our Lord; refresh my bowels in the Meshiha.
B057C001V021	57	1	21	Because I am confident of thy hearing me, I have written to thee, and I know that more than I have asked thou wilt do.
B057C001V022	57	1	22	But at once also prepare me a house of lodging, for I hope through your prayers I shall be given to you.
B057C001V023	57	1	23	Epaphra, a captive with me in Jeshu Meshiha,
B057C001V024	57	1	24	and Markos, and Aristarkos, and Dema, and Luka, my helpers, ask for your peace.
B057C001V025	57	1	25	The grace of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha be with your spirit, my brethren. Amen.
B058C001V001	58	1	1	In manifold portions and in all manners, spake Aloha with our fathers by the prophets from the first: but in these last days he hath spoken with us by his Son;
B058C001V002	58	1	2	whom he constituted the heir of every thing, and by whom he made the worlds;
B058C001V003	58	1	3	who himself is the resplendence of his glory, and the image of his Being, and upholdeth all (things) by the power of his word; and he, in his (own) person, hath made purification of sins, and hath sat down at the right hand of the Majesty on high .
B058C001V004	58	1	4	And this (person) is altogether more excellent than the angels, by so much as the name he hath inherited (is) more excellent than theirs.
B058C001V005	58	1	5	For unto which one from (among) the angels at any time said Aloha, Thou art MY SON; I to-day have begotten thee? And again, I will be to him the Father, and he shall be to me the Son?
B058C001V006	58	1	6	But again, when bringing in the First-begotten into the world, he said, Let all the angels of Aloha worship him.
B058C001V007	58	1	7	But concerning the angels, thus hath he spoken: Who hath made his angels spirit, and his ministers a flaming fire.
B058C001V008	58	1	8	But concerning the Son he hath said, Thy throne, Aloha, (is) for ever and ever, a right sceptre (is) the sceptre of thy kingdom.
B058C001V009	58	1	9	Thou hast loved righteousness, and hast hated iniquity; therefore Aloha thy God hath anointed thee with the oil of exultation more (abundantly) than thy fellows.
B058C001V010	58	1	10	And again, Thou in the beginning hast laid the foundations of the earth, and the heavens are the work of thy hands.
B058C001V011	58	1	11	They pass away, but thou art enduring; and all they as vestments shall become old,
B058C001V012	58	1	12	and as a garment thou shalt fold them up, they shall be changed; but thou (shalt be) as Thou Art, and thy years shall not fail
B058C001V013	58	1	13	But to which from (among) the angels hath he said at any time, Sit at my right hand, until I put thine adversaries a footstool beneath thy feet?
B058C001V014	58	1	14	Are not all they spirits of ministration, who (are) sent forth in service on behalf of those who are hereafter to inherit salvation?
B058C002V001	58	2	1	Therefore we are obligated to be more exceedingly heedful in what we have heard, that we fall not.
B058C002V002	58	2	2	For if the word which was uttered by angels was confirmed, and every one who heard it, and transgressed against it, received a just retribution,
B058C002V003	58	2	3	how shall we escape if we despise those (words) which themselves are our salvation? Those which began by our Lord to be spoken, and by them who from him heard them in us were confirmed,
B058C002V004	58	2	4	when Aloha witnessed concerning them by signs, and by miracles, and by various powers, and by distributed gifts of the Spirit of Holiness, that were bestowed according to his will.
B058C002V005	58	2	5	For it was not to the angels he subjected the world which is future, of which we discourse.
B058C002V006	58	2	6	But, as the scripture testifieth and saith, What is man, that thou rememberedst him, and the Son of man, that thou didst visit him?
B058C002V007	58	2	7	Thou didst humble him (to be) less than the angels; glory and honour hast thou placed upon his head, and hast empowered him over the work of thy hands,
B058C002V008	58	2	8	and every thing hast thou put in subjection under his feet. in this, that he subjected every thing to him, he hath left nothing which he hath not subjected. Yet hitherto we see not that every thing is subjected to him.
B058C002V009	58	2	9	But him who was humbled to be less than the angels, we see to be JESHU himself, for the sake of the passion of his death; and glory and honour set upon his head; for He Aloha, in his grace, for every man hath tasted death!
B058C002V010	58	2	10	For it was proper to him by whose hand are all, and on account of whom all are, (and who) would lead many sons to his glory, that the Prince of their salvation by sufferings should be perfected.
B058C002V011	58	2	11	For he who sanctified, and they who are sanctified, are all from one: wherefore he has not been ashamed to call them his brethren.
B058C002V012	58	2	12	(As) when he saith, I will announce thy name unto my brethren, and in the midst of the church I will praise thee.
B058C002V013	58	2	13	And again, I will put my confidence in him. And again, Behold me, and the sons whom thou hast given me, Aloha.
B058C002V014	58	2	14	Forasmuch as the sons have been made to participate in flesh and blood, he also likewise was made a partaker of these very things; that by his death he might abolish him who held the power of death, who is Satana,
B058C002V015	58	2	15	and set loose them who in the fear of death had been all their lives subjected to servitude.
B058C002V016	58	2	16	For not from the angels he took, but from the seed of Abraham he took.
B058C002V017	58	2	17	Therefore it was right that in every thing he should be rendered like unto his brethren, that he might be compassionate, and a High Priest faithful in to Aloha, and become an expiation for the sins of the people.
B058C002V018	58	2	18	For in this, that he hath suffered and been tempted, he is able to help those who are tempted.
B058C003V001	58	3	1	Wherefore, my holy brethren, who have been called with the calling that from heaven, contemplate this Apostle and High Priest of our confession, JESHU MESHIHA!
B058C003V002	58	3	2	who was faithful to him who made him, as (was) Musha in all his house.
B058C003V003	58	3	3	For greater is the glory of this (One) by far than (the glory) of Musha, even as the honour of him who built the house is far greater than his building.
B058C003V004	58	3	4	For every house by some man is builded; but He who built all is Aloha.
B058C003V005	58	3	5	And Musha, as a servant, was faithful in all his house, for the testimony of those that were to be announced him;
B058C003V006	58	3	6	but the Meshiha as THE SON over his house: and his house are we, if, unto the end, we shall hold fast our confidence, and the triumph of his hope.
B058C003V007	58	3	7	Therefore the Spirit of Holiness hath said, to-day if ye will hear his voice,
B058C003V008	58	3	8	harden not your hearts unto the angering of him, as (did) the embitterers, and as the day of temptation in the desert,
B058C003V009	58	3	9	when your fathers tempted me, and proved (and) saw my works forty years.
B058C003V010	58	3	10	On which account I was wearied with that generation; and said, It is a people that doth err (in) their heart, and that hath not known my ways.
B058C003V011	58	3	11	So that I sware in my wrath, that they should not enter into my rest.
B058C003V012	58	3	12	Beware, therefore, my brethren, lest there be in any man among you an evil heart which believeth not, and ye depart from Aloha the living.
B058C003V013	58	3	13	But examine yourselves all the days, until the day which is called THAT DAY, lest any one of you be hardened by the deceptiveness of sin.
B058C003V014	58	3	14	For we are made participators with the Meshiha, if, from the beginning and unto the end, in this very standing we steadfastly persist.
B058C003V015	58	3	15	As that it is said, To-day, if ye will hear his voice, harden not your hearts to provoke him.
B058C003V016	58	3	16	For who are they who heard and provoked him? Not all they who came out of Metsreen by the hand of Musha.
B058C003V017	58	3	17	And with whom was he wearied forty years, but with them who sinned, and whose bones fell in the desert?
B058C003V018	58	3	18	And of whom did he swear that they should not enter into his rest, but of them who would not be persuaded?
B058C003V019	58	3	19	And we see that they were not able to enter in, because they did not believe.
B058C004V001	58	4	1	Let us fear, therefore, lest, while there is a confirmed promise of an entrance into his rest, any one shall be found among you remaining from entering in.
B058C004V002	58	4	2	For we have been evangelized as well as they: but the word which they heard did not profit them, because not contempered with faith in them who heard it.
B058C004V003	58	4	3	But we enter into the rest, we (being of) those (who) have believed. But as He hath said, So I sware in my wrath, that they should not enter into my rest: for, behold, the works of Aloha from the beginning of the world were.
B058C004V004	58	4	4	As he said concerning the shabath, God rested on the seventh day from all his works.
B058C004V005	58	4	5	Yet here again he saith, They shall not enter into my rest.
B058C004V006	58	4	6	Therefore, because there was a place into which every one of them might have entered, and they who had it announced first did not enter in, forasmuch as they would not be persuaded;
B058C004V007	58	4	7	---moreover, (as) another day he appointeth, after much time; as above it is written, that David hath said, To-day if his voice ye will hear, harden not your hearts;
B058C004V008	58	4	8	---but if Jeshu-bar-Nun had established them in rest, he not have spoken afterwards of another day:
B058C004V009	58	4	9	---Therefore, yet to enjoy a shabathism is confirmed to the people of Aloha.
B058C004V010	58	4	10	For he who is entered into his rest hath also reposed himself from his works, as Aloha (did) from his.
B058C004V011	58	4	11	Let us, therefore, anxiously endeavour to enter into that rest, that we fall not after the manner of those who were not persuaded.
B058C004V012	58	4	12	For living is the Word of Aloha, and all-acting, and more penetrating than a two-edged sword, and entereth to the separation of the soul and the spirit, and of the joints, and of the marrow, and the bones, and discerneth the reasonings and counsel of the heart.
B058C004V013	58	4	13	Neither is there any creature that is concealed from before him; but every thing (is) naked and manifest before his eyes, to whom they shall give account .
B058C004V014	58	4	14	Therefore having such a great High Priest, Jeshu Meshiha, the Son of Aloha, who hath ascended to heaven, let us persevere in the confession of him.
B058C004V015	58	4	15	For we have not an high priest who cannot suffer along with our infirmity, but (one) who, tempted in every thing as we, (was) separate from sin.
B058C004V016	58	4	16	Let us therefore approach with confidence to the throne of his grace, that we may receive mercy, and find grace for help in the time of affliction.
B058C005V001	58	5	1	For every high priest who is from among men, on the behalf of men, standeth over those things which are of Aloha, to offer oblation and sacrifices for sins:
B058C005V002	58	5	2	and (is one) who can humble himself, and suffer with those who know not and err, since he also himself with infirmity is clothed.
B058C005V003	58	5	3	And on this account he is obligated as on the behalf of the people, so (also) for himself, to offer up for his sins.
B058C005V004	58	5	4	Yet no man to himself taketh the honour, but he who is called by Aloha, as of Aharun .
B058C005V005	58	5	5	Thus also the Meshiha glorified not himself to be a High Priest; but He who said to him, Thou art my Son, I to-day have begotten thee.
B058C005V006	58	5	6	So, too, in another place he saith, Thou art the Priest for ever, after the likeness of Malki-Zedek.
B058C005V007	58	5	7	When also with flesh he had been clothed, prayer and supplication, with a powerful cry, and with tears, he offered up unto Him who was able from death to revive him, and was heard.
B058C005V008	58	5	8	And though he was the Son, yet from the fear and the sufferings which he sustained he learned obedience.
B058C005V009	58	5	9	And so was he perfected, and became unto all them who obey him the Cause of eternal salvation;
B058C005V010	58	5	10	and was named by God, The High Priest after the likeness of Malki-Zedek.
B058C005V011	58	5	11	But concerning this Malki-Zedek himself, we have much discourse to utter, and hard to explain, because ye are infirm in your hearing.
B058C005V012	58	5	12	For ye ought to be teachers, on account of the time by you in learning; but now ye have need again to be taught those which are the first scriptures of the beginningwords of Aloha; and need have ye for milk, and not for solid food.
B058C005V013	58	5	13	But every one whose food is milk is not versed in the doctrine of righteousness, because he is a babe.
B058C005V014	58	5	14	But for the perfect is solid food; those, (namely,) who, because exercised, have trained their senses to distinguish the good and the evil.
B058C006V001	58	6	1	Wherefore let us leave the beginning of the word of the Meshiha, and let us come unto perfection. Or why again another foundation lay you for repentance from dead works, and for faith which is in Aloha,
B058C006V002	58	6	2	and for the doctrine of ablution and of imposition of the hand, and for the resurrection from the place of the dead, and for the judgment which is eternal?
B058C006V003	58	6	3	If the Lord permit, we will do this.
B058C006V004	58	6	4	But they who once unto baptism have descended, and have tasted the gift which is from heaven, and have received the Spirit of Holiness,
B058C006V005	58	6	5	and have tasted the good word of Aloha, and the power of the world to come,
B058C006V006	58	6	6	(and) who again shall sin, cannot again be renewed unto conversion, who would afresh crucify and put to shame the Son of God.
B058C006V007	58	6	7	For the earth that hath drunk the rain which hath come upon it many times, and shall have brought forth the herb that is useful for them on whose account it is cultured, receiveth blessing from Aloha;
B058C006V008	58	6	8	but that which shall produce thorns and briers hath reprobation; nor is it far from the curse, but its end is burning.
B058C006V009	58	6	9	But we are persuaded concerning you, my brethren, those things which are good, and that draw nigh unto salvation, though thus we speak.
B058C006V010	58	6	10	For not unrighteous is Aloha, that he should forget your works and your charity which ye have manifested in his name, who have ministered unto the saints, and do minister.
B058C006V011	58	6	11	But we desire that every one of you manifest the same diligence for the full completion of your hope until the end;
B058C006V012	58	6	12	and that it be not cut off from you, but that ye be imitators of them who by fidelity and patience have become heirs of the promise.
B058C006V013	58	6	13	For when to Abraham Aloha gave promise, because there was no one greater than himself to swear by, he sware by his own Self,
B058C006V014	58	6	14	and said, Blessing I will bless thee, and multiplying I will multiply thee.
B058C006V015	58	6	15	And so he waited patiently, and obtained the promise.
B058C006V016	58	6	16	For men swear by one greater than themselves: and every controversy which occurs among them hath a sure conclusion in the oath.
B058C006V017	58	6	17	On this account Aloha, willing abundantly to manifest to the heirs of the promise that his engagement is changeless, hath bound it in an oath:
B058C006V018	58	6	18	that by two things that are not changed, in which it cannot be that Aloha should lie, great consolation should be ours who have fled unto him: and that we may retain the hope that is promised to us,
B058C006V019	58	6	19	which we have as an anchor that holdeth our soul, that it may not be moved, and entereth within the veil,
B058C006V020	58	6	20	where Jeshu hath first entered for us, and become the Priest for ever in the likeness of MALKI-ZEDEK.
B058C007V001	58	7	1	For this Malki-Zedek is king of Sholim, the priest of Aloha the Most High. And he (it was who) met Abraham when he returned from the slaughter of the kings, and blessed him.
B058C007V002	58	7	2	And to him Abraham separated the tenth from every thing which he had with him. Now his name, being expounded, (is,) the King of Righteousness; and again, MalekSholem, which is, King of peace:
B058C007V003	58	7	3	whose father and mother were not written in the genealogies; neither the beginning of his days, nor the conclusion of his life; but in the likeness (of that) of THE SON OF ALOHA standeth his priesthood for ever.
B058C007V004	58	7	4	But see how great this (person was,) that Abraham, head of the fathers, gave to him the tenths and the choicest things.
B058C007V005	58	7	5	For they of the sons of Levi who have received the priesthood, have a commandment of the law to receive tenths from the people, they from their brethren, they also from the loins of Abraham having sprung.
B058C007V006	58	7	6	But he who is not written in their genealogies took tithes from ABRAHAM, and blessed him who had received the promise.
B058C007V007	58	7	7	But, without controversy, he who is less is blessed by one who is Greater than himself.
B058C007V008	58	7	8	And here the sons of men who die receive the tithes; but there he concerning whom the scripture testifieth that he liveth.
B058C007V009	58	7	9	And as one may say, by the hand of Abraham, even Levi, he who taketh tithes, himself also is tithed.
B058C007V010	58	7	10	For he was yet in the loins of his father when he met Malki-Zedek.
B058C007V011	58	7	11	If, therefore, Perfection were to be through the priesthood of the Levoyee, by which the law has been put upon the people, why was there another Priest required, who should arise in the resemblance of Malki-Zedek? For he had said, In the likeness of Aharun he shall be.
B058C007V012	58	7	12	But as a change hath been made in the priesthood, so is there also a change made in the law.
B058C007V013	58	7	13	For he concerning whom these things are said was born from another tribe, from which no man hath ministered at the altar.
B058C007V014	58	7	14	For it is manifest that from Jihuda arose our Lord, from the tribe of whom Musha hath said nothing concerning priesthood.
B058C007V015	58	7	15	And again: it is more fully known by that which hath said, In the likeness of MalkiZedek ariseth another Priest;
B058C007V016	58	7	16	who was made not by the law of bodily commandments, but in the power of a life which is indissoluble.
B058C007V017	58	7	17	For he testifieth concerning him, Thou art a Priest for evermore according to the likeness of Malki-Zedek.
B058C007V018	58	7	18	But the change which was made in the first institution was on account of its powerlessness, and because profit was not in it.
B058C007V019	58	7	19	For the law perfected nothing: but instead of it a hope has entered which is more excellent, (and) by which we are brought nigh unto Aloha.
B058C007V020	58	7	20	And he hath confirmed it unto us in an oath.
B058C007V021	58	7	21	For they were made priests without an oath; but this with an oath: as he said unto him by the hand of David, The Lord hath sworn and will not lie, that thou art the Priest for ever in the likeness of Malki-Zedek.
B058C007V022	58	7	22	In all this more excellent is the covenant of (which) Jeshu is the sponsor .
B058C007V023	58	7	23	There were (moreover) many priests, because they were dying, and were not permitted to remain.
B058C007V024	58	7	24	But because this (one) standeth for ever, his priesthood passeth not away.
B058C007V025	58	7	25	And he is able to save for eternity them who approach by him unto Aloha; for he liveth through all time, and offereth up prayers on their behalf.
B058C007V026	58	7	26	For such an High Priest as this was adequate for us; pure, and without evil, and without spot; who was separate from sins, and exalted higher than heaven.
B058C007V027	58	7	27	With him there was no necessity daily, like the chief of the priests, that first for his own sins he should offer sacrifices, and then on behalf of the people: for this he did once when in himself he offered.
B058C007V028	58	7	28	For the law constituted infirm men priests; but the word of the oath, which was subsequent to the law, (hath constituted) THE SON perfect for evermore.
B058C008V001	58	8	1	But the sum of them all (is)---We have a High Priest who hath sat down at the right hand of the throne of the Majesty in heaven;
B058C008V002	58	8	2	and who hath become a Minister of the holy place, and of the true tabernacle, which Aloha hath framed, and not man.
B058C008V003	58	8	3	And every high priest is appointed to offer oblations and victims: hence it was right that this one should also have that which he might offer.
B058C008V004	58	8	4	But were he upon the earth, he would not be a priest, because there were priests who offered oblations as by the law;
B058C008V005	58	8	5	they, (namely,) who minister at an emblem and shadow of those (things) that are in heaven. As it was said unto Musha when he made the tabernacle, See and make every thing according to the pattern which was showed to thee in the mountain.
B058C008V006	58	8	6	But now a ministry which is better than that hath Jeshu Meshiha received, by so much as that covenant of which he is made the Mediator is better, and was given with better promises, than that.
B058C008V007	58	8	7	For if the first covenant had been faultless, no place had there been for this second.
B058C008V008	58	8	8	For reprehending them he saith, Behold, the days are coming, saith the Lord, and I will complete with the family of the house of Israel, and with the family of the house of Jihuda,
B058C008V009	58	8	9	THE NEW COVENANT: not as was that covenant which I gave to their fathers in the day that I took them by their hand, and led them from the land of Metsreen; because they did not persevere in my covenant, therefore I have neglected them, saith the Lord.
B058C008V010	58	8	10	But this is the covenant that I will give to the family of the house of Israel after these days, saith the Lord: I will in-give my law in their minds, and upon their hearts will I inscribe it; and I will be to them, even I, Aloha, and they shall be unto me the people:
B058C008V011	58	8	11	and no man shall (have need to) teach the son of his city, nor his brother, and say, Know the Lord; because all shall know me, from the least of them to the eldest of them.
B058C008V012	58	8	12	And I will purify them from their unrighteousness, and their sins again will I not remember unto them.
B058C008V013	58	8	13	In that he said, THE NEW, he hath made the former old: and that which is antiquated, and hath grown old, is nigh unto decay.
B058C009V001	58	9	1	But in the first there were ordinances of ministry, and a worldly sanctuary.
B058C009V002	58	9	2	For in the first tabernacle that was made there were the candelabrum, and the table, and the presencebread; and this was called the Holy place.
B058C009V003	58	9	3	But the interior tabernacle, that was within the second veil, was called the Holy of Holies:
B058C009V004	58	9	4	in it were the incense-vessel of gold, and the ark of the covenant, which was altogether covered with gold; and within it were the golden urn, in which was the manna, and the rod of Aharun that budded, and the tablets of the covenant:
B058C009V005	58	9	5	and above this the cherubim of glory overshadowing the mercy-seat. But time there is not to speak upon every one of these which were thus ordained.
B058C009V006	58	9	6	Now, into the outer sanctuary at all times entered the priests, and fulfilled their offices;
B058C009V007	58	9	7	but into the tabernacle which was within, one day in the year, alone, entered the high priest, with that blood which he offered for himself and the sins of the people.
B058C009V008	58	9	8	By this the Spirit of Holiness made known that the way of the holies was not yet manifested, so long as was the standing of the first tabernacle.
B058C009V009	58	9	9	And this was a figurative representation for the time in which oblations and victims have been offered;-those which have not been able to perfect the consciousness of him who offered them;
B058C009V010	58	9	10	but (have consisted) in meat and drink only, and in various kinds of baptism, being institutions of the flesh appointed until the time of setting right.
B058C009V011	58	9	11	But the Meshiha who hath come was a High Priest of good things which he wrought out, and hath entered into the great and perfect tabernacle (which was) not made with hands, nor made from these creatures.
B058C009V012	58	9	12	Nor entered he with the blood of goats and calves, but with the blood of himself he entered once the holy place, and hath found eternal redemption.
B058C009V013	58	9	13	For if the blood of goats and of calves, and the dust of an heifer, sprinkled upon those who were unclean, sanctifieth them for the purification of their flesh,
B058C009V014	58	9	14	how much more then shall the blood of the Meshiha, who, by the Eternal Spirit, himself hath offered without spot unto Aloha, purify our conscience from dead works, to serve the Aloha the Living?
B058C009V015	58	9	15	For this was he made the Mediator of the new covenant, that by his death he might become the ransom for those who had transgressed against the first covenant, (and) that they might receive the promise, they, who are called unto the inheritance which is eternal.
B058C009V016	58	9	16	For where a covenant is, there is indicated the DEATH of that which made it.
B058C009V017	58	9	17	For upon death only is it confirmed; because while he who made it lived there is no value in it.
B058C009V018	58	9	18	Wherefore neither the first without blood was confirmed.
B058C009V019	58	9	19	For when every precept had been enjoined by Musha to the whole people according to the law, Musha took the blood of the heifer, and water, with the scarlet wool, and hyssop, and sprinkled upon the books and upon all the people,
B058C009V020	58	9	20	and said to them, This is the blood of that covenant which is commanded by Aloha.
B058C009V021	58	9	21	Also upon the tabernacle and upon all the vessels of the service from it with blood he sprinkled.
B058C009V022	58	9	22	Because every thing with blood was purified under the law; and without shedding of blood there is no remission.
B058C009V023	58	9	23	For it was necessary that these which are a type of the heavenlies, with (these) things should be purified; but the heavenlies themselves with sacrifices that are more excellent than they.
B058C009V024	58	9	24	For not into the sanctuary made with hands hath the Meshiha entered, which is an emblem of the true one, but into heaven itself hath he entered, that he might appear before the face of Aloha for us.
B058C009V025	58	9	25	Nor that he should offer himself many times, as did the chief of the priests, entering every year into the holy place with blood not his own;
B058C009V026	58	9	26	otherwise he would have been obligated many times to suffer from the beginning of the world. But now, in the end of the world, once hath he offered himself, that by his sacrifice he might abolish sin.
B058C009V027	58	9	27	And as it is ordained to the sons of men, that they must once die, and after their death the judgment;
B058C009V028	58	9	28	so also the Meshiha was once offered, and in his (own) person sacrificed (for) the sins of many; but the second time without sins he appeareth for the salvation of them who expect him.
B058C010V001	58	10	1	For there was in the law the shadow of good things to come, not the subsistence of the very things, therefore (though) every year the same sacrifices were offered they could never perfect those who offered them.
B058C010V002	58	10	2	For if they had perfected, they would have ceased afterward from the presentation of them; because the conscience of those who had been once purified by them would not henceforth have been troubled by (such) sins.
B058C010V003	58	10	3	But in those sacrifices their sins are brought to remembrance every year.
B058C010V004	58	10	4	For it is impossible for the blood of bulls and of goats to purify (from) sins.
B058C010V005	58	10	5	Wherefore when he cometh into the world he saith, Sacrifices and oblations thou hast not willed, but with a body hast thou clothed me:
B058C010V006	58	10	6	and entire burnt-offerings for sins thou hast not required.
B058C010V007	58	10	7	Then said I, Behold, I come; in the sum of the books it is written concerning me, that I shall do thy will, Aloha.
B058C010V008	58	10	8	Above he said, Victims, and oblations, and entire burnt-offerings for sin thou hast not willed; those which are offered in the law.
B058C010V009	58	10	9	And afterwards he said, Behold, I come, that I may do thy will, Aloha. In this he hath done away with the first, that he may establish the second.
B058C010V010	58	10	10	For by this his will we are sanctified by the offering of the body of Jeshu Meshiha, which was once.
B058C010V011	58	10	11	For every high priest who stood and ministered every day, offered the same sacrifices, which can never purify (from) sins.
B058C010V012	58	10	12	But this one sacrifice hath offered for sins, and hath sat down at the right hand of Aloha for ever:
B058C010V013	58	10	13	waiting from henceforth until his adversaries are set as a footstool beneath his feet.
B058C010V014	58	10	14	For by one offering he hath perfected those who are sanctified through him for ever.
B058C010V015	58	10	15	Now the witness unto us is the Spirit of Holiness, when he saith,
B058C010V016	58	10	16	This is the covenant that I will give to them from after those days, saith the Lord: I will give my law in their minds, and upon their hearts will I inscribe it;
B058C010V017	58	10	17	and their iniquity and their sins I will not remember against them.
B058C010V018	58	10	18	BUT WHERE THERE IS REMISSION OF SINS, THERE IS NOT REQUIRED AN OFFERING FOR SINS.
B058C010V019	58	10	19	We have, therefore, my brethren, confidence to enter the holy place through the blood of Jeshu;
B058C010V020	58	10	20	and a way of life which he hath now made new to us through the veil, which is his flesh;
B058C010V021	58	10	21	and we have the High Priest over the house of God.
B058C010V022	58	10	22	Let us, therefore, draw near with a confirmed heart, and the full security of faith, with our hearts sprinkled and cleansed from an evil conscience, and our body washed with pure waters;
B058C010V023	58	10	23	and let us persevere in the confession of our hope, and not swerve; for faithful is He who hath promised us.
B058C010V024	58	10	24	And let us consider one another with incitement to charity and good works.
B058C010V025	58	10	25	And let us not forsake our congregation, as is the custom with some; but pray one with another; (and) so much the more as ye see that day to be approaching.
B058C010V026	58	10	26	For if with his will any man shall sin after he hath received the knowledge of the truth, there is not still a victim to be offered for sins;
B058C010V027	58	10	27	but a fearful judgment to come, and burning fire which devoureth the adversaries.
B058C010V028	58	10	28	For if he who transgressed the law of Musha, upon the mouth of two or three witnesses, without mercy died;
B058C010V029	58	10	29	how much greater punishment, think ye, shall he receive who hath trampled upon the Son of Aloha, and hath counted the blood of the covenant of him by which he had been sanctified as that of every man and hath insulted the Spirit of grace?
B058C010V030	58	10	30	We know him who hath said, Retribution is mine, and I will repay: and again, The Lord shall judge his people.
B058C010V031	58	10	31	How terrible to fall into the hands of Aloha the Living!
B058C010V032	58	10	32	Be mindful, therefore, of the first days, those in which ye received baptism; and when ye sustained a great agony of sufferings,
B058C010V033	58	10	33	with ignominy and affliction; and when ye were made gazing-stocks, and were associated with men who also endured these (things).
B058C010V034	58	10	34	And it afflicted you on account of them who were bound; and the pillage of your goods with joy ye sustained, as knowing that ye have a possession in heaven, which is better, and passeth not away.
B058C010V035	58	10	35	Destroy not, therefore, the confidence which you have, for which there is a great reward.
B058C010V036	58	10	36	But patience is needed by you, that ye may do the will of Aloha, and receive the promise.
B058C010V037	58	10	37	Because (yet) a little time, and a very little, and He who cometh shall come, and not be slow.
B058C010V038	58	10	38	But the just by the faith of me shall live; but if he become weary, my soul delighteth not in him.
B058C010V039	58	10	39	But we are not of the weariness which bringeth to perdition, but of the faith which maketh us to possess our soul.
B058C011V001	58	11	1	Now FAITH is the persuasion concerning things which are in hope, as if they were in reality, and a revelation of those which are not seen.
B058C011V002	58	11	2	And for this was the testimony concerning the elders.
B058C011V003	58	11	3	For by faith we perceive that the worlds were ordained by the word of Aloha, and (how) these (things) which are seen were from those which are not seen.
B058C011V004	58	11	4	By faith Habel offered a sacrifice which was far better than that of Koen unto Aloha; and because of it there is respecting him a testimony that he was righteous; and Aloha gave witness concerning his oblation; and on account thereof also while dead he is speaking.
B058C011V005	58	11	5	Through faith Hanak was translated, and did not taste death; nor was he found, because Aloha had translated him: for before that he would translate him, there was respecting him the testimony that he pleased Aloha.
B058C011V006	58	11	6	But without faith it is not possible for man to please Aloha; for he who draweth near unto Aloha must believe that he is, and that of those who seek him he will be the rewarder.
B058C011V007	58	11	7	By faith Nuch, when spoken with upon those things which had not been seen, feared, and made him the ark for the salvation of his family; by which he condemned the world, and was an heir of the righteousness which is by faith.
B058C011V008	58	11	8	By faith Abraham, when he was called, heard that he was to go forth to a place which he should receive for an inheritance; and he went out, while he knew not whither he was going.
B058C011V009	58	11	9	By faith he was a sojourner in the land that was promised to him, as in an alien state, and dwelt in tabernacles with Ishok and Jakub, sons of the inheritance which was his by the promise:
B058C011V010	58	11	10	for he was expecting the city which hath foundations, whose builder and maker is Aloha.
B058C011V011	58	11	11	By faith Saro, who was barren, received strength to conceive seed, and, which (thing) was not in the time of her years, gave birth (to a son); because she was sure that he who had promised to her was faithful.
B058C011V012	58	11	12	Therefore from one who had failed from old age, were there begotten multitudes as the stars of heaven, and as the sand upon the shores of the sea, which have no number.
B058C011V013	58	11	13	In faith died these all, not having gotten their promise, but from afar had beheld it, and exulted in it, and confessed that strangers they were, and sojourners in the earth.
B058C011V014	58	11	14	For they who these things say, make manifest that their city they are seeking.
B058C011V015	58	11	15	But if that city from which they had gone out they desired, they had opportunity to return and go to it.
B058C011V016	58	11	16	But now it is known that a better (one) than that they desired; that (namely) which is in heaven. Wherefore Aloha was not ashamed their God to be called; for he hath prepared for them a city.
B058C011V017	58	11	17	By faith Abraham offered Ishok in his temptation and his only-born he lifted upon the altar, even him whom he had received by the promise:
B058C011V018	58	11	18	for it had been said to him, In Ishok shall be called to thee the seed.
B058C011V019	58	11	19	For he thought within himself, that Aloha could even from the dead upraise: and on account of this in a similitude he was given to him.
B058C011V020	58	11	20	By faith in that which was to come, Ishok blessed Jakub and Isu.
B058C011V021	58	11	21	By faith, when dying, Jakub blessed each of the sons of Jauseph; and worshipped upon the head of his staff.
B058C011V022	58	11	22	By faith Jauseph, when dying, was mindful of the going forth of the sons of Israel, and commanded concerning his bones.
B058C011V023	58	11	23	By faith the parents of Musha concealed him when he had been born three months, because they saw that he was a beautiful child; and they feared not the edict of the king.
B058C011V024	58	11	24	By faith Musha, when he became a man, refused to be called the son of the daughter of Pherun;
B058C011V025	58	11	25	and chose to himself to be in affliction with the people of Aloha, and not for a little time to delight (himself) in sin;
B058C011V026	58	11	26	and considered the riches of the reproach of Meshiha to be far greater than the treasures of Metsreen: for he contemplated the recompence of the reward.
B058C011V027	58	11	27	By faith he forsook Metsreen, and feared not the wrath of the king; and hoped, as one who beheld Aloha who is the invisible.
B058C011V028	58	11	28	By faith they performed the passover, and the sprinkling of the blood, that he might not come near,-he, who was destroying the first-born.
B058C011V029	58	11	29	By faith they traversed the sea of Sooph, as those who (march) upon dry land; but the Metsroyee were swallowed up in it, when they had dared to enter it.
B058C011V030	58	11	30	By faith the ramparts of Jirichu fell down, after they had been encompassed seven days.
B058C011V031	58	11	31	By faith Rachob the harlot perished not with those who would not hearken, because she had received the explorers in peace.
B058C011V032	58	11	32	What shall I yet say? For (too) brief is the time for me to tell of Gedhun, and of Borok, and of Shemshun, and of Nephtoch, and of David, and of Shomuel, and of the rest of the prophets;
B058C011V033	58	11	33	they who through faith conquered kingdoms, and wrought righteousness, and received promises, and shut the mouths of lions,
B058C011V034	58	11	34	and quenched the powers of fire, and were delivered from the edge of the sword, and were made strong from infirmities, and became valiant in battle, and overthrew the camps of the adversaries.
B058C011V035	58	11	35	And they gave unto women their sons by the resurrection of the dead; and others in torments died, nor hoped to be delivered, that the better resurrection they might have.
B058C011V036	58	11	36	But others went through mockings and scourgings; others unto chains and imprisonments were given up,
B058C011V037	58	11	37	others were stoned, others divided, others died by the edge of the sword, others wandered about clothed with skins of sheep and of goats, necessitous, afflicted, and driven out.
B058C011V038	58	11	38	Men, of whom the world was not worthy, became as wanderers in the desert, and in mountains, and in dens, and in caverns of the earth.
B058C011V039	58	11	39	And these all, of whom there hath been (such) a testimony concerning their faith, received not the promise;
B058C011V040	58	11	40	because Aloha had afore contemplated for our help, that without us they should not be made perfect.
B058C012V001	58	12	1	Wherefore we also, having all these witnesses, who as clouds encompass us, will set ourselves loose from every weight, and the sin which at all time is prepared for us, and with perseverance will we run this race which is appointed to us.
B058C012V002	58	12	2	And let us look unto Jeshu, who hath become the chief and the perfecter of our faith; who, for the joy that was before him, endured the cross, and unto shame delivered himself, and at the right hand of the throne of Aloha hath sat down.
B058C012V003	58	12	3	Consider, therefore, how much he endured from sinners who were adversaries to themselves, that ye weary not, nor fail in your souls.
B058C012V004	58	12	4	Not yet have ye come unto blood in the conflict which is against sin.
B058C012V005	58	12	5	And ye have forgotten the instruction of him who, as unto children, hath said to you, My son, contemn not the discipline of the Lord, and let not thy soul fail when by him thou art corrected:
B058C012V006	58	12	6	for whom the Lord loveth he chastiseth, and scourgeth those children in whom he taketh pleasure.
B058C012V007	58	12	7	Endure, therefore, correction, because Aloha acteth towards you as with children: for who is a son whom his father doth not correct?
B058C012V008	58	12	8	And if ye be without the correction with which every one is corrected, ye are aliens, and not children.
B058C012V009	58	12	9	And if (when) the fathers of the flesh have chastised us we have revered them, how much more are we bound to be subject to our spiritual fathers, that we may live?
B058C012V010	58	12	10	For they, during a little time, as they willed, chastised us; but Aloha for our advantage, that we might partake of his holiness.
B058C012V011	58	12	11	For all chastisement, in its time, is not considered as joy, but as grief; but, in the end, the fruit of peace and righteousness it giveth unto them who with it have been exercised.
B058C012V012	58	12	12	Wherefore your relaxed hands and your trembling knees make strong;
B058C012V013	58	12	13	and right ways make for your feet, that the member which is lame may not wander, but be healed.
B058C012V014	58	12	14	Follow after peace with every man, and after holiness, without which man our Lord seeth not.
B058C012V015	58	12	15	And be aware lest any one be found among you failing of the grace of Aloha; or lest any root of bitternesses should put forth the flower and injure you, and many be contaminated:
B058C012V016	58	12	16	or lest there be found among you any fornicator, or dissolute, as Isu, who for one meal sold his birthright.
B058C012V017	58	12	17	For ye know, also, that afterward he desired to inherit the blessing, but was rejected; for place for repentance he found not, though with tears he sought it.
B058C012V018	58	12	18	For ye have not drawn nigh to the burning fire, and to that which may be touched, neither to darknesses, to mist, and to tempest,
B058C012V019	58	12	19	nor to the voice of the trumpet, and the voice of words, which they who heard withdrew (from), that it might not be additionally spoken to them.
B058C012V020	58	12	20	For they could not endure that which was commanded. For if an animal should approach to the mountain, it was to be stoned:
B058C012V021	58	12	21	and so terrible was the sight, that Musha said, I fear and tremble
B058C012V022	58	12	22	But ye have come nigh unto the Mount of Ziun, and to the city of Aloha the Living, to the Urishlem which is in heaven, and to the congregation of myriads of angels,
B058C012V023	58	12	23	and to the church of the firstborn (ones) who are written in heaven, and to Aloha the Judge of all, and to the spirits of the just who are perfected,
B058C012V024	58	12	24	and to Jeshu the Mediator of the new covenant, and to the sprinkling of his blood, which speaketh better than that of Habel.
B058C012V025	58	12	25	Beware, therefore, lest ye be averse from Him who hath spoken with you; for if they escaped not who were averse from one who spake with them on earth, how much less we, if we withdraw from one who hath spoken to us from heaven?
B058C012V026	58	12	26	Him whose voice moved the earth? But now hath he promised and said, Yet once I will move not only earth, but also heaven.
B058C012V027	58	12	27	But that which he hath said, ONCE, showeth the (final) changing of these which are moved, because they are made, that those may remain which are immutable.
B058C012V028	58	12	28	Therefore because we have received the kingdom which is immoveable, let us hold the grace by which we may serve and please Aloha with reverence and with fear:
B058C012V029	58	12	29	for our God is a devouring fire.
B058C013V001	58	13	1	Let the love of the brethren continue in you;
B058C013V002	58	13	2	and kindness to strangers forget not; for in this some who were made worthy, while not perceiving it, have received angels.
B058C013V003	58	13	3	Remember those who are bound, as if with them ye were bound: be mindful of those who are afflicted, as men (should) who are clothed with flesh.
B058C013V004	58	13	4	Honourable is marriage among all, and their bed is undefiled; but whoremongers and adulterers Aloha judgeth.
B058C013V005	58	13	5	Let not your mind love money; but let whatever ye have suffice you: for the Lord hath said, I will not abandon thee, nor withhold from thee support .
B058C013V006	58	13	6	And it is ours to say confidently, My Lord is my helper, I will not fear: what a man do to me?
B058C013V007	58	13	7	Remember your leaders; those who have spoken to you the word of Aloha: reflect on the consummation of their course, and imitate their faith.
B058C013V008	58	13	8	Jeshu Meshiha is yesterday, and to-day, and for ever.
B058C013V009	58	13	9	Unto strange and variable doctrines be not led away; for it is good that with grace we confirm our hearts, and not by meats, because they have not been helped who have walked in them.
B058C013V010	58	13	10	But we have an altar of which it is not lawful for them to eat who minister in the tabernacle.
B058C013V011	58	13	11	For those animals, whose blood the high priest took into the sanctuary for sins, had their flesh burned without the camp.
B058C013V012	58	13	12	On this account Jeshu, that he might sanctify his people by his blood, without the city suffered.
B058C013V013	58	13	13	Therefore let us also go forth unto him without the camp, being, clothed with his ignominy.
B058C013V014	58	13	14	For we have no city which is permanent here; but one that is to come we are expecting.
B058C013V015	58	13	15	By him, therefore, let us offer up at all time unto Aloha the sacrifices of praise, which are the fruits of the lips which give thanks to his name.
B058C013V016	58	13	16	And forget not compassion and communication to the poor: for with these sacrifices a man pleaseth Aloha.
B058C013V017	58	13	17	Be persuaded by your leaders, and obey them; for they watch for your souls as men who must render an account of you, that with joy they may do this, and not with groans; for that is not profitable for you.
B058C013V018	58	13	18	Pray for us; for we are confident we have a good conscience, that in all things we desire to act aright.
B058C013V019	58	13	19	And more especially I ask from you to do this, that I may be turned to you quickly.
B058C013V020	58	13	20	But the God of peace, who brought up from the house of the dead the great Shepherd of the flock, by the blood of the eternal covenant, who is Jeshu Meshiha, our Lord,
B058C013V021	58	13	21	make you perfect in every good work, that ye may do his will, and effect in you whatever is good before him, by Jeshu Meshiha: to him be glory unto the age of ages. Amen.
B058C013V022	58	13	22	Now I request from you, my brethren, that ye prolong your minds on the word of exhortation; for in a few (words) I have written to you.
B058C013V023	58	13	23	But know that our brother Timotheos is released; and if he come soon, with him I will see you.
B058C013V024	58	13	24	Ask for the peace of all your leaders, and of all the saints: they of Italia ask for your peace.
B058C013V025	58	13	25	Grace be with you all. Amen.
B059C001V001	59	1	1	JAKUB, a servant of Aloha and of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, unto the twelve tribes who are dispersed among the nations: Peace.
B059C001V002	59	1	2	All joy shall be to you, my brethren, when you shall have entered into temptations many and various.
B059C001V003	59	1	3	For you know that the proving of faith maketh you to possess patience;
B059C001V004	59	1	4	but to patience let there be a perfect work, that you may be complete and perfected, and in nothing be deficient.
B059C001V005	59	1	5	If any of you be deficient in wisdom, let him ask of Aloha, who giveth to all expansively, and upbraideth not, and it is given to him.
B059C001V006	59	1	6	But let him ask in faith, not wavering. For he who wavereth is like the waves of the sea which the wind disturbeth.
B059C001V007	59	1	7	And let not that man expect to receive any thing from the Lord,
B059C001V008	59	1	8	who is divided in his mind, and disturbed in all his ways.
B059C001V009	59	1	9	But let the humble brother glory in his exaltation,
B059C001V010	59	1	10	and the rich in his humility; for as the flower of an herb, so he passeth.
B059C001V011	59	1	11	For the sun ariseth in his heat, and drieth the herb, and the flower of it falleth, and the beauty of its appearance perisheth; so also the rich withereth in his reverses.
B059C001V012	59	1	12	Blessed the man who endureth temptations: for when he hath been proved he shall receive the crown of life, which Aloha hath promised unto them who love him.
B059C001V013	59	1	13	Let no man say, when he is tempted, From Aloha I am tempted; for Aloha is not tempted with evils, and he no man tempteth.
B059C001V014	59	1	14	But each man from his concupiscence tempteth himself, and desireth, and is drawn away.
B059C001V015	59	1	15	And this desire conceiveth and beareth sin; and sin, when it is perfected, beareth death.
B059C001V016	59	1	16	Do not err, my beloved brethren;
B059C001V017	59	1	17	every good gift and perfect from above descendeth, from the Father of lights, with whom is no alteration, nor the shadow of vicissitude.
B059C001V018	59	1	18	He willed, and begat us by the word of truth, that we might be the first-ones of his creatures.
B059C001V019	59	1	19	And you, my beloved brethren, let every one of you be swift to hear, and slow to speak, and slow to be angry;
B059C001V020	59	1	20	for the wrath of man the righteousness of Aloha worketh not.
B059C001V021	59	1	21	Wherefore, remove from you all impurity and the abounding of wickedness, and with meekness receive the word which is engrafted in our nature, which is able to save your souls.
B059C001V022	59	1	22	BUT be doers of the word, and not hearers only, neither deceive yourselves.
B059C001V023	59	1	23	For if a man be a hearer of the word and not a doer of it, this (man) is like one who vieweth his face in a mirror;
B059C001V024	59	1	24	for he seeth himself and passeth, and hath forgotten what (manner of person) he was.
B059C001V025	59	1	25	But every one who looketh into the perfect law of liberty, and continueth therein, he is not a hearer of the hearing of forgetfulness, but a doer of works; and this shall be blessed in his work.
B059C001V026	59	1	26	And if a man thinketh that he serveth Aloha, and holdeth not his tongue, but deceiveth his own heart, of this man his service is vain.
B059C001V027	59	1	27	For the service which is pure and true before Aloha the Father, is this, to visit the orphans and widows in their afflictions, and that a man keep himself from the world without blemish.
B059C002V001	59	2	1	My brethren, do not hold with acceptance of faces the faith of the glory of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B059C002V002	59	2	2	For if there come into your congregation a man who hath rings of gold or beautiful vestments, and there come in a poor man in sordid vestments,
B059C002V003	59	2	3	and you look upon him who clothed in beautiful vestments, and say to him, Sit is here well; and you say to the poor man, Stand thou there, or, Sit thou here before the stool of our feet;
B059C002V004	59	2	4	behold, are you not divided in yourselves, and become separaters for evil reasons?
B059C002V005	59	2	5	Listen, my beloved brethren: Hath not Aloha chosen the poor of the world, but rich in faith, to be heirs in that kingdom which Aloha hath promised to them who love him?
B059C002V006	59	2	6	But you have despised the poor. Behold, are not the rich uprisen against you? and do they not drag you to the house of judgment?
B059C002V007	59	2	7	Do they not blaspheme against that Good Name which is pronounced upon you?
B059C002V008	59	2	8	And if the law of Aloha in this you accomplish, as it is written, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself, you do well;
B059C002V009	59	2	9	but if you accept persons, you commit sin, and are convicted by the law as transgressors against the law.
B059C002V010	59	2	10	For he who keepeth the whole law, and in one offendeth, of the whole LAW he is guilty.
B059C002V011	59	2	11	For he who hath said, Thou shalt not commit adultery, is he who hath said, Thou shalt not steal; but if thou do not commit adultery, yet steal, thou hast become a transgressor against the LAW.
B059C002V012	59	2	12	So speak and so act, as those who by the law of liberty are to be judged.
B059C002V013	59	2	13	For judgment is to be without mercy, upon him who hath not done mercy. Be you exalted by mercy over judgment.
B059C002V014	59	2	14	WHAT is the use, my brethren, if a man say, I have faith, and works he hath not? How can his faith save him?
B059C002V015	59	2	15	And, if a brother or sister be naked, and wanting the food of to-day,
B059C002V016	59	2	16	and any one of you shall say to them, Go in peace, be warm, and be satisfied, and give them not what is necessary for the body, what (would be) the use?
B059C002V017	59	2	17	Thus also the faith that hath not works is dead, (being) alone.
B059C002V018	59	2	18	For a man saith, Thou hast faith, and I have works; show me thy faith without thy works, and I will show thee my faith from my works.
B059C002V019	59	2	19	Thou believest that Aloha is one: thou doest well; the demons also believe and tremble.
B059C002V020	59	2	20	Art thou willing to know, O weak man, that faith without works is dead?
B059C002V021	59	2	21	Our father Abraham, was he not by works justified, when he offered Ishok his son on the altar?
B059C002V022	59	2	22	Thou seest that his faith was helpful unto his works; and by works his faith was perfected,
B059C002V023	59	2	23	and the scripture was accomplished which said, that Abraham believed in Aloha, and it was reckoned unto him for righteousness, and the friend of Aloha he was called.
B059C002V024	59	2	24	Thou seest that by works man is justified, and not by faith alone.
B059C002V025	59	2	25	So also Rachab the harlot, was she not by works justified when she received the spies, and by another way sent them forth?
B059C002V026	59	2	26	Thus, as the body without the spirit is dead, so also the faith which is without works is dead.
B059C003V001	59	3	1	LET there not be many teachers among you, my brethren, but know that a greater condemnation we incur.
B059C003V002	59	3	2	For (in) many we all offend. Every one who in word offendeth not, this is a perfect man, who is able to make subject also all his body.
B059C003V003	59	3	3	For, behold, bridles into the mouth of horses we throw that we may make them submissive to us, and their whole body we turn.
B059C003V004	59	3	4	Also the mighty ships, while the furious winds drive them, by a little wood are turned about to the region which the will of him who guideth doth contemplate.
B059C003V005	59	3	5	So also the tongue is a small member, and uplifteth itself. A little fire also burneth many forests;
B059C003V006	59	3	6	and the tongue is a fire, a world of sin, like a forest is the tongue itself among our members; it defileth all of our body, and burneth the course of our generations which run (forward) as a wheel, and kindleth also itself with fire.
B059C003V007	59	3	7	For every nature of animals, and of birds, and reptiles of the sea, and of the dry land, have been subjected to the human nature;
B059C003V008	59	3	8	but the tongue no one can subdue; this is an evil not ordered, (and) full of the poison of death.
B059C003V009	59	3	9	For by it we bless the Lord and the Father, and by it we curse men who in the likeness of Aloha were made;
B059C003V010	59	3	10	and from the same mouth go forth curses and blessings. My brethren, it is not fit that these should so be done.
B059C003V011	59	3	11	Can it be that one fountain shall send forth waters sweet and bitter?
B059C003V012	59	3	12	Or can the fig-tree, my brethren, make olives, or the vines figs? thus also salt waters cannot be made sweet.
B059C003V013	59	3	13	Who of you is wise and instructed? let him show his works in good conversations in meek wisdom.
B059C003V014	59	3	14	But if you have bitter envy among yourselves, or contention be in your hearts, be not inflated against the truth, nor lie;
B059C003V015	59	3	15	because this wisdom from above descendeth not; but is earthly, from the reasonings of the soul, and from demons.
B059C003V016	59	3	16	For where there are envy and contention, there also are tumult and every thing that is evil.
B059C003V017	59	3	17	But the wisdom that is from above is pure, and full of peace, and meekness, and obedience, and full of mercies and good fruits, and is without division, and faces accepteth not.
B059C003V018	59	3	18	But the fruits of righteousness in quietness are sown by them who make peace.
B059C004V001	59	4	1	From whence are there among you wars and strifes? Is it not from the lusts which war in your members?
B059C004V002	59	4	2	You desire, and have not; you kill and are emulous, yet it cometh not into your hands; you strive and make wars, and nothing have because you do not ask;
B059C004V003	59	4	3	you ask and receive not, because you ask wickedly, as that you may cherish your lusts.
B059C004V004	59	4	4	Adulterers, know you not that the friendship of this world is enmity with Aloha? He, therefore, who willeth to be the friend of this world, hath become the enemy of Aloha.
B059C004V005	59	4	5	Or do you vainly think that the scripture saith, that In emulation desireth the Spirit who dwelleth in us?
B059C004V006	59	4	6	But more excellent grace hath our Lord given unto us. Wherefore he saith, Aloha humbleth the proud, and to the humble he giveth grace.
B059C004V007	59	4	7	BE subject, therefore, unto Aloha; withstand Satana, and he will flee from you;
B059C004V008	59	4	8	and draw nigh unto Aloha, and he will be nigh you. Purify your hands, sinners, and sanctify your hearts, divided of soul.
B059C004V009	59	4	9	Be humbled and sorrowful, and let your laughter be turned into grief, and your gladness into anxiety.
B059C004V010	59	4	10	Be humbled before the Lord, and he will exalt you.
B059C004V011	59	4	11	Speak not against one another, my brethren; for he who speaketh against his brother, or judgeth his brother, speaketh against the law, and judgeth the law. And if the law thou judgest, thou art not a doer of the law, but the judge of it.
B059C004V012	59	4	12	For one is the appointer of the law and the Judge, who can save and destroy. But thou, who art thou, who judgest thy neighbour?
B059C004V013	59	4	13	But what shall we say of them who say, To-day or tomorrow we will go to this city, or that, and work there one year, and negotiate, and make gain?
B059C004V014	59	4	14	and they know not what shall be on the morrow: for what is our life, but a vapour which for a little while is seen, and vanisheth and endeth?
B059C004V015	59	4	15	For instead they should say, If the Lord will, and we live, we will do this or that.
B059C004V016	59	4	16	They glory in their pride. All glorying such as this is from the Evil.
B059C004V017	59	4	17	And he who knoweth the good and doeth it not, sin is to him.
B059C005V001	59	5	1	O rich men, howl and weep for the miseries which are coming upon you.
B059C005V002	59	5	2	Your riches are corrupt and stink, and your vestments are eaten of the moth,
B059C005V003	59	5	3	and your gold and your silver rusteth, and the rust of them is for a witness against you, and is to eat your flesh. You have gathered fire for you for the last days!
B059C005V004	59	5	4	Lo, the hire of the labourers who have reaped your lands, which you have refused, clamoureth, and the cry of the harvests to the ears of the Lord of Sabaoth hath ascended.
B059C005V005	59	5	5	For you have lived daintily on the earth, and have been wanton, and have nourished your bodies, as for the day of slaughter.
B059C005V006	59	5	6	You have condemned and have killed the just, and he hath not resisted you.
B059C005V007	59	5	7	BUT you, my brethren, prolong your spirit until the coming of the Lord; as the husbandman who expecteth the precious fruits of his lands, and prolongeth his spirit for them, until he receive the rain the early and the latter;
B059C005V008	59	5	8	so also you, prolong your spirit, and your hearts confirm; for the coming of our Lord draweth nigh.
B059C005V009	59	5	9	Groan not one against another, my brethren, that you be not judged; for, behold, the Judge standeth before the door.
B059C005V010	59	5	10	The example of the prophets take to you, my brethren, to prolong your spirits in your afflictions, them who have spoken in the name of the Lord.
B059C005V011	59	5	11	For, behold, we give blessedness to them who have endured. You have heard of the patience of Iob, and the end which the Lord wrought for him you have seen; because that merciful is the Lord and compassionate.
B059C005V012	59	5	12	But before every thing, my brethren, swear not; by heaven nor by earth, nor with any other oath; but let your word be Yes, yes, and No, no, that you be not bound under condemnation.
B059C005V013	59	5	13	And if any of you be in affliction, let him pray; and if he rejoice, let him sing;
B059C005V014	59	5	14	and if he be sick, let him call for the presbyters of the church, and they will pray over him and anoint him with oil in the name of our Lord.
B059C005V015	59	5	15	And the prayer of faith shall make whole him who was sick, and our Lord shall raise him up; and if he have committed sins, they shall be forgiven him.
B059C005V016	59	5	16	But confess your faults one to another, and pray one for another, that you may be healed. For great is the power of that prayer which the righteous prayeth.
B059C005V017	59	5	17	Elia also was a man of suffering, as we; and he prayed that the rain should not fall upon the earth, and it fell not (for) three years and six months.
B059C005V018	59	5	18	And again he prayed, and the heaven gave rain, and the earth gave her fruits.
B059C005V019	59	5	19	my brethren, if any of you shall err from the way of truth, and one shall convert him from his error,
B059C005V020	59	5	20	let him know, that he who turneth a sinner from the error of his way, saveth his soul from death, and hideth the multitude of his sins.
B060C001V001	60	1	1	PETROS, an apostle of Jeshu Meshiha, to the chosen-ones and sojourners who are scattered in Pontos and in Galatia, and in Kapadukia, and in Asia, and in Bithunia:
B060C001V002	60	1	2	them who are elected by the foreknowledge of Aloha the Father, through sanctification of the Spirit, that they might be unto obedience, and unto the sprinkling of the blood of Jeshu Meshiha: grace and peace be multiplied with you.
B060C001V003	60	1	3	Blessed be Aloha, the Father of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, who by his abundant grace hath begotten us anew through the resurrection of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha unto the hope of salvation,
B060C001V004	60	1	4	and to the inheritance which is not corruptible, and not defiled, and not to be consumed, which is prepared for you in heaven,
B060C001V005	60	1	5	while you are kept by the power of Aloha and through faith, unto the salvation which is prepared to be revealed in the last times;
B060C001V006	60	1	6	wherein you will rejoice for ever, though in this little time you are afflicted by manifold temptations which pass over you;
B060C001V007	60	1	7	that the proof of your faith may be seen, which is more precious than gold refined which is proved in fire, unto praise and unto honour and unto glory, at the revelation of Jeshu Meshiha;
B060C001V008	60	1	8	whom you have not seen and (yet) love, and in whose faith you exult with glorious joy that is not spoken:
B060C001V009	60	1	9	that you may receive the recompence of your faith, the salvation of your souls.
B060C001V010	60	1	10	That salvation which the prophets investigated when they prophesied concerning the grace which was to be given unto you,
B060C001V011	60	1	11	and searched into, what time the Spirit of the Meshiha who dwelt in them showed and testified of the future sufferings of the Meshiha, and his glory which (should be) after them.
B060C001V012	60	1	12	And all that they searched was revealed to them; for not for themselves they inquired, but to us (and) of us they prophesied those (blessings) which now are revealed to you by them who have preached to you by the Spirit of Holiness which is sent from heaven; for into these themselves the angels also desire to look.
B060C001V013	60	1	13	Wherefore gird up the loins of your minds, and be fully wakeful, and hope for the joy that cometh to you at the revelation of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha;
B060C001V014	60	1	14	as obedient children, and not partaking again of the former desires which you desired when ignorant.
B060C001V015	60	1	15	But be holy in all your conversations, as he is holy who calleth you;
B060C001V016	60	1	16	because it is written, Be ye holy, as I also am holy.
B060C001V017	60	1	17	And if you call him Father before whom there is no respect of persons, and who judgeth every man according to his works, with fear conduct you in this time of your sojourn;
B060C001V018	60	1	18	while you know that not with silver which wasteth away, nor with gold, you have been redeemed from your vain works which you received from your fathers,
B060C001V019	60	1	19	but with the precious blood of the Lamb spotless and unblemished, who is the Meshiha;
B060C001V020	60	1	20	who was afore-separated for this from before the foundations of the world, and hath been manifested in these last times for you,
B060C001V021	60	1	21	who by him believe in Aloha, who raised him from the dead, and gave him glory, that your faith and your hope may be in Aloha.
B060C001V022	60	1	22	Let your souls be sanctified in obedience to the truth, and be filled with the charity which respecteth not persons, that with a pure heart and perfect you may love one another,
B060C001V023	60	1	23	as men who are regenerated, not by a perishable seed, but by that which is imperishable, by the living word of Aloha which abideth for ever.
B060C001V024	60	1	24	Because all flesh is grass, and all its beauty as the flower of the field. The grass withereth and the flower drieth up,
B060C001V025	60	1	25	but the word of our God abideth for ever; and this is that word which is preached unto you.
B060C002V001	60	2	1	MAKE to cease therefore from you all malice and all guile, and dissimulation, and envy, and slander;
B060C002V002	60	2	2	and be as (new)-born babes, and be desirous of the word as of milk pure and spiritual, that by it you may increase unto life.
B060C002V003	60	2	3	If you have tasted and seen how good is the Lord,
B060C002V004	60	2	4	unto whom you have come, who is the living stone whom men have rejected, yet (who is) chosen and honourable with Aloha.
B060C002V005	60	2	5	And you also as living stones are builded, and become a spiritual temple, and holy priests to offer sacrifices, which are acceptable before Aloha by Jeshu Meshiha.
B060C002V006	60	2	6	For it is said in the scripture, Behold, I lay in Zion a stone choice and honourable in the head of the corner: whosoever believeth in him shall not be ashamed.
B060C002V007	60	2	7	To you therefore is given this honour, to them who believe: but to them who are disobedient he is a rock of offence,
B060C002V008	60	2	8	or a stone of stumbling, and they are offended at him in not obeying the word, because to this they are set.
B060C002V009	60	2	9	But you are a chosen race, who minister as priests to the kingdom, a holy people, a congregation redeemed to announce the praises of him who hath called you from darkness to his transcendant light:
B060C002V010	60	2	10	those who before were not reputed a people, but now the people of Aloha; upon whom also mercies were not; but now, mercies are poured upon you.
B060C002V011	60	2	11	MY beloved, I beseech you as strangers and as sojourners, be separate from all the lusts of the body which make wars against the soul.
B060C002V012	60	2	12	And let your conversation be good before all men; and they who speak against you malicious words shall see your good deeds, and shall glorify Aloha in the day of the probation.
B060C002V013	60	2	13	And be subject to all men for the sake of Aloha: to kings, on account of their authority;
B060C002V014	60	2	14	and to judges, because from him they are sent for the punishment of transgressors, and for the commendation of good works.
B060C002V015	60	2	15	For so is the will of Aloha, that by your comely works you may shut the mouth of fools who know not Aloha.
B060C002V016	60	2	16	As the sons of liberty, yet not as men who make their liberty a veil for their wickedness, but as the servants of Aloha.
B060C002V017	60	2	17	Honour all; your brethren love; and Aloha revere; and kings honour.
B060C002V018	60	2	18	And those servants who are among you, be subject to your masters with reverence; not only to the good and gentle, but also to the hard and the severe.
B060C002V019	60	2	19	For these are pleasing before Aloha, who, for the sake of a good conscience, endure the afflictions that come upon them unjustly.
B060C002V020	60	2	20	For they who on account of their offences suffer tribulations, what praise have they? But when you do well and they afflict you, and you endure, then doth your praise become great with Aloha.
B060C002V021	60	2	21	For unto this have you been called; because the Meshiha also hath died for us, and left us this example, that in his steps we may walk.
B060C002V022	60	2	22	Who did no sin, nor was guile found in his mouth;
B060C002V023	60	2	23	who was reviled and reviled not, and suffered and threatened not, but delivered his cause to the Judge of righteousness;
B060C002V024	60	2	24	and took all our sins and upbore them in his body on the cross; that when dead to sin, in the righteousness of him we might live; for by his stripes you are healed,
B060C002V025	60	2	25	who had wandered as sheep, and are returned now unto the Shepherd and Guardian of your souls.
B060C003V001	60	3	1	So you also, wives, be subject to your own husbands, that them who have not obeyed the word, by your comely manners without labour you may win,
B060C003V002	60	3	2	while they see that with reverence and with chastity you conduct yourselves.
B060C003V003	60	3	3	Neither be adorned with outward adornings of the entwinement of your hair, or necklaces of gold, or of excelling vestments,
B060C003V004	60	3	4	but adorn yourselves in the hidden man of the heart, with the spirit of gentleness which perisheth not, the ornament of excellence before Aloha.
B060C003V005	60	3	5	For so also of old the holy women who confided in Aloha adorned themselves, and were subject to their husbands,
B060C003V006	60	3	6	even as Sara was subject to Abraham, and called him My Lord: of her be you the daughters in good works, not being perturbed by any fear.
B060C003V007	60	3	7	AND you, men, dwell likewise with your wives with knowledge, and as feeble vessels in honour hold them; for they also with you inherit the gift of the life of eternity; that you be not hindered in your prayers.
B060C003V008	60	3	8	But, finally be all unanimous, and suffer with those who suffer, and love one another, and be merciful and gentle;
B060C003V009	60	3	9	and let no man render evil for evil, nor invective for invective, but, that which is contrary to them, bless: for unto this are you called, that the blessing you may inherit.
B060C003V010	60	3	10	Who then willeth life, And loveth good days to see? Let him keep his tongue from evil, And his lips that they speak not guile.
B060C003V011	60	3	11	Let him depart from evil and do good, And seek peace and run after it.
B060C003V012	60	3	12	For the eyes of the Lord are upon the righteous, And his ears, to hear them; And the face of the Lord is against the wicked.
B060C003V013	60	3	13	And who (is he) who will do you evil if you be emulous of good (actions)?
B060C003V014	60	3	14	And (yet) if you suffer for the sake of righteousness, you are happy. And you will not fear them who would make you afraid, nor be shaken.
B060C003V015	60	3	15	But sanctify in your hearts the Lord Meshiha. AND be prepared to make defence to every one who shall seek of you speech concerning the hope of the faith, with meekness and with seriousness, while you have a good conscience;
B060C003V016	60	3	16	that as they speak against you as against evil men, they may be made ashamed who have traduced your good conversations in the Meshiha.
B060C003V017	60	3	17	For it helpeth you (if) while doing goodly works you have to sustain evil, if so it be the will of Aloha, and not while working evils.
B060C003V018	60	3	18	Because the Meshiha also once died on account of sins, the just on account of sinners, that he might bring us unto Aloha. And dead in the body and alive in the Spirit,
B060C003V019	60	3	19	he preached unto those souls who were held in sheul,
B060C003V020	60	3	20	those who before were disobedient in the days of Nuch; while the long-suffering of Aloha commanded that he should make the ark, upon the hope of their conversion, and eight souls only entered therein, and were saved in the waters.
B060C003V021	60	3	21	After which very type also you are saved in baptism, not while you cleanse the body from filth, but while you make confession of 6 Aloha with a pure conscience, and of the resurrection of Jeshu Meshiha;
B060C003V022	60	3	22	who is exalted unto heaven, and is at the right hand of Aloha, and unto whom are subject angels and authorities and powers.
B060C004V001	60	4	1	If then the Meshiha hath suffered for you in the flesh, be you also armed in it with the same mind; for every one who dieth in his body hath ceased from all sins,
B060C004V002	60	4	2	that henceforth to the lusts of men he should not live, what time he is in the body, but to the will of Aloha.
B060C004V003	60	4	3	For the time which hath passed sufficeth to have served the will of the Gentiles in indulgence, in drunkenness, in vileness, in revellings, and in the service of demons.
B060C004V004	60	4	4	And, behold, now they wonder and blaspheme at you because you riot not with them in that former indulgence;
B060C004V005	60	4	5	they who shall give account to Aloha, who will judge the dead and the living.
B060C004V006	60	4	6	For on this account the dead also have been evangelized; that they might be judged as men in the flesh, and live with Aloha in the Spirit.
B060C004V007	60	4	7	BUT the end of all cometh; therefore be sober, and watch unto prayer.
B060C004V008	60	4	8	And before every thing have ardent love for one another; for love covereth a multitude of sins.
B060C004V009	60	4	9	And be lovers of guests without murmuring.
B060C004V010	60	4	10	And every man of you the gift which he hath received from Aloha, let him minister thereof unto his neighbours as good stewards of the various grace of Aloha.
B060C004V011	60	4	11	Whoever shall speak, as the word of Aloha let him speak and whoever ministereth, (he shall minister) as from the power which Aloha giveth to him, that in every thing which you do Aloha may be glorified through Jeshu Meshiha, whose are the glory and honour to the age of ages. Amen.
B060C004V012	60	4	12	My beloved, be not amazed at the temptations which you have, as that something strange happeneth to you, because for your probation they have been;
B060C004V013	60	4	13	but rejoice that you are partakers of the sufferings of the Meshiha, that so also at the revelation of his glory you may rejoice and exult.
B060C004V014	60	4	14	And if you be reviled for the sake of the name of the Meshiha, you are happy; for the Spirit of the glory of Aloha resteth upon you.
B060C004V015	60	4	15	Only, let no man of you suffer as a murderer, or as a thief, or as a doer of evils.
B060C004V016	60	4	16	But if he suffer as a Christian, let him not be ashamed, but let him glorify Aloha in that very name.
B060C004V017	60	4	17	For the time is, that judgment shall begin from the house of Aloha. But if from us it begin, what is the end (to be) of them who obey not the gospel of Aloha?
B060C004V018	60	4	18	And if the righteous scarcely be saved, the wicked and the sinner where shall he be found?
B060C004V019	60	4	19	Wherefore, let them who suffer according to the will of Aloha commend to him their souls in good works, as unto the Faithful Creator.
B060C005V001	60	5	1	BUT I entreat of the presbyters who are among you, I, a presbyter, your companion, and a witness of the sufferings of the Meshiha, and a partaker of his glory that is to be revealed;
B060C005V002	60	5	2	feed the flock of Aloha which is delivered to you, and take care (of it) spiritually, not by constraint, but with the will; not for corrupt gain, but with all your heart;
B060C005V003	60	5	3	not as lords of the flock, but that you may be to them a goodly example;
B060C005V004	60	5	4	that when the Chief of pastors shall be revealed, you may receive from him a crown of glory which fadeth not.
B060C005V005	60	5	5	And you younger, be subject to your presbyters, and be clothed carefully with humility of mind towards one another; because Aloha is against those who exalt themselves, and to the humble he giveth grace.
B060C005V006	60	5	6	Be humbled, therefore, under the mighty hand of Aloha, that he may exalt you at the right time.
B060C005V007	60	5	7	And all your anxiety cast upon Aloha, because he is careful over you.
B060C005V008	60	5	8	Watch, and be mindful, because your adversary Satana, as a lion, roareth and walketh and seeketh whom he may devour.
B060C005V009	60	5	9	Withstand him then, being confirmed in the faith; and know that upon your brethren also who are in the world, these same sufferings come.
B060C005V010	60	5	10	But the God of grace, who hath called us to his eternal glory by Jeshu Meshiha, will give to us while we endure these few afflictions to be strengthened, and confirmed, and established in him for ever.
B060C005V011	60	5	11	To Him be glory and dominion and honour unto the age of ages. Amen.
B060C005V012	60	5	12	These few, as I consider, I have written to you by the hands of Silvanos, a faithful brother; and I persuade and testify, that this is the true grace of Aloha, this wherein you stand.
B060C005V013	60	5	13	The elect church which is in Babel, asketh for your peace, and Markos my son.
B060C005V014	60	5	14	Salute one another with the holy kiss. Peace be with all of you who are in the Meshiha. Amen.
B061C001V001	61	1	1	SHEMUN PETROS, a servant of Jeshu Meshiha, to those who by faith the same in preciousness with us have been made equal, through the righteousness of our Lord and our Redeemer Jeshu Meshiha.
B061C001V002	61	1	2	Grace and peace be multiplied to you through the knowledge of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B061C001V003	61	1	3	As He who all (things) which of the divine power are unto life and godliness hath given (us), through the knowledge of Him who hath called us unto the glory of him and of virtue,
B061C001V004	61	1	4	by annunciations great and precious which he hath given to you, that by them you may be partakers of the divine nature, while you escape the corruption of the lusts which are in the world;
B061C001V005	61	1	5	So, with this, bringing in all diligence, add to your faith virtue; but to virtue knowledge,
B061C001V006	61	1	6	but to knowledge perseverance, but to perseverance patience, but to patience godliness,
B061C001V007	61	1	7	but to godliness brotherly kindness, but to brotherly kindness love.
B061C001V008	61	1	8	For while these are found with you, and abound, neither slothfulness nor unfruitfulness will stand against you in the knowledge of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha.
B061C001V009	61	1	9	For he with whom these are not found is blind, and seeth not, and hath forgotten the purification of his former sins.
B061C001V010	61	1	10	Upon this the more, my brethren, be careful, that by your good works your calling and your election you may confirm; for, while you do these, you will never lapse;
B061C001V011	61	1	11	for so abundantly shall be given to you the entrance of the eternal kingdom of our Lord and our Saviour Jeshu Meshiha.
B061C001V012	61	1	12	Wherefore it doth not weary me to remind you constantly of these, that you may know well, and be established upon this truth.
B061C001V013	61	1	13	But I consider it right, so long as I am in this body, to stir you up in remembrance:
B061C001V014	61	1	14	knowing that the decease of my body is shortly (to be,) as also our Lord Jeshu Meshiha hath made me know.
B061C001V015	61	1	15	But be careful also that (these) you may continually have; that also after my going forth the memorial of them you may observe.
B061C001V016	61	1	16	For it is not after fables which are made with art that we have gone, in making known to you the power and coming of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, but as we were spectators of his majesty.
B061C001V017	61	1	17	For when he received from Aloha the Father honour and glory, while a voice came to him as this, after the glorious beauty of his majesty, This is my Son, the Beloved, in whom I have delighted;
B061C001V018	61	1	18	we also this voice heard from heaven, as it came to him when we were with him in the holy mount.
B061C001V019	61	1	19	We have that which is sure also, the word of prophecy; that into which you do well to look, as to a light shining in a dark place, until the day dawn, and the sun arise in your hearts.
B061C001V020	61	1	20	While this first you know, that every prophecy of the scripture its own solution is not.
B061C001V021	61	1	21	For not by the will of man came any prophecy, but while by the Holy Spirit led spake the holy men of God.
B061C002V001	61	2	1	BUT there were false prophets in the world, as also among you there will be false teachers, they who introduce heresies of destruction, and, the Lord who bought them denying, bring upon themselves swift destruction.
B061C002V002	61	2	2	And many will go after their wickedness; they, on account of whom the way of truth will be blasphemed.
B061C002V003	61	2	3	And with fraudulency of deceptive words will they make merchandise of you; they, whose judgment (denounced) before tarrieth not, and whose destruction doth not sleep.
B061C002V004	61	2	4	For if Aloha upon the angels who sinned was not lenient, but in chains of darkness shut them in the deeps, and delivered them to be kept to the judgment of pain;
B061C002V005	61	2	5	and on the former world was not lenient, but Nuch, who was the eighth preacher of righteousness, he preserved, when the deluge came upon the world of the wicked;
B061C002V006	61	2	6	the cities of Sadum and of Omuro he burned, and with overthrow condemned them, while an example to the wicked who should be he set them;
B061C002V007	61	2	7	also Lut the righteous, who was bruised with the impure conversation of the lawless, he delivered;
B061C002V008	61	2	8	-for in sight and in hearing, while (that) just (man) dwelt among them, from day to day, his righteous soul by their lawless works was tortured;-
B061C002V009	61	2	9	the Lord knoweth how to deliver from affliction them who fear him, but the evil unto the day of judgment to be tormented will he reserve.
B061C002V010	61	2	10	But most those who after the flesh follow the concupiscence of impurity, and of authority are contemptuous; daring and arrogant, (and) who by greatness are not moved while they blaspheme:
B061C002V011	61	2	11	whereas angels, who in power and strength are (so much) greater than they, bring not against them a judgment of blasphemy.
B061C002V012	61	2	12	But these, as the dumb animals, by nature (ordained) to the knife and to destruction, blaspheming what they know not, in their own destruction will be destroyed;
B061C002V013	61	2	13	while they in whom is iniquity the wages of iniquity shall receive. They repute as pleasure the luxury which is in the day. Blemishes (are they), full of spots, who delighting in their refreshments are luxurious:
B061C002V014	61	2	14	having eyes full of adultery, and sins which cease not, alluring souls that are not established. An heart have they which is disciplined in covetousness; sons of malediction,
B061C002V015	61	2	15	who, forsaking the straight way, have erred, and gone in the way of Belam bar Beur, who the wages of iniquity loved. But he had reproof of his transgression;
B061C002V016	61	2	16	(for) the dumb ass which spake with the voice of man rebuked the madness of the prophet.
B061C002V017	61	2	17	These are wells without water, clouds driven from above, unto whom the blackness of darkness is reserved.
B061C002V018	61	2	18	For while they speak scoffing words of vanity, they allure with impure desires of the flesh those who almost escaped from them who have their conversation in error.
B061C002V019	61	2	19	And liberty to them they promise, while they (themselves) are the servants of corruption; for the thing by which a man is overcome, to that he is subject.
B061C002V020	61	2	20	For if they have escaped from the pollutions of the world through the knowledge of our Lord and Saviour Jeshu Meshiha, with those very things entangled they are again over-come, their end becomes worse than the beginning.
B061C002V021	61	2	21	For it had been more tolerable for them not to have known the way of righteousness, than, when they knew, to turn backward from the holy commandment delivered to them.
B061C002V022	61	2	22	But it hath happened to them according to the true proverb, that The dog hath turned unto his vomit; the sow which had washed into the wallow of the mire.
B061C003V001	61	3	1	Now this, my beloved, the second epistle I write to you; in both of which I awaken to remembrance your fair mind.
B061C003V002	61	3	2	That you may remember the words which were before spoken by the holy prophets, and the commandments of our Lord and our Saviour (delivered) by the apostles.
B061C003V003	61	3	3	This first know you, that there will come in the last of the days deriders who will deride, as after their own lusts they walk,
B061C003V004	61	3	4	and saying, Where is the promise of his advent? for, since our fathers have slept, every thing (abideth) as from the beginning of the creation.
B061C003V005	61	3	5	Unknown to them is this while they are willing, that the heaven was from of old, and the earth from the waters and through the waters subsisted, by the word of Aloha:
B061C003V006	61	3	6	those (waters) by which the world that then was, again (was covered) with waters, and perished.
B061C003V007	61	3	7	But the heaven which is now, and the earth, by his own word are set, being reserved unto fire, unto the day of judgment and the perdition of wicked men.
B061C003V008	61	3	8	But this one (truth) be not ignorant of, my beloved, That one day with the Lord (is) as a thousand years, and a thousand years as one day.
B061C003V009	61	3	9	Not dilatory is the Lord in his promises, as some consider delay; but is patient on your account, not willing that any man should perish, but (that) every man to repentance should come.
B061C003V010	61	3	10	But the day of the Lord cometh as a thief: that (day) in which the heavens suddenly shall pass away, but the elements burning be dissolved, and the earth and the works that are in it be found not.
B061C003V011	61	3	11	As, therefore, all these are to be dissolved, how behoveth it you to be holy in your conversation, and in the fear of Aloha;
B061C003V012	61	3	12	expecting and desiring the coming of the day of Aloha; that (day) in which the heavens, tried with fire, shall be dissolved, and the elements burning shall melt?
B061C003V013	61	3	13	But new heavens and earth, according to his promise, we expect; those wherein righteousness dwelleth.
B061C003V014	61	3	14	Wherefore, my beloved, while these you expect, be diligent, that, without blemish and without spot, of Him you may be found in peace.
B061C003V015	61	3	15	And the long-suffering of the Lord consider (to be for) salvation; as also our beloved brother Paulos according to the wisdom which hath been given to him hath written to you.
B061C003V016	61	3	16	As in all his epistles he speaks concerning these; in which there is somewhat difficult for intelligence. Those who are not knowing nor settled pervert them, as also the remaining scriptures, to their perdition.
B061C003V017	61	3	17	You therefore, my beloved, knowing this before, keep yourselves, lest, going after the error of those who are lawless, you fall from your support.
B061C003V018	61	3	18	But increase in grace, and in the knowledge of our Lord and our Saviour Jeshu Meshiha, and (of) Aloha the Father, Whose be glory both now, and in all time, and to the days eternal. Amen.
B062C001V001	62	1	1	WE announce to you that which was from the beginning, that which we have heard, and seen with our eyes, have seen, and touched with our hands, that which is the Word of life.
B062C001V002	62	1	2	And the life was manifested, and we have seen, and testify, and preach to you the eternal life which was with the Father, and was manifested to us.
B062C001V003	62	1	3	And what we have seen and heard, we make known also to you, that you may have communion with us; and our communion is with the Father, and with his Son Jeshu the Meshiha.
B062C001V004	62	1	4	And these write we unto you, that our joy which is in you may be complete.
B062C001V005	62	1	5	And this is the annunciation which we have heard from him, and announce to you, that Aloha is light, and in him is no darkness at all.
B062C001V006	62	1	6	And if we say that we have communion with him, and walk in darkness, we lie, and in the truth do not proceed;
B062C001V007	62	1	7	but if in the light we walk, as He is in the light, we have communion with one another, and the blood of Jeshu his Son cleanseth us from all our sins.
B062C001V008	62	1	8	And if we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and the truth is not in us;
B062C001V009	62	1	9	but if we confess our sins, he is faithful and just to forgive us our sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.
B062C001V010	62	1	10	And if we say we have not sinned, we make him a liar, and his word is not in us.
B062C002V001	62	2	1	My sons, these write I to you, that you sin not. And if a man shall sin, we have an Advocate with the Father, Jeshu Meshiha, the Just;
B062C002V002	62	2	2	for he is the propitiation for our sins, and not on behalf of ours only, but also on behalf of the whole world.
B062C002V003	62	2	3	And by this we feel that we know him, if we keep his commandments.
B062C002V004	62	2	4	For he who saith that he knoweth him, and his commandments keepeth not, is a liar, and the truth is not in him.
B062C002V005	62	2	5	But he who keepeth his word, in him is perfected truly the love of Aloha; for by this we know that we are in him.
B062C002V006	62	2	6	He who saith, I am in him, ought according to his walkings to walk.
B062C002V007	62	2	7	MY beloved, a new commandment I write not to you, but the old commandment, that which was with you from the beginning; but the old commandment is the word which you have heard.
B062C002V008	62	2	8	Again, a new commandment I write to you, that which is true in him and in you; because the darkness hath passed, and the true light beginneth to appear.
B062C002V009	62	2	9	Whoever saith, then, that he is in the light, and hateth his brother, is in darkness until now.
B062C002V010	62	2	10	He who loveth his brother, in the light abideth, and offence is not in him.
B062C002V011	62	2	11	He who hateth his brother is in darkness, and in the darkness walketh, and knoweth not whither he goeth, because the darkness itself hath blinded his eyes.
B062C002V012	62	2	12	I write to you, sons, because forgiven to you are your sins for the sake of his name.
B062C002V013	62	2	13	I write to you, fathers, because you have known him who hath been from the beginning. I write to you, young men, because you have overcome the wicked. I have written to you, children, because you have known the Father.
B062C002V014	62	2	14	I have written to you, fathers, because you have known Him who (hath been) from the beginning. I have written to you, young men, because you are strong, and the word of Aloha remaineth in you, and you have overcome the wicked.
B062C002V015	62	2	15	Love not the world, nor any thing which is in it; for whoever loveth the world, the love of the Father is not in him.
B062C002V016	62	2	16	For every thing that is in the world, is the lust of the body, and the lust of the eyes, and the pride of the world. These which are not of the Father, but they are from the world itself.
B062C002V017	62	2	17	And the world passeth, (both) it and its lusts; but he who doeth the will of Aloha, continueth for ever.
B062C002V018	62	2	18	my sons, it is the last time: and as you have heard, the false meshiha cometh; and now there are many false meshihas, and from this we know that it is the last time.
B062C002V019	62	2	19	From us they went forth, but they were not of us; for if they had been of us, with us would they have remained. But they went forth from us, that it might be known that they were not of us.
B062C002V020	62	2	20	And you have an anointing from the Holy, and you discern every man.
B062C002V021	62	2	21	I have not written to you because you know not the truth, but you know it, and that no lie is of it, of the truth.
B062C002V022	62	2	22	Who is a liar, if not he who denieth that Jeshu is the Meshiha? and this (one) is a false meshiha. He who denieth the Father, denieth also the Son;
B062C002V023	62	2	23	and he who denieth the Son, disbelieveth also the Father. Whoso confesseth the Son, the Father also confesseth.
B062C002V024	62	2	24	And you, what you have heard from the first, let it continue with you. For, if what you have heard from the first continue with you, you also will continue in the Father and in the Son.
B062C002V025	62	2	25	And this is the promise which he promised to us, eternal life.
B062C002V026	62	2	26	But these I have written to you, because of those who would seduce you.
B062C002V027	62	2	27	And you, also, if the anointing continue with you which you have received from him, have not need that a man should teach you; but as the anointing that is from Aloha itself teacheth you concerning every thing, and is true, neither is falsity in it; and as it hath taught you, continue in it.
B062C002V028	62	2	28	And now, my sons, continue in him: that when he is manifested we may not he confounded of him, but we may have confidence at his coming.
B062C002V029	62	2	29	If you know that he is righteous, know also that every one who doeth righteousness is of him.
B062C003V001	62	3	1	And see how great is the love of the Father toward us, that sons he hath called us, and also made us! Therefore the world doth not know us, because that it hath also not known him.
B062C003V002	62	3	2	MY beloved, now are we the sons of Aloha; and it is not manifest, as yet, what we are to become, but we know, that when he is manifested, in his likeness we are and see him, according to that which he is.
B062C003V003	62	3	3	And every one who hath in him this hope, purifieth himself, as He is pure.
B062C003V004	62	3	4	But whoever committeth sin doeth iniquity; for all sin is iniquity.
B062C003V005	62	3	5	And you know that he was manifested to bear our sins, and sin in him is not.
B062C003V006	62	3	6	And every one who in him abideth, sinneth not. And every one who sinneth, hath not seen him, nor known him.
B062C003V007	62	3	7	My sons, let no man deceive you: he who worketh righteousness is righteous, as also the Meshiha himself is righteous.
B062C003V008	62	3	8	And he who doeth sin is of Satana, because that from the commencement Satana was a sinner. And for this cause did the Son of Aloha appear, that he might destroy the works of Satana.
B062C003V009	62	3	9	Every one who is born of Aloha, sin doth not work, because that his seed is in him, and he cannot sin, because of Aloha he is born.
B062C003V010	62	3	10	In this are distinguished the sons of Aloha from the sons of Satana; every one who doeth not righteousness, nor loveth his brother, is not of Aloha.
B062C003V011	62	3	11	For this is the commandment which you have heard from before, that you love one another.
B062C003V012	62	3	12	Not as Koen, who was from the Evil, and killed his brother. And on what account killed he him? unless that his own works were evil and his brother's righteous.
B062C003V013	62	3	13	Do not wonder, my brethren, if the world hate you.
B062C003V014	62	3	14	We know that we have passed from death unto life, by this, that we love our brethren. He who loveth not his brother, in death continueth.
B062C003V015	62	3	15	For every one who hateth his brother is a man-killer; and we know that in no man-killer can abide the life which is eternal.
B062C003V016	62	3	16	In this we know His love toward us, that he gave himself for us; (so) also it is right for us for the sake of our brethren to give ourselves.
B062C003V017	62	3	17	And he who hath the possession of the world, and shall see his brother that he needeth, and shall shut his compassions from him, how is there in him the love of Aloha?
B062C003V018	62	3	18	My sons, let us not love one another in words and in tongue, but in works and in truth.
B062C003V019	62	3	19	And by this we make known that we are of the truth, and before that he cometh we make confident our hearts.
B062C003V020	62	3	20	And if our heart condemn us, how much (more) Aloha, who is greater than our heart, and knoweth every thing!
B062C003V021	62	3	21	My beloved, if our heart condemn us not, we have openness of face before Aloha.
B062C003V022	62	3	22	And whatever we ask, we shall receive from him, because we keep his commandments, and do the things which are beautiful before him.
B062C003V023	62	3	23	And this is his commandment, That we believe in the name of his Son Jeshu Meshiha, and love one another, as he hath commanded us.
B062C003V024	62	3	24	And he who keepeth his commandments, is kept by him, and he dwelleth in him: and by this we perceive that he dwelleth in us, by his Spirit whom he hath given to us.
B062C004V001	62	4	1	MY beloved, believe not all spirits, but discern the spirits whether they be from Aloha; because many false prophets have gone forth into the world.
B062C004V002	62	4	2	By this we know the Spirit of Aloha: Every spirit who confesseth that Jeshu Meshiha hath come in the flesh, is from Aloha.
B062C004V003	62	4	3	And every spirit who confesseth not that Jeshu hath come in the flesh, is not from Aloha: but this is from that false meshiha, of whom you have heard that he cometh, and now is in the world already.
B062C004V004	62	4	4	But you of Aloha are the children, and have overcome them; because greater is he who is with you, than he who is in the world.
B062C004V005	62	4	5	And these are of the world, therefore the world heareth them. But we are of Aloha; and he who knoweth Aloha heareth us;
B062C004V006	62	4	6	and he who is not of Aloha heareth us not. In this itself we perceive the Spirit of truth and the spirit of deception.
B062C004V007	62	4	7	my beloved, let us love one another, because love is of Aloha; and every one who loveth from Aloha is born, and knoweth Aloha.
B062C004V008	62	4	8	For Aloha is Love; and every one who loveth not, knoweth not Aloha.
B062C004V009	62	4	9	In this was made known the love of Aloha towards us, that Aloha sent his only Son into the world that we might live by him.
B062C004V010	62	4	10	In this is love: it was not that we had loved Aloha, but that Aloha himself loved us, and sent his Son a propitiation for our sins.
B062C004V011	62	4	11	MY beloved, if Aloha so hath loved us, we also are indebted to love one another.
B062C004V012	62	4	12	Aloha no man hath seen but if we love one another, Aloha in us abideth, and his love is fulfilled in us.
B062C004V013	62	4	13	And by this we know that in him we abide, and he abideth in us, because of his Spirit he hath given us.
B062C004V014	62	4	14	And we have seen and we testify that the Father hath sent his Son, the Redeemer of the world.
B062C004V015	62	4	15	Whosoever confesseth Jeshu that he is the Son of Aloha, in him Aloha abideth, and he abideth in Aloha.
B062C004V016	62	4	16	And we have believed and known the love which Aloha hath toward us; for Aloha is Love. And every one who abideth in love in Aloha abideth.
B062C004V017	62	4	17	And in this is his love perfected with us, that openness of face we might have in the day of judgment; because that as He was, so also we are in this world.
B062C004V018	62	4	18	Fear in love is not: but perfect love hath cast out fear, because fear is in terror. He who feareth is not perfect in love.
B062C004V019	62	4	19	We then will love Aloha, because he hath first loved us.
B062C004V020	62	4	20	But if one shall say, I love Aloha, and his brother he hateth, he is a liar. For he who his brother whom he hath seen loveth not, how can he love Aloha himself whom he hath not seen?
B062C004V021	62	4	21	And this commandment we have received from him, That every one who loveth Aloha shall love also his brother.
B062C005V001	62	5	1	WHOSOEVER believeth that Jeshu is the Meshiha of Aloha is born. And every one who loveth the Generator loveth also him who is generated of him.
B062C005V002	62	5	2	And by this we know that we love the children of Aloha, when we love Aloha, and work his commandments.
B062C005V003	62	5	3	For this is the love of Aloha, that we keep his commandments; and his commandments are not heavy.
B062C005V004	62	5	4	Because every one who is born of Aloha overcometh the world: and this is the victory which overcometh the world, our faith.
B062C005V005	62	5	5	For who (is he) that overcometh the world, but he who believeth that Jeshu is the Son of Aloha?
B062C005V006	62	5	6	This is he who came by water and blood, Jeshu the Meshiha: it was not by water only, but by water and blood; and the Spirit testifieth, because the Spirit himself is truth.
B062C005V007	62	5	7	And there are three that testify, the Spirit, and the water, and the blood;
B062C005V008	62	5	8	and these three are in one.
B062C005V009	62	5	9	If the testimony of men we receive, how much greater is the testimony of Aloha? and this is the testimony which Aloha hath testified concerning his Son.
B062C005V010	62	5	10	Whosoever believeth in the Son of Aloha hath this testimony in himself. Every one who believeth not Aloha hath made him a liar, in not believing the testimony that he hath testified concerning his Son.
B062C005V011	62	5	11	And this is the testimony, That the life which is eternal, Aloha hath given to us, and this life is in his Son.
B062C005V012	62	5	12	Every one who apprehendeth the Son, apprehendeth also life; and every one who apprehendeth not the Son of Aloha, hath not life.
B062C005V013	62	5	13	These I have written to you, that you may know that you have the life which is eternal, who believe in the name of the Son of Aloha.
B062C005V014	62	5	14	And this is the assurance that we have toward him, that all that we ask of him according to his will, he heareth us.
B062C005V015	62	5	15	And if we are persuaded that he heareth us concerning what we ask from him, we are confident of receiving already the requests that we ask from him.
B062C005V016	62	5	16	if a man shall see his brother sin a sin not obnoxious to the death, he shall ask, and life be given to him, to those who sin not as unto the death. For there is the sin of death;-it is not concerning this I say that a man shall pray.
B062C005V017	62	5	17	For all iniquity is sin; and there is sin which is not of death.
B062C005V018	62	5	18	And we know that every one who is born of Aloha sinneth not. For he who is born of Aloha keepeth himself, and the Evil doth not approach him.
B062C005V019	62	5	19	We know that we are of Aloha, and the whole world in the Evil is lying.
B062C005V020	62	5	20	And we know that the Son of Aloha hath come, and hath given us knowledge to know the truth, and to be in him in the truth, in his Son Jeshu the Meshiha. This is Aloha the true, and the life which is eternal.
B062C005V021	62	5	21	My sons, keep yourselves from the service of idols.
B063C001V001	63	1	1	THE presbyter to the elect Kuria and to her sons, whom I love in truth, nor I only, but all they who know the truth,
B063C001V002	63	1	2	on account of the truth which abideth in us, and is with us for ever;
B063C001V003	63	1	3	Grace be with you and mercy and peace, from Aloha the Father, and from Jeshu Meshiha the Son of the Father, in truth and in love.
B063C001V004	63	1	4	I have rejoiced much to have found of thy sons who walk in the truth, after the commandment we have received from the Father.
B063C001V005	63	1	5	And now I entreat thee, Kuria,-no new commandment writing to thee, but that which we have had from the beginning,-that we love one another.
B063C001V006	63	1	6	And this is love, that we walk according to the commandment; this commandment is according to that which you have heard from the beginning, that in it we should walk.
B063C001V007	63	1	7	Because many deceivers are come out into the world who confess not that Jeshu Meshiha came in the flesh. This is the deceiver and antichrist.
B063C001V008	63	1	8	Be watchful of yourselves, that not any thing perish which you have wrought; but (that with) a complete reward you may be recompensed.
B063C001V009	63	1	9	Every one who transgresseth, and abideth not in the doctrine of the Meshiha, hath not Aloha. He who abideth in his doctrine, this hath both the Father and the Son.
B063C001V010	63	1	10	If any one come to you, and this doctrine bring not, receive him not into the house, and "Joy to you," and " Farewell," say not to him.
B063C001V011	63	1	11	For he who saith to him, " Farewell," becometh a participator of his evil deeds.
B063C001V012	63	1	12	Though I have many things to write to you, I will not with parchment and ink; but I hope to come to you, and mouth with mouth to speak, that our joy may be complete.
B063C001V013	63	1	13	The sons of thy elect sister ask your peace. Grace be with you. Amen.
B064C001V001	64	1	1	THE presbyter unto Gaios my beloved, whom I love in truth.
B064C001V002	64	1	2	Our beloved, in all things I pray for thee, that thou mayest prosper and be healthful, even as thy soul prospereth.
B064C001V003	64	1	3	For I have rejoiced greatly when the brethren have come, and have testified concerning thy integrity, even as in the truth thou walkest.
B064C001V004	64	1	4	And greater joy than this I have not (than) when I hear that my sons walk in the truth.
B064C001V005	64	1	5	Our beloved, in faithfulness thou performest what thou doest unto the brethren, and especially to those who are strangers,
B064C001V006	64	1	6	who have testified of thy charity, before all the church, to whom thou hast done well according to that which is worthy of Aloha.
B064C001V007	64	1	7	For after his name they went forth, taking nothing from the Gentiles.
B064C001V008	64	1	8	We therefore ought to receive such, that we may be helpers of the truth.
B064C001V009	64	1	9	I would have written to the church; but he who loveth to be foremost of you, Diotrapas, receiveth us not.
B064C001V010	64	1	10	On account of this, if I come, I will remember the works which he doeth, who words of evil maketh concerning us; and these not satisfying him, he hath not received the brethren, and those who receive he forbiddeth, and also expelleth from the church.
B064C001V011	64	1	11	Our beloved, be not imitative of the evil, but of the good. He who doeth good is of Aloha, and he who doeth evil hath not seen Aloha.
B064C001V012	64	1	12	Concerning Demetrios is a testimony from every man, and from the church, and from the truth itself. But we also bear witness, and you know that our testimony is true.
B064C001V013	64	1	13	I have many things which I would write to thee, but I will not with ink and reed write to thee.
B064C001V014	64	1	14	But I hope that soon I shall see thee, and mouth to mouth we will speak. Peace be with thee. The friends ask thy peace. Ask the peace of the friends each by his name.
B065C001V001	65	1	1	JIHUDA, servant of Jeshu Meshiha, but brother of Jakub, to the called people, who are beloved of Aloha the Father, (and) in Jeshu Meshiha preserved:
B065C001V002	65	1	2	Mercy and peace in love be multiplied unto you.
B065C001V003	65	1	3	My beloved, while giving all diligence to write to you concerning our common salvation, it is needful for me to write to you, exhorting you (in particular) to do battle for the faith which was once delivered to the saints.
B065C001V004	65	1	4	For certain men have obtained entrance, who from the beginning were proscribed in this condemnation; depraved men, who the grace of Aloha turn unto lasciviousness, and him who is the only Lord GOD, our Lord Jeshu Meshiha, deny.
B065C001V005	65	1	5	But I will to remind you, though all of you know, that Aloha, when once the people from Metsreen he had redeemed, yet afterward destroyed them who believed not.
B065C001V006	65	1	6	And the angels who kept not their primacy, but left their habitation, unto the judgment of the great day in chains unknown, under darkness, he hath kept.
B065C001V007	65	1	7	As Sadum and Omuro, and the cities which were around them, which in manner of them committed fornication, and went after other flesh, are lying under everlasting fire, condemned unto judgment.
B065C001V008	65	1	8	In this manner also (will perish) those who, in sleep imagining, defile the flesh, but contemn government, and blaspheme majesty.
B065C001V009	65	1	9	Yet Mikael, chief of angels, when, with the accuser speaking, he contended on account of the body of Musha, dared not bring against him a reviling judgment, but said, The Lord rebuke thee.
B065C001V010	65	1	10	But these the things which they know not revile; but through those by which naturally as the beasts they are swayed, they are corrupted.
B065C001V011	65	1	11	Woe to them; for in the way of Koen they have gone, and after the error of Belam for gain they have burned, and in the rebellion of Kurach they have perished.
B065C001V012	65	1	12	These are they who, in their recreations contaminating, behave wantonly, feeding themselves without reverence; clouds without rain, roaming with the winds; trees whose fruit withereth, and which are unfruitful, twice dead, and uplifted from their root;
B065C001V013	65	1	13	turbulent waves of the sea, which, by their foaming, manifest their shame; erring stars, unto whom the blackness of darkness that is eternal is reserved.
B065C001V014	65	1	14	But Hanuk also, who was the seventh from Adam, prophesied of these, saying, Behold, the Lord cometh, with myriads of his saints,
B065C001V015	65	1	15	To execute judgment upon all; And to convict all the wicked for all their deeds Which they have wickedly done; And for all those obdurate words Which ungodly sinners have spoken.
B065C001V016	65	1	16	These are they who murmur and complain of every thing, while walking according to their own desires; their mouth speaking portentous things, and extolling persons for the sake of gain.
B065C001V017	65	1	17	But you, my beloved, remember those words which before were spoken by the apostles of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha,
B065C001V018	65	1	18	who told you that in the last times there would be those who scoff, who according to their own desires go after wickedness.
B065C001V019	65	1	19	These are they who separate;-animals, in whom the Spirit is not.
B065C001V020	65	1	20	But you, my beloved, in your holy faith be edified anew, praying in the Holy Spirit,
B065C001V021	65	1	21	ourselves in the love of Aloha to keep, while looking for the mercy of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha unto our eternal salvation.
B065C001V022	65	1	22	And some of them snatch from the fire.
B065C001V023	65	1	23	But when they repent, have compassion on them, with fear, hating even the tunic which by the flesh is contaminated.
B065C001V024	65	1	24	But to him who is able to keep you without falling and without spot, and to establish you without blemish, Aloha our only Saviour by Jeshu Meshiha our Lord, before his majesty with joy,
B065C001V025	65	1	25	Be glory, and dominion, and honour, and grandeur, both now and in all ages. Amen.
B066C001V001	66	1	1	THE Revelation of Jeshu Meshiha, which Aloha gave unto him, to show unto his servants the things which must be done speedily; and which he made known, sending by his angel unto his servant Juhanon,
B066C001V002	66	1	2	who attested the word of Aloha and the testimony of Jeshu Meshiha, and all which he beheld.
B066C001V003	66	1	3	Blessed is he who readeth, and they who hear the words of this prophecy, and keep those which are written therein; for the time hath approached.
B066C001V004	66	1	4	Juhanon to the seven churches which are in Asia: grace to you and peace from him who is, and who was, and who cometh; from the seven Spirits who are before his throne;
B066C001V005	66	1	5	and from Jeshu Meshiha who is the faithful Witness, the First-born of the dead, and Head of the kings of the earth, who hath loved us, and released us from our sins by his blood,
B066C001V006	66	1	6	and hath made us a priestly kingdom unto Aloha and his Father; to whom be glory and dominion for ever and ever. Amen.
B066C001V007	66	1	7	Behold, he cometh with clouds, and all eyes shall see him, and they also who transfixed him; and for him shall mourn all the tribes of the earth. Yes, Amen!
B066C001V008	66	1	8	I am Olaph and Thau, saith Aloha the Lord, who is, and who was, and who cometh, the Omnipotent.
B066C001V009	66	1	9	I, Juhanon your brother, and your fellow-sharer in the affliction, and in the patience, which are in Jeshu Meshiha, was in the island which is called Pathamon, for the word of Aloha and for the testimony of Jeshu Meshiha.
B066C001V010	66	1	10	I was in the Spirit on the Lord's day; and I heard behind me a great voice as a trumpet, saying,
B066C001V011	66	1	11	What thou seest, write in a book; and send to the seven churches, at Ephesos, and at Smurna, and at Pergamos, and at Thiatira, and at Sardis, and at Philidaphia, and at Laodikia.
B066C001V012	66	1	12	And I turned to see the voice that spake with me; and being turned, I saw seven candlesticks of gold.
B066C001V013	66	1	13	And in the midst of the candlesticks (one) who was like the Son of man, clothed to the foot, and girded about his paps with a circlet of gold.
B066C001V014	66	1	14	But his head and hair were white as wool, white as snow; and his eyes (were) as a flame of fire,
B066C001V015	66	1	15	and his feet were like refined brass, which flamed as in a furnace, and his voice as the voice of many waters.
B066C001V016	66	1	16	And he had in his right hand seven stars; and from his mouth a sharp sword of two edges went forth; and his countenance was as the sun shining in his strength.
B066C001V017	66	1	17	And when I saw him I fell at his feet as dead. And he laid upon me his right hand, saying, Fear not: I am the First and the Last;
B066C001V018	66	1	18	and who liveth and who have been dead; and, behold, I am alive for ever and ever. Amen! And I have the keys of death and of Sheul.
B066C001V019	66	1	19	Write, then, what thou hast seen; and those which are, and those which are to be after them.
B066C001V020	66	1	20	(This is) the mystery of the seven stars which thou sawest in my right hand, and of the seven candlesticks of gold: the seven stars are the angels of the seven churches, and the seven candlesticks are the seven churches.
B066C002V001	66	2	1	To the angel of the church which is in Ephesos, write: These saith the Holder of all, and of the seven stars in his right hand, who walketh in the midst of the seven candlesticks of gold.
B066C002V002	66	2	2	I know thy works, and thy labour, and thy patience, and (that) thou canst not bear evils; and hast tried those who say they are apostles, and are not, and hast found them liars.
B066C002V003	66	2	3	And thou hast patience, and hast laboured on account of my name, and hast not fainted.
B066C002V004	66	2	4	But I have against thee, because thy first love thou hast forsaken.
B066C002V005	66	2	5	Remember, therefore, from whence thou art fallen, and repent, and do the first works. But if not, I will come to thee quickly, and will remove thy candlestick from its place, if thou convert not.
B066C002V006	66	2	6	But this thou hast, that thou hatest the works of the Nikolitu, which also I (hate).
B066C002V007	66	2	7	He who hath ears, let him hear what the Spirit saith to the churches. To him who overcometh I will give to eat of the tree of life, which is in the paradise of my God.
B066C002V008	66	2	8	And to the angel of the church which is in Smurna, write: These saith the First and the Last, who was dead, and liveth.
B066C002V009	66	2	9	I know thy works, and affliction, and poverty, but thou art rich; and the blasphemy of them who say of themselves that they are Jihudoyee, and are not, but the synagogue of Satana.
B066C002V010	66	2	10	Fear not any thing of those that thou art to suffer; for, behold, it will be that the accuser will cast some of you into prison, so that you may be tried; and you will have affliction ten days. Be faithful unto the death, and I will give thee the crown of life.
B066C002V011	66	2	11	He who hath ears, let him hear what saith the Spirit to the churches. He who overcometh shall not be injured by the second death.
B066C002V012	66	2	12	And to the angel of the church which is in Pergamos, write: These saith he who hath the sharp sword with two edges.
B066C002V013	66	2	13	I know thy works, and where thou dwellest, where (is) the throne of Satana; and thou hast held my name, and not denied my faith in those days when my witness was exposed, my faithful one, who was killed with you where dwelleth Satana.
B066C002V014	66	2	14	But I have against thee a little, because thou hast there those who hold the doctrine of Belam, who taught Balok to cast a stumbling-block before the sons of Israel, to eat that which the sons of idols (eat), and to commit fornication.
B066C002V015	66	2	15	So hast thou who hold the doctrine of the Nikolitu: of it,
B066C002V016	66	2	16	in like (manner), repent; and if not, I will come to thee quickly, and will war against them with the sword of my mouth.
B066C002V017	66	2	17	He who hath ears, let him hear what saith the Spirit to the churches. To him who overcometh will I give to eat of the manna which is hidden; and I will give to him the white stone, and upon the stone a new name written, which no man knoweth but he who receiveth.
B066C002V018	66	2	18	And to the angel and church which is in Thiatiros, write: These saith the Son of Aloha, who hath his eyes as the flame of fire, and his feet like refined brass.
B066C002V019	66	2	19	I know thy works, and thy love and faith and service; and also thy patience, and thy last works to be greater than the first.
B066C002V020	66	2	20	But I have against thee that thou permittest thy wife Izabel, who calleth herself a prophetess, to teach and seduce my servants to commit fornication, and to eat what the sons of idols (eat).
B066C002V021	66	2	21	And I gave her time when she might convert, and she willed not to repent of her fornication.
B066C002V022	66	2	22	Behold, I cast her into a bed, and those who have committed adultery with her into great affliction, if they repent not of their works.
B066C002V023	66	2	23	And her sons will I kill with death, and all the churches shall know that I am he who searcheth the reins and the hearts: and I will give to you every one according to your works.
B066C002V024	66	2	24	But to you I say, to those of the rest who are in Thiatiros, all them who have not this doctrine, the men who know not the depths Of Satana, as they speak; I will not throw upon you another burden;
B066C002V025	66	2	25	but that which you have, hold, until I come.
B066C002V026	66	2	26	And he who conquereth, and he who keepeth until the end my works, I will give to him power over the peoples,
B066C002V027	66	2	27	and he shall rule them with a rod of iron, and as a vessel of the potter shall they be destroyed, as also I have received from my Father;
B066C002V028	66	2	28	and I will give to him the morning star.
B066C002V029	66	2	29	He who hath ears, let him hear what the Spirit saith to the churches.
B066C003V001	66	3	1	AND to the angel who is in Sardis write: These saith he who hath the seven Spirits of Aloha, and the seven stars: I know thy works, that a name thou hast that thou livest, and thou art dead.
B066C003V002	66	3	2	Awake, and keep those things which remain, which are about to die; for I have not found thy works complete before my God.
B066C003V003	66	3	3	Remember then how thou hast received, and hearken, and keep, and repent. And if then thou wilt not awake, I will come against thee as the thief, and thou shalt not know in what hour I come against thee.
B066C003V004	66	3	4	But thou hast a few names in Sardis who have not defiled their vestments; and they shall walk with me in white, because they are worthy.
B066C003V005	66	3	5	He who overcometh shall be clothed in white vestments, and I will not blot their name from the book of life; and I will confess their name before my Father, and before his angels.
B066C003V006	66	3	6	He who hath ears, let him hear what the Spirit saith to the churches.
B066C003V007	66	3	7	And to the angel of the church which is in Philadelphia write: These saith the Holy, the True, who hath the key of David; who openeth and no man shutteth, and who shutteth and no man openeth.
B066C003V008	66	3	8	I know thy works; and, behold, I have given before thee an open door, which no man can shut; because thou hast a little strength, and hast kept my word, and hast not denied my name.
B066C003V009	66	3	9	Behold, I will give of the synagogue of Satana, who say that they are Jihudoyee, and are not, but lie; behold, I will make them to come and worship before thy feet, and they shall know that I have loved thee.
B066C003V010	66	3	10	Because thou hast kept the word of my patience, I will keep thee from the hour of temptation, which is to come upon all the habitable world, to try them who dwell upon the earth.
B066C003V011	66	3	11	I come quickly. Hold that which thou hast, that no man take thy crown.
B066C003V012	66	3	12	Him who overcometh I will make a column in the temple of my God, and he shall go out no more; and I will write upon him the name of my God, and of Urishlem the new, which descendeth from heaven from my God, and my new name.
B066C003V013	66	3	13	He who hath ears, let him hear what the Spirit saith to the churches.
B066C003V014	66	3	14	And to the angel of the church which is in Ladikia write: These saith the Amen, the Witness, the faithful, the true, the Head of the creation of Aloha.
B066C003V015	66	3	15	I know thy works, that thou art neither hot nor cold. Would that thou wast cold or hot!
B066C003V016	66	3	16	So, because thou art lukewarm, and neither hot nor cold, I will vomit thee from my mouth.
B066C003V017	66	3	17	Because thou sayest, I am rich, and have become opulent, and of nothing have need; and knowest not that thou art infirm, and miserable, and needy, and blind, and naked;
B066C003V018	66	3	18	I counsel thee to buy of me gold, proved by fire, that thou mayest be rich; and white raiment, that thou mayest be clothed, and the shame of thy nakedness be not seen; and lave with collyrium thine eyes, that thou mayest see.
B066C003V019	66	3	19	All those whom I love, I reprove and chasten: be zealous therefore, and repent.
B066C003V020	66	3	20	Behold, I stand at the door and knock: if any man hear my voice, and will open the door, I will enter unto him, and will sup with him, and he with me.
B066C003V021	66	3	21	And to him who overcometh I will give to sit with me upon my throne, as also I have overcome, and have sat with my Father in his throne.
B066C003V022	66	3	22	He who hath ears, let him hear what the Spirit saith to the churches.
B066C004V001	66	4	1	AFTER these I saw, and, behold, a door (was) open in heaven. And the first voice that I had heard as a trumpet talking with me, said, Come up hither, and I will make thee see the (things) which must be after these.
B066C004V002	66	4	2	At once I was in the spirit: and, behold, a throne placed in heaven, and upon the throne (One) sat.
B066C004V003	66	4	3	And he who sat was like to the appearance of the stone of jaspon, and of sardion; and the bow of the clouds was around the throne, in resemblance to the appearance of zmragda.
B066C004V004	66	4	4	Around the throne were seats twenty and four; and upon those seats twenty and four presbyters sitting, who were robed in white vestments, and upon their heads wore coronets of gold.
B066C004V005	66	4	5	And from the throne went forth lightnings and the voice of thunders. And there were seven lamps of fire which burned before His throne, which are the seven Spirits of Aloha.
B066C004V006	66	4	6	And before the throne was a sea of brightness like chrystalos; and in the midst of the throne, and around it, and before the throne, four living-ones, who were full of eyes before and behind.
B066C004V007	66	4	7	And the first living-one was like the lion, and the second living-one was like the calf, and the third living-one had a face as a man, and the fourth living-one was like the eagle which flieth.
B066C004V008	66	4	8	And these four living-ones, each of them, had six wings round about; and within were full of eyes; and they rest not day and night from saying, Holy, holy, holy, Lord God Almighty, Who wast, and art, and art to come.
B066C004V009	66	4	9	And when those living-ones give glory and honour and thanks unto Him who sitteth upon the throne, to Him who liveth for ever and ever,
B066C004V010	66	4	10	the four and twenty presbyters fell before Him who sitteth upon the throne, and worshipped Him who liveth for ever and ever, and cast their crowns before the throne, saying,
B066C004V011	66	4	11	Worthy art thou, O Lord, And our God the Holy One, To receive glory and honour and power; For thou hast created all, And by thy hand they are, And through thy will they were and are created.
B066C005V001	66	5	1	AND I saw in the right hand of him who sat on the throne a writing which was written within and on the back, and sealed with seven seals.
B066C005V002	66	5	2	And I saw a mighty angel who proclaimed with a great voice: Who is worthy to open the book, and to loose the seals thereof?
B066C005V003	66	5	3	And no one was able, in heaven above, nor upon earth, nor under the earth, to open the book, or to inspect it.
B066C005V004	66	5	4	And I wept much, because no one could be found who was worthy to open the book, or to inspect it.
B066C005V005	66	5	5	And one of the presbyters said to me, Weep not; behold, the Lion of the tribe of Jihuda, who is the root of David, hath prevailed. He will open the book and the seven seal thereof.
B066C005V006	66	5	6	And I saw, in the midst of the presbyters, a Lamb standing, as slain, who had seven horns and seven eyes which are the seven Spirits of Aloha, which are sent forth to all the earth.
B066C005V007	66	5	7	And he came and took the book from the right hand of him who sat upon the throne.
B066C005V008	66	5	8	And when he had taken the book, the four living-ones and the twenty and four presbyters fell down before the Lamb, having each of them an harp, and vials of gold full of perfumes, which are the prayers of the saints.
B066C005V009	66	5	9	And they hymned a new hymn, saying, Thou art worthy to take the book, And to open the seals thereof; Because thou wast slain, And hast redeemed us to Aloha by thy blood, From every tribe and tongue and people and nation.
B066C005V010	66	5	10	And thou hast made them to our God kings and priests, And reigning upon the earth.
B066C005V011	66	5	11	And I saw and heard as the voice of many angels around the throne, and the living-ones, and the presbyters, and the number of them was ten thousand times ten thousand, and thousands of thousands,
B066C005V012	66	5	12	which said with a great voice, Worthy is the Lamb that was slain, To receive power, and riches, and wisdom, and strength, And honour, and glory, and blessing,
B066C005V013	66	5	13	And every creature which is in heaven, and on earth, And under the earth, and in the sea, And all them which are therein. And I heard him who sat upon the throne saying: To the Lamb let there be given blessing, and honour, and glory, and praise, and dominion, for ever and ever.
B066C005V014	66	5	14	And the four living-ones said, Amen! And the presbyters fell, and worshipped.
B066C006V001	66	6	1	AND I saw, when the Lamb had opened one of the SEVEN SEALS. And I heard one of the four living-ones speaking as the voice of thunder, Come, and see!
B066C006V002	66	6	2	And I looked: and there was a white horse; and he who sat upon him had a bow, and there was given to him a crown; and he went forth conquering, so that he might conquer.
B066C006V003	66	6	3	And when he had opened the SECOND SEAL, I heard the second living-one, who said, Come!
B066C006V004	66	6	4	And there went out another horse (which was) red; and to him who sat upon him was given to take peace from the earth, and thus that one another they should kill; and there was given to him a great sword.
B066C006V005	66	6	5	And when he had opened the THIRD SEAL, I heard the third living one, saying, Come, and see! And I saw, and, behold, a black horse, and he who sat upon him had a balance in his hand.
B066C006V006	66	6	6	And I heard a voice from the midst of the four living-ones, saying, A choenix of wheat for a dinar; And three choenices of barley for a dinar; And the oil and the wine hurt not.
B066C006V007	66	6	7	And when he had opened the FOURTH SEAL, I heard the fourth living-one, saying, Come, and see!
B066C006V008	66	6	8	And I saw a green horse, and he who sat upon him had the name of Death, and Shiul followed after him. And there was given to him power over the fourth of the earth, to kill with the sword, and with famine, and with death, and with the toothed beast of the earth.
B066C006V009	66	6	9	And when he had opened the FIFTH SEAL, I saw under the altar the souls of them who had been killed for the word of Aloha, and for the testimony of the Lamb, which had been theirs.
B066C006V010	66	6	10	And they cried with a great voice, saying, Until when, O Lord, holy (and) true, Dost thou not judge and avenge our blood On those who dwell upon the earth?
B066C006V011	66	6	11	And there was given to each of them the white robe; and it was told them, that they should rest yet a little time, until should be completed their fellow-servants, their brethren who would be killed as also they.
B066C006V012	66	6	12	And I saw when he opened the SIXTH SEAL, there was a great movement; and the sun became black as sackcloth of hair, and all the moon became as blood;
B066C006V013	66	6	13	and the stars of heaven fell to the earth, as the fig-tree casteth her figs, when from a great wind she is shaken.
B066C006V014	66	6	14	And the heavens were sundered as a book that is rolled, and all the mountains and islands from their places were moved;
B066C006V015	66	6	15	and the kings of the earth and great ones, and the chiefs of thousands, and the rich and the mighty ones, and every servant, and every freeman, hid them in the caverns, and in the rocks of the mountains,
B066C006V016	66	6	16	saying to the mountains and to the rocks, Fall upon us, and hide us from the face of him who sitteth upon the throne and from the wrath of the Lamb.
B066C006V017	66	6	17	For the great day of their wrath has come, and who is able to stand?
B066C007V001	66	7	1	AND after these, I saw four angels standing upon the four corners of the earth, holding the four winds of the earth, that the winds should not blow upon the earth, nor upon the sea, nor upon the trees.
B066C007V002	66	7	2	And I saw another angel, and he ascended from the rising of the sun; who had the seal of Aloha the Living. And he cried with a great voice to the four angels to whom it had been given to hurt the earth and the sea,
B066C007V003	66	7	3	saying, Hurt not the earth, nor the sea, neither the trees, until we have sealed the servants of our God upon their foreheads.
B066C007V004	66	7	4	And I heard the number of them who were sealed, an hundred and forty and four thousands, sealed of every tribe of Israel:
B066C007V005	66	7	5	of the tribe of Jihuda, twelve thousand were sealed; of the tribe of Rubill, twelve thousand; of the tribe of Gad, twelve thousand;
B066C007V006	66	7	6	of the tribe of Ashir, twelve thousand; of the tribe of Naphtoli, twelve thousand; of the tribe of Manasha, twelve thousand;
B066C007V007	66	7	7	of the tribe of Shemun, twelve thousand; of the tribe of Levi, twelve thousand; of the tribe of Isokar, twelve thousand;
B066C007V008	66	7	8	of the tribe of Zabolon, twelve thousand; of the tribe of Jauseph, twelve thousand; of the tribe of Benjomin, twelve thousand
B066C007V009	66	7	9	After these I saw, and, behold, a great assembly, which to number no man was able, from all people and nations and tribes and tongues, were standing before the throne and before the Lamb, arrayed in white robes, and with palms in their hands;
B066C007V010	66	7	10	and, crying with a great voice, said, Salvation to our God! To him who sitteth on the throne, And to the Lamb!
B066C007V011	66	7	11	And all the angels stood around the throne, and the presbyters, and the four living-ones; and they fell before his throne upon their faces, and worshipped Aloha,
B066C007V012	66	7	12	saying, Amen. Blessing, and glory, and wisdom, and thanksgiving, And honour, and might, and power, To our God, for ever and ever. Amen.
B066C007V013	66	7	13	And one of the presbyters answered and said to me: These, who are arrayed in white robes, who are they? and from whence do they come?
B066C007V014	66	7	14	And I said to him, My lord, thou knowest. And he said to me, These are they who have come from great affliction, and have washed their robes, and made them white in the blood of the Lamb.
B066C007V015	66	7	15	On account of this they are before the throne of Aloha, and minister to him day and night in his temple. And he who sitteth upon the throne will protect them.
B066C007V016	66	7	16	They will not hunger or thirst again, nor will the sun come down upon them, nor any heat;
B066C007V017	66	7	17	for it is the Lamb who is in the midst of the throne who will feed them, and will lead them unto fountains of living waters, and Aloha will wipe away every tear from their eyes.
B066C008V001	66	8	1	AND when he had opened the SEVENTH SEAL, silence was in heaven, as the dividing of an hour.
B066C008V002	66	8	2	And I saw the seven angels who stood before Aloha, and there were given to them SEVEN TRUMPETS.
B066C008V003	66	8	3	And another angel came, and stood at the altar, and he had a censer of gold, and many perfumes were given to him, which he should give with the prayers of all saints upon the altar of gold that is before the throne;
B066C008V004	66	8	4	and the cloud of the perfumes of the prayers of the saints ascended from the hand of the angel before Aloha.
B066C008V005	66	8	5	And the angel took the censer, and filled it from the fire of the altar, and cast forth upon the earth. And there were thunders, and lightnings, and voices, and movement.
B066C008V006	66	8	6	And the seven angels which had the seven trumpets prepared them to sound. And the First sounded.
B066C008V007	66	8	7	And there was hail, and fire mingled with the waters, and they were cast upon the earth; and the third of the earth burned, and the third of the trees burned, and every green herb burned.
B066C008V008	66	8	8	And the Second angel sounded. And as a great mountain burning with fire was cast into the sea; and the third of the sea also became blood.
B066C008V009	66	8	9	And the third of all creatures which were in the sea, which had lives, died, and the third of the ships were destroyed.
B066C008V010	66	8	10	And the Third angel sounded. And there fell from heaven a star burning as a lamp, and it fell upon the third of the rivers, and upon fountains of waters.
B066C008V011	66	8	11	And the name of the star is called Aphsinthos; and the third of the waters became bitterness, and many men died from the waters because they were bitter.
B066C008V012	66	8	12	And the Fourth angel sounded. And the third of the sun was absorbed, and the third of the moon, and the third of the stars, as that the third of them should be darkened; and they were darkened, and the day shone not a third of it, and the night, in like manner.
B066C008V013	66	8	13	And I beheld, and heard an eagle, flying in the midst, having a tail of blood, saying with a great voice, Woe, woe, to those who dwell upon earth, from the voice of the rest of the trumpets of the three angels which are about to sound!
B066C009V001	66	9	1	AND the Fifth angel sounded. And I saw a star which fell from heaven unto the earth and there was given to him the key of the pit of the abyss.
B066C009V002	66	9	2	And he opened the pit of the abyss, and smoke ascended from the pit, as the smoke of a burning furnace; and the sun was darkened, and the air, from the smoke of the pit.
B066C009V003	66	9	3	And from the smoke came forth locusts upon the earth. And there was given to them power such as scorpions have upon the earth.
B066C009V004	66	9	4	And it was told them, that they should not hurt the herbage of the earth, nor any green (thing), nor any tree, but only those men who had not the seal of Aloha upon their foreheads.
B066C009V005	66	9	5	And it was given them, that they should not kill them, but torture them five months. And their torture was as the torture of a scorpion when he striketh a man.
B066C009V006	66	9	6	And in those days men shall seek death, and shall not find; and shall desire to die, and death will flee from them.
B066C009V007	66	9	7	And the likeness of those locusts (was this): they resemble the appearance of horses prepared for battle. And upon their heads (was) a crown of the likeness of gold; and their faces (were) as the faces of men.
B066C009V008	66	9	8	And they had hair as the hair of women, and their teeth were as of lions;
B066C009V009	66	9	9	and they had breast-plates as breast-plates of iron, and the sound of their wings was as the sound of the chariots of many horses running to battle.
B066C009V010	66	9	10	And they had tails like those of scorpions, and stings; and in their tails they have power to hurt men five months.
B066C009V011	66	9	11	And they had a king over them, the angel of the abyss, and his name in Hebrew is Abadon; but in Javanith his name is Apolon.
B066C009V012	66	9	12	One woe hath gone. Behold, two woes yet come after it.
B066C009V013	66	9	13	And the Sixth angel sounded. And I heard one voice from the horns of the altar of gold which was before Aloha,
B066C009V014	66	9	14	saying to the sixth angel who had the trumpet, Release the four angels which are bound in the great river Phraat.
B066C009V015	66	9	15	And the four angels were released, they who were prepared for an hour, and for a day, and for a month, and for a year, to kill the third (part) of men.
B066C009V016	66	9	16	And the number of the host of the horsemen was two myriads of myriads. I heard the number of them.
B066C009V017	66	9	17	And as I beheld those horses in the vision, and those who sat upon them, (I saw that) they had breast-plates of fire, and jacinth, and sulphur; and the heads of the horses were as the heads of lions, and from their mouths went out fire, and smoke, and sulphur.
B066C009V018	66	9	18	And by these three plagues were the third of men killed; from the fire, and from the smoke, and from the sulphur which went out of their mouths.
B066C009V019	66	9	19	For the power of the horses is in their mouth and in their tails: for their tails were like serpents which had heads, and with them they wound.
B066C009V020	66	9	20	And the rest of men who were not killed by those plagues, did not repent of the works of their hands, that they should not worship demons and idols of gold and of silver and of brass and of stone and of wood, which can neither see nor hear;
B066C009V021	66	9	21	nor repented they of their murders, nor of their sorceries, nor of their fornications, nor of their robberies.
B066C010V001	66	10	1	AND I saw another mighty angel descending from heaven, clothed (with a) cloud, and the bow of the cloud (was) upon his head; and his countenance was as the sun, and his feet as columns of fire.
B066C010V002	66	10	2	And he had in his hand an open book; and he set his right foot upon the sea, but the left upon the land,
B066C010V003	66	10	3	and cried with a great voice, as the roar of a lion. And when he had cried, seven thunders spoke their voices.
B066C010V004	66	10	4	And when those seven thunders had spoken, I was about to write. And I heard a voice from heaven, which said, Seal those (things) which the seven thunders have spoken, and write them not.
B066C010V005	66	10	5	And the angel whom I saw standing upon the sea and upon the land, lifted his right hand to heaven,
B066C010V006	66	10	6	and sware by Him who liveth for ever and ever, who created heaven and those who are in it, and the earth and those that are in it, and the sea and those that are in it, That time no more shall be;
B066C010V007	66	10	7	but (that) in the days of the voice of the seventh angel, when he is about to sound, the mystery of Aloha shall be completed, as he hath declared to his servants the prophets.
B066C010V008	66	10	8	And the voice which I heard from heaven spake with me again, and said, Go, take the book which is open in the hand of the angel who standeth upon the sea and upon the land.
B066C010V009	66	10	9	And I went to the angel, and said to him, Give me the book. And he said to me, Take, and eat it; and it will embitter thee thy belly, but in thy mouth it will be sweet as honey.
B066C010V010	66	10	10	And I took the book from the hand of the angel, and ate it. And it was in my mouth as sweet as honey; and when I had eaten it my belly was made bitter.
B066C010V011	66	10	11	And he said to me, It behoves thee yet to prophesy concerning many nations, and concerning peoples and princes and kings.
B066C011V001	66	11	1	AND there was given to me a reed, like a staff; and the angel stood, saying, Arise, measure the temple of Aloha, and the altar, and them who worship therein;
B066C011V002	66	11	2	and the court which is without the temple cast out, and do not measure it, because it is given to the Gentiles, and the holy city shall be trodden down, MONTHS FORTY AND TWO.
B066C011V003	66	11	3	And I will give my two witnesses, and they shall prophesy, DAYS A THOUSAND AND TWO HUNDRED AND SIXTY, clothed in sackcloth.
B066C011V004	66	11	4	These are the two olive (trees) and two candlesticks which before the Lord of the earth do stand.
B066C011V005	66	11	5	And if a man willeth to wound them, fire cometh forth from their mouth, and devoureth their adversaries. And if a man willeth to wound (them), thus must he be killed.
B066C011V006	66	11	6	These have power to shut heaven, that rain it may not rain in those days; and power have they over the waters, to turn them into blood, and to smite the earth with every plague as many times as they will.
B066C011V007	66	11	7	And when they shall have completed their testimony, the beast of prey, which ascended from the abyss, will make war against them, and overcome them,
B066C011V008	66	11	8	and their dead bodies (will be) upon the wide street of the great city, which is called, spiritually, Sedum, and Metsreen, where also our Lord hath been crucified.
B066C011V009	66	11	9	And of the peoples and tribes and nations and tongues, seeing their dead bodies days three and a half, will not suffer them to be laid in the tomb.
B066C011V010	66	11	10	And they who dwell upon earth will rejoice over them and be gratified, and will send gifts to one another, because these two prophets tormented them who dwell upon earth.
B066C011V011	66	11	11	And after those three days and a half, the spirit of life from Aloha entered into them, and they arose upon their feet. And great fear fell upon them who saw them.
B066C011V012	66	11	12	And they heard a great voice from heaven, saying to them, Ascend hither. And they ascended to heaven in a cloud, and their adversaries beheld them.
B066C011V013	66	11	13	And in that hour there was a great movement; and one of ten of the city fell; and there were killed in the movement the names of men seven thousand. And they who were left were made afraid, and gave glory to Aloha.
B066C011V014	66	11	14	That second woe hath passed. Behold, the third woe cometh quickly.
B066C011V015	66	11	15	And the Seventh angel sounded. And there were voices and thunders, saying, The kingdom of the world Is of our Lord, and of his Meshiha; And he will reign for ever and ever!
B066C011V016	66	11	16	And the twenty and four presbyters who were before the throne of Aloha, who were sitting upon their thrones, fell upon their faces and worshipped,
B066C011V017	66	11	17	saying, We give thanks to thee, Lord God omnipotent, Who art, and who wast; Because thou hast taken thy great power, And hast reigned.
B066C011V018	66	11	18	And the nations were angry; But thy wrath is come, And the time of the dead, That they should be avenged; And to give reward to thy servants, To the prophets, and to the saints, And to them who fear thy Name, To the small and to the great; And to destroy them who have destroyed the earth.
B066C011V019	66	11	19	And the temple of Aloha was opened in heaven; and there was seen the ark of his covenant in his temple. And there were lightnings, and thunderings, and voices, and movement, and great hail.
B066C012V001	66	12	1	AND a great sign was seen in heaven; a woman clothed with the sun, and the moon beneath her feet, and upon her head a crown of twelve stars.
B066C012V002	66	12	2	And having in her womb, she cried, and was in travail, and was pained to give birth.
B066C012V003	66	12	3	And I saw another sign in heaven; and behold a great dragon of fire, which had seven heads and ten horns, and upon his heads seven diadems.
B066C012V004	66	12	4	And his tail drew the third of the stars of heaven, and cast them to the earth. And the dragon stood before the woman when she was about to give birth, that when she had given birth he might devour her son.
B066C012V005	66	12	5	And she gave birth to a male child, who is to rule all nations with a rod of iron; and her son was rapt unto Aloha and unto his throne.
B066C012V006	66	12	6	And the woman fled into the desert, where she had a place prepared of Aloha, that there they might nourish her, DAYS A THOUSAND AND TWO HUNDRED AND SIXTY.
B066C012V007	66	12	7	And there was war in heaven. And Mikoel and his angels to fight with the dragon; and the dragon and his angels warred.
B066C012V008	66	12	8	And they could not prevail, and their place was found no more in heaven.
B066C012V009	66	12	9	And the great dragon was cast down, the old serpent, who is called the Deceiver, and the Adversary, which seduceth the whole habitable world. And he was cast upon the earth, and his angels with him were cast.
B066C012V010	66	12	10	And I heard a great voice in heaven saying, Now is there salvation and strength, And the kingdom of our God, And the power of his Meshiha; Because the accuser of our brethren is cast down, Who accused them before Aloha day and night.
B066C012V011	66	12	11	And they overcame him by the blood of the Lamb, And by the word of his testimony. But they loved not their lives unto death.
B066C012V012	66	12	12	Wherefore let the heavens be glad, And those who dwell in them. Woe to the earth and to the sea! Because the deceiver hath gone down to you, Having great indignation, Knowing that little time is to him.
B066C012V013	66	12	13	And when the dragon saw that he was cast down upon the earth, he pursued the woman which gave birth to the son.
B066C012V014	66	12	14	And there were given to the woman two wings of a great eagle, that she might fly into the desert unto her place, where she was to be nourished A TIME, AND TIMES, AND THE DIVIDING OF A TIME, from the face of the serpent.
B066C012V015	66	12	15	And the serpent cast forth from his mouth after the woman waters like a river, as that she might be carried off by the river which he would make.
B066C012V016	66	12	16	And the earth succoured the woman, and the earth opened her mouth, and swallowed the river which the dragon had cast forth from his mouth.
B066C012V017	66	12	17	And the dragon raged against the woman, and went to make war with those of the rest of her seed which kept the commandments of Aloha, and had the testimony of Jeshu.
B066C013V001	66	13	1	And he stood upon the sand of the sea. AND I saw that a beast of prey ascended from the sea, having ten horns and seven heads, and upon his horns seven diadems; and upon his heads names of blasphemy.
B066C013V002	66	13	2	And the beast of prey which I saw was like a leopard, and his feet were as (those) of a bear, and his mouth as the mouth of a lion, and the dragon gave to him his power, and his throne, and great authority.
B066C013V003	66	13	3	And one of his heads was wounded as to death. And his stroke of death was healed; and all the earth wondered after the beast of prey.
B066C013V004	66	13	4	And they worshipped the dragon because he had given authority to the beast of prey, (saying, Who is like the beast of prey,) and who is able to make war with him?
B066C013V005	66	13	5	And there was given him a mouth speaking great sayings and blasphemies, and authority was given him to act, MONTHS, FORTY AND TWO.
B066C013V006	66	13	6	And he opened his mouth to blaspheme against Aloha, blaspheming his name, and his tabernacle, and those who dwell in heaven.
B066C013V007	66	13	7	And there was given to him authority over every tribe, and people, and tongue, and nation; and there was given to him to make war with the saints, to overcome them.
B066C013V008	66	13	8	And all those who inhabit on the earth will worship him, they whose name is not written in the book of life of the Lamb from the foundation of the world.
B066C013V009	66	13	9	If a man have ears, let him hear.
B066C013V010	66	13	10	If any man into captivity leadeth, into captivity he shall go. If any man kill with the sword, it behoveth him by the sword to be killed. This is the patience and the faith of the saints.
B066C013V011	66	13	11	And I saw another beast of prey ascending from the earth; and he had two horns like those of the lamb, and he spake as the dragon.
B066C013V012	66	13	12	And all the authority of the first beast of prey he exercised before him; and he made the earth and those who inhabit therein to worship the first beast of prey, whose wound of death was healed.
B066C013V013	66	13	13	And he wrought great signs, as that also he would make fire to come down from heaven upon earth before men.
B066C013V014	66	13	14	And he will seduce those who dwell upon earth to the making an image of the beast of prey who had the wound of the sword and lived.
B066C013V015	66	13	15	And it was given to him to give spirit to the image of the beast of prey, (that the image also of the beast of prey should speak,) and to cause that all those whosoever who worshipped not the image of the beast of prey should be killed.
B066C013V016	66	13	16	And he caused all, small and great, and rich and poor, and sons of freedom and slaves, to have given to them a signature upon their right hands, or upon their foreheads;
B066C013V017	66	13	17	as that no man might be able to buy or sell, unless he had the signature of the name of the beast of prey, or the number of his name.
B066C013V018	66	13	18	Here is wisdom. Let him who hath mind, calculate the number of the beast of prey; for the number is of man; and his number is Six hundred and sixty and six.
B066C014V001	66	14	1	AND I saw, and, behold, the Lamb stood upon the mountain of Sion, and with him the number, an hundred and forty and four thousand, who had his name, and the name of his Father, written upon their foreheads.
B066C014V002	66	14	2	And I heard a voice from heaven, as the sound of many waters, and as the sound of great thunder; and the voice which I heard was as harpers striking on their harps.
B066C014V003	66	14	3	And they hymned a new hymn before the throne, and before the four living-ones, and the presbyters. And no man was able to learn the hymn, but the hundred and forty and four thousand (who were redeemed from the earth).
B066C014V004	66	14	4	These are they who with women have not been defiled, for they are virgins. These are they who follow the Lamb wherever he goeth. These by Jeshu were redeemed from men, first-fruits unto Aloha and to the Lamb.
B066C014V005	66	14	5	And in their mouth falsehood was not found, for they are without spot.
B066C014V006	66	14	6	And I saw another angel flying through heaven, who with blood had the everlasting gospel to preach to them who dwell on the earth, and unto every nation and tribe, and tongue and people;
B066C014V007	66	14	7	saying with a great voice, Serve Aloha, and give him glory: For the hour of his judgment cometh: And worship him who made heaven and earth, And the sea, and the fountains of waters.
B066C014V008	66	14	8	And another angel, a second, followed him, saying, Fallen, fallen is Babel the Great, Which of the wine of the rage of her fornication Hath made all nations to drink.
B066C014V009	66	14	9	And another angel, a third, followed them saying with a great voice, If any man worship the beast of prey and his image, And receive his mark on his brow, or in his hand,
B066C014V010	66	14	10	He also shall drink of the wine of the wrath of Aloha, Which is mingled without sparing In the cup of his anger. And he shall be tormented in fire and sulphur, Before his holy angels and before the throne:
B066C014V011	66	14	11	And the smoke of their torment For ever and ever will ascend. And they have no rest day and night Who worship the beast of prey and his image.
B066C014V012	66	14	12	Here is the patience of the saints, Who keep the commandments of Aloha, And the faith of Jeshu.
B066C014V013	66	14	13	And I heard a voice from heaven, saying, Write, Blessed are the dead Who in Aloha die from now. Yes, saith the Spirit, That they may rest from their labours, For their works follow with them.
B066C014V014	66	14	14	And I looked, and behold a white cloud, and upon the cloud sat (one) like the Son of man, having on his head a crown of gold, and in his hand a sharp sickle.
B066C014V015	66	14	15	And another angel came out of the temple, crying with a great voice to him who sat upon the cloud.
B066C014V016	66	14	16	And he thrust his sickle over the earth, and the earth was reaped.
B066C014V017	66	14	17	And another angel came out of the temple which is in heaven, having also a sharp sickle.
B066C014V018	66	14	18	And another angel came forth from the altar who had authority over the fire, and he cried with a great cry to him who had the sharp sickle, saying, Send forth thy sharp sickle, and reap the clusters of the vintage of the earth; for the grapes of the earth are ripe.
B066C014V019	66	14	19	And the angel thrust forth his sickle unto the earth, and reaped the vintage of the earth, and he cast into the winepress of the wrath of Aloha the Great.
B066C014V020	66	14	20	And the winepress was trodden (without the city, and blood flowed from the winepress) unto the bridles of the horses, a thousand and six hundred stadia.
B066C015V001	66	15	1	AND I saw another sign in heaven, great and wondrous, seven angels having the seven last plagues; for in them is completed the wrath of Aloha.
B066C015V002	66	15	2	And I saw as a sea of brightness commingled with fire; and them who had won-the-victory from the beast of prey, and from his image, and from the number of his name, standing on the sea of brightness, having the harps of Aloha.
B066C015V003	66	15	3	And they sang the song of Musha the servant of Aloha, and the song of the Lamb, saying, Great and wondrous are thy works, Lord God Omnipotent; Just and true are thy ways, King of ages!
B066C015V004	66	15	4	Who shall not fear thee, Lord, And glorify thy name? For thou only art and holy and just; Therefore all nations shall come And worship before thee; Because thy judgments are revealed.
B066C015V005	66	15	5	After these I saw, and the temple of the tabernacle of testimony which is in heaven was opened.
B066C015V006	66	15	6	And the seven angels came forth, having the seven plagues, from the temple, clothed in linen pure, resplendent, and girded at their breasts with zones of gold.
B066C015V007	66	15	7	And one of the four living-ones gave to the seven angels SEVEN VIALS of gold, which were full of the wrath of Aloha, who liveth for ever and ever.
B066C015V008	66	15	8	And the temple was filled with smoke from the glory of Aloha, and from his power. And no man was able to enter the temple, until should be completed the seven plagues of the seven angels.
B066C016V001	66	16	1	AND I heard a great voice saying to the seven angels, Go, and pour forth the seven vials of the wrath of Aloha upon the earth.
B066C016V002	66	16	2	And the first went, and poured his vial upon the earth: and there became an ulcer, evil and painful, upon the men who had the mark of the beast of prey, and who worshipped the image of him.
B066C016V003	66	16	3	And the second angel poured his vial upon the sea; and it became blood as of the dead, and every living soul died which was in the sea.
B066C016V004	66	16	4	And the third angel poured his vial upon the rivers, and upon the fountains of waters, and they became blood.
B066C016V005	66	16	5	And I heard the angel of the waters saying, Righteous art Thou, who art, And who wast, and just; Because thou hast judged these.
B066C016V006	66	16	6	For the blood of saints and of prophets have they shed, And blood to them hast thou given to drink For they are worthy.
B066C016V007	66	16	7	And I heard from the altar saying, Yes, Lord God Almighty! True and just is thy judgment.
B066C016V008	66	16	8	And the fourth poured out his vial upon the sun, and it was given to him to scorch men with fire;
B066C016V009	66	16	9	and men were scorched with great heat; and men blasphemed the name of Aloha who hath power over these plagues; and they repented not to give him glory.
B066C016V010	66	16	10	And the fifth poured his vial upon the throne of the beast of prey; and his kingdom became darkness, and they gnawed their tongues from pain;
B066C016V011	66	16	11	and they blasphemed the God of heaven from their pains, and from their ulcers, and repented not of their works.
B066C016V012	66	16	12	And the sixth poured his vial upon the great river Phrat, and his waters were dried, that might be prepared the way of the kings who (are) from the rising of the sun.
B066C016V013	66	16	13	And I saw from the mouth of the dragon, and from the mouth of the beast of prey, and from the mouth of the false prophet, three unclean spirits like frogs.
B066C016V014	66	16	14	For they are spirits of demons, working signs; they go to the kings of the whole inhabited world, to gather them to the battle of the great day of Aloha the Omnipotent.
B066C016V015	66	16	15	And BEHOLD, I COME, as the thief. Blessed is he who watcheth, and keepeth his garments, lest naked he walk, and they see his shame.
B066C016V016	66	16	16	And they gathered them to a place which is called in Hebrew Armagedon.
B066C016V017	66	16	17	And the seventh poured his vial upon the air; and a great voice went forth from the temple, from the throne, saying, IT IS DONE.
B066C016V018	66	16	18	And there were lightnings and thunders and voices, and a great movement, such as was not since men were upon earth, as this movement so great.
B066C016V019	66	16	19	And the great city became three parts, and the city of the nations fell; and Babel the great was remembered before Aloha, to give to her the cup of the wine of the fury of his wrath.
B066C016V020	66	16	20	And every island fled, and the mountains were not found.
B066C016V021	66	16	21	And great hail, as of a talent (in weight), was from heaven upon men; and men blasphemed Aloha from the plague of hail, because the plague thereof was exceeding great.
B066C017V001	66	17	1	AND one of the seven angels who had the seven vials came and spake with me, saying, Come; I will show thee the judgment of the great harlot, which sitteth upon many waters:
B066C017V002	66	17	2	with whom the kings of the earth have committed fornication, and they who dwell in the earth have been made drunk by the wine of her fornication.
B066C017V003	66	17	3	And he led me into the desert, in the spirit; and I saw a woman sitting on a beast of prey which was red, full of names of blasphemy, (and) having seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V004	66	17	4	And the woman was arrayed in purple and scarlet, and golden with gold and precious stones and pearls; having a cup of gold in her hand, full of pollutions and uncleanness of her fornications the earth.
B066C017V005	66	17	5	And upon her forehead the name was written, Mystery: Babel the Great, the Mother of Harlots and of the Abominations of the Earth.
B066C017V006	66	17	6	And I saw the woman drunk with the blood of the saints, and with the blood of the martyrs of Jeshu; and I wondered, when I saw, with great wonder.
B066C017V007	66	17	7	And the angel said to me, Why wonderest thou? I will tell thee the mystery of the woman, and of the beast of prey which beareth her, which hath the seven heads and the ten horns.
B066C017V008	66	17	8	The beast of prey which thou seest, was, and is not; and will ascend from the abyss, and go into perdition: and they who dwell on the earth will admire, they whose name is not written in the book of life from the foundations of the world, while they see the beast of prey, who was, and is not, and draweth nigh.
B066C017V009	66	17	9	Here is the mind of him who hath wisdom: The seven heads are seven hills where the woman sitteth upon them.
B066C017V010	66	17	10	And the kings are seven; five have fallen, one is, the other not yet hath come: and when he hath come, a little while it behoveth him to abide.
B066C017V011	66	17	11	And the beast of prey which was and is not, this is an Eighth, and is of the Seven, and is unto perdition.
B066C017V012	66	17	12	And the ten horns which thou sawest are ten kings, the men who kingdom not yet have received; but authority as kings one hour receive with the beast of prey.
B066C017V013	66	17	13	They have one will, and their power and their authority unto the beast of prey they will give.
B066C017V014	66	17	14	They with the Lamb will make war, and the Lamb will overcome them; for he is the Lord of lords, and the King of kings, and they who are with him (are) the called and the chosen and the faithful.
B066C017V015	66	17	15	And he said to me, The waters which thou sawest where the harlot is sitting, are peoples, and assemblages, and tongues.
B066C017V016	66	17	16	And the ten horns which thou sawest, and the beast of prey, will hate the harlot, and make her desolate and naked; and her flesh they will eat, and herself burn with fire.
B066C017V017	66	17	17	For Aloha hath ingiven it to their hands that they might do his will, and perform one will to give their kingdom to the wild beast, until shall be fulfilled the words of Aloha.
B066C017V018	66	17	18	And the woman which thou sawest is the great city which hath kingdom over the kings of the earth.
B066C018V001	66	18	1	AFTER these I saw another angel descending from heaven, having great power; and the earth brightened with his glory.
B066C018V002	66	18	2	And he cried with a mighty voice, saying, Fallen, fallen hath Babel the Great, and hath become a den of demons, and the keep of every unclean spirit, and the keep of every unclean and abominable bird, and the keep of every unclean and abominable beast of prey.
B066C018V003	66	18	3	For that of the wine of her rage have all nations drunk; and the kings of the earth have with her committed fornication, and the merchants of the earth from the power of her luxuriance have become rich.
B066C018V004	66	18	4	And I heard another voice from heaven, saying: COME OUT OF HER, MY PEOPLE, that you be not partakers of her sins, and lest of her plagues you receive.
B066C018V005	66	18	5	For her sins have reached unto heaven, and Aloha hath remembered her iniquity.
B066C018V006	66	18	6	Deal with her as she hath dealt with you, and double to her according to her works. In the cup which she mingled mingle to her double.
B066C018V007	66	18	7	How much she hath pleased herself to be wanton, all this give her suffering and sorrow. For she said in her heart, I sit the queen, and am not a widow, and sorrow I see not.
B066C018V008	66	18	8	Therefore in one day will come these her plagues, death and sorrow and hunger; and in fire she will burn, for mighty is the Lord God who judgeth her.
B066C018V009	66	18	9	And the kings of the earth who with her have committed fornication, and have been wanton, shall weep and lament and wail over her, when they see the smoke of her burning;
B066C018V010	66	18	10	standing from far, for fear of her torment, saying, Woe, woe, that great city Babel, that mighty city! For in one hour hath come thy judgment.
B066C018V011	66	18	11	And the merchants of the earth shall be sorrowful over her, because no man buyeth of their burden.
B066C018V012	66	18	12	No more (shall there be in thee) the burden of gold, and of silver and of precious stones, and of pearls; and of fine linen, and of purple, and of silk and scarlet; and of every aromatic wood, and every vessel of elephant's-tooth, and every vessel of wood of great price, and of brass and of iron and of marble;
B066C018V013	66	18	13	and cinnamon and omomun and perfumes, and ointment and frankincense and wine and oil, and fine meal, and wheat, and cattle, and slaves, and horses and chariots, and bodies and souls of men.
B066C018V014	66	18	14	And the fruit of the desire of thy soul hath gone from thee, and all those things which are delicious and brilliant have perished from thee,
B066C018V015	66	18	15	and the merchants of these things will find them no more. They who were made rich by her from afar will stand for fear of her torment, and wail and be sorrowful,
B066C018V016	66	18	16	saying, Woe, woe, that great city, which was arrayed in fine linen and purple and scarlet, and golded with gold, and (adorned) with precious stones and pearls;
B066C018V017	66	18	17	for in one hour hath been destroyed wealth like this. And every captain and every pilot who navigateth to the place, and the mariners, and all who serve on the sea, stood from afar,
B066C018V018	66	18	18	and cried, while beholding the smoke of her burning, saying, What is like to this great city!
B066C018V019	66	18	19	And they cast dust upon their heads, and cried, weeping and lamenting, and saying, Woe, woe, that great city, in which were made rich all they who have ships in the sea, from the preciousness of her! For in one hour she becometh desolate!
B066C018V020	66	18	20	Rejoice over her, heaven, and the angels and apostles and prophets, because Aloha hath judged your judgment upon her.
B066C018V021	66	18	21	And an angel took a stone, as a great millstone, and cast it into the sea, saying, Thus with force is cast down Babel the great city, and to be found no more.
B066C018V022	66	18	22	And the voice of harpers, and of musicians, and of singers, and of trumpeters, shall be heard in thee no more. And no artificer, nor art, shall more be found in thee.
B066C018V023	66	18	23	And the light of a lamp shall be seen in thee no more. And the voice of the bridegroom and of the bride shall be heard in thee no more. For thy merchants were the great ones of the earth; for by thy sorcery were all nations seduced.
B066C018V024	66	18	24	And in her was found the blood of prophets and of saints, and of all those who had been killed upon the earth.
B066C019V001	66	19	1	AFTER these I heard a great voice of a multitudinous host in heaven, saying, Halleluia! Salvation, and power, and glory, and honour, Be unto our God.
B066C019V002	66	19	2	For true and righteous are his judgments; Because he hath judged the great harlot Who corrupted the earth with her fornication, And hath avenged the blood of his servants at her hand.
B066C019V003	66	19	3	And the second time they said, Halleluia! And her smoke went up for ever and ever.
B066C019V004	66	19	4	And the four-and-twenty presbyters fell, and the four living-ones, and worshipped Aloha who sitteth upon the throne, saying, Amen, Halleluia!
B066C019V005	66	19	5	And a voice came forth from the throne, saying, Praise our God, all his servants, And they who fear him, small and great.
B066C019V006	66	19	6	And I heard as the voice of a great host, as the voice of many waters, as the voice of mighty thunders, saying, Halleluia, For the Lord our God the Omnipotent reigneth!
B066C019V007	66	19	7	Let us rejoice and exult and give glory unto him; Because the marriage feast of the Lamb hath come, And his bride hath made herself ready.
B066C019V008	66	19	8	And it was given to her to be arrayed in fine linen, resplendent and pure; for the fine linen is the righteousness of saints.
B066C019V009	66	19	9	And he said to me, Write, Blessed are they who to the supper of the marriage feast of the Lamb are called. And he said to me, These my words are the true sayings of Aloha.
B066C019V010	66	19	10	And I fell before his feet to worship; and he said to me, See (that thou do it) not; thy fellowservant (am I), and of thy brethren who have the testimony of Jeshu. Aloha worship; for the testimony of Jeshu is the spirit of prophecy.
B066C019V011	66	19	11	And I saw heaven opened. And behold a white horse, and he who sat upon him was called the Faithful and the True; and in righteousness he judgeth and maketh war.
B066C019V012	66	19	12	But his eyes were as the flame of fire, and upon his head were many diadems, having names written; and the name which was written of him no man knoweth but himself.
B066C019V013	66	19	13	And he was arrayed in a vestment sprinkled with blood, and his name was called The Word of Aloha.
B066C019V014	66	19	14	And the armies of heaven followed him upon white horses, clothed in garments of fine linen, pure (and) white.
B066C019V015	66	19	15	And from his mouth went forth a sharp sword of two edges, that therewith he might smite the nations. And he will rule the nations with a rod of iron, and he will tread the winepress of the fierceness of the wrath of Aloha the Omnipotent.
B066C019V016	66	19	16	And he had upon his vestment and upon his thigh the name written, King of kings, and Lord of lords.
B066C019V017	66	19	17	And I saw an angel standing in the sun. And he cried with a great voice, saying to all the fowls that fly in the midst of heaven, Come, gather to the great supper of Aloha;
B066C019V018	66	19	18	that ye may eat the flesh of kings, and the flesh of chiefs of thousands, and the flesh of heroes, and the flesh of horses and them who sit upon them, and the flesh of all the sons of liberty and of the slaves, and of the small and of the great.
B066C019V019	66	19	19	And I saw the beast of prey, and the kings of the earth, and their armies, gathered together to make war with him who sat on the throne, and with his armies.
B066C019V020	66	19	20	And the beast of prey was taken, and the false prophet with him who wrought signs before him, with which he deluded them who received the signature of the beast of prey, and them who worshipped his image; and living they were both cast into the lake of fire which burneth with sulphur.
B066C019V021	66	19	21	And the rest were slain with the sword of him who sat upon the horse; with that (sword) which went forth from his mouth. And all the fowls were satiated with their flesh.
B066C020V001	66	20	1	AND I saw an angel descending from heaven, having the key of the abyss, and a great chain in his hand.
B066C020V002	66	20	2	And he laid hold of the dragon, that ancient serpent, who is the deceiver, and Satana, who seduced all the habitable world, and bound him a thousand years;
B066C020V003	66	20	3	and cast him into the abyss, and shut and sealed over him, that he should no more seduce the nations, until the thousand years be completed: but after them he will be loosed a little time.
B066C020V004	66	20	4	And I saw thrones, and they sat upon them, and judgment was given to them; and to the souls of them who had been cut asunder for the sake of the testimony of Jeshu, and for the word of Aloha, and them who had not worshipped the beast of prey nor his image, nor received his signature upon their forehead and upon their hands. And they lived and reigned with their Meshiha the thousand years.
B066C020V005	66	20	5	This is the first resurrection.
B066C020V006	66	20	6	Blessed and holy is he who hath part in the first resurrection: upon them the second death hath not power; but they shall be priests of Aloha and of his Meshiha, and shall reign with him the thousand years.
B066C020V007	66	20	7	And when the thousand years shall be fulfilled, Satana will be loosed from the place of his keeping,
B066C020V008	66	20	8	and will go forth and seduce the nations which are in the four corners of the earth, Gug and Mogug, to gather them to war, of whom the number is as the sand of the sea.
B066C020V010	66	20	10	And the accuser who seduced them was cast into the lake of fire and of sulphur, as was also the beast of prey and the false prophet; and they will be tormented day and night for ever and ever.
B066C020V011	66	20	11	And I saw a great white throne, and Him who sat thereon, from whom from his face fled earth and heaven; and place (as) to this was not found for them.
B066C020V012	66	20	12	And I saw the dead, great and small, standing before the throne; and the books were opened; and another book was opened, which is (the Book) of Life. And the dead were judged from the (records) which are written in the books according to their works.
B066C020V013	66	20	13	And the sea gave up the dead which were in it, and death and shiul gave up the dead which were in them. And they were judged every one according to their works.
B066C020V014	66	20	14	And death and shiul were cast into the lake of fire, which is the second death.
B066C020V015	66	20	15	And if a man was not found written in the Book of Life, he was cast into the lake of fire.
B066C021V001	66	21	1	AND I saw new heavens and a new earth: for the first heaven and the first earth had gone, and the sea was no more.
B066C021V002	66	21	2	And the holy city, Urishlem the new, I saw descending from heaven from Aloha, prepared as the bride is decked for her husband.
B066C021V003	66	21	3	And I heard a great voice from heaven, saying, Behold, the tabernacle of Aloha is with men; and he will dwell with them, and they shall be his people; and Aloha himself will be with them, and will be their God.
B066C021V004	66	21	4	And every tear shall be wiped away from their eyes, and death shall be no more; nor sorrow, nor clamour, nor pain, shall be any more; for the former things are passed away.
B066C021V005	66	21	5	And He who sat upon the throne said, Behold, I make all things new. And he said, Write: for these are the faithful and true words of Aloha.
B066C021V006	66	21	6	And he said to me, I am Olaph and Thau, the Beginning and the End. To him who thirsteth I will give of the water of life freely.
B066C021V007	66	21	7	He who overcometh shall inherit these; and I will be to him Aloha, and he shall be my son.
B066C021V008	66	21	8	But the fearful, and the faithless, and sinners, and the unclean, and murderers, and fornicators, and sorcerers, and servers of idols, and all liars, (shall have) their portion in the lake which burneth with fire and sulphur; which is the second death.
B066C021V009	66	21	9	And one of the seven angels who had the seven vials full of the seven last plagues, came and spake with me. saying, Come, I will show thee the bride, the wife of the Lamb.
B066C021V010	66	21	10	And he led me in spirit upon a great and high mountain, and showed me the holy city Urishlem, descending from heaven from Aloha;
B066C021V011	66	21	11	having the glory of Aloha, as the clearness of light, like a stone of great price, as the stone Jaspon, resembling crystallos;
B066C021V012	66	21	12	having a wall great and high, which had twelve gates, and names written upon them, which are the names of the twelve tribes of the sons of Israel.
B066C021V013	66	21	13	On the east three gates, and on the north three gates, and on the south three gates, and on the west three gates.
B066C021V014	66	21	14	And the wall of the city had twelve foundations; and upon them the twelve names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb.
B066C021V015	66	21	15	And he who talked with me had a measure, a rod of gold, that he might measure the city and the gates and the walls thereof.
B066C021V016	66	21	16	And the city was set four-square, and the length of it was as the breadth: and he measured the city with the rod, upon twelve stadia of twelve thousand. And the length and the breadth and the height of it are equal.
B066C021V017	66	21	17	And he measured the wall of it, an hundred and forty and four measures of the cubits of a man, that is, of the angel.
B066C021V018	66	21	18	And the structure of the wall of it is (of) jaspis, and the city is of pure gold, like pure brightness.
B066C021V019	66	21	19	And the foundations of the wall of the city were adorned with every precious stone: the first foundation was of jaspis, the second sathphiros, the third caledon, the fourth zmoragdo,
B066C021V020	66	21	20	the fifth sardonicos, the sixth sardion, the seventh crisuthilos, the eighth berulla, the ninth topadion, the tenth chrosoposius, the eleventh hyacinthos, the twelfth amuthistos.
B066C021V021	66	21	21	And the twelve gates are twelve pearls, each of every one of the gates (a pearl), and each of every one of the pearls (a gate). And the wide street of the city was of pure gold as the brightness of light.
B066C021V022	66	21	22	And a temple I saw not in it; for the Lord, the Omnipotent, is the temple thereof and the Lamb.
B066C021V023	66	21	23	And the city hath no need of the sun nor of the moon to enlighten it; for the glory of Aloha illuminateth it, and the light thereof is the Lamb.
B066C021V024	66	21	24	And the nations of the saved walk by the light of it, and the kings of the earth bring their glory and the honour of the nations into it.
B066C021V025	66	21	25	And the gates of it shall not be shut by day, for night is not there.
B066C021V026	66	21	26	And they shall bring the glory and honour of the nations into it;
B066C021V027	66	21	27	and nothing shall enter into it that defileth, nor that worketh uncleanness; but they who are written in the book of life of the Lamb.
B066C022V001	66	22	1	AND he showed me a river of waters of life, clear as crystal, coming forth from the throne of Aloha and of the Lamb.
B066C022V002	66	22	2	In the midst of the wide street of it, and by the river, here and there, (was) the tree of life, which produced twelve fruits, in every month giving each one its fruit. And the leaves of the tree (are) for the healing of the nations.
B066C022V003	66	22	3	And there shall be no more falling away; and the throne of Aloha and of the Lamb shall be in it, and his servants shall serve him.
B066C022V004	66	22	4	And they shall see his face, and his name shall be upon their foreheads.
B066C022V005	66	22	5	And night shall be no more: nor any need have they of the light of a lamp, or the light of the sun; for the Lord God enlighteneth them, and they will reign for ever and ever.
B066C022V006	66	22	6	And he said to me, These sayings are faithfulness and truth. And the Lord God of the spirit of the prophets hath sent me, his angel, to show to his servants the things which must soon be done.
B066C022V007	66	22	7	And behold, I come quickly. Blessed is he who keepeth the words of the prophecy of this book.
B066C022V008	66	22	8	And also I Juhanon am he who heard and saw these. And when I had heard and seen, I fell to worship before the feet of the angel who showed them to me.
B066C022V009	66	22	9	And he said to me, See (that thou do it) not. I am thy fellow-servant, and of thy brethren the prophets, and of them who keep the words of this book. Worship Aloha.
B066C022V010	66	22	10	And he said to me, Seal not the words of the prophecy of this book; for the time draweth nigh.
B066C022V011	66	22	11	He who doeth evil shall work evil still; and he who is filthy shall be filthy still; and the righteous shall still do righteousness, and the holy be holy still.
B066C022V012	66	22	12	Behold, I come quickly; and my reward is with me, to render to every one according as is his work.
B066C022V013	66	22	13	I am Olaph and Thau, the First and the Last, the Beginning and the End.
B066C022V014	66	22	14	Blessed are they who do his commandments, that they may have authority to the tree of life, and by the gates may enter into the city.
B066C022V015	66	22	15	Without are dogs, and sorcerers, and fornicators, and murderers, and servers of idols, and every one who loveth and maketh a lie.
B066C022V016	66	22	16	I JESHU have sent mine angel to testify unto you these things before the churches. I am the root and the offspring of Dawid, as the bright, the morning star.
B066C022V017	66	22	17	AND THE SPIRIT AND THE BRIDE SAY, COME! AND HE WHO HEARETH SHALL SAY, COME! AND HE WHO THIRSTETH MAY COME, AND HE WHO WILLETH, TO TAKE THE WATERS OF LIFE FREELY.
B066C022V018	66	22	18	I testify to every one who heareth the words of the prophecy of this book, That if any man shall set upon them, Aloha will set upon him the plagues which are written in this book.
B066C022V019	66	22	19	And if any man make to cease from the words of the book of this prophecy, Aloha will make to cease his portion of the tree of life, and of the holy city of which is written in this book.
B066C022V020	66	22	20	He who testifieth these saith, Yes: I come quickly. Amen. Come, Lord Jeshu.
B066C022V021	66	22	21	The grace of our Lord Jeshu Meshiha be with all the saints. Amen.
